INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('summit', '[\'sʌmɪt]', 'n.顶点,最高阶层;adj.政府首脑的;vi.参加最高级会议的', '1. It was a warm climb to the summit. 向顶峰攀登时身上都热起来了。 2. The Hungarian view is magnificent from the summit of the mountains. 从群山之颠看到的匈牙利景色非常壮丽。 3. The news is all about the latest summit meeting. 这条消息是关於最近的首脑级会议的。 4. He attained the summit of his ambition. 他达到了追求的最高目标。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('electronic', '[ɪˌlek\'trɑːnɪk]', 'adj.电子的', '1. This dictionary is available in electronic version. 这部词典有电子版。 2. I like to read books on electronic music. 我喜欢读一些关于电子音乐的书。 3. Helen became an electronic engineer. 海伦成了一名电子工程师。', '副词: electronically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('aggregate', '[\'æɡrɪɡət]', 'n.合计,总计,集合体;adj.合计的,集合的,聚合的;v.聚集,集合,合计', '1. What were your aggregate wages last year? 去年你的工资一共是多少? 2. The cause of unemployment was inadequate aggregate demand. 失业的原因在于总需求不足。 3. Manager wants to know the aggregate sales in that market. 经理想知道那个市场的总销售量。 4. The tax increases will, in the aggregate, cause much hardship. 增加税收归结起来将造成很多困难。 5. Occasionally the cells might aggregate to form lentoid bodies. 偶而，细胞能聚集形成类晶体球体。', '形容词: aggregative 副词: aggregately 名词: aggregation 过去式: aggregated 过去分词: aggregated 现在分词: aggregating 第三人称单数: aggregates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sue', '[suː]', 'vt.控告,向...请求,请愿;vi.提出诉讼,提出请求', '1. If you don\'t complete the work, I will sue you for damages. 如果你不把工作做完,我就要控告你支付赔偿。 2. Lucy is going to sue Antony for breach of promise. 露西准备控告安东尼毁婚约。 3. They feel very angry because Cathy is going to sue Tony. 他们感到非常的生气,因为凯西即将要起诉托尼。 4. She decided to sue her employer for wrongful dismissal. 她决定起诉雇主非法解雇她。 5. You can sue to the committee for permission. 你可以向委员会请求获准。', '名词: suer 过去式: sued 过去分词: sued 现在分词: suing 第三人称单数: sues');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('disposal', '[dɪ\'spoʊzl]', 'n.处理,处置,布置,安排,配置,支配', '1. We placed everything at his disposal. 我们把一切事情都交给他处理。 2. The disposal of rubbish is always a problem. 垃圾的处理总是个难题。 3. The safe disposal of nuclear waste is a major problem. 安全处置核废料是个大问题。 4. The money is at our own disposal. 这钱由我们自由支配使用。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('handbook', '[\'hændbʊk]', 'n.手册,便览', '1. This medical handbook helps a lot. 这本医药手册很有用。 2. She is reading a handbook on gardening. 她正在阅读一本园艺手册。 3. I bought a handbook of English grammar last week. 上星期我买了一本英文文法手册。 4. Could you get a handbook of London for me? 你能为我买一本伦敦旅游指南吗?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('notwithstanding', '[ˌnɑːtwɪθ\'stændɪŋ]', 'prep.虽然,尽管;adv.尽管,还是;conj.虽然,尽管', '1. He went, notwithstanding he was ordered to stay. 他虽被命令不许去，但还是去了。 2. Notwithstanding her naughtiness, I love my little girl. 尽管我的小姑娘很淘气，我还是很爱她。 3. Notwithstanding the bad weather, the match went on. 尽管天气很糟，比赛还是照常进行。 4. He still went home, notwithstanding the midnight. 尽管已近午夜，他还是回家去了。 5. Many people told me not to try, but I went ahead notwithstanding. 很多人都劝我不要尝试,我还是决意去做了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('eliminate', '[ɪ\'lɪmɪneɪt]', 'vt.排除,消除;v.除去', '1. You must eliminate an unknown quantity. 你必须消去一个未知数。 2. Let us eliminate all uncertain on thought. 让我们从思想上消除一切疑惑。 3. We must eliminate unnecessary steps and get directly to the point. 我们必须忽略不必要的步骤,直接切入主题。 4. Their team was eliminated in the first round. 他们队在第一轮就被淘汰了。', '形容词: eliminative 名词: elimination 过去式: eliminated 过去分词: eliminated 现在分词: eliminating 第三人称单数: eliminates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('surplus', '[\'sɜːrpləs]', 'n.剩余,过剩,[会计]盈余;adj.过剩的,剩余的;vt.转让,卖掉', '1. Mexico has a large surplus of oil. 墨西哥有大量过剩的石油。 2. Countries with surplus are called creditor nations. 有顺差的国家则称为债权国。 3. Surpluses of food can be sold for cash. 多余的食物可卖钱。 4. Every country has a lot of surplus labor. 每个国家都有大量的剩余劳动力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mutter', '[\'mʌtər]', 'n.咕哝,嘀咕;v.咕哝,嘀咕', '1. Mutter Sarah was muttering away to herself as she did the washing-up. 萨拉一边洗碗碟一边独自咕哝个没完。 2. Some members of the government are beginning to mutter about the prime minister. 一些政府官员开始咕咕哝哝地抱怨首相。 3. Some members of the government are beginning to mutter about the prime minister. 一些政府官员开始咕咕哝哝地抱怨首相。 4. Don\'t mutter when they are studying. 当他们学习时不要轻声低语。 5. Some members of the government are beginning to mutter about the prime minister. 一些政府官员开始咕咕哝哝地抱怨首相。', '名词: mutterer 过去式: muttered 过去分词: muttered 现在分词: muttering 第三人称单数: mutters');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('flask', '[flæsk]', 'n.瓶,长颈瓶,细颈瓶,烧瓶,小水瓶', '1. A balloon is mysteriously \"sucked\" into a flask. 一个气球神秘地被吸进了一个细颈瓶。 2. Please carry a flask with you at all times during the hike. 在徒步旅行期间请随身携带一个长颈瓶。 3. The graduation is marked on the side of the flask. 烧瓶侧面有刻度标志。 4. A flask, conjured from thin air, was thrust into his shaking hand by Hermione. 赫敏将一个凭空变出来的烧瓶塞在了他颤抖着的手里。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('numerous', '[\'nuːmərəs]', 'adj.众多的,许多的,无数的', '1. The Earth is only one of the numerous planets in the universe. 地球只是宇宙中众多星球中的一个。 2. Those birds have become more numerous lately. 近来那种鸟变得越来越多了。 3. Numerous interruptions have prevented me from finishing my work. 我屡遭搅扰以致工作未能完成。 4. He appeared, surrounded by his numerous progeny. 他出现时，子女前呼后拥不计其数。', '副词: numerously 名词: numerousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('denial', '[dɪ\'naɪəl]', 'n.否认,否定,谢绝,拒绝', '1. The accusation brought a speedy denial. 指责马上遭到否认。 2. The prisoner repeated denials of the charges against him. 囚犯对被控罪名再三否认。 3. He met the charge with a plump denial. 他断然否认对他的指控。 4. The government has issued a denial of an election in May. 政府发表声明否认五月份要进行选举。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('extravagant', '[ɪk\'strævəɡənt]', 'adj.奢侈的,浪费的,过分的,放纵的', '1. She\'s got very extravagant tastes. 她有很奢侈的嗜好。 2. Extravagant people never save money. 奢侈的人攒不下钱。 3. The millionaire talked cold turkey to his extravagant nephew, hinting that he might be disinherited. 那百万富翁对他挥霍无度的侄儿晓以利害，并暗示其继承权可能被剥夺。 4. She was pilloried in the press for her extravagant parties. 她的聚会十分铺张，新闻界对她大加嘲弄。', '副词: extravagantly 名词: extravagantness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('lane', '[leɪn]', 'n.（乡间）小路,巷,里弄,狭窄的通道,航线', '1. The lane is the boundary of our land from theirs. 那条小路就是我们这片地与他们那片地的分界线。 2. She drives carefully up the rocky lane. 她驾车小心地从这条很多石头的小路上驶过去。 3. That lane will take you to his house. 你从那条小巷就可以走到他家。 4. The lane was rutted with tyre tracks. 这小巷有车胎轧出的凹痕。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('digest', '[\'dɑɪdʒɛst]', 'n.分类,摘要;vi.消化;vt.消化,融会贯通', '1. This is a digest of the week\'s news. 这是一周新闻摘要。 2. The baby is too small to digest meat. 婴儿太小,吃肉不消化。 3. Saliva helps one chew and digest food. 唾液能帮助咀嚼和消化食物。 4. It took me some time to digest what I had heard. 我花了一些时间才把听到的东西弄明白。 5. This rich food doesn\'t digest easily. 这种油腻的食物不易消化。', '过去式: digested 过去分词: digested 现在分词: digesting 第三人称单数: digests');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('overhead', '[ˌoʊvər\'hed]', 'adj.在头上的,高架的;n.企业一般管理费用,天花板adv.在头顶上,在空中,在高处', '1. Their office is in central Beijing, so their overhead is very high. 他们的办事处设在北京市中心，所以他们的日常开支很大。 2. The overhead costs are ridiculously expensive. 日常开支太高了。 3. This button turns on your overhead light. 这个按钮用来开亮您头顶上方的灯。 4. The hawk is hovering overhead. 鹰在头顶上盘旋。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sponge', '[spʌndʒ]', 'n.海绵,(外科用的)棉球,纱布;v.用海绵冼涤,揩拭,清除,用海绵吸收(液体),(俗)依赖某人生活,诈取某人,海绵般吸收', '1. The sponge soaked in the water on the desk. 海绵将书桌上的水吸了进去。 2. That child soaks up new facts like a sponge! 那孩子吸收新知识像海绵似的。 3. I like to sponge myself down in a hot bath. 洗热水澡时我喜欢用海绵擦洗全身。 4. Sponge the mud spots off the car. 用海绵擦去车上的污泥。', '过去式: sponged 过去分词: sponged 现在分词: sponging 第三人称单数: sponges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('survival', '[sər\'vaɪvl]', 'n.生存,幸存,残存,幸存者,残存物', '1. Hopes are fading for the survival of the missing climbers. 失踪的登山者幸存的希望越来越渺茫。 2. The miraculous survival of some people in the air crash was widely reported by the press. 空难事件中有些人大难不死被新闻界广泛报导。 3. She is the only survival in the accident. 她是事故中的惟一幸存者。 4. Survival is our first imperative. 我们当务之急是设法生存下来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('persistent', '[pər\'sɪstənt]', 'adj.持久稳固的', '1. He is a persistent pursuer of truth. 他是个坚持不懈追求真理的人。 2. His great success cannot depart from his persistent effort. 他取得这么大的成功和他坚持不懈的努力分不开。 3. A persistent cough may be a symptom of tuberculosis. 持续的咳嗽可能是肺病的症候。 4. His persistent questions finally goaded me into an angry reply. 他三番五次地问问题惹得我回答时也没有好气。', '副词: persistently');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('territory', '[\'terətɔːri]', 'n.领土,版图,地域', '1. The territory was carved up by the occupying powers. 领土被侵占者瓜分。 2. Each of the two countries claimed the territory. 这两个国家各自声称这片领土是自己的。 3. He seems to regard that end of the office as his territory. 他把办公室的那一头看成是他的地盘。 4. Our country is vast in territory. 我国版图辽阔。', '名词复数: territories');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('extensive', '[ɪk\'stensɪv]', 'adj.广大的,广阔的,广泛的', '1. The device had undergone extensive testing. 这种装置经受过广泛的试验。 2. I have benefited a lot from extensive reading. 广泛的阅读使我受益匪浅。 3. The teacher had both extensive knowledge and profound scholarship. 先生的学问博大精深。 4. The mansion has extensive grounds. 这大厦四周的庭园广阔。', '副词: extensively 名词: extensiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('perpetual', '[pər\'petʃuəl]', 'adj.永久的', '1. He was perpetual president of the country. 他是该国的终身总统。 2. He has run his course and takes his perpetual rest. 他已走完他的行程而长眠了。 3. She lives in perpetual fear of being discovered. 她永远生活在怕被发现的恐惧中。 4. It is the secret of perpetual youth. 它是青春永驻的秘诀。', '副词: perpetually');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('glide', '[ɡlaɪd]', 'v.滑行,悄悄地走,(时间)消逝,滑翔;n.滑行,滑翔,滑移,滑音', '1. The figure skater glided gracefully over the ice. 花样滑冰者在冰上优雅地滑行。 2. The swans glide gracefully on the lake. 天鹅在湖的上空优美地滑翔。 3. The plane managed to glide down to the runway. 飞机终于成功地滑翔降落在跑道上。 4. He glide away from the classroom. 他溜出教室。 5. When a word ends in a vowel sound and the next word begins with a vowel sound, they are connected with a glide between the two vowels. 如果一个单词以元音结束，下一个单词以元音开始的话，两个元音之间用一个滑音连在一起。', '过去式: glided 过去分词: glided 现在分词: gliding 第三人称单数: glides');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rotary', '[\'roʊtəri]', 'adj.旋转的', '1. The central unit is a rotary drum. 核心设备是一个旋转的滚筒。 2. The rotary agitator irrigated him. 旋转的鼓动者可灌溉的他。', '名词复数: rotaries');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pathetic', '[pə\'θetɪk]', 'adj.可怜的,悲惨的', '1. We saw the pathetic sight of starving children. 我们看到挨饿的儿童悲惨可怜的样子。 2. She dances well, but as a singer, she is pathetic. 她跳舞跳得好，但唱歌就差劲了。 3. God! The freshmen are pathetic this year! 天啊！今年的大一新生什么也不懂！ 4. I never heard anything that sounded so pathetic. 我从未听说过如此悲伤的事了。', '副词: pathetically 异体字: pathetical');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tack', '[tæk]', 'n.大头钉,粗缝,行动方针,食物;vt.以大头针钉住,附加;vi.抢风航行,作文字形移动', '1. Joe hammered a tack into the wall to hang a picture. 乔用锤子把一只大头钉敲进墙中用来挂一幅画。 2. It would be unwise to change tack now. 现在改变方针是不明智的。 3. It was a brave decision to change tack in the middle of the project. 在项目进行过程当中改变方针是个大胆的决定。 4. The speaker suddenly changed tack and left us all rather confused. 演讲人突然改变了论调，把我们都搞糊涂了。 5. My mother tacked the sleeves on before sewing them. 我妈妈在把袖子缝好之前，先用大针脚把它缝好。', '形容词: tackless 名词: tacker 过去式: tacked 过去分词: tacked 现在分词: tacking 第三人称单数: tacks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rip', '[rɪp]', 'v.撕,剥,劈,锯,裂开,撕裂;n.裂口,裂缝', '1. The poster had been ripped to pieces. 那张广告画已被撕得粉碎。 2. I ripped my stocking on a nail. 一个钉子挂破了我的袜子。 3. You should rip the cover off the box first. 你首先应当把这个盒子的封套扯掉。 4. She sewed up the rip in his sleeve. 她缝好了他衣袖上的裂口。', '名词: ripper 过去式: ripped 过去分词: ripped 现在分词: ripping 第三人称单数: rips');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('clue', '[kluː]', 'n.线索', '1. There is no clue to the identity of the thief. 没有确定窃贼身分的线索。 2. We have no clue as to where she went after she left home. 我们对她离家後去往何处毫无线索。 3. They are now trying to chase down all possible clues. 他们现在正在设法寻找一切可能的线索。 4. I gave him another clue, but he still didn\'t twig (the answer). 我又提示他一次，他还是不理解(那答案).', '过去式: clued 过去分词: clued 现在分词: clueing/cluing 第三人称单数: clues');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('adjoin', '[ə\'dʒɔɪn]', 'v.邻接,毗连', '1. We heard laughter in the adjoining room. 我们听到了邻屋的笑声。 2. The playing field adjoins the school. 体育场紧靠着学校。 3. Our house adjoins theirs. 我们的房屋与他们的毗连。', '过去式: adjoined 过去分词: adjoined 现在分词: adjoining 第三人称单数: adjoins');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rank', '[ræŋk]', 'n.等级,横列,阶级;adj.繁茂的,恶臭的,讨厌的,下流的;vt.排列,归类于,把...分等;vi.列为,列队;n.[数]秩', '1. He is above me in rank. 他的级别比我高。 2. They are people of all ranks and classes. 他们来自各阶层各阶级。 3. Taxis stand in a taxi rank waiting to be hired. 出租汽车排成一行等人雇车。 4. The riot police quickly fell into rank for action. 防暴警察迅速列队准备行动。 5. Rank the states in the order of size. 按大小把这些州排列一下。', '副词: rankly 比较级: ranker 最高级: rankest 名词: rankness 过去式: ranked 过去分词: ranked 现在分词: ranking 第三人称单数: ranks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('chip', '[tʃɪp]', 'n.碎片,筹码;v.削成碎片,碎裂;芯片', '1. It was difficult finding two cups without some kind of chip on them. 很难找到两个一点没有缺口的杯子。 2. A small chip of ice flew into the air. 一小块碎冰飞溅到了空中。 3. She had a hamburger and a portion of chip. 她吃了一个汉堡包和一份炸薯条。 4. I\'ve got chocolate chip for you. 我给你们买了巧克力薄片。 5. Be careful with these plates they chip very easily. 小心这些盘子--边缘容易破损。', '过去式: chipped 过去分词: chipped 现在分词: chipping 第三人称单数: chips');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('appraisal', '[ə\'preɪzl]', 'n.评价,估价(尤指估价财产,以便征税),鉴定', '1. All events have proved our appraisal to be correct. 一切事实都证明，我们估计得正确。 2. The judge made a cold appraisal of the evidence. 法官对这一证据作了一番毫无偏见的估计。 3. She gave us a realistic appraisal of our chances. 她对我们的机会做了一个现实的评估 4. His appraisal of the novel is appropriate. 他对这部小说的评价非常得当。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('coincide', '[ˌkoʊɪn\'saɪd]', 'vi.一致,符合', '1. They didn\'t coincide in opinion. 他们的意见不统一。 2. Our opinions did not coincide on this case. 在这个案例上,我们的意见不一致。 3. My religious beliefs don\'t coincide with yours. 我的宗教信仰跟你的不一样。 4. Their stories coincided. 他们的叙述一致.', '过去式: coincided 过去分词: coincided 现在分词: coinciding 第三人称单数: coincides');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('acute', '[ə\'kjuːt]', 'adj.敏锐的,[医]急性的,剧烈', '1. He suffers from acute depression. 他患有严重的抑郁症。 2. This area has an acute shortage of water. 这个地方缺水严重。 3. She has acute hearing. 她有很敏锐的听力。 4. The doctor said that you had acute appendicitis. 医生说您患的是急性阑尾炎。', '副词: acutely 名词: acuteness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('aspiration', '[ˌæspə\'reɪʃn]', 'n.热望,渴望', '1. His true aspiration is to become the President of the United States. 他真正的抱负是想成为美国总统。 2. He nursed an aspiration to be a poet. 他心怀当诗人的愿望。 3. The generalship was his aspiration. 将官之职位是他梦寐以求的目标。 4. These are not just my goals, but our common aspiration. 这些不仅仅是我的目标,而且是我们的共同志向。 5. Aspiration cytologic examination reealed a fibrocystic change. 抽吸细胞学检查为纤维囊性变。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('additional', '[ə\'dɪʃənl]', 'adj.另外的,附加的,额外的', '1. He had to pay some additional charges. 他不得不付些附加费。 2. Additional material is overprinted in red. 附加材料是用红色加印上的。 3. You should know the additional responsibilities that are incidental to the job. 你该知道做这项工作要承担额外责任。 4. We are willing to pay an additional fee for immediate delivery . 我们愿意为即期交货支付一笔额外的费用。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('multiple', '[\'mʌltɪpl]', 'adj.多样的,多重的;n.倍数,若干;v.成倍增加', '1. He is the person with multiple injuries. 他就是那个多处受伤的人。 2. A multiple crash can often be seen on that motorway. 那条公路上的联环撞车事故很多。 3. Words can have multiple meanings. 词汇可以有许多释义。 4. 10 is a multiple of 5. 10是5的倍数。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('vary', '[\'veri]', 'vt.改变,变更,使多样化;vi.变化,不同,违反', '1. Although this is the general approach, you can vary it to some degree. 尽管这是常规方法,但可以在一定程度上改变它。 2. The prices of some goods vary with the season. 某些货物的价格随着季节的变化而变动。 3. Teachers shall vary their lessons to make them more interesting. 为了增加趣味，教师应该使自己的课多样化。', '副词: varyingly 过去式: varied 过去分词: varied 现在分词: varying 第三人称单数: varies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('poke', '[poʊk]', 'n.刺,戳,懒汉,袋子;vt.戳,捅,拨开,刺;vi.戳,刺,捅,伸出,刺探,闲荡', '1. In his view, a pinch, a whack or a poke essentially tugged on a neural rope that then rang a pain alarm bell in the brain. 他的看法是，无论是捏、打或戳的动作，基本上都拉动了某根神经索，而敲响脑中某个疼痛的警铃。 2. I didn\'t know Haku had a fast poke. 我还不知道白有快速刺拳这一手。 3. He used a nail to poke a hole. 他用钉子刺了个洞。 4. At frequent intervals the driver used to stop, poke the fire and add fresh fuel. 在经常性的间歇中，司机常常停下来拨一下火，加上新的汽油。 5. Don\'t poke her eye out with that stick! 别让那根棍子戳着她的眼！', '过去式: poked 过去分词: poked 现在分词: poking 第三人称单数: pokes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('symbol', '[\'sɪmbl]', 'n.符号,记号,象征', '1. The chemical symbol for copper is \"Cu\". 铜的化学符号是Cu。 2. The dove is the symbol of peace. 鸽子是和平的象征。 3. The river-sea dividing marker must be a symbol which separates the Yalu River from the Yellow Sea. 江海分界碑,这里就是鸭绿江和黄海分界的标志吧。', '过去式: symboled 过去分词: symboled 现在分词: symboling 第三人称单数: symbols');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('enclosure', '[ɪn\'kloʊʒər]', 'n.围住,围栏,四周有篱笆或围墙的场地', '1. Please see enclosure for details. 详细资料请看附件! 2. I received your enclosure with gratitude. 附件收到, 十分感谢。 3. There are several enclosures in the envelope. 信封内装有几份附件。 4. She keeps a horse in that enclosure. 她在那个围栏里养了一匹马。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('consist', '[kən\'sɪst]', 'vi.由...组成,在于,一致', '1. The United Kingdom consists of Great Britain and Northern Ireland. 联合王国由大不列颠和北爱尔兰组成。 2. How many players does a baseball team consist of? 棒球队由几名队员组成? 3. Matters consist of molecules, and molecules of atoms. 物质由分子构成，而分子由原子构成。 4. The islands consist of oyster reefs covered with a thin veneer of black mud. 由牡蛎礁构成的小岛上覆盖着一层薄薄的黑色软泥。', '过去式: consisted 过去分词: consisted 现在分词: consisting 第三人称单数: consists');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('intrigue', '[ɪn\'triːɡ]', 'n.阴谋,诡计;vi.密谋,私通;vt.激起...的兴趣,用诡计取得', '1. The shapes of clouds intrigue me. 云的形状激起我的兴趣。 2. She was intriguing with her sister against her mother. 她和妹妹串通捣鬼和母亲作对。 3. Some of the members had been intriguing to get the secretary dismissed. 有些人一直密谋想让老板把秘书解雇。 4. I\'ll never intrigue against my friends 我决不会对我的朋友耍阴谋，施诡计。 5. It is said that he is a master of intrigue. 据说他是搞阴谋诡计的老手。', '副词: intriguingly 名词: intriguer 过去式: intrigued 过去分词: intrigued 现在分词: intriguing 第三人称单数: intrigues');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('delicate', '[\'delɪkət]', 'adj.精巧的,精致的,病弱的,脆弱的,微妙的,棘手的,灵敏的,精密的', '1. The international situation is very delicate at present. 目前的国际形势极其微妙。 2. He persecuted me with various delicate questions. 他用种种微妙的问题把我难倒了。 3. She wears a dress with delicate lace. 她穿了一件带有精致花边的裙子。 4. Don\'t grasp at the delicate branch, or you may break it. 不要去抓这嫩枝,你会把它折断的。', '副词: delicately 名词: delicateness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('voluntary', '[\'vɑːlənteri]', 'adj.自动的,自愿的,主动的,故意的,非官办的,志愿的,自发的', '1. He made a voluntary statement to the police. 他自愿为警方作供。 2. Many social services are still provided by voluntary societies in our city. 在我们的城市，许多社会服务仍然是有志愿团体提供的。 3. We rely entirely on voluntary contribution. 我们全靠自愿捐赠。 4. She\'s very taken up with voluntary work at the moment. 她目前大部分时间和精力都用在志愿工作上了。', '副词: voluntarily 名词: voluntariness 名词复数: voluntaries');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pilgrim', '[\'pɪlɡrɪm]', 'n.圣地朝拜者,朝圣', '1. We met many pilgrims on their way to Mecca. 我们遇到许多去麦加朝圣的人。 2. At length the pilgrim could shake the dust off his feet at Heidelberg. 那个朝圣者终于可以在海德堡停下来了。 3. I edged closer like a pilgrim approaching a shrine. 我像一位走近庙宇的朝圣者一样再往近走。 4. Their family goes back to the time of the Pilgrim Fathers. 他们家族的渊源可追溯到清教徒前辈移民时代。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('innumerable', '[ɪ\'nuːmərəbl]', 'adj.无数的,数不清的', '1. Human beings once created innumerable miracles. 人类曾经创造了无数的奇迹。 2. Stars resemble innumerable dots of lights in the night sky. 夜空中，星星象无数的小亮点。 3. There are innumerable constellations in the sky. 天空中有数不清的星座。 4. Innumerable small shops presented a collection of cheap plastic goods. 数不清的小商店里陈列着一批廉价的塑料制品。', '副词: innumerably 名词: innumerableness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('permeate', '[\'pɜːrmieɪt]', 'vt.弥漫,渗透,透过,充满;vi.透入', '1. His subtle satisfaction seemed to permeate the space around them. 他难以捉摸的满足感好像弥漫在了他们的周围。 2. If your wine is still, pour it into the centre of the glass to let the bouquet permeate the vessel. 如果是无汽泡的酒，直接倒入杯子中央，使酒的香气充分散发，弥漫整个酒杯。 3. Water will permeate blotting paper. 水能渗透吸水纸。 4. Functional relationships permeate every part of science. 函数关系渗透自然科学的每个部分。', '形容词: permeant 名词: permeation 过去式: permeated 过去分词: permeated 现在分词: permeating 第三人称单数: permeates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('optimism', '[\'ɑːptɪmɪzəm]', 'n.乐观,乐观主义', '1. A mood of optimism pervaded the gathering. 会上充满乐观的气氛。 2. We view these changes with guarded optimism. 我们以审慎的乐观看待这些变化。 3. They professed optimism about the outcome. 他们对结果表示乐观。 4. We are influenced by his radiant optimism. 他那具有感染力的乐观主义影响了我们。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('enthusiastic', '[ɪnˌθuːzi\'æstɪk]', 'adj.热心的,热情的', '1. He is enthusiastic about helping others. 他热心助人。 2. He doesn\'t know much about this subject, but he\'s very enthusiastic. 他对这事所知不多,但他非常热心。 3. The audience were enthusiastic on the opening night of the play. 那出戏首次公演之夜观众非常热情。 4. His idea received an enthusiastic response. 他的想法获得热烈的响应。', '副词: enthusiastically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('circulation', '[ˌsɜːrkjə\'leɪʃn]', 'n.循环,流通,发行额', '1. The old coins have been withdrawn from circulation. 旧硬币已经收回不再流通了。 2. The coins were taken out of circulation. 这种硬币已停止流通。 3. Harvey discovered the circulation of the blood. 哈唯发现了血液循环。 4. The newspaper\'s circulation has trebled since last year. 去年以来该报的发行量已增加到原来的三倍。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('deprive', '[dɪ\'praɪv]', 'vt.剥夺,使丧失', '1. We have no right to deprive their life. 我们没有权利去剥夺它们的生命。 2. The spread of television have considerably deprive us of our time for reading. 电视的普及剥夺了我们相当多的阅读时间。 3. You can\'t deprive her of her rights. 你不能剥夺她的权利。 4. These trees deprive my house of light. 这些树遮住了我房屋的光线。', '形容词: deprivable 过去式: deprived 过去分词: deprived 现在分词: depriving 第三人称单数: deprives');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('arrange', '[ə\'reɪndʒ]', 'v.安排,排列,协商', '1. You must arrange these books in alphabetical order. 你要把这些书按字母顺序排好。 2. I have arranged one of my staff to meet you at the airport. 我已经安排好一个职员到飞机场接你。 3. If you can arrange the tourist destinations for me, I will be very grateful. 如果你能为我计划一下,我将不胜感激。 4. I have arranged with the neighbours about taking care of the cat. 我已和邻居们商量好照顾猫咪的事情。', '名词: arranger 过去式: arranged 过去分词: arranged 现在分词: arranging 第三人称单数: arranges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cast', '[kæst]', 'n.投掷,铸件,脱落物,一瞥,演员表;v.投,抛,投射,浇铸,计算,派(角色)', '1. The angler cast her line into the stream. 那个垂钓者把鱼线掷进了小溪里。 2. The storm cast the little rowboat onto the rocks. 风暴把这条小划艇抛到岩石上。 3. The two world wars cast a shadow over the people all over the world. 两次世界大战在全世界人民中投下了阴影。 4. The metals most frequently cast are iron, steal, aluminum and so on. 最常用来铸造的金属是铁、钢、铝等。 5. The play succeeded thanks to the wonderful performance of all the cast. 由于演员们的精彩表演,这部戏获得了成功。', '过去式: cast 过去分词: cast 现在分词: casting 第三人称单数: casts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('outward', '[\'aʊtwərd]', 'adj.外面的,外表的,公开的,向外的,外出的;adv.向外,在外,表面上n.外表,周围世界', '1. A detonation projects an instantaneous pulse of pressure outward in all directions. 爆炸的瞬间会朝各个方向发出向外的压力波。 2. Frost consists of tiny crystals of ice which grow outward from a solid surface. 霜是由冰的微晶组成，它生长在固体表面的外部。 3. The Sun\'s outermost layer begins about 10,000 miles above the visible surface and goes outward for millions of miles. 太阳的最外层从其可见表面的约一万英里处开始，向外延伸数百万英里。 4. And there have been morbid miseries fostered by gloomy creeds, which have led men into profound inner discords that made all outward prosperity of no avail. 悲观的信念孳生了病态的痛苦，致使人类的内部极不和谐，从而使外部的繁荣毫无成果。 5. The walls of the dilapidated shed lean outward. 那座破棚屋的墙向外倾。', '名词: outwardness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('surge', '[sɜːrdʒ]', 'n.巨涌,汹涌,澎湃;vi.汹涌,澎湃,振荡,滑脱,放松;vt.使汹涌奔腾,急放', '1. A surge of demonstrators broke through the fence. 汹涌而来的示威者冲破了围栏。 2. The great surge had built up in the Gulf Stream. 汹涌的巨浪在墨西哥湾流形成了。 3. Oil was the prime cause of the price surge. 石油是物价上涨的主要原因。 4. The tides surged over the rocks. 潮水奔腾着涌过礁石。', '过去式: surged 过去分词: surged 现在分词: surging 第三人称单数: surges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ambitious', '[æm\'bɪʃəs]', 'adj.有雄心的,野心勃勃的', '1. Mr. Lin is an ambitious businessman. 林先生是个有雄心的生意人。 2. I ought to do something a bit more ambitious. 我应当做些更有雄心的事。 3. They ventured on an ambitious program of reform. 他们冒然采取一项野心勃勃的改革计划。 4. The ambitious boy learned very quickly. 那位有抱负的少年学得很快。', '副词: ambitiously 名词: ambitiousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('convict', '[kən\'vɪkt]', 'vt.证明...有罪,宣告...有罪;n.罪犯', '1. You can\'t convict a man of a crime on circumstantial evidence alone. 不能只靠旁证就判定一个人有罪。 2. The criminal was convicted of murder. 歹徒被判谋杀罪。 3. He was convicted of his errors. 他认识到自己所犯的过失。 4. The convict fled away with a hostage. 囚犯带着一个人质跑了。 5. Let a convict person go free without any punishment. 让被定罪的人自由，不进行任何惩罚。', '过去式: convicted 过去分词: convicted 现在分词: convicting 第三人称单数: convicts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sieve', '[sɪv]', 'n.筛,滤网,不会保密的人;v.筛,过滤', '1. We can separate the stones out with a sieve. 我们可以用一个筛子把石头分离出来。 2. This boat leaks like a sieve,ie very badly. 这条船漏得像个筛子。 3. We often shake flour through a sieve. 我们经常用筛子筛面粉。 4. You\'ll need to sieve out the stone from the soil. 你得将石块从土中筛出。', '过去式: sieved 过去分词: sieved 现在分词: sieving 第三人称单数: sieves');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tuck', '[tʌk]', 'n.缝摺,活力,鼓声,船尾突出部下方,食物(尤指点心,蛋糕);vt.打摺,卷起,挤进,塞,使隐藏;vi.折成摺子,缩拢', '1. The baby\'s dress was beautifully tucked with tiny stitches. 婴儿衫的褶裥打得针脚细密，很漂亮。 2. Please help me tuck up my sleeves. 请帮我卷起袖子。 3. He was asleep before I tucked him in. 我还没来得及给他盖好被子，他就睡着了。 4. The hen tucked her head under her wing. 那母鸡把头缩在翅膀下。 5. The dress was too big, so Mother put a tuck in it. 衣服太大，所以妈妈在里面打了裥。', '过去式: tucked 过去分词: tucked 现在分词: tucking 第三人称单数: tucks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('inevitable', '[ɪn\'evɪtəbl]', 'adj.不可避免的,必然的', '1. You\'ll have to bow to the inevitable. 你将不得不向不可避免的事态低头。 2. But most agree that change is inevitable. 但她们多数人同意改变是不可避免的。', '副词: inevitably 名词: inevitability');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('encounter', '[ɪn\'kaʊntər]', 'v.遭遇,遇到,相遇;n.遭遇,遭遇战', '1. If both participate, it may be an actual encounter of bodiless consciousness. 如果是双向的，这会是一个真实的与灵魂的相见。 2. A fortunate encounter brought us together. 一次幸运的邂逅使我们相识。 3. It was a bloody encounter between the two armies. 这是那两军之间的一次激烈的遭遇战。 4. Don\'t be afraid to encounter risks. 不要害怕遭遇危险。', '过去式: encountered 过去分词: encountered 现在分词: encountering 第三人称单数: encounters');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('counterpart', '[\'kaʊntərpɑːrt]', 'n.副本,极相似的人或物,配对物', '1. The secretary of state is the counterpart of the foreign minister. 国务卿相当于外交部长。 2. The sale director phoned her counterpart in the other firm. 这位销售主任给另一家公司的销售主任打电话。 3. Night is the counterpart of day. 黑夜与白天相辅相成。 4. I racked my memory in vain for its counterpart in literature: perhaps you could think of one. 我绞尽脑汁也想不出它在文学中的对等物，也许你可以想出一个。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('defiance', '[dɪ\'faɪəns]', 'n.挑战,蔑视,挑衅', '1. His defiance of the law cost him dearly. 蔑视法律使他付出沈重的代价。 2. Those who bid defiance to the law will get into trouble. 蔑视法律者终要倒霉。 3. They went in defiance of the order. 他们违抗命令还是去了。 4. He had been deposed because of his defiance of Roman law. 亚那因为违抗罗马的法律而被罢免。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('subtract', '[səb\'trækt]', 'v.(～from)减去,减', '1. If you subtract 2 from 8, you get 6. 8减去2是6。 2. Please subtract a quarter of the money for your own use. 请扣除四分之一的钱由你自己支配使用。 3. The little girl has begin to learn to add and subtract. 这小女孩已在学做加减法了。', '名词: subtracter 过去式: subtracted 过去分词: subtracted 现在分词: subtracting 第三人称单数: subtracts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hatch', '[hætʃ]', 'n.孵化,舱口,舱口盖,(门、墙壁、地板上的)开口;vt.孵,孵出,策划,图谋;vi.孵化', '1. The hatch date for tit eggs appears to be determined about a month earlier, when the eggs are laid. 白颊山雀孵化的时间，似乎在孵化前一个月，也就是下蛋时便已决定。 2. Both men quickly disappeared down the hatch. 两个人很快从舱口下去不见了。 3. We heard the noise of a hatch being closed. 我们听到关舱口的声音。 4. An incubator is used to hatch chicken. 孵卵器用来孵小鸡。', '名词: hatcher 过去式: hatched 过去分词: hatched 现在分词: hatching 第三人称单数: hatches');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('assistance', '[ə\'sɪstəns]', 'n.协助,援助,补助,<英>国家补助', '1. We are ready to render them economic assistance. 我们愿意向他们提供经济援助。 2. He gave the assistance to me when I was in trouble. 我有麻烦时,他向我伸出援助之手。 3. You can not rely on his assistance. 你不能指望他能帮助你。 4. I really appreciate your assistance. 衷心感谢您的帮助。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sober', '[\'soʊbər]', 'adj.冷静的;v.镇定', '1. He was tipsy yesterday , but now is sober. 他昨天醉醺醺的,但现在是清醒的。 2. We should make a sober estimate of the situation. 我们对形势要有清醒的估计。 3. He is a very sober and hard-working young man. 他是一个非常稳重而勤奋的年轻人。 4. He talked with us in a sober and friendly fashion. 他以冷静而友好的方式同我们交谈。 5. He drank a cup of strong tea to sober himself up. 他喝下一杯浓茶以使自己清醒过来。 6. He sobered up quickly when he heard the terrible news. 他听到这个坏消息，马上就清醒过来了。', '副词: soberly 比较级: soberer 最高级: soberest 名词: soberness 过去式: sobered 过去分词: sobered 现在分词: sobering 第三人称单数: sobers');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('throne', '[θroʊn]', 'n.王座,君主', '1. Henry IV usurped the throne of England. 亨利四世篡夺了英国的王位。 2. He set up a claim to the throne. 他自称王位是属于他的。 3. He was only eight when he ascended the throne. 他登上王位时才八岁。 4. He swore allegiance to the throne. 他宣誓效忠国王。', '过去式: throned 过去分词: throned 现在分词: throning 第三人称单数: thrones');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('concentrate', '[\'kɑːnsntreɪt]', 'v.集中,浓缩', '1. I can\'t concentrate on my work when I\'m tired. 我累了就无法集中精力工作。 2. The confusing matters make him unable to concentrate on his study. 那么多烦心事使他无法专心学习。 3. The crowds concentrated round the palace. 人群汇集在宫殿的四周。 4. Birds concentrate in places where food is abundant. 鸟聚集在食物丰盛的地方。 5. It is an orange concentrate which you dilute with water. 这是一种兑水饮用的浓缩橙汁.', '形容词: concentrative 副词: concentratively 名词: concentrator 过去式: concentrated 过去分词: concentrated 现在分词: concentrating 第三人称单数: concentrates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dolphin', '[\'dɑːlfɪn]', 'n.海豚', '1. The dolphin is an intelligent animal. 海豚是聪明的动物。 2. We like to see the performance of dolphins. 我们喜欢看海豚的表演。 3. The dolphin balanced the ball on its nose. 海豚用鼻子顶着球，使其保持平衡。 4. They have taught a new trick to the dolphin. 他们教给了海豚一种新的把戏。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('prime', '[praɪm]', 'n.最初,青春,精华;adj.主要的,最初的,有青春活力的,最好的,第一流的,根本的,[数]素数的;v.预先准备好,<口>让人吃(喝)足,灌注,填装', '1. He reached his prime and then, when he had the most to live for, he died. 他到了壮年时期,该做出最大贡献,活得最好的时候,却死掉了。 2. We were well prime for the journey with a large breakfast. 为了去旅行,我们早餐都吃得饱饱的。 3. What was said was of prime importance. 说过的那件事是很重要的。 4. Britain has a queen, but it is the prime minister and the cabinet who govern. 英国有女王,但执政的是首相和内阁。 5. He died in the prime of his life. 他在壮年时死去。 6. It states that every even number greater than two can be expressed as the sum of two primes (a prime is a number that is only divisible by itself and by 1, such as 7 and 13). 其陈述是：每一个大于2的偶数都可以表达成两个素数之和(素数是指只能被1和它本身整除的数，如7和13)。 7. She has been well primed about what to say. 她已经有人指点,知道要说些什么。 8. Peace is the prime objective of our foreign policy. 我们把争取和平作为对外政策的首要任务。', '副词: primely 名词: primeness 过去式: primed 过去分词: primed 现在分词: priming 第三人称单数: primes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('drawback', '[\'drɔːbæk]', 'n.缺点,障碍,退还的关税,退税(指进口货物再出口时退还其进口时的关税)', '1. The great drawback to living near a main road is noise. 住在大街旁最大的缺点是噪音。 2. Everything has its drawbacks. 凡事都有不足之处。 3. Many people are talking about the impact of export drawback system reform on the economy in China these days. 这些天来许多人都在讨论出口退税制度改革对我国经济的影响。 4. Illness is a great drawback to a learner. 患病对学生来说是大为不利的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('graphic', '[\'ɡræfɪk]', 'adj.绘画似的,图解的', '1. The general gave a graphic account of the battle. 将军对战斗作了生动的描述。 2. He was a man of many words and many graphic gestures. 他是一个话多的人，还不停比划着生动的手势。 3. The newspaper article gave a graphic description of the earthquake. 报纸文章生动地描述了地震的情况。 4. The principal kept a graphic record of school attendance. 校长用图表记录学生的出席率。 5. Please help me to make a graphic. 请帮我做份图表。', '副词: graphically 名词: graphicness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('jerk', '[dʒɜːrk]', 'n.性情古怪的人,急推,猛拉,肌肉抽搐,(生理)反射,牛肉干;vi.痉挛,急拉,颠簸地行进;vt.猛拉', '1. The bus jerked to a stop. 公共汽车猛然刹车停住了。 2. He jerked the string and the puppet jumped. 他猛地一拉绳子，木偶就跳了起来。 3. He give his tooth a sharp jerk and it come out 他猛一使劲把牙拔了下来 4. The knife was stuck but she pulled it out with a jerk. 那把刀子被卡住了，她猛地一拔，把它拔了出来。', '副词: jerkingly 名词: jerker 过去式: jerked 过去分词: jerked 现在分词: jerking 第三人称单数: jerks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('slum', '[slʌm]', 'n.贫民窟;vi.访问贫民区', '1. They\'ve demolished the slum district. 贫民区已拆除。 2. The bar in the slum is a den of iniquity. 这个贫民窟里的小酒吧是一个充满罪恶的场所。 3. The slum area was sordid and filthy beyond belief. 该贫民区之污秽肮脏简直令人难以置信。 4. She could not speak the jargon of the slum. 她不会讲贫民区的黑话。', '形容词: slummy 名词: slummer 过去式: slummed 过去分词: slummed 现在分词: slumming 第三人称单数: slums');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('claim', '[kleɪm]', 'n.(根据权利提出)要求,要求权,主张,要求而得到的东西;vt.(根据权利)要求,认领,声称,主张,需要', '1. The matter claimed our serious attention. 这件事需要我们认真注意。 2. Did you claim on the insurance after your car accident? 出了车祸后，你向保险公司要求赔偿了吗？ 3. The government would not even consider his claim for money. 政府甚至不考虑他的赔款要求。 4. He set up a claim to the throne. 他自称王位是属于他的。', '形容词: claimable 名词: claimer 过去式: claimed 过去分词: claimed 现在分词: claiming 第三人称单数: claims');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bounce', '[baʊns]', 'v.(使)反跳,弹起,(指支票)被银行退票,弹跳;n.(球)跳起,弹回', '1. The ball hit the wall and bounced off it. 球打在墙上又反弹回来。 2. She\'s had many misfortunes in her life but she always bounces back. 她一生中经历过许多挫折，然而总是能重新振作起来。 3. He is young enough to bounce back from this disappointment. 他很年轻，能够从这次挫折中恢复过来。 4. I hope this cheque doesn\'t bounce. 我希望这张支票别遭退票 5. I bounced the baby on my knee. 我把婴儿放在膝上上下颠着。 6. The volleyball gave a high bounce. 排球高高地弹起来。', '过去式: bounced 过去分词: bounced 现在分词: bouncing 第三人称单数: bounces');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bound', '[baʊnd]', 'n.跃进,跳,范围,限度;adj.正要启程的,开往...去的,被束缚的,装订的;v.跳跃,限制', '1. It\'s bound to rain soon. 过一会儿肯定会下雨。 2. You are not legally bound to answer these questions. 在法律上，你没有义务非回答这些问题不可。 3. We are bound hand and foot by the contract, so we are unable to help you. 我们受到合同的约束而不能帮你。 4. He bought a bound volume of the magazine. 他买了一本该杂志的合订本。 5. The dog bounded down the hill. 狗跳跃着朝山下跑去。 6. With one bound, he was over the wall. 他纵身一跃就跳过了墙。', '过去式: bounded 过去分词: bounded 现在分词: bounding 第三人称单数: bounds');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('verdict', '[\'vɜːrdɪkt]', 'n.[律](陪审团的)裁决,判决,判断,定论,结论', '1. The jury announced their verdict. 陪审团做出了裁决。 2. The jury brought in a verdict of guilty. 陪审团作出有罪的裁决。 3. \"A science fiction cannot not be regarded as a mere entertainment, but in fact it tells the reader much more.\" \"科幻小说不能简单地看成是供消遣的，而实际上它给读者展示更深刻的内容。\" 4. They have had the verdict of the electors. 他们已经知道了选举人的决定。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('solitary', '[\'sɑːləteri]', 'adj.孤独的', '1. His childhood was repressed and solitary. 他的童年是压抑而孤独的。 2. The trapper leads a solitary life in the mountains. 那个设陷阱捕猎的人孤独地生活在山里。 3. Solitary as their lives were, is there no one person who would serve my purpose? 尽管他们过的是遗世独立的生活，难道就没有一个能够对我的计划有帮助的人吗? 4. A solitary rider was seen in the distance. 远处有个孤零零的骑马的人。', '副词: solitarily 名词: solitariness 名词复数: solitaries');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rebel', '[\'rebl]', 'n.造反者,叛逆者,反抗者,叛乱者;adj.造反的,叛逆的,反抗的;v.造反,反叛,反抗,叛乱', '1. The rebels made regular attacks on the railways. 叛军不时地袭击铁路。 2. The rebel wanted to get away from the country. 造反者想脱离国家。 3. The woman was a rebel against feudal ethics. 那个女人是封建礼教的叛逆。 4. I\'ve always been the rebel of the family. 我在家里向来是个叛逆者。 5. When a lot of people rebel, there is a rebellion. 当许多人造反时，就出现了起义。', '过去式: rebelled 过去分词: rebelled 现在分词: rebelling 第三人称单数: rebels');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('arc', '[ɑːrk]', 'n.弧,弓形,拱', '1. The first figure is an arc followed by a line. 第一个图形是一段弧,后跟一条直线。 2. The beach swept around in an arc. 海滩呈弧形伸展开来。 3. His arm described an arc in the air. 他的手臂在空中划出一道弧形。 4. The rainbow formed a beautiful arc in the sky. 虹在天上成美丽的弧形。', '过去式: arced/arcked 过去分词: arced/arcked 现在分词: arcing/arcking 第三人称单数: arcs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sophisticated', '[sə\'fɪstɪkeɪtɪd]', 'adj.诡辩的,久经世故的', '1. She is such a sophisticated woman that she saw through his trick at the first sight. 她是个十分老练的女人,她一眼就看穿了他的把戏。 2. As far as defense is concerned, we need to buy more sophisticated weapons. 就防御的观点来说，我们需要购买更多精密的武器。 3. The publisher\'s techniques for the promotion of his books have become increasingly sophisticated since the 1950s. 自20世纪50年代以来,出版商推销书籍的方式愈加复杂。 4. I\'d rather deal with a simple man than a sophisticated man. 我宁愿与纯朴的人打交道,不愿与世故的人交往。', '副词: sophisticatedly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('collaboration', '[kəˌlæbə\'reɪʃn]', 'n.协作,通敌', '1. Then the long collaboration fell apart. 长期的兄弟合作就这样破裂。 2. He wrote the book in collaboration with his colleagues. 他与同事合作写了这本书。 3. It was a collaboration that produced extremely useful results. 这是一次富有成果的合作。 4. He was shot for collaboration with the enemy. 他因通敌而被枪毙了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dissipate', '[\'dɪsɪpeɪt]', 'v.驱散,(使)(云、雾、疑虑等)消散,浪费(金钱或时间)', '1. The sun dissipated the mist. 太阳驱散了雾。 2. Her son\'s letter dissipated all her fears and anxiety. 她儿子的来信消除了她一切恐惧和焦虑。 3. The crowd dissipated soon after the police arrived. 在警察到达之后，人群很快散去了。 4. He soon dissipated his fortune. 他很快就把财产浪费光了。', '形容词: dissipative 名词: dissipater 过去式: dissipated 过去分词: dissipated 现在分词: dissipating 第三人称单数: dissipates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hemisphere', '[\'hemɪsfɪr]', 'n.半球', '1. the party out ofoffice 2. If you cut a round fruit into two, each half is a hemisphere. 如果你把一个圆的水果切成两半，每一半就是一个半球。 3. The Northern Hemisphere is the part of the world north of the equator, and the Southern Hemisphere is south of the equator. 北半球是地球赤道以北的部分，南半球是赤道以南的部分。', '形容词: hemispheric 副词: hemispherically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('toss', '[tɔːs]', 'v.投,掷', '1. The decision depended on the toss of a coin. 那项决定是靠掷硬币的方法做出的。 2. The first toss here would appear to favor Candida. 第一次投掷结果看来对坎迪德有利。 3. The children tossed the ball to each other. 孩子们互相把球扔来扔去。 4. My husband was tossing and turning all night. 我丈夫整夜翻来覆去睡不着。', '名词: tosser 过去式: tossed 过去分词: tossed 现在分词: tossing 第三人称单数: tosses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('remainder', '[rɪ\'meɪndər]', 'n.残余,剩余物,其他的人,[数]余数;v.廉价出售;adj.剩余的,出售剩书的', '1. The remainder must be paid by the end of June. 剩余部分的金额必须在月底前付清。 2. He spent the remainder of his life in the country. 他在乡村度过余生。 3. Nine people came in and the remainder stayed outside. 9个人进来，余下的人留在外面。 4. Take 4 from 9 and the remainder is 5. 9除以4余数为5。', '过去式: remaindered 过去分词: remaindered 现在分词: remaindering 第三人称单数: remainders');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('inclusive', '[ɪn\'kluːsɪv]', 'adj.包含的,包括的', '1. The monthly rent is $20 inclusive of everything. 月房租总共二十美元,包括一切费用在内。 2. His concept of history is modern and inclusive. 她的历史观现代又富包容性。 3. The party must adopt more inclusive strategies and a broader vision. 这个党必须采取更广泛的策略和更远大的视野。 4. I\'ll be away from the 20th to the 31st of May inclusive. 我从五月二十号到三十一号（包括这两天）,都不会在。', '副词: inclusively 名词: inclusiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('confront', '[kən\'frʌnt]', 'vt.使面临,对抗', '1. We must confront future with optimism. 我们必须乐观地面对未来。 2. You must confront your problems. 你必须面对自己的问题。 3. It\'s no use to confront your boss. 对抗你的老板是没有用的。 4. A soldier often has to confront danger. 士兵常常要身临险境。', '名词: confronter 过去式: confronted 过去分词: confronted 现在分词: confronting 第三人称单数: confronts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('petition', '[pə\'tɪʃn]', 'n.请愿,情愿书,诉状,陈情书;v.请求,恳求,请愿', '1. Many subscribers\' names are in the petition. 请愿书上有很多签名者的名字。 2. They signed a petition in support of the workers\' demands. 他们在请愿书上签名，支持工人的请求。 3. She made a silent petition to God for help. 她默默地祈求上帝给予帮助。 4. She filed a petition for divorce. 她提出了离婚申请。 5. I can petition for Junie\'s custody. 我可以申请做琼妮的监护人。 6. She petitioned her neighbor to turn down the radio. 她请求邻居把收音机关小点声。', '形容词: petitionary 名词: petitioner 过去式: petitioned 过去分词: petitioned 现在分词: petitioning 第三人称单数: petitions');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('discrete', '[dɪ\'skriːt]', 'adj.不连续的,离散的', '1. They give off discrete amounts of radiant energy. 它们放出不连续的辐射能量。 2. The proteins initially appear as discrete bodies. 蛋白质体最初作为分离体而出现。', '副词: discretely 名词: discreteness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('brew', '[bruː]', 'v.酿造,酝酿', '1. He brews his own beer at home. 他在家自己酿造啤酒。 2. The tea is brewing and will be served soon. 茶正在泡，一会儿就送来。 3. A storm is brewing. 暴风雨正在酝酿中。 4. They are brewing a plot behind the scenes. 他们正在幕后策划一个阴谋。 5. The machine produces a brew that is dark in colour and complex in taste. 这台机器酿造出来的酒颜色很深，味道很复杂。', '名词: brewage 过去式: brewed 过去分词: brewed 现在分词: brewing 第三人称单数: brews');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('orient', '[\'ɔːriənt]', 'n.东方,东方诸国(地中海以东各国);adj.东方的,上升的,灿烂的;vi.适应形势,向东;vt.使朝东,使适应,确定方向', '1. They love paintings from the Orient. 他们喜欢来自东方的绘画。 2. China is the biggest country in the orient. 中国是东方最大的国家。 3. The idea of cantilever construction is ancient in the Orient. 在亚洲古代就已实行过悬臂施工。 4. The vase seems to have an orient origin. 这花瓶好像来自东方。 5. I need some time to orient my thinking. 我需要一些时间来使我的思想适应。', '过去式: oriented 过去分词: oriented 现在分词: orienting 第三人称单数: orients');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('complication', '[ˌkɑːmplɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.复杂化,(使复杂的)因素;n.[医]并发症', '1. This was an unforeseen complication. 这是未预见到的复杂情况。 2. We cannot allow further complication of this matter. 我们不能让这件事变得更复杂了。 3. Complications set in, and the patient died. 病人因出现并发症而死亡。 4. Pneumonia is the complication we most fear. 肺炎是我们最害怕的并发症。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('siege', '[siːdʒ]', 'n.包围,围城,长期努力,不断袭击,围攻;v.包围,围攻', '1. The town was forced to yield after a long siege. 该城受长期围困而被迫弃守。 2. He was smitten with Mary\'s attractions and laid siege to her heart. 他被玛丽的魅力迷惑，对她苦缠不休。 3. The citizens sallied out in an attempt to break the siege. 市民们进行突击，试图冲破包围。 4. He captained the siege of Berlin. 他指挥了围攻柏林的战役。', '过去式: sieged 过去分词: sieged 现在分词: sieging 第三人称单数: sieges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('veil', '[veɪl]', 'n.面纱,面罩,帐,幕,掩饰物,遮蔽物,口实,假托;vt.戴面纱,隐藏,遮蔽,掩饰;vi.蒙上面纱', '1. The bride\'s face was covered in a white veil. 新娘的脸上蒙著白色的面纱。 2. Most Moslem women wear veils in public places. 大多数穆斯林妇女在公共场所都戴着面纱。 3. Rochester assures her it is only a bad dream, but in the morning Jane finds the ripped fragments of the veil. 罗切斯特安慰她说这只是一个恶梦，但清晨简却发现了被撕破的婚纱碎片。 4. Her face was buried behind a veil. 她的脸被面罩遮起来了。 5. The women there used to veil their faces in public. 那里的妇女过去在公共场合通常戴面纱。 6. The women there used to veil their faces in public. 那里的妇女过去在公共场合通常戴面纱。', '过去式: veiled 过去分词: veiled 现在分词: veiling 第三人称单数: veils');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('paperback', '[\'peɪpərbæk]', 'n.平装本,纸面本', '1. This writer\'s books are all issued as paperback. 这位作家的书都是平装书。 2. We are doing a special promotion of our paperback list. 我们正在搞推销平装书的特别宣传活动。', '形容词: paperbacked');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('estimate', '[\'estɪmət]', 'v.&n.估计,估价,评估', '1. This is an outside estimate of the price. 这是最高的估价。 2. Your estimate was rejected by the seller. 你的估价单被卖家回绝了。 3. This is a safe estimate. 这是个有把握的估计。 4. We need to make an accurate estimate beforehand. 我们需要事先作出准确的估计。 5. I estimate it will take three months to build the bridge . 我估计建造这座桥得用3个月时间。', '形容词: estimative 名词: estimator 过去式: estimated 过去分词: estimated 现在分词: estimating 第三人称单数: estimates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('innovation', '[ˌɪnə\'veɪʃn]', 'n.改革,创新', '1. There is no end to practice or innovation. 实践永无止境,创新永无止境。 2. In the age of global competition, design innovation is vital. 在全球激烈竞争的时代,设计创新至关重要。 3. It was a period of innovation. 这是革新时期。 4. A surge of innovation in techniques is on the horizon. 技术改进的浪潮即将出现。', '形容词: innovational');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('layer', '[\'ler]', 'n.层,阶层', '1. This layer of rock contains a lot of flint. 这一岩层中有大量燧石。 2. There is a fine layer of dust on the desk. 桌子上有一层薄薄的尘土。 3. There are several layers of meaning. 有几层不同的含意。 4. The pollution had destroyed ozone layer and caused many changes in weather. 污染破坏了臭氧层，并引起了许多天气变化。 5. Mists layered thick about him. 层层雾霭笼罩着他。 6. Layer the potatoes and onions in a dish. 把土豆和洋葱分层放在盘子里。', '过去式: layered 过去分词: layered 现在分词: layering 第三人称单数: layers');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('Easter', '[\'iːstər]', 'n.[宗](耶稣)复活节', '1. Christmas and Easter are Christian festivals. 圣诞节和复活节是基督教的节日。 2. Easter comes early this year. 今年复活节来得早。 3. At Easter, attendances at church rose. 复活节期间，到教堂做礼拜的人多了。 4. Each of my cousins received an Easter egg on Easter Day. 我的表兄弟们每人在复活节都得到了一枚复活节彩蛋。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('maneuver', '[mə\'nuːvər]', 'v.机动;n.机动', '1. The mouse had a quick wit and was able to maneuver his way out of danger. 老鼠有急智可以灵巧地脱离危险。 2. They have had to maneuver the ship to avoid unforeseen shoals and shallows. 他们必须设法避开无法预见的暗礁和浅滩。 3. The maneuver aims to strengthen special police forces\' emergency response and combat capabilities. 此次演习的目的在于提高特种警力的危机反应能力和战斗能力。 4. An anti-failure maneuver is very important for power system safety and stability in operation. 反事故演习是保证电网安全稳定运行的重要一环。 5. He must have considered the patrol as an effective maneuver. 他思想上一定还以为派兵侦察是条妙计。', '形容词: maneuverable 名词: maneuverability 过去式: maneuvered 过去分词: maneuvered 现在分词: maneuvering 第三人称单数: maneuvers');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cripple', '[\'krɪpl]', 'n.跛子;v.削弱', '1. They helped the cripple up to the bank. 他们把那跛脚的人扶上岸。 2. It is impolite to make fun of a cripple. 取笑一个跛足是不礼貌的。 3. A long delay might cripple me in a way. 长期拖下去可能在某些方面把我拖垮了。 4. His first task was to cripple the enemy at sea. 他的首要任务是使海上的敌人失去战斗力。', '名词: crippler 过去式: crippled 过去分词: crippled 现在分词: crippling 第三人称单数: cripples');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('appease', '[ə\'piːz]', 'vt.平息,安抚,缓和,使满足', '1. Chamberlain tried to appease Hitler at Munich. 张伯伦在慕尼黑尽量安抚希特勒。 2. His attempts to appease her only added fuel to the fire. 他试着安抚她，结果却造成火上加油的局面。 3. State governments are left scrabbling to appease ruraldisgruntlement rather than investing in efforts to lift theproductivity of land and labour. 政府花钱努力来提高农民和工人的生产力还不如想办法缓和农民的不满。 4. Many in the New Republic began to turn against the Jedi in an effort to appease the Yuuzhan Vong and blunt their destructive incursions. 新共和国的许多人开始反对绝地，他们对遇战疯人实施绥靖政策，试图以此缓和遇战疯人毁灭性的入侵行动。', '形容词: appeasable 副词: appeasably 名词: appeaser 过去式: appeased 过去分词: appeased 现在分词: appeasing 第三人称单数: appeases');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('deviate', '[\'diːvieɪt]', 'vi.背离,偏离;v.偏离', '1. Don\'t always deviate to minor issues. 不要老是偏离到次要问题上去。 2. You will not deviate from your present course. 你不能偏离目前航线 3. His remarks usually deviate from truth. 他的话通常都与事实不符。 4. Do not deviate from the beaten track. 不要逸出常轨。', '形容词: deviatory 名词: deviator 过去式: deviated 过去分词: deviated 现在分词: deviating 第三人称单数: deviates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('court', '[kɔːrt]', 'n.法院,庭院,朝廷,球场,奉承,求爱;vt.向...献殷勤,追求,博得(喝彩),招致(失败危险等);vi.求爱', '1. Sherman recommended that Clarke be disciplined, but higher-ups rejected the idea. 谢尔曼建议对克拉克进行纪律惩戒，但高层拒绝了这个意见。 2. My court is deserted but I do not care. 我的庭院一片荒芜但是我无心照看。 3. The court of King Solomon was noted for its splendor. 所罗门国王的宫廷以其华丽著称。 4. The court moves to the country in the summer. 夏天王室上下都移居到乡下去。 5. He has been courting the director, hoping to get the leading role in the play. 他一直在讨好导演，想在剧中扮演主角。', '过去式: courted 过去分词: courted 现在分词: courting 第三人称单数: courts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('deserve', '[dɪ\'zɜːrv]', 'vt.应受,值得;v.应受', '1. He has done nothing to deserve death. 他没做过该受死刑的事。 2. You deserve a reward for being so helpful. 你帮了这么大的忙，理应受到奖励。 3. These proposals deserve careful study. 这些建议值得认真研究。', '过去式: deserved 过去分词: deserved 现在分词: deserving 第三人称单数: deserves');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('recede', '[rɪ\'siːd]', 'v.后退', '1. His hair is beginning to recede from his forehead. 他的头发开始从前额往后秃了。 2. As the tide receded we were able to look for shells. 潮水退去，我们就能寻找贝壳了。 3. The prospect of bankruptcy has now receded. 破产的危险已经减少了。 4. Eventually the danger began to recede. 这种危险终于开始减轻。 5. The company decided to recede from a bargain. 公司决定撤销买卖合同。', '过去式: receded 过去分词: receded 现在分词: receding 第三人称单数: recedes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('charge', '[tʃɑːrdʒ]', 'n.负荷,电荷,费用,主管,掌管,充电,充气,装料;v.装满,控诉,责令,告诫,指示,加罪于,冲锋,收费', '1. As group leader, you should take charge. 你身为组长, 应当负起责任来。 2. He was arrested on a charge of armed robbery. 他被指控犯武装抢劫罪而遭逮捕。 3. Rub the leather and the rubber will produce the charge. 摩擦皮毛和橡胶会产生电荷。 4. He was arrested on a charge of armed robbery. 他被指控犯武装抢劫罪而遭逮捕。 5. How much do you charge per unit? 你们每件要价多少呢？ 6. The suspect was charged with murdering his wife. 嫌疑犯被控诉为谋杀他的妻子。', '过去式: charged 过去分词: charged 现在分词: charging 第三人称单数: charges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('economy', '[ɪ\'kɑːnəmi]', 'n.经济,节约,节约措施,经济实惠,系统,机体,经济制度的状况', '1. The state of the economy is very worrying. 目前的经济状况令人十分担忧。 2. The determinate factor of our economy is to control inflation. 我们经济的决定性因素是控制通货膨胀。 3. The last five years have seen a consistent improvement in the country\'s economy. 在最近的五年里，这个国家的经济状况一直在好转。 4. She preached economy as the best means of solving the crisis. 她大力鼓吹节约是解决危机的关键。 5. An economy class air ticket is fit for ordinary workers, because it costs much less. 经济舱机票对一般工作人员比较合适,因为它的价格要便宜得多。', '名词复数: economies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('climate', '[\'klaɪmət]', 'n.气候,风土,思潮', '1. Britain has a temperate climate. 英国气候温和。 2. She adapted herself quickly to the new climate. 她很快就适应了这种新气候。 3. The small city has the climate that is changeable in the extreme. 这座小城有变化多端的气候。 4. In the current critical climate her work is not popular. 在当前评论风气影响下，她的作品不怎么受欢迎。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cork', '[kɔːrk]', 'n.软木塞,软木,(用塞子)塞住', '1. The cork\'s too big, it won\'t go in. 这软木塞太大了，塞不进去。 2. Do you have any tools to draw out the cork? 你有工具把软木塞拔开吗？ 3. The cork is tight in the bottle. 软木瓶塞紧紧地塞在瓶中。 4. Cork is a very buoyant material. 软木是极易浮起的材料。', '过去式: corked 过去分词: corked 现在分词: corking 第三人称单数: corks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('adjacent', '[ə\'dʒeɪsnt]', 'adj.邻近的,接近的', '1. The house adjacent to ours has been sold. 与我们家邻接的房子已经售出。 2. His house is adjacent to mine. 他的寓所与我的相毗连。 3. The planes landed on adjacent runways. 这些飞机在毗连的跑道上降落。 4. The island of Cuba is adjacent to Florida. 古巴岛接近佛罗里达。', '副词: adjacently');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('descendant', '[dɪ\'sendənt]', 'n.子孙,后裔,后代', '1. He is a descendant of Queen Victoria. 他是维多利亚女王的后裔。 2. I am a descendant of George Washington. 我是乔治华盛顿的后代子孙。 3. A static method does not change when inherited by a descendant class. 当被子孙类继承时，静态方法并不改变。 4. The coastal areas were occupied by the descendants of Greek colonists. 沿海地带居住着希腊殖民者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('visa', '[\'viːzə]', 'n.签证;vt.签准;维萨信用卡', '1. We\'ve had to cut a few corners to get your visa ready in time. 我们得简化手续才能将你的签证及时办妥。 2. He is applying to the Consul for a visa. 他正向领事申请签证。 3. He experienced great difficulty in getting a visa to leave the country. 他申请出国签证经历了很大的困难。 4. He has applied for an entry visa. 他已申请入境签证。 5. I have my passport visaed. 我已取得了护照签证。', '过去式: visaed 过去分词: visaed 现在分词: visaing 第三人称单数: visas');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bleed', '[bliːd]', 'v.使出血,放血', '1. All the young soldiers are ready to bleed for the country. 所有的年轻战士都愿意为祖国洒热血。 2. If you cut your finger it will bleed. 如果你割破手指,那么它会流血的。 3. A page trimmed so as to bleed. 被剪裁的页次经切裁以印成出血版的纸页 4. The tax man is trying to bleed me white. 税务员正想榨尽我的血汗。', '过去式: bled 过去分词: bled 现在分词: bleeding 第三人称单数: bleeds');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('minimal', '[\'mɪnɪməl]', 'adj.最小的,最小限度的', '1. The work was carried out at minimal cost. 这项工作是以最少的开销完成的。 2. She gained only minimal recognition for her work. 她的工作仅仅得到极少的赞誉。 3. There is a minimal quantity of imperfection in the batch. 这批产品的残次品极少。 4. Fortunately, the storm only did minimal damage to the farmer\'s crops. 很幸运, 暴风雨只使农民的庄稼受到轻微的损害。', '副词: minimally 名词: minimality');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('apology', '[ə\'pɑːlədʒi]', 'n.(为某种思想,宗教,哲学等)辩解,道歉', '1. I demand an apology. 我要求道歉。 2. Please accept my apology. 请接受我的道歉。 3. He made a contrite apology. 他深表懊悔地致歉。 4. In my judgement, we should accept their apology. 依我看，我们应该接受他们的道歉。', '名词复数: apologies 动词: apologize');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reliable', '[rɪ\'laɪəbl]', 'adj.可靠的,可信赖的', '1. I don\'t think he is a reliable man. 我认为他不是一个可靠的人。 2. She may be slow but at least she\'s reliable. 她迟钝是迟钝，但无论如何她很可靠。 3. A reliable car is worth its weight in gold. 靠得住的汽车就是无价之宝。 4. A man who is dead to the justice is not reliable. 一个没有正义感的人是不可信的。', '副词: reliably 名词: reliability');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('shipment', '[\'ʃɪpmənt]', 'n.装船,出货', '1. Better to postpone the shipment than to cancel the contract. 与其撤约还不如延期装运。 2. We have reached an agreement with him in regard to the shipment. 我们已经就装运问题同他达成协议。 3. A signed invoice presumes receipt of the shipment. 经过签字的发票表示货物已经收到。 4. The merchant had received a shipment of tea. 这个商人收到了一船茶叶。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('administration', '[ədˌmɪnɪ\'streɪʃn]', 'n.管理,经营,行政部门', '1. He is responsible for the administration of justice. 他负责赏罚。 2. He works in hospital administration. 他从事医院管理工作. 3. The company developed rapidly under his administration. 在他的管理下，公司发展得很快。 4. Head teachers are more involved in administration than in teaching. 校长的行政工作比教学工作多。', '形容词: administrative 副词: administratively');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('nourish', '[\'nɜːrɪʃ]', 'vt.滋养,使健壮,怀有(希望,仇恨等)', '1. They needed good food to nourish their bodies. 他们需要好食品滋养身体。 2. Milk is all we need to nourish a small baby. 我们供给婴儿营养只需喂奶就够了。 3. Most plants are nourished by water drawn up through their roots. 多数植物是靠着根吸收水分来维持生命的。 4. The school\'s goal is to nourish young musical talent. 这个学校的目标是培育年轻的音乐人才。', '名词: nourisher 过去式: nourished 过去分词: nourished 现在分词: nourishing 第三人称单数: nourishes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('effective', '[ɪ\'fektɪv]', 'adj.有效的,被实施的,给人深刻印象,有生力量', '1. Advertising is often the most effective method of promotion. 做广告往往是最有效的推销方法。 2. Their efforts to improve the production have been very effective. 他们提高生产力的措施卓有成效。 3. When does the new system become effective? 新制度何时生效？ 4. Her brother is the king, but she is the effective ruler. 她的兄弟是国王, 但她才是实际的主宰者。', '名词: effectiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('define', '[dɪ\'faɪn]', 'vt.定义,详细说明', '1. We should clearly define the scope of our research. 我们应该明确规定我们的研究范围。 2. The bank needs to define and delegate the responsibilities related to the various aspects of its marketing programme. 银行必须规定并授予与营销计划有关的各项职权。 3. The dependent claim shall,by additional technical features,further define the claim which it refers to. 从属权利要求应当用附加的技术特征，对引用的权利要求作进一步限定。 4. The section defines the extent of application of the Act. 该条款用来限定该法令的适用范围。', '形容词: definable 副词: definably 名词: definability 过去式: defined 过去分词: defined 现在分词: defining 第三人称单数: defines');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('intense', '[ɪn\'tens]', 'adj.强烈的,剧烈的,热切的,热情的,激烈的', '1. He\'s been under intense pressure. 他面对着很大的压力。 2. My work is so intense that I even have no time to take a rest. 我的工作非常紧张，以致于我没有时间休息。 3. Her feelings are so intense as to move the present into tears. 她的感情如此之切,使在场的人都流下了眼泪。 4. There was intense competition between the rival companies to get the contract. 为得到这份合同,各不相让的两家公司展开了激烈的竞争。', '副词: intensely 比较级: intenser 最高级: intensest 名词: intenseness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('artillery', '[ɑːr\'tɪləri]', 'n.炮的总称,炮兵的总称', '1. The invaders would also have artillery. 进攻者还将配备火炮。 2. All Artillery Shells have been depleted. 火炮炮弹已经用尽。 3. Artillery and aircraft were involved in the action. 在这次战斗中，使用了大炮和飞机。 4. There is a continuing artillery barrage. 大炮持续不断的轰击伊军。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reckless', '[\'rekləs]', 'adj.不计后果的', '1. He\'s a reckless driver. 他是个鲁莽的司机。 2. He apologized for their reckless behavior. 他对他们的鲁莽行为道了歉。 3. His brother is a reckless gambler. 他的弟弟是个不计后果的赌徒。 4. It\'s the way you try to sound rough or reckless. 你说起话来故意这样显得很粗野或者毫不在乎。', '副词: recklessly 名词: recklessness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fuse', '[fjuːz]', 'n.保险丝,熔丝;v.熔合', '1. The fuse-box is in the kitchen. 保险丝盒子在厨房里。 2. Changing a fuse is one of those fiddly jobs I hate. 我最不愿意干换保险丝这类活儿了。 3. It seems that you\'ve blown a fuse. 看样子你把保险丝烧断了。 4. I know how to mend a fuse and I don\'t need you shoving your oar in! 我知道怎麽弄保险丝，用不著你管！ 5. We fuse copper and tin to make bronze. 我们把铜和锡熔制成青铜。 6. The metal will fuse at a relatively low temperature. 这金属在不太高的温度下熔化。', '过去式: fused/fuzed 过去分词: fused/fuzed 现在分词: fusing/fuzing 第三人称单数: fuses/fuzes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('poisonous', '[\'pɔɪzənəs]', 'adj.有毒的', '1. Some mushrooms are poisonous. 有些蘑菇有毒。 2. Some snakes have poisonous fangs. 有些蛇长有毒牙。 3. She gave him a poisonous look. 她恶狠狠地瞪了他一眼。 4. He said some poisonous things to me. 他对我说了一些恶毒的事。', '副词: poisonously 名词: poisonousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('stall', '[stɔːl]', 'n.货摊,畜栏,厩,出售摊;v.(使)停转,(使)停止,迟延', '1. The excited horse flung about in the stall. 受惊的马在马厩里乱冲乱踢。 2. The horse chafed against his stall. 马在厩栏上擦著身子。 3. Our house has a shower stall. 我们房子里有淋浴小隔间。 4. Never buy food from a market stall. 千万别在小摊上买食物。 5. You\'d better stall the pigs. 你最好把猪关在猪圈里饲养。', '过去式: stalled 过去分词: stalled 现在分词: stalling 第三人称单数: stalls');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('flutter', '[\'flʌtər]', 'n.摆动,鼓翼,烦扰;vi.鼓翼,飘动,悸动,乱跳,烦扰;vt.拍(翅),使焦急', '1. There was a flutter of wings among the trees. 树林里响起一阵飞鸟的拍翅声。 2. He immediately fell into a great flutter. 他立刻变得心慌意乱。 3. The news caused a flutter among the teaching staff. 这个消息在全体教师中引起了不安。 4. Banners fluttered in the breeze. 旗帜在微风中飘扬。', '形容词: fluttery 名词: flutterer 过去式: fluttered 过去分词: fluttered 现在分词: fluttering 第三人称单数: flutters');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ward', '[wɔːrd]', 'n.守卫,保卫,保护,牢房,病房,行政区,监护,锁孔;vt.守护,保卫,防止,挡住,躲开,避免', '1. The hospital has a medical ward and a surgical ward. 这医院有内科病房和外科病房。 2. The patient lay quietly on his bed in the medical ward. 病人安静地躺在内科病房的床上。 3. There are two nurses in the ward. 病房里有两个护士。 4. They phoned to every ward and suburb. 他们给各城区和郊区打电话。 5. The soldiers warded over the city. 士兵们守护着这座城市。', '过去式: warded 过去分词: warded 现在分词: warding 第三人称单数: wards');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('consensus', '[kən\'sensəs]', 'n.一致同意,多数人的意见,舆论', '1. The two parties have reached a consensus. 这两个政党达成了一致意见。 2. It would be a good idea to predict which proposal is most likely to achieve consensus. 不妨研究一下哪项提案最有可能获得一致同意。 3. Yet the events of the past two years have called that consensus in question. 然而,过去两年来发生的各种事件使人们对这一共识产生了疑虑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('temperament', '[\'temprəmənt]', 'n.气质,性情,易激动,急躁', '1. He really has a leader temperament. 他真的有些领袖气质。 2. He is a man with an artistic temperament. 他是个有艺术家气质的男子。 3. I\'ve got a mild temperament. 我的性情很温和。 4. The two brothers have entirely different temperaments. 他们兄弟俩的性情完全不同。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sanction', '[\'sæŋkʃn]', 'n.&v.批准,同意,支持,制裁,认可', '1. The minister can only act in this matter with the sanction of Parliament. 部长只有得到国会批准才能就此事采取行动。 2. The book was translated without the sanction of the author. 这本书未经作者许可就给翻译了。 3. Western nations imposed tough sanctions on the country. 西方各国对这个国家实行了严厉制裁。 4. The church would not sanction the king\'s second marriage. 教会不会批准国王第二次结婚。', '过去式: sanctioned 过去分词: sanctioned 现在分词: sanctioning 第三人称单数: sanctions');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('subtle', '[\'sʌtl]', 'adj.狡猾的,敏感的,微妙的,精细的,稀薄的', '1. There were subtle hints in his letter. 他的信中有些微妙的暗示。 2. What meaning will my subtle signal make? 我的微妙信号表达了什么意思? 3. She has a very subtle mind. 她有个很敏锐的头脑。 4. Satire is a high and subtle art. 讽刺是一门崇高而又含蓄的艺术。', '副词: subtly 比较级: subtler 最高级: subtlest 名词: subtleness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tedious', '[\'tiːdiəs]', 'adj.单调乏味的,沉闷的,冗长乏味的', '1. The tedious job simply ate me up. 那单调乏味的工作简直把我烦死了。 2. He told me a tedious story. 他给我讲了一个冗长乏味的故事。 3. He is an exceedingly tedious fellow. 他是一个非常令人生厌的家伙。 4. How can he give us such a tedious lecture. 他怎么能做这么沉闷乏味的演讲。', '副词: tediously 名词: tediousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('assignment', '[ə\'saɪnmənt]', 'n.分配,委派,任务,(课外)作业', '1. This is Robert Mundell\'s assignment rule. 这就是罗伯特·蒙代尔的分配原则。 2. He is the best man who can finish the assignment. 他是能完成这项任务的最佳人选。 3. How are you going to get through the assignment? 你将如何完成作业呢? 4. I await assignment at any moment. 我随时听候差遣。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('outrage', '[\'aʊtreɪdʒ]', 'n.暴行,侮辱,愤怒;vt.凌辱,引起...义愤,强奸', '1. The Government has been dilatory in condemning the outrage. 政府迟迟才谴责是次暴行。 2. We should never forget the outrage committed by the Japanese invaders. 我们永远都不应该忘记日本侵略者犯下的暴行。 3. All right-minded people will be surely shocked by this outrage. 凡是有正义感的人都一定会对这种暴行感到震惊。 4. Her answer was greeted with cries of outrage. 她的回答引起了一片愤怒的吼叫。 5. He was outraged by their behavior. 他们的行为使他感到愤慨。', '过去式: outraged 过去分词: outraged 现在分词: outraging 第三人称单数: outrages');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('retention', '[rɪ\'tenʃn]', '保持力', '1. The retention is withheld only for bonus situation. 滞留金只是为了发奖金。 2. Did you specify a reasonable retention age? 是否指定了合理的保持期? 3. Plan a retention policy for e-mail messages and log entries. 为电子邮件和日志项计划一个保持策略。 4. His retention of energy at this hour is really surprising. 人们惊叹他在这个时候还能保持如此旺盛的精力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('buzz', '[bʌz]', 'n.嗡嗡声;v.作嗡嗡声,嗡嗡作响,逼近', '1. My brain is buzzing. 我的脑袋嗡嗡响。 2. The room buzzed with excitement. 房间里发出一片兴奋的嚷嚷声。 3. He buzzed for his secretary to come. 他按蜂鸣器叫秘书进来。 4. The courtroom buzzed as the defendant was led in. 被告被带进来时，审判室里发出一阵嘈杂声。 5. The plane buzzed the wood. 那架飞机低空掠过树林。 6. The phone had already clicked down,leaving a faint buzz. 电话已经挂了，只有微弱的嗡嗡声。', '过去式: buzzed 过去分词: buzzed 现在分词: buzzing 第三人称单数: buzzes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('signify', '[\'sɪɡnɪfaɪ]', 'vt.表示,意味;vi.要紧,有重要性;v.颇为重要,表示', '1. She signifies her disagreement. 她表示她不同意。 2. Do dark clouds signify rain? 有乌云是否显示要下雨? 3. A red sunset signifies fine weather. 红红的晚霞是晴天的预兆。 4. A fever usually signifies that there is something wrong with the body. 发烧通常意味着身体有点毛病。 5. It doesn\'t signify, so you needn\'t worry about it. 这无所谓，你不必担心。', '形容词: signifiable 名词: signifier 过去式: signified 过去分词: signified 现在分词: signifying 第三人称单数: signifies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('prospective', '[prə\'spektɪv]', 'adj.预期的', '1. We receive prospective results in the experiment. 我们在实验中得到了预期的结果。 2. Tom is the prospective buyer of my house. 汤姆是可能购买我的房屋的人。 3. I hope you can give this your immediate attention so that I can notify the prospective guests promptly. 我希望您能对此予以迅速考虑，以便我能及时通知期待的客人。 4. She is married to a prospective lawyer. 她嫁给了一个未来的律师。', '副词: prospectively');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('brand', '[brænd]', 'n.商标,牌子,烙印;vt.打火印,污辱', '1. As an author who was in a period when the new and the old interlaced, Cervantes had a brand of two ages inevitably. 作为新旧两个时代交替期的作家,塞万提斯身上不可避免地带有两个时代的烙印。 2. You may personalize the design to match your company\'s existing brand identity and design specifications. 您也可以进行个性化设计,使其符合公司的现有商标与设计规范。 3. The advertising manager may set as a goal for advertising an increase of 15 percent in consumer brand awareness in the next six months. 广告经理确定的目标为:在今后的6个月里，通过广告，提高消费者商标知晓率的15%25。 4. She\'s gone over to a milder brand of cigarettes. 她已改吸另一牌子味道较淡的香烟。 5. Those who have triumphantly withstood such strains may brand his name. 那些成功地经受了严峻考验的人们或许会污辱他的名声。', '名词: brander 过去式: branded 过去分词: branded 现在分词: branding 第三人称单数: brands');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dim', '[dɪm]', 'adj.暗淡的,模糊的,无光泽的,悲观的,怀疑的;vt.使暗淡,使失去光泽;n.<美俚>笨蛋、傻子', '1. Most comets are so dim that they can not be seen by the naked eye. 彗星很暗淡,肉眼看不见。 2. He spoke with firmness, but his face was very sad and his eyes at times were dim. 他讲话时预期坚定，但面带愁容，时而眼神暗淡。 3. I made out two dim shapes in the gloom. 我在朦胧中看出有两个模糊的影子。 4. She is rather dim about the importance of keeping records. 她不明白作记录的重要性。 5. Old age hasn\'t dimmed her memory. 她虽然年事已高，但记忆并未模糊。', '副词: dimly 比较级: dimmer 最高级: dimmest 名词: dimness 过去式: dimmed 过去分词: dimmed 现在分词: dimming 第三人称单数: dims');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('timely', '[\'taɪmli]', 'adj.及时的,适时的', '1. What we expected is nothing less than a timely payment. 及时付款正是我们所盼望的。 2. Had it not been for your timely help, our company would have been on the verge of bankruptcy. 若非你及时伸出援助之手,本公司将会濒临破产。 3. His wife was so poignant and timely. 他的妻子是这样有分寸和适时宜。 4. I think timely rain is good for the crops. 我认为适时地下雨对庄稼生长有好处。 5. I really appreciate your timely help. 真的感谢你及时的帮忙。', '比较级: timelier 最高级: timeliest 名词: timeliness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('robust', '[roʊ\'bʌst]', 'adj.精力充沛的', '1. She was almost 90, but still very robust. 她将近90岁了，但身体仍然十分强健。 2. But I can say for sure that our monetary system is robust. 但是,我可以很肯定地讲,我们的货币体系是稳固。 3. He bought a robust metal cabinet for his new house. 他为新家购置了一个坚固耐用的金属柜。 4. He is a man with a rather robust sense of humor. 他具备颇为粗俗的幽默感。', '副词: robustly 名词: robustness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('gauge', '[ɡeɪdʒ]', 'n.标准尺,规格,量规,量表;v.测量', '1. The fuel gauges dropped swiftly. 燃料表指针迅速下降。 2. What gauge of wire should we use for this job? 我们干这活应该用多大号的铅丝? 3. This is a narrow-gauge railway. 这是一条窄轨铁路。 4. We must gauge the diameter of wire first. 我们必须先测量电线的直径。 5. It was difficult to gauge how people would respond. 大家的反应如何难以估计。', '形容词: gaugeable 过去式: gauged/gaged 过去分词: gauged/gaged 现在分词: gauging/gaging 第三人称单数: gauges/gages');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('luminous', '[\'luːmɪnəs]', 'adj.发光的,明亮的', '1. These reactions are not luminous. 这些反应是不发光的。 2. They like the luminous stones like diamonds in our reality. 他们喜欢发光的石头像现实中的钻石。 3. With this watch you can tell time in the dark because its hands and dial are luminous. 用这只表你可以在黑暗中看时间，因为它的针和针盘都是会发亮的。 4. We are part of eternity, a tremendously luminous experience of ecstasy that is beyond words. 我们是永恒的一部分，有一个极其巨大的发亮的狂喜体验很难用语言表达。', '副词: luminously 名词: luminousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('snack', '[snæk]', 'n.小吃,快餐,一份;v.吃快餐(小吃)', '1. We are in a hurry so we have to make doing with a quick snack . 我们时间很紧,只好胡乱吃了顿小吃 2. Usually I only have a snack at lunchtime. 我中午通常只吃点心。 3. Apples are a more nutritional snack than popcorn. 苹果是比爆米花更有营养的零食。 4. If you snack too much, you may get fat. 零食吃的太多,你会长胖的。', '名词: snacker 过去式: snacked 过去分词: snacked 现在分词: snacking 第三人称单数: snacks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('insulate', '[\'ɪnsəleɪt]', 'vt.使绝缘,隔离', '1. We can insulate a live wire with rubber. 我们可用橡胶使带电的电线绝缘。 2. Rubber is used to insulate electric wires. 橡胶被用来使电线与外界绝缘。 3. Her parents tried to insulate her from dangerous influences. 她的父母试图把她与危险的影响隔绝。 4. It is important to insulate the furnace from any neighbouring woodwork with brick and asbestos. 用砖和石棉把炉子与周围所有的木制品隔开，这很重要。', '过去式: insulated 过去分词: insulated 现在分词: insulating 第三人称单数: insulates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reception', '[rɪ\'sepʃn]', 'n.接待,招待会,接收', '1. The bridal suite was prepared for the reception of the honeymooners. 新婚套间已准备好以接待度蜜月的人。 2. The play got a favourable reception from the critics. 该剧获评论界好评。 3. Wait for me at reception. 在接待处等我吧。 4. The bridal suite was prepared for the reception of the honeymooners. 新婚套间已准备好以接待度蜜月的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('designate', '[\'dezɪɡneɪt]', 'vt.指明,指出,任命,指派;v.指定,指派', '1. She was designated sportswoman of the year. 她被指定为本年度的体坛明星。 2. The chairman has designated that boy as his successor. 主席已经指定那个男孩作他的继承人。 3. Black lines designate boundaries on this map. 在这幅地图上黑线标示疆界。 4. The ruler of a kingdom is designated a king. 王国的统治者称作国王。 5. The ambassador designate is going to meet honored foreign guests. 大使指定人选将要迎接外国贵客。', '形容词: designative 名词: designator 过去式: designated 过去分词: designated 现在分词: designating 第三人称单数: designates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('specific', '[spə\'sɪfɪk]', 'n.特效药,细节;adj.详细而精确的,明确的,特殊的,特效的,[生物]种的', '1. He gave us very specific instructions. 他给我们做了非常明确的指示。 2. This tells you that there is a specific distinction between the right and the wrong. 这件事告诉你是与非是有明确的区别的。 3. Let us take a look at three specific areas of concern. 让我们看一看三个特殊的令人关切的领域。 4. There is no specific remedy for the malady. 没有医治这种病的特效药。 5. This is a specific for cancer. 这是一种治疗癌症的特效药。', '副词: specifically 名词: specificity');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('exceed', '[ɪk\'siːd]', 'vt.超越,胜过;vi.超过其他', '1. His knowledge of history exceeds mine. 他的历史知识超过我。 2. Demand began to exceed supply. 开始供不应求。 3. The fine shall not exceed $300. 罚款不超过三百美元。', '过去式: exceeded 过去分词: exceeded 现在分词: exceeding 第三人称单数: exceeds');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('issue', '[\'ɪʃuː]', 'n.出版,发行,论点,问题,结果,(水血)流出;vi.发行,流出,造成...结果,辩护,传下;vt.使流出,放出,发钞,发令,出书;[律]子女,后嗣', '1. You\'re just avoiding the issue. 你只不过是在回避问题。 2. The union plans to raise the issue of overtime. 工会打算提出加班的问题。 3. Parliament will debate the nationalization issue next week. 议会将在下周辩论国有化议题。 4. They make an issue of this with UEFA. 他们就此向欧足联提出上诉。 5. Xinhua News Agency is authorized to issue the following statement. 新华社受权发表如下声明。', '形容词: issueless 名词: issuer 过去式: issued 过去分词: issued 现在分词: issuing 第三人称单数: issues');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('blossom', '[\'blɑːsəm]', 'n.花(尤指结果实者),花开的状态,兴旺期;vi.开花,兴旺,发展', '1. The sunshine will bring out the blossom. 阳光将使花朵开放。 2. The tree was covered with beautiful pink blossom. 这树开满了美丽的粉红色的花。 3. The apple trees are in blossom. 苹果树正在开花。 4. There are many pear trees covered in blossom. 那里有许多开满花的梨树。 5. The apple trees are blossoming. 苹果树正在开花。', '形容词: blossomy 过去式: blossomed 过去分词: blossomed 现在分词: blossoming 第三人称单数: blossoms');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fabricate', '[\'fæbrɪkeɪt]', 'vt.制作,构成,捏造,伪造,虚构', '1. The defense accused police of fabricating evidence. 被告指责警察编造证据。 2. The story was fabricated and completely untrue. 这故事是捏造的，一点不真实。 3. It is not easy to fabricate DNA evidence. 要假造染色体为证是不容易的。 4. The finest crafts people fabricated this golden ring. 这枚金戒指是由最优秀的工匠制作的。', '名词: fabrication 过去式: fabricated 过去分词: fabricated 现在分词: fabricating 第三人称单数: fabricates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('foul', '[faʊl]', 'adj.污秽的,邪恶的,恶劣的;vt.弄脏,妨害,污蔑,犯规;vi.腐烂,犯规,缠结;n.犯规,缠绕;adv.违反规则地,不正当地', '1. He opened the window to let out the foul air. 他打开窗户，放出污浊的空气。 2. The foul weather spoiled our vacation. 恶劣的天气把我们的假期糟踏了。 3. She has a foul temper. 她脾气暴躁。 4. The ball was foul. 这球犯规了。 5. The forward made a foul in the penalty area. 前锋在禁区内犯规了。 6. Owners who allow their dogs to foul the footpath will be fined. 主人若放任狗弄脏人行道将受处罚。', '副词: foully 比较级: fouler 最高级: foulest 名词: foulness 过去式: fouled 过去分词: fouled 现在分词: fouling 第三人称单数: fouls');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dominant', '[\'dɑːmɪnənt]', 'adj.有统治权的,占优势的,支配的;adj.[生物]显性的', '1. Peace was the dominant theme of the conference. 和平是大会的首要议题。 2. He is a dominant leader in our university. 他是我们学校最主要的一位领导。 3. The right hand is dominant in most people. 大多数人的右手是优势手。 4. The company can\'t preserve its dominant position in the market. 该公司在市场上不能让自己保持优势地位。 5. We should be the dominant of ourselves. 我们要做自己的主宰者。', '副词: dominantly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('incline', '[ɪn\'klaɪn]', 'n.倾斜,斜坡,斜面;vt.使倾向于,使倾斜;vi.倾向,倾斜', '1. The houses followed the curve of the road, which wound up a slight incline. 这些房子沿着道路有些倾斜的曲线而建。 2. She plunged instantly down the slippery incline. 她立刻沿着光滑的斜坡向下跌落。 3. Galileo rolled small metal balls down the incline. 伽利略让小金属球从斜面滚下。 4. I incline to his opinion on this matter. 对这件事我倾向于他的观点。', '名词: incliner 过去式: inclined 过去分词: inclined 现在分词: inclining 第三人称单数: inclines');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('directory', '[də\'rektəri]', 'n.姓名地址录,目录', '1. He thumbed through the directory to look for her number. 他翻阅电话号码簿找寻她的号码。 2. He found their address in the telephone directory. 他在电话薄里找到了他们的住址。 3. And here is our service directory. 这是服务指南。', '名词复数: directories');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('insist', '[ɪn\'sɪst]', 'v.坚持,强调', '1. He insisted that he had done right. 他坚决认为自己做对了。 2. They insist that I stay there for supper. 他们坚决要求让我留下吃晚饭。 3. Since you insist, I must amend the letter of credit. 既然你坚持，我就只好修改信用证。 4. He insisted on paying for the meal. 他坚持要付饭钱。', '副词: insistingly 名词: insistence 过去式: insisted 过去分词: insisted 现在分词: insisting 第三人称单数: insists');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('deem', '[diːm]', 'v.认为,相信', '1. They were deemed to be illegal immigrants. 他们被认为是不法移民。 2. They deemed that he was no longer capable of managing the business. 他们认为他没有能力再继续管理这个公司了。 3. These buildings are deemed to be of architectural importance and must be protected. 这些楼房被视为具有建筑的重要性', '过去式: deemed 过去分词: deemed 现在分词: deeming 第三人称单数: deems');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ore', '[ɔːr]', 'n.矿石,含有金属的岩石', '1. We will make an assay of the ore that he brought. 我们将对他带来的矿石做实验鉴定。 2. The ore is smelted in this large factory. 这个大型工厂里熔炼矿石。 3. This is an area rich in ore. 这里是个矿产丰富的地区。 4. But few of them had actually dug up any ore. 然而他们中只有少数几个确实挖了矿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('intelligible', '[ɪn\'telɪdʒəbl]', 'adj.可理解的', '1. His theory is not intelligible to us. 他的理论我们无法理解。 2. The book is intelligible to anyone. 这本书任何人都看得懂。 3. The answers must be intelligible, but they do not have to be in complete sentences. 答案必须要清楚明晰，不过不必是完整的句子。', '副词: intelligibly 名词: intelligibility');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('infant', '[\'ɪnfənt]', 'n.婴儿,幼儿;adj.婴儿的,幼稚的', '1. She gazed at the newborn infant and smiled. 她望着这个初生的婴儿笑了。 2. My sister\'s infant is very lovely. 我姐姐的小婴儿非常可爱。 3. A 35-day-old male infant was scheduled for bilateral inguinal herniorrhaphy. 摘要一个三十五天大的幼儿接受二沟腹股沟疝气门诊手术。 4. Infant family education is an important education environment which can\'t be irreplaceable by preschool education and social education. 幼儿家庭教育是幼儿园教育和社会教育所不能替代的重要教育环境。 5. Infant mortality is still very high in some developing countries. 某些发展中国家的婴儿死亡率仍然很高。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('proximity', '[prɑːk\'sɪməti]', 'n.接近,亲近', '1. Their house is in close proximity to ours. 他们的房子很接近我们的。 2. The sum is in close proximity to the amount of revenue. 总数接近岁入之值。 3. My proximity to your office adds flexibility. 我住的地方靠近贵公司，工作可以说是更加方便有利。 4. Marriages in proximity of blood are forbidden by the law. 法律规定禁止近亲结婚。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('salute', '[sə\'luːt]', 'n.(尤指军队等之)举手礼,升降旗致敬,呜礼炮等,敬礼;v.行礼致敬,敬礼', '1. We salute the flag everyday at school. 我们在学校每天向国旗行礼。 2. This ignoramus failed to salute me. 这个蠢汉看见我不行礼。 3. They saluted each other by raising their hats. 他们举起帽子互相致意。 4. Shanghai people salute guests and friends from all over the world. 上海人民向海内外宾朋致意。', '名词: saluter 过去式: saluted 过去分词: saluted 现在分词: saluting 第三人称单数: salutes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('symposium', '[sɪm\'poʊziəm]', 'n.讨论会,座谈会', '1. We will hold a symposium this afternoon. 今天下午，我们要召开一次讨论会。 2. In this symposium, my part is only to sit in silence. 在这次讨论会上，我只要安静的坐着就够了。', '名词复数: symposiums');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('closet', '[\'klɑːzət]', 'n.壁橱,储藏室,厕所;adj.关起门来的;vt.关入私室密谈', '1. Put the coats back into the closet. 请把大衣放回到壁橱里。 2. You may put these books in the closet. 你可以把这些书放在壁橱里。 3. The Prince\'s bedroom is large, but his closet is larger. 王子的卧室也很大,不过他的衣帽间则更大。 4. The loser closely enclosed himself in the closet. 那个失败者把自己严密地封闭在小室内。 5. We must guard against closet racists. 我们必须警惕隐蔽的种族主义者。 6. He used to closet himself with a book. 过去他常把自己关在小房间里读书。', '名词: closetful 过去式: closeted 过去分词: closeted 现在分词: closeting 第三人称单数: closets');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('premium', '[\'priːmiəm]', 'n.额外费用,奖金,奖赏,保险费,(货币兑现的)贴水', '1. Who will pay the premium for the risk of breakage? 加保破碎险的费用由谁负担? 2. A premium of 2 percent is paid on long-term investments. 对投资期限较长者可获百分之二的奖励。 3. He\'s had to lay his car up for he can\'t afford the insurance premiums. 因付不起保险费他只得把汽车搁置起来。 4. Shares are selling at a premium. 股票溢价出售。 5. People are prepared to pay premium prices for quality products. 人们已经作好为优质产品花费更多的准备。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('memorize', '[\'meməraɪz]', 'v.[亦作memorise]记住,记忆', '1. The boy can memorize the data easily. 这男孩能轻松地记住这些数据。 2. Actors have to memorize their lines. 演员们不得不记住台词。 3. Of course you have to learn a lot.And you have to memorize a lot of characters. 当然必须学习很多东西，必须记下很多汉字。 4. If a teacher wrote something on the board that had to be memorized verbatim for an upcoming exam, I\'d memorize it then and there.Then I wouldn\'t have to go back and study it later. 如果老师在黑板上面写下一些考试的时候必考的内容的话，我会当堂记下，这样的话我就不用花费课余的时间去重新记忆了。', '形容词: memorizable 名词: memorization 过去式: memorized 过去分词: memorized 现在分词: memorizing 第三人称单数: memorizes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('crisp', '[krɪsp]', 'adj.脆的,易碎的', '1. It tastes sweet and crisp. 吃起来又甜又脆。 2. I like the delicious salad of crisp lettuce and tomatos. 我喜欢这种脆莴苣和番茄做的沙拉，很好吃。 3. Her voice was crisp and authoritative. 她的声音干脆利落，具有权威性。 4. You see how the finish is much more crisp than the rest of the hair. 大家看到了,成型的头发比其余的头发看起来更卷曲。 5. I lay in the sun all day and got burnt to a crisp. 我在太阳下躺了一整天，都快烤焦了。 6. These biscuits have gone soft,you\'d better crisp them up in the oven. 这些饼干变软了，你最好把它们放在烘炉上烤脆。', '副词: crisply 比较级: crisper 最高级: crispest 名词: crispness 过去式: crisped 过去分词: crisped 现在分词: crisping 第三人称单数: crisps');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('intensify', '[ɪn\'tensɪfaɪ]', 'vt.加强;vi.强化', '1. You must intensify your sense of responsibility. 你必须加强责任感。 2. We need to intensify our effort to fight corruption and to prevent and eliminate its root causes. 加大治本力度，从源头上预防和治理腐败。 3. Her anger intensified. 她更加生气了。', '名词: intensification 过去式: intensified 过去分词: intensified 现在分词: intensifying 第三人称单数: intensifies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('thereafter', '[ˌðer\'æftər]', 'adv.其后,从那时以后', '1. Thereafter his idea of attending school gradually strengthened. 其后他求学的信念逐渐增强。 2. In the months thereafter he sank almost completely from view. 其后几个月他差不多完全消失了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('stabilize', '[\'steɪbəlaɪz]', 'v.稳定', '1. His condition has now stabilized. 他的情况稳定下来了。 2. He can now ride his bike without stabilizers. 他现在骑自行车不需要平衡器了。', '名词: stabilization 过去式: stabilized 过去分词: stabilized 现在分词: stabilizing 第三人称单数: stabilizes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tub', '[tʌb]', 'n.浴盆', '1. He scooped some ice-cream out of the tub. 他从桶里舀了一些冰淇淋。 2. He grabbed up the lid of the bran tub. 他把麦麸桶的盖子抓了起来。 3. I soaked in the hot tub for an hour. 我在热浴盆里浸了一个小时。 4. He will bath only after we fill the tub with toys. 他只有在我们在浴盆中装满玩具后才洗澡。 5. Do not tub for more than 5 min for cardiopathy sufferer. 心脏病患者浸泡时间不宜超过5分钟。', '形容词: tubbable 名词: tubber 过去式: tubbed 过去分词: tubbed 现在分词: tubbing 第三人称单数: tubs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('eccentric', '[ɪk\'sentrɪk]', 'adj.古怪;n.行为古怪的人', '1. The old lady is a bit of an eccentric. 这位老太是个有点古怪的人。 2. She put him down as an eccentric person. 她认为他是个行为古怪的人。 3. His actions since that morning have been eccentric and unpredictable. 自从那天早晨,他的行动一直是反常而不可捉摸。 4. The motors and drive units on these two types of polisher\'s oscillate in an eccentric circular motion. 发动机和转速单位在这两种抛光机上的振蒎是一个偏圆心的运动。 5. He had the name of an eccentric. 他有怪人之称。', '副词: eccentrically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ammunition', '[ˌæmju\'nɪʃn]', 'n.军火,弹药', '1. There was no ammunition laid up in the storehouses. 仓库里没有贮存军火。 2. We were desperately short of ammunition. 我们非常缺乏弹药。 3. The soldiers expended all their ammunition in that fight. 士兵在那场战斗中用尽了所有的弹药。 4. They went on firing until they had spent all their ammunition. 他们不停地射击，耗尽了所有的弹药。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reflect', '[rɪ\'flekt]', 'v.反射,反映,表现,反省,细想', '1. Her sad looks reflected the thought passing through her mind. 她忧戚的面容反映出她内心的思想。 2. The results reflect the greatest credit upon all concerned. 这些成绩带给所有有关人员最大的荣誉。 3. The sunlight was reflected in the water. 日光由水面反射出来。 4. I often reflect on the beauty and complexity of life. 我们经常思考人生的美丽与复杂。', '过去式: reflected 过去分词: reflected 现在分词: reflecting 第三人称单数: reflects');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('alter', '[\'ɔːltər]', 'v.改变', '1. But nothing can alter the facts. 但任何东西也改变不了这些事实。 2. Alter Current Boot Record Serial Number. 更改当前引导纪录序列号。 3. Marshaling the structure can transform the layout and alter the offset. 封送结构可转换布局并更改偏移量。', '过去式: altered 过去分词: altered 现在分词: altering 第三人称单数: alters');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('float', '[floʊt]', 'n.漂流物,浮舟,浮萍,彩车;vi.浮动,飘浮,散播,摇摆,(计划等)付诸实行;vt.使漂浮,容纳,淹没,发行,用水注满', '1. There is not enough water to float the ship. 没有足够的水使船漂浮起来。 2. These plants float on the surface of the water. 这些植物漂浮在水面上。 3. They float the canoe out into the middle of the river. 他们将独木舟漂浮到河中央。 4. Survival bobbing lets you float for a long time on your stomach. 救生浮游就是让你长时间地仰卧着漂浮在水上。 5. Pay attention to your float! 注意你的浮标！', '形容词: floatable 过去式: floated 过去分词: floated 现在分词: floating 第三人称单数: floats');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('acquaintance', '[ə\'kweɪntəns]', 'n.相识,熟人', '1. He is not a friend of mine, only an acquaintance. 他不是朋友我的,只是个熟人。 2. I made his acquaintance at a party. 我是在一次聚会上认识他的。 3. Their acquaintance was of long standing. 他们相识多年。 4. He has only a limited acquaintance with the matter. 他对这件事的了解很有限。', '名词: acquaintanceship');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('defeat', '[dɪ\'fiːt]', 'n.击败,战胜,失败;vt.击败,战胜,使失败,挫折;v.击败', '1. He was depressed by his defeat. 失败让他沮丧。 2. This defeat was a powerful blow to the enemy. 这次失败是对敌人的有力的打击。 3. The news of army\'s defeat cast a gloom over the town. 军队败北的消息给小城蒙上了一层忧郁。 4. They are still wailing over their defeat. 他们仍在为比赛失利而悲叹。 5. It was a sound strategy to defeat the enemy. 那是战胜敌人的良策。', '名词: defeater 过去式: defeated 过去分词: defeated 现在分词: defeating 第三人称单数: defeats');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('questionnaire', '[ˌkwestʃə\'ner]', 'n.调查表,问卷', '1. We gave them some questionnaires for collecting data. 为了收集数据我们发给他们一些调查表。 2. Please fill up the blanks in the questionnaire. 请把调查表填写一下。 3. Please complete and return the enclosed questionnaire. 所附问卷请填妥交回。 4. Is a questionnaire answered by 500 people truly representative of national opinion? 一份调查问卷有500人作答,是否能真正代表全国人民的意见?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('poverty', '[\'pɑːvərti]', 'n.贫穷,贫困,贫乏,缺少', '1. People in this area were ground down by hunger and poverty. 这个地区的人们受着饥饿和贫穷的折磨。 2. The man lived in poverty after his unemployment. 这人失业后就生活在贫困之中。 3. Poverty reduced him to begging. 贫穷迫使他行乞。 4. They were handicapped by (a) poverty of resources. 他们因资源短缺处境窘迫。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('endow', '[ɪn\'daʊ]', 'v.捐赠,赋予', '1. I can only endow 100 dollors at most. 我充其量只能捐助100美元。 2. He endowed the hospital with a large fortune. 他捐赠一笔巨款给这家医院。 3. She both built and endowed the hospital. 她不仅建了医院还给医院捐赠资金。 4. He is endowed with literary talent. 他有文学天分。', '过去式: endowed 过去分词: endowed 现在分词: endowing 第三人称单数: endows');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('calcium', '[\'kælsiəm]', 'n.[化]钙(元素符号Ca)', '1. We need some calcium everyday. 我们每天需要些钙。 2. I have a slight calcium deficiency. 我有点缺钙。 3. Like most dairy products, such as milk and cheese, yogurt contains a lot of calcium. 像大部分的乳制品，如牛奶和奶酪一样，优酪乳含有许多钙质。', '简写符号: Ca');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('culture', '[\'kʌltʃər]', 'n.文化,文明', '1. He has to learn the culture of bees. 他得学养蜂。 2. She has studied the cultures of Oriental countries. 她研究过东方各国的文化。 3. He is a man of little culture. 他没多少文化修养。 4. The culture of the mind is vital. 修心养性是极其重要的。', '过去式: cultured 过去分词: cultured 现在分词: culturing 第三人称单数: cultures');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('knob', '[nɑːb]', 'n.(门,抽屉等的)球形捏手,节,瘤,旋钮,球形突出物,(煤,砂糖等的)小块;vt.使有球形突出物;vi.鼓起', '1. Twist the knob to the right setting. 把旋钮拧到适当的定位挡上。 2. As he turned the knob, the sound diminished. 他一转旋钮，声音就变小了。 3. You may turn the right knob on the TV to switch it on. 你可以拧电视上右边的旋钮把它打开。 4. He could not find the knob in the dark. 黑暗中，他无法找到门把手。', '形容词: knobbed');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('correlate', '[\'kɔːrəleɪt]', 'vt.使相互关联;vi.和...相关', '1. Research workers find it hard to correlate the two sets of figures. 研究人员发现很难使这两组数字互相关连。 2. We can often correlate age with frequency of illness. 年龄的大小往往与发病率有关。 3. The results of this experiment do not correlate with the results of earlier ones. 这次试验的结果与以往试验的结果毫不相干。 4. Hatred is a correlate of love. 恨与爱是互相关联的。', '过去式: correlated 过去分词: correlated 现在分词: correlating 第三人称单数: correlates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mourn', '[mɔːrn]', 'v.哀悼,忧伤,服丧', '1. People wore crapes to mourn our leader. 人们戴着黑纱哀悼我们的领导。 2. We mourn for our fallen soldiers. 我们哀悼阵亡的兵士。 3. The old woman still mourns for her son. 这位老太太还在为儿子的死伤心。 4. We mourn in black. 我们穿黑色衣服服丧。', '副词: mourningly 名词: mourner 过去式: mourned 过去分词: mourned 现在分词: mourning 第三人称单数: mourns');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('preferable', '[\'prefrəbl]', 'adj.更可取的,更好的,更优越的', '1. To be honest, I\'ve got a preferable offer. 老实说，我有唯一更好的任务机遇。', '副词: preferably 名词: preferability');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('saturate', '[\'sætʃəreɪt]', 'v.使饱和,浸透,使充满', '1. We lay on the beach, saturated in sunshine. 我们躺在沙滩上，沐浴在阳光里。 2. We were caught in the rain and came home saturated. 我们挨了雨淋, 回家时已浑身湿透。 3. The air was saturated with the perfume of the flowers. 空气中飘荡着花香。 4. The films manufactured by Hollywood are saturated in the cinemas all over the world. 在全世界电影市场上充斥着好莱坞的影片。', '形容词: saturable 名词: saturator 过去式: saturated 过去分词: saturated 现在分词: saturating 第三人称单数: saturates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('aid', '[eɪd]', 'n.帮助,援助,帮助者,有帮助的事物;vt.资助,援助,帮助', '1. The regime has been propped up by foreign aid. 该政权是靠外国援助维持着的。 2. Filled with fears all day long, he decided to seek the aid of a psychiatrist. 他终日恐惧不安,决定寻求心理医生的帮助。 3. In his father\'s presidential race in 1988, George W. Bush became his father\'s aid. 1988年在他父亲竞选总统时,小布什成为父亲的助手。 4. A dictionary is an invaluable aid in learning a new language. 在学习一种新语言时,辞典是非常有用的工具。 5. We were greatly aided in our investigation by the cooperation of the police. 我们在调查的过程中得到警方的大力协助。', '名词: aider 过去式: aided 过去分词: aided 现在分词: aiding 第三人称单数: aids');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('manufacture', '[ˌmænju\'fæktʃər]', 'vt.制造,加工;n.制造,制造业,产品', '1. This firm manufactures cars. 这家公司生产汽车。 2. We manufacture various types of machine tools. 我公司生产各种型号的机床。 3. You will have to manufacture some kind of excuse. 你得找些借口。 4. She manufactured a false story to hide the facts. 她编 造瞎话以掩盖事实。 5. The manufacture of these small components is expensive. 制造这些小部件是非常昂贵的。', '形容词: manufacturable 名词: manufacturing 过去式: manufactured 过去分词: manufactured 现在分词: manufacturing 第三人称单数: manufactures');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('irrespective', '[ˌɪrɪ\'spektɪv]', 'adj.不顾的,不考虑的,无关的', '1. The laws apply to everyone irrespective of race, color, or creed. 法律对人人都适用，不分种族，肤色或信仰。 2. We will have the work done, irrespective of cost. 不管花多大代价,我们也要把这项工作做好。 3. He rushed toward to help, irrespective of the consequence. 他不顾后果，冲上前去帮助。 4. He married her, irrespective of the will of his parents. 他违背父母的意愿与她结了婚。', '副词: irrespectively');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('alcohol', '[\'ælkəhɔːl]', 'n.酒精,酒', '1. Whisky contains a large percentage of alcohol. 威士忌所含酒精的百分比很高。 2. Alcohol has a very bad effect on drivers. 酒精对司机的影响很大。 3. This substance is soluble in alcohol. 这种物质能够溶解在酒精中。 4. He is addicted to alcohol. 他嗜好喝酒。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('deny', '[dɪ\'naɪ]', 'v.否认,拒绝', '1. He is not trustworthy, but at the same time, we cannot deny that he is clever. 他不可信赖,然而我们不能否认他很聪明。 2. He denied that it was his fault. 他拒不承认这是他的过错。 3. I was denied the chance of going to university. 我得不到上大学的机会。 4. We should try to deny ourselves from indulging in computer games. 我们应该尽力克制自己,不使自己沉溺于电脑游戏。', '过去式: denied 过去分词: denied 现在分词: denying 第三人称单数: denies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('association', '[əˌsoʊʃi\'eɪʃn]', 'n.协会,联合,结交,联想', '1. Have you joined the teachers\' association? 你加入教师协会了吗? 2. About 20 people have registered in the association. 大约有20人已登记加入这一协会。 3. There is a hide-and-seek association with a leader who is nowhere to be found. 有一个躲猫猫社团，他们的团长现在还没有找到。 4. Horwath refers to Horwath International Association, a Swiss verein. 浩华是指浩华国际协会，为一个根据瑞士法律所组成的社团组织。', '形容词: associational');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('consecutive', '[kən\'sekjətɪv]', 'adj.连续的,联贯的', '1. It has rained for four consecutive days. 已连续下了四天雨。 2. He was re-elected for four consecutive terms. 他连着四届当选。 3. The policy of our Party is consecutive. 我党的政策始终如一。', '副词: consecutively 名词: consecutiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('blaze', '[bleɪz]', 'n.火焰,光辉,情感爆发;vi.燃烧,照耀,激发;vt.在树皮上刻路标,公开宣布', '1. We warmed our hands near the blaze of the campfire. 我们在篝火的火焰旁暖手。 2. The firemen were unable to control the blaze. 消防队员无法控制这场大火。 3. Seven people died in the blaze at the nightclub. 在夜总会的熊熊烈火中有七人丧生。 4. The blaze of your eyes can burn the beaven and earth. 双瞳的光辉足以灼烧大地。 5. The following morning the building was still blazing. 第二天早上,大楼还在燃烧。', '副词: blazingly 过去式: blazed 过去分词: blazed 现在分词: blazing 第三人称单数: blazes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('furnish', '[\'fɜːrnɪʃ]', 'vt.供应,提供,装备,布置;v.供给', '1. They are renting a furnished flat. 他们租用了一套带有家具的公寓房子。 2. We propose to furnish our own house according to our own taste. 我们建议按自己的爱好布置自己的房子。 3. They scouted around for some antiques to furnish their new apartment. 他们到处搜罗一些古董来装饰新居。 4. I am bound to furnish my antagonists with arguments, but not with comprehension. 我一定要向对手提供争论点，但并无予以理解的必要。', '名词: furnisher 过去式: furnished 过去分词: furnished 现在分词: furnishing 第三人称单数: furnishes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('olive', '[\'ɑːlɪv]', 'n.橄榄树,橄榄叶,橄榄枝,橄榄色', '1. The olive leaf is a badge of peace. 橄榄叶是和平的象征。 2. She speared an olive with her fork. 她用叉子扎起一个橄榄。 3. The olive branch is the emblem of peace. 橄榄枝是和平的象征。 4. She was sitting in the shade of a big olive tree. 她正坐在一棵大橄榄树的树荫下。 5. He has an olive skin. 他的皮肤是黄褐色的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('format', '[\'fɔːrmæt]', 'n.开本,版式,形式,格式;vt.安排...的格局(或规格),[计]格式化(磁盘)', '1. The book has been styled in a modern format. 该书已按照现代版式制作。 2. It\'s the same book,but a new format. 还是那本书 3. The format of the meeting was such that every one could ask a question. 会议安排好可让每个人都能提一个问题。 4. The disk is too large to format for the specified file system. 磁盘过大,无法为指定文件系统进行格式化。', '过去式: formatted 过去分词: formatted 现在分词: formatting 第三人称单数: formats');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('abortion', '[ə\'bɔːrʃn]', 'n.流产,堕胎,失败,夭折,中止,早产', '1. Abortion is illegal in this country. 人工流产在这个国家是不合法的。 2. She decided not to go through with the abortion. 她决定不做流产。 3. Abortion issues are political dynamite. 堕胎问题在政治上是个爆炸性问题。 4. They are discussing the morality of abortion. 他们正在讨论堕胎的道德性。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('frequency', '[\'friːkwənsi]', 'n.频率,周率,发生次数', '1. Accidents on that highway are happening with increasing frequency. 那条高速公路上车祸发生得越来越频繁。 2. Accidents are happening with increasing frequency. 事故正在愈加频繁地发生。 3. He wrote to both with tolerable frequency. 他和他们通信，相当频繁。 4. He varied the transmission frequency. 他变换了无线电传送的频率。', '名词复数: frequencies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('buck', '[bʌk]', 'n.<美口>元,雄鹿,公羊,公兔;v.(马等)突然一跃(将骑手摔下)', '1. People want to make a quick buck. 人人都想赚容易钱。 2. The buck shook his antlers ferociously. 那雄鹿猛烈地摇动他的鹿角。 3. The buck jumped into the woods before the hunter raised his gun. 还没等猎人举起枪来那只雄鹿就跳进了树林。 4. Both buck and doe have a little gait and both their eyelids palpitate. 雄兔脚扑朔，雌兔眼迷离。 5. The horse may still buck, but now the peeler can start topping it off. 虽然那匹马还会猛然弯背跃起，但现在驯马者可以结束对它的驯服工作了。', '名词: bucker 过去式: bucked 过去分词: bucked 现在分词: bucking 第三人称单数: bucks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hawk', '[hɔːk]', 'n.鹰,掠夺他人的人,鹰派成员;vi.放鹰,像鹰一般地袭击,清嗓,咳嗽;vt.捕捉,咳出,兜售,(沿街)叫卖,散播', '1. The hawk is hovering overhead. 鹰在头顶上盘旋。 2. The hawk pounced on its prey and carried it off. 那只鹰向那小动物猛扑过去把它叼走了。 3. He is neither a dove nor a hawk, but betwixt and between. 他既不是鸽派，也不是鹰派，而是中间派。 4. In a free market, retailers hawk their wares. 自由市场里商贩们不停地叫卖着。', '形容词: hawkish 副词: hawkishly 名词: hawkishness 过去式: hawked 过去分词: hawked 现在分词: hawking 第三人称单数: hawks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('grease', '[ɡriːs]', 'n.油脂,贿赂;vt.涂脂于,<俗>贿赂', '1. Mother smeared grease on her hands. 母亲用油脂涂沫了双手。 2. The engine was covered in grease. 发动机上有层油脂。 3. I use the floor cleaner to remove grease. 我用地板除垢剂清除油污。 4. You\'re supposed to grease the pan first. 你应该先往锅里加点儿油。', '形容词: greaseless 过去式: greased 过去分词: greased 现在分词: greasing 第三人称单数: greases');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('terrific', '[tə\'rɪfɪk]', 'adj.令人恐怖的', '1. The ceiling came down with a terrific crash. 随着一声可怕的巨响，天花板塌了下来。 2. The agony of that moment was terrific. 那一刹那的痛苦是可怕的。 3. The view was terrific. 景色美极了。 4. I feel absolutely terrific today. 我今天的感觉真是好极了!', '副词: terrifically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('burden', '[\'bɜːrdn]', 'n.担子,负担;v.负担', '1. The burden on his back seemed to be crushing him to the earth. 他背上的重负似乎要把他压倒在地。 2. People on high incomes face a huge tax burden. 高收入的人面临着沉重的纳税负担。 3. The burden of organizing the campaign fell to me. 组织这次活动的责任落到了我头上。 4. I don\'t want to lay a burden on you. 我不想让你承担责任。 5. I don\'t want to burden you with my problem. 我不想让我的问题给你添麻烦。', '过去式: burdened 过去分词: burdened 现在分词: burdening 第三人称单数: burdens');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('asset', '[\'æset]', 'n.资产,有用的东西', '1. It was too early to conclude if there was an asset price bubble. 在现阶段下结论,认为出现资产价格泡沫属言之尚早。 2. Private consumption improved and asset prices rose sharply. 私人消费有所改善,资产价格更大幅攀升。 3. The tennis player\'s speed is his great asset. 那个网球运动员动作迅速，这是他的一大优势。 4. A sense of humour is a great asset for a person. 幽默感是一个人的宝贵资产。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('universe', '[\'juːnɪvɜːrs]', 'n.宇宙,世界,万物,领域', '1. The universe exists in space. 宇宙存在于太空。 2. The depth of the universe is immeasurable. 宇宙无限深广。 3. The Earth is only one of the numerous planets in the universe. 地球只是宇宙中众多星球中的一个。 4. Man is the soul of the universe. 人是万物之灵。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('plausible', '[\'plɔːzəbl]', 'adj.似是而非的', '1. Such a theory seems very plausible. 这一理论貌似十分有理。 2. He can not find a plausible reason for his absence. 翻译他找不到缺席的合理理由。 3. Though controversial, it is plausible. 虽有争议，却似乎行得通。 4. He trotted out a most plausible story, but most of us were inclined to doubt the truth of it. 他提出了一个听起来很有道理的说法，但我们大多数人对此都持怀疑态度。', '副词: plausibly 名词: plausibility');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('avail', '[ə\'veɪl]', 'vi.有益于,有帮助,有用,有利;vt.有利于;n.效用,利益', '1. Such a statement will not avail. 这样的声明没有什么用。 2. It will avail them to dispose of their booty. 转让赃物对他们来说是有利的。 3. His subtlety could not avail him here. 他精明机智在这里无济于事了。 4. I\'m afraid my help didn\'t avail you much. 恐怕我的帮助对你用处不大。 5. He tried and tried but all his efforts were of no avail. 他试了又试，但一切努力都不起作用。', '副词: availingly 过去式: availed 过去分词: availed 现在分词: availing 第三人称单数: avails');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('elementary', '[ˌelɪ\'mentri]', 'adj.初步的,基本的,[化]元素的,自然力的', '1. He is ignorant of even the most elementary facts. 他连最基本的事实都不知道。 2. They lack the most elementary sanitary facilities. 他们缺乏最基本的卫生设备。 3. This is the elementary rules of social conduct. 这是社会行为的基本原则。 4. This elementary school is affiliated to a university. 这所小学附属于一所大学。', '副词: elementarily 名词: elementariness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('quantify', '[\'kwɑːntɪfaɪ]', 'vt.确定数量;v.量化', '1. The cost of the flood damage is impossible to quantify. 这次水灾的损失是无可估量的。 2. Now, a new study has helped quantify this trend. 现在有一项新的研究对这一趋势进行了量化。 3. It\'s difficult to quantify the value of space exploration. 把太空探索的价值进行量化是很困难的。', '形容词: quantifiable 名词: quantification 过去式: quantified 过去分词: quantified 现在分词: quantifying 第三人称单数: quantifies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cannon', '[\'kænən]', 'n.大炮,加农炮;v.炮轰', '1. The cannon shot the town to pieces. 大炮的射击毁了这座城市。 2. Being destitute of cannon, they mounted Quaker guns in the fort. 因为没有大炮，他们只得在城堡上装设假炮。 3. The cannon thundered in the hills. 大炮在山间轰鸣。 4. Our fighter planes are all armed with cannon. 我们的战斗机都装备了机关炮。 5. put a finger into another pie', '名词复数: cannon 过去式: cannoned 过去分词: cannoned 现在分词: cannoning 第三人称单数: cannons');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('enhance', '[ɪn\'hæns]', 'vt.提高,增强;v.提高', '1. He made many efforts to enhance his reputation. 他做了许多努力来提高他的声誉。 2. Martial education is an important means to exercise volition and enhance national defense notion. 提出军事教育是锻炼意志,提高国防观念的重要手段。 3. This year, we will review the functions and other aspects of District Councils and enhance our support for them. 今年将展开对区议会功能等方面的检讨,增加对区议会的支持。 4. The programme aims to enhance the employment of young people with disabilities or early signs of mental illness. 计划的目的,是加强残疾或出现精神病早期徵状的青少年的就业能力。', '形容词: enhancive 名词: enhancement 过去式: enhanced 过去分词: enhanced 现在分词: enhancing 第三人称单数: enhances');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bull', '[bʊl]', 'n.[动]公牛,粗壮如牛的人', '1. The bull bellowed angrily. 公牛怒吼起来。 2. His bull will come to serve our cows tomorrow. 明天我们用他的公牛与我们的母牛配种。 3. A bull market is a situation in which share prices are rising. 牛市是指股价不断攀升的行情。 4. He likes to throw the bull. 他喜欢吹牛。 5. The pope issued a bull declaring that abortion was not approved by the church. 教皇发布训令，宣布堕胎不被教堂认可。 6. Still another depicted Europa deceived by Jupiter under the disguise of a bull. 再一幅是描写欧罗巴尼如何被化身成公牛的朱庇特所欺骗。', '过去式: bulled 过去分词: bulled 现在分词: bulling 第三人称单数: bulls');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('contract', '[\'kɑːntrækt]', 'n.合同,契约,婚约;v.使缩短,感染,订约', '1. They had set a term to the contract. 他们已给合同定了期限。 2. Families sought favourable alliances, either by marriage or contract. 各个家庭通过婚姻或者婚约来建立有力的亲缘关系。 3. Several companies will bid for the contract. 数家公司要投标争取合约。 4. He managed to disengage himself from the contract. 他成功地为自己解除了契约义务。 5. The heat contracted the woollen garment. 高温让羊毛衣缩小了。', '形容词: contractible 名词: contractibility 过去式: contracted 过去分词: contracted 现在分词: contracting 第三人称单数: contracts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('comprehensive', '[ˌkɑːmprɪ\'hensɪv]', 'adj.全面的,广泛的,能充分理解的,包容的', '1. The reporter has made a comprehensive report. 记者已做了全面的报道。 2. She has a comprehensive grasp of the subject. 她已全面掌握了这一学科。 3. Applying the most comprehensive metal is iron. 应用最广泛的金属是铁。 4. We have a rather comprehensive subway system here. 我们这儿有相当广泛的地铁系统。', '副词: comprehensively 名词: comprehensiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dismiss', '[dɪs\'mɪs]', 'vt.解散,下课,开除,解职,使(或让)离开;vi.解散', '1. If you are late again, you will be dismissed. 如果你再迟到，你将被解雇。 2. Let us dismiss and return in an hour. 让我们先解散,一个钟头后再回来。 3. We should dismiss all thought of revenge. 我们应该屏除一切报复的念头。 4. The justice dismissed his evidence out of hand. 法官当即驳回了他的证据。', '形容词: dismissible 名词: dismission 过去式: dismissed 过去分词: dismissed 现在分词: dismissing 第三人称单数: dismisses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cocaine', '[koʊ\'keɪn]', 'n.古柯碱,可卡因', '1. He was addicted to cocaine. 他吸可卡因上瘾。 2. Cocaine is a highly addictive drug. 可卡因是一种极为容易上瘾的毒品。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('chorus', '[\'kɔːrəs]', 'n.合唱,合唱队,齐声', '1. The audience chimed in on the chorus. 听众开始跟合唱队一起唱起来。 2. The chorus is dressed as fairies. 歌舞队的人都装扮成仙子。 3. When I asked questions, they answered up in chorus. 我提问题时,他们迅速齐声回答。 4. The chorus is very catchy to say the least. 副歌部分很容易上口。 5. The papers all chorused the praises of the President. 各报都异口同声地对总统表示赞扬。', '名词复数: choruses 过去式: chorused/chorussed 过去分词: chorused/chorussed 现在分词: chorusing/chorussing 第三人称单数: choruses/chorusses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dedicate', '[\'dedɪkeɪt]', 'vt.献(身),致力,题献(一部著作给某人)', '1. She dedicated her life to science. 她毕生致力于科学。 2. I will dedicate myself to science in the future. 我将来一定要投身于科学事业。 3. I dedicate this song to my wife. 我要把这首歌献给我太太。 4. I\'d like to dedicate the book to my parents. 我想把这本书献给我的父母。', '名词: dedicator 过去式: dedicated 过去分词: dedicated 现在分词: dedicating 第三人称单数: dedicates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('foremost', '[\'fɔːrmoʊst]', 'adj.(位置或时间)最先的,最初的,最重要的;adv.首要地,首先', '1. He is one of the foremost scientists in China. 他是中国最重要的科学家之一。 2. He was one of the foremost literary scholars in England. 他是英格兰最重要的文学专家之一。 3. Good schemes will do more than funnel money from latecomers to early takers, allowing the foremost to prosper at the expense of the hindmost. 好的庞式计划将不仅仅是将钱从后来者转到早的加入者手中，以最后面的加入者为代价来使最初的加入者获得成功。 4. First and foremost, I think you should work harder on your biology. 首先，我认为你应该多在生物学上下功夫。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('worthy', '[\'wɜːrði]', 'n.杰出人物,知名人士;adj.有价值的,应...的,可敬的,值得的,相称的', '1. This is a worthy English-Chinese dictionary. 这是一本有价值的英汉词典。 2. This book is worthy of reading. 这本书值得一读。 3. No man thinks more highly than I do of the patriotism, as well as abilities, of the very worthy gentlemen who have just addressed the house. 没有人比我对刚刚向议会全体代表发言的可尊敬的先生们的爱国精神和才干更钦佩了。 4. Mr. Foker himself is a worthy man, though not of high extraction or indeed much education. 福克先生本人也是值得尊敬的,尽管他出身不太高贵,受的教育确实也有限。 5. I want you to sell these two and find more worthy replacements. 我需要你卖这些二和发现更多杰出人物替换。', '副词: worthily 比较级: worthier 最高级: worthiest 名词: worthiness 名词复数: worthies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('soar', '[sɔːr]', 'v.高飞,高丛,滑翔,剧增,昂扬;n.高飞范围,高涨程度', '1. The eagle can soar without flapping their wings. 老鹰无需振翼就能翱翔。 2. Food prices soar during the cold weather. 这个寒冷的冬季食品价格猛涨。 3. Air pollution will soon soar above safety levels. 空气污染会很快突破安全标准。 4. Finally, the river continued to soar, the priest was merciless floods drowned. 最后，河水继续高涨，神父被无情的洪水淹死了。 5. The soar of trade brings big benefits to the two countries. 贸易的剧增给两国带来了极大的好处。', '副词: soaringly 名词: soarer 过去式: soared 过去分词: soared 现在分词: soaring 第三人称单数: soars');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sprinkle', '[\'sprɪŋkl]', 'v.撒(某物)于(某物之表面),洒,喷撒', '1. He sprinkled vinegar on his fish and chips. 他把醋洒在鱼和薯条上。 2. He wanted to tell her to sprinkle the floor. 他想告诉她在地上洒点水。 3. Sprinkle a little salt on the rice. 在米饭上撒点盐。 4. Grate the cheese and sprinkle it over the tomatoes. 把干酪磨碎撒在西红柿上。 5. We covered the cakes with chocolate sprinkles. 我们给蛋糕洒上巧克力末。', '过去式: sprinkled 过去分词: sprinkled 现在分词: sprinkling 第三人称单数: sprinkles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('credit', '[\'kredɪt]', 'n.信任,信用,声望,荣誉,[财务]贷方,银行存款;vt.相信,信任,把...归给', '1. Credit counseling helped us get out from under. 信用咨询使我们免除了忧虑 2. Where can I see my credit score? 我在哪能看到我的信用分数? 3. They are working hard for the credit of China. 他们在为中国的荣誉而努力工作。 4. You must pass the examination to get credit for the course. 你必须通过考试才能获得那门课程的学分。 5. At the time, we used to credit everything to one person. 那时大家把什么都归功于一个人。', '过去式: credited 过去分词: credited 现在分词: crediting 第三人称单数: credits');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rival', '[\'raɪvl]', 'n.竞争者,对手;v.竞争,对抗,相匹敌', '1. He is hound out of his job by jealous rival. 他受到忌妒他的竞争者的算计而被迫离职。 2. The party leader has been supplanted by his rival. 那位政党领导已被他的对手取而代之了。 3. He was utterly unscrupulous in his competition with rival firms. 他与对立公司竞争完全不讲道德。 4. Ships can\'t rival aircraft for speed. 轮船在速度方面无法与飞机匹敌。', '过去式: rivaled/rivalled 过去分词: rivaled/rivalled 现在分词: rivaling/rivalling 第三人称单数: rivals');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('confusion', '[kən\'fjuːʒən]', 'n.混乱,混淆', '1. He gazed in confusion at the strange sight. 他惶惑地凝视着这种奇怪的景象。 2. This misprint led to great confusion. 这个印刷错误造成很大的混淆。 3. Words like\"believe\" and \"receive\" are a source of confusion in spelling. 诸如 believe和 receive 这样的词在拼写上容易混淆。 4. The most brilliant person may be mired in details and confusions. 即使是最聪明的人也会陷入琐事与混乱之中。', '形容词: confusional');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('instrument', '[\'ɪnstrəmənt]', 'n.工具,手段,器械,器具,手段', '1. This instrument monitors the patient\'s heartbeats. 这台仪器监听病人的心跳。 2. He can play nearly every musical instrument. 他几乎能演奏每一件乐器。 3. A plough is an instrument used for farming. 犁是用于耕作的工具。 4. The hospital imported some surgical instruments. 医院进口了一些外科器械。', '过去式: instrumented 过去分词: instrumented 现在分词: instrumenting 第三人称单数: instruments');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('explore', '[ɪk\'splɔːr]', 'v.探险,探测,探究', '1. The experts are exploring every part of the island. 专家们正在勘查这个岛的各个部分。 2. He had an itch to get away and explore. 他等不及要动身去探险。 3. Can you explore the market possibility for us? 您能为我们考察一下市场前景吗？ 4. Columbus discovered America but did not explore the new continent. 哥伦布发现了美洲', '过去式: explored 过去分词: explored 现在分词: exploring 第三人称单数: explores 名词: exploration');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bracket', '[\'brækɪt]', 'n.墙上凸出的托架,括弧,支架;v.括在一起', '1. Their incomes are brought into a higher bracket. 他们的收入已进入一个较高的等级段。 2. Put your name in brackets at the top of each page. 把你的名字填写在每页上端的括号内。 3. The worker fixed a bracket on the wall. 工人在墙上固定了一个支架。 4. You\'d better bracket those shelves with two-by-fours. 你最好用截面为2英寸×4英寸的木材为那些架子做托架。', '过去式: bracketed 过去分词: bracketed 现在分词: bracketing 第三人称单数: brackets');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('paradox', '[\'pærədɑːks]', 'n.似非而是的论点,自相矛盾的话', '1. The gorilla is something of a paradox in the African scene. 在非洲大舞台上大猩猩有点象似是而非的隽语。 2. This paradox cannot be explained, you have to experience it. 这种悖论是不能解释的，你必须经历它。 3. Paradox and irony are characteristics of her style. 她善於运用似非而是的隽语和反语。 4. `More haste, less speed\' is a well-known paradox. ｀欲速不达＇是人所熟知的隽语。', '形容词: paradoxical 副词: paradoxically 名词: paradoxicalness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('compromise', '[\'kɑːmprəmaɪz]', 'n.妥协,折衷;v.妥协,折衷,危及...的安全', '1. He did it without compromise of his dignity. 他做这事而不损及他的尊严。 2. The agreement is a compromise, not a sell-out. 这个协议是双方妥协的产物而不是一方让步。 3. After some discussion we arrive at a compromise. 经过一番讨论之后，我们达成一项折衷方案。 4. Or are we ready to compromise our faith? 或者，我们准备好了在信仰上折衷吗？ 5. With this increased awareness, attackers are finding it more difficult to compromise systems at the network level. 由于对这些认识得越来越清楚，攻击者发现在网络级上危害系统更加困难。 6. They found it wiser to compromise with her. 他们觉得与她妥协更明智。', '名词: compromiser 过去式: compromised 过去分词: compromised 现在分词: compromising 第三人称单数: compromises');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('assurance', '[ə\'ʃʊrəns]', 'n.确信,断言,保证,担保', '1. He gave me assurance in black and white. 他给了我书面保证。 2. I have full assurance of his honesty. 我完全相信他的诚实。 3. He gave me a definite assurance that the repairs would be finished tomorrow. 他给我确切保证，修理将于明日完工。 4. They were waiting with assurance for me to discover the truth for myself. 他们自信地等待我自己发现事实真相。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('attain', '[ə\'teɪn]', 'vt.达到,获得;v.达到', '1. We can attain whatever goal we set in our mind. 我们设定了什么目标，就能实现什么目标。 2. We should be able to attain that goal. 我们应该能够实现这个目标。 3. The country attained its independence in 1972. 这个国家在1972年获得了独立。 4. They\'re sure to attain emancipation in the end. 他们最后一定能获得解放。', '形容词: attainable 名词: attainability 过去式: attained 过去分词: attained 现在分词: attaining 第三人称单数: attains');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('barrier', '[\'bæriər]', 'n.(阻碍通道的)障碍物,栅栏,屏障', '1. The ice skater rammed into the barrier. 溜冰者撞到护栏上了。 2. Heavy duties on imports and exports are a barrier to international trade. 进出口的高关税是国际贸易的障碍。 3. The Sahara Desert is a natural barrier between north and central Africa. 撒哈拉沙漠是北非与中非之间的天然屏障。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dreadful', '[\'dredfl]', 'adj.可怕的,<口>讨厌的', '1. Oh, no! How dreadful! 哦，不!真可怕！ 2. There presents a dreadful sight. 那里呈现出可怕的情景。 3. We are waiting for God\'s dreadful judgement. 我们在等待上帝令人生畏的审判。 4. The dreadful sight chilled her to the marrow. 这种可怕的景象使她感到毛骨悚然。', '副词: dreadfully 名词: dreadfulness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('electrical', '[ɪ\'lektrɪkl]', 'adj.电的,有关电的', '1. There is a fault in the electrical system. 电路系统出了故障。 2. Now electrical appliances have entered into ordinary families. 现在家用电器已经步入普通家庭。 3. There are some electrical apparatus in the room. 房间里有些电器。 4. Electrical problems may be an issue. 可能会遇到有关电的问题。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ruin', '[\'ruːɪn]', 'v.(使)破产,(使)堕落,毁灭;n.毁灭,崩溃,废墟,遗迹', '1. He ruined his prospects by carelessness. 他因疏忽大意而断送了前途。 2. The politics of the company will ruin their image. 公司的策略会毁掉他们的形象。 3. His enemies maliciously conspired to ruin him. 他的敌人恶毒地密谋搞垮他。 4. The rain ruined my painting. 这场雨把我的画给毁了。 5. His rashness led ultimately to his ruin. 他的急躁鲁莽最终导致了他的毁灭。', '形容词: ruinable 名词: ruiner 过去式: ruined 过去分词: ruined 现在分词: ruining 第三人称单数: ruins');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('spy', '[spaɪ]', 'n.特工人员,间谍,侦探,探员,秘密侦察他人行动者;v.侦察,侦察,发现', '1. The spy was expelled from the realm. 这名间谍被驱逐出境。 2. This evidence reinforces my view that he is a spy. 这个证据证实了我认为他是间谍的这一看法。 3. The scout was sent to spy out the land. 侦探被派出去秘密侦察高地去了。 4. She hired a detective to spy on her husband. 她雇了一个侦探来监视她丈夫。 5. The scout was sent to spy out the land. 侦探被派出去秘密侦察高地去了。', '名词复数: spies 过去式: spied 过去分词: spied 现在分词: spying 第三人称单数: spies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('deficiency', '[dɪ\'fɪʃnsi]', 'n.缺乏,不足', '1. I have a slight calcium deficiency. 我有点缺钙。 2. The result in either case is an energy deficiency. 不论哪种情况结果都会导致能量损失。 3. Things will go much better if people of the same trade make up the other\'s deficiency from their own surplus. 同行业之间互通有无，调剂余缺，事情就好办得多了。 4. The deficiency of this plan is very clear and it can\'t possibly succeed. 这项计划的缺陷是很明显的，它不可能成功。', '名词复数: deficiencies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('obstacle', '[\'ɑːbstəkl]', 'n.障碍,妨害物', '1. Lack of education is an obstacle of success. 缺乏教育是成功的障碍。 2. This is the chief obstacle to world peace. 这是世界和平的主要障碍。 3. He took every obstacle in his stride. 他轻易地度过一切难关。 4. Overstaffing has become the obstacle for reforms. 人浮于事已成为改革的绊脚石。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('object', '[\'ɑːbdʒekt]', 'n.物体,目标,宾语,对象;vi.反对,拒绝,抗议;vt.提出...来反对', '1. Various objects were on the table. 桌子上摆着各种各样的物体。 2. His one object in life is to earn as much money as possible. 一生中的他的一个目标将挣得尽可能多的钱。 3. This church is the main object of his interest. 他最感兴趣的是这座教堂。 4. If it is a transitive verb, what is its object? 如果是及物动词,它的宾语是什么? 5. In the final analysis, I object to the proposal. 归根结底,我反对这个建议。', '名词: objector 过去式: objected 过去分词: objected 现在分词: objecting 第三人称单数: objects');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('recipe', '[\'resəpi]', 'n.处方', '1. What\'s your recipe for success? 你取得成功有什么窍门？ 2. He knows the recipe for this dish. 他知道这道菜的烹饪方法。 3. This recipe will be enough for four servings. 本食谱为四人食用分量。 4. In fact, could I ask you for the recipe? 事实上,我能向你要这道菜的食谱吗?', '名词复数: recipes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cafeteria', '[ˌkæfə\'tɪriə]', 'n.自助餐厅', '1. They had their lunch in a cafeteria. 他们在一家自助餐厅吃了午饭。 2. The cafeteria is on the basement level. 自助餐厅在地下一层。 3. I found him work in a cafeteria by chance. 我偶然发现他在一家自助餐厅工作。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('extraordinary', '[ɪk\'strɔːrdəneri]', 'adj.非常的,特别的,非凡的,特派的', '1. He has an extraordinary memory. 他有非凡的记忆力。 2. His extraordinary skill was praised by all. 他超凡的技艺博得了广泛的赞誉。 3. I find it very extraordinary. 我觉得这非常离奇。 4. He is full of extraordinary ideas. 他满脑子都是离奇的想法。', '副词: extraordinarily');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('prone', '[proʊn]', 'adj.倾向于', '1. He was prone to anger. 他易于发怒。 2. The child is rather accident-prone. 那个小孩很容易出事儿。 3. People are more prone to make mistakes when they are tired. 人们疲劳时更容易出差错。 4. He\'s probably prone to domestic violence. 他也许有家庭暴力的倾向。', '副词: pronely 名词: proneness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('supreme', '[suː\'priːm]', 'adj.极度的,极大的,至高的,最高的', '1. The general was girded with the supreme power. 将军被授予最高权力。 2. The safety of the people is the supreme law. 人民的安全是最高的法律。 3. Supreme authority resides in the State. 最高权力属于国家。 4. Wisdom is the supreme part of happiness. 智慧是幸福的顶峰。', '副词: supremely 比较级: supremer 最高级: supremest 名词: supremeness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mortal', '[\'mɔːrtl]', 'n.凡人,人类;adj.必死的,致命的,人类的,临终的;adj.<口>极端的,非常大(长)的', '1. His injuries proved mortal. 他的伤成了致命伤。 2. He received a mortal wound soon after the battle began. 战争开始后不久, 他就受到了致命的重伤。 3. Man is mortal. 人都是会死的。 4. The antagonisms between the two empires and systems were mortal. 这两个帝国和两种制度之间，有着不共戴天的仇恨。 5. No mortal could vie with Zeus. 任何凡人都没法与宙斯匹敌。', '副词: mortally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('proof', '[pruːf]', 'n.证据,试验,考验,[印刷]校样;adj.不能透入的,证明用的,防...的,有耐力的;vt.检验,校对,使不被穿透', '1. This fact is too evident to require proof. 这事实很明显, 用不着证明。 2. Have you got any proof that you own this bike? 你有什么证据证明这辆自行车是你的？ 3. There are a few misprints which I will correct in proof. 有几处印错了,我将在校样上一一改正。 4. The shelter was proof against the bitter weather. 这个棚子可以避寒。 5. It is part of your duty to proof twenty pages. 校对20页是你分内之事。', '名词: proofer 过去式: proofed 过去分词: proofed 现在分词: proofing 第三人称单数: proofs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('paradise', '[\'pærədaɪs]', 'n.天堂', '1. Hawaii is called an island paradise. 夏威夷被称为海岛乐园。 2. I see no sign of the actual approach of this hundred per cent French paradise. 我看不出有什么迹象表明这种十全十美的法国天堂真正会到来。 3. Hong Kong is a travellers\' paradise. 香港是旅游者的乐园。 4. This club is a paradise for athletes. 这个俱乐部是运动员的天堂。', '形容词: paradisiacal 副词: paradisiacally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('blur', '[blɜːr]', 'v.涂污,污损(名誉等),把(界线,视线等)弄得模糊不清,弄污;n.污点', '1. The damp paper caused the ink to blur. 潮纸因墨水弄上污渍。 2. Don\'t blur the distinctions between things. 不要模糊事物之间的差别。 3. Do drunkards blur reality, or come closer to it? 酒醉之后是使现实模糊不清，还是更加接近现实了呢? 4. But we see it only as a hazy blur. 但我们看到的只是模糊的斑点。', '形容词: blurry 名词: blurriness 过去式: blurred 过去分词: blurred 现在分词: blurring 第三人称单数: blurs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('resemblance', '[rɪ\'zembləns]', 'n.类同之处', '1. Mary bears a striking resemblance to her sister. 玛丽和她的姐妹极其相像。 2. There was a distant resemblance between them. 他俩有隐约相似的地方。 3. Twins often show great resemblance. 双生子常极相似。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('compute', '[kəm\'pjuːt]', 'v.计算,估计,用计算机计算(或确定)', '1. Ask the waiter to compute the bill. 请侍者算帐。 2. He failed to compute the interest. 他没有把利息算进去。 3. People appear to be born to compute. 人似乎生来就会计算。 4. We can compute the circular area with radius. 我们能用半径计算出圆的面积。', '形容词: computable 名词: computability 过去式: computed 过去分词: computed 现在分词: computing 第三人称单数: computes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('glitter', '[\'ɡlɪtər]', 'vi.闪闪发光,闪烁,闪光;n.闪光', '1. Wealth\'s glitter never washed a foul life clean. 财富的光辉永远洗不净肮脏的生涯。 2. In these cities what remains of the old China is hidden by the glitter. 在这些城市里，旧中国所遗留下来的东西都被闪烁的灯光掩埋了。 3. He stared at me with a cruel glitter in his eyes. 他眼露凶光地瞪着我。 4. She felt the glitter of the visions mounting to her brain. 这个梦幻世界放射出的华丽光辉逐渐侵入了她的脑海。 5. The diamond ring on her finger glittered in the light. 她手指上的钻石戒指在灯光下闪闪发光。', '形容词: glittery 副词: glitteringly 过去式: glittered 过去分词: glittered 现在分词: glittering 第三人称单数: glitters');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('patriotic', '[ˌpeɪtri\'ɑːtɪk]', 'adj.爱国的,有爱国心的', '1. They had a pile of stuff put out by some kind of East-Prussian patriotic blood-and-soil gang. 他们手头上有一大堆材料，是东普鲁士一帮标榜爱国的纳粹分子散发出来的。 2. They are still sceptical about socialism, but they are patriotic when it comes to facing imperialism. 他们对社会主义还有怀疑，但是在帝国主义面前，他们还是爱国的。', '副词: patriotically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('inhabit', '[ɪn\'hæbɪt]', 'vt.居住于,存在于,占据,栖息', '1. Broadly, we investigate the world\'s lakes and rivers and the creatures which inhabit them. 宽广地，我们调查世界的湖和河和居住于他们的人。 2. Wookiees inhabit the upper levels of the forest, having built their massive cities within the interwoven canopy. 伍基人占据了树林的上层，并在交织的树冠上建造了巨大的城市。 3. Under Forman\'s tutelage, actors fully inhabit their roles, the hospital becomes an evil institution, and the movie poignantly celebrates the human spirit. 根据福尔曼的指导，演员完全占据自己的角色，医院成为一个邪恶的机构，和电影尖锐地庆祝人类的精神。 4. Many types of seabirds inhabit the coral island. 这个珊瑚岛上栖息着很多种海鸟。', '形容词: inhabitable 名词: inhabitability 过去式: inhabited 过去分词: inhabited 现在分词: inhabiting 第三人称单数: inhabits');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('squad', '[skwɑːd]', 'n.班', '1. They are the precision shooting asset of a squad. 他们是步兵班里的神枪手。 2. The sergeant barked an order to his squad. 中士厉声向他班士兵下命令。 3. After a long drill he told the squad to fall out. 操练了好半天之后，他让这个班解散了。 4. As the rest of the squad wandered away, I remained at attention. 我们班的人都走了以后，我还在原地立正。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('prohibit', '[prə\'hɪbɪt]', 'vt.禁止,阻止', '1. Smoking is prohibited here. 这里禁止吸烟。 2. We should prohibit the sale of pornographic literature. 我们应该禁止出售淫秽文学。 3. Some areas prohibit dogs or require them to be on a leash at all times. 一些区域禁止狗或者要求一直拴住它们。 4. Rainy weather and fog prohibited flying. 雨天和大雾妨碍了飞行。', '过去式: prohibited 过去分词: prohibited 现在分词: prohibiting 第三人称单数: prohibits');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('unemployment', '[ˌʌnɪm\'plɔɪmənt]', 'n.失业,失业人数', '1. Mass unemployment may lead to social upheaval. 大批失业会导致社会动乱。 2. The specter of unemployment haunted the land. 失业的恐怖笼罩全国。 3. The decrease in unemployment was 30 percent. 失业人数减少了百分之三十。 4. One deals with unemployment claims. 一个涉及到失业人数情况。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('haul', '[hɔːl]', 'n.用力拖,拖拉,捕获物,努力得到结果,一网捕获鱼量,拖运距离;vi.拖,拉,改变方向,改变主意;vt.拖拉,拖运', '1. They hauled the boat up the beach. 他们把船拖上岸。 2. It cost him no end of time and groans to haul his wounded leg behind him; 他拖着那条受伤的大腿往上爬，时不时地呻吟一声，速度非常慢。 3. So I won\'t have to haul you around all the time. 这样我就不用老是拉着你去这去那了。 4. Falumpasets haul battle wagons and the catapults of the Gungan Grand Army into the battlefield, and Boss Nass uses a decorated falumpaset as a ceremonial transport. 费隆帕斯特拖运刚耿大军的战车及投石机上战场，而那斯老大以一只装饰华丽的费隆帕斯特做为典礼上用的交通工具。 5. It is a long haul to drive across the country. 开车越过这个国家，是一段艰苦的长途旅行。', '名词: hauler 过去式: hauled 过去分词: hauled 现在分词: hauling 第三人称单数: hauls');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('economic', '[ˌiːkə\'nɑːmɪk]', 'adj.经济(上)的,产供销的,经济学的', '1. Economic analysis displays its effectiveness in tackling pollution. 通过对污染税的经济学分析可以看出其较强的治理效果。 2. They had led the country into economic disaster. 他们把国家带入了经济灾难中。 3. The threat of an economic depression hangs over the world. 经济衰退的威胁笼罩着世界。 4. The economic sanctions could not prevent the development of that country. 经济制裁不能阻碍那个国家的发展。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('subjective', '[səb\'dʒektɪv]', 'adj.主观的,个人的', '1. His arguments were never subjective. 他的论点从来不是主观的。 2. He took a subjective view of the problem. 他用主观的方法看问题。 3. Grading of oral tests is quite subjective. 口语考试的打分是相当主观的。', '副词: subjectively 名词: subjectiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('verbal', '[\'vɜːbl]', 'adj.口头的', '1. They had made a verbal agreement to sell. 他们达成了口头售货协定。 2. Don\'t be afraid of verbal abuse or criticism. 不要害怕口头上的辱骂或批评。 3. The teacher teaches us the verbal skills. 老师告诉我们使用言辞的技巧。 4. The verbal imagery has hardly changed. 语言文字的意象几乎没有改变。', '副词: verbally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('straightforward', '[ˌstreɪt\'fɔːrwərd]', 'adj.正直的,坦率的,简单的,易懂的,直接了当的;adv.坦率地', '1. The instructions are reasonably straightforward. 用法说明还算简单易懂。 2. I wonder if the literature can be put in straightforward Chinese. 我不知道那些说明书能不能译成简明易懂的中文。 3. This book presents an up-to-date, straightforward course for students. 这本书为学生提供了一本最新式的、简明易懂的教程。 4. They took a straightforward route to the lake. 他们走了一条笔直通向湖的路。', '副词: straightforwardly 名词: straightforwardness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('graze', '[ɡreɪz]', 'v.放牧,吃草,擦伤,擦过;n.放牧,牧草,轻擦,擦破处', '1. We are grazing the sheep in the next field. 我们在旁边的地里放羊。 2. The sheep usually graze in the grass land. 羊通常在草地吃草。 3. Cattle are not allowed to graze in the plots. 禁止牛在田里吃草。 4. The bullet grazed my shoulder. 子弹擦过我的肩膀。 5. Cows are left to graze in the pasture. 奶牛都是留给放牧在牧场。 6. His knee stung from the graze. 他的膝盖擦伤后十分疼痛。', '形容词: grazeable 名词: grazer 过去式: grazed 过去分词: grazed 现在分词: grazing 第三人称单数: grazes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tendency', '[\'tendənsi]', 'n.趋向,倾向', '1. There is a tendency towards regional cooperation. 有一种地区性合作的趋势。 2. There is a growing tendency for people to work at home instead of in offices. 人们在家里而不是在办公室里工作的趋势日益增长。 3. Today there is a tendency for people to opt out of social activity. 现在,越来越多的人倾向于不参加社会活动。 4. They tried to stop the tendency of inflation. 他们设法阻止住了通货膨胀的势头。', '名词复数: tendencies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('atmosphere', '[\'ætməsfɪr]', 'n.大气,空气,气氛', '1. The burning of fossil fuels results in the pollution of the atmosphere. 矿物燃料的燃烧导致了大气污染。 2. The atmosphere of the city is very much polluted. 那个城市的空气受到严重污染。 3. The atmosphere is very stuffy here and can we open a window? 这里的空气很闷,咱们能打开一扇窗吗？ 4. The atmosphere changed as soon as she walked in. 她一进来气氛就变了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('shark', '[ʃɑːrk]', 'n.[鱼]鲨鱼,骗子<俚>内行,专家;v.敲诈', '1. The shark snapped its jaws shut. 鲨鱼啪嗒一声把嘴合上了。 2. The shark is dangerous to swimmers. 鲨鱼对游泳的人来说很危险。 3. He told me he once caught a shark, but I know he was swinging the lead. 他告诉我有一回他捕到了一条鲨鱼，我知道他是在胡诌。 4. That shark lent me money at very high interest rate. 那个贪婪狡猾的人以很高的利率借给我钱。', '过去式: sharked 过去分词: sharked 现在分词: sharking 第三人称单数: sharks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('consume', '[kən\'suːm]', 'vt.消耗,消费,消灭,大吃大喝,吸引;vi.消灭,毁灭', '1. His old car consumed much gasoline. 他的旧汽车耗油很多。 2. Each year Americans consume a high percentage of the world\'s energy. 每年美国人都消耗掉世界能源的很大比例 3. I\'m sure that Chinese people consume the largest amount of rice in the world. 我敢肯定,世界上中国人吃掉的大米最多。 4. I saw the flames consuming the whole building. 我看见火焰吞噬了整栋建筑物。', '过去式: consumed 过去分词: consumed 现在分词: consuming 第三人称单数: consumes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('contradict', '[ˌkɒntrə\'dɪkt]', 'vt.同...矛盾,同...抵触', '1. He did not contradict his attorney\'s comment. 他没有反驳律师的意见。 2. She doesn\'t like to contradict her husband in public. 她不愿在众人面前反驳她丈夫。 3. Don\'t contradict your father. 别和你父亲犟嘴。 4. The report contradicts what we heard yesterday. 这个报道与我们昨天听到的有矛盾。', '形容词: contradictable 名词: contradicter 过去式: contradicted 过去分词: contradicted 现在分词: contradicting 第三人称单数: contradicts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('feature', '[\'fiːtʃər]', 'n.面貌的一部分(眼,口,鼻等)特征,容貌,特色,特写;vt.是...的特色,特写,放映;vi.起重要作用', '1. Their candor is a very pleasing feature. 他们的坦白是很愉快的特征。 2. Wet weather is a feature of life in this area. 天气潮湿是这个地区生活的一个特色。 3. Her mouth is her best feature. 她的嘴是她容貌上最好看的部分。 4. The local newspaper ran a feature on child labor. 地方报纸登载一篇有关童工的特写。 5. This restaurant seems to feature vegetarian dishes. 这家餐厅似乎以素菜为其特色。 6. Jazz and Blues feature prominently in the magazine. 爵士和蓝调在杂志中占重要篇幅。', '过去式: featured 过去分词: featured 现在分词: featuring 第三人称单数: features');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('contrive', '[kən\'traɪv]', 'v.发明,设计,图谋', '1. The prisoner contrived a way to escape. 囚犯图谋越狱。 2. He contrived to gain their votes. 他施展计谋获得了他们的选票。 3. He contrived a new machine for flying. 他设计了一种新式飞行器。 4. Can you contrive to be at the station by noon? 你能设法在中午前赶到车站吗?', '名词: contriver 过去式: contrived 过去分词: contrived 现在分词: contriving 第三人称单数: contrives');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('solo', '[\'soʊloʊ]', 'n.独奏曲;adj.单独的', '1. The first piece is a piano solo by Berio. 第一个节目是贝里奥的钢琴独奏。 2. The concert began with piano solo. 音乐会以一首钢琴独奏开始。 3. He has been asked to sing a solo at the concert. 他已被邀请在演奏会上表演独唱。 4. The student essayed his first solo flight. 该学员尝试作首次单独飞行。 5. His landing was awkward,but it was only the second time he\'d flown solo. 他的着陆技术很不熟练,但这只是他第二次单飞。', '名词复数: solos 过去式: soloed 过去分词: soloed 现在分词: soloing 第三人称单数: solos');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('impart', '[ɪm\'pɑːrt]', 'vt.给予(尤指抽象事物),传授,告知,透露', '1. A teacher\'s aim is to impart knowledge. 教师的作用是传授知识。 2. They had come to impart their experience in stock raising. 他们是来传授饲养牲畜的经验的。 3. The red curtains impart a certain elegance to the room. 红色的窗帘使房间平添几分雅致。 4. Your presence will impart an air of elegance to the party. 您的光临将会为宴会增添优雅的气氛。', '过去式: imparted 过去分词: imparted 现在分词: imparting 第三人称单数: imparts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('confer', '[kən\'fɜːr]', 'vt.授予(称号、学位等),赠与,把...赠与,协议;v.协商,交换意见', '1. I must confer with my lawyer before I decide. 我必须先同我的律师商量一下才能做出决定。 2. I will confer with him on the subject. 我将和他商议这件事。 3. The Queen conferred knighthood on several distinguished men. 女王将爵士头衔授予几位杰出人士。 4. The university confers master degree on her. 学校授予她硕士学位。', '形容词: conferrable 名词: conferment 过去式: conferred 过去分词: conferred 现在分词: conferring 第三人称单数: confers');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('merit', '[\'merɪt]', 'n.优点,价值;v.有益于', '1. This method at least had the merit of simplicity. 这种办法至少有简单明了的优点。 2. Charms strikes the sight, but merit wins the soul. 美貌吸引目光,优点赢得心灵。 3. That will subtract nothing from his merit. 那将无损于他的功绩。 4. Promotion should be based on merit alone. 晋升应完全根据功绩。 5. His new achievements merit our attention. 他取得的新成就值得关注。', '形容词: meritless 过去式: merited 过去分词: merited 现在分词: meriting 第三人称单数: merits');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('restore', '[rɪ\'stɔːr]', 'vt.恢复,使回复,归还,交还,修复,重建', '1. The military government promised to restore democracy within one year. 军人政府答应在一年内重新建立民主体制。 2. Drastic measures will have to be taken to restore order. 为恢复秩序必须采取严厉措施。 3. The police must try to restore order. 警方必须努力恢复治安。 4. The new manager\'s job is to restore the company to profitability. 新经理的工作是让这家公司能恢复盈利状况。', '名词: restorer 过去式: restored 过去分词: restored 现在分词: restoring 第三人称单数: restores');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('excessive', '[ɪk\'sesɪv]', 'adj.过多的,过分的,额外', '1. Excessive patriotism can lead to xenophobia. 爱国主义过了头即可导致仇视一切外国人。 2. Excessive dosage of this drug can result in injury to the liver. 这种药使用过量会损害肝脏。 3. The quality of urban living has been damaged by excessive noise levels. 城市生活的质量已被过度的噪音所破坏。 4. I consider the excessive smoking and drinking tend to cloud the brain. 我认为过多的抽烟和过量的酗酒，会使人的头脑迟钝。', '副词: excessively 名词: excessiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('initiative', '[ɪ\'nɪʃətɪv]', 'n.主动', '1. She took an initiative part in the Wildlife Conservation Society. 她主动参加野生动物保护协会。 2. It is innovation plus initiative that has kept it thriving. 创新与进取精神使得它蓬勃发展。 3. In the economic trend of the new era, having the initiative is the key. 在新时期的经济大潮中，拥有主动权是关键。 4. Thus the initiative was lost at the very first move, and that is really the worst and most stupid way to fight. 开脚一步就丧失了主动权，真是最蠢最坏的打法。', '副词: initiatively');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('intact', '[ɪn\'tækt]', 'adj.完整无缺的,尚未被人碰过的,(女子)保持童贞的,(家畜)未经阉割的', '1. Despite his misfortunes, his faith and optimism remained intact. 虽然他遭到一连串的不幸，他的信心和乐观丝毫未减。 2. You may have your money back on this woolen sweater if it is kept clean and intact. 如果羊毛衫保持清洁、完好无缺，您可以退款。 3. The money was returned intact by its finder. 钱原封未动地被捡拾者送还。 4. This stretch of wetlands has remained intact. 这块湿地一直保持着自然的面貌。', '副词: intactly 名词: intactness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('diffuse', '[dɪ\'fjuːz]', 'v.散播,传播,漫射,扩散,(使)慢慢混合;adj.散开的,弥漫的', '1. The problem is how to diffuse power without creating anarchy. 问题在于如何将权力分散而不造成无政府状态。 2. Fashion trends diffuse themselves rapidly around the globe. 时装新潮很快就在全世界流行起来。 3. The roses diffuse the scent to the air miles around. 玫瑰花的香味儿弥漫在几英里的空气中。 4. He resolved to diffuse the special knowledge that he possessed. 他决心要传播他所具有的特别的知识。 5. Around the cluster is a huge vague diffuse nebulae. 围绕该星团的是一个巨大的模糊的弥漫星云。 6. Professor Smith cut off their diffuse speech and agreed to help them. 史密斯教授打断他们冗长的演讲,答应帮助他们。', '副词: diffusely 名词: diffuseness 过去式: diffused 过去分词: diffused 现在分词: diffusing 第三人称单数: diffuses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('trial', '[\'traɪəl]', 'n.试验,考验,审讯,审判', '1. He went through hell during the trial. 审讯期间他吃尽了苦头。 2. The flier is flying a new-type jet plane on trial. 飞行员正在驾驶一架新式喷气机作试验飞行。 3. She agreed to employ me for a trial period. 她同意试用我一段时间。 4. Trial and error is the source of our knowledge. 尝试和失败同是学识之源。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('confidence', '[\'kɑːnfɪdəns]', 'n.信心', '1. The servant enjoyed his master\'s confidence. 这仆人深得主人的信赖。 2. We have full confidence that we shall succeed. 我们完全有把握取得成功。 3. The worst barrier to your success is not lack of money, but lack of confidence. 你成功最大的障碍不是缺钱,而是缺乏信心。 4. The two girls told each other confidences about their boyfriends. 这两个姑娘相互谈了关于各自男友的悄悄话。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('testify', '[\'testɪfaɪ]', 'v.证明,证实,作证', '1. He testified that he had not seen the accident. 他作证说他没有看见那次事故。 2. He agreed to testify on behalf of the accused man. 他同意为被告作证。 3. Her actions testify to her good character. 她的行为证明了她的人品是好的。 4. All kinds of human experience testify to the close link between love and fear. 人类的种种经验都证明了爱与怕之间的紧密联系。', '名词: testification 过去式: testified 过去分词: testified 现在分词: testifying 第三人称单数: testifies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('clearance', '[\'klɪrəns]', 'n.清除', '1. He introduced a project for slum clearance. 他提出一个清除贫民窟的计划。 2. Clearance of the site required the removal of a number of trees. 清理这一场所需要移走不少树。 3. The clearance of the old furniture made the room more spacious. 清理了旧家俱，屋里更宽敞了。 4. This shoe boutique is having a clearance sale now. 这家精品鞋店正在清仓大拍卖呢。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sip', '[sɪp]', 'v.吸吮', '1. He took one sip of the wine and spat it out. 他抿了一口酒，又吐了出来。 2. He paused to take a sip of water, and then went on with his story. 他停下来呷了一口水，然後继续讲他的事。 3. I sipped at the coffee. 我啜饮咖啡。 4. When you drink your soup, don\'t sip it, but swallow it all in one mouthful. 喝汤时不要啜饮,而应一口吞下去。', '名词: sipper 过去式: sipped 过去分词: sipped 现在分词: sipping 第三人称单数: sips');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('register', '[\'redʒɪstər]', 'n.记录,登记簿,登记,注册,寄存器;vt.记录,登记,注册,提示,把...挂号;vi.登记,注册,挂号', '1. You must register if you intend to vote. 如果你要投票选举,你就必须登记。 2. He registered the trial proceedings. 法庭速记员记录下了审判进程。 3. You must register as a member first. 你必须先注册成为会员。 4. I want this letter registered. 我想挂号邮寄这封信。 5. Would you sign the register? 请你在登记簿上签名好吗? 6. Official documents are written in formal register. 官方文件是以正式语体写成的。', '形容词: registrable 名词: registration 过去式: registered 过去分词: registered 现在分词: registering 第三人称单数: registers');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('prominent', '[\'prɑːmɪnənt]', 'adj.卓越的,显著的,突出的', '1. That school is prominent in baseball. 那个学校以棒球著称。 2. Virginia Woolf is one of the most prominent writers in English literature. 弗吉尼亚·尔夫是英国文学史中一名重要的作家。 3. Einstein was a prominent scientist. 爱因斯坦是一位卓越的科学家。 4. She is having a lean, gaunt frame with prominent bones. 他骨瘦如柴的身材又细又瘦,骨骼突出的', '副词: prominently');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('consent', '[kən\'sent]', 'vi.同意,赞成,答应;n.同意,赞成,允诺', '1. My father will never give his consent to our marriage. 我父亲决不会同意我们的婚姻的。 2. By the common consent of critics, Shakespeare is the prince of character delineators. 评论家一致公认莎士比亚是刻画人物的大师。 3. Her smile implied her consent to our proposal. 她的微笑暗示她赞成我们的提议。 4. On the other hand, it is not likely that the few landlords from the upper strata of the Miao nationality will consent to their demand. 但是这样的要求，可能苗族上层少数地主分子不赞成。 5. I\'m sure he wouldn\'t consent 我确信他不会同意。', '名词: consenter 过去式: consented 过去分词: consented 现在分词: consenting 第三人称单数: consents');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('provoke', '[prə\'voʊk]', 'vt.激怒,挑拨,煽动,惹起,驱使', '1. If you provoke the dog, he may bite you. 你如果激怒了这条狗，它可能会咬你。 2. Don\'t provoke the animals in the cage. 不要激怒笼中的动物。 3. His rudeness provoked me to strike him. 他的粗鲁惹得我揍了他。 4. Such a questionable assertion is sure to provoke criticism. 这种有问题的主张肯定会招致非议。', '副词: provokingly 过去式: provoked 过去分词: provoked 现在分词: provoking 第三人称单数: provokes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hover', '[\'hʌvər]', 'v.盘旋', '1. The hawk is hovering overhead. 鹰在头顶上盘旋。 2. After the alien spacecraft had hovered over the park for a short time, it vanished. 那只外星来的宇宙飞船在公园上空盘旋了一会儿之后就不见了。 3. He hovered nervously in the doorway. 他在门口紧张地来回踱步。 4. The mercury hovered around 35 Celsius degree. 水银温度计停留在摄氏35度左右。 5. He felt creeping of fate, the circling of wolves, the hover of vultures. 他感到厄运已经来到，豺狼正在包围，秃鹰也在盘旋。', '副词: hoveringly 名词: hoverer 过去式: hovered 过去分词: hovered 现在分词: hovering 第三人称单数: hovers');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('substantial', '[səb\'stænʃl]', 'adj.坚固的,实质的,真实的,充实的', '1. New economic development policies led to substantial and rapid growth. 新的经济发展政策带来了快速和大量的增长。 2. Those workers have built many substantial buildings in the recent years. 近几年那些工人建造了许多坚固的建筑。 3. The reforms have made substantial headway. 改革取得了实质的进展。 4. The article is devoid of substantial matter. 这篇文章缺乏实质性的内容。', '副词: substantially 名词: substantiality');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('patent', '[\'pætnt]', 'n.专利权,执照,专利品;adj.特许的,专利的,显著的,明白的,新奇的;vt.取得...的专利权,请准专利', '1. The patent runs out in three years time. 这项专利期限为3年。 2. He got a patent for this invention. 他获得了这项发明的专利权。 3. The government patented the device to its inventor. 政府给予发明者专利权。 4. This is a packet of a patent cement mix. 这是一包专利水泥混合料。', '形容词: patentable 名词: patentability 过去式: patented 过去分词: patented 现在分词: patenting 第三人称单数: patents');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('expense', '[ɪk\'spens]', 'n.费用,代价,损失,开支,费钱之物', '1. It\'s too much of an expense for me to own a car. 对我来说，拥有一辆汽车的花费太大。 2. Societies should try to save every plant and animal species, regardless of the expense to humans in effort, time, and financial well-being. 社会应尽力挽救每一动植物物种,不管花费多少人力、时间和财力。 3. Don\'t involve yourself in unnecessary expense. 勿做不必要的花费。 4. He finished the job at the expenses of his health. 他以牺牲健康完成了这项工作。', '过去式: expensed 过去分词: expensed 现在分词: expensing 第三人称单数: expenses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('prolong', '[prə\'lɔːŋ]', 'vt.延长,拖延', '1. How can we endeavor to prolong the brevity of human life? 我们怎样才能延长短促的人生？ 2. The meeting may be prolonged into the evening because so many problems have to be solved tonight. 会议可能要延长到夜里，因为今晚有太多问题要解决。 3. Low leakage current helps to prolong battery life. 低漏电流有助于延长电池使用寿命。 4. Clear evidence of his intent is to prolong the ritual. 显然他意在拖延典礼时间。', '名词: prolonger 过去式: prolonged 过去分词: prolonged 现在分词: prolonging 第三人称单数: prolongs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('resident', '[\'rezɪdənt]', 'n.居民;adj.居住的,常驻的', '1. The residents of the town are proud of its new library. 该镇的居民都为镇上新建的图书馆感到自豪。 2. I have been resident in this hotel for two weeks. 我已经在这家旅馆里住了两个星期了。 3. I would get the neurosurgery resident down here. 我想请神经外科住院医师下楼到这儿来。 4. This dove was resident with us all the year round. 这只鸽子一年到头居住在这里和我们为伴。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('transport', '[\'trænspɔːrt]', 'n.传送器,运输,运输机,激动,流放犯,狂喜;vt.传送,运输,流放,放逐', '1. The goods have been cased up for transport. 货物已装箱待运。 2. London Transport run extra trains during the rush-hour. 伦敦运输公司在交通高峰时 间增开加班列车。 3. Please find alternative means of transport. 请另外找一个运输方法。 4. The transport of goods by air is very expensive. 空运货物费用十分昂贵。 5. A helicopter was used to transport the wounded. 一架直升飞机被用来运送伤员。', '形容词: transportable 名词: transportability 过去式: transported 过去分词: transported 现在分词: transporting 第三人称单数: transports');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('token', '[\'toʊkən]', 'n.表示,向征,记号,代币;adj.象征的,表意的', '1. He gave me a necklace as a token of his affection.. 他给了我一根项链作为爱情的象征。 2. We sent the poor girl a birthday present in token of friendship. 我们送给那个可怜的小女孩一份生日礼物作为友谊的表示。 3. These flowers are a small token of my gratitude. 谨以此花聊表谢忱。 4. He gave his friend a book as a go-away token. 他送朋友一本书作为临别纪念。 5. The government agreed to send a small token force to the area. 政府同意派遣一小支象征性的部队到那一地区。', '过去式: tokened 过去分词: tokened 现在分词: tokening 第三人称单数: tokens');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('majesty', '[\'mædʒəsti]', 'n.最高权威,王权,雄伟', '1. Policemen and judges uphold the majesty of the law. 警察和法官维护法律的权威。 2. Even in great adversity, he kept his majesty. 既使身处绝境，他仍保持自己的威严。 3. The king had unspeakable majesty. 国王有无法形容的威严。 4. The majesty of the occasion thrilled us all. 那庄严的场面使我们每个人都激动不已。 5. I\'m not a very good rider, Your Majesty. 我可不是个好骑手，陛下。', '名词复数: majesties');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('premier', '[prɪ\'mɪr]', 'adj.第一的,首要的;n.总理', '1. Premier Zhou is a distinguished politician. 周总理是一位卓越的政治家。 2. The premier deals with important affairs of state. 总理处理国家重要事务。 3. The premiers of the two countries met in Geneva yesterday. 两国首相昨天在日内瓦会晤。 4. His work on the cause of the diseases is of premier importance to the whole world. 他的病理研究工作对全世界至关重要。', '名词: premiership');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('spectacle', '[\'spektəkl]', 'n.观览物,展览物,公开展示,奇观,景象,光景,(apairof～s)眼镜', '1. The sunrise was a splendid spectacle. 日出是个壮观的景象。 2. The celebrations provided a magnificent spectacle. 庆祝活动呈现一派宏伟的景象。 3. The carnival parade was a magnificent spectacle. 狂欢节游行场面热烈，蔚为大观。 4. The children took in the spectacle open-mouthed. 孩子们张着嘴注视精彩表演。 5. I can\'t see things through your spectacles. 我和你的看法不同。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('adopt', '[ə\'dɑːpt]', 'vt.采用,收养', '1. They adopt new techniques in raising sheep. 他们采用新的养羊技术。 2. The schools must adopt new methods of teaching foreign languages. 学校应采用新的外语教学法。 3. She was left an orphan and a poor peasant woman adopted her. 她成了孤儿，一位贫农妇女收养了她。 4. To adopt the fruits of sin was to give countenance to it. 收养罪恶的果实就等于纵容罪恶。', '形容词: adoptable 名词: adopter 过去式: adopted 过去分词: adopted 现在分词: adopting 第三人称单数: adopts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('limb', '[lɪm]', 'n.肢,翼,分支', '1. Men and women have four limbs; two arms and two legs. 人都有四肢，两只胳膊两条腿。 2. He stood up and stretched his limbs. 他站起来,伸了伸胳膊和腿。 3. A grey squirrel is scampering from limb to limb. 一只灰色的松鼠在树枝间跳来跳去。 4. The workers saw off a limb from the tree. 工人从树上锯下了一根大树枝。', '过去式: limbed 过去分词: limbed 现在分词: limbing 第三人称单数: limbs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('merge', '[mɜːrdʒ]', 'v.合并,并入,结合,吞没,融合', '1. His department will merge with mine. 他的部门将和我的合并。 2. The two marching columns moved closer and finally merged. 行进中的两路纵队越走越近，终于合成一路。 3. The shadows slowly merge together. 这些阴影慢慢地融合在一起了。 4. The water and the sky merge into a pure whole. 水与天连成一线,不染纤尘。', '名词: mergence 过去式: merged 过去分词: merged 现在分词: merging 第三人称单数: merges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('withdraw', '[wɪð\'drɔː]', 'vt.收回,撤消;vi.缩回,退出;v.撤退', '1. In view of members reservation and request for further information, the Administration agreed to withdraw the item. 鉴于委员有所保留,并要求取得进一步资料,政府当局同意撤回该项目。 2. He wanted to withdraw his name from the guest list. 他想从客人名单中撤出自己的名字。 3. I\'d like to withdraw some money from my account. 我想从户头里提出一些钱。 4. The troops have been withdrawn from the danger area. 部队已经撤出危险地带。 5. Tell the men to withdraw from their new position. 告诉那些人从新的阵地上撤出。', '形容词: withdrawable 名词: withdrawer 过去式: withdrew 过去分词: withdrawn 现在分词: withdrawing 第三人称单数: withdraws');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cordial', '[\'kɔːrdʒəl]', 'n.兴奋剂,兴奋性饮料;adj.热忱的,诚恳的,兴奋的', '1. By means of a few drops of strong cordial, the doctor revived the besotted corpse for a few minutes. 博士滴了几滴强烈的兴奋剂，使这个没有知觉的身躯复活了几分钟。 2. It was a cordial affair in which Pancalli expressed his appreciation for the work carried out by Juventus in recent months. 这是一次热忱的会晤，潘卡利感谢了近几个月来尤文所做的工作。 3. Please accept my cordial and humblest apologies. 请接受我诚恳的道歉。', '副词: cordially 名词: cordiality');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dual', '[\'duːəl]', 'adj.双的,二重的,双重', '1. She has dual nationality. 她有双重国籍。 2. His dual role as a composer and a conductor made him very busy. 他作曲家和指挥家的双重身份使他非常繁忙。 3. The car has dual exhaust pipes. 这车有双排气管。', '副词: dually');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('originate', '[ə\'rɪdʒɪneɪt]', 'vt.引起,发明,发起,创办;vi.起源,发生', '1. They originated the plan. 他们首先提出这一计划。 2. Who originated the concept of stereo sound? 立体声是谁发明的？ 3. And how did this peculiar custom originate? 而且，这种奇特的习俗又是怎么开始的呢? 4. The quarrel originated in rivalry between the two families. 这次争吵是两家不和引起的。', '形容词: originative 副词: originatively 名词: origination 过去式: originated 过去分词: originated 现在分词: originating 第三人称单数: originates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('norm', '[nɔːrm]', 'n.标准,规范', '1. Criminal behaviour seem to be the norm in this neighbourhood. 犯罪行为似乎是这一带的正常现象。 2. Law is a social norm reflecting the will of a state. 法是具有国家意志的社会规范。 3. You must adapt to the norms of the society you live in. 在社会中生活就要遵循社会行为准则。 4. There\'s a production norm below which each worker must not fall. 每个工人的产量都不得低于生产指标。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reign', '[reɪn]', 'vi.统治,支配,盛行,占优势;n.统治,统治时期,支配', '1. He has a tyrannical reign on his empire. 他是个残暴的皇帝。 2. People will remember the tyrannies of his reign. 人们不会忘记他统治时期的暴行。 3. The reign of Queen Victoria lasted more than sixty years. 维多利亚女王的统治持续了六十多年。 4. The American Revolution took place during the reign of George III. 美国独立战争发生在英王乔治三世统治时期。 5. He reigned over the country for forty years. 他统治了这个国家四十年。', '过去式: reigned 过去分词: reigned 现在分词: reigning 第三人称单数: reigns');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('inject', '[ɪn\'dʒekt]', 'vt.注射,注入', '1. The nurse injected penicillin into her arm. 护士给她的胳膊注射了青霉素。 2. His medicine is a drug that can be injected or taken by mouth. 他的药可以注射或口服。 3. His appointment may inject some new life into the committee. 他的任命可能给这委员会注入新生命。 4. He injected new ideas into the discussion. 他把新的概念引入讨论中。', '名词: injector 过去式: injected 过去分词: injected 现在分词: injecting 第三人称单数: injects');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('underlying', '[ˌʌndər\'laɪɪŋ]', 'adj.在下面的,根本的,潜在的,[商]优先的', '1. This word has its underlying meaning. 这个单词有它潜在的含义。 2. The underlying assumption is that the amount of money available is limited. 隐含的假定是可用的资金有限。 3. We dug down to the underlying rock. 我们往下挖直到碰到了下面的石块。 4. The underlying idea is an appealing one. 基础的概念是一种吸引人的概念。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('senator', '[\'senətər]', 'n.参议员,(大学的)评议员,(古罗马的)元老院议员', '1. The senator spoke against the law. 这位参议员反对这条法律。 2. The senator voted to support the president. 这位参议员投票支持总统。 3. The senator addressed the gathering informally. 那位参议员非正式地向与会者发表演说。 4. The senator declaimed against higher taxes. 该参议员抨击增加税收。', '名词: senatorship');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('situated', '[\'sɪtʃueɪtɪd]', 'adj.位于,被置于境遇,处于...的立场', '1. The school is situated just outside the town. 学校就位于镇子的外面。 2. Most of China is situated in the temperate zone. 中国大部分地区处于温带。 3. The corporation is rather awkwardly situated. 公司处境相当尴尬。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('recovery', '[rɪ\'kʌvəri]', 'n.恢复,痊愈,防御', '1. We are surprised by the rapidity of her recovery. 她恢复得那么快，我们都有些惊讶。 2. He is well on his way to recovery. 他正在顺利恢复。 3. A lot has been done in the recovery of national economy in the past few years. 在过去的几年中我们为了国民经济的恢复做了大量的工作。 4. The doctors held out no hope of recovery. 医生们对痊愈不抱希望。', '名词复数: recoveries');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('environment', '[ɪn\'vaɪrənmənt]', 'n.环境,外界', '1. She is not used to the new environment. 她对新环境不习惯。 2. We are required by environment protecting department to use anthracite. 环保部门要求我们使用无烟煤。 3. At one time, children didn\'t have to learn any more than how to cope with their physical environment. 曾经有一段时间,儿童除了学习适应外界环境以外,什么都不学。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('settle', '[\'setl]', 'n.有背的长凳;vt.安放,使定居,安排,解决,决定,整理,支付,使平静;vi.安家,定居,停留,下陷,沉淀,决定,澄清', '1. If you pay for both of us now, we can settle up later. 你要是现在先付清咱们两人的帐，事后咱们俩再细算。 2. An official mission was sent to settle the dispute. 一个官方使团被派去解决争端。 3. The two companies settled out of court. 两家公司在法院外了结了争端。 4. They moved the local people and settle them in another place. 他们把当地人迁移到别处定居。', '形容词: settleable 过去式: settled 过去分词: settled 现在分词: settling 第三人称单数: settles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('individual', '[ˌɪndɪ\'vɪdʒuəl]', 'n.个人,个体;adj.个别的,单独的,个人的', '1. A teacher can\'t give individual attention to each pupil if his class is large. 如果班上的人数多，老师就不能给予个别辅导了。 2. It is difficult for a teacher to give individual attention to children in a large class. 教师在人数多的班上，很难对各个学生都照顾到。 3. She has her own individual style of doing things. 她有自己独特的行事风格。 4. No individual shall overtop the law. 任何个人的权力都不能凌驾于法律之上。', '副词: individually');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('undermine', '[ˌʌndər\'maɪn]', 'v.破坏', '1. They will do anything to undermine their adversary\'s reputation. 他们会不择手段地去损害对手的名誉。 2. The President\'s enemies are spreading rumours to undermine his authority. 总统的敌人在散布谣言以逐渐破坏他的威信。 3. Badgers had undermined the foundations of the church. 獾在这座教堂的地基处打了洞。 4. A mole can undermine the strongest rampart. 一只田鼠能毁坏最坚固的堡垒。', '过去式: undermined 过去分词: undermined 现在分词: undermining 第三人称单数: undermines');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tunnel', '[\'tʌnl]', 'n.隧道,地道', '1. The heavy traffic crawled through the narrow tunnel. 拥挤的车辆慢吞吞地穿过狭窄的隧道。 2. Suddenly the train roared into a tunnel and everything was black. 突然火车轰隆隆地驶入一个隧道，四周的一切都漆黑一团。 3. The kid dug a tunnel in the sand. 小孩在沙堆里挖了一个地道。 4. Moles make underground tunnels. 鼹鼠常打地洞。 5. The engineers had to tunnel through solid rock. 工程师须要在坚实的岩石中开凿隧道。', '名词: tunneler 过去式: tunneled/tunnelled 过去分词: tunneled/tunnelled 现在分词: tunneling/tunnelling 第三人称单数: tunnels/tunnels');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('patrol', '[pə\'troʊl]', 'v.出巡,巡逻;n.巡逻', '1. Terrorists attacked two soldiers on patrol. 恐怖分子袭击了两名正在巡逻的士兵。 2. The patrol was waylaid by bandits. 巡逻队遭到土匪伏击。 3. The police hustled the tramps into the patrol car. 警察将那些流浪者强行推入巡逻车中。 4. The plane will patrol Australia\'s coastline. 未来这架飞机的任务是巡逻澳洲海岸线。', '名词: patroller 过去式: patrolled 过去分词: patrolled 现在分词: patrolling 第三人称单数: patrols');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('temper', '[\'tempər]', 'n.(钢等)韧度,回火,性情,脾气,情绪,心情,调剂,趋向;v.(冶金)回火、锻炼,调和,调节', '1. He slammed the door in a temper. 他生气地摔门。 2. You should learn to keep your temper under control. 你应该学会控制自己的脾气。 3. They are of congenial temper. 他们的性情相投。 4. If you temper criticism with reason,everyone can obey you. 如果以说理来缓和批评，谁都会服从你。', '形容词: temperable 名词: temperability 过去式: tempered 过去分词: tempered 现在分词: tempering 第三人称单数: tempers');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('assure', '[ə\'ʃʊr]', 'vt.断然地说,确告,保证,担保', '1. Her success as an actress was now assured. 她当演员很成功，已毋庸置疑了。 2. They tried to assure him of their willingness to work. 他们尽力使他相信他们乐意工作。 3. I can assure you that your son will be happy here. 我可以向你保证，你儿子在这里会很快乐的。 4. They were assured that everything possible was being done. 已经向他们保证，凡是可能做的都做到了。', '形容词: assurable 名词: assurer 过去式: assured 过去分词: assured 现在分词: assuring 第三人称单数: assures');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('orthodox', '[\'ɔːrθədɑːks]', 'adj.正统的,传统的,习惯的,保守的,东正教的', '1. He is very orthodox in his views. 他的观点十分正统。 2. The young generation today don\'t like orthodox teaching. 当今的年轻一代不喜欢正统的说教。 3. Orthodox Christian churches often have elaborate steeples. 传统的基督教堂都有精致的尖塔。 4. The restaurant offers the orthodox Christmas dinner of turkey. 这个餐馆供应传统的圣诞火鸡餐。', '副词: orthodoxly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('precise', '[prɪ\'saɪs]', 'adj.精确的,准确的;n.精确', '1. With the new technique, measurement was claimed to be much more precise. 有了这种技术,人们断言测量的结果会精确得多。 2. At the precise moment that I put my foot on the step, the bus started. 恰恰就在我登上公共汽车踏板的时候，车子开动了。 3. I am not clear about the precise bearing of the word in this passage. 我说不准这个字在这段文章里的确切意义是什么。 4. Precise employees are highly appreciated in our company. 我们公司十分欣赏工作态度严谨的员工。', '名词: preciseness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('commentary', '[\'kɑːmənteri]', 'n.注释,解说词', '1. His running commentary on the football match was excellent. 他对这次足球赛所作的实况报道十分精彩。 2. Tours have live English commentary. 旅游配有现场英语解说。 3. We\'d better not make any commentary on others. 我们最好不要评论他人。 4. I think his commentary on this issue is not correct. 我认为他对这个问题的评论是不正确的。', '形容词: commentarial 名词复数: commentaries');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('obscure', '[əb\'skjʊr]', 'adj.暗的,朦胧的,模糊的,晦涩的;vt.使暗,使不明显', '1. The rules for the competition are somewhat obscure. 比赛的规则有点让人费解。 2. The reasons why he did it are obscure. 他做那事的理由还不清楚。 3. The report had been published in an obscure German journal. 这个报道刊登在德国一家不著名的报纸上。 4. He set the bed in an obscure corner. 他把床放在一个昏暗的角落。 5. The moon was obscured by clouds. 月亮被云遮住了。 6. Hence things whichhave perplexed you and made the case more obscure have served to enlighten meand to strengthen my conclusions. 因此，那些使你们大惑不解并且使案情更加模糊不清的事物，却会对我有所启发，并且能加强我的论断。', '副词: obscurely 比较级: obscurer 最高级: obscurest 名词: obscureness 过去式: obscured 过去分词: obscured 现在分词: obscuring 第三人称单数: obscures');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dodge', '[dɑːdʒ]', 'v.避开,躲避;n.<俗>诡计,躲藏', '1. He dodged past me. 他躲躲闪闪地从我旁边走过。 2. He dodged the falling rock and escaped unhurt. 他闪身躲过了滚落的岩石，安然脱险了。 3. She was sharp-witted enough to dodge her attacker. 她才思敏捷足以避开别人的攻击。 4. The man jumped aside to dodge the speeding truck. 这人跳到旁边以躲避疾驶的卡车。 5. Do you like to go playing dodge ball with us? 要不要和我们一起去打躲避球?', '过去式: dodged 过去分词: dodged 现在分词: dodging 第三人称单数: dodges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('domain', '[doʊ\'meɪn]', 'n.领土,领地,(活动、学问等的)范围,领域', '1. Each of her cousins had charge of his own domain. 她的每一个亲属主管着自己的领地。 2. The kitchen is my wife\'s domain, and she doesn\'t like me going into it. 厨房是我妻子的领地,她不愿让我进去。 3. As soon as you create an account for the user, the user can participate in a secure domain. 一旦您为用户创建了一个帐号，用户就可以进入安全域中。 4. The doctor works in the domain of public health. 医生在公众健康范围内工作。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('trench', '[trentʃ]', 'n.沟渠,堑壕,管沟,电缆沟,战壕;v.掘沟,挖战壕', '1. The farmers gouged out a trench across the field. 农民们挖了一条穿过田野的沟。 2. They dig trench to keep the forest fire from spread. 他们挖沟以阻止森林大火蔓延。 3. I forgot to dig a trench around the tent. 我忘了在帐篷四周挖一条沟。 4. They toiled all day digging the trench. 他们整天艰苦地挖壕沟。 5. The troops received orders to trench the outpost. 部队接到命令在前哨周围筑壕加强防卫。', '过去式: trenched 过去分词: trenched 现在分词: trenching 第三人称单数: trenches');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('institute', '[\'ɪnstɪtuːt]', 'n.学会,学院,协会;vt.创立,开始,制定,开始(调查),提起(诉讼)', '1. New methods of teaching foreign languages are adopted in this institute. 该学院采用新的外语教学法。 2. Integrity and professionalism are the two main corporate values of the Institute. 诚信和专业精神是学会的两个主要机构价值观。 3. The UK\'s Securities & Investment Institute provides education and qualifications for many of these staff. 英国证券与投资协会为许多这样的员工提供培训和资格证书。 4. The police instituted an inquiry into the cause of the accident. 警方开始调查事故的原因。', '名词: instituter 过去式: instituted 过去分词: instituted 现在分词: instituting 第三人称单数: institutes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('readily', '[\'redɪli]', 'adv.乐意地,欣然,容易地', '1. These problems are not readily soluble. 这些问题不容易解决。 2. They can readily be brought anywhere. 它们易于携带。 3. She stood up readily. 她迅速地站了起来。 4. She readily accepted his proposal of marriage. 她乐意地接受了他的求婚。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('military', '[\'mɪləteri]', 'adj.军事的,军用的', '1. They are making further efforts to decrease military spending. 他们正在做进一步的努力来减少军费开支。 2. In some countries all the young men do a year\'s military service. 有些国家，所有年轻男子都要服一年兵役。 3. The military were called in to deal with the riot. 已将军队调来镇压暴乱。 4. The military has tightened its hold on the country. 军方加强了对这个国家的控制。', '副词: militarily 名词复数: military');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('instrumental', '[ˌɪnstrə\'mentl]', 'adj.仪器的,器械的,乐器的', '1. These tests require an extremely sophisticated instrumental effort. 这些试验需要极其尖端仪器才能办到。 2. I like instrumental music better than vocal music. 我喜欢器乐胜于声乐。 3. His instrumental works are popular amongst the students. 他的器乐曲在学生中很受欢迎。 4. Your advice has been instrumental in settling the question. 你的劝告对决这个问题是有帮助的。 5. His instrumental works are popular amongst the students. 他的器乐曲在学生中很受欢迎。', '副词: instrumentally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('optical', '[\'ɑːptɪkl]', 'adj.眼的,视力的,光学的', '1. The optical system of the eye stimulate cell of the retina. 眼睛的视觉系统刺激视网膜内的细胞。 2. A mirage is an optical illusion. 海市蜃楼是一种视错觉。 3. The canal on Mars is believed to be an optical illusion. 火星运河被认为是一种视觉错觉。 4. Microscopes and telescopes are optical instruments. 望远镜和显微镜是光学仪器。', '副词: optically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('protein', '[\'proʊtiːn]', 'n.[生化]蛋白质;adj.蛋白质的', '1. You need more protein to build you up. 你需要增加蛋白质以增强体质。 2. Try to balance your diet by eating more fruit and less protein. 多吃些水果，少摄入些蛋白质，使饮食均衡合理。 3. Pulses are a good source of protein for vegetarians. 对于素食者来说,豆类食物是蛋白质的理想来源。 4. A vegetarian gets protein not from meat but from its analogues. 素食者所摄取的蛋白质不是来自肉类而是来自近似肉类的食物。', '形容词: proteinaceous');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('minority', '[maɪ\'nɔːrəti]', 'n.少数,少数民族', '1. Only a minority of British households do not have a car. 英国只有少数家庭没有汽车。 2. A small minority voted against the motion. 投票反对该提议的人占少数。 3. The question of which state the minority group should belong to was decided by (a) plebiscite. 该少数民族应归属哪一州的问题已由公民投票表决。 4. There are 56 minorities in our country. 我国有56个少数民族。', '名词复数: minorities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('plea', '[pliː]', 'n.恳求,请求,辩解,藉口', '1. The prisoner made a plea for mercy. 囚犯恳求宽恕。 2. She made an impassioned plea for justice. 她激昂地抗辩，恳求获得公正。 3. In making that plea he will breathe in vain. 他做那种恳求是白费口舌的。 4. The thief entered a plea of not guilty. 这个贼提出了无罪申诉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ferry', '[\'feri]', 'n.摆渡,渡船,渡口;vt.渡运,(乘渡船)渡过,运送;vi.摆渡,(船)来往行驶', '1. There\'s a good duty-free shop (ie one selling such goods) on the ferry. 渡船上有个挺不错的免税商店。 2. The sway of the ferry made him feel sick. 渡船摇摇晃晃，他感到恶心。 3. We crossed the river by ferry. 我们坐渡船过了河。 4. He went down to the ferry but found the boat on the other side. 他到了渡口，却发现渡船在对岸。 5. Two small boats ferry people back and forth. 两只小船往返为人摆渡。 6. The tourists ferried across to the opposite bank. 游客摆渡到对岸。', '名词复数: ferries 过去式: ferried 过去分词: ferried 现在分词: ferrying 第三人称单数: ferries');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('neutral', '[\'nuːtrəl]', 'n.中立者,中立国,非彩色,齿轮的空档;adj.中立的,中立国的,中性的,无确定性质的,(颜色等)不确定的', '1. That country remained neutral in the war. 那个国家在那场战争中保持中立。 2. He has a rather neutral character. 他品性平平。 3. When you start the engine, be sure the car is in neutral. 你在发动引擎时，一定要让汽车处于空档。 4. A neutral tie can be worn with a shirt of any colour. 暗灰色的领带配什麽颜色的衬衣都行。 5. For Britain, Switzerland was a useful and friendly neutral. 对英国来说,瑞士是一个有利和友好的中立国。', '副词: neutrally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reciprocal', '[rɪ\'sɪprəkl]', 'adj.互惠的,相应的,倒数的,彼此相反的;n.倒数,互相起作用的事物', '1. Thus there is an important reciprocal relationship between honesty and trust. 基于此,诚实与信任成为重要的互惠关系。 2. It is mutually Beneficial and reciprocal to do this deal with the Japanese. 与日本人做这笔生意，互利互惠。 3. They show reciprocal affection to each other. 他们表达了彼此之间的爱慕。 4. Although I gave him many presents, I had no reciprocal gifts from him. 虽然我给他很多礼物, 但我没有收到过他给我的礼物。 5. I trust the reciprocal nature of our love. 我相信爱情是相互的。', '副词: reciprocally 名词: reciprocality');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('origin', '[\'ɔːrɪdʒɪn]', 'n.起源,由来,起因,出身,血统,[数]原点', '1. The social unrest has its origins in economic problems. 社会动荡是经济问题引起的。 2. This is the true story of the weeds: the origin of the species. 这是一个关于野草的真实故事:关于他们的物种起源。 3. He is a Dane by origin. 他原籍丹麦。 4. The family had its origin in Canada. 这家祖上是加拿大人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('autonomous', '[ɔː\'tɑːnəməs]', 'adj.自治的', '1. Each of the U.S. states has an autonomous government. 美国的每个州都有一个自治政府。 2. The former Soviet Union is formed of several autonomous republic. 前苏联是由数个自治共和国组成的。', '副词: autonomously');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('compensate', '[\'kɑːmpenseɪt]', 'v.偿还,补偿,付报酬', '1. Nothing can compensate for the loss of one\'s health. 什么都不能补偿健康受损。 2. She was compensated by the insurance company for her injuries. 她受伤后获得保险公司的赔偿。 3. You will have to compensate us for the loss. 你必须赔偿我们的损失。', '形容词: compensative 名词: compensator 过去式: compensated 过去分词: compensated 现在分词: compensating 第三人称单数: compensates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('morality', '[mə\'ræləti]', 'adj.道德的;n.道德', '1. Have standards of morality improved? 道德标准是否有所改进？ 2. I am unconcerned with questions of religion or morality. 我对宗教问题和道德问题不感兴趣。 3. The crusade for sexual morality is turning into a witch-hunt. 捍卫性道德的运动正在转化成对持异议人士的迫害。 4. The morality they absorbed was beyond question. 他们的美德无可置疑。', '名词复数: moralities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('acquaint', '[ə\'kweɪnt]', 'vt.使熟知,通知', '1. We should first try to acquaint ourselves with the facts. 我们先要想法了解事实。 2. These books acquaint Chinese readers with the ancient cultures of these lands. 这些书帮助中国读者了解这些地区的古代文化。 3. You must acquaint yourself with your new duties. 你必须熟悉自己的新职务。 4. Please acquaint him with my arrival. 请通知他我到了。', '过去式: acquainted 过去分词: acquainted 现在分词: acquainting 第三人称单数: acquaints');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('discern', '[dɪ\'sɜːrn]', 'v.目睹,认识,洞悉,辨别,看清楚', '1. Sometimes it\'s not easy to discern between the true and the false. 有时辨别真伪并不容易。 2. He was just able to discern the road in the dark. 他在黑暗中勉强能辨出道路。 3. They can discern me in spite of the fog. 虽然有雾，但他们能认得出我。 4. I soon discerned that the man was lying. 我马上察觉出那人在撒谎。', '名词: discerner 过去式: discerned 过去分词: discerned 现在分词: discerning 第三人称单数: discerns');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('extract', '[\'ekstrækt]', 'n.精,汁,榨出物,摘录,选粹;vt.拔出,榨取,开方,求根,摘录,析取,吸取', '1. She extracted passages for the students to translate. 她选了些短文让学生翻译. 2. She extracted a small notebook from her handbag. 她从手提包里取出了一个小笔记本。 3. He tried to extract his pole from the mud. 他试图用力将杆子从泥中拔出来。 4. It takes a major operation to extract money from a minor poet. 要从小诗人那儿榨出钱来，得施行一次大手术。 5. I would like to quote two extracts from the book. 我很想引用这本书的两段文字。', '形容词: extractable 名词: extractor 过去式: extracted 过去分词: extracted 现在分词: extracting 第三人称单数: extracts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('assault', '[ə\'sɔːlt]', 'n.攻击,袭击;v.袭击', '1. Trainee commandos are put through an exhausting assault course. 受训的突击队员要参加令人筋疲力尽的突击课程。 2. The court determined that the man was guilty of assault. 法庭裁定那个人犯了侵犯人身罪。 3. A deep, wide ditch, usually filled with water, typically surrounding a fortified medieval town, fortress, or castle as a protection against assault. 护城河一条深而宽的、通常有水沟环绕设防的中世纪城镇城堡或堡垒，用以抵抗外来袭击 4. The article was a vicious assault on Bell\'s integrity. 这篇文章是对贝尔完整性的恶劣抨击。 5. Six women have been sexually assaulted in the area recently. 最近这一带有六个女子遭受强奸猥亵。', '名词: assaulter 过去式: assaulted 过去分词: assaulted 现在分词: assaulting 第三人称单数: assaults');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('label', '[\'leɪbl]', 'n.标签,签条,商标,标志;vt.贴标签于,指...为,分类,标注;[计]加上或修改磁盘的标签', '1. Put a label on your luggage. 在你行李上做个标记。 2. I read the information on the label before deciding which jam to buy. 我先看果酱标签上的说明再决定买哪种. 3. He has been given a label of \"playboy\" by his friends. 他的朋友给他起了一个“花花公子”的绰号。 4. It\'s his first release for a major label. 这是他在大唱片公司发行的第一张唱片。 5. The bottle is labeled poison. 瓶上标明有毒。', '名词: labeler 过去式: labeled/labelled 过去分词: labeled/labelled 现在分词: labeling/labelling 第三人称单数: labels');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('diverse', '[daɪ\'vɜːrs]', 'adj.不同的,变化多的', '1. They are the people from diverse cultures. 他们是些有着不同文化背景的人。 2. Since then，she has played a diverse range of roles. 从那时起,她出演了各种不同的角色。 3. Her interests are very diverse. 她的兴趣非常广泛。 4. Their way of life is rich, diverse and rooted. 他们的生活方式丰富多彩,多种多样,扎根传统。', '副词: diversely 名词: diverseness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('permissible', '[pər\'mɪsəbl]', 'adj.可允许的', '1. Our basic idea is to make use of the permissible clock skew to enhance the timing reliability of a circuit. 我们的基本想法，是利用可允许的时序差异值来提高电路的时序可靠度。 2. Level transmitters to automatically turn off the unloading compressors to prevent ammonia from exceeding the highest or maximum permissible level. 水平变送器自动地关闭卸料压缩机以阻止氨超过最高或可允许的最大高度值。 3. It is not only permissible but praiseworthy to want to benefit your own family by your own efforts. 希望通过自己努力发家致富的意愿，不仅是容许的，而且是值得赞扬的。', '副词: permissibly 名词: permissibility');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reaction', '[ri\'ækʃn]', 'n.反应,反作用,反动(力)', '1. Her arrest produced an immediate reaction from the press. 她被捕的事立刻在新闻界引起反应。 2. I had a bad reaction after my typhoid injection. 我注射了伤寒针剂后产生了不良反应。 3. His reaction of swiftness surprised us. 他快速的反应能力让我们吃了一惊。 4. After all the excitement there was an inevitable reaction. 热闹一番过后,生活沉闷如故。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('embed', '[ɪm\'bed]', 'vt.使插入,使嵌入,深留,嵌入,[医]包埋', '1. The harpoon struck but did not embed. 鱼叉击中了但并没有插入。 2. You can embed URLs in your comment lines. 可以将URL嵌入注释行。 3. The scene was embedded in his memory. 那一幕情景深深地留在他的记忆。 4. The idea bacame embedded in his mind. 这想法在他头脑中根深蒂固了。', '异体字: imbed 名词: embedment 过去式: embedded 过去分词: embedded 现在分词: embedding 第三人称单数: embeds');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sniff', '[snɪf]', 'v.用力吸,嗅,闻到,发觉,轻视,用力吸气;n.吸,闻,吸气声,嗤之以鼻', '1. The dog was sniffing at the lamppost. 那条狗在街灯柱旁嗅来嗅去。 2. They are training these dogs to sniff out drugs. 他们训练狗嗅出毒品来。 3. His generous offer is not to be sniffed at. 对他的慷慨厚意不可嗤之以鼻。 4. We shouldn\'t sniff at this opportunity--we any not get another like it. 我们不可小看这个机会--也许我们再也找不到这样的机会了。 5. Doves and wolves love to sniff puff enough to cough and sneeze. 鸽子和野狼喜欢嗅粉扑，嗅到咳嗽，打喷嚏。 6. They are training these dogs to sniff out drugs. 他们训练狗嗅出毒品来。', '形容词: sniffable 名词: sniffer 过去式: sniffed 过去分词: sniffed 现在分词: sniffing 第三人称单数: sniffs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('orchestra', '[\'ɔːrkɪstrə]', 'n.管弦乐队,乐队演奏处', '1. The orchestra tuned their instruments. 乐队在给乐器调音。 2. The orchestra has several concert engagements. 这管弦乐队已安排好几场音乐会。 3. This orchestra has been established under the patronage of the government. 这个交响乐团是在政府赞助下成立的。', '形容词: orchestral 副词: orchestrally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('spiral', '[\'spaɪrəl]', 'adj.螺旋形的;n.螺旋;v.盘旋', '1. Society invariably moves forward in a spiral. 社会的运动总是采取螺旋形前进的。 2. This caused a downward spiral into depression. 这使经济下滑恶化为经济萧条。 3. The smoke spiraled upwards. 那股烟袅袅上升。 4. Prices are still spiralling. 价格仍然在急剧上涨。 5. A snails shell is spiral in form. 蜗牛的外壳形状是螺旋形的。', '副词: spirally 名词: spirality 过去式: spiraled/spiralled 过去分词: spiraled/spiralled 现在分词: spiraling/spiralling 第三人称单数: spirals/spirals');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('spacious', '[\'speɪʃəs]', 'adj.广大的,大规模的', '1. The hotel is neither spacious nor comfortable. 这旅馆既不宽敞也不舒服。 2. The systematic arrangement of chairs makes the hall look spacious. 座椅按照顺序排列，这使得礼堂里显得很宽敞。 3. In its spacious halls are displayed over8000 priceless relics. 在它宽敞的大厅里，展出了8000多件珍贵文物。 4. The museum is complemented by a spacious garden. 广大宽阔的庭院为博物馆增色不少。', '副词: spaciously 名词: spaciousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('census', '[\'sensəs]', 'n.人口普查', '1. The census is taken one time every four years in our country. 我国每四年一次人口普查。 2. The census revealed a declining birth rate. 人口普查结果表明出生率在下降。 3. This census is an invaluable resource for tracing family history. 人口普查是追查家族史的一种宝贵资源。 4. In the United States there is a census every ten years. 在美国每十年做一次户囗调查。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sequence', '[\'siːkwəns]', 'n.次序,顺序,序列', '1. We will deal with events in historical sequence. 我们将按照历史上的先后顺序研究这些事件。 2. She made a sequence of dance movements. 她做了一个连续的舞蹈动作。 3. He described the events of that day in sequence. 他按先后次序描述了那一天发生的种种事件。 4. A sequence of murders had prompted the police to actions. 一连串的谋杀迫使警方不得不采取行动。 5. Please sequence the names in alphabetical order. 请按字母顺序排列好名单。', '过去式: sequenced 过去分词: sequenced 现在分词: sequencing 第三人称单数: sequences');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('feasible', '[\'fiːzəbl]', 'adj.可行的,切实可行的', '1. The plan did not seem feasible. 这个计划似乎没法实行。 2. It\'s quite clear that the electric car is technically feasible. 电动汽车明显在工艺技术上是可行的。 3. It\'s not feasible to follow your proposals. 按照你的建议去做是行不通的。 4. It\'s not feasible to dismiss him. 不可开除他。', '副词: feasibly 名词: feasibility');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('prosecute', '[\'prɑːsɪkjuːt]', 'vt.实行,从事,告发,起诉;vi.告发,起诉,作检察官', '1. Trespassers will be prosecuted. 闲人免进，违者必究。 2. He was prosecuted for exceeding the speed limit. 他被告发超速行驶。 3. He vowed that he would prosecute them for fraud. 他郑重宣布将起诉他们犯有欺诈罪。 4. We should never prosecute the innocent. 我们决不应控告无辜的人。 5. The police decided not to prosecute. 警方决定不予起诉。', '形容词: prosecutable 过去式: prosecuted 过去分词: prosecuted 现在分词: prosecuting 第三人称单数: prosecutes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('adolescent', '[ˌædə\'lesnt]', 'adj.青春期的,青春的;n.青少年', '1. It is not unusual for grown adults to act in an adolescent way. 成人表现出青春期的样子很正常。 2. She says that risk-taking is normal adolescent behaviour. 她说冒险是青春期的正常表现。 3. I still remember my adolescent life. 我仍然记得我青少年时期的生活。 4. The adolescent period is one\'s best time. 青少年时期是一个人最美好的一段时光。 5. Overgrowth is common in adolescents. 青少年成长过快是普遍现象。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('gloomy', '[\'ɡluːmi]', 'adj.黑暗的,阴沉的,令人沮丧的,阴郁的', '1. Being alone in that gloomy house gave me the willies. 我一个人在那所阴暗的房子心里就发毛。 2. A few faint gleams of sunshine lit up the gloomy afternoon. 有几束隐约的阳光使阴暗的下午有些明亮。 3. Her smile is a breath of fresh air in this gloomy office. 她的微笑给沉闷的办公室带来生气。 4. There is a gloomy, overcast expression on his face. 他愁眉苦脸。', '副词: gloomily 比较级: gloomier 最高级: gloomiest 名词: gloominess');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('compliment', '[\'kɑːmplɪmənt]', 'n.称赞,恭维,致意,问候,道贺;vt.称赞,褒扬,恭维', '1. I was embarrassed by their compliment. 对他们的称赞我感到很不安。 2. I feel greatly flattered at your compliment. 我对你的称赞感到受宠若惊。 3. They paid him a high compliment. 他们非常恭维他。 4. My compliments to your wife. 向您的夫人致意。 5. He complimented her on her new dress without even looking at it. 他连看都没看一眼，就称颂她的新衣服。', '过去式: complimented 过去分词: complimented 现在分词: complimenting 第三人称单数: compliments');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('minimize', '[\'mɪnɪmaɪz]', 'vt.将...减到最少;v.最小化', '1. Governments consider it prudent to minimize the risk. 各国政府均认为把这种危害降低到最小程度的做法是明智的。 2. The polar explorers took every precaution to minimize the dangers of their trip. 极地探险者十分小心谨慎，以便使旅途的危险性减少到最小。 3. A sound approach to the problem is to minimize the number of parts. 正确解决这一问题的方法是把零件的数目减至最少。 4. He minimized the value of her contribution to his research so that he got all the praise. 他极力贬低她在那项研究中的贡献，从而独获全部奖励。', '名词: minimization 过去式: minimized 过去分词: minimized 现在分词: minimizing 第三人称单数: minimizes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('utilize', '[\'juːtəlaɪz]', 'vt.利用', '1. What criteria do you utilize in selecting employees? 在筛选雇员时你使用什么标准？ 2. In order to utilize land more fully, they adopted close planting. 为了更充分利用土地，他们采取了密植的办法。', '形容词: utilizable 名词: utilization 过去式: utilized 过去分词: utilized 现在分词: utilizing 第三人称单数: utilizes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('terminate', '[\'tɜːmɪneɪt]', 'v.停止,结束,终止', '1. Communist Party of China terminated the rule of feudal landlord class. 中国共产党结束了封建地主阶级的统治。 2. Your contract has been terminated. 你的合同已经被终止。 3. We have to terminate this contract. 我们不得不终止这个合同。 4. The contract will terminate soon. 契约快要期满了。', '过去式: terminated 过去分词: terminated 现在分词: terminating 第三人称单数: terminates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('interfere', '[ˌɪntər\'fɪr]', 'vi.干涉,干预,妨碍,打扰', '1. Don\'t interfere with my business. 不要干涉我的事情。 2. Constant interruptions interfere with my work. 一次又一次的干扰妨碍我的工作。 3. Don\'t allow pleasure to interfere with duty. 不要让娱乐妨碍了职责。', '副词: interferingly 名词: interferer 过去式: interfered 过去分词: interfered 现在分词: interfering 第三人称单数: interferes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('appliance', '[ə\'plaɪəns]', 'n.用具,器具', '1. The appliance carries a full-year guarantee. 器具有一年的保证期。 2. These appliances are made of stainless iron. 这些器具是用不锈钢制成的。 3. The appliance of electricity to household task makes housework much easier. 电力应用于家务上使做家务事容易多了。 4. You\'d better not install the appliance in a confined space. 你最好不要把装置安装在密闭的地方。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tease', '[tiːz]', 'n.揶揄,戏弄,逗惹;vt.取笑,逗恼,奚落,欺负,嘲弄,取笑,强求,梳理', '1. He is a terrible tease. 他特别爱戏弄人。 2. It\'s too bad of you to tease the child like that. 你那样逗弄小孩真不好。 3. You must never tease a child because he stutters . 你切不可因为一个孩子口吃而去取笑他。 4. Don\'t take it seriously. He\'s only teasing. 别把它当真，他只不过是在开玩笑。', '副词: teasingly 过去式: teased 过去分词: teased 现在分词: teasing 第三人称单数: teases');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('incidence', '[\'ɪnsɪdəns]', 'n.落下的方式,影响范围,[物理]入射', '1. Each incidence of truancy will impact the citizenship credit. 每次发生玩忽职守事件都会影响公民的信用。 2. Basically, can effectively control the incidence of bird strike. 基本上可以有效控制鸟击事件的发生。 3. Then I have to think deeply what benefit there is behind the incidence. 那时候我就必须深思发生的事情背后有什么益处。 4. he measured the angle of incidence of the reflected light. 他仔细测量了光的入射的角度。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hoist', '[hɔɪst]', 'n.提升间,升起', '1. They hoist cargo with a locomobile crane. 他们用自动推进的起重机吊起货物。', '名词: hoister 过去式: hoisted 过去分词: hoisted 现在分词: hoisting 第三人称单数: hoists');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('capacity', '[kə\'pæsəti]', 'n.容量,生产量,容量,智能,才能,能力,接受力,地位', '1. That bowl has a capacity of two pints. 那只碗的容量有两品脱。 2. What is the capacity of this jug? 这个水壶的容积多大? 3. He has a great capacity for learning languages. 他学语言的能力很强。 4. China\'s grain production capacity has improved. 中国的粮食生产能力提高了。', '名词复数: capacities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('scorn', '[skɔːrn]', 'n.轻蔑,嘲笑,被叱责的人;vt.轻蔑,不屑做', '1. He eyed me with a terrible scorn. 他极其轻蔑地打量着我。 2. He spat out the words with scorn. 他用轻蔑的口吻说了这番话。 3. He were to become a mark of public scorn. 他将成为公众奚落的典型。 4. The loser\'s scorn for the award is pure sour grape. 失败者对奖品的轻视纯粹是吃不到葡萄说葡萄酸。 5. You\'ve no right to scorn a poor girl. 你没有权利藐视一个穷女孩。', '形容词: scornful 副词: scornfully 名词: scorner 过去式: scorned 过去分词: scorned 现在分词: scorning 第三人称单数: scorns');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('regime', '[reɪ\'ʒiːm]', 'n.政体,政权,政权制度', '1. The people are held down by a vicious and repressive military regime. 人民受着凶恶而专制的军事政权的压迫。 2. The old capitalist regime is on its last legs. 旧的资本主义制度即将灭亡。 3. The regime has been propped up by foreign aid. 该政权是靠外国援助维持着的。 4. The overthrow of the regime was followed by a period of anarchy. 那政权被推翻以後，有一段时期是无政府状态。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('composite', '[kəm\'pɑːzət]', 'adj.合成的,复合的;n.合成物', '1. The police artist made a composite picture of the murderer. 警察局的拼图师拼出了一幅谋杀罪犯的图片。 2. The play is a composite of reality and fiction. 该剧是现实与想象的合成。 3. English is a composite of many languages. 英语是多种语言混合而成的。 4. The main character in her latest novel is a composite of several public figures of that era. 她最近发布的小说中的主人公是那个时代几个公众人物的结合体。', '副词: compositely 名词: compositeness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('oxide', '[\'ɑːksaɪd]', 'n.[化]氧化物', '1. The nitride on oxide layers remains intact. 氧化物表层上面的氮化物保持原状不动。 2. Oxide is usually seen in our daily life. 在我们的日常生活中氧化物很常见。', '形容词: oxidic');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('intimidate', '[ɪn\'tɪmɪdeɪt]', 'v.胁迫', '1. Nobody was going to intimidate them. 没有人能胁迫他们。 2. He was intimidated into silence. 他吓得不敢作声。 3. Bob intimidate the witness into silence. 鲍勃威胁证人保持沉默。 4. Your sons don\'t intimidate me. And neither do you. 你的儿子们威胁不了我,你也一样。', '副词: intimidatingly 名词: intimidation 过去式: intimidated 过去分词: intimidated 现在分词: intimidating 第三人称单数: intimidates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pact', '[pækt]', 'n.合同,公约,协定', '1. It was a pact made in fun long ago. 这是很久以前在开玩笑时定下的契约。 2. Tell Me Why You and I must make a pact. 你和我必须订立契约。 3. They made a pact not to tell anyone. 他们有协定，不告诉任何人。 4. They ratify the pact because they think it will bring peace. 他们批准了这项协定，因为他们认为它将能带来和平。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('scrutiny', '[\'skruːtəni]', 'n.详细审查', '1. Counting is now underway under the close scrutiny of several thousand observers. 现在,计票工作正在几千名观察员的密切监视下进行。 2. She was conscious of his scrutiny of her face. 她觉察到了他长时间的注视着她的脸。 3. The diamond passed the scrutiny of the jeweler. 钻石通过了珠宝商的仔细检查。 4. His theory wouldn\'t bear scrutiny. 他的理论经不起周密的调查。', '名词复数: scrutinies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('stump', '[stʌmp]', 'n.树桩,残余,烟头;v.掘去树桩,砍成树桩,绊倒,难住,截去', '1. The code was no longer anything more than a stump in his hand. 法典在他手里只是一根断株残桩了。 2. Just before starting the driver picked up in the street a stump of a cigar an inch long, and put it in his mouth. 临出发前，赶车的在街头捡了截一英寸长的雪茄烟蒂，塞在嘴里。 3. He went on the stump in his home state. 他到故乡所在的州去发表演说。 4. I\'m stumped: I just don\'t know what to do. 我很为难，简直不知如何是好。', '形容词: stumpy 名词: stumper 过去式: stumped 过去分词: stumped 现在分词: stumping 第三人称单数: stumps');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('constitute', '[\'kɑːnstətuːt]', 'vt.制定(法律),建立(政府),组成,任命', '1. Twelve months constitute one year. 十二个月构成一年。 2. Correct grammar and sentence structure do not in themselves constitute good writing. 正确的语法和句子结构本身并不能构成一篇好文章。 3. The committee is constituted of members of all three parties. 委员会由所有三个政党的成员组成。 4. He was constituted representative of the party. 他被任命为该党的代表。', '名词: constituter 过去式: constituted 过去分词: constituted 现在分词: constituting 第三人称单数: constitutes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('stun', '[stʌn]', 'vt.使晕倒,使惊吓,打晕;n.晕眩,打昏,惊倒', '1. This speech seemed to stun the king. 这话似乎使国王大吃一惊。 2. He was stunned by the sudden news. 他因听到这突然的消息而目瞪口呆。 3. She sat stunned for a while, until she recovered. 她一时昏迷，坐下呆了一会儿才醒过来。 4. The punch stunned me for a moment. 那一拳把我打得昏了一阵。 5. How do I set a laser printer to stun? 我怎么把一台激光打印机设置到震惊？', '过去式: stunned 过去分词: stunned 现在分词: stunning 第三人称单数: stuns');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('doctrine', '[\'dɑːktrɪn]', 'n.教条,学说', '1. This is the doctrine of the nominalist party. 这是唯名主义学派的学说。 2. Christian and Muslim doctrines are very different. 基督教教义和穆斯林教义极为不同。 3. He was impelled to proclaim his doctrine. 他不得不宣扬他的教义。 4. He preached a doctrine which was new to him. 他对教义的解释一改旧貌。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reproach', '[rɪ\'proʊtʃ]', 'v.责备', '1. His reply sounded to me like a reproach. 他的回答在我听来象是责备。 2. Her behaviour was above/beyond reproach. 她的行为是无可指责的。 3. His reply sounded to her like a reproach. 他的回答在她听来像是责备。 4. A coward is a reproach to an army. 懦夫是军队的耻辱。 5. She reproached her husband for having forgotten their wedding anniversary. 她责怪丈夫忘了他们的结婚周年纪念日。', '形容词: reproachable 副词: reproachably 名词: reproachableness 过去式: reproached 过去分词: reproached 现在分词: reproaching 第三人称单数: reproaches');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('discriminate', '[dɪ\'skrɪmɪneɪt]', 'v.歧视,区别,区别待遇', '1. You must learn to discriminate fact from opinion. 你必须学会把事实和看法区分开。 2. Can you discriminate good books from bad? 你能区别好书与坏书吗？ 3. Death does not discriminate; it comes to everyone. 死亡对每个人都一视同仁，它会降临到每个人的身上。 4. He is able to discriminate good book from bad. 他具有区分优秀图书与低劣图书的能力。 5. You must learn to discriminate between things. 你必须学会区别事物。', '副词: discriminately 过去式: discriminated 过去分词: discriminated 现在分词: discriminating 第三人称单数: discriminates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reputation', '[ˌrepju\'teɪʃn]', 'n.名誉,名声', '1. This store has an excellent reputation for fair dealing. 这家商店因公平交易而获好名声。 2. He has not too good a reputation in the matter of honesty. 就诚实而言, 他的名声不太好。 3. He trades on his father\'s reputation. 他用他父亲的名誉牟利。 4. He spotted his reputation by lying repeatedly. 他因反复说谎而败坏了自己的名声。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('kidnap', '[\'kɪdnæp]', 'vt.诱拐(小孩),绑架,勒赎', '1. Police have uncovered a plot to kidnap the President\'s son. 警方已侦破一起绑架总统之子的阴谋。 2. If you improve security at embassies, they kidnap businessmen. 如果你加强了大使馆的安全防范，他们就绑架商人。', '名词: kidnapper 过去式: kidnapped/kidnaped 过去分词: kidnapped/kidnaped 现在分词: kidnapping/kidnaping 第三人称单数: kidnaps/kidnaps');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('formal', '[\'fɔːrml]', 'adj.外形的,正式的,合礼仪的,形式的,整齐匀称的;n.正式的社交活动', '1. At the formal party I felt very awkward and out of place. 在正式的舞会上，我感到局促不安，很不自在。 2. This job doesn\'t require any formal training. 这种工作不需要任何正规训练。 3. There is only a formal resemblance between the two systems; they are in fact radically different. 这两种体系只是在表面上有某种相似之处，其实根本不同。 4. The writer made a formal denial of the hearsay. 这位作家公开否认了这一传闻。', '副词: formally 名词: formalness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('solution', '[sə\'luːʃn]', 'n.解答,解决办法,溶解,溶液,解决方案', '1. He reasoned out a solution to the problem. 他经过推断,找出了解决问题的办法。 2. We haven\'t found the solution yet, but I\'m sure we\'re on the right track. 我们还没有找到解决办法，但我肯定我们的思路是对的。 3. The solution of the problem has just come to me. 我刚想起如何解答这个问题。 4. What color is copper sulphate solution? 硫酸铜溶液是什么颜色？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('lure', '[lʊr]', 'v.引诱', '1. The travel brochure lured me into taking a Caribbean vacation. 这本旅游小册子诱使我去加勒比地区度假。 2. The enticement of the big city lure her away from her home. 大城市的种种诱惑吸引了她离家出走。 3. It\'s very difficult to lure talent away from Silicon Valley. 很难将硅谷的人才吸引走。 4. Do not lure her away from her duty . 不要引诱她离开职守。 5. He left home because of the lures of the life in the city. 由于受到城市生活的诱惑,他离开了家。', '副词: luringly 名词: lurer 过去式: lured 过去分词: lured 现在分词: luring 第三人称单数: lures');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('various', '[\'veriəs]', 'adj.不同的,各种各样的,多方面的,多样的', '1. There are various ways of solving the problem. 有各种各样解决问题的方法。 2. He decided to leave school for various reasons . 由于各种各样的原因,他决定离开学校。 3. Their hobbies are many and various. 他们的业余爱好五花八门。', '副词: variously 名词: variousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('casual', '[\'kæʒuəl]', 'adj.偶然的,不经意的,临时的', '1. He was wearing casual clothes. 他穿着便服。 2. The plan grew out of a casual conversation. 这个计划出自于一次非正式的谈话。 3. He sidled past, trying to seem casual. 他悄悄地溜了过去,竭力装作漫不经心的样子。 4. She is casual about winning the prize. 她对获奖漫不经心。', '副词: casually 名词: casualness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('commodity', '[kə\'mɑːdəti]', 'n.日用品', '1. Coal is becoming a rare commodity. 煤正在成为一种稀缺商品。 2. In spite of the depression, the price of commodity is still high 尽管有些萧条,但商品的价格仍然很高。 3. The country is heavily dependent on its exports of agricultural commodities. 这个国家很大程度上依靠农产品的出口。 4. Time is our most valuable commodity. 时间是最有价值之物。', '名词复数: commodities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('vision', '[\'vɪʒn]', 'n.视力,视觉,先见之明,眼力,想象力,幻想,幻影,景象;vt.梦见,想象,显示', '1. I\'ve had my eyes tested and the report says that my vision is perfect. 我的眼睛检查过了，检查报告说我的视力非常好。 2. How do you cope with the problem of poor vision? 怎样解决视力不好这一难题呢? 3. As it were,where there is human vision,there is almost needs machine vision. 可以说 ,需要人类视觉的场合几乎都需要机器视觉。 4. High above, a vision of prisming colour takes wing; 在远远的天空中,一个幻觉般的影像正在高高地飞翔; 5. He tried to vision himself in a past century. 他假想自己身处百年之前。', '形容词: visional 副词: visionally 过去式: visioned 过去分词: visioned 现在分词: visioning 第三人称单数: visions');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('enthusiasm', '[ɪn\'θuːziæzəm]', 'n.狂热,热心,积极性,激发热情的事物', '1. His refusal iced our enthusiasm. 他的拒绝浇熄了我们的热情。 2. She seemed lacking in enthusiasm when we were talking about that film. 我们谈论那部电影时,她看来好像没多大热情。 3. His enthusiasm made everyone else interested. 他的热心激发了大家的兴致。 4. One of my great enthusiasms is music. 我的一大爱好就是音乐。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cylinder', '[\'sɪlɪndər]', 'n.圆筒,圆柱体,汽缸,柱面', '1. The cylinder is a crucial part of the washing machine. 滚筒是洗衣机必不可少的部分。 2. She handed over a small metal cylinder. 她递过来一个小的金属圆筒。 3. The engine is misfiring badly on one cylinder. 发动机有一个汽缸严重失灵。 4. The accident didn\'t do much damage to the cylinder. 在意外事故中，汽缸没有受到重大损坏。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('resent', '[rɪ\'zent]', 'v.愤恨,怨恨', '1. Kate said she felt we resent her. 凯特说她感到我们大家恨她。 2. I resent the encroachment on my time. 我讨厌别人侵占我的时间。 3. I bitterly resent his attempts to interfere in my work. 我非常讨厌他企图干涉我的工作。 4. I resent having to get his permission for everything I do. 我讨厌做每件事都要得到他的许可。', '过去式: resented 过去分词: resented 现在分词: resenting 第三人称单数: resents');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fixture', '[\'fɪkstʃər]', 'n.固定设备,预定日期,比赛时间,[机]装置器,工作夹具', '1. A new fireplace fixture was fixed in the wall. 新的壁炉的固定物被固定在墙上。 2. In America, this kind of computers have become a fixture in offices. 这种电子计算机现在已成为美国各地办公室里的必备之物。 3. The flagpole has been a fixture since the building was first opened a century ago. 这个旗杆从一个世纪前饭店开业起就一直固定在那里。 4. The price includes all fixtures and fittings. 这个价钱把全部固定装置和设备都打在里面了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('faculty', '[\'fæklti]', 'n.才能,本领,能力,全体教员,(大学的)系,科,(授予的)权力', '1. He is the dean of the Faculty of Medicine. 他是医学院院长。 2. We haven\'t set up the Faculty of Law in our university. 我们学校还没下设法学院。 3. Both faculty and students oppose the measures. 全体教师和学生都反对这种方法。 4. She has the faculty to learn languages easily. 她有轻而易举学会语言的才能。', '名词复数: faculties');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('grope', '[ɡroʊp]', 'v.n.摸索', '1. I groped for the door handle in the dark. 我在黑暗中摸索着门把手。 2. We groped our way through the dark streets. 我们摸索着走过黑暗的街道。 3. We have to grope for ways to do thing. 我们只能边探索边干。 4. Just friends. I won\'t grope you, I promise. 只是朋友嘛。我不会对你动手动脚的，我保证。', '副词: gropingly 名词: groper 过去式: groped 过去分词: groped 现在分词: groping 第三人称单数: gropes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('slip', '[slɪp]', 'n.滑倒,事故,片,纸片;vi.滑动,滑倒,失足,减退;vt.使滑动,滑过,摆脱,闪开,塞入;adj.滑动的,活络的,有活结的;abbr.SerialLineInterfaceProtocol,串行线路接口协议,是旧式的协议', '1. She slipped on the ice. 她在冰上滑倒了。 2. I was unlucky to slip on a banana skin and fall over. 我真倒霉，踩在香蕉皮上滑倒了。 3. The gear slipped. 齿轮滑脱了 4. The wheel slipped from my frozen hand, and the car went right across the road. 方向盘从我冻僵的手里滑脱, 汽车便横着穿过了马路。 5. Leaving his name off the list was a bad slip up. 名单上没有他的名字是个严重的疏忽。', '过去式: slipped 过去分词: slipped 现在分词: slipping 第三人称单数: slips');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('disable', '[dɪs\'eɪbl]', 'v.使残废,使失去能力,丧失能力', '1. He was disabled from walking by the accident. 由于车祸，他不能走路了。 2. Old age disabled him for hard labour. 年迈使他不能干繁重的工作。 3. The soldier disabled by wounds in his leg is buried in sadness. 那个腿部受伤致残的士兵正沉浸在悲哀之中。', '形容词: disabling 副词: disablingly 名词: disablement 过去式: disabled 过去分词: disabled 现在分词: disabling 第三人称单数: disables');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rejoice', '[rɪ\'dʒɔɪs]', 'v.(使)欣喜,(使)高兴,喜悦', '1. I always rejoice in my comrades\' achievements. 我总是为同志们的成就感到高兴。 2. We rejoiced at the good news. 我们为这个好消息而高兴。 3. They all rejoiced to hear the happy news. 他们都很乐于听到这个令人高兴的消息。 4. It rejoices my heart to hear that my son is still alive. 听到儿子仍活着，我心很高兴。', '名词: rejoicer 过去式: rejoiced 过去分词: rejoiced 现在分词: rejoicing 第三人称单数: rejoices');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('arena', '[ə\'riːnə]', 'n.竞技场,舞台', '1. The Roman arena was very famous. 罗马竞技场是很出名的。 2. The arena was crowded with thousands of spectators. 竞技场中挤满了数千名观众。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('meadow', '[\'medoʊ]', 'n.草地,牧场', '1. The bright sun lit up the meadow. 灿烂的太阳照亮草地。 2. A lazy stream winds through the meadow. 一条缓慢流动的溪水蜿蜒曲折流经草地。 3. Cattle were grazing on the meadow. 牛在牧场上吃草。', '形容词: meadowy');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('giggle', '[\'ɡɪɡl]', 'v.哈哈地笑;n.傻笑', '1. Stop giggling, children; this is a serious matter. 孩子们，别傻笑了，这是严肃的事情。 2. The children couldn\'t stop giggling at the teacher\'s high-pitched voice. 教师的嗓音很高，孩子们都不禁咯咯地笑起来。 3. There was a giggle from the back of the class. 从教室后面传来咯咯的笑声。 4. What a giggle! 多有意思的玩意儿！', '形容词: giggly 副词: gigglingly 名词: giggler 过去式: giggled 过去分词: giggled 现在分词: giggling 第三人称单数: giggles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('monitor', '[\'mɑːnɪtər]', 'n.班长,监听器,监视器,监控器;vt.监控;v.监控', '1. Police officers have been closely monitoring the organization\'s activities. 警方密切地监视着该组织的活动。 2. He will monitor and review the company\'s rules and regulations. 他将监督并审查该公司的规章制度。 3. This instrument monitors the patient\'s heartbeats. 这台仪器监听病人的心跳。 4. The monitor handed the papers out to the classmates. 班长把试卷分发给同学们。', '名词: monitorship 过去式: monitored 过去分词: monitored 现在分词: monitoring 第三人称单数: monitors');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('capable', '[\'keɪpəbl]', 'adj.有能力的,能干的,有可能的,可以...的', '1. Not everyone is capable of judging art. 并不是每个人都有鉴赏艺 术的能力。 2. Only human beings are capable of speech. 只有人类才具有说话的能力。 3. Bill is rated as very capable. 大家公认比尔很能干。 4. He is a very capable administrator. 他是个十分能干的行政人员。', '副词: capably 名词: capableness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('disease', '[dɪ\'ziːz]', 'n.疾病,弊病', '1. The disease is still in its primary stage. 这疾病仍然在初发阶段。 2. The entire population was wiped out by the terrible disease. 所有的居民都被可怕的疾病夺去了生命。 3. The rapid spread of the disease is alarming the medical authorities. 这种疾病的迅速蔓延使医疗当局感到忧虑不安。 4. The treatment arrested the growth of the disease. 治疗抑制了病情的发展。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('realistic', '[ˌriːə\'lɪstɪk]', 'adj.现实(主义)的', '1. He was realistic about difficulties. 他对困难持现实的态度。 2. We should encourage pupils to set realistic goals. 我们要鼓励学生设定现实的目标。 3. This is a realistic novel about ghetto life. 这是一部描写贫民窟的现实主义小说。 4. The great majority are realistic politicians. 绝大多数是现实主义的政治家。', '副词: realistically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fury', '[\'fjʊri]', 'n.狂怒,狂暴,激烈,狂怒的人', '1. He slammed the door with a vehement fury. 他愤怒地用力把门关上。 2. He was white with fury. 他气得脸色发白。 3. In a fury, she could not speak. 她气得连话也说不出来。 4. The fury of the storm abated. 暴风雨的威力已经减弱。', '名词复数: furies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tug', '[tʌɡ]', 'v.用力拖,吃力地搬运,苦干,用拖轮拖,拖拉;n.拖,苦干,拖船,(牵引用的)绳索', '1. Tom felt a tug at his sleeve. 汤姆觉得有人拉了拉他的衣袖。 2. Tom gave his sister\'s hair a hard tug. 汤姆使劲地扯了一下他姐姐的头发。 3. We had a great tug to persuade him. 我们费了很大的精力去劝服他。 4. The tug will lead the liner into the harbor. 拖船将把那艘客轮引入港口。 5. She tried to tug my hand away. 她试图把我的手拉开。', '名词: tugger 过去式: tugged 过去分词: tugged 现在分词: tugging 第三人称单数: tugs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('stubborn', '[\'stʌbərn]', 'adj.顽固的,固执的,坚定的,坚决的,难应付的,难处理的', '1. That stubborn man always cleaves to his idea. 那固执的人不愿改变想法。 2. The child has a stubborn temper. 这个小孩脾气执拗。 3. This detergent can remove stubborn stains. 这种去污剂能去除难洗的污渍。 4. I have a stubborn cold and cough day and night. 我得了很难治的感冒，日夜咳嗽。', '副词: stubbornly 比较级: stubborner 最高级: stubbornest 名词: stubbornness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('furthermore', '[ˌfɜːrðər\'mɔːr]', 'adv.此外,而且', '1. The house is too small, and furthermore, it\'s too far from the office. 房子太小,而且离办公地点太远。 2. I don\'t want to go there, furthermore, I have no time to do so. 我不想去那里, 而且我也没时间去。 3. Furthermore, it teaches in dependence. 此外，体育还能教会人独立。 4. Furthermore, the work flow was irregular. 此外，厂里的生产流程也时断时续。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sample', '[\'sæmpl]', 'n.标本,样品,例子;vt.取样,采样,抽取...的样品,试验的一部分,尝试', '1. Thousands of people have written in to us for a free sample. 现已有数千人给我们来信索要免费样品。 2. What I need is nothing but a sample. 我需要的不过是一件样品而已。 3. The sample size would have to be quadrupled. 样本量必须增大三倍。 4. I\'ll send you some sample menus. 我会给您寄些菜单样本去。 5. We sampled the stuff and found it satisfactory. 我们抽验了这批材料，认为满意。', '过去式: sampled 过去分词: sampled 现在分词: sampling 第三人称单数: samples');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('propel', '[prə\'pel]', 'vt.推进,驱使', '1. He used a paddle to propel the boat. 他用船桨将船推进。 2. The proper use of imagination can then propel ideas in the directions you desire. 适当运用想象力可以将思想往你所希望的方向推进。', '过去式: propelled 过去分词: propelled 现在分词: propelling 第三人称单数: propels');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('positive', '[\'pɑːzətɪv]', 'adj.肯定的,实际的,积极的,绝对的,确实的;adj.[数]正的;adj.[电]阳的;adj.[语法]原级的', '1. He has a positive attitude towards life. 他对生活持有积极的态度。 2. We regret out inability to let you know anything positive concerning the above firm. 很抱歉，我方无法让您了解上述公司任何肯定的资料。 3. We still don\'t have a positive answer as to how he died. 他究竟是如何死的，我们还未得出明确的答案。 4. These developments will have a positive effect on the stability of our financial market. 这些发展对稳定我们的金融市场会产生正面的作用。 5. The relationship with this supplier is positive. 我与供应商的关系是正面的。', '副词: positively 名词: positiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('coupon', '[\'kuːpɑːn]', 'n.息票,商家的优待券', '1. This coupon can be redeemed at any of our branches. 这种息票可在我们的任何分行兑现。 2. let\'s fill in a football coupon. 我们填一下足球彩票吧。 3. Coupon must be presented when ordering. 请于落单前出示此券。 4. Please remember to bring the meal coupon. 会议代表凭餐票用餐。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('immune', '[ɪ\'mjuːn]', 'adj.免疫的', '1. This patient\'s immune system has been destroyed. 这位病人的免疫系统受到了破坏。 2. I\'m immune to smallpox as a result of vaccination. 我接种过疫苗了,所以对天花有免疫力。 3. Nobody is immune from criticism. 谁都难免受批评。 4. The criminal was told he would be immune if he helped the police. 这个罪犯被告知，如果他协助警方就可以免于被起诉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pearl', '[pɜːrl]', 'n.珍珠', '1. The pearl sparkled in the moonlight. 那颗珍珠在月光下闪闪发光。 2. She wears a pearl necklace today. 今天她戴了一条珍珠项链。 3. Then there must be some pearl powder in it. 那么这里一定有一些珍珠粉。 4. The Riverview deluxe rooms of Pearl Haosheng Hotel with elegant decorative style are the best choice of you for business membership and sightseeing. 江城明珠豪生大酒店江景豪华房，装饰风格高贵典雅细节之处更令人不胜惊喜，是您商务会友及观光旅游的理想首选。', '过去式: pearled 过去分词: pearled 现在分词: pearling 第三人称单数: pearls');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('scramble', '[\'skræmbl]', 'n.爬行,攀缘,抢夺,混乱;vi.攀缘,杂乱蔓延,争夺,拼凑,匆忙;vt.攀登,搅乱,使混杂', '1. A table was pushed over in the scramble. 在混乱中一张桌子被推翻了。 2. It\'s quite a scramble to get to the top of the hill! 要往上爬很长一段路才能到达山顶呢！ 3. He broke his leg in his scramble down the wall. 他爬墙摔断了腿。 4. There was a scramble for the best seats. 大家都在抢最好的座位。 5. How can you scramble up such a steep hillside? 你怎么能爬上这么陡峭的山坡?', '过去式: scrambled 过去分词: scrambled 现在分词: scrambling 第三人称单数: scrambles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('brief', '[briːf]', 'n.摘要,大纲;adj.简短的,短暂的;vt.摘要,(军事)下达简令', '1. There was a brief pause in the conversation. 对话中有短暂的停顿。 2. We have a tight schedule for your brief visit. I hope you don\'t mind. 对您短暂的访问,我们为您安排的日程很紧,希望您不介意。 3. In the beginning, the teacher gave us a brief introduction about the subject. 开始时,老师给我们做了关于这门课程的简短介绍。 4. I don\'t want to keep you long, so let me be brief. 我不想浪费大家的时间,就简明扼要地讲几句吧。 5. He drew up a brief for his speech. 他起草了一份讲话的摘要。 6. The chairman will brief the Board on the most recent developments. 主席将向董事会概述最近的发展。', '副词: briefly 比较级: briefer 最高级: briefest 名词: briefer 过去式: briefed 过去分词: briefed 现在分词: briefing 第三人称单数: briefs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('courtesy', '[\'kɜːrtəsi]', 'n.谦恭,允许,礼貌', '1. They showed us every courtesy. 他们对我们彬彬有礼。 2. Bill did me the courtesy of answering the question. 比尔很有礼貌地回答我的问题。 3. Thank you very much for your courtesy. 承蒙您的好意，甚为感谢。 4. Not to do so would show a lack of courtesy. 不这样做就会有失礼之嫌。', '名词复数: courtesies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('remote', '[rɪ\'moʊt]', 'adj.遥远的,偏僻的,细微的', '1. The most remote two points in this world are two estranged hearts. 人世间相距最远的两点,是两颗隔膜的心。 2. This is a village remote from the madding crowd. 这是一个远离喧嚣尘世的村庄。 3. Mail comes to this remote village only once a week. 邮车每周只到这个偏僻的村庄一次。 4. The bomb was exploded by remote control. 这颗炸弹是遥控引爆的。 5. Actuation is often desired for process automation, precision timing, and remote operation not possible with manual valves alone. 执行机构经常用于实现紧靠手动阀门无法实现的工艺过程的自动化，准确定时，以及远程操作。', '副词: remotely 比较级: remoter 最高级: remotest 名词: remoteness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('genuine', '[\'dʒenjuɪn]', 'adj.真实的,真正的,诚恳的', '1. He has a genuine desire to help us. 他真心诚意地愿意帮助我们。 2. A genuine friend will not desert you in time of adversity. 真正的朋友不会在患难时弃你而去。 3. It appears to be genuine, but I have my suspicions (about it). 这看来好像是真的，不过我(对此)有怀疑。 4. Viewed from the outside, the company seemed genuine. 从外表上看，这家公司倒像是真的。', '副词: genuinely 名词: genuineness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('porch', '[pɔːrtʃ]', 'n.门廊,走廊', '1. A pigeon perched on our porch railing. 一只鸽子栖息在我们门廊的栏杆上。 2. I met that person at the porch of the church. 我是在教堂的门廊处遇到那个人的。 3. The roof inclines over the porch . 这个屋顶朝那门廊上面倾斜。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fund', '[fʌnd]', 'n.资金,基金;v.支助,投资', '1. Our company is in want of fund. 我们的公司需要资金。 2. The pension fund owns shares in several major public companies. 该养老基金在几家主要出售股份给公众的公司中均有股份。 3. The factory has built up reserve fund. 这个工厂已积累了后备基金。 4. A fund will be set up for the dead men\'s families. 抚恤死难工人家属的基金会即将建立起来。 5. The National Asthma Campaign is funding research into allergy and air pollution. 国家哮喘运动组织为对过敏和空气污染进行研究提供基金。', '过去式: funded 过去分词: funded 现在分词: funding 第三人称单数: funds');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('slump', '[slʌmp]', 'n.消沉,衰退,(物价)暴跌;v.失败,消沉,(物价)暴跌,跌落', '1. Sales have slumped in the last month. 上月销售量骤降。 2. Business slumped after the holiday. 节日过后生意下降了。 3. She slumped, exhausted, onto the sofa. 她疲惫之极地倒在沙发上 4. He swayed forward and slumped down in his chair. 他身子向前一歪,猛地倒在靠椅里。 5. The slump hit his business hard. 物价暴跌使他的生意大受打击。', '过去式: slumped 过去分词: slumped 现在分词: slumping 第三人称单数: slumps');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('vocational', '[voʊ\'keɪʃənl]', 'adj.职业的', '1. Vocational training will fit them for a good job. 职业的培训使他们能找到一个好工作。 2. Education is an approach for establishing individual human capital, and it also affects the vocational propensity of individuals. 摘要教育不但是个人人力资本积累的途径，也会形成个人职业的趋向和偏好。', '副词: vocationally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('shrug', '[ʃrʌɡ]', 'n.关闭者,百叶窗,快门,<美俚>安眠药;vt.关上,装以遮门,以百叶窗遮闭', '1. She gave a shrug of her shoulders. 她耸了耸肩膀。 2. She gave a shrug and walked away. 她耸了耸肩就离开了。 3. I would answer with a shrug of my shoulders. 我总是耸耸肩回答。 4. They would shrug their shoulders, and treat you like a child. 他们一定会耸耸肩膀,把你当作孩子看待!', '过去式: shrugged 过去分词: shrugged 现在分词: shrugging 第三人称单数: shrugs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('transcend', '[træn\'send]', 'vt.超越,胜过', '1. Humans should always transcend their limits. 人类应该不断超越自己的极限。 2. We can\'t transcend the limitations of the ego. 我们无法超越自我的局限性。 3. They transcend national borders and generations. 它们超越国界及世代。 4. The song of the future must transcend creed. 赞美未来的颂歌一定要胜过这类教条。', '过去式: transcended 过去分词: transcended 现在分词: transcending 第三人称单数: transcends');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('assign', '[ə\'saɪn]', 'vt.分配,指派;v.赋值;[计]将驱动器符重定向至第二个驱动器符', '1. All the students are assigned to suitable jobs. 所有的学生都分到了合适的工作。 2. For example, you might assign each order a unique order number. 例如,可能会为每个订单分配一个唯一的订单号。 3. After establishing roles, you can assign individual users to a role. 建立角色后,可以将各个用户分配到角色。 4. For each class, you have to assign an instance name. 对于每个类,您都必须指定一个实例名称。', '形容词: assignable 副词: assignably 名词: assignability 过去式: assigned 过去分词: assigned 现在分词: assigning 第三人称单数: assigns');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('unanimous', '[ju\'nænɪməs]', 'adj.意见一致的,无异议的', '1. The Chinese are unanimous in their condemnation. 全中国人民一致提出谴责。 2. Politicians from all parties were completely unanimous in condemning his action. 所有党派的政治家们都一致谴责他的行为。 3. He was elected with unanimous approval. 他以全体一致同意而中选。 4. The committee were unanimous that the application should be turned down. 委员会一致同意拒绝这项申请。', '副词: unanimously 名词: unanimousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reconcile', '[\'rekənsaɪl]', 'vt.使和解,使和谐,使顺从', '1. I can\'t reconcile the two extreme views. 我无法调和这两种极端的观点。 2. We tried to reconcile her with her family. 我们试图让她和她的家庭和好。 3. We were finally reconciled when he apologized. 他道歉以后我们终于言归于好了. 4. He had to reconcile himself to his fate. 他必须接受自己的命运。', '形容词: reconciliatory 名词: reconcilement 过去式: reconciled 过去分词: reconciled 现在分词: reconciling 第三人称单数: reconciles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rim', '[rɪm]', 'n.边,轮缘,蓝框;vt.镶边,为...装边,沿...边缘滚动;vi.形成边状', '1. The water was even with the rim of the basin. 盆里的水与盆边平齐了。 2. She put a flower on the rim of the hat. 她在帽子边上放了一朵花。 3. She opened the door, and the yellow light from inside rimmed about her. 她打开门，里面射出的灯光在她的身影四周镶了一圈黄色的边。 4. The ball hit the rim and bounced off. 球击中篮框边缘并弹开了。 5. Trees rimmed the pool. 池塘边长了一圈树。 6. She opened the door, and the yellow light from inside rimmed about her. 她打开门，里面射出的灯光在她的身影四周镶了一圈黄色的边。', '过去式: rimmed 过去分词: rimmed 现在分词: rimming 第三人称单数: rims');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('peak', '[piːk]', 'n.山顶,顶点,帽舌,(记录的)最高峰;adj.最高的;vi.到达最高点,消瘦,缩小;vt.使竖起,使达到最高点', '1. In Yersa I noticed a spike on the peak of the pyramid-shaped roof of a church. 在叶拉萨村,我发现一座教堂的金字塔屋顶的尖端有一颗尖钉。 2. The mountain peaks are covered with snow all year. 山顶上终年积雪。 3. Many mountaineers have reached that mountain peak. 许多登山家都登上过那座大山的顶峰。 4. Tourism is at its peak in August. 旅游业在八月份达到高峰。 5. Primary school enrolment will peak this year. 今年小学入学人数将达到最高峰。', '过去式: peaked 过去分词: peaked 现在分词: peaking 第三人称单数: peaks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('survive', '[sər\'vaɪv]', 'v.幸免于,幸存,生还', '1. She was the only one to survive the crash. 她是这次飞机失事的唯一幸存者。 2. These birds are able to survive the perils of the Arctic winter. 这些鸟能在北极寒冷的冬天里生存。 3. I don\'t know how I ever survived high school. 我都不知道我是怎样熬过高中那段岁月的。 4. Santos is survived by his wife of 49 years. 桑托斯的妻子比他多活了49年。 5. You need to be tough to survive in the jungle. 要在丛林中活下来就要有坚忍不拔的意志。', '名词: survivor 过去式: survived 过去分词: survived 现在分词: surviving 第三人称单数: survives');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('booth', '[buːθ]', 'n.货摊,售货亭,棚', '1. Would you please watch over my booth? 请您照料一下我的摊位好吗? 2. I\'ll give him a call from the phone booth on the corner. 我到街角的电话亭给他打个电话。 3. It happened that there was a telephone booth nearby. 碰巧在附近有个公用电话亭。 4. They sat in a corner booth, away from other diners. 他们坐在餐厅角落的小隔间里，与别的就餐者分开。', '名词复数: booths');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('formulate', '[\'fɔːrmjuleɪt]', 'vt.用公式表示,明确地表达,作简洁陈述;v.阐明', '1. Survey the material first to get a sense of it: formulate some questions. 考查原始材料首先要了解它的意义：用公式解答问题。 2. He formulated his thought clearly. 他清楚确切地表达了自己的思想。 3. He struggled to formulate an answer. 他努力字斟句酌地回答。 4. He thought it time to formulate some plan of action. 他认为这是该筹划一些行动计划的时候了。', '名词: formulation 过去式: formulated 过去分词: formulated 现在分词: formulating 第三人称单数: formulates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('slap', '[slæp]', 'vt.拍,掌击,拍击;n.拍,掌击,拍击', '1. It is a slap in the fame to call me a\'fat pig\'. 叫我“胖猪”是对我的侮辱。 2. It is a bit of a slap in the face when she refuseed to see me. 她拒绝见我，这简直是侮辱我。 3. He gave her a slap on the cheek and she began to cry. 他打了她一耳光，她就哭起来了。 4. He hit the water with a resounding slap. 他啪的一声拍了一下水。 5. You were slapping me just now. 你刚才正在侮辱我。 6. The thief ran slap into a policeman. 那贼与警察撞了一个满怀。', '名词: slapper 过去式: slapped 过去分词: slapped 现在分词: slapping 第三人称单数: slaps');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dilemma', '[dɪ\'lemə]', 'n.进退两难的局面,困难的选择', '1. In the process of modern urban development, we often find ourselves in a dilemma. 在都市的发展中,我们往往会陷入困境。 2. The bad weather put us in a dilemma——shall we move on or go back? 糟糕的天气使我们进退两难——是继续前进呢,还是打道回府？', '形容词: dilemmatic');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('texture', '[\'tekstʃər]', 'n.(织品的)质地,(木材,岩石等的)纹理,(皮肤)肌理,(文艺作品)结构', '1. This kind of cloth has a close texture. 这种布质地很紧密。 2. We could feel the smooth texture of silk. 我们能感觉出丝绸的光滑质地。 3. The texture of the rug was very soft. 毯子的手感非常柔软。 4. The cake has a nice light texture. 这蛋糕松软可口。', '形容词: textural 副词: texturally 过去式: textured 过去分词: textured 现在分词: texturing 第三人称单数: textures');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('eject', '[i\'dʒekt]', 'vt.逐出,撵出,驱逐,喷射;n.推断的事物', '1. When endangered,octopuses eject an inky substance,which is used as a screen. 遇到危险的时候，章鱼能够喷射一种墨水状的液体，掩蔽它们逃走。 2. When triggered,these cells eject poison-tipped barbs that help the jellyfish catch food in the ocean. 当受到触发时，这些细胞喷射出有助于海蜇在海洋中捕捉食物的有毒倒钩。 3. If the voters go further and eject Mr Harper, that, sadly, will not be because they have been convinced by the cerebral Mr Dion\'s worthy carbon tax. 如果选民进一步驱逐哈珀，遗憾的是，这不会发生，因为他们在脑海里确信狄恩应得烟尘排放税。 4. He says Pyongyang\'s recent moves to eject international inspectors and resume activity at its main nuclear reactor have dealt a serious blow to the process. 他说，平壤最近驱逐国际核查人员以及恢复其主要核反应堆的作法都对和谈进程造成了严重的打击。', '形容词: ejectable 过去式: ejected 过去分词: ejected 现在分词: ejecting 第三人称单数: ejects');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('deceive', '[dɪ\'siːv]', 'v.欺骗,行骗', '1. It\'s not honorable to deceive them. 欺骗他们是不光彩的。 2. He was foiled in his attempt to deceive us. 他企图欺骗我们,但没有得逞。 3. He deceived me into signing the papers. 他骗我在文件上签了字。 4. You are deceiving yourself if you still believe that she loves you. 你如果还相信她爱你，你就是在欺骗自己。 5. Appearances can deceive. 外表是有欺骗性的。', '形容词: deceivable 副词: deceivingly 名词: deceiver 过去式: deceived 过去分词: deceived 现在分词: deceiving 第三人称单数: deceives');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('console', '[kən\'soʊl]', 'vt.安慰,藉慰;n.[计]控制台', '1. I tried to console her, but in vain. 我试着去安慰她，但是无效。 2. He consoled himself with the thought that it might have been worse. 他聊以自慰的是幸亏事情没有更糟。 3. He was beyond my skill to quiet or console! 我可没有那个本事使他安静下来，或者能给他慰藉！ 4. There are many lights and electrical instruments on the computer console. 电脑控制板上有许多小灯和电子设备。', '形容词: consolable 副词: consolingly 名词: consoler 过去式: consoled 过去分词: consoled 现在分词: consoling 第三人称单数: consoles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('segment', '[\'seɡmənt]', 'n.段,节,片断;v.分割', '1. The company dominates this segment of the market. 这家公司控制了这一部分市场。 2. She cleaned a small segment of the painting. 她把画儿上的一小部分擦干净了。 3. The waiter brought us a dish of orange segments. 服务员给我们端来一盘掰开的橘子瓣。 4. Essentially, each segment is its own address space. 从本质上来说,每个段就是自己的地址空间。 5. Do you know how to segment an orange? 你知道怎么切橙子吗?', '形容词: segmentary 过去式: segmented 过去分词: segmented 现在分词: segmenting 第三人称单数: segments');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('erroneous', '[ɪ\'roʊniəs]', 'adj.错误的,不正确的', '1. We must oppose these erroneous trends of thought. 我们必须反对所有这些错误的思潮。 2. Sometimes this information may be erroneous. 有时候这种信息是错误的。 3. Some of the erroneous pictures of America are painted by others. 但是对美国的一些不正确的描述也来自外部世界。 4. So on bad CD-ROM drives it is possible that you receive erroneous results. 以至于使用不好的光驱抓轨，可能会接收到不正确的结果。', '副词: erroneously 名词: erroneousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('discard', '[dɪs\'kɑːrd]', 'vt.丢弃,抛弃;v.放弃', '1. He discarded his winter clothing. 他把冬天穿的衣服都丢弃了。 2. My mother-in-law would discard them on the spot. 我的岳母是会当场把它们扔掉的。 3. History discarded him. 他被历史所抛弃。 4. You\'ve got to discard before you can pick up another card. 你得先打出一张牌，才能拿另一张牌。', '形容词: discardable 名词: discarder 过去式: discarded 过去分词: discarded 现在分词: discarding 第三人称单数: discards');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('comic', '[\'kɑːmɪk]', 'n.滑稽演员;adj.滑稽的,喜剧的', '1. Children like to read comics. 孩子们喜欢看连环漫画。 2. He is looking for his comic book. 他在找他的连环画。 3. He is a popular TV comic. 他是观众喜爱的电视喜剧演员。 4. The comic scenes in the play were overdone. 这剧的滑稽场面太夸张了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cliff', '[klɪf]', 'n.悬崖,绝壁', '1. The sea had undermined the cliff. 海水侵蚀了悬崖的基部。 2. He couldn\'t find a hold on the cliff. 他在悬崖上找不到一个可以站住脚的地方。 3. The narrow path zigzags up the cliff. 这条狭窄的小径曲曲折折地向峭壁伸延。 4. They slowly clawed their way up the cliff. 他们缓慢地爬上峭壁。', '形容词: cliffy');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('concern', '[kən\'sɜːrn]', 'vt.涉及,关系到;n.(利害)关系,关心,关注,关注,所关心的是', '1. Hardly a whisper of concern has been voiced. 没有人表示过一点点的关心。 2. Provision of shelter was their main concern for the disaster victims. 为灾民提供避难处是他们最关切的事。 3. I am not insensible of your concern. 我不是没察觉到你的忧虑。 4. The theory of relativity is concerned with two seemingly opposite ideas. 相对论涉及两个似乎对应的概念。 5. Rarely would a single concern have the entire facilities required for a complete testing program. 很少有一个公司能拥有为完成整个试验大纲所需要的全部设备。', '过去式: concerned 过去分词: concerned 现在分词: concerning 第三人称单数: concerns');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('complement', '[\'kɑːmplɪment]', 'n.补足物,[文法]补语,[数]余角;vt.补助,补足', '1. This wine complements the food perfectly. 用这种酒配这种菜肴最妙不过了。 2. His business skill complements her flair for design. 他的经营技巧和她的设计才能相辅相成。 3. A wine is a complement to a good meal. 美食加美酒才算完备。 4. In the sentence \'I\'m angry\', \'angry\' is the complement. 在I\'m angry一句中,angry是补语。', '过去式: complemented 过去分词: complemented 现在分词: complementing 第三人称单数: complements');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('batter', '[\'bætər]', 'n.击球手;v.打坏,猛击', '1. Someone is battering at the door. 有人在使劲敲门。 2. A thousand rocket bombs would not batter it down. 一千发火箭弹，也没法将它摧毁。 3. The ship was battered against the rocks. 船被岩石撞坏了。 4. We need a good batter on our team. 我们队需要一个好击球手。', '过去式: battered 过去分词: battered 现在分词: battering 第三人称单数: batters');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cope', '[koʊp]', 'vi.(善于)应付,(善于)处理', '1. He was scarcely able to cope with the situation. 他几乎不知道如何去应付这个局面。 2. I don\'t know how she copes with looking after her family and doing a full-time job. 既要照顾家庭又要全天工作，我不知道她是如何对付的。 3. No one could cope with him in debate. 没人能同他在辩论中对抗。 4. I cannot cope with such a pile of work. 我无法处理这么多工作。 5. The cope of clouds covering the city cleared up by mid-day. 笼罩城市的厚重乌云在中午时散开了。 6. The judge was wearing a black cope. 这位法官穿著一件黑色的法衣。', '名词: coper 过去式: coped 过去分词: coped 现在分词: coping 第三人称单数: copes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('stab', '[stæb]', 'n.刺,刺伤的伤口,一阵突然而强烈的感觉,中伤,伤痛;v.剌,刺伤,伤害(感情等)', '1. Good friends stab you in the front. 当面刺痛你的是你的好朋友。 2. He stabbed at the earth with his stick. 他拿手杖戳著地。 3. She stabbed at the air with her finger to emphasize what she was saying. 她手指一戳一戳的，强调她说的话。 4. He stabbed the meat with his fork/stabbed his fork into the meat. 他用叉子叉肉。 5. The hunter made a stab at the wolf, but missed. 猎人向狼刺去，但没有刺中。', '名词: stabber 过去式: stabbed 过去分词: stabbed 现在分词: stabbing 第三人称单数: stabs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('encourage', '[ɪn\'kɜːrɪdʒ]', 'vt.鼓励,怂恿;v.鼓励,鼓励', '1. Her success encouraged me to try the same thing. 她的成功鼓励我尝试做同样的事。 2. Her parents encouraged her in her studies. 她的父母鼓励她好好学习。 3. He aims to encourage mutual understanding. 他的目的在于增进相互了解。 4. Broadband support flat salary structure, to encourage their staff to study hard. 宽带薪酬支持扁平型结构，鼓励员工努力学习。', '名词: encourager 过去式: encouraged 过去分词: encouraged 现在分词: encouraging 第三人称单数: encourages');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('decisive', '[dɪ\'saɪsɪv]', 'adj.决定性的', '1. The enemy was defeated in a decisive battle. 敌人在一场决定性的战斗中被击败。 2. His opinion is decisive on the question. 他对这个问题的意见是决定性的。 3. She handles affairs in a decisive manner. 她办事果断。 4. A decisive person is needed to decide this matter. 需要一个果断的人来决定这件事。', '副词: decisively 名词: decisiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ignore', '[ɪɡ\'nɔːr]', 'vt.不理睬,忽视,[律](因证据不足而)驳回诉讼', '1. If you ignore your diet, trouble will follow. 如果你忽视自己的饮食，必然会遇到麻烦 2. I agree in principle, but we can\'t ignore the differences. 我原则上同意,但我们不能忽视这些差异。 3. The wisest course would be to ignore it. 上上策是不予理睬。 4. We could ignore him and go direct to the chairman, but we\'d be skating on very thin ice. 我们可以不理会他而直接去找主席，但那样做我们就如履薄冰了。', '形容词: ignorable 名词: ignorer 过去式: ignored 过去分词: ignored 现在分词: ignoring 第三人称单数: ignores');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('contaminate', '[kən\'tæməˌneɪt]', 'v.污染', '1. Contaminate your bed, and you will one night suffocate in your own waste. 如果你弄脏了自己的环境，总有一天会窒息在你所丢弃的垃圾之中。 2. All over the world, oil spills regularly contaminate coasts. 在世界各地，油溢出物经常污染着海岸。 3. They are contaminating the minds of our young people with these subversive ideas. 他们这些颠覆性的思想是对我们年轻人的精神污染。', '形容词: contaminative 名词: contaminator 过去式: contaminated 过去分词: contaminated 现在分词: contaminating 第三人称单数: contaminates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('vertical', '[\'vɜːrtɪkl]', 'adj.垂直的,直立的,顶点的,[解]头顶的;n.垂直线,垂直面,竖向', '1. The northern face of the mountain is almost vertical. 这座山向北的一面几乎是垂直的。 2. The vertical line meets the horizontal one here. 垂直线与水平线在此相交。 3. Wire saws can cut in any orientation, vertical or horizontal. 钢丝锯能够切割任何方向,纵向或横向。 4. The angles refer to the polar view angle, i.e. the angle measured from the vertical. 角涉及到极面观的角，例如垂直物上测量的角。', '副词: vertically 名词: verticality');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sympathy', '[\'sɪmpəθi]', 'n.同情,同情心', '1. I felt much sympathy for the blind. 我对盲人深感同情。 2. I have great sympathy for people in affliction. 我对那些受苦受难的人们充满同情。 3. The story stirred her sympathy. 这故事激起了她的同情心。 4. You shouldn\'t trade on her sympathy. 你不应该利用她的同情心。', '名词复数: sympathies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dismay', '[dɪs\'meɪ]', 'n.沮丧,惊慌;v.使沮丧,使惊慌', '1. The enemy retreated in perfect dismay. 敌人沮丧地退去。 2. To my dismay, he made the same mistakes. 让我感到沮丧的是，他又犯了同样的错误。 3. He watched the burning bouse with dismay. 他绝望地看着着火的房子。 4. The teacher was dismayed at the students\' lack of response. 老师对学生的毫无反应感到沮丧。', '副词: dismayingly 过去式: dismayed 过去分词: dismayed 现在分词: dismaying 第三人称单数: dismays');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('stationary', '[\'steɪʃəneri]', '固定的', '1. He crashed into a stationary bus. 他撞了一辆停着不动的公共汽车。 2. A stationary object is easy to be aimed at. 一个静止不动的物体是容易瞄准的。 3. An astronaut will attempt to leave the stationary spaceship and then return to it. 一名宇航员试着离开静止不动的宇宙飞船，然后再返回。', '名词: stationariness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('withhold', '[wɪð\'hoʊld]', 'vt.使停止,拒给,保留,抑制;vi.忍住', '1. The readers cannot withhold their admiration. 读者无法抑制自己的敬佩。 2. How shall I withhold from tears when we part? 我们离别时我如何忍得住眼泪呢？ 3. The dam is too weak to withhold the pressure of the rising water. 水坝不够牢固，抵挡不住水上涨的压力。 4. The board have decide to withhold part of their grant money from certain student. 委员会决定不发给某些学生的部分助学金。', '名词: withholder 过去式: withheld 过去分词: withheld 现在分词: withholding 第三人称单数: withholds');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cluster', '[\'klʌstər]', 'n.串,丛;vi.丛生,成群', '1. A cluster of tourists are waiting for their tour guide. 一群游客正在等他们的导游。 2. You can see stars in clusters in the night sky. 你可以看到夜空中的星群。 3. You can see clusters of berries in the garden. 花园里能见到一簇簇浆果。 4. You can see ivy growing in thick clusters anywhere. 到哪儿都能看见成丛生长的常春藤。 5. The men clustered together round the fire and sang songs. 人们聚集在篝火周围唱歌。', '过去式: clustered 过去分词: clustered 现在分词: clustering 第三人称单数: clusters');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('advocate', '[\'ædvəkeɪt]', 'n.提倡者,鼓吹者;vt.提倡,鼓吹', '1. Many educators advocate a liberal education. 很多教育家提倡通才教育。 2. We don\'t advocate learning by rote. 死记硬背的学习方法，我们是不提倡的。 3. Many people advocate building more hospitals. 许多人主张增设医院。 4. We advocate higher salaries for teachers. 我们主张涨老师的工资。 5. She is a passionate advocate of education reform. 她是一名教育改革的热情拥护者。', '形容词: advocatory 名词: advocator 过去式: advocated 过去分词: advocated 现在分词: advocating 第三人称单数: advocates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('elapse', '[ɪ\'læps]', 'vi.(时间)过去,消逝;v.流逝', '1. Five months have elapsed since he joined the army. 自从他参军以后,已经五个月了。 2. Three years have elapsed since we met last time. 我们上次相见至今已经三年了。 3. Fifteen minutes elapsed before the performance began. 过了15分钟演出才开始。 4. They met again after an elapse of many years. 他们多年后又相逢。', '过去式: elapsed 过去分词: elapsed 现在分词: elapsing 第三人称单数: elapses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('nil', '[nɪl]', 'n.零', '1. Our immediate capacity for an offensive was nil. 我们尚无立刻进攻的时机。 2. Our football team won by four goals to nil. 我们的足球队以四比零取胜。 3. My knowledge of the subject is practically nil. 我在这方面的知识几乎等于零。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('treaty', '[\'triːti]', 'n.条约,谈判', '1. The treaty gave (a) fresh impetus to trade. 这条约使双方的贸易又推进了一步。 2. There is a contentious clause in the treaty. 这条约中有一条有争议的条款。 3. The Government has signed a treaty with Moscow. 政府已与莫斯科签了一项条约。 4. The house was sold by private treaty. 这所房子以私人协议的方式售出。', '名词复数: treaties');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('slogan', '[\'sloʊɡən]', 'n.口号,标语', '1. The advertising slogan was a play on words. 那条广告口号是双关语。 2. A slogan is over the blackboard. 一条标语在黑板正上方。 3. He daubed the wall with a slogan. 他在墙上写了一条标语。 4. A product will sell better if it is promoted with a slogan. 如果用标语促销,产品的销势会更好。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('gross', '[ɡroʊs]', 'adj.总的,毛重的;n.总额', '1. The gross national product had increased 5 percent last year. 去年的国民生产总值提高了百分之五。 2. You can tell from his gross language that the man was uneducated. 从他那粗俗的语言可以看出，这个人没受过教育。 3. They were accused of gross negligence. 他们因公然渎职而被指控。 4. That is a gross distortion of the truth. 这是对真相的荒唐歪曲。 5. The goods are to be sold by the gross. 这些货物是要趸批出售的。 6. The new movie grossed an estimated $36.4 million at the box office. 这部新电影总共收获了3640万美元的票房成绩。 7. He earned $60,000 gross. 他总共赚了6万美元。', '副词: grossly 比较级: grosser 最高级: grossest 名词: grosser 过去式: grossed 过去分词: grossed 现在分词: grossing 第三人称单数: grosses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('device', '[dɪ\'vaɪs]', 'n.装置,设计,图案,策略,发明物,设备;[计]安装设备驱动程序', '1. The data logger device has been fitted to ship\'s engine room. 数字记录仪装置已安装在船只的机舱里。 2. The printer is the most commonly used output device after the monitor. 打印机是除显示器外最常用的输出设备。 3. It\'s just a tactical device to get over a split in their own Party. 这不过是他的想要克服党内分歧的一种策略。 4. Sending advertising by mail is very successful as a marketing device. 邮寄广告作为一种营销策略是非常成功的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bump', '[bʌmp]', 'n.撞击,肿块;v.碰(伤),撞(破),颠簸', '1. I\'ve bumped my knee on the wall. 我的膝盖撞上了墙壁。 2. I am so sorry to bump into you. 对不起，我撞到你了。 3. The old bus bumped along the mountain road. 旧公共汽车沿著山路颠簸行驶。 4. We bumped up and down along the gravel path. 我们沿砾石小路颠簸而行。 5. She got a bump on her head. 她头上撞起了一个包。', '过去式: bumped 过去分词: bumped 现在分词: bumping 第三人称单数: bumps');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('interact', '[ˌɪntər\'ækt]', 'vi.互相作用,互相影响', '1. These factors interact intimately and cannot be separated. 这些因素相互之间紧密联系，不能分开。 2. Mother and baby interact in a very complex way. 母亲与婴儿以非常复杂的方式相互影响。 3. Economists also study how people interact with one another. 经济学家也研究人们之间的相互影响。 4. Teachers should interact with students more frequently in the class. 老师应该在课堂上与学生有更多的互动。', '过去式: interacted 过去分词: interacted 现在分词: interacting 第三人称单数: interacts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('panic', '[\'pænɪk]', 'n.惊慌,恐慌,没有理由的', '1. There was a panic when the building caught fire. 大楼起火时, 人们一片惊慌。 2. Rumours of an imminent earthquake startled a panic. 谣传即将发生地震引起了一阵恐慌。 3. The thunder panicked the horse. 雷声使马受惊了。 4. The idea might panic the investors. 这个想法可能会使投资者惶恐不安。 5. The financial crisis caused panic selling of securities. 金融危机引发了恐慌之下的债权抛售。', '形容词: panicky 过去式: panicked 过去分词: panicked 现在分词: panicking 第三人称单数: panics');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('decent', '[\'diːsnt]', 'adj.正派的,端庄的,有分寸的,(服装)得体的,大方的;adj.<口>相当好的、象样的', '1. Are there any decent restaurants around here? 这附近有没有好的餐厅？ 2. He dreamed of living in decent conditions. 他梦想着过体面的生活。 3. The lack of decent public transport is a great disadvantage. 没有适当的公共交通工具是很不方便的。 4. John and his wife Leah are very decent people. 约翰是他的妻子丽亚都是非常正派的人。', '副词: decently 名词: decentness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('invest', '[ɪn\'vest]', 'v.投(资),购买(有用之物)～,授予,投资', '1. I won\'t invest my money in his company. 我不会把我的钱投资到他的公司。 2. I\'d like to invest some money in real estate. 我想在地产上投资点钱。 3. They intended to invest hugely in new technology. 他们打算在新技术方面投入大量资金。 4. Everyone should invest some time in community service. 每个人都应该花些时间在社区服务上。', '形容词: investable 名词: investor 过去式: invested 过去分词: invested 现在分词: investing 第三人称单数: invests');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('lounge', '[laʊndʒ]', 'n.闲逛,休闲室,长沙发;vi.闲荡,懒洋洋地躺卧;vt.虚度光阴', '1. We watched television in the hotel lounge. 我们在旅馆休息室里看电视。 2. Please move forward to the passenger lounge . 请向前走到旅客休息室。 3. She is waiting for me in the departure lounge. 她在候机室等我。 4. The children have made an awful mess in the lounge. 孩子们把起居室弄得凌乱不堪。 5. I don\'t want to lounge about town. I have other things to do. 我不想在市区闲逛。我还有别的事要做。', '名词: lounger 过去式: lounged 过去分词: lounged 现在分词: lounging 第三人称单数: lounges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fringe', '[frɪndʒ]', 'n.边缘,须边,刘海;adj.边缘的,额外的;v.在...上加以缘饰,成为...的边缘', '1. The girl wore her hair in a fringe. 那个女孩子额前梳着刘海。 2. The edge of the carpet was frayed into a fringe. 地毯的边缘被散编成一绺绺流苏。 3. They put up tent on the fringe of the woods. 他们在树林边缘搭起帐篷。 4. A fringe of trees stood round the pool. 池塘四周耸立着一圈树木。 5. Coconut palms fringe the shoreline. 岸边点缀着椰子树。', '形容词: fringy 过去式: fringed 过去分词: fringed 现在分词: fringing 第三人称单数: fringes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('gaze', '[ɡeɪz]', 'v.盯,凝视;n.凝视', '1. She sat gazing out of the window. 她坐着凝视着窗外。 2. He gaze ruefully in the mirror at his greying lock. 他凝视著镜中自己日见花白的头发，感慨岁月不待人。 3. She gazed at me in disbelief when I told her the news. 我告诉她这消息时，她以怀疑的目光注视著我。 4. Your intent gaze made her uncomfortable. 你的注目凝视使她感到不自在。', '名词: gazer 过去式: gazed 过去分词: gazed 现在分词: gazing 第三人称单数: gazes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('coincidence', '[koʊ\'ɪnsɪdəns]', 'n.一致,相合,同时发生或同时存在(尤指偶然)的事', '1. What a coincidence! 真是太巧了！ 2. That was a really creepy coincidence. 那样的巧合实在太离奇了。 3. That\'s the most incredible coincidence I\'ve ever heard of! 那是我听说过的最难以置信的巧合！ 4. The plot of the novel relies too much on coincidence to be realistic. 这部小说的情节多靠巧合安排而无真实感。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('recite', '[rɪ\'saɪt]', 'v.背诵,朗读,叙述,[律]书面陈述(事实)', '1. Can you recite the Ten Commandants? 你能背诵十诫吗？ 2. I like to recite his poetical works. 我喜欢背诵他的诗。 3. She can recite the whole poem from memory. 她能背诵全诗。 4. Politicians recite their liturgies in TV studios. 政客们在电视演播室里朗诵祷文。 5. I don\'t like reciting in public. 我不喜欢当众朗诵。', '名词: reciter 过去式: recited 过去分词: recited 现在分词: reciting 第三人称单数: recites');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pave', '[peɪv]', 'v.铺', '1. The road was paved with cobblestones. 那条路是用鹅卵石铺成的。 2. The town council decided to pave the square before the Hall. 市议会决定在市政厅前铺一个广 3. The bricks are to pave the courtyard. 这些砖要用来铺院子。 4. Our garden is well paved with flowers. 我们的园子里鲜花遍地。', '名词: paver 过去式: paved 过去分词: paved 现在分词: paving 第三人称单数: paves');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('exploit', '[ɪk\'splɔɪt]', 'vt.开拓,开发,开采,剥削,用以自肥;v.使用', '1. The capitalists exploit the workers in order to maximize profits. 资本家剥削工人是为了使利润最大化。 2. You must exploit all your spare time to learn English. 你必须利用一切空闲时间来学习英语。 3. People should read the related regulations before they exploit natural resources. 在开发自然资源前，人们应该先了解相关的规定。 4. We should look for blank parts in the market and exploit new market continuously. 我们应找准市场空白,不断开拓新市场。 5. Great men are remembered for their notable exploits. 伟人们因其丰功伟绩而被世人铭记。', '形容词: exploitable 副词: exploitatively 名词: exploitability 过去式: exploited 过去分词: exploited 现在分词: exploiting 第三人称单数: exploits');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rating', '[\'reɪtɪŋ]', 'n.等级级别(尤指军阶),额定,责骂,申斥', '1. Many national newspapers carry adverts for companies purporting to repair your credit rating. 很多的全国性报纸都刊登公司广告，宣称这样可以提升公司的信用等级。 2. The Army is testing a new system for rating the performance of sergeants. 军方正在测试一种新的系统，以此来评定警官的军阶。 3. Such tendencies can best be investigated by use of dynamic stability rating techniques. 这种趋势最好用动态稳定性评定技术来研究。 4. Everyone like this program, so it enjoys a high audience rating. 大家都喜欢看这个栏目，所以它的收视率相当不错。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fragile', '[\'frædʒl]', 'adj.易碎的,脆的', '1. Glasses are fragile and must be handled with great care. 玻璃制品易碎，必须小心轻放。 2. This glass plate is very fragile. 这个玻璃盘子很容易碎。 3. The fragile boxes arrived intact. 这些易碎的箱子完整无损地运到了。 4. Happiness is made of glass, it shines the brightest where it is most fragile. 幸福是玻璃做成的,它最脆弱的地方最闪亮!', '副词: fragilely 名词: fragility');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('chapel', '[\'tʃæpl]', 'n.小礼拜堂,礼拜', '1. The chapel was dedicated in 1880. 这座小教堂于1880年举行献堂礼。 2. He built a chapel as a shrine to the memory of his dead wife. 他建了一座小教堂作为悼念亡妻的圣所。 3. The frescos in the Sistine Chapel are world-famous. 西斯廷教堂的壁画举世闻名。 4. The ghost of Lady Margaret is supposed to haunt this chapel. 据说玛格丽特女士的鬼魂常在这个礼拜堂出没。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('exhaust', '[ɪɡ\'zɔːst]', 'vt.用尽,耗尽,抽完,使筋疲力尽;vi.排气;n.排气,排气装置;adj.用不完的,不会枯竭的', '1. Caring for young children can exhaust you physically and mentally. 照顾小孩子会使你身心疲惫。 2. The expedition was forced to turn back when it exhausted its food supply. 没有了食物,这个探险队不得不返航。 3. He failed to exhaust this subject. 他没能对这个题作详尽无遗的论述。 4. The car needs a new exhaust. 这辆车需要换一个新的排气管。', '形容词: exhaustible 副词: exhaustedly 名词: exhauster 过去式: exhausted 过去分词: exhausted 现在分词: exhausting 第三人称单数: exhausts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('electric', '[ɪ\'lektrɪk]', 'adj.电的,导电的,电动的,电气', '1. They still live in the houses without electric lights. 他们仍然住在没有电灯的房子里。 2. The solar cell can convert the energy of sunlight into electric energy. 太阳能电池能把阳光的能量转化为电能。 3. He uses an electric razor for shaving. 他用一把电动刮脸刀刮脸。 4. He bought an electric hair-drier for Mary. 他给玛丽买了一个电吹风。 5. The lawn mower is an electric. 割草机是电动的机器。', '副词: electrically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('presentation', '[ˌpriːzen\'teɪʃn]', 'n.提供显示外观', '1. Amy did her presentation on her cat. 艾米做的介绍是关于她的猫的。 2. I was asked to give a short presentation on the aims of the plan. 他们要求我就这计划的目的作一个简短的陈述。 3. We want to make her a presentation to celebrate her jubilee. 我们想送她一件礼物以庆贺她的纪念日。 4. I have to make a big presentation in the meeting. 我必须在会议中作重要报告。', '形容词: presentational');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('depress', '[dɪ\'pres]', 'vt.使沮丧,使消沉,压下,压低,使不活泼,使萧条;v.压下', '1. He was depressed by his defeat. 失败让他沮丧。 2. The thought of having to take the exam again depressed me. 想到还需重新考试，我就感到沮丧。 3. The rainy days always depress me. 雨天总是使我沮丧。 4. Depress this button to rewind the tape. 按下这个按钮倒带。', '形容词: depressible 过去式: depressed 过去分词: depressed 现在分词: depressing 第三人称单数: depresses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('impair', '[ɪm\'per]', 'v.削弱', '1. Loud noise would impair your hearing. 大的噪音会损害你的听觉。 2. Smoking can impair the sexual response. 抽烟可以削弱性反应。 3. His illness has impaired his efficiency. 生病降低了他的效率。 4. Don\'t boil the sauce as this and impair the flavor. 酱汁还要煮沸，否则会影响味道。', '名词: impairment 过去式: impaired 过去分词: impaired 现在分词: impairing 第三人称单数: impairs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('prospect', '[\'prɑːspekt]', 'n.景色,前景,前途,期望;vi.寻找,勘探', '1. A rich harvest is in prospect. 丰收在望。 2. I see little prospect of an improvement in his condition. 我看他的情况没有什么改进的希望。 3. What do you think about the marketing prospect? 你觉得市场前景怎么样? 4. The prospect from the balcony was breathtaking. 从阳台上看去景色美极了。 5. They went there to prospect for gold . 他们去那儿勘探金矿。', '过去式: prospected 过去分词: prospected 现在分词: prospecting 第三人称单数: prospects');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('component', '[kəm\'poʊnənt]', 'n.成分;adj.组成的,构成的', '1. The factory supplies components for the car industry. 该工厂向汽车业供应零部件。 2. Each of the components is useful in its degree. 每一个元件都各有程度不同的用处。 3. The militia is a component of the state\'s armed forces. 民兵是国家武装力量的组成部分。 4. A chemist can seperate a medicine into its components. 化学家能把一种药物的各种成分分解出来。 5. Can you resolve it into its component elements? 你能把它分解为组成它的元素吗?', '形容词: componential');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('strand', '[strænd]', 'n.绳、线之一股,线,绳,串,海滨,河岸;vi.搁浅;vt.使搁浅,使落后,使陷于困境,弄断,搓', '1. She twirled a strand of hair round her finger. 她把一绺头发卷绕在手指上。 2. One strand of silk doesn\'t make a thread; one tree doesn\'t make a forest. 单丝不成线,独木不成林。', '过去式: stranded 过去分词: stranded 现在分词: stranding 第三人称单数: strands');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('esthetic', '[es\'θetɪk]', 'adj.感觉的', '1. My esthetic standards are quite different from his. 我的审美标准与他的大不相同。 2. From the esthetic view, it was a beautiful continent. 从美学的观点来看，那是一个美丽的大陆。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('annual', '[\'ænjuəl]', 'n.一年生植物,年刊,年鉴;adj.一年一次的,每年的,一年生的', '1. The firm has an annual turnover of $75 million. 这家公司的年营业额为7500万美元。 2. Now, again, his annual trip to Paris begins. 现在,他一年一度的巴黎之行又开始了。 3. The kind of plant is a hardy annual. 这种植物是耐寒的一年生植物。 4. Annual or perennial herbs, or tall woody bamboos. 一年生或多年生草本，或高的木质的竹子。 5. His essay is copied from a college annual. 他的论文是从一本大学年刊上抄下来的。', '副词: annually');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('specialty', '[\'speʃəlti]', 'n.专业', '1. This job does not match my specialty. 这个工作与我的专业不对口。 2. I have never regretted my choice in such specialty. 我至今仍不后悔我选择这个专业。 3. His specialty is Chinese history. 他的专长是中国史。 4. Now, potato chips were not a specialty. 现在薯条也不是特别食品了。', '名词复数: specialties');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('loyalty', '[\'lɔɪəlti]', 'n.忠诚,忠心', '1. His loyalty is above suspicion. 他的忠诚无可置疑。 2. My judgement was frequently faulty, but my loyalty to the nation could not be questioned. 我的判断经常出错，但是我对祖国的忠诚是无可置疑的。 3. You can\'t put a price on that sort of loyalty. 那样的忠心是不能用金钱来衡量的。 4. Loyalty to the former king still persists in parts of the country. 该国一些地方仍有人忠于前国王。', '名词复数: loyalties');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('agreeable', '[ə\'ɡriːəbl]', 'adj.使人愉快的,惬意的,适合的', '1. I enjoyed an agreeable holiday this summer. 今年夏天我度过了一个愉快的假期。 2. We spent a most agreeable day together. 我们在一起度过了非常愉快的一天。 3. I find her a very agreeable woman. 我发现她是个和蔼可亲的女人。 4. To a more agreeable adviser, or one from whom he would be more likely to learn, Mr. Harthouse could never be recommended. 赫德豪士先生表示谁也不能给他介绍一位更和蔼可亲的顾问，或者他会更可能向之学习的顾问了。', '副词: agreeably 名词: agreeability');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('given', '[\'ɡɪvn]', 'adj.赠予的,沉溺的,特定的,假设的;vbl.give的过去分词', '1. You have to finish the work within the given time. 你们必须在规定时间内完成这项工作。 2. The given radius being 4 ft., find the circumference. 已知半径为四英尺,求周长。 3. He is given to boasting. 他喜欢吹牛。 4. Given his age, he did it quite well. 考虑到他的年龄，他做得相当好。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('solicitor', '[sə\'lɪsɪtər]', 'n.律师,法律顾问', '1. The documents are in the custody of my solicitor. 文件由我的律师保管著。 2. He is a partner in a country solicitor\'s practice. 他是一个农村律师事务所的合伙人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('weapon', '[\'wepən]', 'n.武器', '1. This weapon fires anti-aircraft missiles. 这种武器是发射防空导弹的。 2. The fisher used a spear as his weapon. 渔夫用矛作为武器。 3. Whether a gun is a weapon of offence or a weapon of defense depends on which end of it you are at. 枪是攻击武器还是防御武器，要看你的目的而定。 4. Logic is her weapon. 逻辑是她的利器。', '过去式: weaponed 过去分词: weaponed 现在分词: weaponing 第三人称单数: weapons');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('differentiate', '[ˌdɪfə\'renʃieɪt]', 'v.区别,区分', '1. Can you differentiate one variety from the other? 你能将这两个品种区别开来吗? 2. He cannot differentiate the two flowers. 他无法辨认这两种花。 3. The only way to differentiate yourself from the competition is through service. 只有服务才能真正使你在竞争中凸显。 4. I cannot differentiate between these two things. 我无法区别这两个东西。', '名词: differentiation 过去式: differentiated 过去分词: differentiated 现在分词: differentiating 第三人称单数: differentiates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rig', '[rɪɡ]', 'n.索具装备,钻探设备,钻探平台,钻塔;v.装上索具,配备,装配', '1. Judging by its rig, I\'d say it was a fishing boat. 从船具装备来看，我认为这是一艘渔船。 2. Our camping rig includes cooking pots and sleeping bags. 我们的野营装备包括锅子和睡袋。 3. Most modern yachts have a fore and aft rig, but the old galleons were squared-rigged. 大多数现代化游艇配备的都是前后帆，而老式大帆船装的却是横帆。 4. On Halloween the children rig themselves up in funny clothes. 万圣节前夕孩子们穿上各种滑稽的服装。 5. I will have our people rig them with explosives. 我将会用炸药让我们的民族装配他们。', '过去式: rigged 过去分词: rigged 现在分词: rigging 第三人称单数: rigs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('avert', '[ə\'vɜːrt]', 'v.转移', '1. It was Scott\'s turn to avert his gaze. 这下轮到斯科特移开他注视的目光了。 2. The government has failed to avert a national strike. 政府没有能够避免这场全国性的罢工。 3. He managed to avert suspicion. 他设法避嫌。 4. The lake will be dyked to avert floods. 将为此湖筑堤以防洪水。', '形容词: avertible 过去式: averted 过去分词: averted 现在分词: averting 第三人称单数: averts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('inflict', '[ɪn\'flɪkt]', 'v.造成', '1. We inflicted a crushing defeat on the enemy. 我们把敌军打得一败涂地。 2. We should inflict severe chastisement on criminals. 我们应该对罪犯施加严厉的惩罚。 3. Don\'t inflict your belief on me. 不要把你的想法强加于我。 4. Don\'t inflict damage on any person. 不要伤害任何人。', '形容词: inflictive 名词: inflicter 过去式: inflicted 过去分词: inflicted 现在分词: inflicting 第三人称单数: inflicts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pendulum', '[\'pendʒələm]', 'n.钟摆,摇锤', '1. A pendulum oscillates. 摆锤能摆动。 2. The pendulum of the clock in my room is a bear. 我房间的钟摆是小熊形状的。 3. The pendulum swings with great regularity. 钟摆很有规律地摆动着。 4. Since the last election, the pendulum of public opinion has swung back against the government. 自从上次大选以来,公众舆论又转回到反对政府。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('recall', '[rɪ\'kɔːl]', 'vt.回忆,回想,记起,取消;n.召回', '1. Do you have any recall of that meeting? 你还记得那次会见吗? 2. The new law is now established beyond recall. 新法律现已制定，不得撤销。 3. The experiment sample the raw test of novel Hero Borns to test for times , and it acquires an accuracy of 86.93% , while an recall rate of 91.83%. 实验对小说《英雄出世》的生文本进行了多次抽样测试 4. With the impulse of \"mercantile system\", the Occident adjust their policy one after the other, recall Jew in succession. 在“重商主义”政策的积极推动下,西欧各国相继调整对犹政策,纷纷召回犹太人。', '形容词: recallable 过去式: recalled 过去分词: recalled 现在分词: recalling 第三人称单数: recalls');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('victim', '[\'vɪktɪm]', 'n.受害人,牺牲者,牺牲品', '1. Think of yourself as a survivor, not a victim. 把自己看作幸运儿,不要看作受害者。 2. The victim was smothered to death. 受害人被窒息致死。 3. She fell an easy victim to his temptation. 她经不起他的诱惑，轻易地被骗了。 4. He was the victim of injustice. 他是不公平的牺牲者。', '名词: victimhood');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('crucial', '[\'kruːʃl]', 'adj.至关紧要的', '1. Her work has been crucial to the project\'s success. 她的工作对项目的成功至关重要。 2. It is crucial that we get this right. 我们把这个问题弄明白是极其重要的。 3. Trust is crucial for successful friendship. 相互信任是维系友谊的关键。 4. The battle had reached a crucial stage. 战斗已到了关键阶段。', '副词: crucially');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dramatic', '[drə\'mætɪk]', 'adj.戏剧性的,生动的', '1. After a dramatic pause, the lawyer finished her summation. 在戏剧性的沉默之后,这位律师作完了她的总述。 2. Her opening words were dramatic. 她的开场白十分动听。 3. It was really a dramatic game. 那确实是场给人印象深刻比赛。 4. She made a dramatic speech at the meeting. 她在会上发表了激动人心的演说。 5. Shakespeare\'s dramatics is very popular among the young people. 莎士比亚的戏剧作品在年轻人中很流行。', '副词: dramatically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('wrinkle', '[\'rɪŋkl]', 'n.皱纹;v.使皱', '1. She\'s beginning to get wrinkles round her eyes. 她的眼角开始有皱纹了。 2. My findings add a new wrinkle to each scenario. 我的发现为两种说法都提供了一点想法。 3. Too much sunbathing will wrinkle your skin. 皮肤晒得过分就能起皱纹。 4. He wrinkled up his forehead in perplexity. 他困惑地皱起了眉头。 5. The apples are beginning to wrinkle. 这些苹果开始起皱纹了。', '形容词: wrinkly 过去式: wrinkled 过去分词: wrinkled 现在分词: wrinkling 第三人称单数: wrinkles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('clamp', '[klæmp]', 'n.夹子,夹具,夹钳;vt.夹住,夹紧', '1. The wood is held in position by a clamp. 木头用钳夹固定住了。 2. He used a clamp to hold the arm on the chair until the glue dried. 他用夹子将扶手夹在椅子上, 直到胶水干后再取下。 3. Try to clamp these two blocks of wood together. 试着把这两块木头夹在一起。 4. The wood is held in position by a clamp. 木头用钳夹固定住了。', '过去式: clamped 过去分词: clamped 现在分词: clamping 第三人称单数: clamps');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tumble', '[\'tʌmbl]', 'n.跌倒,摔跤,翻斤斗;vi.翻倒,摔倒,倒塌,滚动,翻筋斗,仓惶地行动;vt.使摔倒,使滚翻,弄乱', '1. Share prices tumbled on the stock-market. 股市上股票价格暴跌。 2. Stock market price tumble after rumor of a rise in interest rate. 谣传利率上升之後，股票市场价格猛跌。 3. That old building could tumble down at any time. 那座古老的楼房随时可能倒塌。 4. It only needed a push and the whole building will come tumble down. 只要稍稍一推，那整幢房子就会倒塌下来。 5. Stock prices took a tumble in the afternoon. 股票价格下午猛跌。', '过去式: tumbled 过去分词: tumbled 现在分词: tumbling 第三人称单数: tumbles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('destiny', '[\'destəni]', 'n.命运,定数', '1. Destiny is sometimes cruel. 命运有时是残酷的。 2. Your destiny is interwoven with mine. 你的命运已和我的命运结合在一起了。 3. Some people believe that the Fates preside over man\'s destiny. 有些人相信，命运之神支配人类的命运。', '名词复数: destinies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('shepherd', '[\'ʃepərd]', 'n.牧羊人,牧羊狗;v.牧羊,看管,带领', '1. The shepherd set out to look for the sheep that had wandered away. 牧羊人出发去找走失的羊。 2. The poor boy was hired as a shepherd when he was only ten. 这个贫穷的小男孩在他十岁的时候就被雇为羊倌。 3. Born into a shepherd family, he is inclined to live a modest life. 他出身于一个牧师家庭，喜欢生活俭朴。 4. The shepherd and his dog gathered in the sheep. 牧羊人和牧羊狗把羊群赶到一块。', '过去式: shepherded 过去分词: shepherded 现在分词: shepherding 第三人称单数: shepherds');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('confident', '[\'kɒnfədənt]', 'adj.自信的,确信的', '1. For my own part, being nice about appearance keeps me confident. 就我而论，注重仪表使我自信。 2. I\'m confident in the path I have chosen. 我对我自己选择的道路有绝对的自信。 3. Your encouragement made me more confident of my future. 你的鼓励使我对我的未来更加有信心。 4. One has to be confident in himself. 一个人一定要对自己有信心。', '副词: confidently');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('perish', '[\'perɪʃ]', 'vi.毁灭,死亡,腐烂,枯萎;vt.毁坏,使麻木', '1. We must plan our civilization or we must perish. 我们必须规划我们的文明，否则我们必定毁灭。 2. Almost a hundred people perished in the hotel fire last night. 近百人在昨夜旅馆的大火中丧生。 3. The ancient Aztec culture has all perished now. 古代阿兹台克文化现在已经全部消亡了。 4. Even the best quality rubber will perish with age. 就是最佳质量的橡胶也会因老化而腐烂。 5. Oil on your car tyres will perish them. 在你车胎上的油将会使车胎损坏。', '过去式: perished 过去分词: perished 现在分词: perishing 第三人称单数: perishes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('grin', '[ɡrɪn]', 'n.露齿笑,裂口笑;v.露齿而笑', '1. They grinned with pleasure when I gave them the sweets. 当我给他们糖果时，他们高兴地咧开嘴笑了。 2. He grin at me, as if sharing a secret joke. 他朝我龇牙一笑，好像彼此会心领略一个笑话。 3. When the rain returns, I will grin even more? 天再下雨时，我会咧嘴笑得更多? 4. He grin at me, as if sharing a secret joke. 他朝我龇牙一笑，好像彼此会心领略一个笑话。 5. He twisted his face into a grin. 他扭歪着脸露齿而笑。', '副词: grinningly 名词: grinner 过去式: grinned 过去分词: grinned 现在分词: grinning 第三人称单数: grins');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('committee', '[kə\'mɪti]', 'n.委员会', '1. The committee meets at three today. 委员会今天三点开会。 2. Moderates have displaced the extremists on the committee. 在委员会中，稳健派人士取代了激进派人士。 3. Some members of the committee expressed reservations about the proposal. 委员会一些成员对这项提议持保留态度。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('integral', '[\'ɪntɪɡrəl]', 'adj.完整的,整体的,[数学]积分的,构成整体所需要的;n.[数学]积分,完整,部分', '1. The transit line is an integral transportation link for the 2010 Winter Olympics. 该隧道是温哥华为2010年冬季奥运会打造的一条完整地下线路。 2. The kitchen is an integral part of a house. 厨房是房子不可缺的部分 3. These policies form an integral whole. 这是很完整的。 4. The bodies of the carts were integral, that is made of one moulding. 马车的车身是完整的，而且是根据同一个模型做出来的。', '副词: integrally 名词: integrality');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('miniature', '[\'mɪnətʃər]', 'n.缩小的模型,缩图,缩影;adj.微型的,缩小的', '1. The little girl has a miniature camera. 小女孩有个小型照相机。 2. The child was playing with his miniature railway. 这孩子正在玩他的小型玩具铁路。 3. The room resembled a miniature battlefield. 这个房间很像一个缩小了的战场。 4. She is just like her mother in miniature. 她简直是她母亲的缩影。', '名词: miniaturist');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('spice', '[spaɪs]', 'n.香料,调味品,趣味,意味,情趣', '1. The cook disguised the flavour with spice. 厨师巧用调料，使人们尝不出食品的原味。 2. Variety is the spice of life. 变化是生活的调味品。 3. Please add more spices to the cake. 请给蛋糕多加点香料。 4. Saffron is an extremely expensive spice. 番红花是一种非常昂贵的香料。 5. Have you spiced this cake? 这蛋糕中加香料了吗？', '过去式: spiced 过去分词: spiced 现在分词: spicing 第三人称单数: spices');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('volunteer', '[ˌvɑːlən\'tɪr]', 'n.志愿者,志愿兵;adj.志愿的,义务的,无偿的;v.自愿', '1. He enlisted as a volunteer in the army. 他以志愿兵从军。 2. He works as a volunteer at off time. 在业余时间 3. He volunteered a statement to the police. 他自动向警方供出情况。 4. Many people volunteer to work on the farms. 许多人自动到农场劳动。', '过去式: volunteered 过去分词: volunteered 现在分词: volunteering 第三人称单数: volunteers');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('contribute', '[kən\'trɪbjuːt]', 'v.捐助,捐献,贡献,投稿', '1. It was generous of her to contribute such a large sum. 她很大方，捐助了这么大笔钱。 2. She asked him to contribute a biweekly article on European affairs. 她让他每两周写一篇有关欧洲情况的文章。 3. Don\'t contribute after the closing date. 请在截止日期前投稿。 4. It is an honour to be invited to contribute to your magazine. 应邀向贵杂志投稿是一个荣誉。', '形容词: contributive 副词: contributively 名词: contributiveness 过去式: contributed 过去分词: contributed 现在分词: contributing 第三人称单数: contributes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('masculine', '[\'mæskjəlɪn]', 'adj.男性的,男子气概的,[语法]阳性的;n.男子,男孩', '1. This coat is masculine. 这件外衣是男式的。 2. She looks rather masculine in that suit. 她穿着那套衣服看上去有些男性化。 3. He was handsome and strong, and very masculine. 他英俊强壮，富有男子汉气概。 4. This noun subscribes to the masculine gender. 这个名词是阳性名词。 5. Host is the masculine noun for hostess. host是与hostess相对应的阳性名词。', '副词: masculinely 名词: masculineness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('commute', '[kə\'mjuːt]', 'v.交换,抵偿,减刑,<电工>整流', '1. Mary used to commute five miles from her home in the suburb. 玛丽过去每天从郊区的家里走五英里来上班。 2. They chose to commute equity into license agreements. 他们选择了将股权转换成许可协议。 3. Regular train travellers may commute a single monthly payment for daily tickets. 经常坐火车的人可以按每天的票价折换购买月票。 4. He seemed at times to be asking God to commute these penalties. 有时他好象还恳求上帝减轻惩罚。 5. Her commute to work will be easy. 她上下班交通会很方便。', '过去式: commuted 过去分词: commuted 现在分词: commuting 第三人称单数: commutes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('vulgar', '[\'vʌlɡər]', 'adj.粗俗的,庸俗的,普通的,通俗的,本土的;n.<古>平民,百姓', '1. Life is a vulgar flare amid the cool radiance. 生命只是惨淡的星光里的平凡的一闪. 2. The vice premier led a vulgar life in his hometown after he resigned. 那位副总理辞职后在故乡过着平民生活。 3. Her taste in clothing is rather vulgar. 她穿着相当俗气。 4. Putting food into one\'s mouth with a knife is considered vulgar in England. 在英国，用刀把食物送进嘴里被认为是粗鲁的行为。', '副词: vulgarly 名词: vulgarness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('equator', '[ɪ\'kweɪtər]', 'n.赤道,赤道似的圈.圆', '1. The equator is an imaginary line. 赤道是一条实际上并不存在的线。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rein', '[reɪn]', 'n.缰绳,统治,支配;vt.以缰绳控制,统治,驾驭;vi.勒住马,止住', '1. He pulled at the reins. 他使劲拉住缰绳。 2. The horse responds to the slightest pull on the rein. 只要缰绳稍稍一拉，这匹马就有反应。 3. He gave rein to his imagination. 他纵情想像。 4. It\'s essential to keep a tight rein on public spending. 对公共开支严加控制极为重要。 5. We need to rein back public spending. 我们需要严格控制公共开销。 6. This horse reins well. 这匹马易于驾驭。', '过去式: reined 过去分词: reined 现在分词: reining 第三人称单数: reins');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('legal', '[\'liːɡl]', 'adj.法律的,法定的,合法', '1. When his father died, his uncle became his legal custodian. 他父亲死后,他叔叔成了他的法定监护人。 2. She started out on her legal career in 1963. 她于1963年干起了法律这一行。 3. We will introduce legal safeguards against fraud. 我们要采取法律保护措施，制止诈骗活动。 4. When you are 18, you are a legal voter. 当你满18岁的时候，你就是一个合法的投票者。', '副词: legally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('vital', '[\'vaɪtl]', 'adj.生死攸关的,重大的,生命的,生机的,至关重要的,所必需的', '1. The government saw the introduction of new technology as vital. 政府认为引进新技术至关重要。 2. She\'s a very vital sort of person. 她是个精力旺盛的人。 3. Confronted with such a vital problem of life and death, he looked as cool as a cucumber. 面对着这样重大的生死问题,他的神态却异常冷静。', '副词: vitally 名词: vitalness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('convince', '[kən\'vɪns]', 'vt.使确信,使信服', '1. I try to convince him of the reality of the danger. 我试图使他相信危险的确存在。 2. It took many hours to convince me of his guilt. 研究了许多个小时我才相信他有罪。 3. He convinced me of his sincerity. 他使我确信他的真诚。 4. There was not an atom of evidence to convince him. 没有一点能使他信服的证据。', '形容词: convincible 名词: convincement 过去式: convinced 过去分词: convinced 现在分词: convincing 第三人称单数: convinces');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('flexible', '[\'fleksəbl]', 'adj.柔韧性,易曲的,灵活的,柔软的,能变形的,可通融的', '1. This tube is flexible but tough. 这管子柔软但很坚固。 2. We need a foreign policy that is more flexible. 我们需要一个更为灵活的外交政策。 3. People use Java because it is flexible and runs on multiple platforms. 人们使用Java是因为它的灵活性及在多种平台上可以运行。 4. Leather and rubber are flexible, glass and iron are not. 皮革和橡胶都是易弯曲的，玻璃和铁则不然。', '副词: flexibly 名词: flexibility');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('comet', '[\'kɑːmət]', 'n.彗星', '1. That comet is invisible to the unaided eye. 那颗彗星只用肉眼是看不到的。 2. Comets move around the sun like planets, but in long oval course. 彗星象行星一样绕太阳运转，然而其轨道呈狭长的椭圆形。', '形容词: cometary');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('geology', '[dʒi\'ɑːlədʒi]', 'n.地质学,地质概况', '1. I know only a few streaks about geology. 我对地质学只是略知一二。 2. Geology is the science of the earth\'s history. 地质学是研究地球历史的科学。 3. The students went to study the geology of that region. 学生们去研究那个地区的地质情况。 4. It\'s essentially a mimic of the natural process of geology on a smaller time scale. 它实际上是对地质情况自然过程的一个模拟，只是时间更短。', '形容词: geologic 副词: geologically 名词: geologist 名词复数: geologies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('intersection', '[ˌɪntər\'sekʃn]', 'n.[数]交集,十字路口,交叉点', '1. The basic algorithm for arriving at the final, applicable set of permissions is to compute the intersection of all. 最后得到的一组适用权限的算法是要计算所有权限的交集。 2. Do not use multiple aliases for a single table in the same query to simulate index intersection. 不要在同一查询中为一个表使用多个别名来模拟索引交集。 3. Breastworks were thrown up at major intersections. 在主要的十字路口都匆匆筑起了胸墙。 4. Cut to the left at the next intersection. 在下一个十字路口向左急转', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('amplify', '[\'æmplɪfaɪ]', 'vt.放大,增强;v.扩大', '1. We must amplify our effort by working a lot harder. 我们必须更努力地工作来扩大成果。 2. The new manager wants to amplify the company. 新经理想要扩大公司。 3. A manufacturer can amplify the demand of a product by advertising widely. 厂商能用大做广告的方法来扩大人们对产品的需求。 4. Please amplify your remarks by giving us some examples. 请举例详述你的话。', '过去式: amplified 过去分词: amplified 现在分词: amplifying 第三人称单数: amplifies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('complex', '[kəm\'pleks]', 'adj.复杂的,合成的,综合的;n.联合体', '1. It was a complex problem. 这是一个复杂的问题。 2. This enhances the complex flavors and bouquet of the wine. 这加强了酒的合成的味道。 3. Complex briary fruit with smoldering oak. 有复合的水果香和烟熏橡木香。 4. They also provide composable functionality required to support complex, large-scale systems. 并提供可复合的功能以支持复杂的大规模系统。 5. Libraries are great complexes of tiny items. 图书馆是细小类目的大综合体。', '副词: complexly 名词: complexness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cling', '[klɪŋ]', 'vi.粘紧,附着,紧贴,坚持(意见),墨守(习惯)', '1. The wet clothes clung to his body. 湿衣服紧贴在他身上。 2. He clung to my arm. 他紧抓着我的胳膊。 3. The cat tried to cling to the edge by its claws. 猫用爪子拼命抓住那边缘。 4. Little children always cling to their mothers. 小孩子总是紧依着母亲。 5. The droid used his magnetized rollers to cling tenaciously to the chromed surface of the ship while deadly turbolaser blasts rained overhead. 在致命的雷射光炮不停地打落在太空船上时，他用具有磁性的滚轮紧抓住舰艇铬制的表面。', '形容词: clingy 名词: clinger 过去式: clung 过去分词: clung 现在分词: clinging 第三人称单数: clings');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('immigrant', '[\'ɪmɪɡrənt]', 'adj.(从外国)移来的,移民的,移居的;n.移民,侨民', '1. He admitted that he was an illegal immigrant. 他承认他是非法移民。 2. California has many immigrants from other states. 加利福尼亚有许多来自其他州的移民。 3. Immigrant workers were classed as aliens. 移民来的工人已归入侨民类。 4. His father is of native Indian extraction and his mother an immigrant Italian. 他父亲有印第安土著血统，母亲是意大利侨民。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('optimistic', '[ˌɑːptɪ\'mɪstɪk]', 'adj.乐观的', '1. The book ended on an optimistic note. 该书的结尾寓意乐观。 2. The stockholders are optimistic about the company\'s future. 股东对公司的前景很乐观。 3. We are still optimistic, whatever the result (may be). 我们仍然乐观，不论结果如何。 4. I was exhausted and relieved, but I wasn\'t wildly optimistic. 我已感到精疲力尽,同时也感到如释重负,然而,我并不抱盲目乐观的态度。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('identical', '[aɪ\'dentɪkl]', 'adj.同一的,同样的', '1. This is the identical hotel we stayed at last year. 这就是我们去年住过的旅馆。 2. Your appearance is identical to hers. 你的相貌和她的一模一样。 3. They\'re wearing identical clothes. 他们穿着完全相同的衣服。', '副词: identically 名词: identicalness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('doubtless', '[\'daʊtləs]', 'adj.无疑的,确定的;adv.无疑地,确定地,<口>大概、多半', '1. That she was angry is doubtless. 她生气是无疑的。 2. We shall produce such kind of engine, which is doubtless. 我们将生产这种发动机，这是肯定无疑的。 3. It is doubtless that he has mistaken my intention. 他无疑误解了我的意思。 4. I am doubtless about the relationship of diligence to success. 我绝不怀疑勤奋与成功的关系。 5. John will doubtless come early as he always does. 约翰无疑会像平时一样很早就来。', '副词: doubtlessly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('exaggerate', '[ɪɡ\'zædʒəreɪt]', 'v.夸大,夸张', '1. Don\'t exaggerate the parallelism between the two cases. 不要夸大那两件事的相似性。 2. The seriousness of the situation has been much exaggerated by the press. 形势的严重性被报纸夸大了。 3. He tends to exaggerate the difficulties. 他往往夸大困难。 4. We should neither exaggerate nor ignore the differences. 虽然我们不能夸大这些不同，但是我们也不能忽视它们的存在。 5. If you exaggerate, you will sound fantastically American. 如果你发音夸张听起来会特别有美国味。', '形容词: exaggerative 副词: exaggeratedly 名词: exaggeration 过去式: exaggerated 过去分词: exaggerated 现在分词: exaggerating 第三人称单数: exaggerates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('blink', '[blɪŋk]', 'v.眨眼,闪亮,无视', '1. The TV announcer never seems to blink. 这个电视广播员似乎从来都不眨眼。 2. Women blink twice as much as man. 女人眨眼的次数是男人的两倍。 3. The lights were blinking on the horizon. 灯光在地平线上闪烁着。 4. You cannot blink the fact that there are wars. 你不能无视于战争存在的事实。 5. She doesnot comprehend the meaning of my blink. 她没有领会我眨眼的意思。', '过去式: blinked 过去分词: blinked 现在分词: blinking 第三人称单数: blinks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('similar', '[\'sɪmələr]', 'adj.相似的,类似的', '1. The two buildings are similar on the whole. 从整体来看，这两幢楼是相似的。 2. I sympathize with you; I\'ve had a similar unhappy experience myself. 我很同情你，我自己也有过类似的不幸遭遇。 3. He talked about it in a similar way. 他对此事有相似的说法。 4. Gold is similar in color to brass. 金和铜颜色相仿。', '副词: similarly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cellar', '[\'selər]', 'n.地窖,地下室,酒窖,藏酒量', '1. This wine cellar stays at an even temperature all year round. 这个酒窖常年保持恒温。 2. The cellar floods whenever it rains heavily. 一下大雨地窖里就灌满了水。 3. The cheese molded in the damp cellar. 乳酪在潮湿的地下室中长了霉。 4. They were ensconced in the cellar. 他们躲在地下室里。 5. The wine has been cellared for ten years. 酒在地窖里存了十年。', '过去式: cellared 过去分词: cellared 现在分词: cellaring 第三人称单数: cellars');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('decrease', '[dɪ\'kriːs]', 'n.减少,减少之量;v.减少', '1. They are making further efforts to decrease military spending. 他们正在做进一步的努力来减少军费开支。 2. His interest in this subject gradually decreases. 他对这门学科的兴趣逐渐减退。 3. The government projected a tax decrease. 政府计划降低税收。 4. They tried to decrease the costs. 他们设法降低成本。 5. The new treatment led to a huge decrease in the number of deaths. 新的疗法使死亡率急剧减少。', '副词: decreasingly 过去式: decreased 过去分词: decreased 现在分词: decreasing 第三人称单数: decreases');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('divert', '[daɪ\'vɜːrt]', 'v.转移,转向,使高兴', '1. A loud noise diverted my attention. 一阵喧闹声转移了我们的注意力。 2. They diverted the river to supply water to the town. 他们使河流改道以便向城市供水。 3. She dished up the anti-pollution business to divert the attention of the public. 她把防止污染的事情说得十分重要,以便转移公众的注意。 4. I found a computer game to divert the children. 我发现了一种供孩子娱乐的电脑游戏。', '副词: divertingly 名词: diverter 过去式: diverted 过去分词: diverted 现在分词: diverting 第三人称单数: diverts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('referee', '[ˌrefə\'riː]', 'n.仲裁人,调解人,[体]裁判员;v.仲裁,裁判', '1. The referee whistled and the game began. 裁判哨子一响，比赛开始了。 2. Does the referee have the power to send him off the field? 裁判员有权勒令他退场吗? 3. He was booked by the referee for foul play. 他因为动作犯规而被裁判记下姓名。 4. At the end of each match, players must maintain the final screens and receive confirmation from a referee. 在每个比赛结束的时候,运动员一定维持最后的荧屏而且受到来自一个仲裁人的证实。 5. Who\'s going to referee the basketball match? 谁将担任这场篮球赛的裁判?', '过去式: refereed 过去分词: refereed 现在分词: refereeing 第三人称单数: referees');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('intermittent', '[ˌɪntər\'mɪtənt]', 'adj.间歇的,断断续续的', '1. They saw the intermittent flashes from a lighthouse. 他们看见了灯塔发出一闪一灭的光。 2. He has intermittent bursts of interest. 他的兴趣是一阵阵的。 3. She suffered from intermittent headache. 她患间歇性头痛。 4. There was intermittent debate about. 有过断断续续的辩论。', '副词: intermittently 名词: intermittence');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('triumph', '[\'traɪʌmf]', 'n.胜利,成功;v.获得胜利', '1. The winning team returned home in triumph. 球队凯旋而归。 2. The bridge is a triumph of modern engineering. 这座桥是现代工程的一大成就。 3. A smile of triumph lit up her face. 她的脸上闪露出胜利的微笑。 4. We finally won a diplomatic triumph. 我们终于赢得了外交的胜利。 5. Advancing culture is bound to triumph over declining culture. 先进的文化必然战胜没落的文化。', '过去式: triumphed 过去分词: triumphed 现在分词: triumphing 第三人称单数: triumphs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sculpture', '[\'skʌlptʃər]', 'n.雕刻,雕刻品,雕塑,雕塑品,[地理]刻蚀;v.雕刻,雕塑,刻蚀', '1. He was a professor of sculpture at the Academy. 他在学院是一位雕塑教授。 2. The smooth contour of the sculpture is wonderful. 雕塑物平滑的轮廓线简直太美了。 3. She studied sculpture at art school. 她在美术学校学习雕刻。 4. There are two horses sculptured in bronze at the gate. 在大门口有两匹用青铜雕塑的马。', '形容词: sculptural 副词: sculpturally 过去式: sculptured 过去分词: sculptured 现在分词: sculpturing 第三人称单数: sculptures');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tame', '[teɪm]', 'adj.(动物)驯服的,柔顺的,(人)没精打彩的,顺从的,被开垦的,沉闷的,乏味的,平淡的;vt.驯养,驯服,制服,使变得平淡;vi.变得驯服', '1. A boy was playing with a tame snake. 一个男孩在玩一条驯服了的蛇。 2. The animals we find in the zoo are quite tame. 我们在动物园看到的动物都很驯服。 3. It\'s incredible that the tame wolf is as mild as a lamb. 令人难以置信的是驯服的狼温和如羊。 4. She is too tame. 她太柔顺了。 5. The Asian elephant can be tamed and trained. 亚洲象可以被驯养和训练。 6. That tiger is impossible to tame. 那只老虎难以驯服。', '形容词: tamable 副词: tamely 比较级: tamer 最高级: tamest 名词: tameness 过去式: tamed 过去分词: tamed 现在分词: taming 第三人称单数: tames');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('acknowledge', '[ək\'nɑːlɪdʒ]', 'vt.承认,答谢,报偿', '1. We acknowledged the need for reform. 我们承认改革的需要。 2. Please acknowledge this cheque as soon as you receive it. 收到该支票后,请立即告知。 3. We hope you can acknowledge your mistake in public. 希望你当众认错。 4. We are sending you some money in acknowledgement of your valuable help. 我们送些酬劳，对您的大力协助聊表谢意。', '形容词: acknowledgeable 过去式: acknowledged 过去分词: acknowledged 现在分词: acknowledging 第三人称单数: acknowledges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('remedy', '[\'remədi]', 'n.药物,治疗法,补救,赔偿;vt.治疗,补救,矫正,修缮,修补', '1. Warmth is the best remedy for colds. 热疗是治感冒的最好方法。 2. I can offer you a sure remedy. 我可以给你提供一个有效的疗法。 3. The remedy he purchased failed to work. 他买的药并不灵验。 4. The mistake is beyond remedy. 这个错误是无法补救的。 5. Aspirin may remedy a headache. 阿斯匹林可治头痛。', '名词复数: remedies 过去式: remedied 过去分词: remedied 现在分词: remedying 第三人称单数: remedies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('synthesis', '[\'sɪnθəsɪs]', 'n.综合,合成', '1. The ribosome is the site of protein synthesis. 核糖体是合成蛋白质的地方。 2. His work is a synthesis of several ideas. 他的作品是由几种构想综合而成的。 3. Our beliefs are a synthesis of Eastern and Western religions. 我们的信仰是东西方宗教的综合体。 4. We made a synthesis of their studies. 我们综合分析了他们的研究报告。', '名词: synthesist 名词复数: syntheses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('alarm', '[ə\'lɑːrm]', 'n.警报,惊慌,警告器;vt.恐吓,警告', '1. The proceedings were interrupted by the fire alarm. 会议的进程被火灾警报打断了。 2. The instant they heard the alarm, they fell in for action. 他们一听到警报，就立即集合准备战斗。 3. The smoke triggered off the alarm. 这些烟把警报器触响了。 4. In case of fire, ring the alarm bell. 如遇失火，请按警铃。 5. Alarm everyone quickly because the house is full of smoke. 快警告大家,屋子理都是烟。', '副词: alarmingly 过去式: alarmed 过去分词: alarmed 现在分词: alarming 第三人称单数: alarms');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('extinguish', '[ɪk\'stɪŋɡwɪʃ]', 'vt.熄灭,消灭,压制,使黯然失色,偿清', '1. Smoking is forbidden. Please extinguish your cigarettes. 吸烟是禁止的，请你把烟熄掉。 2. They tried to extinguish the flames. 他们竭力要把火焰扑灭。 3. The dictator wanted to extinguish all of his opposition in one go. 这位独裁者想一口气消灭所有对手。 4. Nothing could extinguish his faith in human nature. 没有什么能使他丧失对人性的信心。', '形容词: extinguishable 名词: extinguishment 过去式: extinguished 过去分词: extinguished 现在分词: extinguishing 第三人称单数: extinguishes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('default', '[dɪ\'fɔːlt]', 'n.默认(值),缺省(值),食言,不履行责任,[律]缺席;v.疏怠职责,缺席,拖欠,默认', '1. The team lost a game by default. 那个队因没有出席而输掉比赛。 2. If not specified, the default value is no password. 如果未指定，则默认值为没有密码。 3. In 1997, no default of travel agent requiring payment of compensation occurred. 在一九九七年，并没有因旅行代理商不履行责任而需要支付赔偿。 4. He said he had to default on that loan. 他说他必须拖欠那笔债务。', '名词: defaulter 过去式: defaulted 过去分词: defaulted 现在分词: defaulting 第三人称单数: defaults');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('suspicious', '[sə\'spɪʃəs]', 'adj.(～of)可疑的,怀疑的', '1. I am suspicious of his intentions. 我怀疑他的用意。 2. Two suspicious characters were brought in. 逮捕了两名嫌疑犯。 3. I feel suspicious about the truth of the account. 我对于这帐目的真实性感到怀疑。 4. The locals tend to be suspicious of strangers. 当地人对陌生人往往有戒心。', '副词: suspiciously 名词: suspiciousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cater', '[\'keɪtər]', 'vi.备办食物,满足(需要),投合', '1. Our hotel also caters for weddings and parties. 本饭店也承办婚礼、宴会。 2. These hotels cater especially to foreign tourists. 这些旅馆专门为外国游客提供服务。 3. They only publish novels which cater to the mass market. 他们只出版迎合大众市场的小说。 4. TV programs must cater for many different tastes. 电视节目必须满足观众的不同爱好。', '名词: caterer 过去式: catered 过去分词: catered 现在分词: catering 第三人称单数: caters');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('proceedings', '[prə\'siːdɪŋz]', 'n.行动,进行,会议录,学报', '1. The workers decided to take judicial proceedings against the company. 工人们决定对公司正式提起诉讼。 2. The proceedings will begin with a speech to welcome the guests. 大会议程首先 是向来宾致欢迎辞。 3. The proceedings were interrupted by the fire alarm. 会议的进程被火灾警报打断了。 4. The proceedings were published in the newspaper. 会议记录已在报上公布。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bonus', '[\'boʊnəs]', 'n.奖金,红利', '1. The firm offered her a generous bonus as a sweetener. 公司提出给她一笔可观的花红借以拉拢她。 2. He received a box of cookies as a bonus when he bought coffee at the shop. 他在商店买咖啡时,意外地得到了一盒免费赠送的饼干。 3. The warm weather in such a freezing winter has been a real bonus. 这么寒冷的冬天有这样暖和的天气真是令人喜出望外。 4. The firm repaid her hard work with a bonus. 公司发给她奖金以酬谢她的辛勤工作。', '名词复数: bonuses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('liner', '[\'laɪnər]', 'n.<美>班机,划线者,衬垫', '1. The liner is in dock for a refit. 班轮正在船坞修理。 2. The liner has been refitted from stem to stern. 那艘班轮已经全面整修。 3. Hundreds died when the liner went down. 班轮沉没时，有数百人罹难。 4. Hundreds of small craft accompany the liner into harbour. 数百只小艇随同这艘班轮驶入港湾。 5. The liner of my coat was broken. 我的外套衬里破了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('oriental', '[ˌɔːri\'entl]', 'n.东方人(尤指中国人和日本人);adj.东方诸国的,亚洲的,东方的,(珍珠等)最优质的', '1. He specializes in oriental history. 他专门研究东方史。 2. She has studied the cultures of Oriental countries. 她研究过东方各国的文化。 3. China is an oriental country with a long history. 中国是一个有着悠久历史的东方国家。 4. This oriental legend is fascinating. 这个东方传说很吸引人。 5. The Oriental is proficient in the ingredients. 东方人对成分熟练。', '副词: orientally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('argue', '[\'ɑːrɡjuː]', 'vi.争论,辩论;vt.说服', '1. We argued her into joining us. 我们说服她参加了宴会。 2. The United States should, he argues, attempt to remain aloof. 他认为，美国应保持超然态度。 3. As we\'ve seen, the experts argue about which diet is best. 正如我们所看见,而专家们争论,是最好的饮食。 4. One student make so bold as to argue with the professor 有个学生真冒失, 竟然和教授争论起来', '名词: arguer 过去式: argued 过去分词: argued 现在分词: arguing 第三人称单数: argues');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('heel', '[hiːl]', 'n.脚后跟,踵,跟部', '1. His heel is raw because his shoe does not fit well. 因鞋子不合适，他的脚后跟擦破皮了。 2. I have a blister on my heel because my shoes are too tight. 鞋子太紧了，我脚后跟起了个泡。 3. He was about to crush the plant with his heel, when a new thought made him stop. 他正想要用脚后跟践碎那株小草,而一个新的的念头使他停下来了。 4. The boat heeled the strong wind. 船在大风吹袭下倾到了一边。', '过去式: heeled 过去分词: heeled 现在分词: heeling 第三人称单数: heels');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('repel', '[rɪ\'pel]', 'vt.击退,抵制,使厌恶,使不愉快', '1. The positive poles of two magnets repel each other. 两块磁铁的正极互相排斥。 2. They stood prepared to repel any attack. 他们准备好打退一切进攻。 3. The crew repelled the attack. 船员击退了进攻。 4. A country must have the will to repel any invader. 一个国家得有决心击退任何入侵者。 5. The positive poles of two magnets repel each other. 两块磁铁的正极互相排斥。', '名词: repeller 过去式: repelled 过去分词: repelled 现在分词: repelling 第三人称单数: repels');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('air-condition', '[\'eəkənˌdɪʃən]', 'n.空调，空调系统,空调机', '1. The room is equipped with air conditioning. 这个房间装有空调设备。 2. He equipped his car with air conditioning. 他给他的汽车装了空调。 3. I want to buy a set of air conditioning. 我想买一台空调。 4. Zibo Chuang\'Erwo Central Air Condition CO., LTD. 淄博创尔沃中央空调有限公司。', '过去式: air-conditioned 过去分词: air-conditioned 现在分词: air-conditioning 第三人称单数: air-conditions');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('transmission', '[træns\'mɪʃn]', 'n.播送,发射,传动,传送,传输,转播', '1. He varied the transmission frequency. 他变换了无线电传送的频率。 2. Animals may serve as a vehicle for viral transmission. 动物可能成为病毒传播的媒介。 3. We now interrupt our normal transmissions to bring you a special news flash. 我们现中断正常节目，播送一条特别新闻。 4. The company has a transmission plant in France. 那家公司在法国有一座变速器工厂。', '形容词: transmissive');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('exclaim', '[ɪk\'skleɪm]', 'v.呼喊,惊叫,大声叫', '1. The children exclaimed with excitement. 孩子们兴奋地大叫。 2. \"How beautiful the lake is!\" we exclaimed. 我们叫喊着说,\"这个湖多美啊!\" 3. She exclaimed at the beautiful view. 她对这美丽的景色感到惊奇。 4. She exclaimed that she was innocent. 她大声呼喊她是无辜的。', '名词: exclaimer 过去式: exclaimed 过去分词: exclaimed 现在分词: exclaiming 第三人称单数: exclaims');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dean', '[diːn]', 'n.(大学)院长,主持牧师,(基督教)教长', '1. The dean returned in the late afternoon. 系主任是在傍晚时分回来的。 2. The dean cautioned him against being late. 系主任告诫他不要迟到。 3. Accompanied by the dean, they visited the hospital. 在院长的陪同下，他们参观了医院。 4. The dean assembled the students in the auditorium. 教务长把学生集合在礼堂里。 5. This was Torvill and Dean at their best. 这是托维尔和迪安的最隹表现。', '名词: deanship');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('disaster', '[dɪ\'zæstər]', 'n.灾难,天灾,灾祸', '1. They had led the country into economic disaster. 他们把国家带入了经济灾难中。 2. The disaster caused him to waver in his faith. 这件灾难使他对信仰发生了动摇。 3. He spoke darkly of possible future disaster. 他悲观地说将来可能大难临头。 4. We are all pervaded with a sense of disaster. 我们普遍有大祸降临的感觉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('intricate', '[\'ɪntrɪkət]', 'adj.复杂的,错综的,难以理解的', '1. It was an intricate and ingenious system. 这是一个复杂而精致的体系。 2. The prisoners designed the intricate escape. 囚犯们策划了那起周密的越狱事件。 3. Taiwan is a complex of intricate relationships. 台湾是个各种关系错综复杂的地方。 4. The situation seems to be intricate. 局势似乎错综复杂。', '副词: intricately 名词: intricateness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('deduce', '[dɪ\'duːs]', 'vt.推论,演绎出', '1. He will deduce a conclusion from premises. 从前提推导出结论。 2. If a = b and b = c, we can deduce that a = c. 设a = b，b = c，可以推断a=c。 3. The police were able to deduce where the fugitive was hiding. 警方成功地推断出那逃亡者躲藏的地方。', '形容词: deducible 过去式: deduced 过去分词: deduced 现在分词: deducing 第三人称单数: deduces');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ponder', '[\'pɑːndər]', 'v.沉思,考虑', '1. You should pause and ponder now. 你现在应该停下来仔细考虑一下。 2. He pondered long and deeply over the question. 他对该问题作了长时间的深思。 3. We pondered whether to tell her. 我们考虑是否要告诉她。 4. He pondered for some minutes before giving an answer. 他思考了几分钟才作答复。', '名词: ponderer 过去式: pondered 过去分词: pondered 现在分词: pondering 第三人称单数: ponders');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('plaster', '[\'plæstər]', 'n.石膏,灰泥,膏药,橡皮膏;vt.涂以灰泥,敷以膏药,减轻,粘贴,重创', '1. His broken leg was encased in plaster. 他折的腿打上了石膏。 2. They closed the cracks in the wall with plaster. 他们用石膏把墙上的裂缝填满了。 3. This plaster may crack when it dries. 这种灰泥变干时可能会龟裂。 4. The plaster had started to come away from the wall. 灰泥已经开始从墙上脱落。 5. Will it take long to plaster the ceiling? 把天花板涂上灰泥要花很长时间吗?', '形容词: plastery 名词: plasterer 过去式: plastered 过去分词: plastered 现在分词: plastering 第三人称单数: plasters');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('purchase', '[\'pɜːrtʃəs]', 'vt.买,购买;n.买,购买', '1. She purchased a number of shares in the company. 她在公司里买了一些股票。 2. Tickets must be purchased two weeks in advance. 票必须提前两周买。 3. The receipt is your proof of purchase. 这张发票是你购物的凭据. 4. The house is the most expensive purchase I have ever made. 房子是我买过的最贵的东西。', '名词: purchaser 过去式: purchased 过去分词: purchased 现在分词: purchasing 第三人称单数: purchases');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('insert', '[ɪn\'sɜːrt]', 'vt.插入,嵌入;n.插入物', '1. She inserted the key into the lock. 她把钥匙插入锁中。 2. You can insert additional pages into that book. 你可以把附加的散页插入那本书里。 3. The next procedure is to insert the battery. 接下来的步骤是装进电池。 4. He tried to insert an advertisement in a newspaper. 他设法将广告刊登在报纸上。 5. She found an insert in the book. 她在那本书中找到了一个插入物。', '名词: inserter 过去式: inserted 过去分词: inserted 现在分词: inserting 第三人称单数: inserts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tempo', '[\'tempoʊ]', 'n.(音乐)速度、拍子,发展速度', '1. We play the music of Mozart at the slow tempo. 我们以慢速演奏了莫扎特的音乐。 2. Don\'t let the other team dictate the tempo of the game. 别让对方球队控制比赛的节奏。 3. We should keep pace with the swift tempo of the day. 我们应跟上时代的飞速步伐。 4. All this was comparatively slow until, with the coming of science, the tempo was suddenly raised. 所有这些发展都比较缓慢，直到出现了科学，其速度才突然加快。', '名词复数: tempos');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('definitely', '[\'defɪnətli]', 'adv.明确地,干脆地', '1. Sincerity will definitely touch people, and what one puts out will definitely be repaid. 真诚肯定会让人感动，付出一定会得到回报。 2. All the students that work hard can definitely pass the exam. 用功的学生必能通过考试。 3. I definitely will give my consent to your plan. 我当然同意您的计划。 4. Her views very definitely. 她非常明确地阐述自己的观点。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hierarchy', '[\'haɪərɑːrki]', 'n.层次,层级', '1. There is a hierarchy in all living creatures. 一切生物均可按等级分类。 2. It\'s not as if he was very important in the company hierarchy. 他在公司的领导层中似乎无多大权力。 3. pull silver', '名词复数: hierarchies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('thigh', '[θaɪ]', 'n.大腿,股', '1. \"The pain runs from the small of my back right down my left thigh, \" he told the doctor. 他告诉医生说：\"从后腰一直到左大腿都疼得很。\" 2. I walked the last six miles in water up to my thighs. 我在深及大腿的水中走完了最后6英里。 3. The arm is no match for the thigh. 胳膊扭不过大腿。 4. He complained about a pain in his right thigh. 他抱怨着右大腿上的疼痛。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('heap', '[hiːp]', 'n.堆,大量,许多;vt.堆,堆起;v.堆积', '1. The books lay in a heap on the floor. 书堆放在地板上。 2. There is a disorderly heap of clothes in his room. 他屋里有一堆乱七八糟的衣服。 3. He fell down the stairs, landing in a heap at the bottom. 他从楼梯上摔下来，直跌到楼梯底部滚成一团。 4. We have a heap of work to do. 我们有许多工作要做。 5. The gardener began to heap up the fallen leaves. 园丁开始把落叶堆起来。', '过去式: heaped 过去分词: heaped 现在分词: heaping 第三人称单数: heaps');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reject', '[\'riːdʒekt]', 'n.被拒之人,被弃之物,不合格品,落选者,不及格者;vt.拒绝,抵制,否决,呕出,驳回,丢弃', '1. He rejected their offer of a job. 他拒绝了他们给他的工作。 2. After the transplant his body rejected the new heart. 他的身体对新移植的心脏产生了排斥作用。 3. If the application is unfounded, the people\'s court shall make an order to reject it. 申请不成立的,裁定予以驳回。 4. The supermarket rejected all spotted apples. 超级市场丢弃了所有的烂苹果。 5. The factory sells some of its better rejects cheaply, but it throws most of the rejects away. 这家公司廉价出售略好一些的次品，但将大多数次品丢弃。', '形容词: rejective 名词: rejecter 过去式: rejected 过去分词: rejected 现在分词: rejecting 第三人称单数: rejects');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('exempt', '[ɪɡ\'zempt]', 'v.免除;adj.被免除的', '1. He is exempt from military service. 他免服兵役。 2. These houses are exempt from paying rates. 这些房子是免付捐税的。 3. Poor eyesight will exempt you from military service. 视力不佳将使你免服兵役。 4. We hope you will exempt us from taxes. 希望贵方能给予我们免征关税待遇。', '形容词: exemptible 过去式: exempted 过去分词: exempted 现在分词: exempting 第三人称单数: exempts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fling', '[flɪŋ]', 'n.投,掷,猛冲,暴躁的行动,急冲,嘲弄,讥笑;vt.猛投,抛,掷,使陷入,挥动,嘲笑,扫视;vi.猛冲,直冲,急行', '1. Boys like to fling stones into water. 男孩子们喜欢向水中投石子。 2. She flung the papers on the desk and leave angrily. 决策层 3. She flung herself in front of a car. 她猛然冲到汽车前面。 4. You must be certain of your facts before you start flinging accusations (around) (at people). 必须对实情胸有成竹才能理直气壮地(到处)指责(别人)。 5. He had his fling before he was drafted. 他在应征入伍之前尽情行乐了一番。 6. She flung on her coat and ran to the bus-stop. 她匆匆穿上大衣就向公共汽车站跑去。', '过去式: flung 过去分词: flung 现在分词: flinging 第三人称单数: flings');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('divine', '[dɪ\'vaɪn]', 'adj.神的,神圣的,非凡的,超人的,非常可爱的;n.牧师', '1. In the Dragon Pond are divine fish. 可都是龙潭里的神鱼啊。 2. Her elegance and beauty was simply divine. 她高雅的气质和美丽的外表简直是上天的恩赐。 3. That play we saw last night was simply divine! 我们昨天晚上看的那出戏真是好极了！ 4. To err is human,to forgive is divine. 犯错误是人之常情，宽恕才难能可贵。 5. At last I divined the truth. 我终于看穿了事情的真相。 6. I don\'t believe that astrologers are able to divine. 我不相信占星家能作预言。 7. He was selected to be a divine for the church. 他被选为教堂的牧师。', '副词: divinely 比较级: diviner 最高级: divinest 名词: divineness 过去式: divined 过去分词: divined 现在分词: divining 第三人称单数: divines');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('haunt', '[hɔːnt]', 'v.神鬼出没', '1. The college library is a favorite haunt. 大学图书馆是人们喜欢的地方。 2. His youthful escapades came back to haunt him. 年轻时的胡作非为时常令他感到苦恼。 3. The memory in later times returned to haunt him. 那回忆后来经常浮现在他脑海。 4. Her wishful face haunt my dream like the rai at ight. 她的热切的脸，如夜雨似的，搅扰着我的梦魂。 5. The area was a haunt of criminals. 这个地区是罪犯经常出没的地方。', '名词: haunter 过去式: haunted 过去分词: haunted 现在分词: haunting 第三人称单数: haunts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bandage', '[\'bændɪdʒ]', 'n.绷带', '1. The nurse eased away the bandage from the wound. 护士小心翼翼地解开伤口处的绷带。 2. I twisted the bandage round her knee. 我用带缠住了她的膝盖。 3. The waitress put a bandage round his hand. 女服务员用绷带将他的手包扎起来。 4. The surgeon bandaged up his injured head. 外科医生把他受伤的头部包扎起来。', '名词: bandager 过去式: bandaged 过去分词: bandaged 现在分词: bandaging 第三人称单数: bandages');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('scratch', '[skrætʃ]', 'n.乱写,刮擦声,抓痕,擦伤;vt.乱涂,勾抹掉,擦,刮,搔,抓,挖出;vi.发刮擦声,搔,抓;adj.打草稿用的,凑合的', '1. The dog is scratching at the door. 狗正在抓门。 2. He pretended to scratch his ear. 他假装搔耳朵。 3. I had to scratch my head to remember his name. 我只想苦苦地回忆他的名字。 4. Be careful not to scratch the furniture. 小心别刮坏家具。 5. There\'s a scratch on the side of my car. 我的汽车侧面有一道划痕。', '名词: scratcher 过去式: scratched 过去分词: scratched 现在分词: scratching 第三人称单数: scratches');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fuel', '[\'fjuːəl]', 'n.燃料;vt.加燃料,供以燃料;vi.得到燃料', '1. Coal is used as fuel. 煤用作燃料。 2. We aim for a 10% saving in fuel. 我们的目标是节省10%的燃料。 3. His indifference was a fuel to her hatred. 他无动于衷使她心中的怨恨火上加油。 4. Higher salaries helped to fuel inflation. 工资提高刺激通货膨胀。 5. All aircraft must fuel before flight. 所有飞机飞行前都必须加油。', '名词: fueler 过去式: fueled/fuelled 过去分词: fueled/fuelled 现在分词: fueling/fuelling 第三人称单数: fuels/fuels');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hostile', '[\'hɑːstl]', 'adj.敌对的,敌方的;n.敌对', '1. Let\'s hope they will refrain from hostile actions. 希望他们不采取敌对行动。 2. I don\'t like her manner -- she\'s very hostile. 我不喜欢她的态度--待人如仇敌。 3. I don\'t know why she is hostile to me. 我不知道她为什么对我抱有敌意。 4. The new government was hostile to them. 新政府对他们怀有敌意。', '副词: hostilely');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('endure', '[ɪn\'dʊr]', 'v.耐久,忍耐', '1. I could not endure the insolence of his behaviour. 我不能再忍受他那傲慢无礼的行为了。 2. I cannot endure listening to that any longer. 我再也不耐烦听那一套了。 3. If help doesn\'t come,we must endure to the end. 如果没人来帮助,我们必须忍耐到底。 4. They vowed their love would endure forever. 他们海誓山盟地久天长。', '过去式: endured 过去分词: endured 现在分词: enduring 第三人称单数: endures');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('recession', '[rɪ\'seʃn]', 'n.撤回,退回,退后,工商业之衰退,不景气', '1. A few days later, there was a gradual recession of flood waters. 几天之后,洪水逐渐消退。 2. The recession has caused thousands of bankruptcy. 经济不景气造成数千万的破产。 3. There is no sign that the recession has bottomed out yet. 没有迹象表明萧条已经到了极点。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('magnitude', '[\'mæɡnɪtuːd]', 'n.大小,数量,巨大,广大,量级', '1. I want to know the magnitude of this equipment. 我想知道这个设备的大小。 2. The magnitude of the epidemic was frightening. 这种流行病传播范围之广令人惶惶不安。 3. I had not realized the magnitude of the problem. 我没意识到这个问题的重要性。 4. The main quake was estimated at magnitude 6.6. 据估计主震区的震级有6.', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('premise', '[\'premɪs]', 'n.[逻][法]前提,(企业,机构等使用的)房屋连地基;vt.提论,预述,假定;vi.作出前提', '1. I wonder whether the whole premise is right. 我怀疑整个前提是否正确。 2. We must act on the premise that the worst can happen. 我们必须在可能发生最坏事态的前提下行动。 3. British justice works on the premise that an accused person is innocent until he\'s proved guilty. 英国司法运作的前提是被告在被证明有罪之前是清白的。 4. You had better premise your argument with a little historical knowledge. 你最好引述一些历史知识作为你立论的前提。', '过去式: premised 过去分词: premised 现在分词: premising 第三人称单数: premises');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('item', '[\'aɪtəm]', 'n.(可分类或列举的)项目,条款,(消息、情报等的)一则,一条', '1. Let us go on to the next item on the agenda. 让我们继续讨论议程上的下一个项目。 2. The item of the contract still stands now. 该项合同条款现在依然有效。 3. Gone forever are the days when this item sold well. 这一品种畅销的日子一去不复返了。 4. Are there any interesting news items in the paper this morning? 今天早晨报上有什么有趣的新闻吗？ 5. The truck you also see is a signature item. 你可以看到的这种卡车也是一种标志。', '过去式: itemed 过去分词: itemed 现在分词: iteming 第三人称单数: items');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('denounce', '[dɪ\'naʊns]', 'vt.公开指责,公然抨击,谴责', '1. The minister\'s action was denounced in the newspaper. 部长的行为受到报界的指责。 2. American trade policies have been denounced by some European governments. 一些欧洲政府指责美国的贸易政策。 3. They denounced him to the police as a criminal. 他们向警方告发他是罪犯。 4. Somebody denounced him to the military police as a spy. 有人向宪兵队告发他为间谍。', '名词: denouncement 过去式: denounced 过去分词: denounced 现在分词: denouncing 第三人称单数: denounces');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('assassination', '[əˌsæsɪ\'neɪʃn]', 'n.暗杀', '1. The press disclosed an assassination attempt. 报界披露了一暗杀企图。 2. I saw the assassination and it got under my skin. 我亲眼看见暗杀的情景，真令我毛骨悚然。 3. The President\'s assassination led to political convulsion. 总统遇刺引起了政治骚乱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hose', '[hoʊz]', 'n.软管,水龙带,长筒袜;v.用软管浇水', '1. On Sundays, he washes his car down with the garden hose. 每逢星期天，他就用花园里的水管把汽车冲洗干净。 2. The stables were sluiced out with water from a hose. 马厩已经用水管子冲洗过了。 3. This fire hose is about sixty feet long. 这段消防水管大约有60 英尺长。 4. He rigged a rubber hose to the tap in the kitchen. 他将一条橡皮软管安装在厨房的水龙头上。 5. Will you hose down my car - it\'s very dirty. 你能用水管冲洗一下我的汽车吗?它太脏了。', '名词复数: hose 过去式: hosed 过去分词: hosed 现在分词: hosing 第三人称单数: hoses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('exquisite', '[ɪk\'skwɪzɪt]', 'adj.优美的,高雅的,精致的,剧烈的,异常的,细腻的,敏锐的', '1. The hostess had exquisite taste in clothes. 女主人对衣著十分讲究。 2. The girl came up with a set of exquisite stamps. 那姑娘拿出一套精美的邮票。 3. Her skirt has very exquisite lace. 她的裙子有非常精致的花边。 4. The bracelet was made with exquisite workmanship. 这只手镯做得巧夺天工。', '副词: exquisitely 名词: exquisiteness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('explicit', '[ɪk\'splɪsɪt]', 'adj.外在的,清楚的,直率的,(租金等)直接付款的', '1. They gave explicit reasons for leaving. 他们明确地说出了离开的原因。 2. A man can try his best to perfect and improve himself only if he has strong desires and explicit goal. 只有怀着强烈的欲望,有着明确的目标,一个人才能竭尽全力去完善自我,提升自我。 3. He has an explicit understanding of this. 他对这个了解得很清晰。 4. He gave me explicit directions on how to get there. 他清清楚楚地告诉我怎样到达那里。', '副词: explicitly 名词: explicitness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('chunk', '[tʃʌŋk]', 'n.大块,矮胖的人或物', '1. A chunk of the cliff had cracked off in a storm. 山崖上的一块石头在暴风雨中崩塌下来。 2. My mother bought a chunk of meat. 我妈妈买了一大块肉。 3. Sawing another chunk from the log of determination. 我的决心又受到很大的打击。 4. The car repairs took quite a chunk out of her salary. 修理汽车的费用占掉她工资相当大的一笔钱。 5. I listen to the electronic printer chunk along. 我听着电子打字机啪嗒地响个不停。', '过去式: chunked 过去分词: chunked 现在分词: chunking 第三人称单数: chunks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('distill', '[dɪs\'tɪl]', 'vt.蒸馏,提取;vi.滴下', '1. When carvone begins to distill, the condensation can be seen inside the thermometer adapter, thus the progress of carvone distillation can be readily monitored. 当香芹酮开始蒸馏时，在温度计转接器内可看到有冷凝，因此能够容易地监察香芹酮的蒸馏过程。 2. You had to somehow distill those feelings. 你必须试图一滴一滴提炼出这些感情。 3. We were asked to distill the crucial points of the book. 要求我们从本书中提炼出关键点。', '形容词: distillable');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pastime', '[\'pæstaɪm]', 'n.消遣,娱乐', '1. His favorite pastime is tinkering with old radios. 他最喜欢的消遣就是整修老旧的收音机。 2. Dancing is mary\'s favourite pastime. 跳舞是玛丽最喜欢的一种娱乐方式。 3. In fact, it\'s something of a national pastime. 事实上，在某种意义上它是全国人民的娱乐。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('deduct', '[dɪ\'dʌkt]', 'vt.扣除,演绎', '1. Nowadays income tax is normally deducted from a person\'s wages. 现在，所得税通常是在发工资前就已经扣除了。 2. Tax is deducted from your salary. 税金从你的薪金中扣除。 3. You may deduct your families health insurance. 你可以扣除你的家庭健康保险. 4. It is not the bank\'s policy to deduct interest on withdrawal. 提款需扣除利息这并非是本银行的政策。', '过去式: deducted 过去分词: deducted 现在分词: deducting 第三人称单数: deducts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('absurd', '[əb\'sɜːrd]', 'adj.荒谬的,可笑的', '1. He finally recovered from an absurd infatuation. 他终于从荒唐的迷恋中醒悟过来。 2. What an absurd suggestion! 多荒谬的建议啊！ 3. We have no intention of lying down under these absurd allegations. 对这些荒谬的指控我们是不甘受辱的。 4. It was absurd of you to suggest such a thing. 你居然建议这样的事，太可笑了。 5. The proposal borders on the absurd. 该提议近乎可笑。', '副词: absurdly 名词: absurdity');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('trait', '[treɪt]', 'n.显著的特点,特性', '1. They suddenly exhibit a striking new trait. 它们突然呈现出一种新的显著特征。 2. One of his less attractive traits is criticizing his wife in public. 他有个不大讨人喜欢的特点，就是爱当众责备妻子。 3. Our CEO talks and behaves without a trait of authority. 我们公司的首席执行官言行举止没有一点官气。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('blush', '[blʌʃ]', 'v.脸红,羞愧,呈现红色,使成红色;n.脸红,红色,红光', '1. Her blush witnessed her agitation. 她脸红表示了她的激动。 2. She turn away to hide her blush. 她扭过脸，怕人见她脸红。 3. That story might raise a blush on a young girl\'s cheeks . 那个故事可能使少女听了脸红。 4. I have to blush to admit that thing. 我不得不羞愧地承认了那件事。 5. She would blush at the drop of a hat. 她动不动就脸红。', '形容词: blushful 副词: blushingly 过去式: blushed 过去分词: blushed 现在分词: blushing 第三人称单数: blushes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('arrest', '[ə\'rest]', 'vt.逮捕,拘留,吸引;n.逮捕,拘留', '1. The police arrested the thief. 警察逮捕了小偷。 2. You shouldn\'t arrest him without warrant. 你不能毫无根据地逮捕他。 3. The constable stop the car and arrest the driver. 警官使车停住并将司机扣留。 4. The riot led to the arrest of three young men. 暴乱导致3 个年轻人被捕。', '名词: arrester 过去式: arrested 过去分词: arrested 现在分词: arresting 第三人称单数: arrests');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('exchange', '[ɪks\'tʃeɪndʒ]', 'vt.交换,调换,兑换,交流,交易;n.交换,调换,兑换,交流,交易', '1. May I exchange seats with you? 我和你调一个座位好吗? 2. You can exchange your car at our nearest office. 你可以到我们附近的公司换车。 3. We exchanged our opinions about the event at the meeting. 在会上，我们就此事交换了意见。 4. I\'d like to exchange some pounds for dollars. 我想把一些英镑兑换成美金。 5. He gave me an apple in exchange of an orange. 他给我一个苹果，交换一个橙子。', '形容词: exchangeable 过去式: exchanged 过去分词: exchanged 现在分词: exchanging 第三人称单数: exchanges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('string', '[strɪŋ]', 'n.线,细绳,一串,一行;v.排成一列', '1. Puppets are worked by strings. 木偶是用线来操纵的。 2. The E string of the violin needs screwing up. 这只小提琴的E弦需要调紧些。 3. We have had a string of complaints about the program. 我们已经收到了对该节目的一连串投诉。 4. If the logon fails, an empty string is returned. 如果登录失败,则返回空字符串。 5. She strung the beads with a fine nylon. 她用细尼龙线把珠子串了起来。', '过去式: strung 过去分词: strung 现在分词: stringing 第三人称单数: strings');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('arbitrary', '[\'ɑːrbətreri]', 'adj.任意的,武断的,独裁的,专断的', '1. My choice was quite arbitrary. 我的选择相当随意。 2. I\'m not used to your arbitrary standards. 我不习惯你们那些随心所欲的标准。 3. Dictators are arbitrary rulers. 独裁者即独断专横的统治者。 4. This is an arbitrary decision. 这是个武断的决定。', '副词: arbitrarily 名词: arbitrariness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pumpkin', '[\'pʌmpkɪn]', 'n.南瓜', '1. I would like to have pumpkin in the salad. 我喜欢在沙拉里放点儿南瓜。 2. When I visited America I loved eating pumpkin pie. 当我在美国的时候，我喜欢吃南瓜馅饼。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('twist', '[twɪst]', 'n.一扭,扭曲,盘旋,曲折,歪曲,手法,螺旋状;vt.拧,扭曲,绞,搓,捻,使苦恼,使转动,编织;vi.扭弯,扭曲,缠绕,扭动,呈螺旋形', '1. She twisted the long scarf round her head. 她把那条长围巾围在头上。 2. Selecting the suitable twist factor in order to meet the needs of flax knitting yarn, it is the key to increase high_grade and productivity of flax knitting products. 选择合理的捻系数以满足针织用纱的要求是提高亚麻针织产品档次和生产效率的关键。 3. We twisted the bed sheets into a rope and escaped by climbing down it. 我们把床单搓成绳子，援绳下坠逃跑了。 4. The cap should twist off easily. 这个帽儿应该容易拧开。 5. She gave the lid another twist and it came off. 她又拧了一下，盖儿开了。', '形容词: twistable 副词: twistingly 名词: twistability 过去式: twisted 过去分词: twisted 现在分词: twisting 第三人称单数: twists');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hostage', '[\'hɑːstɪdʒ]', 'n.人质,抵押品', '1. The highjackers held two women hostage. 劫机者扣留两名妇女作人质。 2. It is likely that they will kill the hostage. 可能他们将杀掉人质。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('consistent', '[kən\'sɪstənt]', 'adj.一致的,调和的,坚固的,[数、统]相容的', '1. She is a consistent girl in her feeling. 在感情方面她是个始终如一的女孩。 2. Our aim is to ensure a consistent growth. 我们的目标是确保持续的增长。 3. Your conduct is not consistent with what you say. 你的言行不一致。', '副词: consistently');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('velocity', '[və\'lɑːsəti]', 'n.速度,速率,迅速,周转率', '1. The car was moving at such a velocity! 那辆汽车的速度简直太快了！ 2. The velocity of sound in water is more than four times that in air. 声音在水中的速度是在空气中的速度的4倍多。 3. Gazelles can move with astonishing velocity. 羚羊跑起来速度惊人。 4. The velocity of light is about 186,000 miles per second. 光速大约是每秒十八万六千英里。', '名词复数: velocities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cynical', '[\'sɪnɪkl]', 'adj.愤世嫉俗的', '1. She is getting more cynical about life. 她变得对生活更加愤世嫉俗。 2. His cynical attitude gave us a surprise. 他那愤世嫉俗的态度让我们惊奇。 3. With that cynical outlook, he doesn\'t trust anyone. 抱着那种愤世嫉俗的观点, 他不相信任何人。 4. The story depicts the hero as a cynical opportunist. 小说把主人公描写成一个悲观的机会主义者。', '副词: cynically 名词: cynicalness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('coarse', '[kɔːrs]', 'adj.粗糙的,粗鄙的', '1. The medicine powder is too coarse, keep grinding it. 药面太粗了，再磨细点。 2. His coarse manners shocked everyone. 他的粗鲁的举止使每个人震惊。', '副词: coarsely 比较级: coarser 最高级: coarsest 名词: coarseness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('swamp', '[swɑːmp]', 'n.沼泽,湿地,煤层聚水;v.陷入沼泽,淹没,覆没', '1. In the swamp we were beset by mosquitoes. 我们在沼泽地受到蚊子的围攻。 2. The heavy rain has turned the small garden into a swamp. 大雨使这小花园变成了一块沼泽地。 3. Walk through the swamp and we can see the hunter\'s cabin. 走过这片湿地就能看到猎人的小屋了。 4. Their company is in a financial swamp. 他们的公司陷入了财政困境。 5. In summer visitors swamp the island. 夏天，这个岛上熙熙攘攘，人满为患。', '形容词: swampy 名词: swampiness 过去式: swamped 过去分词: swamped 现在分词: swamping 第三人称单数: swamps');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('elegant', '[\'elɪɡənt]', 'adj.文雅的,端庄的,雅致的,<口>上品的,第一流的', '1. He strolled about, looking very debonair in his elegant new suit. 他穿了一身讲究的新衣服逛来逛去，显得颇为惬意。 2. He proudly promenaded his elegant companion in the park. 他得意地领著他那标致的伴侣遛公园。 3. We all wonder how you always look so young and beautiful and elegant! 我们都很想知道,为什么你总是那么优雅年轻。 4. The lady wears an elegant dark suit. 那位女士穿着雅致的深色套装。', '副词: elegantly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('suite', '[swiːt]', 'n.(一批)随员,(一套)家具,套房,套,组,组曲', '1. The suite is for the honeymoon couple. 这套房是为新婚夫妇设的。 2. He brought a three-piece suite for his new house. 他为新房子买了三件一套的家具。 3. He left the hotel with his suites yesterday. 他昨天带着一群随员离开了那家酒店。 4. He has composed a suite of music for the film. 他为该电影配写了一套乐曲。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('convene', '[kən\'viːn]', 'v.召集,集合', '1. The tribunal will convene tomorrow. 法庭将于明日开庭。 2. The committee will convene at 11.30 next Thursday. 委员会将在下星期四上午 11:30 开会。 3. The Board shall convene an emergency meeting to review and confirm such report. 董事会应召开紧急会议对该报告进行审议并核准。 4. People were convened here for an emergency meeting. 人们被召集到这里举行紧急会议。', '形容词: convenable 名词: convener 过去式: convened 过去分词: convened 现在分词: convening 第三人称单数: convenes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('adore', '[ə\'dɔːr]', 'v.崇拜,爱慕,(口语)喜爱', '1. Men can only adore women who are adorable. 男人们只爱慕那些让人爱慕的女人。 2. The kids adore their father and confide in him. 孩子们崇拜并信赖他们的父亲。 3. The boys adore their mothers. 男孩们敬慕他们的母亲。 4. All the girls in our school adore the handsome mathematics teacher who happens to be a bachelor. 我们学校里所有女孩子都崇拜那个恰巧是单身汉的英俊数学老师。', '副词: adoringly 名词: adorer 过去式: adored 过去分词: adored 现在分词: adoring 第三人称单数: adores');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('expedition', '[ˌekspə\'dɪʃn]', 'n.远征,探险队,迅速,派遣', '1. They equipped themselves for the expedition. 他们为远征治装。 2. They planned to organize a scientific expedition. 他们计划组织一次科学考察。 3. He is the commander of the expedition. 他是探险队的队长。 4. The expedition suffered all the rigors of a Canadian winter. 这支探险队饱受了加拿大严冬的折磨。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('shutter', '[\'ʃʌtər]', 'n.耸肩;v.耸肩', '1. Open the shutter and see what the weather is like. 打开百叶窗，看看外面的天气如何。 2. She regained her balance and opened the shutter. 她重新站稳脚步，然后打开百叶窗。 3. This shutter device for fading a picture can be operated by hand. 这个使画面惭入的遮板装置可以用手操作。 4. He adjusted the shutter before taking a photo. 在照相前，他调整了快门。 5. The house was empty and shuttered. 这所房子是空的，窗板都关上了。', '过去式: shuttered 过去分词: shuttered 现在分词: shuttering 第三人称单数: shutters');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('glance', '[ɡlæns]', 'vi.扫视,匆匆一看;n.一瞥,眼光,匆匆一看', '1. She glanced round the room before she left. 她略微环视了一下房间才离开。 2. I\'m just going to glance over these documents, then we can go. 我再看一下这些文件，然后我们就可以走了。 3. On the bus I always manage to glance at the headline in the newspaper. 在公共汽车上我总能设法匆匆看一眼报纸大标题。 4. He glanced at the envelope and recognized his uncle\'s handwriting. 他瞥了一眼那个信封,认出是他叔父的笔迹。 5. He gave her an admiring glance. 他向她投以敬慕的一瞥。', '过去式: glanced 过去分词: glanced 现在分词: glancing 第三人称单数: glances');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('gown', '[ɡaʊn]', 'n.长袍,法衣,礼服,睡袍', '1. She is in a purplish mantle, pink gown. 她身穿一件紫色披肩，桃红色长袍。 2. She wore a black silk evening gown. 她穿着一件黑色丝质晚礼服。 3. She put on her silken gown before going to bed. 睡觉前，她穿上丝质的睡衣。 4. She wore an antique gown to the costume party. 她穿着一件过时的长袍参加化妆舞会。', '过去式: gowned 过去分词: gowned 现在分词: gowning 第三人称单数: gowns');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('propaganda', '[ˌprɑːpə\'ɡændə]', 'n.宣传,[天主教]传道总会', '1. Art may be used as a vehicle for propaganda. 艺术可用作宣传工具。 2. There has been a lot of anti-war propaganda. 一直有许多反战宣传。 3. She even helped us do propaganda among the women. 她甚至还帮助我们在妇女中间做宣传工作。 4. here has been so much propaganda against smoking that many people have given it up. 反对吸烟的宣传很多,许多人因而戒了烟。', '形容词: propagandistic 副词: propagandistically 名词: propagandism');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('initiate', '[ɪ\'nɪʃieɪt]', 'vt.开始,发动,传授;v.开始,发起', '1. This term we will initiate a new teaching plan. 这学期我们将开始实行一个新的教学计划。 2. The company initiated a management training program for small businesses. 该公司发起了针对小企业的管理培训方案。 3. I shall initiate you into our business methods. 我将把我们的营业方法介绍给你。 4. My father wanted to initiate me into fishing. 我爸爸想教我钓鱼。', '名词: initiator 过去式: initiated 过去分词: initiated 现在分词: initiating 第三人称单数: initiates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('breakthrough', '[\'breɪkθruː]', 'n.突破', '1. It is a major technological breakthrough. 这是一次重要的技术突破。 2. He finally has a breakthrough in his creation. 他终于在创作上有了突破。 3. The scientists strive for a breakthrough in cancer research. 科学家们力争在癌症研究方面有个突破。 4. The medical breakthrough proves that guzzling ale is not the only reason why men develop saggy stomachs. 医学上的这一突破表明，男人们的啤酒肚并不完全是因为狂饮啤酒而造成的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('brilliant', '[\'brɪljənt]', 'adj.灿烂的,闪耀的,有才气的', '1. He has got brilliant achievements in the field of physics. 他在物理学方面已经取得了卓越的成就。 2. The brilliant sun lit up their rooms. 灿烂的阳光照亮了他们的屋子。 3. Memory is like a living book whose brilliant fragments worth reading a hundred times in my life. 回忆就像是一本生动的书,生活中那些精彩的片段令我百读不厌。 4. The novel is considered a brilliant performance. 这部小说被认为是出色的佳作。', '副词: brilliantly 名词: brilliantness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('destined', '[\'destɪnd]', 'adj.去往…的', '1. He is only beginning to realize the role he is destined to play in the great saga. 他刚开始认识到他在这伟大的冒险故事里所扮演的角色是命中注定的。 2. If all things have being destined, then is that mean sometimes the destiny depends on a particular time? 如果命运是命中注定的，是不是说某些时候命运是随某个特定时代而定的？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('preclude', '[prɪ\'kluːd]', 'n.排除', '1. That will preclude him from escaping. 那将阻止他逃走，那将使他无法逃走。 2. Their move does not preclude others from investing. 他们这一行动并不影响其他人进行投资。 3. My present finances preclude the possibility of buying a car. 按我目前的财务状况我是不可能买车的。 4. Small volume this year does not preclude huge volume next year. 今年业绩不多，不代表明年就一定会很少，', '形容词: preclusive 副词: preclusively 名词: preclusion 过去式: precluded 过去分词: precluded 现在分词: precluding 第三人称单数: precludes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('disclose', '[dɪs\'kloʊz]', 'vt.揭露,透露', '1. I have no intention of disclosing their names. 我无意泄露他们的姓名。 2. The Government disclosed that another diplomat has been arrested for spying. 政府透露 3. The violets disclose their petals. 紫罗兰绽开花瓣。 4. Science can disclose the mysteries of nature. 科学能解开自然界的奥秘。', '形容词: disclosable 名词: discloser 过去式: disclosed 过去分词: disclosed 现在分词: disclosing 第三人称单数: discloses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('supplementary', '[ˌsʌplɪ\'mentri]', 'n.(supplementaries)增补者,增补物;adj.附助的', '1. This reader is supplementary to the textbook. 这本读物是补充教科书的。 2. The supplementary goods have been gotten gready. 要补充的货物已经准备好了， 3. What supplementary services will be offered? 提供什么样的附加服务? 4. Supplementary punishments may also be applied independently. 附加刑也可以独立适用。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('consolidate', '[kən\'sɒləˌdeɪt]', 'v.巩固', '1. The two companies consolidated last year. 这两个公司去年合并了。 2. We will consolidate and deliver together then. 我们届时将提前统一运输。 3. He bribes his leader to consolidate his position. 他贿赂他的领导来巩固他的地位。 4. We\'ve made a good start, now it\'s time to consolidate. 我们有了一个良好的开端, 现在应该加以巩固。', '名词: consolidator 过去式: consolidated 过去分词: consolidated 现在分词: consolidating 第三人称单数: consolidates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('nurture', '[\'nɜːrtʃər]', 'n.养育,教育,教养,营养品;vt.养育,给与营养物,教养', '1. She nurtured the child as if he had been her own. 她把那个孩子当作自己的孩子来教育。 2. Most vegetables we buy in winter are nurtured in the greenhouse. 我们冬天买的大多数蔬菜都是在温室里培育的。 3. We have to care for and nurture the plant first. 我们必须先要照顾灌溉树木。 4. They are best friends and nurture each other. 他们是最好的朋友，并且相互扶持。 5. The child got his nurture from his loving parents. 这个孩子的教育来自他慈爱的双亲。', '名词: nurturer 过去式: nurtured 过去分词: nurtured 现在分词: nurturing 第三人称单数: nurtures');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tariff', '[\'tærɪf]', 'n.关税,关税表,税则,(旅馆,饭店等的)价目表、价格表;vt.课以关税', '1. Tariff barriers crimped the flow of imports. 关税障碍妨碍了进囗货的流入。 2. The government decided to impose a protective tariff on foreign cars. 政府决定对进口汽车征收保护税。 3. A copy of tariff is placed in each room of the hotel. 旅馆的每一个房间都有一份价目表。', '过去式: tariffed 过去分词: tariffed 现在分词: tariffing 第三人称单数: tariffs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pistol', '[\'pɪstl]', 'n.手枪', '1. A pistol shot rang out. 响起了手枪的声音。 2. It sounded like a small pistol going off. 那声音听起来像一支小手枪响。 3. He pushed forward the safety catch of his pistol. 他把他手枪的安全锁扣向前推了推。 4. The general came in, hipping a pistol. 将军走了进来,他的胯部佩带着一柄手枪。', '过去式: pistoled 过去分词: pistoled 现在分词: pistoling 第三人称单数: pistols');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('litter', '[\'lɪtər]', 'n.垃圾,(供动物睡眠或防冻用的)干草,树叶,(一)窝,轿,担架;vt.乱丢,铺草,弄乱;vi.产仔,乱丢垃圾', '1. There was litter strewn all over the pavement. 人行道上到处都是扔的垃圾。 2. The desk was covered with a litter of documents. 书桌上满满地放着一堆杂乱的文件。 3. His litter strewn room really needed to be cleaned. 他杂乱的房间该好好收拾一下了。 4. His dog hasn\'t had a litter of puppies. 他的狗还没有生过一窝小狗。', '名词: litterer 过去式: littered 过去分词: littered 现在分词: littering 第三人称单数: litters');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('resort', '[rɪ\'zɔːrt]', 'vi.求助,诉诸,采取(某种手段等),常去;n.凭借,手段,常去之地,胜地', '1. The island is a favorite summer resort for tourists. 这座岛是旅游者的避暑胜地。 2. Its unique natural scenery makes it an ideal holiday resort. 独具特色的自然景观,使这里成为度假休闲的理想胜地。 3. A carriage was the only resort. 乘马车是唯一的办法。 4. The resort to force is forbidden in this school. 该学校禁止动武。 5. If other means fail，we shall resort to force. 如果其他手段均失败,我们就将诉诸武力。', '过去式: resorted 过去分词: resorted 现在分词: resorting 第三人称单数: resorts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mutual', '[\'mjuːtʃuəl]', 'adj.相互的,共有的', '1. Other organizations have joined the confederation for mutual benefit. 其他组织为了共同的利益也加入了这个联盟。 2. My friend and I have mutual enthusiasm for music. 我和我的朋友对音乐有着共同的爱好。 3. Let\'s give mutual support and inspiration to each other. 让我们互相支持，互相鼓励。 4. Language differences are often a barrier to mutual understanding. 语言不同,常常阻碍到彼此的了解。', '副词: mutually 名词: mutuality');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('converge', '[kən\'vɜːrdʒ]', 'v.聚合,集中于一点;vt.会聚', '1. The roads converge just before the station. 四面八方的道路会聚在火车站前。 2. These lines converge at a certain point. 这些线集中于某一点。 3. If you look at the end of your nose, your eyes converge. 如果你看着你的鼻尖，你的两眼就向一点集中。 4. In this case the rays obviously do not converge. 此时，光线显然不会聚。', '过去式: converged 过去分词: converged 现在分词: converging 第三人称单数: converges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('criterion', '[kraɪ\'tɪriən]', 'n.(批评判断的)标准,准据,规范', '1. Practice is the sole criterion for testing truth. 实践是检验真理的唯一标准。 2. He thinks that the criterion of success is the ability to work joyfully. 他认为成功的检验标准是看能否愉快地生活。 3. We have a clear-cut criterion to go by. 我们有个可供遵循的明确标准。 4. The table shows the scoring for each criterion and criterion group. 上表显示每一准则和准则组别的评分。', '形容词: criterial 名词复数: criteria');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('residential', '[ˌrezɪ\'denʃl]', 'adj.住宅的,与居住有关的', '1. Gradually the surrounding farmland turned residential. 周围的农田渐渐变成了住宅区。 2. The residential districts were all plotted out. 住宅区都一块块地标划出来了。 3. This is an exclusive white residential area. 这是一个纯粹的白人居住区。 4. I often go on residential summer courses. 我经常去学习必须住校的暑期课程。', '副词: residentially');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('minibus', '[\'mɪnibʌs]', 'n.中客车,小型公共汽车(我国俗称面包车,乘员10人左右)', '1. Some of the children go to school in a minibus. 有些孩子乘坐小型公共汽车去上学。 2. Minibus is most popular in towns. 小面包车在城镇很吃香。 3. We will go in the minibus from Calgary. 我们将从卡尔加利乘小巴出发。', '名词复数: minibuses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('significant', '[sɪɡ\'nɪfɪkənt]', 'adj.有意义的,重大的,重要的', '1. The question under discussion is significant. 讨论中的问题是重要的。 2. Economic conditions are significant in many ways. 经济条件在许多方面都是很重要的。 3. All of us want our lives to be significant. 我们每个人都希望我们的人生是有意义的。 4. It was truly a significant conversation. 这是非常有意义的谈话。', '副词: significantly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('community', '[kə\'mjuːnəti]', 'n.公社,团体,社会,(政治)共同体,共有,一致,共同体,(生物)群落', '1. Here is a local Jewish community. 这是当地犹太人的一个社区。 2. Everyone should invest some time in community service. 每个人都应该花些时间在社区服务上。 3. Community colleges have become popular and their enrollments have increased rapidly. 社区大学日渐增多，报名人数迅速增长。 4. The international community forbids use of any chemical weapons. 国际社会禁止使用一切化学武器。', '名词复数: communities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('complain', '[kəm\'pleɪn]', 'v.抱怨,悲叹,控诉', '1. The tourist complained that the room was too dirty. 游客抱怨说房间太脏了。 2. She complained to me about his rudeness. 他向我抱怨他的卤莽。 3. He will complain to the police that I struck him. 这人要到警察局去控告我打他。 4. The patient is complaining of acute earache. 病人说耳部剧痛。', '名词: complainer 过去式: complained 过去分词: complained 现在分词: complaining 第三人称单数: complains');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('allocate', '[\'æləkeɪt]', 'vt.分派,分配', '1. The system was unable to allocate a new data object. 系统无法分派新的数据对象。 2. Allocate rations for a week - long campingtrip. 分配一星期外出野营的定额。 3. You must allocate the money carefully. 你们必须谨慎地分配钱。', '形容词: allocable 名词: allocation 过去式: allocated 过去分词: allocated 现在分词: allocating 第三人称单数: allocates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('notorious', '[noʊ\'tɔːriəs]', 'adj.声名狼籍的', '1. He is notorious for his goings-on. 他因行为不检点而声名狼藉。 2. The district is notorious for its fogs. 那地区以浓雾出名。 3. Hitler is a notorious dictator. 希特勒是一个臭名昭著的独裁者。 4. The notorious thief will be put up for trial next week. 那个臭名昭著的偷窃犯将于下周出庭受审。', '副词: notoriously 名词: notoriousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('stern', '[stɜːrn]', 'adj.严厉的,苛刻的;n.船尾', '1. He received a stern rebuke from his superior. 他受到上司的严厉斥责。 2. She had a stern father who never praised her. 她父亲很严厉，他从来没有表扬过她。 3. The teacher\'s stern look reduced him to silence. 教师神情严肃，他便静了下来。 4. He came close to the painter and looked steadfastly into his stern eyes. 他走近画家,并且死死地盯着他那目光严峻的眼睛。 5. Move your stern, I want to sit down. 你把屁股挪一挪，我想坐下。', '副词: sternly 比较级: sterner 最高级: sternest 名词: sternness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reward', '[rɪ\'wɔːrd]', 'n.报酬,奖金;vt.酬劳,奖赏', '1. An act of kindness deserves a reward. 做好事,当然要有报答。 2. By rights, half the reward should be mine. 按理说，有一半奖赏应该是我的。 3. You have received a just reward. 你已得到了应有的报酬。 4. They rewarded the winners with gifts of fruits and flowers. 他们奖给优胜者一些水果和鲜花。', '形容词: rewardable 名词: rewarder 过去式: rewarded 过去分词: rewarded 现在分词: rewarding 第三人称单数: rewards');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('leather', '[\'leðər]', 'n.皮革,皮革制品', '1. This wallet feels to me like leather. 我觉得这钱包像是皮的。 2. Leather can deteriorate in damp conditions. 皮革受潮可变质。 3. Plastic is sometimes used instead of leather. 塑胶有时可以替代皮革。 4. Our factory\'s leather products show genuine leather in its natural colors. 本厂皮制品，还我真皮本色。 5. I have a pair of leather mittens. 我有一副皮连指手套。 6. I\'d like to leather him black and blue. 我要把他揍得青一块紫一块的。', '过去式: leathered 过去分词: leathered 现在分词: leathering 第三人称单数: leathers');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('infinite', '[\'ɪnfɪnət]', 'n.无限的东西(如空间、时间),[数]无穷大;adj.无穷的,无限的,无数的,极大的', '1. The number of positive numbers is infinite. 正数的数目是无穷的。 2. Teaching little children takes infinite patience. 教幼儿需有极大的耐心。 3. It is difficult to grasp the concept of infinite space. 掌握无限空间的概念是很难的。 4. Incense can attune the finite to the Infinite. 薰香可以使有限调谐至无限。', '副词: infinitely 名词: infiniteness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cradle', '[\'kreɪdl]', 'n.摇篮,发源地,支船架;vt.将...放在摇篮内', '1. The child slept soundly in her cradle. 那孩子在摇篮里睡得很熟。 2. Life is a battle from cradle to grave . 人生是从摇篮到坟墓的一场搏斗。 3. The sea is thought to have been the cradle of life. 人们认为海洋是生命的发源地。 4. Greece was the cradle of Western civilization. 希腊是西方文明的发祥地。', '名词: cradler 过去式: cradled 过去分词: cradled 现在分词: cradling 第三人称单数: cradles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('disguise', '[dɪs\'ɡaɪz]', 'v.假装,伪装,掩饰;n.伪装', '1. She could not disguise her amusement at his mistake. 她对他的错误忍俊不禁。 2. It proved difficult to disguise his anxiety. 他的焦虑难以掩饰。 3. She disguised herself as a man, but she couldn\'t disguise her voice. 她把自己乔装成一个男子，但她改变不了自己的声音。 4. He plans to disguise himself as a policeman. 他打算把自己假扮成一个警察。 5. The supposed beggar was really a police officer in disguise. 那个众人眼中的乞丐，其实是化了装的警察。', '副词: disguisedly 名词: disguisement 过去式: disguised 过去分词: disguised 现在分词: disguising 第三人称单数: disguises');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('possess', '[pə\'zes]', 'vt.占有,拥有,持有,摆布,支配', '1. Different workers possess different skills. 不同的工作者有不同的技能。 2. Rose is a woman who possesses a rare intelligence. 罗丝是一个拥有非凡智慧的女人。 3. The police asked me if I possessed a gun. 警察问我是否有枪。 4. She was possessed by the desire to be rich. 她被致富的欲望所支配。', '名词: possessor 过去式: possessed 过去分词: possessed 现在分词: possessing 第三人称单数: possesses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('clan', '[klæn]', 'n.部落,氏族,宗族,党派', '1. They still kept traces of the clan society. 他们还保留了氏族社会的痕迹。 2. The hunter killed for the clan, not for himself. 猎手是为氏族，而不是为自己打猎。 3. They relied upon the patriarchal clan to control all or most of towns business. 他们依靠宗族的力量，控制城镇集市的全部或大部分贸易。 4. Clansmen who had achieved distinction would be eulogisedas they would bring reflected honour to their family and clan. 卓越非凡的宗族成员被视为光宗耀祖，因此会被褒扬。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('household', '[\'haʊshoʊld]', 'n.一家人,家庭,家族,王室;adj.家庭的,家族的,家属的,普通的,平常的', '1. The whole household got up early last Sunday. 上个星期天全家人都起得很早。 2. He peddled small articles around the town from household to household. 他在镇上挨家挨户兜售一些小件物品。 3. I disputed with my wife on household expenses. 我跟太太争论有关家庭费用的问题。 4. Microsoft has become a household word. 微软已经成为一个家喻户晓的名词。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('kidney', '[\'kɪdni]', 'n.肾,(动物可食用的)腰子,个性,性格', '1. Each man has a pair of kidneys. 每个人有一对肾脏。 2. Joe has also heard of kidney stones. 乔也听人提到过肾结石。 3. Those two brothers are men of the same kidney. 这两兄弟是同一类型的人。', '名词复数: kidneys');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('classical', '[\'klæsɪkl]', 'adj.古典的,正统派的,古典文学的', '1. Beethoven is regarded as one of the immortals of classical music. 贝多芬被认为是不朽的古典音乐大师。 2. Some young people like pop music, while still others like classical music. 一些年青人喜欢流行音乐，但仍有其它人喜欢古典音乐。 3. He is regarded as one of the classical composers in this century. 他被认为是本世纪第一流的作曲家之一。 4. The classical approach could be realized in at least two forms. 传统的道路被认为至少有两种形式。', '副词: classically 名词: classicality');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('exclusive', '[ɪk\'skluːsɪv]', 'adj.排外的,孤高的,唯我独尊的,独占的,唯一的,高级的', '1. He is part of an exclusive social circle and belongs to an exclusive club. 他所处的社交圈子很排外，而且参加的又是个很排外的社团。 2. The interview is exclusive to this magazine. 本杂志得到独家访问权。 3. Painting has not been her exclusive occupation. 绘画并非她唯一的职业. 4. The teacher tried to gain the students\' exclusive attention. 老师努力试着获得学生的全部注意力。 5. Everyone was surprised by the Times exclusive about the prince\' marriage. 泰晤士报关于王子大婚的独家新闻令很多人惊奇不已。', '副词: exclusively 名词: exclusiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('spouse', '[spaʊs]', 'n.配偶(指夫或妻)', '1. He never mentioned his spouse. 他从来不提自己的妻子。 2. They get free ticket for their spouse. 他们为家属领到了免费的票。 3. What is your spouse immigration status? 你配偶的移民身份是什么? 4. Your spouse\'s family are your -in-laws. 你配偶的家人是你的姻亲。', '过去式: spoused 过去分词: spoused 现在分词: spousing 第三人称单数: spouses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('liable', '[\'laɪəbl]', 'adj.有责任的,有义务的,易...的,有...倾向的,负有责任的,很有可能的', '1. He declared that he was not liable for his wife\'s debts. 他宣称对妻子的债务不负责。 2. Parents are liable forchildren\'s education. 父母应负责孩子的教育。 3. They are liable to run off with your money. 他们有卷款而走的倾向。 4. We are liable to make mistakes. 我们都易犯错误。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('grip', '[ɡrɪp]', 'vt.紧握,紧夹;n.掌握,控制,把手;v.抓住', '1. The eagle seized its prey in a tenacious grip. 鹰将捕获物紧紧抓住。 2. The child would not let go his grip on Tom. 这孩子紧紧地抓住汤姆不放。 3. He kept a firm grip on his children. 他对小孩管得很严。 4. It is a leather grip. 这是一个皮制手提包。 5. The audience were gripped by the play. 这群观众被这部戏剧吸引住了。', '副词: grippingly 名词: gripper 过去式: gripped 过去分词: gripped 现在分词: gripping 第三人称单数: grips');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('receipt', '[rɪ\'siːt]', 'n.收条,收据,收到;v.收到', '1. May I have a receipt? 我可以要一张收据吗？ 2. Please send me a receipt for the money. 请寄给我一张收到此款的收据。 3. We only take goods back if customers can produce the receipt. 顾客如能出示收据，我们才能予以退货。 4. Please give the receipt to the bearer. 收条请交来人带回。 5. His main work is to receipt for each lot of goods. 他的主要工作是给每一批货物开收据。', '过去式: receipted 过去分词: receipted 现在分词: receipting 第三人称单数: receipts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('stumble', '[\'stʌmbl]', 'v.绊倒,使困惑,蹒跚,结结巴巴地说话,踌躇;n.绊倒,错误', '1. I stumbled over a tree root. 我在一个树根上绊了一跤。 2. Any man may stumble into crime when among criminals. 同犯罪分子混在一起,任何人都可能失足犯罪。 3. Any man may stumble into crime when among criminals. 同犯罪分子混在一起,任何人都可能失足犯罪。 4. You never knew when you might stumble across some new talent. 谁也说不准什么时候会碰上一位新的天才。 5. The horse recovered itself after stumble. 马绊倒后又站起来了。', '副词: stumblingly 名词: stumbler 过去式: stumbled 过去分词: stumbled 现在分词: stumbling 第三人称单数: stumbles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('outbreak', '[\'aʊtbreɪk]', 'n.(战争的)爆发,(疾病的)发作', '1. There has been an outbreak of typhoid. 那儿正爆发伤寒。 2. The research project fetched up because of the outbreak of the war. 由于战争爆发，这个研究计划搁浅了。 3. The hospital wards were fumigated after the outbreak of typhus. 发现斑疹伤寒以后，医院的病房进行了烟熏消毒。 4. The outbreak of riot caused many people to die. 暴乱的发生使很多人丧生。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('monopoly', '[mə\'nɑːpəli]', 'n.垄断,垄断者,专利权,专利事业', '1. Liberty and monopoly cannot live together. 自由与垄断不能并存。 2. The company will become a state-owned monopoly. 这家企业将变成一家国有的垄断企业。 3. Imperialism is the monopoly stage of capitalism. 帝国主义是资本主义的垄断阶段。 4. The government has a monopoly of oil production in that country. 在那个国家，政府独占石油开采权。', '形容词: monopolistic 副词: monopolistically 名词: monopolism 名词复数: monopolies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dispose', '[dɪ\'spoʊz]', 'v.处理,处置,部署;vt.布置,安排,除去,使愿意', '1. I want to dispose of these old books. 我想处理掉这些旧书。 2. Most complaints can be disposed of pretty quickly. 大多数投诉可以很快地解决。 3. The president ruthlessly disposed of his rivals. 这位总统无情地除掉了政敌。 4. She disposed of the champion in straight sets. 她一盘未输战胜了冠军。', '名词: disposer 过去式: disposed 过去分词: disposed 现在分词: disposing 第三人称单数: disposes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('unity', '[\'juːnəti]', 'n.团结,联合,统一,一致', '1. These works, taken together, are essentially a unity. 这些作品，放在一起，基本上是一个整体。 2. The figure on the left spoils the unity of the painting. 左边的人物有损于画面的整体性。 3. He made a speech about the need for unity. 他发表了有关统一之必要的演讲。 4. They maintained only formal unity among themselves. 他们只在表面上保持一致。', '名词复数: unities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('apparatus', '[ˌæpə\'rætəs]', 'n.器械,设备,仪器', '1. The bird has specialized vocal apparatus. 这只鸟有特殊的发音器官。 2. The demonstrators set up apparatus for the experiment. 示范者安装好了实验装置。 3. The whole apparatus operates under high vacuum. 整个装置在高真空下运转。 4. The city\'s security apparatus needs reforming. 这个城市的治安机构需要改良。', '名词复数: apparatus');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('atlas', '[\'ætləs]', 'n.地图,地图集', '1. The atlas was published by our company. 这个地图集是由我们公司出版的。 2. The little box of icons at the front of the atlas helps you decipher the maps. 地图集前面的小标记说明能帮助你读懂地图的含义。', '名词复数: atlases');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('escort', '[\'eskɔːrt]', 'n.护卫(队),护送,陪同(人员),护卫队;v.护卫,护送,陪同', '1. He offered to be her escort, but she declined it. 他提出护送她，但她谢绝了。 2. The government provided an armed escort for the visiting head of State. 政府为到访的元首派出了武装卫队。 3. He is the commander in chief of this escort ,and he holds great power. 他是这艘护航舰的总指挥，权利很大。 4. The Queen\'s yacht had an escort of ten destroyers. 有十艘驱逐舰为女王的游艇护航. 5. He will escort you through the forest. 他护送你穿过森林。', '过去式: escorted 过去分词: escorted 现在分词: escorting 第三人称单数: escorts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('nasty', '[\'næsti]', 'adj.污秽的,肮脏的,令人厌恶的,淫秽的,下流的,凶相的,威胁的', '1. He is a person with a nasty mind. 他是个思想肮脏的人。 2. It\'s a tacky,nasty little movie,frankly. 坦率地说,那是一部低级下流、微不足道的影片。 3. The dog gave me a nasty nip on the leg. 那狗在我腿上狠咬了一口。 4. I was frightened when I saw the nasty gash in her arm. 她胳膊上又深又长的大伤口吓坏了我。', '副词: nastily 比较级: nastier 最高级: nastiest 名词: nastiness 名词复数: nasties');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('comply', '[kəm\'plaɪ]', 'vi.顺从,答应,遵守', '1. She was told to pay the fine, but refused to comply. 通知她交纳罚款，但她拒不服从。 2. He was willing to comply with my proposal. 他愿意顺从我的建议。 3. Everyone should comply with the law. 每个人都应该遵守法律。 4. Is it our duty to comply with his requests? 我们有义务满足他的要求吗?', '过去式: complied 过去分词: complied 现在分词: complying 第三人称单数: complies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('entrepreneur', '[ˌɑːntrəprə\'nɜːr]', 'n.<法>企业家,主办人', '1. He is a shipping entrepreneur. 他是个航运企业家。 2. The entrepreneur has become a news figure. 这位企业家变成了新闻人物。', '形容词: entrepreneurial 名词: entrepreneurialism');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('medieval', '[ˌmedi\'iːvl]', 'adj.中世纪的,仿中世纪的,老式的,<贬>原始的', '1. Knighthood was an ideal in medieval Europe. 在中世纪的欧洲，成为骑士是理想。 2. The medieval town was fortified with a high wall and a deep moat. 这座中世纪的城市周围建有城墙和护城河。 3. This church is a classic example of medieval architecture. 这座教堂是中世纪建筑风格的典型实例。 4. The gallery is a treasure trove of medieval art. 这个画廊是中世纪艺术的宝库。', '副词: medievally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('afflict', '[ə\'flɪkt]', 'vt.使痛苦,折磨', '1. I don\'t want to afflict you with my troubles. 我不想使你为我的困难而苦恼。 2. He was afflicted with cancer. 他患了癌症。 3. AIDS and cancer are maladies that afflict humanity. 爱滋病和癌症是折磨人类的疾病. 4. He will not afflict us beyond our power of endurance. 不会折磨得我们超过了承受能力的。', '形容词: afflictive 副词: afflictively 名词: afflicter 过去式: afflicted 过去分词: afflicted 现在分词: afflicting 第三人称单数: afflicts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('promote', '[prə\'moʊt]', 'vt.促进,发扬,提升,提拔,晋升为', '1. They discussed how to promote cooperation between the two countries. 他们讨论如何促进两国间的合作。 2. He has been promoted to general manager. 他已被提升为总经理。 3. He failed to get promoted for lack of resolution. 他因缺乏果断力而未能得到升迁。 4. He promoted a campaign to remind the public of protecting the wildlife. 他发起了一项旨在提醒人们保护野生动物的活动。', '形容词: promotable 名词: promotability 过去式: promoted 过去分词: promoted 现在分词: promoting 第三人称单数: promotes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('crash', '[kræʃ]', 'n.碰撞,坠落,坠毁,撞击声,爆裂声;v.碰撞,坠落,坠毁,(指商业公司,政府等)破产,垮台', '1. He crashed his car into a wall. 他的汽车撞到了墙上。 2. The rocks crashed down onto the car. 岩石轰隆一声砸在汽车上。 3. She was frightened that the plane would crash. 她害怕飞机会坠毁。 4. The plane crashed (into the mountain). 飞机撞毁(在山上)了。 5. The building fell with a crash as loud as thunder. 建筑物轰隆一声倒塌了，声如雷鸣。 6. The project was launched on a crash basis. 此计划作为最优先项目而付诸实施。', '名词: crasher 过去式: crashed 过去分词: crashed 现在分词: crashing 第三人称单数: crashes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('expand', '[ɪk\'spænd]', 'vt.使膨胀,详述,扩张;vi.张开,发展', '1. Metals expand when they are heated. 金属遇热则膨胀。 2. Would you expand upon the matter a little further? 请你再进一步谈谈这件事好吗? 3. They conferred on the best way to expand business. 他们商议扩展业务的最好方法。 4. Our foreign trade has expanded during recent years. 近年来我们的对外贸易有所增加。', '形容词: expandable 名词: expander 过去式: expanded 过去分词: expanded 现在分词: expanding 第三人称单数: expands');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tremendous', '[trə\'mendəs]', 'adj.极大的,巨大的', '1. He has a tremendous hold over his younger brother. 他对他弟弟很有影响。 2. She does her work with tremendous vigour. 她工作起来干劲十足。 3. The discovery caused a tremendous commotion in the scientific world. 那项发现在科学界引起极大的震动。 4. We got a tremendous surprise when she arrived. 她的到来使我们大吃一惊。', '副词: tremendously 名词: tremendousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ultraviolet', '[ˌʌltrə\'vaɪələt]', 'adj.紫外线的,紫外的;n.紫外线辐射', '1. The ozone layer shields the earth from the sun\'s ultraviolet rays. 臭氧层保护地球不受太阳紫外线的辐射。 2. A suncream provides adequate protection against harmful ultraviolet rays. 使用防晒霜可以保护皮肤不受紫外线的伤害。 3. Ultraviolet rays can penetrate through clouds. 紫外线可以穿透云层。 4. What are infrared and ultraviolet rays? 什么是红外线和紫外线？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('revolutionary', '[ˌrevə\'luːʃəneri]', 'adj.革命的', '1. His heart glows with revolutionary enthusiasm. 他心中充满着革命的热情。 2. The revolutionary point remained primary. 革命的观点继续占上风。 3. He styles himself a revolutionary. 他自称为革命者。 4. A revolutionary\'s life used to be beset with dangers and hardships. 一个革命者的生活中往往充满危险和艰难。', '副词: revolutionarily 名词: revolutionariness 名词复数: revolutionaries');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('communicate', '[kə\'mjuːnɪkeɪt]', 'v.沟通,通信,(房间、道路、花园等)相通,传达,感染', '1. He has communicated his wishes to me. 他已经把他的愿望告诉了我。 2. I like to communicate with my family. 我喜欢和我的家人沟通。 3. The door communicates with my room. 这门和我的房间相通。 4. Good manners are not only about the way we talk, but also about all other things we do when we communicate with other people. 好的礼节不仅仅是指我们谈话的方式,还包括我们在与别人交流时进行各种活动的处理办法与态度。', '名词: communicator 过去式: communicated 过去分词: communicated 现在分词: communicating 第三人称单数: communicates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('preference', '[\'prefrəns]', 'n.偏爱,优先选择', '1. She has a preference for blue. 她特别喜欢蓝色。 2. It\'s entirely a matter of preference. 这完全是个见仁见智的问题。 3. A polar bear has a preference for cold weather. 北极熊喜欢寒冷的天气。 4. While selecting job applicants, we usually give preference to those with some experience. 在筛选求职者的过程中,我们通常优先考虑有一定经验的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('acquire', '[ə\'kwaɪər]', 'vt.获得,学到', '1. We should try to acquire good habits. 我们应该努力养成良好的习惯。 2. He will acquire the right to permanent residency here. 他将获得这里的永久居留权。 3. We hope to acquire the knowledge in the happiness. 我们希望在快乐中获得知识。 4. One can never acquire enough experience. 经验是永远学不足的。', '形容词: acquirable 名词: acquirer 过去式: acquired 过去分词: acquired 现在分词: acquiring 第三人称单数: acquires');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('autonomy', '[ɔː\'tɑːnəmi]', 'n.自治', '1. The separatist is demanding full autonomy for their state. 分裂主义者在要求他们的州完全自治。 2. They are agitating to assert autonomy. 他们正在鼓吹实行自治。 3. The central government granted autonomy to a national minority. 中央政府对少数民族授予自治权。 4. County boroughs lose their autonomy. 自治郡失去了它们的自治权。', '名词: autonomist 名词复数: autonomies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('oxygen', '[\'ɑːksɪdʒən]', 'n.[化]氧', '1. Water contains hydrogen and oxygen. 水含有氢和氧。 2. Hydrogen and oxygen are gases. 氢和氧是气体。 3. Plants can absorb carbon dioxide and release oxygen. 植物可以吸收二氧化碳释放氧气。 4. Mars is too dry and poor in oxygen. 火星上面过于干燥，并且缺乏氧气。', '形容词: oxygenic 副词: oxygenically 简写符号: O');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sovereign', '[\'sɑːvrən]', 'n.君主,统治;adj.至高无上的,君主的,独立自主的,完全的', '1. The sovereign completely recovered from his illness. 元首完全自病中复原了。 2. No earthly sovereign can do what he pleases. 没有一个世间君王可以为所欲为。 3. A sovereign fell, bright and new, on the soft pile of the tablecloth. 一枚金镑，锃亮而崭新，落在厚实柔软的桌布上。 4. Morocco is a sovereign independent monarchy. 摩洛哥是个有主权而独立的君主国。', '副词: sovereignly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('legend', '[\'ledʒənd]', 'n.传说,伟人传,图例;联想集团，中国最大的国有品牌微机制造商之一', '1. According to the old legend, Romulus was the founder of Rome. 按照古老的传说，罗穆卢斯是古罗马的建国者。 2. This oriental legend is fascinating. 这个东方传说很吸引人。 3. The little girl is very interested in the old legend of immortal creatures. 小女孩对有关永生的精灵的古老传奇非常感兴趣。 4. He is a legend in his lifetime for his scientific discoveries. 他的科学发现使他一生成为传奇人物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('canon', '[\'kænən]', 'n.教会法教规,教规,(基督教的)正典圣经(简称正经),一个作家的真作;日本佳能公司', '1. A person specializing in canon law is respectable. 对教规有专门研究的人很值得尊敬。 2. This canon has been enacted by the church council very recently. 这项规定最近刚刚由教堂理事会颁布。 3. His behavior is against social canon. 他的行为不符合社会规范。 4. His behavior offends the canons of good manners. 他的行为冒犯了公认的礼貌规范。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('slash', '[slæʃ]', 'v.猛砍,鞭打,砍伤,大量削减,严历批评,抽打;n.猛砍,(大幅度)削减,斜线', '1. We had to slash our way through the undergrowth with sticks. 我们挥舞着木棍一路劈砍，才在密林里开出一条路，穿了过去。 2. He is slashing wildly at his opponent with a sword. 他正用剑疯狂地朝对手乱砍。 3. They\'ll break your horns and slash you with steel. 他们会打破你的号角 4. The blade slashed his leg open. 刀刃把他的腿划破了。 5. You can use a slash here. 这儿你可以用斜线号。', '名词: slasher 过去式: slashed 过去分词: slashed 现在分词: slashing 第三人称单数: slashes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('incidentally', '[ˌɪnsɪ\'dentli]', 'adv.附带地,顺便提及', '1. Her name was just incidentally mentioned at the end of the speech. 她的名字只是在讲话最后被附带地提了一下。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('authoritative', '[ə\'θɔːrəteɪtɪv]', 'adj.权威的,有权威的,命令的', '1. This is an authoritative biography. 这是一本具有权威性的传记。 2. They have not yet relinquished the childish need for an authoritative father. 他们还没有消除儿童对一个权威性的父亲的需要。 3. I make no claims that either are authoritative or independent. 我没有提出任何命令式的或者独立的权利主张。', '副词: authoritatively 名词: authoritativeness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('guardian', '[\'ɡɑːrdiən]', 'n.护卫者,保护人,监护人;adj.守护的', '1. Already, the fact that the great Cowperwood is my guardian has gotten around. 事实上，伟大的柯帕乌就是我的保护人，早在这里传遍了。 2. Before I graduated from middle school I stayed in Boston, and my guardian was a female Korean. 我中学毕业前在波士顿，我的保护人是一位女韩侨。 3. The legal guardian must act on behalf of the child. 法定监护人应该维护这个孩子的利益。 4. Your father chose to leave me your guardian. 你父亲遗命托我为你的监护人。', '名词: guardianship');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('magnificent', '[mæɡ\'nɪfɪsnt]', 'adj.华丽的,高尚的,宏伟的', '1. The magnificent sights collect a jolly crowd. 壮丽的景色引来欢乐的人群。 2. The Hungarian view is magnificent from the summit of the mountains. 从群山之颠看到的匈牙利景色非常壮丽。 3. Just look at this magnificent autumn landscape! 看看这壮丽的秋景吧！ 4. The Taj Mahal is a magnificent building. 泰姬陵是一座宏伟的建筑。', '副词: magnificently');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('purity', '[\'pjʊrəti]', 'n.纯净,纯洁,纯度', '1. We must ensure the purity of drinking water. 我们必须确保饮用水的纯净。 2. Chinese people regard lotus as an emblem of purity. 中国人把莲花看作是纯洁的象征。 3. White symbolizes purity and cleanness. 白色代表纯洁和干净。 4. It\'s a soprano of great compass and of great purity. 这是一种音域宽广，高度纯正的女高音。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('engage', '[ɪn\'ɡeɪdʒ]', 'vt.使忙碌,雇佣,预定,使从事于,使参加;vi.答应,从事,交战,[机]接合,啮合', '1. The restaurant decide to engage a pop singer. 餐馆决定雇用一名流行歌手。 2. If the big gear did not engage with the small one,the machine would refuse to work. 如果大齿轮与小齿轮不相啮合的话，机器就不会工作。 3. Our orders are to engage (the enemy) immediately. 我们的命令是立即(与敌军)开战。 4. I will engage to manage the business if you will engage to provide the capital. 如果你答应出资本，我答应经管这个生意。', '名词: engager 过去式: engaged 过去分词: engaged 现在分词: engaging 第三人称单数: engages');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('monster', '[\'mɑːnstər]', 'adj.道德(上)的,精神的;n.道德', '1. A hideous monster attacked the helpless villagers. 有个丑恶的怪物袭击了手无寸铁的村民。 2. I saw a horrible monster in the forest. 我在林中见到一头可怕的怪物。 3. The judge told the murderer that he was a monster. 法官对凶手说他是一个穷凶极恶的人。 4. He\'s a lovely man, but when he gets jealous he turns into a monster. 他是个讨人喜欢的人,但是当他嫉妒起来时,就成了一个恶魔。 5. Many monster high-rise buildings spring up all over the city. 许多巨大的高层建筑在这座城市拔地而起。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('spontaneous', '[spɑːn\'teɪniəs]', 'adj.自发的,自然产生的', '1. He is spontaneous to offer help. 他主动提供帮助。 2. It is a spontaneous cheer from the crowd. 那是群众自发的喝彩。 3. The spontaneous applause cut the singer short. 自发的掌声打断了歌唱家的演唱。 4. The eruption of volcanoes is spontaneous. 火山爆发是自然产生的。', '副词: spontaneously 名词: spontaneousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('boycott', '[\'bɔɪkɑːt]', 'n.&vt.联合抵制,联合排斥某国货物或与某国绝交', '1. He urged all citizens to boycott Korean goods. 他呼吁所有民众联手抵制韩国货。 2. We boycott all products tested on animals. 我们抵制用动物做产品实验。 3. We boycott some country because it hurts our ego. 我们抵制某国货，因为他伤了我们的面子。 4. We are determined to boycott them. 我们决定拒绝跟他们来往。', '名词: boycotter 过去式: boycotted 过去分词: boycotted 现在分词: boycotting 第三人称单数: boycotts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('scent', '[sent]', 'n.气味,香味,香水,线索,嗅觉,臭迹;vt.闻出,嗅,发觉,循着遗臭追踪,使充满气味;vi.嗅猎,发出气味', '1. The dog easily picked up the scent of the murderer. 狗毫不费力地嗅出了谋杀者的气味。 2. The scent was of leaves and turned earth. 这是树叶和新翻泥土的气味。 3. Through the window I caught the scent of syringa. 从窗口我闻到紫丁香的香味。 4. His nostrils dilated with the scent of the air. 他的鼻孔因为空气中的香味而张大了。 5. The dog scented a rat. 那狗嗅出有老鼠的气味。', '形容词: scentless 过去式: scented 过去分词: scented 现在分词: scenting 第三人称单数: scents');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('nominate', '[\'nɑːmɪneɪt]', 'vt.提名,推荐,任命,命名', '1. I nominate Bill for the club president. 我提名比尔为俱乐部主席候选人。 2. Only students may nominate someone for the award. 只有学生才可以提名一些教师去拿这个奖项。 3. The board nominated him as the new director. 董事会指定他为新董事。', '名词: nominator 过去式: nominated 过去分词: nominated 现在分词: nominating 第三人称单数: nominates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('indignation', '[ˌɪndɪɡ\'neɪʃn]', 'n.愤慨,义愤', '1. He could scarcely keep in his indignation. 他愤怒得难以自持。 2. Moral indignation is jealousy with a halo. 道德上的愤怒是萦绕着光环的嫉妒。 3. The atrocity caused widespread indignation. 那暴行引起了普遍的愤慨。 4. Such a humiliation filled me with indignation. 这种污辱使我感到极其愤慨。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('shrewd', '[ʃruːd]', 'adj.精明', '1. Her brother is a shrewd businessman. 她兄弟是个精明的生意人。 2. It was a shrewd assessment and probably pretty close to the truth. 这个评估很有道理，可能相当正确。 3. He\'s an artist, a scientist and a shrewd businessman (all) rolled into one. 他既是艺术家，又是科学家，同时还是个精明的生意人。 4. His skill in negotiating earned him a reputation as a shrewd tactician. 他的谈判技巧使他赢得了精明战略家的名声。', '副词: shrewdly 比较级: shrewder 最高级: shrewdest');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('combat', '[\'kɑːmbæt]', 'n.战斗,格斗;v.战斗,搏斗,抗击', '1. The fighter planes quickly disengaged from the combat. 歼击机很快从战斗中撤出了。 2. He is stuck in the combat against this problem. 他在解决这个难题的过程中遇到了障碍。 3. The nation will combat all invaders. 这个民族将同所有的入侵者战斗。 4. The ship is combating the wind and waves. 那只船正与风浪搏斗。 5. The soldiers are ready to fly the 50 combat mission. 战士们已经准备好了执行第50号战斗任务。', '过去式: combated/combatted 过去分词: combated/combatted 现在分词: combating/combatting 第三人称单数: combats/combats');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('radius', '[\'reɪdiəs]', 'n.半径,范围,辐射光线,有效航程,范围,界限', '1. Nobody is allowed to enter the operation radius. 不允许任何人进入工作半径范围以内。 2. What is the radius of this circle? 这个圆的半径有多长? 3. We can compute the circular area with radius. 我们能用半径计算出圆的面积。 4. The radius expands markedly at its lower end. 桡骨下端明显扩张。', '名词复数: radii');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rectangular', '[rek\'tæŋɡjələ(r)]', 'adj.矩形的,成直角的', '1. We have rectangular plates,square plates, triangular plates and oval plates. 我们有矩形的盘和正方形的盘，还有三角形的盘,还有椭圆盘。 2. I put a rectangular box on the table. 我把一个长方形的盒子放在桌子上。 3. We have a rectangular playground in our school. 我们学校有一个长方形的操场。 4. The equations are written in rectangular coordinates. 这些方程是在直角座标系中写出的。', '副词: rectangularly 名词: rectangularity');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('peg', '[peɡ]', 'n.钉,栓,桩,销子,借口;vt.钉木钉,固定,限制;vi.坚持不懈地工作', '1. He hung his coat on the wooden peg. 他把上衣挂在木钉上。 2. First hammer the tent pegs into the ground, then tie the ropes onto them. 先把系帐篷的桩子打进地里，再把绳子系在桩子上。 3. Whatever, I needed to find a peg to stay at home. 我无论如何要想个借口留在“家”里。 4. He had not a peg to hang on and got dumb for some time. 他一点借口也找不出来,楞在那儿好一会儿。 5. We pegged the tent to the ground. 我们用木桩把帐篷固定到地面上了。 6. We pegged away until our luck turned. 我们一直坚持干下去直到我们时来运转。', '过去式: pegged 过去分词: pegged 现在分词: pegging 第三人称单数: pegs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('constant', '[\'kɑːnstənt]', 'n.[数、物]常数,恒量;adj.不变的,持续的,坚决的', '1. In our world nothing seems constant. 在我们这个世界上似乎没有东西是永恒不变的。 2. The birth rate in this city is almost constant. 这城市的出生率几乎是不变的。 3. The machinery requires constant maintenance. 这些机器需要经常保养维修。 4. The constant friction between the young couple finally caused divorce. 小夫妻俩之间经常的冲突终于导致了离婚。 5. The speed of light is an important constant. 光速是一个重要的常数。', '副词: constantly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('arrogant', '[\'ærəɡənt]', 'adj.傲慢的,自大的', '1. One should never be arrogant even when he is at his best. 一个人在最得意时也不应傲慢。 2. Well as he does in study, he is not arrogant. 虽然他功课很好，却一点都不傲慢。 3. It\'s arrogant of you to say that. 你竟然那样说，未免太自大了。 4. He is an arrogant man. 他是一个自高自大的人。', '副词: arrogantly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('shuttle', '[\'ʃʌtl]', 'n.往返汽车(列车、飞机),航天飞机,梭子,穿梭;v.穿梭往返', '1. The shuttle flies back and forth on the loom. 织布机上梭子来回飞动。 2. He refined the whole art of shuttle diplomacy. 他把穿梭外交艺术提高到炉火纯青的地步。 3. There is a shuttle service between the city center and the air station. 在市中心和飞机场之间有往返的穿梭运行班车。 4. The U.S. made the first space shuttle in the world. 美国制造了世界上第一架航天飞机。 5. We shuttled the passengers to the city center by helicopter. 我们来来回回地用直升机把旅客运送到市中心。', '名词: shuttler 过去式: shuttled 过去分词: shuttled 现在分词: shuttling 第三人称单数: shuttles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('lash', '[læʃ]', 'n.鞭子,鞭打,睫毛,责骂,讽刺;vt.鞭打,摆动,扎捆,冲击,煽动,讽刺;vi.猛击,急速甩动', '1. By rod and lash, the boy was punished. 木棍和鞭子用来惩罚这个男孩。 2. The pirate captain beat his crew with a lash. 海盗船长用鞭子抽打他的船员。 3. With a lash of its tail the tiger leaped at her. 老虎把尾巴一甩朝她扑过来。 4. Does the Lash Extender come in other colors apart from black ? 睫毛增长液除黑色外，还有什么其它颜色？ 5. He began to lash Luke unmercifully across buttocks and thighs. 他开始无情地鞭打卢克的屁股和大腿。', '过去式: lashed 过去分词: lashed 现在分词: lashing 第三人称单数: lashes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('threshold', '[\'θreʃhoʊld]', 'n.开始,开端,极限', '1. The cabin has a flat stone for a threshold. 这间小屋用一条扁平的石头做门槛。 2. The treaty will be the threshold of lasting peace. 这个条约将成为持久和平的开端。 3. He was on the threshold of his career. 他的事业刚刚起步。 4. The tax threshold for a pensioner is $6,000. 领退休金的人的纳税起点是六千美元。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fatigue', '[fə\'tiːɡ]', 'n.疲乏,疲劳,累活,[军]杂役;vt.使疲劳,使心智衰弱;vi.疲劳', '1. She hoped to sleep off her fatigue. 她希望睡一觉之后会消除疲劳。 2. The aeroplane wing showed signs of metal fatigue. 机翼显出有金属疲劳的现象。 3. He was beaten out with fatigue when he got home. 他回到家里时已是疲惫不堪。 4. Who is on fatigue duty today? 今天谁担任杂役? 5. The patient fatigues easily. 病人容易疲劳。 6. They were shedding their fatigue. 身上疲劳的感觉渐渐都消失了。', '过去式: fatigued 过去分词: fatigued 现在分词: fatiguing 第三人称单数: fatigues');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('valve', '[vælv]', 'n.阀,[英]电子管,真空管', '1. The valve of the heart allows the blood to pass in one direction only. 心脏的瓣膜使血液只能朝一个方向流动 2. We need a valve detector. 我们需要个真空管检波器。 3. The pump sucks air out (of the vessel) through this valve. 这台泵通过这个阀门把(容器中的)空气抽出。 4. We need an eye bolt to fit this valve. 我们需要一个有眼螺栓来固定这个阀门。', '形容词: valveless 过去式: valved 过去分词: valved 现在分词: valving 第三人称单数: valves');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('confine', '[kən\'faɪn]', 'vt.限制,禁闭;n.界限,边界', '1. I wish the speaker would confine himself to the subject. 我希望演说者不要离题。 2. I am sick, I have to confine to bed. 我病了，我得卧床休息。 3. The thief was confined in a prison. 窃贼被关押在监狱里。 4. Is it cruel to confine a bird in a cage? 把鸟关在笼子里残忍不残忍? 5. This is outside the confines of human knowledge. 这超出了人类知识范畴。', '形容词: confinable 名词: confiner 过去式: confined 过去分词: confined 现在分词: confining 第三人称单数: confines');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('toll', '[toʊl]', 'n.通行税(费),费,代价,钟声;vt.征收,敲钟,鸣(钟)(特指宣布死亡),勾引,引诱;vi.征税,鸣钟', '1. The death toll mounted (to 100). 死亡人数上升(至100). 2. The government tried to keep the death toll at a lower level. 政府力图将死亡人数控制在较低标准。 3. We heard the toll of the church bells. 我们听到了教堂大钟传来的钟声。 4. When you hear the bells toll, you\'ll know I\'m not far. 当你听到钟声，就说明我已经在附近了。 5. The church bell tolled the hour. 教堂的鸣钟报时。', '过去式: tolled 过去分词: tolled 现在分词: tolling 第三人称单数: tolls');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('recruit', '[rɪ\'kruːt]', 'n.新兵,新分子,新会员;vt.使恢复,补充,征募;vi.征募新兵,复原', '1. We are having difficulties in recruiting well-qualified staff. 我们难以招募到素质好的职员。 2. His job was to recruit for the army. 他的工作是为陆军募兵。 3. We lower the standards in order to recruit real talents. 我们降低标准是为了招纳真正的人才。 4. This job presents many difficulties to the new recruit. 这件工作对那个新手来说困难重重。', '名词: recruiter 过去式: recruited 过去分词: recruited 现在分词: recruiting 第三人称单数: recruits');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('compare', '[kəm\'per]', 'v.比较,相比,比喻n.比较', '1. I compared the copy with the original, but there was not much difference. 我比较了复印件和原件，但是差别不是很大。 2. The police compared the suspect\'s fingerprints with those found at the crime scene. 警察将嫌疑犯的指纹和犯罪现场的指纹进行了对比。 3. Life is poetically compared to the morning dew. 在诗歌中，人生被比喻为朝露。 4. She is lovely beyond compare. 她真是可爱得无与伦比。', '名词: comparer 过去式: compared 过去分词: compared 现在分词: comparing 第三人称单数: compares');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('offspring', '[\'ɔːfsprɪŋ]', 'n.(单复数同形)儿女,子孙,后代,产物', '1. His offspring are diligent and intelligent. 他的后代既勤奋又聪明。 2. The hybrid offspring of a zebra and a horse. 杂交斑马斑马与马杂交的后代 3. His offspring inherit the estate. 他的孩子继承了房地产。 4. How do parents pass genes on to their offspring? 父母是怎样把基因遗传给自己的子女的？', '名词复数: offspring');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('revolve', '[rɪ\'vɑːlv]', 'v.(使)旋转,考虑,循环出现', '1. The wheels began to revolve slowly. 车轮开始慢慢转动。 2. Their troubles revolve around money management. 他们的麻烦围绕在金钱处理上。 3. We must revolve the problem before giving an answer. 我们必须在回答之前把问题仔细考虑一下。 4. My life revolves around my job. 我的工作是我生活的中心。', '形容词: revolvable 过去式: revolved 过去分词: revolved 现在分词: revolving 第三人称单数: revolves');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('muscular', '[\'mʌskjələr]', 'adj.肌肉的,强健的', '1. In order to climb hills, muscular power is another key trait. 为了爬坡，肌肉的力量是另一种关键特性。 2. Eucalyptus oil is good for easing muscular aches and pains. 桉树油可以很好地缓解肌肉的疼痛。 3. The rib cage is moderately sprung and extends back to a short and muscular loin. 肋骨适度撑起，向后延伸到短而肌肉发达的腰部。 4. Her gaze rested for a moment on the muscular neck,heavy corded,almost bull-like,bronzed by the sun,spilling over with rugged health and strength. 她的目光在那肌肉发达的脖子上停留了片刻，那脖子被太阳晒成了青铜色，筋位突出，洋溢着粗糙的健康与强力，几乎像公牛。', '副词: muscularly 名词: muscularity');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('expert', '[\'ekspɜːrt]', 'n.专家,行家,[军](特等)射手;adj.老练的,内行的,专门的;vt.在...中当行家,当专家', '1. She is a reputable expert. 她是个有声望的专家。 2. According to expert opinions, they gave up the experiment immediately. 根据专家们的意见，他们马上放弃了这项试验。 3. He is an expert in unarmed combat. 他是徒手格斗的能手。 4. The surgeon cut away the tumour with expert skill. 外科大夫用熟练的技术把肿瘤切去。', '副词: expertly 名词: expertness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('distinct', '[dɪ\'stɪŋkt]', 'adj.清楚的,明显的,截然不同的,独特的', '1. There is a distinct possibility that she\'ll be your teacher next term. 她下学期当你们的老师的可能性非常大。 2. On the contrary, he was looking at Harry with distinct pride. 相反,他望着哈利的目光中带着明显的自豪。 3. There\'s a distinct smell of cigarettes every time he comes into the room. 他每次进房间,都带着一股浓重的烟味。 4. Two people may both dream of the other,and find that their dreams had a distinct connection. 两个人可能互相梦见对方,而且发现他们的梦有着清晰的联系。', '副词: distinctly 名词: distinctness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('theft', '[θeft]', 'n.偷,行窃,偷窃的事例,偷窃行为', '1. Avarice drove him into theft. 贪婪驱使他偷窃。 2. The building has been insured against fire and theft. 这座大楼保了火险和失窃险。 3. The prosecutor brought an accusation of theft against him. 检察官指控他偷窃。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('eloquent', '[\'eləkwənt]', 'adj.雄辩的,有口才的,动人的,意味深长的', '1. He addressed the audience in an eloquent speech. 他向听众发表了雄辩的演说。 2. Eloquent elephants telephoned other eloquent elephants. 雄辩的大象打电话给其他雄辩的大象。 3. Such an eloquent man will easily talk us down. 这样一个有口才的人很容易把我们驳得无话说。 4. An eloquent speaker is one skilled in the use of words. 有口才的人善于用词。', '副词: eloquently 名词: eloquentness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('overlook', '[ˌoʊvər\'lʊk]', 'vt.俯瞰,耸出,远眺,没注意到;n.眺望,俯瞰中的景色', '1. My room overlooked the garden. 我的房间俯瞰花园。 2. We overlook the church from our house. 我们可从家中俯瞰教堂。 3. My room overlooks the sea. 从我的房间可眺望大海。 4. He overlooked a spelling error on the first page. 他没有看出第一页中有个拼写错误。 5. It was a slight overlook on my part. 这是我的小疏忽。', '过去式: overlooked 过去分词: overlooked 现在分词: overlooking 第三人称单数: overlooks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('arouse', '[ə\'raʊz]', 'vt.唤醒,唤起,鼓励,引起;vi.睡醒', '1. It took her some time to arouse her husband. 她费了好一会儿才把丈夫叫醒。 2. Diana aroused them just before dawn. 戴安娜在黎明前唤醒了他们。 3. He fell into a sound sleep, don\'t arouse him. 他睡熟了，别唤醒他。 4. The slogan was designd to arouse the people. 该标语是为唤醒国民而拟定的。', '名词: arousal 过去式: aroused 过去分词: aroused 现在分词: arousing 第三人称单数: arouses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('wallet', '[\'wɑːlɪt]', 'n.皮夹,钱夹,钓鱼带', '1. She placed the receipt in her wallet. 她把收条放到皮夹子里了。 2. I lost my wallet yesterday. 我昨天丢了钱包。 3. My wallet has disappeared from the table. 我放在桌子上的钱包不见了。 4. The wallet was just under his nose, but he didn\'t see it. 钱包就在他眼前，可他没看见。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('creation', '[kri\'eɪʃn]', 'n.创造,创作物', '1. The creation of life remains a mystery. 生命的创造仍是个谜。 2. Job creation has become an imperative for the government. 创造就业机会是政府必须做的事。 3. Life is the source of literary creation. 生活是文学创作的源泉。', '形容词: creational');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('represent', '[ˌreprɪ\'zent]', 'vt.表现,描绘,声称,象征,扮演,回忆,再赠送,再上演;vi.提出异议', '1. Monsters in dreams often represent fears. 怪物在梦里经常表现为恐惧。 2. Both represent the triumph of passion over reason. 两者都表现出理智之外的激情。 3. Dotted arrows represent flow of information. 虚矢线表示信息流程。 4. You must represent your complaints to Head Office. 你必须向总部表示出你的抱怨。', '形容词: representable 名词: representability 过去式: represented 过去分词: represented 现在分词: representing 第三人称单数: represents');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('literary', '[lɪtəreri]', 'adj.文学(上)的,从事写作的,文艺的,精通文学的,书本的', '1. He is endowed with literary talent. 他有文学天分。 2. Dickens\' A Tale of Two Cities is a literary classic. 狄更斯的《双城记》是文学名著。 3. I don\'t like to read his literary criticism. 我不喜欢读他的文学批评。 4. Her poetry is full of obscure literary allusions. 他的诗里用了很多晦涩的文学典故。', '副词: literarily 名词: literariness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('toxic', '[\'tɑːksɪk]', 'adj.有毒的,中毒的', '1. The factory had been sending out toxic fumes. 这家工厂一直在排放有毒的废气。 2. The toxic gas is extremely dangerous. 有毒的汽体是非常地危险的。 3. Too much toxic waste is being dumped at sea. 太多的有毒废料在向大海里倾倒。', '副词: toxically 名词: toxin');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('depict', '[dɪ\'pɪkt]', 'vt.描述,描写', '1. Her novel depicts life in modern London. 她的小说描写的是伦敦现代的生活。 2. The book depicts him as a rather unpleasant character. 这本书把他刻画成一个相当令人讨厌的人物。 3. This painting depicts the birth of Venus. 这幅画描绘的是维纳斯的诞生。 4. It\'s a picture depicting him as a clown. 这是一幅把他画成小丑的画。', '名词: depiction 过去式: depicted 过去分词: depicted 现在分词: depicting 第三人称单数: depicts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('solemn', '[\'sɑːləm]', 'adj.庄严的,隆重的,严肃的', '1. The ceremony proceeded in a solemn atmosphere. 仪式在庄严的气氛中进行。 2. They watched the solemn ceremony. 他们观看那庄严的仪式。 3. He looked at her with a solemn expression. 他表情严肃地望着她。 4. Her solemn face told them that the news was bad. 她严肃的表情告诉他们那是坏消息。', '副词: solemnly 名词: solemnness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ethnic', '[\'eθnɪk]', 'adj.人种的,种族的,异教徒的', '1. Canada is a multicultural country. Regardless of your ethnic origin, you will feel at home in Canada; 加拿大是一个多元文化国家,无论你为何种族,在加拿大你都会感到安适; 2. Along the way, tourists can see the Tujia ethnic minorities tilling the land. 沿着这条路,旅游者可以看到土家族的人在耕地。 3. That\'s why you can find almost every kind of ethnic food in America. 那也就是为什么在美国你几乎可以看到所有不同民族的食物。 4. Now all the 55 ethnic minorities have their own college students,and some even are master\'s and doctor\'s degree holders. 目前，55个少数民族都有了本民族的大学生，有的还有了硕士生和博士生。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('wrench', '[rentʃ]', 'n.扳钳,扳手,猛扭,痛苦,扭伤,歪曲;vt.猛扭,使扭伤,曲解,抢,折磨;vi.猛扭,绞痛', '1. It\'s hard to get at the spark plug without a proper wrench. 没有一把合适的扳钳，要抓住那个火花塞是困难的。 2. The knob broke off when he gave it a sudden wrench. 当他突然扭了一下球形把手，它便断了。 3. Leaving home was a terrible wrench for him. 他觉得离开家十分痛苦。 4. She couldn\'t stand the wrench of departure. 她受不了离别的痛苦。 5. Be careful. Don\'t wrench yourself. 小心点，别扭伤了。 6. I had to wrench the lid off the bottle. 我只好把瓶盖拧开。', '副词: wrenchingly 过去式: wrenched 过去分词: wrenched 现在分词: wrenching 第三人称单数: wrenches');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('current', '[\'kɜːrənt]', 'adj.当前的,通用的,流通的,现在的,草写的,最近的;n.涌流,趋势,电流,水流,气流', '1. Nothing disturbs the peaceful current of life in the village. 没有任何事干扰村里一向平静的生活. 2. The block becomes magnetic when the current is switched on. 通电时线圈即具磁性。 3. The current is deep and strong down the stream. 下游的水又深又急。 4. The current trend is towards informal clothing. 目前的趋势是穿着比较随便。', '副词: currently 名词: currentness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('exhibit', '[ɪɡ\'zɪbɪt]', 'vt.展出,陈列;n.展览品,陈列品,展品;v.展示', '1. Many unearthed cultural relics were exhibited at the museum. 博物馆展出了许多出土文物。 2. He was given a whole room to exhibit his paintings. 整个房间用来展览他的画作。 3. She exhibited great powers of endurance during the climb. 她在攀登过程中表现出极大的耐力。 4. They deprecated the new exhibit. 他们很不赞成新展品。', '形容词: exhibitory 名词: exhibitor 过去式: exhibited 过去分词: exhibited 现在分词: exhibiting 第三人称单数: exhibits');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('unique', '[ju\'niːk]', 'adj.唯一的,独特的', '1. He occupies a unique place in English literature. 他在英国文学中占有独特的地位。 2. The elephant\'s trunk is a unique form of appendage. 象的鼻子是一种独特的附肢。 3. It\'s a unique work of art. 这是独一无二的艺术作品。 4. The custom is unique to the region. 这种风俗是这一地区特有的。', '副词: uniquely 名词: uniqueness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('multiply', '[\'mʌltɪplaɪ]', 'v.繁殖,乘,增加', '1. If you multiply four by five, the answer is twenty. 四乘以五,答案是二十。 2. Let us multiply the height by the width to determine the area. 用宽乘以高来确定面积。 3. This will multiply our chances of success. 这将增加我们成功的机会。 4. He managed to multiply his profits. 他成功地增加了利润。 5. He learned to multiply at the age of five. 他五岁学会做乘法。', '过去式: multiplied 过去分词: multiplied 现在分词: multiplying 第三人称单数: multiplies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('imperial', '[ɪm\'pɪriəl]', 'adj.皇帝的', '1. Imperial sovereignty rests on a mixed constitution. 帝国的主权基于一种复杂的构成。 2. There are many ways to get to the imperial Theater. 到帝国戏院有很多条路。 3. The Palace Museum is the imperial palace of ancient Chinese emperors. 故宫是中国古代皇帝的皇宫。 4. Imperial gardens occupy large areas. 皇家园林占地很广。 5. An imperial edict is a writ in the name of an emperor. 诏书是以皇帝名义发布指令的专用文书。', '副词: imperially');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('offensive', '[ə\'fensɪv]', 'adj.讨厌的,无礼的,攻击性的;n.进攻,攻势', '1. His hasty temper made him offensive. 他急躁的脾气使他令人讨厌。 2. His remarks were rather offensive. 他的话非常无礼。 3. The boss kicked him out for an offensive remark. 老板因为他说了一句冒犯的话就把他开除了。 4. She has been greatly annoyed by his offensive remarks. 他出言不逊,这使她很反感。 5. In meetings she always takes the offensive before she can be criticized. 在会上，她不等别人批评她而总是先发制人。', '副词: offensively 名词: offensiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('recover', '[rɪ\'kʌvər]', 'vt.重新获得,恢复,使改过;vi.痊愈,复原,胜诉;n.DOS命令:从含有损坏磁盘扇区的磁盘上恢复文件', '1. He\'s now fully recovered from his stroke. 他现已从中风病完全康复了。 2. He is very ill and unlikely to recover. 他病得非常厉害，不大可能恢复健康了。 3. I nearly fell but managed to recover myself. 我差一点倒下,但最后还是站稳了脚根。 4. I sat down to recover from my agitation. 我坐下以使自己平静下来。', '形容词: recoverable 名词: recoverer 过去式: recovered 过去分词: recovered 现在分词: recovering 第三人称单数: recovers');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('furious', '[\'fjʊriəs]', 'adj.狂怒的,狂暴的,激烈的,热烈兴奋的,极为激烈', '1. I was annoyed, indeed furious, over what happened. 出了这件事我很不痛快,实际上是愤怒至极。 2. If this news ever reaches her ears, she\'ll be furious. 这个消息万一传到她的耳朵里，她一定得大发雷霆。 3. She maintained a calm exterior, though really she was furious. 在外表上她保持着平静，但实际上她生气极了。 4. After receiving the insulting letter, he became furious. 他收到辱骂信后怒不可遏。', '副词: furiously');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('communication', '[kəˌmjuːnɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.传达,信息,交通,通讯', '1. Most important of all, computers create wide communication around the world. 最重要的是,计算机在世界范围内建立了广泛的交流。 2. Being able to hold a conversation does not necessarily mean having effective communication. 能够对话并不意味着在进行有效的交流。 3. This area has not been covered by the communication net. 这个地区还不在通讯网的覆盖之内。 4. The beach life-guards usually flag one another for communication. 海滨救生员通常用旗号传达讯息。', '形容词: communicational');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('relish', '[\'relɪʃ]', 'n.意味', '1. Take each day and relish each moment. 认真过每一天并且好好享受每一时刻。 2. He seemed to relish the scandal. 他似乎对这件丑闻十分欣赏。 3. Take a moment and relish this with me! Soon all will be revealed! 和我一起品味这份经历吧！很快一切都会浮出水面！ 4. His wife won\'t relish having to wash all those dishes. 他的妻子不会喜欢洗这一大堆碟子的。 5. He drank up the wine with relish. 他津津有味地把酒喝光了。', '过去式: relished 过去分词: relished 现在分词: relishing 第三人称单数: relishes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('aviation', '[ˌeɪvi\'eɪʃn]', 'n.飞行,航空,航空学,航空术', '1. He devoted all his life to China\'s aviation. 他的一生都奉献给了中国的航空事业。 2. At that time aviation was still in its infancy. 当时航空仍在萌芽阶段。 3. Jets are a new development in aviation. 喷气式飞机是航空事业上的一个新成就。 4. In old China,there was hardly any machine- building industry,to say nothing of automobile and aviation industries. 旧中国几乎没有机器制造业，更不用说汽车制造业和飞机制造业了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('detain', '[dɪ\'teɪn]', 'v.拘留,留住,阻止', '1. You cannot detain the eagle in the forest. 你没有法子将一只老鹰扣留在森林里。 2. We shall have to detain him and question him. 我们只好把他扣起来，讯问他一下。 3. Allow me to detain you for a moment. 请允许我耽搁你一会儿。 4. This matter isn\'t very important, and shouldn\'t detain us very long. 这事不很重要，不该耽搁我们很久。', '名词: detainment 过去式: detained 过去分词: detained 现在分词: detaining 第三人称单数: detains');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reluctant', '[rɪ\'lʌktənt]', 'adj.不顾的,勉强的,难得到的,难处理的', '1. They were very reluctant to help. 他们不大愿意帮忙。 2. I was reluctant to do over the stitching in the dress. 我不愿意把衣服上的线脚拆了重缝。 3. By 1982 they had become reluctant to extend new loans to public borrowers. 到1982年，他们已不愿向公共借贷者发放新的贷款。 4. Margaret gave him a reluctant consent. 玛格丽特勉强答应了他。', '副词: reluctantly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('expansion', '[ɪk\'spænʃn]', 'n.扩充,开展,膨胀,扩张物,辽阔,浩瀚', '1. Metals undergo expansion when heated. 金属加热时会膨胀。 2. The thermostat is based on the fact that different metals have different coefficients of expansion. 恒温器是以不同的金属有不同的膨胀系数这一事实为根据的。 3. His economic policies paved the way for industrial expansion. 他的经济政策为工业的扩展铺平了道路。 4. The time has come for the firm to consolidate after several years of rapid expansion. 公司经过几年的迅速发展之後，该整顿一下了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cocktail', '[\'kɑːkteɪl]', 'n.鸡尾酒,(第一道用杯盛的)开味食品;adj.鸡尾酒的', '1. Would you care for a cocktail or wine? 你喜欢鸡尾酒还是葡萄酒？ 2. I have no idea about Chinese cocktail. 我对中国式鸡尾酒不太了解。 3. The cocktail sharpens his appetite. 鸡尾酒刺激他的食欲。 4. I never use a single worm on the hook, preferring a cocktail of worm and maggot. 我从不单用一只虫作钓饵,而喜欢用虫和蛆的混合物。 5. Stocks of northern shrimp, the essential ingredient in the ubiquitous prawn cocktail, could be badly affected if ocean temperatures rise. 北方对虾的数量，虾鸡尾酒的主要成分，可能因为海洋温度升高而遭受很坏的影响。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('heritage', '[\'herɪtɪdʒ]', 'n.遗产,继承权,传统', '1. One of the glories of the British heritage is the right to a fair trial. 英国人引以自豪的传统之一是有获得公正审判的权利。 2. A novelist must be able to use the cultural heritage of his nation. 小说家要善于利用他本国的文化遗产。 3. These beautiful old palaces are part of our national heritage. 这些美丽的古老宫殿是我们民族遗产的一部分。 4. It is the heritage of all human beings. 这都是整个人类继承的东西', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('disgust', '[dɪs\'ɡʌst]', 'n.厌恶,嫌恶;vi.令人厌恶,令人反感;vt.使作呕', '1. She turned away in disgust. 她厌恶地转过脸去。 2. His behavior filled her with disgust. 她对他的行为充满了厌恶。 3. He returned downstairs in disgust. 他厌恶地转身下楼。 4. I can only feel disgust for these criminals. 对这些罪犯我只感到憎恶。 5. His ideas disgust me; they are terrible. 他的一些想法使我很反感，它们实在是太可怕了。', '过去式: disgusted 过去分词: disgusted 现在分词: disgusting 第三人称单数: disgusts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('refute', '[rɪ\'fjuːt]', 'vt.驳倒,反驳', '1. As for the Flat Earth theory, I believe I could refute it. 至于地平学说，我相信我能驳斥它。 2. Historical facts refute such a fallacy. 历史事实驳斥了这种谎言。 3. He had hardly finished when someone rose to refute his points. 他还没全说完，就有人起来反驳他的论点。 4. Nothing could refute her testimony that the driver was drunk. 她关于那个司机已经喝醉的证词无可辩驳。', '形容词: refutable 副词: refutably 名词: refutability 过去式: refuted 过去分词: refuted 现在分词: refuting 第三人称单数: refutes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tentative', '[\'tentətɪv]', 'n.试验,假设;adj.试验性的,试探的,尝试的,暂定的', '1. He still held a tentative relationship with Mary. 他还和玛丽保持着若即若离的关系。 2. Could we make a tentative appointment for Friday? 我们能暂时先约在星期五吗? 3. We\'ve drawn up a tentative program for the next two weeks. 我们制定了一个之后两个星期的试探性计划。 4. Each step he took was slightly tentative. 他每走一步都有些迟疑不决。', '副词: tentatively 名词: tentativeness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('doom', '[duːm]', 'n.厄运,毁灭,死亡,世末日;v.注定,判决;著名的3D动作游戏', '1. The dictator met his doom after ten years of rule. 独裁者统治了十年终於完蛋了。 2. The slightest miscalculations in trajectory can spell doom for a successful space mission . 对轨道的细小的计算错误可以意味着对成功的太空任务的灭顶之灾。 3. She had then offered him the chance to baffle his doom. 当时她向他提供战胜厄运的机会。 4. The doom which I have passed upon her is irrevocable 我对她下的判决是不能挽回的。 5. Everyone is doomed to die. 每个人都是注定要死的。', '过去式: doomed 过去分词: doomed 现在分词: dooming 第三人称单数: dooms');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('venture', '[\'ventʃər]', 'n.冒险,投机,风险;v.冒险,冒昧,斗胆,胆敢(谦语)', '1. All our hopes rested upon this venture. 我们所有的希望都寄托在这次冒险上了。 2. These foreigners have put forward a proposal for a joint venture. 这些外国人提出了一个合资企业的建议。 3. The hi-tech industry attracts much venture capital. 高科技产业吸引着许多风险投资。 4. Any business venture contains an element of risk. 任何商业投资都包含一定的风险因素。 5. Don\'t venture into the jungle without a guide 如果没有向导,就不要冒险到森林里去。', '名词: venturer 过去式: ventured 过去分词: ventured 现在分词: venturing 第三人称单数: ventures');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('latent', '[\'leɪtnt]', 'adj.潜在的,潜伏的,隐藏的;n.隐约的指印', '1. He was infected with a latent infection. 他被感染了一种潜伏性的传染病。 2. We must take measures to control the latent disease germs. 我们必须采取措施控制潜伏的病菌。 3. Within everyone there was a latent volcano of unhappiness and discontent. 在每个人心中都有一座潜伏着不幸福与不满的火山。 4. The latent cause of crime is often avarice. 贫婪常是犯罪的潜在诱因。', '副词: latently');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('adjust', '[ə\'dʒʌst]', 'vt.调整,调节,校准,使适合', '1. Could you teach me how to adjust the iris of the camera? 你能教我怎么调照相机的光圈吗？ 2. This kind of desk can be adjusted to the height you need. 这种书桌的高低可以按照你的需要调节。 3. He can\'t adjust himself to the whirl of modern life in this big city. 他无法适应这个大都市的现代生活的忙碌。 4. Over the years, we all learned to adjust, to become more comfortable with each other, and to adapt to our new family arrangement. 年复一年，我们都学会了调整自己，学会了彼此宽容，学会了适应我们新的家庭规则。', '形容词: adjustable 副词: adjustably 名词: adjuster 过去式: adjusted 过去分词: adjusted 现在分词: adjusting 第三人称单数: adjusts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('character', '[\'kærəktər]', 'n.(事物的)特性,性质,特征(的总和),(人的)品质,字符,性格,特征,人物;vt.写,刻,印,使具有特征', '1. The boy has a strong character. 这孩子个性很强。 2. He is remembered for the nobility of his character. 他因品质高尚而被人怀念。 3. We need only keep track of the last marked character. 我们只要记住最后标记的字符。 4. I never saw a character so thoroughly hit off . 我从没看见过一个人物被描写得如此淋漓尽致。', '形容词: characterless 过去式: charactered 过去分词: charactered 现在分词: charactering 第三人称单数: characters');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('urge', '[ɜːrdʒ]', 'vt.催促,力劝;n.强烈欲望,迫切要求;v.促进', '1. He urged the horses on with a whip. 他用鞭子策马前行。 2. Many physicians urge aerobic exercise. 很多医生鼓励有氧运动。 3. We will urge them to adhere to the Paris Agreement. 我们将敦促他们遵守巴黎协议。 4. They urged on us the need for cooperation. 他们向我们强调合作的必要性。 5. He urged against the adoption of the measure. 他极力反对采取这项措施。 6. I feel the urge to be outside when spring comes again. 当春天再次来临,我就有了到户外活动的冲动。', '过去式: urged 过去分词: urged 现在分词: urging 第三人称单数: urges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('zinc', '[zɪŋk]', 'n.锌;vt.涂锌于', '1. The fusion of copper and zinc make the metal brass. 铜和锌的熔化制成黄铜。 2. Zinc is generally caustic to foliage. 锌常对幼叶有腐蚀作用。', '简写符号: Zn 过去式: zinced/zincked 过去分词: zinced/zincked 现在分词: zincing/zincking 第三人称单数: zincs/zincks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('expel', '[ɪk\'spel]', 'v.驱逐,开除,排出,发射', '1. Russia has lately decided to expel a US diplomat from its land, . 俄国最近驱逐了一名美国外交官。 2. He was expelled from the school. 他被学校开除了。 3. The headmaster decided to make an example of the pupil and expel him from the school. 校长决定开除该生以儆效尤。 4. The lungs expel carbon dioxide when we exhale. 当我们呼气时,肺所排出来的是二氧化碳。', '形容词: expellable 名词: expeller 过去式: expelled 过去分词: expelled 现在分词: expelling 第三人称单数: expels');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('discharge', '[dɪs\'tʃɑːrdʒ]', 'vt.卸下,放出,清偿(债务),履行(义务),解雇,开(炮),放(枪),射(箭);vi.卸货,流注;n.卸货,流出,放电', '1. The Nile discharge itself into the Mediterranean. 尼罗河水注入地中海。 2. The water pipe doesn\'t discharge freely. 水管排水不畅。 3. The judge discharged the prisoner. 法官把囚犯释放了。 4. I am going to discharge our chauffeur. 我要解雇我们的司机。 5. How long will the discharge of the cargo take? 卸货需要多久？', '形容词: dischargeable 名词: dischargee 过去式: discharged 过去分词: discharged 现在分词: discharging 第三人称单数: discharges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('profession', '[prə\'feʃn]', 'n.职业,专业,表白,宣布', '1. He is a doctor by profession. 他的职业是医生。 2. Nursing is a vocation as well as a profession. 护理工作既是职业又是救死扶伤的责任。 3. I don\'t believe her profession of friendship for us. 我不相信她声称同我们友好。 4. He is a leading member of the medical profession. 他是医疗业中首屈一指的医生。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('amend', '[ə\'mend]', 'v.修正,改进,改正', '1. They decided to amend the bill. 他们决定修正这条议案。 2. Please amend your copy of the contract accordingly. 请将你的合同文本作相应的修正。 3. Since you insist, I must amend the letter of credit. 既然你坚持，我就只好修改信用证。 4. I would advise you to amend your manners. 我劝你改正你的态度', '过去式: amended 过去分词: amended 现在分词: amending 第三人称单数: amends');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('stalk', '[stɔːk]', 'n.茎,柄,梗,秆', '1. It doesn\' t produce a stalk at all the first year? 在头一年绝对长不出茎秆? 2. He cut off the flowers at the stalk with a pair of scissors. 他用剪子连花带茎都剪下来。 3. He ate the apple, stalk and all. 他把那个苹果吃了个干净，连梗都没剩下。 4. He moved like a tiger stalking its prey. 他像老虎一样悄悄潜近他的猎物。', '形容词: stalky 名词: stalker 过去式: stalked 过去分词: stalked 现在分词: stalking 第三人称单数: stalks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ridiculous', '[rɪ\'dɪkjələs]', 'adj.荒谬的,可笑的', '1. His social pretensions make him appear ridiculous. 他冒充上流社会人士而出尽洋相。 2. His aristocratic manners seemed ridiculous in this poor area. 在这个贫穷的地区，他的贵族气派显得很可笑。 3. I\'ll show you how to settle such ridiculous stuff. 你瞧我怎样来对付这种无稽之谈。 4. That\'s ridiculous. 那太荒唐了。', '副词: ridiculously 名词: ridiculousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mechanical', '[mə\'kænɪkl]', 'adj.机械的,机械制的,机械似的,呆板的', '1. The new car had to be withdrawn from the market because of a mechanical defect. 那种新汽车因有机械缺陷只好撤出市场。 2. They were using a mechanical shovel to clear up the streets. 他们用机械铲土机清理街道。 3. The inhomogeneity of the physical and mechanical characteristics can be considered in these models. 在这些模型中考虑了土的物理和力学的非线性特性。 4. Blinking is a mechanical action of the eyelids. 眨眼是眼睑的无意识动作。', '副词: mechanically 名词: mechanicalness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('symmetry', '[\'sɪmətri]', 'n.对称,匀称', '1. These values constitute the symmetry waveform. 有这些数据来构成对称波形。 2. Many stems and roots show radial symmetry. 很多的茎和根都是辐射对称的。 3. His teeth spoiled the symmetry of his face. 他的牙齿破坏了他的面部匀称。 4. This addition may interfere with the symmetry of the layout. 这么一加，会破坏整个布局的匀称。', '名词复数: symmetries');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('grief', '[ɡriːf]', 'n.悲痛,伤心事,不幸,忧伤', '1. She uttered a wail of grief. 她悲痛地大声尖叫。 2. She was prostrate with grief. 她因悲痛而一蹶不振。 3. The poor woman was buried in grief after her son died. 这个可怜的妇人在儿子死后一直沉浸在悲痛之中。 4. No words can express my grief. 我的忧伤无法用语言表达。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('primitive', '[\'prɪmətɪv]', 'adj.原始的,远古的,粗糙的,简单的', '1. Primitive peoples deified the sun. 原始部落将太阳奉为神。 2. The constitution of a primitive society is not necessarily simple. 原始社会的结构并不一定就是简单的。 3. They built a primitive shelter out of the tree trunks 他们用一些树干建造了一个简陋的棚子。 4. Primitive people often lived in caves. 原始人常常住在山洞里。', '副词: primitively 名词: primitiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('appendix', '[ə\'pendɪks]', 'n.附录,附属品,[解]阑尾', '1. There is an appendix at the back of the book. 该书末尾处有一附录。 2. This is the appendix to the investigation report. 这是调查报告的附件。 3. The details are clearly set out in an appendix. 详细情况在一个附录里清楚列出。 4. He had his appendix taken out. 他的阑尾割去了。', '名词复数: appendixes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('belly', '[\'beli]', 'n.腹部,胃;vi.涨满', '1. My belly is empty. 我肚子饿了。 2. A hungry belly has no ears. 人肚子饿了就听不进道理。 3. The robber stabbed the young man in the belly. 强盗刺伤了这名年轻人的腹部。 4. The boat carried with much cargo in its belly. 该船的舱里载了很多的货物。 5. The sails bellied in the wind. 帆在风中鼓得满满的。', '名词复数: bellies 过去式: bellied 过去分词: bellied 现在分词: bellying 第三人称单数: bellies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('academic', '[ˌækə\'demɪk]', 'adj.学院的,理论的', '1. Sir Lawrence Alma-Tadema was an English painter in the academic tradition. 阿尔玛·台德玛是学院派的英国画家。 2. With my strong academic background, I am competent. 依我良好的学术背景,我能胜任。 3. Applicant must possess good conduct and obtain satisfactory academic results. 申请者必须拥有良好品性,并考获令人满意的成绩; 4. During the past four years I have had a good deal of academic experience in communications technology. 四年来,我掌握了丰富的通信技术上的理论知识。', '副词: academically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('attractive', '[ə\'træktɪv]', 'adj.吸引人的,有魅力的', '1. Ice-cream is attractive to children. 冰淇淋对孩子们非常有吸引力。 2. It\'s an attractive idea. 这是个使人感兴趣的想法。 3. It\'s a very attractive offer, and I\'m tempted to accept. 这项建议很有吸引力,我确实有些动心。 4. I think she is a very attractive girl. 我认为她是很有魅力的女孩。', '副词: attractively 名词: attractiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('biography', '[baɪ\'ɑːɡrəfi]', 'n.传记', '1. He likes to read biographies of great men to promote himself. 他喜欢读伟人传记来提高自己。 2. His biography is a saga of scientific research. 他的传记就是一部科研记实。 3. I have read a biography of Abraham Lincoln. 我读过一部亚伯拉罕•林肯的传记。', '名词复数: biographies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cucumber', '[\'kjuːkʌmbər]', 'n.[植]黄瓜', '1. Have some cucumber. 吃点黄瓜吧。 2. I like to eat cucumber sandwiches. 我喜欢吃有黄瓜的三明治。 3. In our garden we have egg-plants, cucumber and potato. 在我们的菜园里，我们种了茄子，黄瓜和土豆。 4. I would like a cucumber salad for an appetizer. 我要一份黄瓜沙拉作为开胃菜。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('commitment', '[kə\'mɪtmənt]', 'n.委托事项,许诺,承担义务', '1. If you are serious about our relationship, you should make a commitment. 如果你对我们的关系很认真，你就应该给个承诺。 2. He made a commitment to pay the rent on time. 他保证按时付房租。 3. It saddens me to recall that I assured him that I had no expectations of a long-term commitment. 现在回想起来，我为我一开始就向他保证说我也不期望一段长期的关系而伤感。 4. It has been argued that this anticipated the punctuated equilibrium hypothesis, but other scholars have preferred to emphasise Darwin\'s commitment to gradualism. 有人认为这加快了间断平衡假说的发展，但其他学者倾向于强调这表明了达尔文对渐进论的信奉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('orientation', '[ˌɔːriən\'teɪʃn]', 'n.方向,方位,定位,倾向性,向东方', '1. I needed some orientation at this stage. 我在这个阶段需要熟悉情况。 2. The arrangement must show a preferred orientation. 排列还必须呈现特定的指向。 3. The following action steps are a part of the foreman\'s orientation of the new worker. 以下内容是工头指导新工人时应采取的部分措施:介绍新的工作。 4. Christian Church that truly welcomes everybody disregarding your sexual orientation or denomination. 一个不论宗派及性取向，真正欢迎所有人的基督信仰教会。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('modify', '[\'mɑːdɪfaɪ]', 'vt.更改,修改;v.修改', '1. We have to modify our plan a little bit. 我们得对我们的计划稍加修改。 2. The policy was agreed by the committee, but only in a modified form. 那项政策经修改后才获得委员会同意。 3. The union has been forced to slightly modify its position. 工会被迫稍稍改变立场。 4. He\'ll have to modify his views if he wants to be elected. 他要想当选就得把观点改得缓和些。', '形容词: modifiable 名词: modifiability 过去式: modified 过去分词: modified 现在分词: modifying 第三人称单数: modifies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('financial', '[faɪ\'nænʃl]', 'adj.财政的,金融的', '1. He is an adventurer in financial field. 他是金融领域的投机者。 2. And I got the financial support after two years. 两年后我终于取得了奖学金。 3. I hear you are in poor financial straits. 我听说你处于经济困难之中。 4. This company was in serious financial difficulties. 这家公司陷入严重的财政困难。', '副词: financially');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('alert', '[ə\'lɜːrt]', 'adj.提防的,警惕的;n.警惕,警报', '1. The alert leopard went up to a deer quietly. 警觉的豹子静悄悄地走近一只鹿。 2. Although he\'s over eighty his mind is still remarkably alert. 他虽已年过八十，但头脑仍然十分机敏。 3. I must alert him to the need to solve the problem. 我必须使他认识到解决这问题的必要性。 4. But we must remain on the alert. 但是我们现在仍然要保持警惕。 5. Troops are on the alert against any possible aggression. 军队戒备着可能的来犯。', '过去式: alerted 过去分词: alerted 现在分词: alerting 第三人称单数: alerts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('elite', '[eɪ\'liːt]', 'n.<法>[集合名词]精华,精锐,中坚分子', '1. The elite are the competitive focus of 21 century. 精英人才是21世纪国际间竞争的焦点。 2. It is a luxury brand established for the elite and the affluent. 这是一个为精英群体和富人所创设的奢侈品牌。 3. It is indubitable that he is an elite in information technology. 毫无疑问，他是信息技术界的精英。 4. Public opinion is influenced by the small elite who control the media. 舆论为少数控制着新闻媒介的上层人士所左右。 5. This is an elite group reserved for members only. 这是仅为会员保留的精英小组。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('abundant', '[ə\'bʌndənt]', 'adj.丰富的,充裕的,丰富,盛产,富于', '1. Indonesia is abundant in petroleum deposits. 印尼的石油蕴藏量丰富。 2. The agricultural commodities are abundant this year. 今年的农产品很丰富。 3. Birds concentrate in places where food is abundant. 鸟聚集在食物丰盛的地方。 4. There is abundant firewood in the forest. 森林里有充裕的薪柴可用。', '副词: abundantly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('brutal', '[\'bruːtl]', 'adj.残忍的,兽性的', '1. The people have been kept down for years by a brutal regime. 人民多年遭受野蛮制度压迫。 2. The enemy made a brutal attack upon the villagers. 敌人对村民们进行了野蛮的攻击。 3. NATO\'s invasion of this independent country is a brutal violation of human rights. 北约对这个独立的国家的侵略是对人权的野蛮侵犯。 4. The brutal soldiers beat their prisoners ruthlessly. 残暴的士兵野蛮地抽打俘虏。', '副词: brutally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('transplant', '[\'trænsplænt]', 'v.移植,移种,移民,迁移;n.移植,被移植物,移居者', '1. The villagers will transplant to another place. 村民们将移居到另外一个地方。 2. The peasants bent over to transplant rice seedlings in the fields. 农民们在地里弯腰插秧。 3. It is now possible to transplant organs from animals into people. 现在将动物身上的器官移植入人体内已经成为了可能。 4. The doctors will transplant a human heart into the patient. 医生们将把一颗人的心脏移植到这个病人身上。 5. I think the heart transplant is a wonderful thing. 我认为心脏移植是件神奇的事。', '形容词: transplantable 名词: transplantation 过去式: transplanted 过去分词: transplanted 现在分词: transplanting 第三人称单数: transplants');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('thrive', '[θraɪv]', 'v.兴旺,繁荣,茁壮成长,旺盛', '1. A business cannot thrive without good management. 没有良好的经营管理，事业就不会兴旺发达。 2. But will they survive and thrive? 但是，他们会生存下来并兴旺繁殖吗? 3. May our country prosper and thrive forever! 希望我们的国家繁荣兴旺，长盛不衰。 4. A business can not thrive without investment. 没有投资任何生意都无法繁荣。', '名词: thriver 过去式: thrived/throve 过去分词: thrived/thriven 现在分词: thriving 第三人称单数: thrives');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('alternative', '[ɔːl\'tɜːrnətɪv]', 'n.二中择一,可供选择的办法,事物;adj.选择性的,二中择一的', '1. We have the alternative plans of having a picnic or taking a boat trip. 我们在去野餐或者去乘船旅游两个计划中只能选一。 2. They are provided with the choice of two alternative flights. 有两个航班可供他们选择。 3. I\'d like to get some alternative music CDs for my niece. 我想买一些非主流的音乐唱片给我侄女。 4. I had no alternative but to accept the offer. 我除了接受该项提议之外，别无选择。', '副词: alternatively');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hop', '[hɑːp]', 'v.单脚跳,(鸟,蛙等)跳跃;n.蛇麻草', '1. The children had a competition to see who could hop the fastest. 孩子们举行比赛, 看谁单足跳跃最快。 2. Several frogs were hopping about on the lawn. 有几只青蛙在草地上跳来跳去。 3. When the burglar heard their car he hopped it out of the window. 那窃贼听到他们汽车的声音就从窗口逃走了。 4. The pursuer cleared the fence in one hop. 追捕者一跳越过了栅栏。', '过去式: hopped 过去分词: hopped 现在分词: hopping 第三人称单数: hops');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('portray', '[pɔːr\'treɪ]', 'v.描绘', '1. It is difficult to portray feelings in words. 感情很难用言语来描写。 2. The book portrays the life of an actor. 这本书描述了一个演员的一生。 3. The picture portrays a beautiful sunset. 这幅画描绘了落日美景。 4. The actor is trying his best to portray the role of Hamlet. 这位演员尽力扮演哈姆雷特的角色。', '形容词: portrayable 名词: portrayer 过去式: portrayed 过去分词: portrayed 现在分词: portraying 第三人称单数: portrays');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('manipulate', '[mə\'nɪpjuleɪt]', 'vt.(熟练地)操作,使用(机器等),操纵(人或市价,市场),利用,应付,假造;vt.(熟练地)操作,巧妙地处理', '1. A clever politician know how to manipulate public opinion. 聪明的政客知道如何操纵公众舆论。 2. He is one of those who manipulate the market. 他是操纵市场者之一。 3. Do you know how to manipulate a computer ? 你知道怎样操作计算机吗? 4. She uses her charm to manipulate people. 她利用其魅力左右他人。', '形容词: manipulatable 副词: manipulatively 名词: manipulability 过去式: manipulated 过去分词: manipulated 现在分词: manipulating 第三人称单数: manipulates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('historian', '[hɪ\'stɔːriən]', 'n.历史学家,史家', '1. A good historian must have an academic mind. 出色的历史学家须有学术头脑。 2. Tacitus was the greatest historian in Ancient Rome. 塔西陀是古罗马最伟大的历史学家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('scale', '[skeɪl]', 'n.刻度,衡量,比例,数值范围,比例尺,天平,等级;vt.依比例决定,攀登,测量;vi.剥落,生水垢,重,攀登,衡量', '1. How much does it read on the scale? 刻度显示的是多少? 2. The force of the wind is measured on a standard scale of 0-12. 风力是按0-12级标准等级测量的。 3. The fifth note of a scale is called a dominant. 音阶的第五音被称为属音。 4. It takes courage and strength to scale these cliffs. 攀登这些悬崖需要勇气和力量。', '形容词: scalelike 过去式: scaled 过去分词: scaled 现在分词: scaling 第三人称单数: scales');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('void', '[vɔɪd]', 'n.空间,空旷,空虚,怅惘;adj.空的,无人的,空闲的,无效的,无用的,没有的', '1. Void function may not return a value 空函数不可返回一个值。 2. The court ruled that the claim was null and void. 法庭裁决此项要求无效。 3. His suggestions are totally void of common sense. 他的建议完全缺乏常识。 4. That part of the town is completely void of interest for visitors. 城镇的那部分对游客完全没有吸引力。 5. In the next weeks, government floated as in a void. 以后的几个星期,政府宛如漂浮于真空之中。 6. We will void the existing and issue a new one. 我们将把现有的作废，然后再出一张新的。', '名词: voider 过去式: voided 过去分词: voided 现在分词: voiding 第三人称单数: voids');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('deliberate', '[dɪ\'lɪbərət]', 'adj.深思熟虑的,故意的,预有准备的;v.商讨', '1. She has a slow, deliberate way of talking. 她谈话的方式缓慢而审慎. 2. He told us a deliberate lie. 他存心说谎。 3. It had more the appearance of a deliberate crime than an accident. 那很像是蓄意的罪行，而不像是意外的事故。 4. He entered the room with deliberate steps. 他从容不迫地走进室内。 5. We had no time to deliberate on the problem. 我们没有时间仔细思考这个问题.', '副词: deliberately 名词: deliberateness 过去式: deliberated 过去分词: deliberated 现在分词: deliberating 第三人称单数: deliberates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('quart', '[kwɔːrt]', 'n.夸脱(容量单位)', '1. There is a quart of milk left in the pail. 桶里还剩下一夸脱牛奶。 2. You cannot get a quart into a pint pot. 你无法把一夸脱的酒装进一品脱的瓶中。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('module', '[\'mɑːdʒul]', 'n.模数,模块,登月舱,指令舱', '1. My desk is my command module. 我的书桌就是我的主要工作场所。 2. Have an overall pass for each module of the programme. 通过每单元之综合评核。 3. A module is a compilation unit or a development unit. 模块是编译单元或开发单元。 4. You will be able to see the contents of that module. 您将能够看到该模块的内容。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fabric', '[\'fæbrɪk]', 'n.织品,织物,布,结构,建筑物,构造', '1. The whole fabric of the society was changed by the war. 战争改变了整个社会结构。 2. The cost of repairing the fabric of the church was very high. 修理教堂结构的花费非常大。 3. This fabric has a tear in it. 这织物上有个破洞。 4. The fabric was displayed on a wired stand. 那种织物陈列在金属制的架子上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('invisible', '[ɪn\'vɪzəbl]', 'adj.看不见的,无形的', '1. Some stars are invisible to the naked eye. 有些星体肉眼是看不见的。 2. Germs are invisible to the naked eye. 细菌用肉眼看不见。 3. The mends were almost invisible. 修补过的地方几乎看不出来。 4. Aunt Harriet presided over an invisible army of servants that continuously scrubbed, cleaned, and published. 姑母哈丽特支配着一大群看不见的仆人，他们不停地刷洗、打扫和擦拭。 5. Her fantasy is to become invisible. 她的幻想是变成隐形人。', '副词: invisibly 名词: invisibility');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('efficiency', '[ɪ\'fɪʃnsi]', 'n.效率,功效', '1. We must improve our efficiency as soon as possible. 我们必须尽快地提高工作效率。 2. Their labor efficiency is very high. 他们的工作效率很高。 3. The two companies consolidated for greater efficiency. 这两家公司已合并以提高效率。 4. This jet has a very high propulsive efficiency. 该喷气机的喷射功率非常大。', '名词复数: efficiencies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('continuity', '[ˌkɑːntə\'nuːəti]', 'n.连续性,连贯性', '1. There is no continuity between the two paragraphs. 那两段间无连续性。 2. Mr Keller sees continuity where others see helter-skelter change. 别人眼中杂乱无章的变迁在凯勒眼里却具有连续性。', '名词复数: continuities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('concept', '[\'kɑːnsept]', 'n.观念,概念', '1. I can not understand such an abstract concept. 我无法理解如此抽象的观念。 2. He presented a new concept of the origins of the universe. 他提出了一种宇宙起源的新概念。 3. We had no concept that this tiny mistake would ruin the whole plan. 我们完全没有想到这个小小的失误会毁掉整个计划。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('magnet', '[\'mæɡnət]', 'n.磁体,磁铁', '1. He picked all the pins up with a magnet. 他用磁铁捡起了所有的大头针。 2. He was deeply attracted by the delicate cast of her features. 他的前途取决于这一机会。 3. Forbidden City is a great magnet for foreign tourists. 紫禁城对外国旅游者来说是个有巨大吸引力的地方。 4. The beautiful actress was the magnet that drew great audiences. 那个漂亮的女演员对很多观众都很有吸引力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('slide', '[slaɪd]', 'v.(使)滑动,(使)滑行;n.滑,滑动,幻灯片', '1. If you pull this lever, the roof will slide back. 拉一下这根杆,顶就往后滑动。 2. The book slid off my knee. 书从我膝上滑落。 3. House values may begin to slide. 房价可能开始逐渐下降了。 4. I had to slide into base to avoid the tag. 我必须滑上垒以免被触杀。 5. We are to slide the box by exerting a force on it. 我们对箱子施加作用力，使它滑动。 6. After you type your comment you can move it around on the slide. 键入批注后,您可以在幻灯片中移动批注。', '过去式: slid 过去分词: slid 现在分词: sliding 第三人称单数: slides');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('thermal', '[\'θɜːrml]', 'adj.热的,热量的', '1. An improved thermal head boosts image quality. 经过改进的热敏头,提高了图像质量。 2. The thermal energy has become more and more important. 热能变得越来越重要了。 3. These are thermal units. 这是热量单位。 4. My mother has bought the thermal underwear for me. 我妈妈已经给我买了保暖内衣。 5. While flying, you feel a weak thermal. 当飞行中，你感觉到一个微弱的热气流。', '副词: thermally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('refreshment', '[rɪ\'freʃmənt]', 'n.点心,饮料,精力恢复,爽快', '1. Refreshment was served after the benediction. 牧师祝福后，有茶点招待弟兄姐妹。 2. So they went to a refreshment room. 于是他们来到茶点室。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dazzle', '[\'dæzl]', 'v.(使)眼花,眩耀;n.耀眼', '1. His eyes dazzled before the strong light. 他面对强光头晕目眩。 2. She was dazzled by her sudden success. 突然的成功使她感到迷惘。 3. The diamond ring worn in her bridle hand\'s third finger dazzle against firelight. 她左手无名指上戴的钻石戒指在火光下闪闪发亮。 4. You will dazzle everyone you meet this week. 遇到的每个人都会为你倾倒。 5. The theatre was a dazzle of bright lights. 剧院是一片光芒耀眼的明亮灯光。', '副词: dazzlingly 名词: dazzler 过去式: dazzled 过去分词: dazzled 现在分词: dazzling 第三人称单数: dazzles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('displace', '[dɪs\'pleɪs]', 'vt.移置,转移,取代,置换;v.转移', '1. Weeds tend to displace other plants. 杂草越来越多，有取代其他植物之势。 2. Moderates have displaced the extremists on the committee. 在委员会中，稳健派人士取代了激进派人士。 3. Please don\'t displace my dictionaries. 请别动我的词典。 4. The indigenous population was soon displaced by the settlers. 没过多久，外来移民就把当地人赶出了家园。', '形容词: displaceable 名词: displacer 过去式: displaced 过去分词: displaced 现在分词: displacing 第三人称单数: displaces');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('alloy', '[\'ælɔɪ]', 'n.合金;vt.使成合金,减低成色', '1. Brass is an alloy of copper and zinc. 黄铜是铜和锌的合金。 2. The alloy has excellent thermal stability. 合金有极好的温度稳定性。 3. Mercy should alloy our stern resentment. 宽容会缓和积怨。 4. Nothing occurred to alloy our happiness. 未发生任何损害我们幸福的事情。', '过去式: alloyed 过去分词: alloyed 现在分词: alloying 第三人称单数: alloys');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rely', '[rɪ\'laɪ]', 'v.依赖,依靠,信赖,信任,依赖于', '1. They have to rely on the river for their water. 他们用水只好依靠这条河。 2. A man should rely upon his own power. 人类应该依靠自身的力量。 3. You can\'t rely on his assistance. 你不能指望他能帮助你。 4. We are relying on your decision. 我们相信你的判断。', '名词: relier 过去式: relied 过去分词: relied 现在分词: relying 第三人称单数: relies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reside', '[rɪ\'zaɪd]', 'vi.居住', '1. This family has resided in this city for 60 years. 这个家族住在本城已有60年了。 2. They reside in a cottage at the foot of the mountain. 他们住在山脚下的一所小屋里。 3. The real power resides in the people. 真正的权力属于人民。 4. Memory has been shown to reside in some metals. 已经证实，记忆存在于某些金属中。', '名词: resider 过去式: resided 过去分词: resided 现在分词: residing 第三人称单数: resides');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('vocal', '[\'voʊkl]', 'adj.发嗓音的,声音的,有声的,歌唱的;n.元音,声乐作品', '1. The tongue is one of the vocals. 舌头是发声器官之一。 2. In the present instance he took no notice of my abrupt vocal response. 在目前这个情况下，他不去注意我那突兀的口头回答。 3. I like instrumental music better than vocal music. 我喜欢器乐胜于声乐。 4. He has been very vocal in his criticism of the government\'s policy. 他对政府政策的批评一直是直言不讳。 5. I select the two artists who have the commeasurable from the multitudinous outstanding vocal music performing artists to analyze and compare. 然而，她们却在声乐作品演唱方面表现出了不尽相同的理解，并形成和确立了截然不同的个人演唱风格。', '副词: vocally 名词: vocalness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('submarine', '[ˌsʌbmə\'riːn]', 'n.潜水艇,潜艇;adj.水下的,海底的', '1. The frigate rammed the submarine. 护卫舰撞击了潜艇。 2. The ship was sunk by an atomic submarine. 这艘船是被一艘核潜艇击沉的。 3. A submarine glided silently through the water. 一艘潜水艇无声地在水中滑行。 4. At the first sign of danger the submarine will submerge. 一有危险迹象，潜艇就会潜入水中。 5. They are building a submarine cable tunnel. 他们正在建设一条海底电缆隧道。', '过去式: submarined 过去分词: submarined 现在分词: submarining 第三人称单数: submarines');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('parallel', '[\'pærəlel]', 'adj.平行的,相同的,类似的,并联的;n.平行线,平行面,类似,相似物;v.相应,平行', '1. In the parallel world, there might be an answer for everything. 在平行世界里,似乎有一切的答案。 2. Parallel processing is the most important peculiarity in this design. 其中,并行化的设计理念是该设计的最大特点。 3. The railway lines run parallel to the road. 铁路线和那条道路平行。 4. My experience in this matter is parallel to yours. 在这件事情上，我的经验和你的类似。 5. It is inappropriate to draw such a parallel. 这种比拟是不恰当的。 6. No one can parallel him in Math. 在数学方面无人能与他匹敌。', '过去式: paralleled/parallelled 过去分词: paralleled/parallelled 现在分词: paralleling/parallelling 第三人称单数: parallels/parallels');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('anonymous', '[ə\'nɑːnɪməs]', 'adj.匿名的', '1. It is unpleasant to receive anonymous letters. 接到匿名信是一件令人不快的事。 2. The man was arrested after an anonymous tip-off. 有人匿名举报后，那个人被抓了起来。 3. The author chooses to remain anonymous. 作者愿不署名。 4. An anonymous author wrote this book. 这本书出自无名氏之手。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('scrap', '[skræp]', 'n.小片,废料,剪下来的图片,文章,残余物,废料,打架;vt.扔弃,敲碎,拆毁;vi.互相殴打;adj.零碎的,废弃的', '1. They wrote messages to each other on scraps of paper. 他们用一些碎纸片互传信息。 2. The cars have been broken down for scraps. 那些汽车已经拆掉当废铁。 3. It won\'t make a scrap of difference. 这不会有丝毫的差别。 4. There is not a scrap of truth in what he has said. 他说的话没有半点是真的。 5. I\'ll soon have to scrap this lawn mower,it\'s beyond repair and on its last legs. 不久将不得不把我这台割草机废弃掉，因它已不能修理，即将报废了。', '名词: scrapper 过去式: scrapped 过去分词: scrapped 现在分词: scrapping 第三人称单数: scraps');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('characteristic', '[ˌkærəktə\'rɪstɪk]', 'adj.特有的,表示特性的,典型的;n.特性,特征', '1. Ambition is a characteristic of all successful businessmen. 雄心勃勃是所有成功生意人的共同特点。 2. Kindness is one of his characteristics. 和善是他的特性之一。 3. A characteristic of the camel is its ability to live for a long time without water. 骆驼的特点是不喝水也能活很长时间。 4. They have been affected by trends in Italy too much to keep their own characteristics. 他们受意大利潮流的影响太大了,以致无法保持自己的特色。 5. It is the characteristic attitude of people towards life in those post-war years. 这是战后人们典型的处世态度。', '副词: characteristically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('weary', '[\'wɪri]', 'adj.疲倦的,厌倦的,令人厌烦的,疲劳;v.疲倦,厌倦,厌烦', '1. After many hours in the saddle he was very weary. 骑马骑了几个小时后，他非常疲倦。 2. I feel weary after such a long journey. 经过这么长时间的旅行后，我觉得很累。 3. We all grew weary of his long-winded speech. 我们对他冗长的发言都感到很厌烦。 4. He began to be weary of the research work. 他开始对研究工作感到厌烦。 5. The long walk completely wearied us. 这麽长的路走得我们疲惫不堪。', '副词: wearily 比较级: wearier 最高级: weariest 名词: weariness 过去式: wearied 过去分词: wearied 现在分词: wearying 第三人称单数: wearies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sheer', '[ʃɪr]', 'adj.全然的,纯粹的,绝对的,彻底的,透明的;vi.避开,躲避,偏航;vt.使避开,使偏航;adv.完全,全然,峻峭;n.偏航', '1. Chiffon is a fabric of sheer silk or rayon. 薄绸是一种极薄的丝绸或人造丝织物。 2. It\'s very difficult to climb a sheer cliff. 攀登陡峭的悬崖是很困难的。 3. She played a trick on him out of sheer devilment. 她捉弄他完全是为了寻开心。 4. He\'s so impatient that waiting in queues is sheer purgatory for him. 他毫无耐性，对他来说排队等候完全是活受罪。 5. The ground dropped away sheer at our feet. 我们脚下的地面垂直地陷落下去。 6. When he saw me coming he sheered off in the opposite direction. 他一看到我过来，掉头就走了。', '副词: sheerly 比较级: sheerer 最高级: sheerest 名词: sheerness 过去式: sheered 过去分词: sheered 现在分词: sheering 第三人称单数: sheers');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('federation', '[ˌfedə\'reɪʃn]', 'n.同盟,联邦,联合,联盟', '1. United Federation of Planets incorporated. 星际联邦组成。 2. One of the states has seceded from the federation. 有一个州已从联邦中退出。 3. The small countries joined together into a federation. 小国联合起来组成一个联盟。 4. This Standard is prepared by China Federation of Power Enterprises. 本标准由中国电力企业联合会提出。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('transition', '[træn\'zɪʃn]', 'n.转变,转换,跃迁,过渡,变调', '1. Such a sudden transition must affect her. 这样的一个突然变化一定会影响她。 2. His attitude underwent an abrupt transition. 他的态度突然改变了。 3. We hope there will be a peaceful transition to the new system. 我们希望能够和平过渡到新的制度。', '形容词: transitional 副词: transitionally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('disposition', '[ˌdɪspə\'zɪʃn]', 'n.部署', '1. She has a calm and introverted disposition. 她性格文静内向。 2. Joanna had a gentle retiring disposition. 乔安娜性格温柔而腼腆。 3. The child had a placid disposition. 这个孩子性情温和。 4. They showed a disposition to sign the contract. 他们表示有签订合同的意愿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('employment', '[ɪm\'plɔɪmənt]', 'n.雇用,使用,利用,工作,职业', '1. I got this job through an employment agency. 我通过职业介绍所找到了这份工作。 2. He enrolled with an employment agency for a secretary. 他在职业介绍所登记要当秘书。 3. He left his home to look for employment. 他离家去找职业。 4. His employment is that of a bookbinder. 他的职业是装订工。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sensible', '[\'sensəbl]', 'adj.有感觉的,明智的,有判断力的', '1. To wink at rudeness in children is not sensible. 对小孩粗鲁的行为视若无睹是不明智的。 2. That sounds very sensible to me. 我觉得这很合理。 3. Saving your presence, I don\'t think the suggestion is very sensible. 请恕我直言，我认为这个建议不太合情理。 4. Her distress was sensible from her manner. 她的悲痛从她的态度上可觉察到。 5. The world of dreams is our real world whilst we are sleeping because our attention then lapses from the sensible world. 在睡眠中梦见的世界便是我们的真实世界，因为那时我们的注意力已从可感知世界转移开。', '副词: sensibly 名词: sensibleness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('display', '[dɪ\'spleɪ]', 'vt.陈列,展览,显示;n.陈列,展览,显示,显示器', '1. Let\'s display the figures and see what we have. 通过显示一下数字看看我们能看到什么。 2. The bottles of whisky on display are all dummies. 所陈列的威士忌酒都是假的。 3. There will be a display of bronze statuary in this museum next week. 下星期这个博物馆将举办一个青铜雕塑作品展览。 4. He made a display of his learning. 他夸耀自己有学问。 5. I have rarely seen her display any sign of emotion. 我难得见到她将喜怒形于色。', '过去式: displayed 过去分词: displayed 现在分词: displaying 第三人称单数: displays');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pastry', '[\'peɪstri]', 'n.面粉糕饼,馅饼皮', '1. Before cooking,she pressed pastry flat and thin. 制做前她把馅饼皮压得薄又平。 2. Roll out the pastry and cut into small triangles.The exact size is up to you. 擀好馅饼皮后，将其切成小的三角形状，具体的大小取决于个人。', '名词复数: pastries');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('manuscript', '[\'mænjuskrɪpt]', 'n.手稿,原稿', '1. I read his novel in manuscript. 我看过他小说的手稿。 2. The illumination of the manuscript is delicate. 这个手稿的装饰很精致。 3. The manuscript requires an expert to understand it. 这份手稿只有专家才看得懂。 4. He revised the manuscript of his book before sending it to the publisher. 他对自己那本书的手稿先进行校订，然后才把它交给出版社。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('diagnose', '[ˌdaɪəɡ\'noʊs]', 'v.诊断', '1. Geological investigations must correctly diagnose a specific soil-like condition. 地质调查必须正确地判断出明确的土状条件。 2. What more will you want to know to diagnose this problem? 要弄清这个问题，你还需要知道些什么? 3. The book diagnoses our present economic ills. 这本书切中了我们现在经济的时弊。 4. The test is used to diagnose a variety of diseases. 此项化验可用于诊断多种疾病。', '形容词: diagnosable 过去式: diagnosed 过去分词: diagnosed 现在分词: diagnosing 第三人称单数: diagnoses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('exceptional', '[ɪk\'sepʃənl]', 'adj.例外的,异常的', '1. Forestry has advanced with exceptional speed. 植树造林以罕见的速度得到了发展。 2. By no means are these cases exceptional. 这些例子绝不是例外。 3. This weather is exceptional for June. 六月里这样的天气是反常的。 4. We\'ve enjoyed an exceptional run of fine weather recently. 我们这里最近天气好极了。', '副词: exceptionally 名词: exceptionality');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('trivial', '[\'trɪviəl]', 'adj.琐细的,价值不高的,微不足道的', '1. It\'s a trivial matter and not worth fighting about. 区区小事不值得争吵。 2. He could remember every trivial incident in great detail. 他能把每件小事的细节都记得很清楚。 3. I object to being jumped upon for trivial matter like this. 我讨厌因这种小事而受人责备。 4. Don\'t be angry over such trivial matters. 别为这些琐事生气。', '副词: trivially');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('foresee', '[fɔːr\'siː]', 'vt.预见,预知', '1. Can you foresee what will happen in the future? 你能预见将来会发生什么吗? 2. Nobody could foresee his running away. 没人预见到他的逃跑。 3. Few analysts foresaw that oil prices would rise so steeply. 几乎没有分析师能预见的到石油价格会上升得这么快。 4. Those who can foresee difficulties on their way to success may keep calm when they really appear. 在走向成功的路途中能够预见到困难的人在困难真正出现的时候常常能保持冷静的态度。', '形容词: foreseeable 名词: foreseer 过去式: foresaw 过去分词: foreseen 现在分词: foreseeing 第三人称单数: foresees');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('superficial', '[ˌsuːpər\'fɪʃl]', 'adj.表面的,肤浅的,浅薄的', '1. Superficial scratches can be easily removed. 表面的划痕很容易擦掉。 2. A superficial injury is not serious. 表面的伤不太严重。 3. This is only superficial prosperity. 这只是表面繁荣。 4. He is too superficial to appreciate great literature like this. 他太肤浅，无法欣赏这类文学巨著。', '副词: superficially 名词: superficiality');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('empirical', '[ɪm\'pɪrɪkl]', 'adj.完全根据经验的,经验主义的,[化]实验式', '1. His science was generally empirical and often bad. 他的科学一般来自经验。 2. Inquiry into the nature of things based on logical reasoning rather than empirical methods. 自然科学基于逻辑推理而不是凭经验得来的方法来探究事物的本质。 3. Unboundedness has a greater empirical credibility. 无界性有更大的经验可信性。 4. The Sprint phase is an empirical process. 冲刺阶段是一个完全根据经验的过程。', '副词: empirically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cumulative', '[\'kjuːmjəleɪtɪv]', 'adj.累积的', '1. It is a cumulative process. 它是一个逐步累积的过程。 2. This form of backup is also known as cumulative backup. 这种形式的备份也称为累积备份。 3. Food additives and preservatives may have a long-term cumulative toxic effect. 食物添加剂和防腐剂长期食用却可产生累积毒性效应。 4. This drug has a cumulative effect. 这种药有渐增的效力。', '副词: cumulatively 名词: cumulativeness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dread', '[dred]', 'n.恐惧,恐怖,可怕的人(或物),畏惧;v.惧怕,担心', '1. I dread having to visit the dentist . 我害怕看牙医。 2. I dread to think what will happen if she finds out the truth. 我不敢去想她知道真相后会怎么样。 3. Much of what we dread is really due to indistinctness of outline. 畏生于不明，大抵如此。 4. The Jews lived in dread of being caught. 这些犹太人生活在会遭到拘捕的恐惧之中。 5. The countryside lay as under some dread enchantment. 乡村好像躺在某种可怖的魔法之下。', '过去式: dreaded 过去分词: dreaded 现在分词: dreading 第三人称单数: dreads');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('poetry', '[\'poʊətri]', 'n.诗,作诗法,诗意,诗情', '1. Poetry helps to interpret life. 诗有助于阐释人生的意义。 2. I spent all my spare time reading poetry. 我所有的业余时间都用在诗歌阅读上。 3. Professor Lee will give us a lecture on poetry. 李教授将就诗歌对我们作学术讲演。 4. In poetry the rose is often a metaphor for love. 玫瑰在诗中通常作为爱的象征。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sneak', '[sniːk]', 'vi.鬼鬼祟祟做事;vt.偷偷摸摸做,<口>偷窃;n.鬼鬼祟祟人,偷偷摸摸行为,<美口>帆布胶底运动鞋;adj.暗中进行的', '1. He sneaked a chocolate from the box. 他从盒子里偷拿了一块巧克力。 2. I\'ll see if I can sneak him in after dark. 我看天黑后能否让他偷偷地溜进去。 3. I can sneak you out without being noticed. 我能把你偷偷地带出去，别人了现不了。 4. The cat ate the food and sneaked off. 猫吃完食物就偷偷跑了。 5. The sneak who took our lunch spoiled our picnic. 那个鬼鬼祟祟偷走了我们午饭的人，破坏了我们的野餐。 6. This sneak raid was very successful. We took the enemy leader captive. 这次偷袭非常成功，活捉了敌酋。', '过去式: sneaked/snuck 过去分词: sneaked/snuck 现在分词: sneaking 第三人称单数: sneaks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('relay', '[\'riːleɪ]', 'n.驿马,接替,[电工]继电器;vt.(消息,货物等)分程传递,使接替,转播;vi.得到接替,转播', '1. Images of the war were relayed around the world. 世界各地转播了战争的图像。 2. I will relay your opinion to the headmaster. 我愿把你的意见转告校长。 3. The Relay Agent could not start up its main thread. 中继代理无法启动其主线程。 4. Frame Relay Connection and Traffic Flow Control. 帧中继连接和流量控制。 5. This relay connects one input to one output. 该继电器将一个输入连接到一个输出。', '过去式: relayed 过去分词: relayed 现在分词: relaying 第三人称单数: relays');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('lever', '[\'levər]', 'n.杆,杠杆,控制杆;v.抬起', '1. He employed his knife as a lever. 他把刀子当杠杆用。 2. This lever must serve some ulterior purpose. 这撬棒准是用于不可告人的目的的。 3. Push hard and the lever will go down. 用力推就能把控制杆按下去。 4. Move this lever to change gear. 换档时扳动这根操纵杆。 5. They managed to lever the door open. 他们设法撬开了门。', '过去式: levered 过去分词: levered 现在分词: levering 第三人称单数: levers');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('blunder', '[\'blʌndər]', 'v.跌跌撞撞地走,犯大错,做错;n.大错,失误', '1. He made a blunder in front of his girlfriend. 他在女朋友面前犯了大错。 2. I saw that I had been guilty of a careless blunder. 我意识到自己因疏忽而酿成大错。 3. I made a terrible blunder in introducing her to my husband. 我把她介绍给我的丈夫是犯了一个极大的错误。 4. I hope you will not blunder again . 我希望你不要再犯大错。', '副词: blunderingly 名词: blunderer 过去式: blundered 过去分词: blundered 现在分词: blundering 第三人称单数: blunders');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('paragraph', '[\'pærəɡræf]', 'n.(文章)段,节,段落', '1. The editor struck out the whole paragraph. 编辑把整段全删掉了。 2. You\'ll find the last paragraph extremely apropos. 你会觉得最后一段文字极为中肯。 3. Look at the second paragraph on page fifteen. 请看第十五页的第二段。 4. This point has been dealt with in the preceding paragraph. 这一点在前面一段里已经交代过了。 5. The student is ask to paragraph an essay in class. 学生们被要求在课堂上给一篇文章分段。 6. The editor asked him to paragraph. 编辑让他写短评。', '形容词: paragraphic 过去式: paragraphed 过去分词: paragraphed 现在分词: paragraphing 第三人称单数: paragraphs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('conduct', '[kən\'dʌkt]', 'n.行为,操行;v.引导,管理,为人,传导', '1. Your conduct is not consistent with what you say. 你的言行不一致。 2. His behavior transgressed the unwritten rules of social conduct. 他的行为违反了不成文的社交规范。 3. His conduct roused the suspicion of the police. 他的举动引起了警察的怀疑。 4. He has good conduct. 他品行端正。 5. The guide conducted us around the ruins of the ancient city. 导游引导我们游览了古城废墟。 6. Most metals can conduct electricity. 大多数金属能导电。', '形容词: conductible 名词: conductibility 过去式: conducted 过去分词: conducted 现在分词: conducting 第三人称单数: conducts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('religion', '[rɪ\'lɪdʒən]', 'n.宗教,信仰', '1. He is a disciple of religion. 他是宗教信徒。 2. Jesus was the founder of the Christian religion. 耶稣是基督教的创始人。 3. Politics and religion are daily topics of conversation. 政治和宗教是人们平常交谈的主要话题。 4. There are many religions in the world. 世界上有许多种宗教信仰。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('narrative', '[\'nærətɪv]', 'adj.叙述性的;n.叙述', '1. She took up the narrative where John had left off. 她接着讲约翰未讲完的故事。 2. His adventure made an interesting narrative. 他的冒险是个有趣的故事。 3. Tatham was lost in wonder at the narrative. 泰瑟姆听了这个故事，惊奇得出了神。 4. Narrative makes up most of the book. 这本书的大部分篇幅都是叙述性的。 5. The lines form a prelude to his long narrative poem. 这几行诗是他那长篇叙事诗的序诗。', '副词: narratively');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('notable', '[\'noʊtəbl]', 'adj.值得注意的,显著的,著名的', '1. The difference contrast is notable. 差别对比是显著的。 2. This book had a notable impact on literature and art. 这本书对文学艺术产生显著的影响。 3. Tsim Sha Tsui is a notable tourist destination. 尖沙咀是著名的游客区。 4. You can also take in some of the notable architectural monuments. 你也可以将一些著名的纪念性建筑包括在参观的项目中。 5. He is the most notable son of Manchester. 他是曼切斯特最显赫的名人。', '副词: notably 名词: notableness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('insect', '[\'ɪnsekt]', 'n.昆虫,卑鄙的人;adj..虫的,虫子一样的,对付虫子的', '1. The insect bit him and drew blood from his arm. 那只昆虫叮在他的手臂上吸血。 2. A cocoon is a kind of silk covering made by an insect. 蚕茧是由昆虫制造的一种由丝组成的外包层。 3. She stamped on the insect and killed it. 她踩死了一只虫子。 4. A locust is a kind of destructive insect. 蝗虫是一种害虫。', '形容词: insectival 名词复数: insects');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('aesthetic', '[es\'θetɪk]', 'adj.美学的,审美的,有审美感的', '1. Later he also gained in aesthetic knowledge. 后来他的美学知识也增加了。 2. From an aesthetic point of view it\'s a thetic view. 从美学观点来说, 这是个武断的看法。 3. The professor advanced a new aesthetic theory. 那位教授提出了新的美学理论。 4. His aesthetic ideas were his own. 他有他自己的审美观念。 5. Natural aesthetic is the core of Chinese aesthetics. 自然审美是中国古代美学的核心。', '副词: aesthetically 异体字: esthetic');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('anticipate', '[æn\'tɪsɪpeɪt]', 'vt.预期,期望,过早使用,先人一着,占先;v.预订,预见,可以预料', '1. We anticipate that we will meet a certain amount of resistance to our plan. 我们预料我们的计划会遇到一些人的反对。 2. I anticipate reading the book with great interest. 我以极大的兴趣期待着读这本书。 3. It is unwise to anticipate your earnings by spending a lot of money. 大量花钱提前使用自己的收入是不明智的。 4. They anticipate ours by just one month. 他们比我们抢先了一个月。', '形容词: anticipatable 名词: anticipator 过去式: anticipated 过去分词: anticipated 现在分词: anticipating 第三人称单数: anticipates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('affirm', '[ə\'fɜːrm]', 'v.断言,确认,肯定', '1. Scientists cannot affirm the existence of life on other planets. 科学家们还不能证实在其它星球上有生命存在。 2. I affirm that what he said is true. 我断言他所说的是实情。 3. They affirmed that the girl did quite a bit of reading. 他们断言这个女孩子读了不少书。 4. I can affirm that no one will lose their job. 我可以肯定，谁都不会丢掉工作。', '形容词: affirmable 副词: affirmably 名词: affirmer 过去式: affirmed 过去分词: affirmed 现在分词: affirming 第三人称单数: affirms');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('contradiction', '[ˌkɑːntrə\'dɪkʃn]', 'n.反驳,矛盾', '1. Motion itself is a contradiction. 运动本身就是矛盾。 2. The contradiction was only apparent. 那矛盾只是表面上的。 3. The contradiction has become apparent. 矛盾表面化了。 4. This contradiction is hushed up . 这个矛盾消除了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('execution', '[ˌeksɪ\'kjuːʃn]', 'n.实行,完成,执行,死刑,制作,(武器等的)破坏效果,杀伤力', '1. The execution of the bandits took place today. 匪徒们於今天处决。 2. He has failed in the execution of his duties. 他没有尽到职责。 3. His original idea was good, but his execution of the scheme was disastrous. 他的设想很好，但实行起来却糟糕透顶。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('repay', '[rɪ\'peɪ]', 'v.偿还,报答,报复', '1. He didn\'t have the wherewithal to repay the loan. 他没有钱偿还贷款。 2. You should repay principal and interest. 你必须偿还本金和利息。 3. I wish I can repay you somehow for your kindness. 我希望我能以某种方式报答您的好意。 4. We must do something to repay him for helping us. 我们得做点事以报答他的帮助。', '形容词: repayable 名词: repayment 过去式: repaid 过去分词: repaid 现在分词: repaying 第三人称单数: repays');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('surgery', '[\'sɜːrdʒəri]', 'n.外科,外科学,手术室,诊疗室', '1. He is preparing for the surgery. 他正在做手术前的准备。 2. He underwent open-heart surgery. 他接受了体外循环心脏手术。 3. He is a plastic surgery specialist. 他是个整形外科医生。 4. I want you to go to the hospital surgery for a general check-up. 希望你到外科医生的诊所进行全面检查。', '名词复数: surgeries');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('magnetic', '[mæɡ\'netɪk]', 'adj.磁的,有磁性的,有吸引力的', '1. The loop becomes magnetic when the current is switched on. 通电时线圈就会有磁性。 2. She has a magnetic personality. 她具有极具吸引力的性格。 3. She was the most magnetic speaker I have ever listened to. 她是我所听过的演讲者中最有吸引力的一位。', '副词: magnetically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('clerk', '[klɜːrk]', 'n.职员,办事员,<美>店员', '1. The bank clerk peered at the customer through/from behind the grille. 银行的职员从格栅後面看著顾客。 2. The bank manager was really to blame, though he tried to pin it on a clerk. 真正受责备的应该是银行经理，可是他却想把责任推到一个职员身上。 3. She is the filing clerk of our company. 她是我们公司的档案员。 4. The clerk marked up his daybook before going home. 办事员在回家前记好当天的日记帐。 5. She clerks in a store(bank). 她在商店（银行）当售货员（职员）。', '名词: clerkdom 过去式: clerked 过去分词: clerked 现在分词: clerking 第三人称单数: clerks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('deport', '[dɪ\'pɔːrt]', 'vt.举止,驱逐', '1. Even if they didn\'t put her in jail, they would deport her. 即使他们不把她关入监狱,他们也会把她驱逐出境。 2. We deport aliens who slip across our borders. 我们把偷渡入境的外国人驱逐出境。 3. It’s important to teach a child how to deport himself in public. 教会小孩在公众场合如何举止得体十分重要。', '过去式: deported 过去分词: deported 现在分词: deporting 第三人称单数: deports');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('flank', '[flæŋk]', 'n.腰窝,侧面,军队侧翼,侧腹,胁,腰窝肉;vt.在...的侧面,侧翼包围,守侧面;vi.侧面与...相接', '1. Sardinia and Corsica lie on the flank of the long Italian boot. 撒丁与科西嘉位于意大利靴形半岛之侧面。 2. The horse\'s flank was vividly visible. 这匹马的侧面看起来生气勃勃。 3. The rider dug his spurs into the horse\'s flank. 骑马者用靴刺戳了戳马的侧腹。 4. Although biologists can easily induce extra limbs to grow on the flank of a tetrapod, this cannot be done in the neck. 虽然生物学家能轻易让四足动物在侧腹长出额外的肢，在颈部却做不到。 5. The old fort flanked on a swamp. 古碉堡的一侧靠着沼泽。', '过去式: flanked 过去分词: flanked 现在分词: flanking 第三人称单数: flanks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('obscene', '[əb\'siːn]', 'adj.淫秽的,猥亵的', '1. No nudity or obscene lyrics in your music are to be used during your routine. 请勿在上台比赛的音乐中加入猥亵或淫秽的曲调或歌词。 2. Something, such as language or printed matter, considered obscene , prurient, or immoral. 这本书中有很多淫秽的语言。 3. He was taking part in some obscene feast. 他是在参加一个卑鄙猥亵的餐会。 4. The protesters shouted some obscene remarks at the police officers. 抗议者们朝警官们叫喊着一些猥亵的话语。', '副词: obscenely');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('abolish', '[ə\'bɑːlɪʃ]', 'vt.废止,废除(法律、制度、习俗等)', '1. Abraham Lincoln abolished slavery in the United States. 亚伯拉罕·林肯在美国废除了奴隶制。 2. There are many bad customs and laws that ought to be abolished. 有许多不良的习俗和法规应予以废除。 3. They petitioned the government to abolish hanging. 他们向政府请愿，要求废除绞刑。 4. The legislature passed a law to abolish the surtax. 立法机关通过了一项废除附加税的法令。', '形容词: abolishable 名词: abolisher 过去式: abolished 过去分词: abolished 现在分词: abolishing 第三人称单数: abolishes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('revelation', '[ˌrevə\'leɪʃn]', 'n.显示,揭露,被揭露的事,新发现,启示,揭示', '1. The revelation of his past lead to his resignation. 对他过去的揭露导致了他的辞职。 2. Have you read the ex-minister\'s amazing revelations in the newspaper? 你看了前任部长在报上揭露的那些惊人的事实没有？ 3. The revelation of the plot of the traitors caused their capture. 反叛者阴谋的泄露使他们被捕。 4. Her true nature was a revelation to me. 她的真实性格对我是一个新发现。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('herb', '[ɜːrb]', 'n.药草,香草', '1. He alighted on a rare medical herb. 他偶然找到了一种稀有的草药。 2. I had to take the herb tea although it\'s bitter. 虽然汤药很苦，我还是不得不喝了。 3. The essence drawn out from this medicinal herb is good for high blood pressure. 从这种药草提炼出来的精华对治疗高血压有效。 4. This herb can act as an antidote against snakebite. 这种药草可以用作被蛇咬后的解毒药。', '形容词: herby');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('aware', '[ə\'wer]', 'adj.知道的,明白的,意识到的', '1. If you were aware of all that, you would change your mind. 如果你知道了那一切,你会改变主意的。 2. Then he became aware that they were regarding him with interest. 这时,他意识到他们都在饶有兴趣地看着他。', '名词: awareness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('consumer', '[kən\'sjuːmə]', 'n.消费者', '1. We need more feedback from the consumer in order to improve our goods. 我们需要从消费者那里多得到些反馈信息以提高产品质量。 2. The price increases were passed on by the firm to the consumers. 那个公司把上涨的费用都转嫁到了消费者身上。 3. We should adopt the consumers\' suggestion. 我们应该接受用户的建议。 4. Consumer goods production was to go up by 6.6 percent in that city. 在那个城市消费品生产将增长6.6%25。', '名词: consumership');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('virtue', '[\'vɜːrtʃuː]', 'n.德行,美德,贞操,优点,功效,效力,英勇', '1. Fidelity to engagement is a virtue. 信守诺言是一种美德。 2. My neighbor is a man of highest virtue. 我的邻居是一个具有高尚品德的人。 3. He said his plan had the virtue of being the easiest to implement. 他说他的计划的优点是最简单易行。 4. Meekness is a virtue he appreciates in his wife. 温顺是他所欣赏的妻子的优点之一。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('drainage', '[\'dreɪnɪdʒ]', 'n.排水,排泄,排水装置,排水区域,排出物,消耗', '1. Bad drainage caused the land to be flooded. 排水不利容易使土地淹水。 2. Make holes through the base to allow for drainage. 在地基中开洞，以便排水。 3. The drainage system has been aged. 排水系统已经老化了。 4. The town\'s drainage is very efficient. 这城市的排水系统很好。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('retrospect', '[\'retrəspekt]', 'n.回顾', '1. In retrospect, it\'s easy to see why we were wrong. 回顾过去就很容易明白我们的错处了。 2. In retrospect, that campaign looks like his last hurrah. 回顾起来，那次竞选看起来像是他的最后奋力一博。 3. In retrospect all successful policies seem preordained. 追溯一切成功的政策，看来都有其预兆。 4. In retrospect, it\'s easy to see why we were wrong. 回顾过去就很容易明白我们的错处了。', '名词: retrospection 过去式: retrospected 过去分词: retrospected 现在分词: retrospecting 第三人称单数: retrospects');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('clash', '[klæʃ]', 'n.冲突,撞击声,抵触;v.(使)发出撞击声,猛撞,冲突', '1. A border clash between the two armies started the war. 双方军队在边境的冲突引发了战争。 2. In some ways,ours is a clash of cultures. 从某种意义上来说，我们的冲突是不同文化间的冲突。 3. The issue really boils down to a clash between left and right. 这场争论确实可归结为左派与右派之间的冲突。 4. His opinions clash against yours. 他的观点和你的相抵触。 5. She clashed these pans down on the floor. 她将这些盘子哗啦一声摔在地上。 6. The enemy armies clashed near the border. 敌军在边境附近发生冲突。', '过去式: clashed 过去分词: clashed 现在分词: clashing 第三人称单数: clashes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('garment', '[\'ɡɑːrmənt]', 'n.衣服,外衣,外表', '1. This garment should be washed carefully. 这件衣服应该小心地洗涤。 2. The garment fits her perfectly. 这件衣服她穿上很合适。 3. In spring nature wears a new garment. 春天', '过去式: garmented 过去分词: garmented 现在分词: garmenting 第三人称单数: garments');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tilt', '[tɪlt]', 'v.(使)倾斜,(使)翘起,以言词或文字抨击', '1. Don\'t tilt your chair back so far, it might fall over. 别把椅子一个劲向后倾斜，它会翻倒的。 2. If you tilt the table,the dishes will slide off onto the floor. 如果你使桌子倾斜，碟子就会滑到地板上。 3. The table top suddenly tilted and all the plates and glasses crashed onto the floor. 桌面突然翘起，所有的盘子和玻璃制品都滑落到地板上打碎了。 4. Tilt pump downward and remove from engine. 将泵向下倾斜，从引擎移出。 5. He is bold enough to tilt at social injustices. 他敢于抨击社会上的不公正现象。 6. Such a tilt is unusual in the solar system. 这样的倾斜在太阳系中不常见。', '名词: tilter 过去式: tilted 过去分词: tilted 现在分词: tilting 第三人称单数: tilts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('superior', '[suː\'pɪriər]', 'n.长者,高手,上级;adj.较高的,上级的,上好的,出众的,高傲的', '1. He always does what his superiors tell him. 他惟上级之命是从。 2. He has no superior as a Shakespearian actor. 他演莎士比亚戏剧无出其右。 3. He smiled a superior smile as he drove past in his expensive new car. 他开着那辆豪华的新车驶过时，傲慢的微微一笑。 4. I\'ll report you to your superior officer! 我要把你的情况报告给你的上司！', '副词: superiorly 名词: superiority');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('confidential', '[ˌkɑːnfɪ\'denʃl]', 'adj.秘密的,机密的', '1. He has been on confidential missions to Berlin. 他前往柏林执行秘密任务。 2. He told me the confidential information. 他向我透露了这个秘密的信息。 3. He was an author whose works were so little known as to be almost confidential. 他这位作家的著作是如此不为人所知，以致几乎等于机密文件。 4. Don\'t be too confidential with strangers. 不要过份相信陌生人。', '副词: confidentially 名词: confidentiality');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('safeguard', '[\'seɪfɡɑːrd]', 'vt.维护,保护,捍卫;n.安全装置,安全措施', '1. There is no safeguard against inappropriate data types being added. 没有保护措施来防止添加不适当的数据类型。 2. We must safeguard our national interests. 我们必须保卫国家的利益。 3. To safeguard the peace is one of the important tasks of the army. 军队的重要任务之一是保卫和平。 4. Safeguard records from damage or deterioration. 保护以防记录损坏或变质。', '过去式: safeguarded 过去分词: safeguarded 现在分词: safeguarding 第三人称单数: safeguards');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('solidarity', '[ˌsɑːlɪ\'dærəti]', 'n.团结', '1. Their sense of solidarity is very low. 他们的团结观念非常薄弱。 2. The strike fostered a sense of solidarity among the workers. 罢工促进了工人之间的团结。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('criticism', '[\'krɪtɪsɪzəm]', 'n.批评,批判', '1. He is impervious to criticism. 他对批评我行我素。 2. His behavior called forth sharp criticism. 他的行为招致尖锐的批评。 3. Such a questionable assertion is sure to provoke criticism. 这种有问题的主张肯定会招致非议。 4. I don\'t like to read his literary criticism. 我不喜欢读他的文学批评。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('precedent', '[\'presɪdənt]', 'n.先例', '1. This decision creates a dangerous precedent. 这个决定开创了一个危险的先例。 2. My decision does not constitute a precedent. 我的决定下不为例。 3. This intervention in another nation\'s affairs has set a precedent which we hope other countries will not follow. 对别国事物的这种干涉开了一个先例，我们希望其他国家不要模仿。 4. The President followed historical precedent in forming the Cabinet. 总统遵循历史惯例来组成内阁。 5. The precedent decision should be understood before we act. 在采取行动之前我们应该弄明白先前的决定。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('passive', '[\'pæsɪv]', 'adj.被动的', '1. He played a passive role in the marriage. 他在婚姻中扮演了一个被动的角色。 2. You are passive when you allow things to happen, but do nothing. 当你让这些事发生,而不做任何事来阻止它,你是消极的。 3. Good is the passive that obeys reason. 善是服从理智的被动性。 4. Passive tear suctioning force can be demonstrated by a Venturi tube model. 被动性泪液吸引之力量，可藉由文氏管模型来解释。', '副词: passively 名词: passiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('penguin', '[\'peŋɡwɪn]', 'n.企鹅', '1. The penguin is a flightless bird. 企鹅是一种不会飞的鸟。 2. The birth of a baby penguin in the zoo was widely reported. 动物园里小企鹅的出生受到了广泛的报道。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('stray', '[streɪ]', 'v.迷路,偏离,漂泊,漂泊游荡;adj.迷路的,离群的,偶遇的', '1. That cat is a stray that we took in. 那是我们收养的一只走失的猫。 2. We were befriended by a stray dog. 有一只失散的狗和我们很好。 3. A stray bullet hit her in the leg. 一颗流弹击中她的腿部。 4. The streets were empty except for a few stray taxis. 除了偶然可以看到的 几辆出租车外 5. Pound the cows so they don\'t stray. 把这些走失的牛关进待领场，这样它们就不会乱跑了。', '名词: strayer 过去式: strayed 过去分词: strayed 现在分词: straying 第三人称单数: strays');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('phenomenon', '[fə\'nɑːmɪnən]', 'n.现象', '1. Their so-called prosperity is only a temporary phenomenon. 但他们所谓的繁荣只是一个暂时的现象。 2. International terrorism is not just a recent phenomenon. 国际恐怖主义并不是近年才有的现象。 3. Magnetism is a natural phenomenon. 磁力是一种自然现象。 4. A child who could read at the age of one would indeed be a phenomenon. 一个一岁的孩子能阅读，会被认为是个神童。', '名词复数: phenomena');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('manufacturer', '[ˌmænju\'fæktʃərər]', 'n.制造业者,厂商', '1. My husband is now a purse manufacturer. 我先生现在是手提包制造商。 2. The manufacturer built the machine to order. 制造商按照定货规格制造了这台机器。 3. They bought the machine directly from the manufacturer. 他们直接从厂商那里购买了这台机器。 4. She wants to buy direct from the manufacturer and cut out the middleman. 她想避开分销商直接自厂家买进货物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pressure', '[\'preʃər]', 'n.压,压力,电压,压迫,强制,紧迫', '1. My father suffers from high blood pressure. 我父亲有高血压。 2. The pressure of work was too great for him. 工作的压力使他承受不了。 3. He works well under pressure. 他在有压力的情况下工作很出色。 4. The tooth became sore to pressure and there is a dull gnawing pain. 该齿对于压迫作痛，且有钝麻如咬的疼痛。 5. Now you are trying to pressure me. 你现在试图向我施压。', '过去式: pressured 过去分词: pressured 现在分词: pressuring 第三人称单数: pressures');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('avoid', '[ə\'vɔɪd]', 'vt.避免,消除', '1. You should avoid unnecessary repetition. 你应避免不必要的重复。 2. They all avoided mentioning that name. 他们都避免提及那名字。 3. He\'ll grab at any excuse to avoid doing the dishes. 他会随便找个借口来逃避洗碗。 4. No one can avoid his own responsibility. 没有人能够逃避自己的责任。', '形容词: avoidable 副词: avoidably 名词: avoider 过去式: avoided 过去分词: avoided 现在分词: avoiding 第三人称单数: avoids');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('impulse', '[\'ɪmpʌls]', 'n.推动,刺激,冲动,推动力;vt.推动', '1. He bought the house on an impulse. 他凭一时冲动买下了这所房子。 2. We were seized by a sudden impulse to run. 我们身不由己突然想跑。 3. On impulse, I picked up the phone and rang my sister in Australia. 我一时心血来潮，拿起话筒就给在澳大利亚的妹妹打了个电话。 4. He had a sudden impulse to stand up and sing. 他突然心血来潮，想站起来歌唱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('statesman', '[\'steɪtsmən]', 'n.政治家', '1. The statesman is respected by people. 这位政治家为人们所敬重。 2. He will go down in history as a great statesman. 他将作为伟大的政治家而载入史册。', '形容词: statesmanlike 名词: statesmanship');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('prejudice', '[\'predʒudɪs]', 'n.偏见,成见,损害,侵害;v.损害', '1. She has a prejudice against modern music. 她对现代音乐怀有偏见。 2. A judge must be free from prejudice. 法官必须不抱成见。 3. The offer was accepted without prejudice to the current pay negotiations. 该提议获得接纳，但对目前正在进行的工资谈判并无影响。 4. A new law has been brought in to discourage racial prejudice. 一项反对种族歧视的新法律已被提出。 5. Your bad spelling may prejudice your chances of getting this job. 你糟糕的拼写会妨碍你获得这个工作的机会。', '过去式: prejudiced 过去分词: prejudiced 现在分词: prejudicing 第三人称单数: prejudices');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('entitle', '[ɪn\'taɪtl]', 'vt.给...权利(或资格),给...题名,给...称号;v.授权,授权', '1. She read a poem entitled The Apple Tree. 她读了一首题为《苹果树》的诗。 2. He entitled the book Savage Love. 他给这本书取名为《野性的爱》。 3. His services entitle him to our respect. 凭他的功劳他应受我们尊敬。 4. Your qualifications entitle you to a higher salary. 你的资格使你有权享有较高的薪水。', '名词: entitlement 过去式: entitled 过去分词: entitled 现在分词: entitling 第三人称单数: entitles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ventilate', '[\'ventɪleɪt]', 'vt.使通风,给...装通风设备', '1. We ventilate a room by opening windows. 我们开窗以使室内空气流通。 2. They should ventilate the galleries of a coal-mine. 他们应该使煤矿坑道通风。 3. Ventilate the spillage area thoroughly. 完全使漏地区通风。', '名词: ventilation 过去式: ventilated 过去分词: ventilated 现在分词: ventilating 第三人称单数: ventilates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dock', '[dɑːk]', 'n.<美>码头,船坞,被告席,尾巴的骨肉部分;vt.靠码头,引入坞,剪短;vi.入船坞', '1. The ship\'s hull scraped along the side of the dock. 船行时船身擦着码头的边。 2. The cruise ship is strikebound in the dock. 巡洋舰因罢工而停泊在码头上。 3. The liner is in dock for a refit. 班轮正在船坞修理。 4. The yacht is lying up in the dock. 那条游艇正停在船坞里。 5. He rowed up the canal looking for a place to dock the boat. 他在运河里划船，寻找一个码头泊船。', '过去式: docked 过去分词: docked 现在分词: docking 第三人称单数: docks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rot', '[rɑːt]', 'v.(使)腐烂,(使)腐败;n.腐烂,腐败', '1. Foot rot is an avoidable affiction. 烂蹄病是可以避免的。 2. Rot in the tree trunk caused the tree to fall. 树干的腐烂导致树倒了。 3. The roof timbers were affected by rot and insect attack. 屋顶的木料已经腐朽并遭虫害。 4. We should stop it the minute the rot sets in. 腐败一产生，我们就应立即制止住。 5. This cheap wine will rot your stomach. 这种劣质葡萄喝了会伤胃。', '过去式: rotted 过去分词: rotted 现在分词: rotting 第三人称单数: rots');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ancestor', '[\'ænsestər]', 'n.祖先,祖宗', '1. During the festival the investor investigated his ancestor. 节日期间投资者调查了他的祖宗。 2. They said their ancestor was a famous hunter and a crack hunter. 他们说他们的祖宗是个有名的猎人，也是个神枪手。 3. People who share an ancestor are called relatives. 有同一个祖先的叫做亲戚。 4. She has worshipped her ancestor. 她已拜过她的祖先。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('racket', '[\'rækɪt]', 'n.球拍,喧闹纷乱;v.过着花天酒地的生活', '1. The ball just tipped the edge of his racket. 球仅仅碰到他球拍的边儿。 2. My hands blistered from holding the racket. 我的手因握球拍而起了水疱。 3. What a racket the children are making! 这些孩子太吵了！ 4. The students kicked up no end of a racket in the street. 这些学生在大街上大吵大闹。 5. The children always racket about in the courtyard. 孩子们总是在院子里吵吵闹闹。', '过去式: racketed 过去分词: racketed 现在分词: racketing 第三人称单数: rackets');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('clarity', '[\'klærəti]', 'n.清楚,透明', '1. These adjectives mean lacking clarity of meaning. 这些形容词都有意思不清楚的含义。 2. Let me try to provide some clarity. 让我提供一些清楚的信息。 3. Clarity is very important for a business letter. 文笔清晰对于商业信件非常重要。 4. Clarity of dictionis vital for a public speaker. 发音清晰对演说家至关重要。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('quench', '[kwentʃ]', 'vt.结束,熄灭，淬火;vi.熄灭,平息', '1. Water will quench a fire. 水可以灭火。 2. Nothing could quench her longing to return home again. 她重返家园的念头怎么也打消不掉。 3. Hot steel is quenched to harden it. 烧热的钢淬火使它坚硬。 4. Her sarcastic remarks quenched his passion. 她讽刺的话冷却了他的热情。', '形容词: quenchable 名词: quencher 过去式: quenched 过去分词: quenched 现在分词: quenching 第三人称单数: quenches');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('consequent', '[\'kɒnsəˌkwent]', 'adj.作为结果的,随之发生的', '1. Finally, suggestions on policy were referred to consequent conclusions. 文章最后根据分析结论提出了相关政策建议。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('condemn', '[kən\'dem]', 'vt.判刑,处刑,声讨,谴责', '1. We must not condemn her on pure supposition. 我们不能单凭猜测就谴责她。 2. We condemn all sorts of slanders. 我们谴责一切诽谤中伤的言论。 3. Most people are willing to condemn violence. 大部分的人极力谴责暴力。 4. The criminal was condemned to death. 这个罪犯被判死刑。', '形容词: condemnable 名词: condemner 过去式: condemned 过去分词: condemned 现在分词: condemning 第三人称单数: condemns');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('profitable', '[\'prɑːfɪtəbl]', 'adj.有利可图的', '1. Betty believed yoga was a very profitable exercise. 贝蒂认为瑜伽是一项非常有益的锻炼。 2. We hope the transaction may lead to a mutually profitable connection between us. 我方希望此次交易能导致对贵我双方有益的联系。 3. The signs bid fair for a profitable deal. 迹象表明可能是一笔有利可图的买卖。 4. Growing grapes for wine became very profitable. 种植葡萄生产葡萄酒变得非常有利可图。', '副词: profitably 名词: profitability');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('incentive', '[ɪn\'sentɪv]', 'n.动机;adj.激励的', '1. Haier is operating with the mechanism of Incentive Management. 海尔实行激励管理机制。 2. We should be incentive to further study in this subject. 我们应在这一课题上鼓励进一步研究。 3. To support the family is an incentive for him to work hard. 养家糊口是他努力工作的刺激因素。 4. Incentives differ from country to country and region to region and are always highest in a depressed area. 这些鼓励措施在国与国、地区与地区之间都不尽相同。一般萧条地区提供的鼓励最高。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tackle', '[\'tækl]', 'n.工具,复滑车,滑车,辘轱,用具,装备,扭倒;vt.固定,应付(难事等),处理,解决,抓住;vi.捉住,扭住,扭倒', '1. Can you suggest how we might tackle the problem? 我们怎样处理这问题，你能给出个主意吗? 2. I suggested to him that we should tackle the problem another way. 我向他建议我们用另一种方式处理这个问题。 3. I\'ll tackle the boss for a raise. 我将与老板交涉要求增加薪水。 4. If Bill is late again I will tackle him about it . 如果彼尔再迟到的话，我就得和他开诚布公地谈谈了。 5. The cupboard was stuffed with old fishing tackle. 小橱里塞满了旧的钓鱼用具。', '名词: tackler 过去式: tackled 过去分词: tackled 现在分词: tackling 第三人称单数: tackles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('despise', '[dɪ\'spaɪz]', 'vt.轻视', '1. He claims to despise riches. 他宣称蔑视钱财。 2. You must not despise a man because he is poor. 你不可因一个人贫穷而轻视他。 3. I despise his refusing to accept responsibility. 他拒不承担责任，我鄙视他。 4. It is incorrect to despise woman. 轻视妇女是错误的。', '名词: despisal 过去式: despised 过去分词: despised 现在分词: despising 第三人称单数: despises');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('degrade', '[dɪ\'ɡreɪd]', 'v.(使)降级,(使)堕落,(使)退化', '1. You should not degrade yourself by telling such a lie. 你不该说那样的谎话降低自己的人格。 2. I felt degraded by having to ask for money. 不得不向别人要钱,我感到有失尊严。 3. No one can degrade us except ourselves. 除了我们自己，没有人能贬低我们。 4. For some reason our balancing reflexes degrade with age. 我们的平衡反射，由于某种原因，随着年龄的增长而退化。', '名词: degrader 过去式: degraded 过去分词: degraded 现在分词: degrading 第三人称单数: degrades');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('donation', '[doʊ\'neɪʃn]', 'n.捐赠品,捐款,贡献', '1. He asked for a donation but went away empty handed. 他请求人们捐款，但离开时却一无所获！ 2. The club received a benevolent donation. 该俱乐部接受了一笔慈善捐款。 3. A wealthy sponsor came to our rescue with a generous donation. 有个富有的赞助人慷慨捐赠来解救我们。 4. This is a donation of money to the disaster area. 这是捐赠给灾区的钱.', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('moan', '[moʊn]', 'n.呻吟,哀悼,呼啸;vi.发出呻吟声,抱怨,哀悼;vt.呻吟', '1. Each time she moved her head she let out a moan. 她每转动一下头，就发出一声呻吟。 2. A moan escaped the badly wounded soldier. 那个重伤员不禁呻吟了一声。 3. His constant moan is that no one understands him. 他老是抱怨没有人理解他。 4. She moaned her misfortunes to anyone who would listen. 她向任何乐于听的人哀叹命运不济。 5. Suddenly he began to moan in his sleep. 突然他在睡梦中开始呻吟。', '过去式: moaned 过去分词: moaned 现在分词: moaning 第三人称单数: moans');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fantasy', '[\'fæntəsi]', 'n.幻想,白日梦', '1. The young always live in a world of fantasy. 年轻人总是生活在幻想中。 2. He is unable to divorce fantasy from reality. 他不能将幻想与现实分开。 3. He fantasies himself a doctor. 他想像自己是一位医生。', '名词复数: fantasies 过去式: fantasied 过去分词: fantasied 现在分词: fantasying 第三人称单数: fantasies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('junk', '[dʒʌŋk]', 'n.垃圾,舢板', '1. Eating too much junk food is bad for your health. 垃圾食品吃得太多对健康有害。 2. I will throw away all of my useless junk. 我会扔掉我所有无用的垃圾。 3. The junk was piled up in the basement. 垃圾被堆放在地下室。 4. She likes to pick up some interesting junk in junk shops. 她喜欢在旧货店买些有趣的旧货。 5. I suggest you junk the old car and buy a new one. 我建议你把旧车扔了,买一辆新的吧。', '过去式: junked 过去分词: junked 现在分词: junking 第三人称单数: junks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('principal', '[\'prɪnsəpl]', 'n.负责人,首长,校长,主犯,本金;adj.主要的,首要的', '1. Our principal problem is lack of time. 我们的主要问题就是缺少时间。 2. My wages are the principal source of my income. 薪金是我收入的主要来源。 3. My principal concern is my family\'s welfare. 我至为关心的是我一家的幸福。 4. How much interest will there be on a principal of $5000? 5000美元本金的利息是多少？', '副词: principally 名词: principalship');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('duplicate', '[\'duːplɪkət]', 'adj.复制的,副的,两重的,两倍的,完全相同;n.复制品,副本;vt.复写,复制,使加倍,使成双', '1. This is a duplicate. 这是个副本。 2. It\'s a duplicate set of keys 这是和另一套完全相同的钥匙. 3. Here is a duplicate copy. 这是份复制的文本。 4. Please duplicate the document for me! 请帮我复写下这份公文。', '形容词: duplicable 副词: duplicately 过去式: duplicated 过去分词: duplicated 现在分词: duplicating 第三人称单数: duplicates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('whirl', '[wɜːrl]', 'v.(使)旋转,急动,急走;n.旋转,—连串快速的活动', '1. It may whirl either clockwise or counterclockwise. 它可能顺时针方向或反时针方向旋转。 2. The electron continues to whirl about the proton. 电子继续绕着质子转。 3. The wind whirled the dead leaves about. 风吹得枯叶在四处回旋。 4. The houses whirled past us as the train gathered speed. 火车越开越快，周围的房子在我们旁边一闪而过。 5. The colorful whirl of the dancer is beautiful to watch. 舞蹈者多彩多姿的旋转令人赏心悦目。', '名词: whirler 过去式: whirled 过去分词: whirled 现在分词: whirling 第三人称单数: whirls');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hamper', '[\'hæmpər]', 'v.妨碍,牵制', '1. Our progress was hampered by the bad weather. 我们前进时受到了恶劣天气的阻碍。 2. Outdated conventions and bad customs hamper the growth of production. 陈规陋习妨碍生产的发展。 3. The heavy rain hampers the flow of traffic. 大雨阻碍了交通运行。 4. There are some apples in a picnic hamper. 在野餐用的大篮子里有许多苹果。', '过去式: hampered 过去分词: hampered 现在分词: hampering 第三人称单数: hampers');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('inhabitant', '[ɪn\'hæbɪtənt]', 'n.居民,居住者', '1. Every inhabitant here has an obligation to pay taxes. 这里的每一位居民都有纳税的义务。 2. The inhabitant can see the Church House and the Death House， but never the exterior of the Court House. 居民也能看到教会安置和死囚刑前的住房，但从未见过法院的外貌。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sour', '[\'saʊər]', 'adj.酸的,发酵的,酸腐的,酸味的', '1. Most green fruit is sour. 大多数未熟的水果都是酸的。 2. The dish\'s gone sour. 这菜已经变质了。 3. He\'s always got a sour look on his face, and he has never said anything friendly. 他总是板着脸,从来不说一句好听的话。 4. The hot weather has soured the milk. 炎热的天气使牛奶变酸了。', '形容词: sourish 副词: sourly 比较级: sourer 最高级: sourest 名词: sourness 过去式: soured 过去分词: soured 现在分词: souring 第三人称单数: sours');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('destination', '[ˌdestɪ\'neɪʃn]', 'n.目的地,[计]目的文件,目的单元格', '1. We eventually arrived at our destination. 我们终于到达了目的地。 2. The parcel was sent to the wrong destination. 包裹送错了地方。 3. The coach followed a rather devious course to its destination. 长途汽车要绕很多弯路才到达目的地。 4. The destination of bus No. 8 is the State University. 8路车的终点是州立大学。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ego', '[\'iːɡoʊ]', 'n.自我,利已主义,自负', '1. We can\'t transcend the limitations of the ego. 我们无法超越自我的局限性。 2. Mind consists of three parts: id, ego and superego. 人的思想意识由三部分构成:以德,自我和超我。 3. He has the biggest ego of anyone I\'ve ever met. 他是我所见的最自负的人。 4. His ego was tickled by the implicit flattery of the journalist\'s attention. 那个记者的蓄意奉承使他的自负得到了满足。', '名词复数: egos');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('accessory', '[ək\'sesəri]', 'n.附件,零件,附加物,从犯,同谋者;adj.附属的,补充的,同谋的,副的', '1. He asked me to buy him some accessories for a car. 他让我给他买些汽车附件。 2. Every item shall include a standard complement of accessories and special tools to ensure the normal operation. 为保证设备的正常运转，每个品目都应包括一套标准定额的附件和专用工具。 3. This silk scarf is the perfect accessory for stylish summer evenings. 这条丝绸围巾对于这个时髦的夏日夜晚,是再合适不过的配件了。 4. He is Tom\'s accessory. 他是汤姆的帮凶。 5. He was using his accessory muscles of respiration. 他在用呼吸辅助肌进行呼吸。', '形容词: accessorial 副词: accessorily 名词: accessoriness 名词复数: accessories');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('alleviate', '[ə\'liːvieɪt]', 'vt.使(痛苦等)易于忍受,减轻', '1. They alleviated the boredom of waiting by singing songs. 他们以唱歌来减轻等候的厌烦。 2. The doctor gave her an injection to alleviate the pain. 医生给她注射以减轻疼痛。 3. This medicine will alleviate your sore throat. 这种药会减轻你的嗓子痛。 4. He could only alleviate the sorrow by drinking. 他只能借酒浇愁。', '名词: alleviation 过去式: alleviated 过去分词: alleviated 现在分词: alleviating 第三人称单数: alleviates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dole', '[doʊl]', 'n.施舍品,悲哀,失业救济金;vt.发放救济', '1. I doled out the food to all the children. 我把食品发放给所有的孩子们。 2. You can\'t expect us to dole out money like a public charity. 你们不能指望我们像慈善机构一样分钱。 3. Life on the dole brings sadness to the soul. 靠人施舍过活，精神不会好受。 4. He received the fixed dole every month. 他每个月都能领到固定的救济金。', '过去式: doled 过去分词: doled 现在分词: doling 第三人称单数: doles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('carve', '[kɑːrv]', 'v.雕刻,切开', '1. The statue was carved out of marble. 这座雕像是用大理石雕刻的。 2. We will look for a pumpkin, to carve into a jack-o-lantern. 我们将要找一颗南瓜来雕刻成南瓜灯。 3. He carved me some very nice pieces of chicken. 他为我切了几块很好的鸡肉。 4. It\'s your turn to carve the meat. 该你来把肉切开了。', '名词: carver 过去式: carved 过去分词: carved 现在分词: carving 第三人称单数: carves');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('contempt', '[kən\'tempt]', 'n.轻视,轻蔑,耻辱,不尊敬,[律]藐视法庭(或国会)', '1. Her gesture was indicative of contempt. 她的动作表示轻视。 2. Such behaviour is beneath contempt. 这种行为令人不齿。 3. They showed nothing but contempt for him. 他们对他轻蔑已极。 4. Her behavior underlined her contempt for him. 她的态度清楚地表示了对他的轻蔑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('athlete', '[\'æθliːt]', 'n.运动员,运动选手', '1. The athlete is suffering from muscular strain. 这名运动员正受肌肉劳损之苦。 2. She will make a very good athlete. 她将来会成为一名很好的运动员。 3. The athlete has an electrifying burst of speed. 这名运动员具有惊人的爆发速度。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dine', '[daɪn]', 'vi.吃饭,进餐', '1. She told me she would have to dine with Helen that night. 她告诉我那夜她必须与海伦一起进餐。 2. Every weekend, we dine at a nice little restaurant in the neighbourhood. 每个周末，我们在附近一家别致的小餐馆进餐。', '过去式: dined 过去分词: dined 现在分词: dining 第三人称单数: dines');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('corresponding', '[ˌkɔːrə\'spɑːndɪŋ]', 'adj.相应的,通讯的', '1. You will be punished in a way corresponding to your profession. 你们将受到相当于你的职业的处罚。 2. Sales are up 10% on the corresponding period last year. 销售额和去年同时期相比增加了10%25。 3. Investment in the subway will bring a corresponding improvement in services. 对地铁进行投资将使服务得到相应的提升。 4. The corresponding results have a good agreement with the reactor dynamics. 得到了与相应反应堆动力学很一致的结果。', '副词: correspondingly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('subsidiary', '[səb\'sɪdieri]', 'adj.辅助的,补充的', '1. be disguised by(with) sth 2. A lack of corporate interest has made the subsidiary an orphan. 因缺乏共同利益,这家附属机构无人管理。 3. I plan to study journalism as a subsidiary course. 我打算辅修新闻学。 4. Public transportation plays a subsidiary role. 公共交通起辅助的作用。', '副词: subsidiarily 名词复数: subsidiaries');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('propagate', '[\'prɑːpəɡeɪt]', 'v.繁殖,传播,宣传', '1. Most plants propagate by seed. 大多数植物靠种子繁殖。 2. Insects propagate themselves by means of eggs. 昆虫以产卵繁殖后代。 3. This kind of cell propagates faster in warm environment. 在温暖的环境中,这种细胞增殖更快。 4. We should propagate scientific ideas . 我们应该传播科学思想。', '形容词: propagable 名词: propagator 过去式: propagated 过去分词: propagated 现在分词: propagating 第三人称单数: propagates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tissue', '[\'tɪʃuː]', 'n.薄的纱织品,薄纸,棉纸,[生]组织,连篇', '1. She gave us a box of tissues. 她递给我们一盒纸巾。 2. She wiped off the sweat from her face with a piece of facial tissue. 她用一张面巾纸擦掉脸上的汗水。 3. On her head was a tiny cap of silver tissue. 她头上戴着一顶银丝小帽。 4. Human tissue is made up of cells. 人体的组织是由细胞构成的。', '形容词: tissuey');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('deficit', '[\'defɪsɪt]', 'n.赤字,不足额', '1. The current trade deficit indicates a serious imbalance between our import and export trade. 当前的贸易赤字表明我们的进出口贸易严重失调。 2. That would still leave a substantial trade deficit. 这样仍然会出现巨额贸易逆差。 3. We have a great deficit this year. 我们今年有很大亏损。 4. The company had a deficit of 5000 dollars. 公司亏空了五千美元。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('potential', '[pə\'tenʃl]', 'adj.潜在的,可能的,势的,位的;n.潜能,潜力,电压', '1. These potential effects must be studied carefully. 这些潜在的影响必须仔细地加以研究。 2. Aha! Now that \'s something that has potential . 啊！ 现在这好像是很有可能的。 3. She has acting potential, but she needs training. 她有表演潜力，但需要训练。 4. He hasn\'t realized his full potential yet. 他还没有意识到他的全部潜能。 5. We can only measure the difference between the potentials of two half cells when they are linked to form an electrochemical cell. 当两个半电池连接形成一个化学电池时,我们仅能测定两个半电池之间电位的差值。', '副词: potentially');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('volume', '[\'vɑːljuːm]', 'n.卷,册,体积,量,大量,音量', '1. This volume contains selections from his early works. 该卷包含了他的早期作品文选。 2. This volume is foxed on the flyleaf. 这卷书的空白页发黄了。 3. A gas has neither definite volume nor definite shape. 气体既无一定体积,又无一定形状。 4. Is that volume still in print? 那册书还能买到吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bud', '[bʌd]', 'n.芽,蓓蕾;vi.发芽,萌芽', '1. The roses are in bud. 玫瑰花正含苞待放。 2. Summertime bud grafting can be cut take shoot piece, or take xylem shoot less piece, in stock bine dry place decorticates. 夏季芽接可削取芽片,或少带木质部芽片,在砧木茎干处剥皮。 3. The bud developed into a blossom. 花蕾开出了鲜花。 4. The magnolia tree is in bud already. 木兰树已经长出花蕾了。 5. Trees begin to bud in the spring. 树在春天开始发芽。 6. Some flowers bud their leaves very early in spring. 有些花在春季里很早发出叶来。', '名词: budder 过去式: budded 过去分词: budded 现在分词: budding 第三人称单数: buds');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('endurance', '[ɪn\'dʊrəns]', 'n.忍耐(力),持久(力),耐久(性)', '1. She exhibited great powers of endurance during the climb. 她在攀登过程中表现出极大的耐力。 2. I honour endurance, perseverance, industry, talent. 我尊敬忍耐、坚毅，勤劳、才干。 3. Her endurance of pain was incredible. 她对痛苦的忍耐力令人难以置信。 4. She was outstanding where endurance was called for. 她在需要忍耐力的地方表现优异。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('restraint', '[rɪ\'streɪnt]', 'n.抑制,制止,克制', '1. The police appealed to the crowd for restraint. 警方呼吁群众保持克制。 2. Nobody could count on his restraint or rationality. 谁也不能指望他会克制或讲道理的态度。 3. There is still need for profit restraint. 现在仍有必要限制利润。 4. His rage was beyond restraint. 他怒不可遏。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('disastrous', '[dɪ\'zæstrəs]', 'adj.损失惨重的,悲伤的', '1. The new system has had a disastrous effect on productivity. 新制度已对生产力造成了灾难性的影响。 2. This environmental effect of this new factory could be disastrous. 这家新工厂给自然环境带来的影响可能是灾难性的。 3. Such a mistake would perhaps lead to disastrous consequences. 这样一种错误可能导致灾难性的后果。 4. The economic position of the country is disastrous. 国家的经济形势非常糟糕。', '副词: disastrously 名词: disastrousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('element', '[\'elɪmənt]', 'n.要素,元素,成分,元件,自然环境', '1. Justice is an important element of good government. 公正是仁政的要素. 2. Honesty, industry and kindness are elements of a good life. 诚实、勤劳和善良是幸福生活的要素。 3. Water is composed of the elements hydrogen and oxygen. 水是由氢元素和氧元素组成的。 4. You must understand the elements of mathematics before we can proceed further. 你必须先弄懂数学基础知识，我们才能进一步学习。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('melody', '[\'melədi]', 'n.悦耳的音调', '1. The melody still rang in her ears. 那个旋律仍然在她的耳际荡。 2. The organist played a famous melody. 这位管风琴手演奏了一首著名的曲子。 3. He played a delightful melody on his flute. 他用笛子吹奏了欢快的曲调。 4. The song has plaintive melody. 这首歌曲的曲调悲伤。', '名词复数: melodies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('conclude', '[kən\'kluːd]', 'v.结束,终止,决定,作出结论;vt.推断,断定,缔结,议定', '1. From his appearance we may safely conclude that he is a chain smoker. 从他的外表，我们可以有把握地断定他烟抽得很凶。 2. The two countries are reported to have concluded a military convention. 据报导,这两个国家已缔结军事协定。 3. He conclude the negotiation with dispatch. 他迅速结束谈判。 4. The concert concluded with the National Anthem. 音乐会最后以演奏国歌结束。', '名词: concluder 过去式: concluded 过去分词: concluded 现在分词: concluding 第三人称单数: concludes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('proposition', '[ˌprɑːpə\'zɪʃn]', 'n.主张,建议,陈述,命题', '1. His proposition is good in theory but cannot be put into practice. 他的建议在理论上可以，但不能付诸实现。 2. This is the inverse of his earlier proposition. 这和他早些时候提的建议截然相反。 3. This is not money-making proposition. 这不是个赚钱的事业。 4. Tunnelling under the English Channel is a big proposition. 在英吉利海峡海底凿隧道是一个大问题。 5. She was propositioned several times in the course of the evening. 整个晚上有人几次向她提出非分要求。', '形容词: propositional 副词: propositionally 过去式: propositioned 过去分词: propositioned 现在分词: propositioning 第三人称单数: propositions');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('gear', '[ɡɪr]', 'n.齿轮,传动装置;v.调整,(使)适合,换档', '1. Careless use of the clutch may damage the gears. 离合器使用不慎可能损坏传动装置。 2. The gear just would not come unstuck. 齿轮就是松不开来。 3. The car has four forward gear and one reverse gear. 那汽车有四个前进挡和一个倒挡。 4. Lifting electromagnet is a kind of lifting gear. 起重电磁铁是起重工具的一种。 5. Education should be geared to the children\'s needs and abilities. 教育应适应儿童的需要和能力。', '过去式: geared 过去分词: geared 现在分词: gearing 第三人称单数: gears');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('gorgeous', '[\'ɡɔːrdʒəs]', 'adj.华丽的,灿烂的', '1. The gorgeous costume added to the brilliance of the dance. 华丽的服装使舞蹈更加光彩夺目。 2. In the evening the rosy clouds were gorgeous. 傍晚的云霞绚丽多彩。 3. The garden is gorgeous with peonies. 花园里盛开着绚丽的牡丹花。 4. What a gorgeous day! 多美好的一天啊!', '副词: gorgeously 名词: gorgeousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('scandal', '[\'skændl]', 'n.丑行,丑闻,诽谤,耻辱,流言蜚语', '1. The scandal caused tempests in the newspaper. 那件丑闻在报纸上引起阵阵风波。 2. The villagers knew about the scandal. 村子里的居民知道这件丑事。 3. This scandal may topple the government. 这桩丑闻有可能使政府垮台。 4. The President is at the center of a recent scandal over revelation about his financial interests. 总统因近来被揭露涉嫌金融权益问题而成为丑闻的主角。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('savage', '[\'sævɪdʒ]', 'adj.野蛮的,未开化的,凶猛的,残忍的;vt.用暴力对付;n.原始的人,粗鲁的人', '1. Most of the time elephants are tame but they can be very savage. 大多数时候大象很温顺,但他们也会大发野性。 2. He was wild and savage, and no man could mount him, or do anything at all with him. 它既野又凶，谁都驾驭不了它，谁也对它没办法。 3. He smarted from the savage attacks on his film. 他因自己的影片受到猛烈攻击而感到痛心。 4. She was irritated by his savage behavior. 他的不文明行为激怒了她。 5. These civilizations flourished while Europeans were still savages living in caves. 当欧洲人还是居住在洞穴中的野蛮人时，这些地方的文化早已十分繁荣昌盛。 6. Smith\'s play was savaged by the critics. 史密斯的剧本遭到评论家的猛烈抨击。', '副词: savagely 名词: savageness 过去式: savaged 过去分词: savaged 现在分词: savaging 第三人称单数: savages');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('abnormal', '[æb\'nɔːrml]', 'adj.反常的,变态的;', '1. We were very surprised at his abnormal behavior. 我们对他的反常行为感到非常吃惊。 2. At one time, she is fine, but at another, she is abnormal. 有时候，她表现得很好，有时候又失常。 3. He is mentally abnormal. 他精神不正常。 4. It\'s abnormal for the boy to eat so much. 这个孩子吃这么多是不正常的。 5. This is an abnormal phenomenon and we must work seriously to eradicate it. 这是一种很不正常的现象，一定要认真扭转。', '副词: abnormally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('commend', '[kə\'mend]', 'vt.称赞,表扬,推荐,委托,吸引', '1. I should like to commend this method to you. 我想向您推荐这一方法。 2. I\'d like to commend him to my friends. 我愿意把他推荐给我的朋友们。 3. He commend them for their enthusiasm. 他称赞他们的热情。 4. The guests commend him upon his good manners 客人们称赞他有礼貌。', '形容词: commendable 副词: commendably 名词: commendableness 过去式: commended 过去分词: commended 现在分词: commending 第三人称单数: commends');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('inlet', '[\'ɪnlet]', 'n.进口,入口,水湾,小港,插入物', '1. The tide flushed through this narrow inlet. 潮水涌过了狭窄的小湾。 2. Here is just the fuel inlet. 这儿正是燃料入口。 3. There\'s only one inlet to the parking lot. 这个停车场只有一个入口。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('catholic', '[\'kæθlɪk]', 'n.天主教徒;adj.天主教的', '1. Anselm\'s theology is not Catholic faith. 安塞姆的神学并不是天主教的信念。 2. The atom bomb is of catholic concern. 原子弹受到普遍的关注。 3. As a young person he had more catholic tastes than he does now. 他在年轻时兴趣比现在广泛得多。 4. Leonardo da Vinci was a catholic genius who excelled in almost everything he did. 达文西是一个广泛的天才,他做的很多事也得到成功。 5. He was a Catholic but didn\'t practise his religion. 他那时是天主教徒，但并不实践信仰。', '副词: catholically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('symphony', '[\'sɪmfəni]', 'n.交响乐,交响曲', '1. The first movement of the symphony is beautiful. 这部交响乐的第一乐章是很优美的。 2. I like listening to the symphony. 我喜欢听交响乐。', '名词复数: symphonies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('petty', '[\'peti]', 'adj.小的,不重要的,小规模的,小型的,细微的,小器的,卑鄙的', '1. The party split into petty factions. 该党分裂成若干小派系。 2. The paymasters of these petty crooks are the big crime syndicates. 操纵这帮小流氓的就是那个大犯罪集团。 3. In his short life he had run the entire gamut of crime, from petty theft to murder. 他在短短的一生中,从小偷小摸到杀人,什么罪都犯过。 4. Don\'t bug me with petty details. 不要讲那些琐碎的细节来烦我。', '副词: pettily 比较级: pettier 最高级: pettiest 名词: pettiness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('comparison', '[kəm\'pærɪsn]', 'n.比较,对照,比喻,比较关系', '1. In comparison with other students, Mike is more diligent. 和其他学生相比，麦克更加勤勉一些。 2. We can only tell good from bad by comparison. 我们可以通过比较来分辨好坏。 3. Reports of consecutive years should also be available for comparison. 网站应登载连续数年的报告,方便读者作比较。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('flap', '[flæp]', 'n.拍打,拍打声,副翼;v.拍打,鼓翼而飞,飘动,拉下(帽)的边,扔,掷', '1. A flap from the tail of the whale upset the boat. 鲸尾轻轻一拍便把小船打翻了。 2. The flap of the birds drew the attention of a cat. 这群鸟不停地振翅吸引了一只猫的注意力。 3. I licked the flap of the envelope and sealed it. 我舔了舔信封盖口,把它封好。 4. I flap the flies away but soon they fly back. 我把苍蝇赶走，但一会儿又飞回来了。', '过去式: flapped 过去分词: flapped 现在分词: flapping 第三人称单数: flaps');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('attitude', '[\'ætɪtuːd]', 'n.姿势,态度,看法,意见', '1. We must maintain a firm attitude. 我们必须采取坚定的态度。 2. She shows a very positive attitude to her work. 她工作态度非常积极。 3. He has a mellow attitude to life. 他对生活有种成熟的看法。 4. As you get older, your attitude towards death changes. 人随著年龄的增长,对死亡的看法也会有所改变。', '形容词: attitudinal');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('maintain', '[meɪn\'teɪn]', 'vt.维持,维修,继续,供养,主张', '1. It is absolutely vital that food supplies should be maintained. 维持食物的供给是绝对必要的。 2. They also help us to maintain the machinery. 他们还帮助我们维修机器。 3. They tell the peasants in detail how to maintain the pumps. 他们详细地教给农民怎样保养抽水机。 4. It is clearly illogical to maintain such a proposition. 坚持这种主张显然是没有道理的。', '形容词: maintainable 名词: maintainability 过去式: maintained 过去分词: maintained 现在分词: maintaining 第三人称单数: maintains');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reel', '[riːl]', 'n.(棉纱,电线的)卷轴,(磁带等的)一盘,旋转,蹒跚;vt.卷...于轴上,使旋转;vi.蹒跚地走,旋转,眩晕,骚乱,退缩,摇晃', '1. I put a new reel of film in my camera. 我一卷新胶卷装入照相机。 2. When you\'re sure that you have hooked the fish, reel in at once. 当你确信鱼儿已经上钩时，赶紧收卷钓线。 3. Help me to reel up this powerful fish. 帮我收绕钓线拉起这条大鱼。 4. He cast the line suddenly just like throw it into the water and then reel it back. 他把线突然抛出，就像扔进水中一样，然后把线绕回。 5. My head reeled with the facts and figures. 我的脑子被一堆事实和数据搞得一片混乱 6. The reel of film is not in the proper order. 电影胶片卷盘的顺序弄错了。', '形容词: reelable 名词: reeler 过去式: reeled 过去分词: reeled 现在分词: reeling 第三人称单数: reels');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('migrate', '[\'maɪɡreɪt]', 'vi.移动,移往,移植,随季节而移居,(鸟类的)迁徙;vt.使移居,使移植', '1. These workers migrate from country to country in search of work. 这些工人为寻找工作从一个国家迁移到另一个国家。 2. Some tribes migrate with their cattle in search of fresh grass. 有些部落为了寻找新鲜的牧草而带着他们的牲畜迁移。 3. In some developing countries more and more people migrate to urban area. 在某些发展中的国家，越来越多的人向市区迁移。 4. Large numbers of birds migrate south every winter. 每年冬季大量的鸟类迁徙南方。', '名词: migrator 过去式: migrated 过去分词: migrated 现在分词: migrating 第三人称单数: migrates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('prey', '[preɪ]', 'n.被掠食者,牺牲者,掠食;vi.捕食,掠夺,折磨', '1. She fell (a) prey to melancholy. 她为忧郁所折磨。 2. She was easy prey for dishonest salesmen. 她很容易地让奸商敲了竹杠。 3. The lion seized its prey and ate it. 狮子抓住猎物，把它吃了。 4. The eagle seized its prey in a tenacious grip. 鹰将捕获物紧紧抓住。 5. In those far- off times Viking pirates used to prey on the coasts of Europe. 在那些遥远的时代里，北欧海盗经常在欧洲海岸一带进行掠夺。', '名词: preyer 过去式: preyed 过去分词: preyed 现在分词: preying 第三人称单数: preys');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('stroke', '[stroʊk]', 'n.击,敲,报时的钟声,(网球等)一击,(划船等)一划,(绘画等)一笔,一次努力,打击;vt.抚摸', '1. I know a doctor. He is expert in curing stroke. 我认识一个医生,专治中风。 2. He fell the tree with one stroke of the axe. 他一斧头就将树砍倒。 3. It\'s easy to draw a snake. Just one stroke. 画蛇不难,一笔就可以完成拉。 4. It was a stroke of luck that I found you here. 我在这里碰见你真是运气。 5. She stroked the ball cleverly past her opponent. 她巧妙地一击把球打过对手。 6. The cat likes being stroked. 猫喜欢让人抚摸。', '名词: stroker 过去式: stroked 过去分词: stroked 现在分词: stroking 第三人称单数: strokes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('evident', '[\'evɪdənt]', 'adj.明显的,显然的', '1. Now it became evident that he spoke two languages at once. 现在我才明白，原来他心里一套表面一套。 2. Inertia is evident in our every day experiences. 惯性在我们日常生活中是很常见的。 3. The purpose may not be immediately evident. 这种目的不一定显而易见。 4. The rationale for the present study is evident. 该研究的理论基础是明显的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('procedure', '[prə\'siːdʒər]', 'n.程序,手续', '1. These procedures are highly irregular. 这些程序是很不合乎规则的。 2. What\'s the procedure for opening a savings account? 开一个储蓄帐户有什么手续? 3. The next procedure is to insert the battery. 接下来的步骤是装进电池。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('outline', '[\'aʊtlaɪn]', 'n.大纲,轮廓,略图,外形,要点,概要;vt.描画轮廓,略述', '1. He wrote down the outline of his lecture. 他写下演讲的提纲。 2. She drew the outline with a sure hand. 她笔力雄健地画出了轮廓。 3. He saw the outline of the house in the moonlight. 在月光下,他看到了那座屋子的轮廓。 4. At the interview, she outlined what i would be doing. 在谈话时,她概述了我将要干的工作。', '过去式: outlined 过去分词: outlined 现在分词: outlining 第三人称单数: outlines');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('highlight', '[\'haɪlaɪt]', 'n.加亮区,精彩场面,最显著(重要)部分;vt.加亮,使显著,以强光照射,突出', '1. Both books highlight the human element of science. 两本书都重点谈到科学中人的因素。 2. Mr Bush also wants to highlight African successes. 布什先生想突出强调一下非洲的成就。 3. What would you highlight about them? 对于他们你想强调些什么呢? 4. Of course we must highlight that the system can hardly be inaccurate. 当然我们必须强调这一点，即该系统根本不可能出错。 5. It is one of the highlights of the match. 这是比赛中最精彩的项目之一。', '过去式: highlighted 过去分词: highlighted 现在分词: highlighting 第三人称单数: highlights');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fatal', '[\'feɪtl]', 'adj.致命的,重大的,命运注定的,不幸的,致命的,毁灭性的', '1. We gave the enemy a fatal blow. 我们给敌人以致命的打击。 2. There is a fatal flaw in the plan. 计划中有一个致命的缺陷。 3. A possibly fatal crisis may be at hand. 毁灭性的危机可能近在咫尺。 4. The fatal day of the election finally arrived. 大选决定命运的一天终于来到了。', '副词: fatally 名词: fatality');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('enlighten', '[ɪn\'laɪtn]', 'vt.启发,启蒙,教导,授予...知识,开导,<古>照耀', '1. This book will enlighten the reader. 这本书将会启发读者。 2. Enlighten me with your thoughts on this matter. 你们在如下事件上的思想启发了我。 3. Can you enlighten me--I don\'t understand this proposal. 我不明白这条建议，你能不能启发我一下。 4. Can you enlighten me on this subject? 关于这个问题，你能指点我一下吗？', '名词: enlightener 过去式: enlightened 过去分词: enlightened 现在分词: enlightening 第三人称单数: enlightens');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('assumption', '[ə\'sʌmpʃn]', 'n.假定,设想,担任,承当,假装,作态', '1. The project was predicated on the assumption that the economy was expanding. 这一计划是以经济发展的设想为依据的。 2. The theory is based on a series of wrong assumptions. 这一理论是以一系列错误的设想为依据的。 3. His assumption of power was welcomed by everyone. 他的当权为大家所欢迎。 4. He talked with an assumption of ease. 他装出从容的样子说话。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('undergo', '[ˌʌndər\'ɡoʊ]', 'vt.经历,遭受,忍受', '1. This city underwent great changes. 这座城市经历了巨大的变化。 2. The castle will undergo extensive and costly renovations. 那城堡要用巨资进行全面整修。 3. Man\'s idea of God would undoubtedly undergo a change if we were to discover other intelligent beings in the universe. 如果我们真的发现宇宙中有其他的智慧生命,人类关于上帝的观念一定会经历一场变化。 4. I hope that I shall never again have to undergo such unpleasant experience. 我希望我永远不会再遭遇到这种不愉快的经历。', '过去式: underwent 过去分词: undergone 现在分词: undergoing 第三人称单数: undergoes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('feeble', '[\'fiːbl]', 'adj.虚弱的,衰弱的,无力的,微弱的,薄弱的', '1. The bishop said it with a feeble voice as he woke. 主教醒过来，用虚弱的声音说出。 2. Feeble and uncertain securities were thrown upon the market. 虚弱的或者没有把握的证券都向市场抛售了。 3. Tighter credit conditions are sapping already feeble demand. 紧缩的信贷让本就无力的需求更加乏力。 4. He bleated out a feeble excuse. 他以微弱的声音作无力的辩解。', '副词: feebly 比较级: feebler 最高级: feeblest 名词: feebleness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('continual', '[kən\'tɪnjuəl]', 'adj.连续的,频繁的,持续不断的', '1. Are you tired of this continual rain? 你对于这不停的雨不感到厌烦吗？ 2. The child\'s continual crying drove me to distraction. 那孩子不断的哭声弄得我几乎要发狂。 3. The noise of cars passing along the road is a continual disturbance to our quiet at home. 马路上来往的车辆声音不断地破坏我们家的安宁。 4. My work has been delayed by his continual visit. 我的工作被他频繁的拜访给耽搁了。', '副词: continually');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('intellect', '[\'ɪntəlekt]', 'n.智力', '1. You estimate his intellect too highly. 你把他的智力评估得太高。 2. The problem challenges us to use our intellect. 这个问题需要我们运用智力。 3. She is short on intellect,but long on shape. 她短于理智而长于姿态。 4. By theory, my behavior is not intellect. 理论上来说，这是不理智的行为。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('spectrum', '[\'spektrəm]', 'n.光,光谱,型谱,频谱', '1. There\'s a wide spectrum of opinions on this problem. 对这个问题的说法众说纷纭，莫衷一是。 2. There are tense competition in the whole spectrum of the industry. 整个工业领域竞争很激烈。 3. The press has published a wide spectrum of books. 这个出版社出版了一系列范围广泛的书籍。 4. In the spectrum, distinct colours shade into each other. 在光谱中，截然不同的颜色相互融合起来。', '名词复数: spectra');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('expertise', '[ˌekspɜːr\'tiːz]', 'n.专家的意见,专门技术', '1. He has the expertise in the management of hotels. 他有酒店管理知识。 2. I have no sewing expertise 我没有缝纫方面的知识。 3. We were amazed at his expertise on the ski slopes. 他斜坡滑雪的技能使我们赞叹不已。 4. The company is eager to develop its own expertise in the area of computer programming. 该公司希望能在计算机程序领域开发出自己的专门技术。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sake', '[seɪk]', 'n.为了...之好处,出于对...的兴趣,缘故,理由,日本米酒', '1. He is away all year for the sake of his work. 因工作关系，他整年出门在外。 2. You should take care of your niece for the sake of your sister. 看在姐妹的份上，你应该照顾你的侄女。 3. Never do wrong for the sake of money. 绝不要为金钱而做坏事。 4. It\'s the company\'s policy to sacrifice short-term profits for the sake of long-term growth. 为长期发展而牺牲短期利润是公司的方针。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('priority', '[praɪ\'ɔːrəti]', 'n.先,前,优先,优先权', '1. This is the key and should be given top priority. 这是关键，要放在第一位。 2. Efficiency does not always have priority. 效率不一定总是优先。 3. Improving the plight of teachers is indeed a priority item. 改善教师的困难处境的确是优先处理的一件事情。', '名词复数: priorities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('refuge', '[\'refjuːdʒ]', 'n.庇护,避难,避难所', '1. They took refuge in a cave yesterday. 他们昨天是在一个洞里避难的。 2. It is a classic sanctuary in which the rationalist fancy may take refuge. 这是一所古雅的圣殿，理性主义者可以躲在其中。 3. A small cave was the only refuge from the cold. 小洞穴是唯一的避寒处。 4. They were forced to seek refuge from the fighting. 他们被迫寻求庇护，以躲避战争。 5. Drug traffickers refuged in these border areas. 毒品贩子在这些边界地区躲避。', '过去式: refuged 过去分词: refuged 现在分词: refuging 第三人称单数: refuges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('resume', '[rɪ\'zuːm]', 'n.摘要,概略,<美>履历;vt.再继续,重新开始,重新占用,再用,恢复', '1. We resumed our work after a rest. 休息之后我们重新开始工作。 2. I tried to persuade her to resume her job as secretary. 我试图劝她重新干她的秘书工作。 3. Two days later, they resumed their journey. 两天以後,他们继续旅行。 4. We\'ll stop now and resume at two o\'clock. 我们现在停下来, 到两点再干。 5. I enclosed my resume in my letter. 我在信里附上了我的简历。', '形容词: resumable 名词: resumer 过去式: resumed 过去分词: resumed 现在分词: resuming 第三人称单数: resumes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('detail', '[\'diːteɪl]', 'n.细节,详情;vt.详述,细说;', '1. The full details of the agreement haven\'t been made public. 协议的细节尚未公布。 2. He told us the accident in detail. 他详细地把事故讲给我们听。 3. He explained it so clearly that I could understand every detail. 他把它解释得很清楚,每一个细节我都明白了。 4. Sadat seemed free of the obsession with detail. 萨达特不那么注重细微末节。 5. Could you detail all your expenses on this form? 请把你的各项开支列在这张表格上，好吗？', '名词: detailer 过去式: detailed 过去分词: detailed 现在分词: detailing 第三人称单数: details');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('drill', '[drɪl]', 'n.钻孔机,钻子,播种机,军事训练,操练,(反复)练习,条播机;v.训练,钻孔,条播', '1. The dentist\'s drill made a lot of noise. 牙钻发出很大的噪音。 2. Jack used a drill to bore a hole in the wall above the fireplace. 杰克用钻子在壁炉上方的墙上钻孔。 3. Today\'s art lesson came to an abrupt end when the gongs sounded for a fire drill. 今天的美术课因火灾演习的铃声大作而突然结束。 4. You\'d better set a goal before you start the drill. 练习开始前，你最好设定一个目标。 5. Listen to the first paragraph, then let them drill in teams. 听第一段,然后分组练习。', '名词: driller 过去式: drilled 过去分词: drilled 现在分词: drilling 第三人称单数: drills');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('discreet', '[dɪ\'skriːt]', 'adj.小心的,慎重的,有思虑的,贤明的', '1. It was not discreet of you to say that. 你那样说有欠考虑。 2. Be more discreet or you\'ll get yourself talked about. 要更谨慎些－－否则你就会成为人们的话柄。 3. I\'ll certainly be most discreet in my conversation. 我在谈话中当然会十分小心的。 4. It was a discreet apartment in a quiet street. 那是间位於一条僻静的街上不引人注意的公寓房间。', '副词: discreetly 名词: discreetness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('resolve', '[rɪ\'zɑːlv]', 'n.决心;v.决心,决定,决心要,(使)分解,溶解,解决;vt.解决', '1. Intensive efforts are being made to resolve the dispute. 现正全力以赴来解决这场纠纷。 2. He resolved that nothing should hold him back. 他下决心不让任何事情阻挡他。 3. We can resolve the problem into more elementary items. 我们能够把这个问题分解成更基本的细目。 4. He resolved on going abroad to study. 他决定到海外留学。 5. He kept his resolve to do better. 他决心干得更出色。', '形容词: resolvable 副词: resolvedly 名词: resolvability 过去式: resolved 过去分词: resolved 现在分词: resolving 第三人称单数: resolves');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('admit', '[əd\'mɪt]', 'v.容许,承认,接纳', '1. He made a terrible mistake, but he refused to admit it. 他犯了一个严重的错误,可是他拒不承认。 2. We have to admit that there is still room for improvement. 我们不得不承认,在这方面有尚待改进的地方。 3. Each ticket admits two people to the party. 每张票可供两人入场参加聚会。 4. I reluctantly admitted to being nervous about the test. 我勉强承认我对测试感到紧张。', '过去式: admitted 过去分词: admitted 现在分词: admitting 第三人称单数: admits');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('thorn', '[θɔːrn]', 'n.[植]刺,棘,荆棘', '1. She got her finger pricked by a thorn. 她的手指被刺扎了一下。 2. One puts on gloves before grasping a thorn cudgel. 为了要握有刺的棍子，首先得戴上手套。 3. Priestesses are immune to their own thorn effects. 女祭司不会受自己创造的荆棘刺影响。 4. And still, we choose the pain of the thorn. 我们仍然选择了那痛苦的荆棘。', '形容词: thornless');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('diplomat', '[\'dɪpləmæt]', 'n.外交官,有外交手腕的人,有权谋的人', '1. They had to ransom the kidnapped diplomat. 他们不得不赎回被绑架的外交官。 2. In all the delicate negotiations, the diplomat never put a foot wrong. 在微妙的谈判中，这位外交家从未出过差错。 3. The diplomat solved the international problem by negotiating. 外交官通过谈判解决了那个国际问题。 4. You act as a diplomat and harmonizer between people with differing viewpoints. 在人们之间，你就应该像一个外交大使一样，见人说人话，见鬼说鬼话。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hum', '[hʌm]', 'v.嗡嗡叫,哼;n.嗡嗡声,吵杂声', '1. He could hear the hum of the bees in the garden. 他听得见花园里蜜蜂的嗡嗡声。 2. His strong voice cut through the hum of conversation like a knife through butter. 他那宏亮有力的声音一下子压倒了嗡嗡的谈话声。 3. The background with all of my phones is totally silent, no hiss, hum at all, just total blackness. 背景与我的所有电话，是完全沉默，没有噪音，哼声一切，在刚刚共有黑。 4. She heard the hum of voices in the house. 她听见了屋子里的嘈杂声。 5. You don\'t need to sing loud, you just hum softly. 你不必大声唱,只要轻轻哼就好了。 6. Hum, you\'re joking! 哼，你在开玩笑吧！', '形容词: hummable 名词: hummer 过去式: hummed 过去分词: hummed 现在分词: humming 第三人称单数: hums');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('superintendent', '[ˌsuːpərɪn\'tendənt]', 'n.主管,负责人,指挥者,管理者', '1. \"I hope he went fishing and comes back tomorrow, but I wouldn\'t bet my paycheck on it, \" said state police superintendent Clinton Pagano ... 州警察局长帕加诺说，\"我希望他钓鱼去了，明天就回来。但是我可不愿意拿我的薪水打赌(并无十分把握)。\"...', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pest', '[pest]', 'n.有害物', '1. Stores of grain are frequently attacked by pests. 储存的谷物经常受到害虫的破坏。 2. It won\'t be long before we can be rid of the pest altogether. 不要太久，我们就能把这种害虫消除干净。 3. That child is being a real pest. 那个孩子真讨厌。 4. My little brother is a pest when he spoils my games. 我的小弟弟破坏我的各种游戏真讨厌。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('vent', '[vent]', 'n.通风孔,出烟孔,出口,(感情等的)发泄;v.放出,排出,发泄', '1. The steam found a vent through a crack in the pipe. 蒸气从管子的裂缝漏出去。 2. The vent is not big enough to get the smoke out. 通风孔太小,不能让烟排出去。 3. The explosion cracks the earth\'s surface and scatters ash and huge chunks of rock for many kilometers around the vent. 这样的爆炸把地表炸开以后，其火山灰和巨大石块可散落到火山口周围好几公里远的地方。 4. Foraging crabs and hungry fish feed on bacteria from giant tube worms near a deep sea vent in the Pacific Ocean. 在太平洋里的一座深海火山口附近，饥肠辘辘的螃蟹和鱼类正享用着来自巨型管虫的细菌。 5. I look down on man who vents his anger on his family after having a bad day at work. 我瞧不起那些工作不顺心就拿家里人出气的男人。', '名词: venter 过去式: vented 过去分词: vented 现在分词: venting 第三人称单数: vents');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('prune', '[pruːn]', 'v.剪除', '1. You should prune your roses in the spring. 你应该在春天修剪一下你的玫瑰花。 2. It is our job to prune the side branches of these trees. 我们的工作就是修剪这些树的侧枝。 3. The gardener pruned the dead branches. 园丁剪去枯枝。 4. Next year\'s budget will have to be drastically pruned. 下一年度的预算将大幅度削减。', '名词: pruner 过去式: pruned 过去分词: pruned 现在分词: pruning 第三人称单数: prunes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('vain', '[veɪn]', 'adj.徒然的,无益的,虚荣的,空虚的,自负的,愚蠢的', '1. She is vain and foolish, and yet people like her. 她自负而愚蠢，然而人们喜欢她。 2. She is vain of her voice. 她自以为她的声音了不起。 3. They endeavoured to make her happy but in vain. 他们尽量使她快乐，却徒劳无功。 4. All his father\'s exhortations were in vain. 他父亲的一切劝告都无效。', '副词: vainly 比较级: vainer 最高级: vainest 名词: vainness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('existence', '[ɪɡ\'zɪstəns]', 'n.存在,实在,生活,存在物,实在物', '1. The newspaper ceased to appear after an existence of three months. 该报发行3 个月后停刊了。 2. According to some philosopher, everything in existence is reasonable. 某位哲学家认为，存在的事物都是合理的。 3. The family lived a precarious existence. 这家人过着朝不保夕的生活。 4. Pollution poses a threat to the continued existence of this species. 污染对这一物种的继续生存造成了威胁。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('band', '[bænd]', 'n.带子,镶边,波段,队,乐队;v.联合,结合', '1. The band played a lively tune. 乐队演奏了一支轻快的乐曲。 2. The brass band is banging away in the park. 铜管乐队在公园里吹吹打打。 3. They are a teenager band made up of four cool boys. 他们是一支由四名酷哥组成的少年演唱队。 4. A band of robbers held up the train. 一群强盗抢劫了火车。 5. She used a rubber band to tie her hair. 她用一根橡皮筋扎头发。 6. If you band the bird\'s leg, you can identify it later. 如果你在鸟腿上套上标记环,以後就能认出它。 7. The children banded together to buy a present for their teacher. 孩子们合起来为他们的老师买了一件礼物。', '过去式: banded 过去分词: banded 现在分词: banding 第三人称单数: bands');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('grieve', '[ɡriːv]', 'v.(使)悲痛,(使)伤心,忧伤', '1. It grieves me to see him in such bad health. 看见他的健康状况如此不佳，我很伤心。 2. It grieves me to hear how disobedient you\'ve been. 听说你很不听话，使我感到非常难过。 3. She was grieving for the dead baby. 她为死去的孩子悲伤。 4. It\'s no use grieving about past errors. 为过去的错误懊悔不已是无济于事的。', '副词: grievingly 名词: griever 过去式: grieved 过去分词: grieved 现在分词: grieving 第三人称单数: grieves');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('consequence', '[\'kɑːnsəkwens]', 'n.结果,[逻]推理,推论,因果关系,重要的地位', '1. It terrified me to contemplate the consequence of your action. 一想到你行动的后果,我就感到害怕。 2. He studied hard, and in consequence he passed the exam. 他努力学习，因此通过了考试。 3. Happiness is not a reward it is a consequence. 幸福不是报偿，而是结果。 4. In consequence of his bad conduct he was dismissed. 由于行为不良，他被开除了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mere', '[mɪr]', 'adj.仅仅的,起码的,纯粹的', '1. Don\'t scold him, he is a mere child. 别责备他,他只不过是个孩子。 2. Her liberal views were soon revealed as mere posturing. 她那些开明的观点很快地就暴露出只不过是做做样子而已。 3. The peasant laboured for a mere pittance. 农民仅仅是为了微不足道的收入而辛苦地劳作。 4. A mere child cannot do the work of a man. 仅仅是个孩子是不能做成人工作的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hysterical', '[hɪ\'sterɪkl]', 'a歇斯底里的,异常兴奋的', '1. Janet became hysterical and began screaming. 珍妮特变得歇斯底里，开始尖叫。 2. His hysterical laughter made everybody stunned. 他那歇斯底里的笑声使所有的人不知所措。 3. He is hysterical at the sight of the photo. 他一看到那张照片就异常激动。', '副词: hysterically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('commonplace', '[\'kɑːmənpleɪs]', 'n.平凡的事,平常话;adj.平凡的', '1. Poets interpret the commonplace freshly. 诗人能把平凡的事物描绘得有声有色。 2. He was an unambitious man destined for a commonplace job. 他是一个没有野心的人，注定要找一个平凡的工作。 3. Soon it will be commonplace for men to travel to the moon. 人们去月球旅行很快就会成为常事。 4. What he has said is a mere commonplace. 他所说的无非是老生常谈而已。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('stagger', '[\'stæɡər]', 'v.摇晃,蹒跚,交错,摇摇摆摆;adj.交错的', '1. She staggered and fell. 她踉跄了几步，跌倒在地。 2. The drunk man staggered across the room. 那个醉汉摇摇晃晃地穿过房间。 3. His resolution had begun to stagger. 他的意志开始动摇了。 4. Such a heavy load would stagger an elephant. 这么重的担子，大象担着也得摇晃。 5. He gave a stagger on hearing the news. 他听到这一消息两腿摇晃起来。', '形容词: staggery 名词: staggerer 过去式: staggered 过去分词: staggered 现在分词: staggering 第三人称单数: staggers');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('discipline', '[\'dɪsəplɪn]', 'n.纪律,学科;v.训练', '1. She is strict in the matter of discipline. 她对纪律的要求是严格的。 2. It takes years of discipline to become a pianist. 要成为钢琴家需经多年训练。 3. Applied linguistics is a new and independent discipline. 应用语言学是一门新兴的独立学科。 4. It showed that they had been well disciplined. 这表明他们受过良好的训练。', '形容词: disciplinal 名词: discipliner 过去式: disciplined 过去分词: disciplined 现在分词: disciplining 第三人称单数: disciplines');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('peculiar', '[pɪ\'kjuːliər]', 'adj.奇特的,罕见的,特殊的;n.特有财产,特权', '1. Did you notice anything peculiar? 你注意到有什么异常的事吗？ 2. The food has a peculiar taste. 这食物有种怪味道。 3. A peculiar feeling came over Feliks. 一种特殊的情感传遍费利克斯全身。 4. This actor has a peculiar charm, which attracts middle-aged women. 这个演员有种特殊的魅力，吸引了很多中年女性。 5. It\'s the manager\'s peculiar to use this meeting room. 使用这间会议室是经理的特权。', '副词: peculiarly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('adverse', '[\'ædvɜːrs]', 'adj.不利的,敌对的,相反的', '1. The judge gave us an adverse decision. 法官作出对我们不利的判决。 2. He ignored all kinds of adverse comments about him. 他不理睬各种各样对他不利的评论。 3. The development was adverse to our interests. 这种发展与我们的利益背道而驰。 4. Diseases are adverse to the best growth of children. 疾病对儿童的健康成长是有害的。', '副词: adversely 名词: adverseness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('factor', '[\'fæktər]', 'n.因素,要素,因数,代理人', '1. The determinate factor of our economy is to control inflation. 我们经济的决定性因素是控制通货膨胀。 2. The committee\'s support is an important factor in the success of the project. 委员会的支持是该项目取得成功的一个重要因素。 3. 2, 3, 4 and 6 are factors of 12. 2、3、4 和6是12的因子。 4. A new factor appears under the integral sign. 积分号内出现了一个新的因子。', '形容词: factorable 名词: factorship 过去式: factored 过去分词: factored 现在分词: factoring 第三人称单数: factors');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('crisis', '[\'kraɪsɪs]', 'n.疾病的转折点(或转好或恶化),决定性时刻,危机,危险期,历史上的紧要关头,[医]危象,转换期', '1. They suffered huge losses in the financial crisis. 他们在经济危机时遭受了巨大的损失。 2. The Cabinet met to resolve the crisis. 内阁开会, 寻求解决危机的办法。 3. In this crisis, all the prejudices fell away. 值此危急时期，各种偏见均已消失。 4. She\'s always to the fore at moments of crisis. 她在危急关头总是挺身而出。', '名词复数: crises');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('priest', '[priːst]', 'n.牧师', '1. A priest exorcized the ghost from the house. 教士将鬼从房屋中驱走。 2. The priest confessed the young man. 神父听取那个青年的忏悔。 3. The priest pronounced them man and wife. 神父宣布他们已结为夫妇。 4. The priest persuaded him to give up his bad habit. 牧师劝他放弃坏习惯。', '过去式: priested 过去分词: priested 现在分词: priesting 第三人称单数: priests');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('glamour', '[\'ɡlæmər]', 'n.[亦作glamor]魔力,魅力;v.迷惑', '1. The glamour of inexperience is over your eyes. 无经验的魔力蒙住了你的眼睛。 2. Why did the time really like to murder all the glamour? 为什么时光真的喜欢杀死所有的魔力呢？ 3. A luxuriant tan bespeaks health and glamour. 丰润的棕色皮肤是健康和魅力的标志。 4. Yet Hollywood has not lost all its glamour. 但是，好莱坞还没有完全失去它的魅力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('privilege', '[\'prɪvəlɪdʒ]', 'n.特权,特别待遇,基本公民权力,特免;vt.给与...特权,特免', '1. I had the privilege of meeting the queen. 我有会见王后的特权。 2. It is a great privilege to know you. 认识你是一件难得的事。 3. It was a privilege to work with him. 和他在一起工作是一项殊荣。 4. Kings cannot privilege what God forbade. 国王不能原谅上帝不允许做的事。', '过去式: privileged 过去分词: privileged 现在分词: privileging 第三人称单数: privileges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reinforce', '[ˌriːɪn\'fɔːrs]', 'vt.加强,增援,补充,增加...的数量,修补,加固;vi.求援,得到增援;n.加固物', '1. We will use metal strap to reinforce the outside. 我们会在纸箱外用金属带加固。 2. Any good speaker should be able to reinforce his argument with facts. 一个好的演讲者会用事实来加强他论点。 3. Public reaction will reinforce it. 社会反响会进一步增强它的作用。 4. This evidence reinforces my view that he is a spy. 这个证据证实了我认为他是间谍的这一看法。', '形容词: reinforceable');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('distribution', '[ˌdɪstrɪ\'bjuːʃn]', 'n.分配,分发,配给物,销售,法院对无遗嘱死亡者财产的分配,分布状态,区分,分类,发送,发行', '1. The species of plant has a very wide distribution. 这种植物的分布范围很广。 2. The Red Cross organized the distribution of food and clothing in the disaster area. 红十字会组织了灾区的食品和衣物分发。 3. Brazil has a very unequal distribution of income and wealth. 巴西的收入和财富分配十分不平均。 4. Bees are largely responsible for the distribution of pollen. 蜜蜂是花粉的主要散布者。', '形容词: distributional');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('inherent', '[ɪn\'hɪrənt]', 'adj.固有的,内在的,与生俱来的', '1. Weight is an inherent property of matter. 重量是物质固有的特性。 2. The desire for freedom is inherent in us all. 渴望自由是我们大家生来就有的愿望。 3. She has an inherent love of beauty. 她天生爱美。 4. There is an inherent weakness in the design. 这设计本身存在弱点。', '副词: inherently');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('incident', '[\'ɪnsɪdənt]', 'n.事件,事变;adj.附带的,易于发生的', '1. The serious incident along the border increased our fears of the war. 边境上的紧张局势加重了我们对战争的忧虑。 2. She couldn\'t erase the incident from her memory. 她难以忘记那次事件。 3. The police are connecting this incident with last week\'s terrorist bombing. 警方认为这次事件和上周的恐怖分子爆炸事件有关。 4. The incident put a dampener on his birthday party. 这件事使得他的生日晚会很扫兴。 5. These diseases are incident to childhood. 儿童易患这类疾病。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('establish', '[ɪ\'stæblɪʃ]', 'vt.建立,设立,安置,使定居,使人民接受,确定;v.建立', '1. We have established trade ties with these regions. 我们和这些地区建立了贸易关系。 2. There is an urgent need to establish a strict responsibility system. 急需建立严格的责任制度。 3. He has established his theory. 他确立了他的学说。 4. The framework of a social security system was established by and large. 社会保障体系框架基本确立。', '名词: establisher 过去式: established 过去分词: established 现在分词: establishing 第三人称单数: establishes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pursue', '[pər\'suː]', 'vt.追赶,追踪,追击,继续,从事', '1. Everyone has the freedom to pursue their dreams. 每个人都有追求各自梦想的自由。 2. The police are pursuing an escaped prisoner. 警方正在追捕一名越狱的逃犯。 3. Let\'s not pursue this argument. 让我们别再继续这个争论了。 4. She wishes to pursue a medical career. 她希望从事医学工作。', '形容词: pursuable 名词: pursuer 过去式: pursued 过去分词: pursued 现在分词: pursuing 第三人称单数: pursues');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('whereby', '[wer\'baɪ]', 'adv.凭什么,为何', '1. He devised a plan whereby he might escape. 他想出了一个可藉以逃脱的办法。 2. Whereby shall we find fault with him? 我们凭什么指责他呢？ 3. There is no other way whereby we can cross the river. 我们没有别的办法过河。 4. Love is the chain whereby to bind a child to his parents. 爱是连结子女与父母的链子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ambiguous', '[æm\'bɪɡjuəs]', 'adj.暧昧的,不明确的', '1. He gave us an ambiguous answer . 他给了我们一个模棱两可的答复。 2. In fact, your ambiguous words amount to a refusal. 实际上,你说的那些模棱两可的话等于是拒绝。 3. Her account was deliberately ambiguous. 她的陈述故意含混不清。 4. Why are you always so ambiguous about this problem? 为什么你总是对这个问题含糊不清？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fertilizer', '[\'fɜːrtəlaɪzər]', 'n.肥料(尤指化学肥料),[动]受精媒介物', '1. The stalks will rot and make good fertilizer. 杆儿腐烂后会成为很好的肥料。 2. Crushed bones make one of the best fertilizers. 碎骨是最好的肥料之一。 3. Farmers bartered rice for fertilizer. 农民们用大米换肥料。 4. The tractor hauled the fertilizer away. 拖拉机把肥料拉走了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('artificial', '[ˌɑːrtɪ\'fɪʃl]', 'adj.人造的,假的,非原产地的', '1. This orange drink contains no artificial flavourings. 这种橙汁饮品不含人工调味料。 2. This dress is made of artificial fibers. 这件衣服是人造纤维的。 3. She welcomed us with an artificial smile on her face. 她脸上挂着虚委的笑容来迎接我们。 4. Her artificial manner made me sick. 她那装腔作势的样子令我恶心。', '副词: artificially 名词: artificiality');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('idiot', '[\'ɪdiət]', 'n.白痴,愚人,傻瓜', '1. What a stupid idiot! 真是个愚蠢的白痴！ 2. I didn\'t mince matters: I said he was an idiot. 我不讳言，我说过他是白痴。 3. He\'s a ruddy idiot. 他是个大傻瓜。 4. Don\'t treat me as if I were an idiot. 别把我当傻瓜。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('crush', '[krʌʃ]', 'vt.压碎,碾碎,压服,压垮,粉碎,(使)变形', '1. A windmill is used to crush grain into flour. 风车被用来把谷粒轧成面粉。 2. It took him only 50 minutes to crush his opponent. 他只用了50分钟时间就击败了对手。 3. This victory inspired vigor in the Armenian national team and they finally crushed the English team. 这场胜利激起了亚美尼亚队的斗志,他们最终击败了英国队。 4. I was crushed that I wasn\'t invited. 没有受到邀请,我感到很失望。 5. I\'ve got a crush on my pretty toy pistol. 我非常喜欢我漂亮的玩具手枪。', '形容词: crushable 名词: crusher 过去式: crushed 过去分词: crushed 现在分词: crushing 第三人称单数: crushes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('skip', '[skɪp]', 'v.跳,蹦,急速改变,跳读,遗漏,跳跃;n.跳跃', '1. Lambs skipped in the field. 小羊在田野里跳跃。 2. Let\' s skip over this page and come to page 55. 咱们越过这一页，看第五十五页。 3. I read the whole book without skipping(a page). 我一页不漏地读完了整本书。 4. He gave a skip of joy as he heard the news. 得知这个消息，他高兴地跳了起来。', '形容词: skippable 过去式: skipped 过去分词: skipped 现在分词: skipping 第三人称单数: skips');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('budget', '[\'bʌdʒɪt]', 'n.预算;vi.做预算,编入预算', '1. Congress has approved the new educational budget. 国会通过了新的教育预算。 2. Our budget needs drastic revision. 我们的预算需作重大修改。 3. The government has budgeted 10000000 pounds for education spending. 政府将10000000英镑编入教育预算。 4. The government plans to budget a new hospital. 政府计划在预算中拨款建一家新医院。 5. If we budget carefully, we\'ll be able to afford a new house. 如果我们精打细算就能买一座新房子了。 6. You can buy high-quality goods at budget prices there. 你可以在那买到物美价廉的商品。', '形容词: budgetary 名词: budgeter 过去式: budgeted 过去分词: budgeted 现在分词: budgeting 第三人称单数: budgets');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('peninsula', '[pə\'nɪnsələ]', 'n.半岛', '1. His house is located on the tip of the peninsula. 他的房子位于半岛的顶端。 2. Leizhou Peninsula lies opposite Hainan Island. 雷州半岛正对着海南岛。', '形容词: peninsular');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('strain', '[streɪn]', 'n.过度的疲劳,紧张,张力,应变;vt.扭伤,损伤;v.拉紧,扯紧,(使)紧张,尽力', '1. The rope finally broke under the strain. 绷紧的绳子终于断了。 2. The tugs took up the strain and the ocean liner edged away from the quayside. 拖船开始拉紧了，远洋客轮徐徐离开了码头。 3. All her senses were on the strain when the test was going on. 测试时，她所有的感官都处于紧张状态。 4. A sudden and severe strain was placed upon us by the cutting off of these supplies. 由于供给突然被切断，我们感到了沉重的压力。 5. Too heavy a load will strain the rope to its breaking point. 负载过重会把绳子拉紧到崩断的地步。', '过去式: strained 过去分词: strained 现在分词: straining 第三人称单数: strains');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('alien', '[\'eɪliən]', 'n.外侨;adj.外国的,相异的,不同,背道而驰', '1. Immigrant workers were classed as resident aliens. 移民来的工人已归入外侨类。 2. She is declared an undesirable alien and deport. 她被宣布是不受欢迎的外国人并被驱逐出境。 3. I followed the alien to see where it was to go. 我跟着外星人看它朝哪儿去。 4. I ran into an old friend in the alien land. 我在异国他乡遇到故知。', '过去式: aliened 过去分词: aliened 现在分词: aliening 第三人称单数: aliens');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('demand', '[dɪ\'mænd]', 'n.要求,需求(量),需要;v.要求,需要,要求知道,查询', '1. Their demand is entirely justified. 他们的要求是完全正当的。 2. The demand for coal begins to slacken off in the spring. 煤的需求在春天开始减少。 3. He had the impertinence to demand a raise. 他竟冒失地要求增加工资。 4. The policeman demanded their names. 那个警察查问了他们的名字。', '形容词: demandable 名词: demander 过去式: demanded 过去分词: demanded 现在分词: demanding 第三人称单数: demands');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('migrant', '[\'maɪɡrənt]', 'n.候鸟,移居者', '1. Migrants to the city send money home to their relatives. 这个城市的移居者把钱寄回家给他们的亲戚。 2. Virus may travel through migrant, and cause epidemic situation to spread. 病毒可能通过候鸟传播，致使疫情蔓延。 3. Migrant workers move from city to city in search of work. 流动工人为了寻找工作从一个城市移居到另一个城市。 4. The army comprised of both the local and migrant soldiers. 军队由地方和移居战士组成。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('implicit', '[ɪm\'plɪsɪt]', 'adj.暗示的,盲从的,含蓄的,固有的,不怀疑的,绝对的', '1. Her attitude was implicit in the answer she gave us. 她在给我们的答复中态度是含蓄的。 2. The system of rules implicit in a language, viewed as a mechanism for generating all sentences possible in that language. 语法规则隐含在一种语言中的规则体系，被看作在该语言中生成所有可能的语句的机制 3. The crew had implicit faith in the captain\'s judgment. 全体船员都绝对相信船长的判断。 4. The oak is implicit in the acorn. 橡实是橡树固有的。', '副词: implicitly 名词: implicitness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cape', '[keɪp]', 'n.海角,岬', '1. Rudolf was rounding a bleak, dangerous cape. 鲁道夫正在绕过一个荒凉险峻的海岬。 2. The cape extends far into the ocean. 那海岬伸向海洋远处。 3. My favorite movie is Cape No. 7. 我最喜欢的电影是”海角七号”。 4. The man has a red cape. 这人有一件红色的斗篷。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('vulnerable', '[\'vʌlnərəbl]', 'adj.易受攻击的,易受...的攻击', '1. Achilles was vulnerable only in his heel. 阿基里斯只有脚后跟会受伤害。 2. The potato is vulnerable to several pests. 马铃薯易受几种害虫的侵害。 3. Young birds are very vulnerable to predators. 幼小的鸟易受食肉动物伤害。 4. Satellites are as vulnerable as they are valuable. 卫星价值很大但也很脆弱。', '副词: vulnerably 名词: vulnerability');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('endeavor', '[ɪn\'devər]', 'n.努力,尽力;vi.尽力,努力', '1. Please make every endeavor to be early. 请尽量早点儿。 2. He failed in convincing the buyer despite endeavor. 尽管他已经尽力了,还是无法说服买主。 3. Where there is no hope, there can be no endeavor. 哪里没有希望,哪里就不可能有努力。 4. His success came from endeavor rather than opportunity. 他的成功与其说是由于机遇 5. The man endeavored to please his beloved wife. 那人尽量使他深爱的妻子快乐。', '名词: endeavorer 过去式: endeavored 过去分词: endeavored 现在分词: endeavoring 第三人称单数: endeavors');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('implication', '[ˌɪmplɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.牵连,含意,暗示', '1. His implication in the crime was obvious to all. 大家都清楚他和这一罪行有牵连。 2. The trial resulted in the implication of several major figures in the organization. 审讯结果表明这个组织中几个主要人物都牵连在案。 3. He has not actually realized the full implication. 他还没有真正认识到全部含意。 4. The new report has far-reaching implications for the future of broadcasting. 这一新报告对广播业的前途有些意味深长的暗示。', '形容词: implicative 副词: implicatively');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('quantitative', '[\'kwɑːntəteɪtɪv]', 'adj.数量的,定量的', '1. He said it was only a quantitative difference. 他说这仅仅是数量上的差别。 2. Arms races have a quantitative and a qualitative aspects. 军备竞赛具有数量和质量两个方面。 3. We need to do a proper quantitative analysis of this problem. 我们需要对这个问题进行适当的定量分析。 4. The primary research method will be both qualitative and quantitative. 本文采用定性和定量相结合的研究方法。', '副词: quantitatively 名词: quantitativeness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('marsh', '[mɑːrʃ]', 'n.湿地,沼泽,沼泽地', '1. There are a lot of frogs in the marsh. 沼泽里有许多青蛙。 2. Be careful not to get stuck in the marsh. 小心别陷进沼泽里。 3. No retrieval romps in the marsh. 在湿地不好游戏。 4. At the mouth of the river, there is a large area of marsh. 这条河流的入口有一大片湿地。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mingle', '[\'mɪŋɡl]', 'v.(使)混合', '1. You can not mingle oil and water . 你不能把油和水混合在一起。 2. She accepted the money with mingled feelings. 她悲喜交集地收下了这笔钱。 3. The two rivers mingle their waters here. 这两条河在这里汇合起来了。 4. He is too shy to mingle with others. 他由于太内向而怯于与他人交往。', '名词: mingler 过去式: mingled 过去分词: mingled 现在分词: mingling 第三人称单数: mingles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('smash', '[smæʃ]', 'v.打碎,粉碎;n.打碎,粉碎;adj.出色的', '1. The bottle slipped and smashed to pieces on the floor. 瓶子滑在地上,摔成碎片。 2. We shall thoroughly smash the scheme of the enemy. 我们要彻底粉碎敌人的阴谋。 3. We must be ready at all times to smash the enemy\'s attacks. 我们必须随时准备粉碎敌人的进攻。 4. I lost my key and had to smash the window open. 我把钥匙弄丢了,只好把窗户撞开进屋了。 5. The teapot fell with an awful smash. 茶壶掉下来摔得粉碎。 6. The play had its smash premiere. 那出戏首场演出引起了极大的轰动。', '名词: smasher 过去式: smashed 过去分词: smashed 现在分词: smashing 第三人称单数: smashes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('indefinite', '[ɪn\'defɪnət]', 'adj.模糊的,不确定的,[语]不定的', '1. He gave me an indefinite answer. 他给我的答复模棱两可。 2. He has rather indefinite views on the question. 他对该问题的看法颇暧昧。 3. She\'ll be away for an indefinite period. 她将离开一段时间，何时回来未定。 4. The union gave notice of indefinite strike. 工会通知无限期罢工。', '副词: indefinitely 名词: indefiniteness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cycle', '[\'saɪkl]', 'n.周期,循环,自行车,一段时间,整套,(电学)周波;vi.循环,轮转,骑自行车;vt.使循环,使轮转', '1. The seasons of the year make a cycle. 一年四季构成一个循环。 2. The business cycle experienced a sudden down. 商业周期经历了突然的萧条。 3. A cycle of the sun takes a year. 太阳循环周期需要一年。 4. I go to school by cycle every day. 我每天骑自行车上学。 5. I usually cycle home through the park. 我通常骑自行车穿过公园回家。', '名词: cycler 过去式: cycled 过去分词: cycled 现在分词: cycling 第三人称单数: cycles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dart', '[dɑːrt]', 'n.标枪,镖,(昆虫的)刺,飞快的动作;v.飞奔,投掷', '1. My blood rages like a dart. 我血液狂奔有如飞镖。 2. In the first there is often a dart board, 在普通酒吧里，通常有一个飞镖盘， 3. The boy hit the target with his first dart. 那男孩第一镖就击中了目标。 4. He made a sudden dart at his opponent. 他向对手做出突然的飞奔。 5. The sun darts forth its beams. 阳光四射。 6. She darted an angry look at her sister. 她生气地向她妹妹瞥了一眼。', '过去式: darted 过去分词: darted 现在分词: darting 第三人称单数: darts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('engine', '[\'endʒɪn]', 'n.发动机,机车,火车头', '1. What\'s the cubic capacity of this engine? 这台发动机的立体容积是多少？ 2. There must be something wrong with the engine of my car. 我汽车的引擎一定是出故障了。 3. Industrialization is the most important engine of economic growth. 工业化是经济增长最重要的拉动因素。 4. There was a puff of steam from the engine before it stopped. 机车喷出一股蒸气后就停了下来。', '过去式: engined 过去分词: engined 现在分词: engining 第三人称单数: engines');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('subsidy', '[\'sʌbsədi]', 'n.补助金,津贴', '1. It\'s the old and the poor who suffer worst when subsidies are cut. 补助津贴一削减，最吃苦头的就是那些老人和贫民。 2. She qualifies for the unemployment subsidy . 她有权获得失业补贴。 3. The townsfolk can\'t understand why the Royal Shakespeare Company needs a subsidy. 市民不明白王室莎士比亚公司为什么需要一个补助金。', '名词复数: subsidies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('planet', '[\'plænɪt]', 'n.[天]行星', '1. The Earth is a planet. 地球是一颗行星。 2. Mars is the fourth planet in order from the sun. 火星是太阳系的第四颗行星。 3. They claimed to have discovered a new planet. 他们宣称发现了一颗新的行星。 4. It is the only planet that we know harbors life. 它是我们所知唯一适合生物生存的行星。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('owl', '[aʊl]', 'n.[动]猫头鹰,枭,惯于晚上活动的人;ObjectWindowLibrary,BorlandC++的类库', '1. The owl swooped down on the mouse. 那只猫头鹰向着老鼠猛扑下来。 2. The owl hunts while you repose in bed. 你躺在床上安然入睡时，猫头鹰却要去觅食。 3. The hooting of an owl broke the silence now and again, giving Linda the creeps. 猫头鹰的叫声不时打破寂静，使琳达心惊肉跳。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('foster', '[\'fɔːstər]', 'vt.养育,抚育,培养,鼓励,抱(希望);n.养育者,鼓励者', '1. People who cannot have a baby of their own sometimes foster (a child). 不能生育的人有时领养别人的(孩子). 2. It is very important to foster an interest. 培养一种兴趣是十分重要的。 3. The mother tried to foster her son\'s interest in music. 母亲设法培养儿子对音乐的兴趣。 4. Ignorance fosters superstition. 无知助长迷信。 5. The foster children also deserve love and care. 收养的孩子也应该得到关爱。', '过去式: fostered 过去分词: fostered 现在分词: fostering 第三人称单数: fosters');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('compose', '[kəm\'poʊz]', 'v.组成,写作,排字,(使)安定,调解', '1. She began to compose songs at an early age. 她还很年轻时就已经开始创作歌曲。 2. He was composing at the piano at the age of seven. 他7岁时就会钢琴作曲。 3. He sat down and composed a letter of resignation. 他坐下来,写了一封辞职信。 4. It is the law-makers\'s duty to compose laws into a coherent system. 将各项法律编排成为一个连贯的体系是立法者的职责。', '过去式: composed 过去分词: composed 现在分词: composing 第三人称单数: composes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('generous', '[\'dʒenərəs]', 'adj.慷慨的,大方的,有雅量的', '1. She was always very generous in her charity. 她行善时总是很慷慨。 2. Such generous actions stamp him as a man of honour. 他的这些慷慨行为表明他是个君子。 3. I regret having been so generous to that scoundrel. 我后悔不该对那坏家伙如此宽宏大量。 4. I am doubly indebted to you-- for the party and for your generous gift! 你为我操办欢送会并赠送厚礼,这样的深情厚谊我铭记在心。', '副词: generously 名词: generousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('henceforth', '[ˌhens\'fɔːrθ]', 'adv.自此以后,今后', '1. The man said that he would work hard henceforth. 那人说从今以后他要努力工作了。 2. Henceforth it will be more difficult to avoid customs examination. 从此以后，避免海关检查将会更加困难。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('virtual', '[\'vɜːrtʃuəl]', 'adj.虚的,实质的,[物]有效的,事实上的', '1. Our deputy manager is the virtual head of the business. 我们的副经理是公司的实际负责人。 2. A virtual state of war exists between the two countries. 这两国间实际上处于战争状态。 3. For　example, in a Virtual space, Students can \"dissect\" a human body, \"visit\" ancient battlefields, or \"talk\" with Shakespeare, ... 比如,在虚拟的空间中,学生们可以与莎士比亚“对话”。', '名词: virtuality');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('shrink', '[ʃrɪŋk]', 'v.收缩,(使)皱缩,缩短', '1. Will this woolen sweater shrink when washed? 这件羊毛衫洗后会缩水吗？ 2. The company\'s profit margins shrank from 32.5% to 17%. 该公司的边际利润率从32.5%降到了17%。 3. We will never shrink from difficulties. 我们在困难面前决不退缩。 4. The economy is shrinking instead of growing. 经济正在萎缩而不是在增长中。 5. The hot water shrank my pullover. 我的套头毛衣遇热水后收缩了。 6. You can expect some shrink when the jeans are washed. 这种牛仔裤洗后要缩些水。 7. My aunt saw this shrink after her divorce. 我阿姨在离婚后去见过这位心理医生。', '形容词: shrinkable 名词: shrinker 过去式: shrank/shrunk 过去分词: shrunk/shrunken 现在分词: shrinking 第三人称单数: shrinks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('attack', '[ə\'tæk]', 'n.进攻,攻击,(用语言)抨击,批评,疾病发作,侵袭;vt.攻击,抨击,动手处理(某事);vi.攻击', '1. The police are launching a major attack on drug dealers. 警方对毒品贩子发动了大规模的攻击。 2. His attack on the government was pure vitriol. 他纯粹出于恶意抨击政府。 3. The enemy attacked us at night. 敌人在夜里向我们进攻。 4. There is a newspaper article attacking the Prime Minister. 报纸上有一篇抨击首相的文章.', '名词: attacker 过去式: attacked 过去分词: attacked 现在分词: attacking 第三人称单数: attacks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('magistrate', '[\'mædʒɪstreɪt]', 'n.文职官员,地方官员', '1. The thief was brought before the magistrate. 窃贼被带到地方法官前受审。 2. The magistrate remanded him in custody for two weeks. 法官命令把他拘留两星期。 3. The President is the chief magistrate of the United States. 总统是美国的最高行政官。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('jury', '[\'dʒʊri]', 'n.[律]陪审团,评判委员会,陪审员;adj.[海]临时应急的', '1. The case was tried before a jury. 此案是有陪审团参加审理的。 2. The jury brought in a verdict of guilty. 陪审团作出有罪的裁决。 3. The jury are unable to reach a unanimous decision. 陪审团未能达成意见一致的裁决。 4. The jury is about to announce the winners. 评委会即将宣布优胜者。 5. He was already called 4 times for jury duty. 他已经因为临时应急的义务被召唤过4次了。 6. Needless to say, the defense wanted McKinny on the stand, and they wanted the jury to hear selected portions of her tapes. 无需再说，被告方要求麦凯金到场，他们要陪审团听她录音挑选的部分。', '名词复数: juries 过去式: juried 过去分词: juried 现在分词: jurying 第三人称单数: juries');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('perspective', '[pər\'spektɪv]', 'n.透视画法,透视图,远景,前途,观点,看法,观点,观察', '1. A fine perspective opened out before us. 一幅美丽的远景展开在我们眼前。 2. Do you agree with this perspective? 你同意这个看法吗? 3. The painting provides us with one of the earliest examples of the use of perspective. 那幅画给我们提供了采用透视画法的最早的范例。 4. The first row of each perspective shows its name. 每个透视的第一行都显示该透视的名称。', '形容词: perspectival 副词: perspectively');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('homogeneous', '[ˌhoʊmə\'dʒiːniəs]', 'adj.同类的,相似的,均一的,均匀的', '1. Life in the United States is no longer if it ever was culturally homogeneous. 美国的生活已经不再是，如果它曾经是，同源文化。 2. Japan has a largely homogeneous population. 日本的人口基本上同属一 个种族。 3. More of the hitherto homogeneous societies are becoming plural ones. 越来越多的单一种族社会逐渐变得多元化。', '副词: homogeneously 名词: homogeneousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('contact', '[\'kɑːntækt]', 'n.接触,联系;vt.接触,联系', '1. The rich secluded themselves from contact with the poor. 富人不肯同穷人接触。 2. I finally made contact with her in Paris. 我终于在巴黎同她取得了联系。 3. She has a contact in the software industry. 她在软件行业有个熟人。 4. Contact the police at once! 立刻与警方联系！ 5. She suffers from a contact skin rash. 她患上了一种接触传染性皮疹。', '形容词: contactual 副词: contactually 过去式: contacted 过去分词: contacted 现在分词: contacting 第三人称单数: contacts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('intuition', '[ˌɪntu\'ɪʃn]', 'n.直觉,直觉的知识', '1. He takes his ground on intuition. 他的意见是凭直觉。 2. She sensed what was wrong by intuition. 她凭直觉意识到什么地方出毛病了。 3. It was said in a flash of intuition. 这话是凭一刹那的直觉说出的。 4. She had an intuition that her friend was ill. 她有一种直觉:她的朋友病了。', '形容词: intuitional 副词: intuitionally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('original', '[ə\'rɪdʒənl]', 'adj.最初的,原始的,独创的,新颖的;n.原物,原作', '1. Our original plan was to go to Spain, but it was too expensive. 我们的原始计划是去西班牙,但是去那里太贵了。 2. I prefer your original plan to these. 我认为你最初的计划比这些都要好。 3. His designs are highly original. 他的设计独树一帜。 4. This is the original painting, and the others are copies. 这画是原作,其他的是复制品。 5. The Greek translation is faithful to the Hebrew original. 希腊语翻译很忠实于希伯来原文。 6. Fujian Province is the original and major production region of jasmine tea. 福建省是茉莉花茶的起源地和主产区。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('beneficial', '[ˌbenɪ\'fɪʃl]', 'adj.有益的,受益的,[法律]有使用权的;adj.有益的,得利的,[律]有使用权的', '1. It\'s a beneficial result to us. 对我们来说那是有利的结果。 2. Word of mouth advertising is the most beneficial. 口碑广告是最有利的。 3. Calcium is beneficial to our bones. 钙对我们的骨骼有益。 4. Fresh air is beneficial to our health. 新鲜空气有益于健康。', '副词: beneficially 名词: beneficialness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('annoy', '[ə\'nɔɪ]', 'vt.使苦恼,骚扰', '1. We can annoy the enemy by raids. 我们可用袭击骚扰敌人。 2. Some peoples\' daily mission is to annoy you! 一些人的日常使命就是骚扰你！', '过去式: annoyed 过去分词: annoyed 现在分词: annoying 第三人称单数: annoys');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('flat', '[flæt]', 'adj.平坦的,扁平的,单调的,干脆的,无聊的;adv.平直地,正好,断然地;n.平面,一层,公寓;v.(使)变平,(使)降半音', '1. Most of our county is as flat as a pancake. 我们县大部分地方非常平坦。 2. In flat open country there is plenty of grass for the cattle to feed on. 在开阔平坦的地区有大量的青草供牛群食用。 3. People used to think that the earth was flat. 过去人们认为地球是扁平的。 4. He spoke in a flat monotone. 他说话单调低沉。 5. She lay flat on her back in the warm sunshine. 她在温暖的阳光下平躺著。 6. She is buying a flat close to her office. 她正在购买一套靠近她办公室的单元房。', '副词: flatly 比较级: flatter 最高级: flattest 名词: flatness 过去式: flatted 过去分词: flatted 现在分词: flatting 第三人称单数: flats');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('notify', '[\'noʊtɪfaɪ]', 'v.通报', '1. Please notify us of any change of address. 地址如有变动，请通知我们。 2. She notified us of the meeting. 她通知我们开会。 3. We\'ll notify her to draw up a contract. 我们将通知她起草一份合同。 4. They will notify her when to appear in court. 他们将通知她何时出庭。', '名词: notifier 过去式: notified 过去分词: notified 现在分词: notifying 第三人称单数: notifies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('multitude', '[\'mʌltɪtuːd]', 'n.多数,群众', '1. A multitude of heroic figures emerge. 大量英雄人物出现了。 2. An angry multitude collected in the street. 街道上聚集了一大群愤怒的人。 3. There are a multitude of reasons against it. 有许多反对理由。 4. The multitude may laugh at his music, but we know better. 一般人也许会嘲笑他的音乐，但我们更了解它。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('corrode', '[kə\'roʊd]', 'v.使腐蚀,侵蚀', '1. Iron corrodes easily. 铁易锈损。 2. This acid may corrode iron. 这种酸能腐蚀铁。 3. Certain chemicals will corrode if left on bare metal. 有些化学药品如留在裸露的金属上会起腐蚀作用。 4. The furniture should be of smooth, hard material not liable to warp or corrode. 家具应使用光滑、坚硬、不易变形和腐蚀的材料制作。', '形容词: corrodible 过去式: corroded 过去分词: corroded 现在分词: corroding 第三人称单数: corrodes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('array', '[ə\'reɪ]', 'n.排列,编队,军队,衣服,大批;vt.部署,穿着,排列', '1. The era also gave birth to a whole array of new social problems. 那个时代还产生了一系列新的社会问题。 2. We have quite an array of leather shoes. 我们有一大批各类皮鞋。 3. Today\'s vehicles offer an array of advanced safety features. 现在的汽车都提供了大量先进的安全设备。 4. Our troops were drawn up in battle array. 我们的部队已严阵以待。 5. I want to array this specimen mount in the display window. 我想把这个标本架放到橱窗里。', '过去式: arrayed 过去分词: arrayed 现在分词: arraying 第三人称单数: arrays');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('intervene', '[ˌɪntər\'viːn]', 'vi.干涉,干预,插入,介入,(指时间)介于其间;v.干涉', '1. Don\'t intervene in the affairs of another country. 不要干涉别的国家的事务。 2. It\'s time that men of good sense and good will to intervene. 这该是那些头脑清醒和心地善良的人们出面干预的时候了。 3. You\'d better not intervene in their dispute. 你最好还是不要介入他们的争端。 4. I am powerless to intervene in the matter. 我对调停此事无能为力。', '形容词: interventional 名词: intervenor 过去式: intervened 过去分词: intervened 现在分词: intervening 第三人称单数: intervenes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('patriot', '[\'peɪtriət]', 'n.爱国者', '1. The patriot sticks to his moral principles. 那个爱国者固守他自已的道德信念。 2. He regards himself as a patriot. 他自认为是个爱国者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('preliminary', '[prɪ\'lɪmɪneri]', 'adj.预备的,初步的', '1. They have made a preliminary investigation. 他们已经做了初步的调查。 2. Our team got beaten in the preliminary rounds of the competition. 我们队在这次比赛的预赛中遭淘汰。 3. Movies at the preliminary stage were silent. 电影在初期是无声的。 4. There are a lot of preliminaries to be gone through before you can visit a foreign country. 在出访外国之前要做好许多准备工作。', '副词: preliminarily 名词复数: preliminaries');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('coverage', '[\'kʌvərɪdʒ]', 'n.覆盖', '1. The wedding got massive media coverage. 婚礼得到大众传播媒介的广泛报道。 2. The television coverage of the event was rather sparse. 电视上对这件事报道很少。 3. This radio station has great coverage. 这个无线电的覆盖范围很广。 4. The proportion of vegetation coverage in this area is 52.7%. 这个地区植被覆盖面积是52.', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reckon', '[\'rekən]', 'vt.计算,总计,估计,猜想;vi.数,计算,估计,依赖,料想', '1. Did you reckon in the cost of the taxi? 你把出租车费算进去了吗？ 2. You should reckon in the cost of fuel. 你应当把燃料费计算在内。 3. They reckon the book as one of his best works. 他们认为这本书是他的优秀作品之一。 4. The news won\'t worry her, I reckon. 我看这消息不会使她不安。', '过去式: reckoned 过去分词: reckoned 现在分词: reckoning 第三人称单数: reckons');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('efficient', '[ɪ\'fɪʃnt]', 'adj.(直接)生效的,有效率的,能干的', '1. This is a highly efficient new heating system. 这是个高效的新取暖系统。 2. Consequently, we have been developing a more efficient engine. 结果,我们已经开发了一台更高性能的发动机。 3. The success of CAD systems is becoming more dependent on the efficient drafting. cad系统的成功在很大程度上取决于草图的制图效率。 4. He\'s efficient at his job. 他胜任工作。', '副词: efficiently');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('schedule', '[\'skedʒuːl]', 'n.时间表,进度表;v.确定时间', '1. I\'ll work out the schedule. 我来拟定时间表。 2. Please show me the taxation schedule. 请让我看看税收一览表。 3. Owing to various delays en route, we arrived two days behind schedule. 由于路上的种种耽搁, 我们比原计划迟到了两天。 4. He was scheduled to attend the party. 他预定出席那个宴会。', '形容词: schedular 名词: scheduler 过去式: scheduled 过去分词: scheduled 现在分词: scheduling 第三人称单数: schedules');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cabinet', '[\'kæbɪnət]', 'n.(有抽屉或格子的)橱柜,<美>内阁;adj.<美>内阁的,小巧的', '1. She needs a cherry cabinet in her room. 她需要在她房里添一个樱桃木的柜子。 2. I put my collection of old glasses in the cabinet. 我把收集的古玻璃器皿放在橱里。 3. The question was discussed in cabinet. 在内阁会议上讨论了这个问题。 4. They have found out the mole in the cabinet. 他们已经发现了内阁中的间谍。 5. He was elevated to cabinet rank. 他被提升到内阁部长级。', '名词: cabinetful');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('transient', '[\'trænʃnt]', 'adj.短暂的,瞬时的;n.瞬时现象', '1. Her feeling of depression was transient. 她那抑郁的心情一会儿就过去了。 2. Their happiness was transient,for the war broke out soon after they got married. 他们的幸福是短暂的，因为他们婚后不久就爆发了战争。 3. We stayed at the inn as transient guests. 我们在小酒馆中只作短暂停留。 4. We are just the transients at the hotel. 我们只是旅馆里的过往旅客。', '副词: transiently');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('addition', '[ə\'dɪʃn]', 'n.加,加起来,增加物,增加,加法', '1. In addition to a diet, she pursues various exercises on TV. 节食以外她还随电视做体操。 2. In addition to an album, I gave him a pen and a pencil. 除了一本照相簿外，我还给了他一支钢笔和一支铅笔。 3. They eat a great deal of fruit in addition. 他们还吃大量的水果。 4. Addition and division are forms of computation. 加法和除法都是计算方法。', '形容词: additional 副词: additionally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('commission', '[kə\'mɪʃn]', 'n.委任,委托,代办(权),代理(权),犯(罪),佣金;vt.委任,任命,委托,委托制作,使服役', '1. Do not deduct any commission from the consignment value. 不要从货物的价值中扣除佣金。 2. The report was submitted to the commission for consideration. 这份报告已呈报委员会审批。 3. He had received the commission to build a new bridge over the river. 他受委托在这条河上建一座新桥。 4. We all approve of the commission of authority to him. 我们都赞成把职权委任於他。 5. He was commissioned captain of the United States Air Force. 他被授予美国空军上校。', '形容词: commissional 过去式: commissioned 过去分词: commissioned 现在分词: commissioning 第三人称单数: commissions');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('conversion', '[kən\'vɜːrʒn]', 'n.变换,转化', '1. He has undergone a religious conversion. 经历一次宗教信仰的转变。 2. In the conversion of saliva into poison, one might suppose that a fixed process took place. 人们可能认为,唾液转变成毒液,其中有固定的程序。 3. When he saw how the theory increased unemployment, he underwent quite a conversion. 当他看到这个理论加重了失业后，他彻底改变了看法。 4. Conversion to gas central heating will save you a lot of money. 改用煤气集中供暖将节省大笔开支。', '形容词: conversional');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('challenge', '[\'tʃælɪndʒ]', 'n.挑战;vt.向...挑战', '1. The crossing of this dangerous river was a challenge to most of us. 对我们大多数人来说,横渡这条充满危险的大河确实是个挑战。 2. He accepted his friend\'s challenge to swim across the river. 他接受朋友提出的挑战，游过这条河。 3. We accepted their challenge to a baseball game. 我们接受了他们棒球邀请的挑战。 4. He ignored the sentry\'s challenge to halt. 他不理睬哨兵喝令止步的盘问。 5. Nowadays no one will challenge the fact that the earth is round. 现在没有人会对地球是圆的这一事实提出异议。', '形容词: challengeable 过去式: challenged 过去分词: challenged 现在分词: challenging 第三人称单数: challenges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('respective', '[rɪ\'spektɪv]', 'adj.分别的,各自的', '1. He drove them both to their respective homes. 他驾车把他们分别送到家里。 2. The three men were given work according to their respective abilities. 这三个人根据各自的能力被分配了工作。 3. Product name is trademark or registered trademark of their respective owner. 产品名称为它们各自所有者的商标或注册商标。', '名词: respectiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('plague', '[pleɪɡ]', 'n.瘟疫,麻烦,苦恼,灾祸;vt.折磨,使苦恼,使得灾祸', '1. Plague came in the wake of earthquake. 地震之后紧跟着就是瘟疫。 2. A great plague was then raging in the city. 那时一场大瘟疫正在该城肆虐。 3. He\'s been avoiding me like the plague since our quarrel. 我们吵架以後，他一直如避蛇蝎似的躲著我。 4. A plague of locusts affected the harvest a lot this year. 蝗灾大大影响了今年的丰收。 5. A demon or spirit once was thought to plague sleeping people. 梦魔被认为折磨睡觉的人的魔鬼或灵魂', '名词: plaguer 过去式: plagued 过去分词: plagued 现在分词: plaguing 第三人称单数: plagues');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('snatch', '[snætʃ]', 'v.攫取;n.攫取', '1. The thief made a snatch at the woman\'s purse. 小偷试图抢夺那妇女的钱包。 2. He made a brave snatch at victory but failed. 他奋力争取胜利，但是失败了。 3. He has a snatch of sleep sitting in his chair. 他坐在椅子里稍睡片刻。 4. They put the snatch on him for a cut of the take. 他们强要他分给他们一分。 5. He snatched up his gun and fired. 他突然拿起枪来射击。', '名词: snatcher 过去式: snatched 过去分词: snatched 现在分词: snatching 第三人称单数: snatches');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('oath', '[oʊθ]', 'n.誓言,宣誓,诅咒', '1. Repeat the oath after me. 请跟着我宣誓。 2. The judge received their oath of allegiance. 法官听取了他们的忠诚誓言。 3. Tom stood by his oath to his father. 汤姆遵守他给父亲立下的誓言。 4. She carries an oath rod that will destory the minds of those it strikes. 她携带着一根誓约之杖，能够摧毁所有被杖击中者的意识。', '名词复数: oaths');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('describe', '[dɪ\'skraɪb]', 'vt.描写,记述,形容,形容;v.描述', '1. The police asked me to describe exactly how it happened. 警察让我描述一下这事是怎样发生的。 2. Words cannot describe the beauty of the scene. 语言难以描述那景色之美丽。 3. He describes himself as a doctor. 他自称是医生。 4. No one could describe the scorn of her expression. 谁也无法形容她那股鄙夷万分的表情。', '形容词: describable 名词: describer 过去式: described 过去分词: described 现在分词: describing 第三人称单数: describes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fragrance', '[\'freɪɡrəns]', 'n.芬芳,香气,香味', '1. This tiny flower gives forth a pleasant fragrance. 这种小花散发出一种令人愉快的香味。 2. The flowers send forth special fragrance. 这些花散发出特别的香味。 3. Lavender has a delicate fragrance. 薰衣草有淡淡的香味。 4. The girl held the flower to her face and the inhalation of its fragrance made her happy. 女孩将花拿到面前闻了一下,花香使她高兴。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('attempt', '[ə\'tempt]', 'n.努力,尝试,企图;vt.尝试,企图', '1. He attempted to smother up the scandal about his family. 他企图掩饰有关他家庭的丑闻。 2. I would be the last to attempt to answer the question. 我是最不可能去尝试回答这个问题。 3. The enemy failed in their attempt to land on the island. 敌人在岛上登陆的企图失败了。 4. He studied hard in an attempt to pass the exam. 他努力学习试图通过考试。', '形容词: attemptable 名词: attempter 过去式: attempted 过去分词: attempted 现在分词: attempting 第三人称单数: attempts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('exception', '[ɪk\'sepʃn]', 'n.除外,例外,反对,异议', '1. There is always an exception to any rule. 任何规律总有例外。 2. All students without exception must take the English examination. 所有的学生毫无例外，都必须参加英语考试。 3. The spelling of this word is an interesting exception to the rule. 这个词的拼写很有趣,是本规则的例外。 4. He took great exception to what I said. 他极力反对我的话。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mediate', '[\'miːdieɪt]', 'v.仲裁,调停,作为引起...的媒介,居中调停', '1. He attempted to mediate their differences. 他试图调停他们的分歧。 2. He cooled the situation down by offering to mediate between the disputing parties. 他提出愿为争执的双方调停，情况因此缓和下来。 3. A well-known local lawyer has been appointed to mediate between the employers and the union leaders, since they can\'t reach an agreement in direct talks. 既然雇主们同工会领袖无法在直接谈判中达成协议，就指定了一位当地的名律师进行调解。 4. He tried to mediate between his colleagues and management. 他设法在同事和管理阶层之间斡旋。 5. There were some mediate contacts between the two countries before their diplomatic relation was established. 在两国外交关系建立之前, 已经有些间接的接触。', '副词: mediately 过去式: mediated 过去分词: mediated 现在分词: mediating 第三人称单数: mediates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('abrupt', '[ə\'brʌpt]', 'adj.突然的,陡峭的,生硬的', '1. The river takes an abrupt bend to the west. 这河突然向西转弯。 2. His speech comes to an abrupt stop. 他的演讲突然停止了。 3. That young man has an abrupt manner. 那个年轻人态度很无礼。 4. His manner of speaking was quite abrupt. 他的说话方式很唐突。', '副词: abruptly 名词: abruptness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('accustomed', '[ə\'kʌstəmd]', 'adj.通常的,习惯的,按照风俗习惯的', '1. He was accustomed to command, not to entreat. 他习惯于发号施令，而不是恳求他人。 2. You will soon get accustomed to the climate here. 你会很快习惯这里的气候的。 3. I might have been incredulous had I not been accustomed to such responses. 若非我已经习惯了这样的回答，我可能不敢轻易相信。 4. He is accustom to get up at six. 他习惯于6点起床。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('conserve', '[kən\'sɜːrv]', 'vt.保存,保藏', '1. This is a recipe for strawberry conserve. 这是制作草莓酱的食谱。 2. I was surprised to find that the strong man liked to eat conserves. 我很惊讶地发现这个强壮的男人喜欢吃蜜饯。 3. This is a recipe for strawberry conserve. 这是制作草莓酱的食谱。 4. We must learn to conserve what remains. 我们必须学会保存那些剩余的资源。', '形容词: conservable 名词: conserver 过去式: conserved 过去分词: conserved 现在分词: conserving 第三人称单数: conserves');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('elevate', '[\'elɪveɪt]', 'vt.举起,提拔,振奋,提升...的职位', '1. They had the attempt to elevate Anderson to the presidency. 他们企图把安德逊抬上总统宝座。 2. He used a couple of bolsters to elevate his head. 他用两个垫枕垫头。 3. They had the attempt to elevate Anderson to the presidency. 他们企图把安德逊抬上总统宝座。 4. Reading good books elevates your mind. 阅读好书使人思想高尚。', '过去式: elevated 过去分词: elevated 现在分词: elevating 第三人称单数: elevates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tutor', '[\'tuːtər]', 'n.家庭教师,(大学)指导教师,助教,监护人,辅导教师;v.辅导', '1. His parents employed a tutor to teach him Greek. 他父母雇佣了一位家庭教师来教他希腊语。 2. My tutor is an accomplished scholar. 我的导师是一位学识渊博的学者。 3. Most parents have no time to tutor their children. 大部分家长没有时间辅导孩子。 4. For extra money, she tutors on weekends. 为了多挣些钱，她在周末当家庭教师。', '过去式: tutored 过去分词: tutored 现在分词: tutoring 第三人称单数: tutors');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('update', '[ˌʌp\'deɪt]', 'v.使现代化,修正,校正,更新;n.现代化,更新', '1. The data should be updated once a week. 这些数据应该每星期更新一次。 2. The feedback from the computer enables us to update the program. 计算机的反馈能使我们更新程序。 3. I would advise you to update the software. 我建议你把这个软件升级。 4. Maps need regular updates. 地图需要经常修订。', '过去式: updated 过去分词: updated 现在分词: updating 第三人称单数: updates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('drag', '[dræɡ]', 'v.拖,拖曳,缓慢而费力地行动;n.拖拉', '1. He dragged the heavy case across the floor. 他在地板上拖着那个沉重的箱子。 2. shrug aside 不予理会 3. She dragged herself out of bed, still half asleep. 她挣扎着起了床,还是睡眼惺忪。 4. She always drags behind us. 她总是在我们后面吃力地跟着。 5. The cat is really excited by the drag of the basket on the floor. 在地板上来来回回拖着篮子可着实让那只猫兴奋了一回。', '过去式: dragged 过去分词: dragged 现在分词: dragging 第三人称单数: drags');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('enroll', '[ɪn\'roʊl]', 'v.[亦作enrol]登记,招收,使入伍(或入会、入学等),参加,成为成员', '1. He enrolled our names. 他把我们的名字登记下来了。 2. He enrolled with an employment agency for a secretary. 他在职业介绍所登记要当秘书。 3. This school plan to enroll 100 students every year. 该校每年只招收100名学生。 4. His son was enrolled for military service a couple of years ago. 他儿子在两三年前应募入伍。', '名词: enrollee');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('stock', '[stɑːk]', 'n.树干,库存,股票,股份,托盘,祖先,原料;adj.股票的,普通的,常备的,存货的,繁殖用的;vt.装把手于,进货,备有,放牧;vi.出新芽,采购', '1. We have a large stock of tinned fruit. 我们有大批水果罐头的存货。 2. The grocer\'s has plenty varieties of goods in stock. 杂货商有种类繁多的存货。 3. We need to replenish our stocks of coal. 我们需要再次补充煤的储备。 4. Branches grow from the stock of the tree. 树枝是从树干上生长出来的。 5. We must stock up with food for the holiday. 我们必须采购一些食品以备假期之需。 6. She\'s tired of her husband\'s stock jokes. 她已听厌了丈夫那老一套的俏皮话。', '名词: stockage 过去式: stocked 过去分词: stocked 现在分词: stocking 第三人称单数: stocks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('neglect', '[nɪ\'ɡlekt]', 'vt.忽视,疏忽,漏做;n.忽视,疏忽,漏做', '1. You shouldn\'t neglect your health. 你不该忽略你的健康。 2. No country can afford to neglect education. 任何国家都不容忽视教育。 3. He neglected to write and say \"Thank you\". 他忘了写信道谢。 4. She was severely criticized for neglect of duty. 她因玩忽职守而受到严厉批评。', '名词: neglecter 过去式: neglected 过去分词: neglected 现在分词: neglecting 第三人称单数: neglects');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('renaissance', '[\'renəsɑːns]', 'n.复兴,复活,新生,文艺复兴,文艺复兴时期', '1. Her book captures the quintessence of Renaissance humanism. 她的书抓住了文艺复兴时期人文主义的精髓。 2. Florence is the shrine of the Renaissance. 佛罗伦萨是文艺复兴的圣地。 3. These are the cultural legacies of the Renaissance. 这些是文艺复兴时期的文化遗产。 4. Leonardo da Vinci is a famous artist in the Italian Renaissance. 利奥纳多·达·芬奇是意大利文艺复兴时期的一位知名画家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('conform', '[kən\'fɔːrm]', 'vt.使一致,使遵守,使顺从;vi.符合,相似,适应环境;adj.一致的,顺从的', '1. His ideas do not conform to mine. 他的想法和我的不一致。 2. He doesn\'t conform to the usual stereotype of the city businessman with a dark suit and rolled umbrella. 他不像典型的城市商人那样，穿一身深色的套服、 带一把收好的雨伞。 3. She refused to conform to the normal social conventions. 她拒绝遵从正常的社会习俗。 4. She left home to escape the pressure to conform to her family\'s way of life. 她离家出走以求摆脱她家生活方式对她的束缚。', '名词: conformer 过去式: conformed 过去分词: conformed 现在分词: conforming 第三人称单数: conforms');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('principle', '[\'prɪnsəpl]', 'n.法则,原则,原理', '1. A bicycle and a motorcycle are built on the same principle. 自行车和摩托车是根据同样的原理制造的。 2. Archimedes ,a great physicist ,discovered the principle of floating bodies . 阿基米德，一位伟大的物理学家，发现了浮体原理。 3. We adhere to the principle that everyone should be treated fairly. 我们坚持人人都应该被平等对待这一原则。 4. It is easier to fight for one\'s principle than to live up to them. 为自己的主义斗争，要比他们施诸实践更容易。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('corporate', '[\'kɔːrpərət]', 'adj.社团的,法人的,共同的,全体的', '1. This company is concerned about its corporate image. 这家公司关心它自身的法人形象。 2. The owner opened a corporate checking account at the bank. 公司老板在银行开了一个法人账户。 3. I\'d like to make an appointment to see your Corporate Finance Manager. 我想约见一下你们公司的财务经理。 4. This is our corporate responsibility. 这是我们共同的责任。', '副词: corporately');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('collide', '[kə\'laɪd]', 'vi.碰撞,抵触', '1. The bus and the van collided. 公共汽车与客货车相撞。 2. The ships collided in the fog. 轮船在雾中相撞。 3. As the bus turned the corner, it collided with a van. 公共汽车转过拐角时与客货车相撞。 4. But during the collision, one galaxy can rip the other apart gravitationally, and dust and gas common to both galaxies does collide. 当星系互撞期间，星系可能因重力拉扯另外一个星系，尘埃与云气也会因此而合并。', '过去式: collided 过去分词: collided 现在分词: colliding 第三人称单数: collides');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('brisk', '[brɪsk]', 'adj.敏锐的,凛冽的,轻快的,活泼的;vt.使活泼;vi.活跃起来', '1. His movements were brisk and boyish. 他的动作仍很敏捷，孩子气。 2. He was a vigorous, brisk person. 他是一个强壮的，活泼有力的人。 3. Diana \'s brisk, commanding voice rang out from a passage way. 黛安娜活泼而威严的声音从一条过道中传了出来。 4. Trading was brisk on the Stock Exchangetoday. 今日证券交易所交投活跃。 5. He brisked up his pace at the beautiful sight. 看到那美丽的景色，他加快了脚步。', '副词: briskly 比较级: brisker 最高级: briskest 名词: briskness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('refund', '[\'riːfʌnd]', 'v.退还,偿还;n.归还,偿还额,退款', '1. The residents made a claim for the refund of property tax. 居民们要求发还物业税。 2. We insisted on a refund of the full amount. 我们坚决要求全额退款。 3. Needless to say, we shall refund any expenses you may incur. 不用说，我们将会偿还你所担负的任何费用。 4. We will refund you if the purchase has any quality defect. 如果所购物品存在质量问题，我们将退款给您。', '形容词: refundable 名词: refunder 过去式: refunded 过去分词: refunded 现在分词: refunding 第三人称单数: refunds');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('contention', '[kən\'tenʃn]', 'n.争夺,争论,争辩,论点', '1. This is an issue of great contention at the moment. 眼下这个问题是争论的热点。 2. The subject deserves contention. 这个问题值得争论。 3. The judge balanced the contention of both parties . 法官权衡了双方的争辩。 4. Three players are in contention to win the title. 三个运动员在争夺这个项目的冠军。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sacred', '[\'seɪkrɪd]', 'adj.神的,宗教的,庄严的,神圣的', '1. In India the cow is a sacred animal. 在印度，牛是神圣的动物。 2. We use them to protect our sacred grounds. 我们使用它们来保卫我们神圣的土地。 3. Nothing is sacred to these wild youths. 这些狂野的年轻人什么都不尊重。 4. This area was hallowed by sacred memories. 这个地区由于宗教上的纪念意义而被视为圣地。', '副词: sacredly 名词: sacredness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('eligible', '[\'elɪdʒəbl]', 'adj.符合条件的,合格的', '1. Mary is not eligible for an award. 玛丽没有申请助学金的资格。 2. Anyone over the age of 18 is eligible to vote. 任何年满18岁的人都有资格投票。 3. I know an eligible young lady who would be an excellent cooperator for you. 我认识一个合适的年青女士,她能成为你最称心如意的合作者。', '副词: eligibly 名词: eligibility');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('envisage', '[ɪn\'vɪzɪdʒ]', 'v.正视', '1. Nobody can envisage the consequences of total nuclear war. 没有人能想像出全面核子战争的后果。 2. I don\'t envisage working with him again. 我想像不出再与他一起工作的可能。 3. Nobody can envisage the consequences of total nuclear war. 没有人能想像出全面核子战争的后果。 4. I can\'t envisage the plan(\'s)working. 我无法设想计划能否行得通.', '过去式: envisaged 过去分词: envisaged 现在分词: envisaging 第三人称单数: envisages');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('design', '[dɪ\'zaɪn]', 'n.设计,图案,花样,企图,图谋,(小说等的)构思,纲要;v.设计,计划,谋划,构思', '1. This dress is of the latest design. 这件衣服是最新设计。 2. He chalked out a design on the blackboard. 他用粉笔在黑板上勾划出一个图样。 3. The bedcover was quilted in a flower design. 床罩被缝成花卉图案。 4. His evil designs were frustrated. 他的罪恶企图未能得逞。 5. He designed us a beautiful house. 他为我们设计了一所很美的房子。', '形容词: designable 过去式: designed 过去分词: designed 现在分词: designing 第三人称单数: designs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cane', '[keɪn]', 'n.细长的茎,藤条;vt.以杖击,以藤编制', '1. He offered to strike the boy with his cane. 他威胁要用手杖打那个男孩。 2. He walks along briskly, twirl his cane in the air. 他一边轻快地走著，一边用手杖在空中旋转。 3. The blow of the cane stung the boy\'s fingers. 藤条的抽打使那男孩的手指感到刺痛。 4. She thrashed the children with a cane. 她用藤条痛打孩子们。 5. They cane our palms according to our marks. 他们根据我们的分数来打手心。', '名词: caner 过去式: caned 过去分词: caned 现在分词: caning 第三人称单数: canes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('comprehension', '[ˌkɑːmprɪ\'henʃn]', 'n.理解,包含', '1. It is above comprehension. 那是难于理解的。 2. This event was a tragedy that strained all comprehension. 这一事件是人们怎么也不能理解的一个悲剧。 3. It\'s quite past my comprehension. 这件事已远超出我的理解力了。 4. Learning Chinese, you must have good comprehension. 学习汉语,必须要有很强的理解力', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('behavior', '[bɪ\'heɪvjə]', 'n.举止,行为', '1. His behavior was, in a word, shocking. 总之，他的行为是令人震惊的。 2. His behavior called forth sharp criticism. 他的行为招致尖锐的批评。 3. His strange behavior made the police suspicious. 他不寻常的举止引起了警察的怀疑。 4. Their behavior towards me shows that they do not like me. 他们对我的举止说明他们不喜欢我。', '形容词: behavioral 副词: behaviorally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('threaten', '[\'θretn]', 'vt.恐吓,威胁,预示(危险),似有发生或来临的可能,可能来临', '1. The rebels threatened to seize civilian hostages. 叛乱分子威胁要扣押平民为人质。 2. The strikers were threatened with dismissal if they did not return to work. 罢工者受到威胁说，如果他们不复工，就会被解雇。 3. They threatened him with a law suit. 他们以控告来恐吓他。 4. The black clouds threatened rain. 乌云密布预示着将要下雨。', '副词: threateningly 名词: threatener 过去式: threatened 过去分词: threatened 现在分词: threatening 第三人称单数: threatens');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('criminal', '[\'krɪmɪnl]', 'n.罪犯,犯罪者;adj.犯罪的,犯法的,罪恶的', '1. The criminal was sentenced to prison for theft. 那个犯人因偷窃被判入狱。 2. Murder and stealing are criminal acts. 谋杀和偷盗都是犯罪行为。 3. I have no criminal record in my whole life. 我一生无犯罪纪录。 4. They were reinvestigating a criminal case. 他们正在复查一桩刑事案件。', '副词: criminally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('parasite', '[\'pærəsaɪt]', 'n.寄生虫,食客', '1. Rupture of the parasite may result in anaphylaxis. 寄生虫的碎裂可能导致过敏反应。 2. These flies carry a dangerous parasite. 这些苍蝇携带一种危险的寄生虫。 3. The parasite\'s host could be any bird. 该寄生生物的宿主可以是任何鸟类。 4. The result is a repeated signal, and a new limb forms in addition to the one to which the parasite attached itself. 这样的结果将是一种持续的讯号，而一种被寄生生物附著在肢体上所产生的新的生长型态将应运而生。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('melt', '[melt]', 'v.(使)融化,(使)熔化,使软化,使感动', '1. These chocolates really melt in your mouth. 这些巧克力真正是入口即化。 2. His heart melted when he saw the little girl crying. 看到这个小女孩哭起来，他的心软了。 3. If you warm ice it will melt into water. 如果你把冰加热，它会融化成水。 4. Metals will melt when heated to a certain temperature. 金属加热到一定的温度都会熔化。 5. The sun melted the snow. 太阳使雪融化。 6. If you warm ice it will melt into water. 如果你把冰加热，它会融化成水。', '形容词: meltable 副词: meltingly 名词: meltability 过去式: melted 过去分词: melted 现在分词: melting 第三人称单数: melts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('aspect', '[\'æspekt]', 'n.样子,外表,面貌,(问题等的)方面', '1. This is only one aspect of the problem. 这只是问题的一个方面。 2. He has made progress in every aspect. 他在各方面都有起色。 3. The building has a southern aspect. 那座建筑是朝南的。 4. The open spaces differ according to aspect. 开敞空地随方位而不同。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('axis', '[\'æksɪs]', 'n.轴', '1. The earth turns (ie rotates) on its axis once every 24 hours. 地球每24小时自转一圈。 2. A wheel revolves round/on its axis. 轮子是绕轴旋转的。 3. The earth\'s axis is the line between the North and South Poles. 地轴是南北极之间的线。 4. The axis of a circle is its diameter. 圆的轴线是其直径。', '名词复数: axes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('convenience', '[kən\'viːnjəns]', 'n.便利,方便,有益,有用的,方便的用具、机械、安排等', '1. It\'s a great convenience to live in town. 住在城市里有很大的方便。 2. I stock upon grocery at the convenience store. 我到便利商店买食品备用。 3. The hotel combines comfort with convenience. 这家旅馆既舒适又方便。 4. Analyzed experiment data, the best one is ultrasonic in the light of convenience, quick, especially avoid sample color disturbing and hydrargyrum pollution. 通过实验得出数据，进行分析，确定了超声法为最适宜样品前处理方法。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('participant', '[pɑːr\'tɪsɪpənt]', 'n.参与者,共享者;adj.参与的', '1. She is an active participant in this activity. 她积极参与这项活动。 2. He is an active participant in the civil rights movement. 他是人权运动的积极参加者。 3. Each participant is to pay his own expenses. 每个参与者都必须自费。', '名词: participance');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('wedge', '[wedʒ]', 'n.楔;vt.楔入,楔进', '1. Put a wedge under the door so that it will stay open. 在门底下塞一块楔子，让门保持开着。 2. The attackers formed a wedge and plowed through the enemy line. 进攻者形成了一个楔子，突破了敌军的阵线 3. He had a banana and a wedge of cheese for lunch. 他中饭吃一根香蕉和一块楔形的奶酪。 4. Please wedge this cabinet to keep it from tipping. 请在橱底楔入楔子以防它倾斜。', '过去式: wedged 过去分词: wedged 现在分词: wedging 第三人称单数: wedges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('boom', '[buːm]', 'n.繁荣,隆隆声;v.发隆隆声,兴隆,大事宣传', '1. It\'s a boom year this year. 今年是繁荣昌盛的一年。 2. He made his pile during the property boom. 在房地产生意兴隆期间他发了大财。 3. The oil market is enjoying a boom. 石油市场欣欣向荣。 4. City growth far outran the general population boom. 城市的发展大大超过总的人口激增。 5. The boom swung over the deck. 帆杠在甲板上转动。 6. Business is booming. 商业正日趋繁荣。 7. Foreign investments boomed the city. 国外投资使这个城市迅速繁荣起来。', '过去式: boomed 过去分词: boomed 现在分词: booming 第三人称单数: booms');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cord', '[kɔːrd]', 'n.绳索,束缚', '1. He tied the package with a cord. 他用绳子把包裹扎紧。 2. The dancer could kick over a cord four feet from the ground. 这位舞蹈家能把脚举到离地4英尺的绳索上面。 3. His mouth was taped, his hands and feet bound with curtain cord. 他的嘴上粘着胶布，手脚给窗帘拉索捆着。 4. Cindy and her fiance think of their letter as cord of love. 辛迪和她未婚夫把他俩的来往书信看作爱情的纽带。', '名词: corder 过去式: corded 过去分词: corded 现在分词: cording 第三人称单数: cords');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hug', '[hʌɡ]', 'n.拥抱', '1. It\'s common to hug when people meet in the US. 在美国,见面拥抱是件很平常的事。 2. He hurries down the gangplank to hug his waiting wife. 他匆匆忙忙走下跳板,张开双臂去拥抱等候着他的妻子。 3. The child was hugging her doll. 那孩子紧抱着她的洋娃娃。 4. He\'ll never change, and will hug his cherished beliefs. 他不会改变的，他将永守他所抱的信仰。 5. He greeted her with a loving hug. 他以一个深情的拥抱来迎接她。', '形容词: huggable 名词: hugger 过去式: hugged 过去分词: hugged 现在分词: hugging 第三人称单数: hugs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cozy', '[\'koʊzi]', 'adj.舒适的,安逸的,惬意的', '1. He lives in a cozy little room. 他住在一个舒适的小屋里。 2. I felt all cozy tucked up in bed. 我钻进被窝里，暖暖和和舒服极了。 3. That night was so peaceful and cozy. 是夜如此平静惬意。 4. In the morning we found all the children cozied up together in the same bed. 早晨，所有的小孩都挤到了一张床上。 5. I made a super cute tea cosy out of a recycled wool blanket. 我用旧毯子上拆下来的线做了一个非常可爱的茶具保温罩。', '副词: cozily 名词: coziness 名词复数: cozies 过去式: cozied/cosied 过去分词: cozied/cosied 现在分词: cozying/cosying 第三人称单数: cozies/cosies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('remain', '[rɪ\'meɪn]', 'vi.保持,逗留,剩余,残存', '1. We must learn to conserve what remains. 我们必须学会保存那些剩余的资源。 2. I didn\'t remain long in the city. 我没在那个城市逗留很长时间。 3. Though the sore being healed, yet a scar may remain. 伤口虽然痊愈, 却可能留下伤疤。 4. The present international situation remains tense and turbulent. 当前的国际局势依然紧张动荡。 5. After maintenance the main remains and remainders are left on the domain. 维修之后，主要遗骸和剩余物留在了领地上。', '过去式: remained 过去分词: remained 现在分词: remaining 第三人称单数: remains');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('quarterly', '[\'kwɔːrtərli]', 'n.季刊;adj.一年四次的,每季的;adv.每季地', '1. The quarterly dividend is their cardinal goal, and quick fixes are the means to accomplish it. 每个季度的分红是他们的主要目标，只要能最快地实现这个目标任何手段都成。 2. Lead the quarterly budgeting process and the monthly cash flow reporting and forecasting. 领导编制每一季度的预算以及定期的资金报告和预测。 3. This journal is bimonthly, and that one quarterly. 这本杂志是双月刊，那本是季刊。 4. Research Quarterly for Exercise and Sport. 锻炼和运动研究季刊。', '名词复数: quarterlies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cautious', '[\'kɔːʃəs]', 'adj.谨慎的,小心的', '1. She is cautious of telling secrets. 她很谨慎，不会泄露秘密。 2. He is cautious in his choice of words. 他措辞很谨慎。 3. They\'ve taken a very cautious approach. 他们采取了十分谨慎的态度。 4. The old lady is very cautious with money. 那位老太太用钱很谨慎。', '副词: cautiously 名词: cautiousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('erupt', '[ɪ\'rʌpt]', 'vt.喷出;vi.爆发', '1. Violence has erupted on the streets. 大街上突然发生了暴乱。 2. The demonstration erupted into violence. 示威游行中突然出现了武斗。 3. An active volcano may erupt at any time. 活火山随时可能喷发。 4. It\'s many years since Mount Vesuvius last erupted. 维苏威火山上一次喷发至今已有很多年了。', '形容词: eruptive 副词: eruptively 过去式: erupted 过去分词: erupted 现在分词: erupting 第三人称单数: erupts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('spine', '[spaɪn]', 'n.脊骨,书脊,地面隆起地带,中心,剌', '1. His spine developed a slight curve. 他的脊柱有点弯曲。 2. He got an injury to his spine when he fell off his horse. 他从马上摔下来，伤了脊梁骨。 3. Crimp spine on pages for permanent binding. 用装订机装订好书脊。 4. A little red cover with a broken spine. 那书有一个红红的封面和破败的书脊。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('insight', '[\'ɪnsaɪt]', 'n.洞察力,见识', '1. I\'ve got an insight into the problem. 我对问题豁然开朗。 2. The book is filled with remarkable insights. 这本书很有真知卓见。 3. In this new book he hits off the American temperament with amazing insight. 在这本新书里，他对美国人性格的描写表现出惊人的洞察力。 4. Once human limits are breached, the person sees beyond the horizon of human insight, to reach a truly cosmic consciousness. 当局限被打破,人们的洞察力就可以超越凡人,看到宇宙真正的奥秘。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('spite', '[spaɪt]', 'n.(in～of)不顾,不管,敌意;v.困扰', '1. I\'m sure he took my parking space just out of spite. 我认为他侵占我的停车位肯定是有意和我作对。 2. They trampled his flowers out of spite. 他们出于恶意踩了他的花。 3. There is no gall or spite in my soul. 我内心对谁都没有怨恨或恶意。 4. He took my best toy just out of spite! 他仅仅出于怨恨拿走了我最好的玩具！ 5. The bad children left the room dirty to spite their maid. 那些坏孩子把房间弄脏来刁难女佣人。', '过去式: spited 过去分词: spited 现在分词: spiting 第三人称单数: spites');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('prototype', '[\'proʊtətaɪp]', 'n.原型', '1. The strange mechanical device is the prototype of modern cars. 这个奇怪的机械装置是现代汽车的原型。 2. Designers have built a working prototype of the car. 设计者已经制造了汽车的工作原型。 3. This is the prototype for future school buildings. 这是未来的学校建筑的蓝本。 4. He is the prototype of good breeding. 他是具有良好教养的典范。', '形容词: prototypal');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('violent', '[\'vaɪələnt]', 'adj.猛烈的,激烈的,暴力引起的,强暴的', '1. The soldiers launched into a violent attack. 士兵们展开猛烈的攻击。 2. The violent blow sent him down on his knees. 那猛烈的一击使他跪倒在地。 3. She was in violent temper. 她暴跳如雷。 4. They showed violent opposition to the oppressor. 他们对压迫者表现出强烈的不满。', '副词: violently');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('series', '[\'sɪriːz]', 'n.连续,系列,丛书,级数', '1. The lecture series falls naturally into three parts. 该系列讲座可自然分作三部分。 2. The theory is based on a series of wrong assumptions. 这一理论是以一系列错误的设想为依据的。 3. He published a new series of readers for students of English. 他出版了一套新的英语学习丛书。 4. After a series of unsuccessful attempts, he has finally passed the driving test. 经过连续几次的失败，他最后终于通过了驾驶考试。', '名词复数: series');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('slot', '[slɑːt]', 'n.缝,狭槽,位置,水沟,细长的孔,硬币投币口,狭通道,足迹;vt.开槽于,跟踪', '1. She placed her card in a slot on the outside the bank. 她在银行外面把她的卡片塞进一条窄缝。 2. A cleaner slot is already reserved. 清洗器插槽已被保留。 3. He inserted a coin into the slot. 他把硬币插入投币口。 4. The best way to accomplish what on the list is to give each task a specific time slot. 完成单子上的各项任务的最好方法是给每项工作留出一个专门的时间。 5. We can slot in the new entry in alphabetical order. 我们可以按照字母顺序将新词条安插进去。', '过去式: slotted 过去分词: slotted 现在分词: slotting 第三人称单数: slots');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('consult', '[kən\'sʌlt]', 'v.商量,商议,请教,参考,考虑', '1. I will have to consult the plane time table first. 我得先查阅飞机时刻表。 2. He paused to consult his notes, and then proceeded with his questions. 他停下来看了看笔记，然后继续提问。 3. If you wish good advice, consult an old man. 若要主意好，老人须请教。 4. I need to consult with my colleagues on the proposals. 我需要和我的同事商讨这些建议。', '名词: consulter 过去式: consulted 过去分词: consulted 现在分词: consulting 第三人称单数: consults');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('prescription', '[prɪ\'skrɪpʃn]', 'n.指示,规定,命令,处方,药方', '1. The doctor is writing a prescription. 医生正在开处方。 2. The doctor dispensed a prescription to his patient. 医生开处方给病人配药。 3. The prescription of drugs is a doctor\'s responsibility. 开药方是医生的职责。 4. His prescription for economic recovery was not well received. 他为经济复苏提出的对策反应不佳。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('verge', '[vɜːrdʒ]', 'v.濒临;n.边缘', '1. The path verges on the edge of a precipice. 这条小径濒临断崖的边缘。 2. He is verging on a breakdown. 他正濒临精神崩溃。 3. The sun was verging towards the horizon. 太阳向地平线下降。 4. The economy verges toward inflation. 经济倾向于通货膨胀。 5. Her land verges on the neighboring township. 她的土地与邻镇相连。 6. The country\'s economy is on the verge of collapse. 这个国家的经济已到了崩溃的边缘。', '过去式: verged 过去分词: verged 现在分词: verging 第三人称单数: verges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('corps', '[kɔːr]', 'n.军团,兵队,团,兵种,技术兵种,特殊兵种,(德国大学的)学生联合会', '1. They were then beating up volunteers for the corps. 当时他们正在为军团募集志愿兵。 2. The Ministry of National Defence has recently embodied the troops in army corps. 最近国防部把军队编成了兵团. 3. The Marine Corps began to slim down under budget restrictions. 由于预算的限制，海军陆战队开始裁员。', '名词复数: corps');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('contest', '[\'kɑːntest]', 'n.论争,竞赛;v.,争论,争辩,竞赛,争夺', '1. She won a gold medal for her fine performance in the contest. 她在竞赛中成绩优异获金牌。 2. This football match is an unequal contest. 这场足球赛是一场实力悬殊的比赛。 3. Janet said she is thinking about attending a KTV contest. 珍妮说她正考虑参加一个KTV歌唱比赛。 4. I intend to contest the judge\'s decision in another court. 我准备下次开庭时反驳法官的判决。', '形容词: contestable 名词: contestation 过去式: contested 过去分词: contested 现在分词: contesting 第三人称单数: contests');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('shed', '[ʃed]', 'vt.流出,发散,散发,脱落,脱皮,摆脱;n.分水岭,棚,小屋,工棚,货棚;v.把...放入棚内,流下', '1. This method can help students shed inhibitions. 这一方法能帮助学生去除顾虑。 2. Most trees shed their leaves in autumn. 大多数树在秋天落叶。 3. It\'s too late to change your mind now and there is no point in shedding tears. 你现在改变主意已经太迟了,而且为此伤心落泪是毫无用处的。 4. Can you shed any light on the situation? 你能说明一下这个情形吗？ 5. The snow has banked up against the shed. 雪在小屋旁聚积起来。', '过去式: shed 过去分词: shed 现在分词: shedding 第三人称单数: sheds');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('motivate', '[\'moʊtɪveɪt]', 'v.激发', '1. He is just sitting there doing nothing. He needs to be motivated. 他坐在那儿什么也不干,他需要一点动力去激发他。 2. The crime appears to have been motivated by hatred. 犯罪似乎都来自于仇恨。 3. A good teacher is one who can motivate his students. 好老师是能激励学生的老师。', '名词: motivator 过去式: motivated 过去分词: motivated 现在分词: motivating 第三人称单数: motivates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sensation', '[sen\'seɪʃn]', 'n.感觉,感情,感动,耸人听闻的', '1. He had a sensation of dizziness. 他有一种晕眩的感觉。 2. I knew the train had stopped, but I had the sensation that it was moving backwards. 我知道火车已经停了，但我觉得火车在倒退。 3. The new discovery caused a great sensation. 这项新发现很轰动。 4. The outrageous book created a sensation. 那部耸人听闻的书曾轰动一时。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('simulate', '[\'sɪmjuleɪt]', 'vt.模拟,模仿,假装,冒充', '1. These insects can simulate dead leaves . 这些昆虫可以伪装成枯叶。 2. I tried to simulate surprise at the news. 听到这个消息后，我竭力装出一副吃惊的样子。 3. He shook a sheet of metal to simulate the noise of thunder. 他摇动一块金属薄片来模拟雷声。 4. You can simulate different browser types for tests. 您可以为测试模拟不同类型的浏览器。', '形容词: simulative 过去式: simulated 过去分词: simulated 现在分词: simulating 第三人称单数: simulates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('strategy', '[\'strætədʒi]', 'n.策略,军略', '1. The strategy was designed to wear down the enemy\'s resistance. 这一策略旨在逐步削弱敌人的抵抗力。 2. We will discuss our sale strategy this year. 我们将讨论有关今年销售策略的问题。 3. He is an expert in military strategy. 他是军事战略专家。 4. Each country needs to forge its own industrial development strategy. 每个国家都需要制定自己的工业发展战略。', '名词复数: strategies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('redundant', '[rɪ\'dʌndənt]', 'adj.多余的', '1. Skill has been made redundant by machine. 由于使用机器，手艺已变得多余。 2. This word is redundant, it can be left out. 这个字是多余的, 可以去掉。 3. There are too many redundant words in this book. 这本书里多余的词太多。', '副词: redundantly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('flare', '[fler]', 'n.闪光,闪耀;vi.闪光,突然烧起来,闪耀;vt.使闪耀,使张开', '1. The flare of the match lit up his face. 火柴的光照亮了他的脸。 2. He stood ready to fire a warning flare. 他站着准备发出警告信号。 3. One possibility is that the blast was like an ultra-powerful solar flare. 一种可能的原因是这种爆炸很像有超级能量的太阳耀斑。 4. These flows occurred after violently unstable magnetic reconnection events above the Sun produced the flare. 这些在太阳表面上空剧烈而又不稳定的磁重联事件会产生耀斑。 5. A gust of wind made the candles flare. 一阵风吹得烛光摇曳。', '过去式: flared 过去分词: flared 现在分词: flaring 第三人称单数: flares');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('convey', '[kən\'veɪ]', 'vt.搬运,传达,转让', '1. I find it hard to convey my feelings in word. 我觉得难以用言语表达我的感情。 2. Word will suffice to convey his grief. 他的悲伤足以用言辞表达。 3. A vibrating membrane in the ear helps to convey sounds to the brain. 耳膜的振动帮助声音传送到大脑。 4. This train conveys both passengers and goods. 这趟列车客货均载。', '形容词: conveyable 过去式: conveyed 过去分词: conveyed 现在分词: conveying 第三人称单数: conveys');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('profess', '[prə\'fes]', 'v.表示', '1. They have become what they profess to scorn. 他们成了自己曾声称看不起的那种人。 2. Those who today pretend to be Christ\'s followers hypocritically profess to carry out those teachings now. 今天那些冒牌的基督教徒假惺惺地声称他们现在要实行这些教导。', '副词: professedly 过去式: professed 过去分词: professed 现在分词: professing 第三人称单数: professes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pledge', '[pledʒ]', 'n.保证,誓言,抵押,抵押品;vt.保证,使发誓,抵押,典当,举杯祝...健康', '1. They pledged never to tell the secret. 他们发誓决不泄密。 2. We all had to pledge allegiance to the flag. 我们大家都得发誓忠于这面旗帜。 3. She pledged her support to us. 她保证支持我们。 4. I pledge myself to fulfil the promise I have made. 我保证实践自己的诺言。 5. And as we walk, we must make the pledge that we shall march ahead. 当我们行动时,我们必须保证勇往直前。', '过去式: pledged 过去分词: pledged 现在分词: pledging 第三人称单数: pledges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('breakdown', '[\'breɪkdaʊn]', 'n.崩溃,衰弱,细目分类', '1. His frequent depressions were the prelude to a complete mental breakdown. 他经常抑郁寡欢,后来精神完全崩溃了。 2. The old car rattled along again after a breakdown. 那辆破车在一次故障后又隆隆地行驶在路上了。 3. She suffered a nervous breakdown. 她患神经衰弱。 4. The accountant gave a breakdown of the expenses. 会计交出一份开支明细帐。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('enormous', '[ɪ\'nɔːrməs]', 'adj.巨大的,庞大的,<古>极恶的,凶暴的', '1. Long ago enormous animals lived on the earth. 很久以前，地球上生活着巨大的动物。 2. She stood alone on the enormous stage. 她孤零零地站在巨大的舞台上。 3. They overlooked the enormous risks involved. 他们忽略了暗含的巨大危险。 4. The sight of such an enormous crowd astonished us. 看到如此庞大的人群我惊讶万分。', '副词: enormously 名词: enormousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('menace', '[\'menəs]', 'n.威胁,危险物;v.恐吓,危及,威胁', '1. These weapons are a menace to world peace. 这些武器是对世界和平的威胁。 2. The man\'s lunatic behavior is a menace to society. 那个人的疯狂行为构成对社会的威胁。 3. That film creates an atmosphere of menace. 那部影片营造出吓人的气氛。 4. Your vicious dog is menacing my cat! 你那条恶狗对我家的猫太凶了！', '副词: menacingly 名词: menacer 过去式: menaced 过去分词: menaced 现在分词: menacing 第三人称单数: menaces');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('navigation', '[ˌnævɪ\'ɡeɪʃn]', 'n.航海,航空,导航,领航,航行', '1. Mechanics discovered problems with the plane\'s navigation system. 机械工发现飞机的导航系统存在问题。 2. Navigation is difficult on this river because of the hide rock. 因为有暗礁，在这条河上航行很困难。 3. The compass is an instrument of navigation. 罗盘是航行仪器。 4. The canal has been opened up to steam navigation. 运河已经可以航行轮船。', '形容词: navigational');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cathedral', '[kə\'θiːdrəl]', 'n.大教堂', '1. Photography is strictly forbidden in the cathedral. 教堂内严禁摄影。 2. This street offers a fine vista of the cathedral. 这条街的尽头是个大教堂，远远望去非常好看。 3. The dome of St. Paul Cathedral is well known in the world. 圣保罗教堂的圆顶闻名于世。 4. This cathedral was regarded as a miracle in architectural history. 这座大教堂被认为是建筑史上的奇迹。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ambition', '[æm\'bɪʃn]', 'n.野心,雄心', '1. You should persist in your ambition. 你应该坚持你的雄心大志。 2. The glory of his country is his ambition. 为国增光是他的雄心。 3. You will achieve your ambition if you work hard. 如果你努力, 你的抱负是可以实现的。 4. That political statesman is full of ambition. 那个政治家野心很大。 5. I never ambitioned it. 我从来不妄想得到它。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('essence', '[\'esns]', 'n.基本,[哲]本质,香精', '1. Flavor of life is always sweet, because they always taste the essence of life. 生活的味道总是甜蜜的,因为他们总是品尝到生活的精髓。 2. Simplicity is the essence of good taste. 纯朴是情趣高尚的主要因素。 3. Caution is the essence of that man\'s character. 谨慎是那人性格的本质。 4. The two things are the same in outward form but different in essence. 那两样东西在外表上相同，但在本质上不同。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('accident', '[\'æksɪdənt]', 'n.意外事件,事故', '1. His left knee was hurt in a traffic accident. 他的左膝在一次交通事故中受伤了。 2. Happily, the accident was prevented. 很幸运，事故得以避免了。 3. The other day I came across an interesting accident. 几天前,我碰到一件意外事情。 4. I started the hobby almost by accident. 我有了这个爱好纯属偶然。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('caution', '[\'kɔːʃn]', 'n.小心,谨慎,警告;vt.警告', '1. The teacher gave Tom a caution and told him never to do it again. 老师给了汤姆一次警告,叫他不许再那样做。 2. He told us to proceed with caution. 他要我们谨慎行事。 3. Always he sought someone to whom he could talk without caution. 他一直在找一个能够随便谈谈的人。 4. I must caution you against the danger. 我必须告诫你应谨防危险。', '过去式: cautioned 过去分词: cautioned 现在分词: cautioning 第三人称单数: cautions');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('author', '[\'ɔːθər]', 'n.作家,创造者', '1. This book shows that he is an ingenious author. 这本书表明他是一个有创造力的作家。 2. The book was translated without the sanction of the author. 这本书未经作者许可就给翻译了。 3. The book is authored by six leading historians. 这本书由六名权威的历史学家编写而成。 4. He authored two best-sellers. 他写过两部畅销书。 5. God is the author and approver of sin, for sin is the accomplishment of His will. 上帝是罪的始创者，罪既然成就上帝的旨意，因此是上帝喜悦的。', '形容词: authorial 过去式: authored 过去分词: authored 现在分词: authoring 第三人称单数: authors');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('precious', '[\'preʃəs]', 'adj.宝贵的,贵重的,珍爱的,过于精致的,珍爱的', '1. You should make good use of every precious minute to study. 你应很好利用宝贵的每一分钟去学习。 2. Pandas are precious creatures. 熊猫是珍贵的动物。 3. That old book is my most precious possession. 那本旧书是我最珍贵的财产。 4. He is a rather precious young man. 他是一个惺惺作态的年轻男子。 5. Precious few people can afford prices like that. 没有什麽人出得起那个价钱。', '副词: preciously 名词: preciousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('merely', '[\'mɪrli]', 'adv.仅仅,只,不过', '1. They are not merely content to fill the stomach. 他们不仅仅满足于填饱肚子。 2. I accepted this job merely for the high salary. 我仅仅是因为高薪才接受了这份工作。 3. She is merely a child. 她只不过是个孩子。 4. I merely suggest you should do it again. 我只是建议你重新做这件事。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('electrician', '[ɪˌlek\'trɪʃn]', 'n.电工,电学家', '1. He\'s neither an electrician nor a mechanic. 他既不是电工也不是技工。 2. Don\'t meddle with the electrical wiring: you\'re not an electrician. 别瞎动电线线路，你又不是电工。 3. We need an electrician to mend the iron. 我们要请电工修理熨斗。 4. He\'s apprenticed to an electrician. 他去跟一名电工技师当学徒。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('authorize', '[\'ɔːθəraɪz]', 'v.批准', '1. The committee authorized the payment of the money. 委员会批准该款之支付。 2. I\'ve been authorized by the court to repossess this property. 我得到法庭认可重新拥有这笔财产。 3. I have authorized him to act for me while I am away. 我已经委托他当我不在的时候代我处理。 4. He confidentially authorized me to act for him while he was abroad. 他信任地委托我在他出国期间代行他的职务。', '名词: authorizer 过去式: authorized 过去分词: authorized 现在分词: authorizing 第三人称单数: authorizes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('subscribe', '[səb\'skraɪb]', 'v.捐款,订阅,签署(文件),赞成,预订', '1. I subscribe to\" Reader\'s Digest\" magazine. 我订了《读者文摘》杂志。 2. They refused to subscribe to the agreement. 他们拒绝在协议上签字。 3. Do you subscribe to her pessimistic view of the state of the economy? 你是否同意她对经济状况所持的悲观看法？ 4. We subscribe to an animal protection society. 我们定期捐款给一个动物保护基金会。', '名词: subscriber 过去式: subscribed 过去分词: subscribed 现在分词: subscribing 第三人称单数: subscribes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('skull', '[skʌl]', 'n.头脑,头骨', '1. Have scientists found Mozart\'s skull? 科学家们已经找到了莫扎特的头骨吗? 2. Her skull had been fractured by two separate blows. 她的头骨在两次重击下骨折。 3. They stamped a skull and crossbones on the label of poisonous drug. 他们在毒药标签上打上骷髅图。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pope', '[poʊp]', 'n.罗马教皇,主教,蒲柏(1688-1744,英国诗人),大腿上要害部位;vt.打大腿上要害部位', '1. The Pope retreats to Castelgondolfo every summer. 罗马教皇每年夏天都退避到圣得罗。 2. Pope John XXIII once was invited to France to attend a banquet. 有一次，罗马教皇约翰二十三世应邀出席法国的一个盛大宴会，一位着装十分暴露的女士正巧坐在他的身边。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tenant', '[\'tenənt]', 'n.承租人,房客,租客;v.出租', '1. The tenant has not yet paid his rent. 房客还没有交付租金。 2. The desk was left by the previous tenant. 这张桌子是前面房客留下的。 3. He\'s a tenant farmer. 他是佃农. 4. There is a clause in the contract forbidding tenant to sublet. 合同中列有条款，禁止承租人转租。 5. I will tenant my building out during the summer vocation. 我会在暑假期间把房子租出去。', '过去式: tenanted 过去分词: tenanted 现在分词: tenanting 第三人称单数: tenants');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('opponent', '[ə\'poʊnənt]', 'adj.对立的,对抗的;n.对手,反对者', '1. He was assailed by his political opponent. 他遭到政敌的攻击。 2. I tried to comfort him after he was defeated by his opponent. 他被对手击败后，我尽力安慰他。 3. He knocked down his opponent with a powerful left. 他一记有力的左手拳将对手击倒。 4. He is slashing wildly at his opponent with a sword. 他正用剑疯狂地朝对手乱砍。 5. The company, which had long been an opponent of electrification, changed its stance earlier this year in light of slipping global sales. 该公司长期以来一直反对的电气化，改变了其立场，在今年早些时候，鉴于全球销售下滑。', '名词: opponency');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('misery', '[\'mɪzəri]', 'n.痛苦,苦恼,悲惨,不幸,穷困', '1. War necessarily causes misery and waste. 战争必然造成痛苦和破坏。 2. He was doomed to undergo another misery. 他注定要经历另一场痛苦。 3. One usually associates poverty with misery. 人们一说到贫穷，常常就联想起悲惨的境遇。 4. He endured agonies of loneliness and misery. 他忍受着寂寞和贫穷的折磨。', '名词复数: miseries');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hasty', '[\'heɪsti]', 'adj.匆忙的,草率的', '1. Some people are prone to jump to hasty conclusions. 有些人往往作出轻率的结论。', '副词: hastily 比较级: hastier 最高级: hastiest 名词: hastiness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('focus', '[\'foʊkəs]', 'n.(兴趣活动)中心,焦点,焦距,[医]病灶,地],震源;vi.聚焦,注视;vt.使集中,在焦点上,定焦点,调焦,集中', '1. He always wants to be the focus of attention. 他总想成为注意力的焦点。 2. He took out the binoculars and adjusted the focus. 他取出双筒望远镜并调整了焦距。 3. The main focus of this manual is the management of fresh ground water resources. 本指南的主要中心是地下淡水资源的管理。 4. The noise made it hard for me to focus on work. 噪音让我无法集中注意力工作。', '名词: focuser 名词复数: focuses 过去式: focused/focussed 过去分词: focused/focussed 现在分词: focusing/focussing 第三人称单数: focuses/focusses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('conference', '[\'kɒnfərəns]', 'n.会议,讨论会,协商会', '1. He is in conference. 他正在开会。 2. An international conference will be held in Beijing next month. 一个国际性的会议下月将在北京举行。 3. There will be a banquet following the conference. 会议过后将有一个宴会。 4. We are all fully confident that the conference will be a great success. 我们都有充分的信心,这次会议将会非常成功。', '形容词: conferential');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('proclaim', '[prə\'kleɪm]', 'vt.宣布,声明,显示,显露', '1. The president proclaimed that a new currency would be issued. 总统宣布将发行新货币。 2. She did not proclaim her intention. 她没有把自己的意图明说出来。 3. He was impelled to proclaim his doctrine. 他不得不宣扬他的教义。 4. His accent proclaimed that he was an American. 他的口音表明他是一个美国人。', '形容词: proclamatory 名词: proclaimer 过去式: proclaimed 过去分词: proclaimed 现在分词: proclaiming 第三人称单数: proclaims');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('occupy', '[\'ɑːkjupaɪ]', 'vt.占,占用,占领,占据', '1. Is that seat occupied? 那个座位有人吗？ 2. Reading occupies most of my free time. 阅读占去了我大部分的闲暇时间。 3. We occupy the farm and raise a lot of poultry. 我们拥有这个农场并养着许多家禽。 4. The enemy occupied the town. 敌人占据了这个城镇。', '名词: occupier 过去式: occupied 过去分词: occupied 现在分词: occupying 第三人称单数: occupies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('summon', '[\'sʌmən]', 'v.召集,召唤,号召,鼓起,振作', '1. I\'ve heard the residents of the Infernos will summon a Diety of Fire to honor any hero who brings them the Grail. 我听说地狱的居民会召唤烈火守护神来纪念为他们带来圣杯的英雄。 2. \"A man brags that he can summon the dead. 一个人炫耀说可以召唤死者灵魂。 3. The shareholders were summoned to a general meeting. 那些股东被召集去叁加股东大会。 4. They had to summon a second conference and change the previous decision. 他们不得不召集第二次会议，改变以前的决定。', '名词: summoner 过去式: summoned 过去分词: summoned 现在分词: summoning 第三人称单数: summons');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('versus', '[\'vɜːrsəs]', 'prep.对(指诉讼,比赛等中),与...相对', '1. That\'s a matter of outs versus ins. 那是在野党人与执政党人的对抗。 2. The big match tonight is England versus Spain. 今晚的大赛是英格兰对西班牙。 3. It is France versus Brazil in the final. 决赛是法国队对巴西队。 4. The most exciting game was Harvard versus Yale. 最富紧张刺激的球赛是哈佛队对耶鲁队。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('grim', '[ɡrɪm]', 'adj.严酷的', '1. Her face wore a grim, set look. 她脸上显出严厉、 木然的神情。 2. His expression was grim when he told them they had lost their job. 当他告诉他们说他们已被解雇时，他的表情十分冷酷。 3. A grim and unsightly picture met his eye. 一幅可怕和难看的情景映入他的眼帘。 4. I had a pretty grim day yesterday. 我昨天很不愉快。', '副词: grimly 比较级: grimmer 最高级: grimmest 名词: grimness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('intensive', '[ɪn\'tensɪv]', 'adj.强烈的,精深的,透彻的,[语法]加强语气的;n.加强器', '1. This patient requires intensive care. 该病人需要加强护理。 2. We concentrated intensive fire on the enemy. 我们集中密集的火力向敌人攻击。 3. An intensive search failed to reveal any clues. 经过彻底搜查未发现任何线索。 4. Do you have an intensive reading of English this term? 这个学期你们有英语精读课程吗？', '副词: intensively 名词: intensiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('remnant', '[\'remnənt]', 'n.残余,剩余,零料,残迹;adj.剩余的,残留的', '1. If something has been partly used or destroyed, we use remains or remnants. 若某物的一部分已用掉或毁掉，其剩余或残存部分可用。 2. I will sell this remnant to you, at cost. 我愿将此剩货照成本卖给你。 3. The remnants of last night\'s meal were still on the table. 昨天晚上的剩余物还在桌子上。 4. The Ainu settlers in Hokkaido are the last remnant of a prehistoric race. 北海道的阿伊努人是史前某个种族的最后残存者。 5. The beautiful curtain is made of remnant materials. 这个漂亮的窗帘是用零头布做的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('eternal', '[ɪ\'tɜːrnl]', 'adj.永恒的,永远的,不灭的,没完没了的', '1. The price of liberty is eternal vigilance. 自由的代价是永久提高警惕。 2. The bad man will suffer eternal damnation. 坏人将会受到永远的惩罚。 3. He is, as it were, an eternal boy. 他好像是个永远年轻的小伙子。 4. She felt eternal gratitude to him for saving her life. 她终生感激他的救命之恩。 5. The eternal motion of the stars fascinated him. 星体永恒的运行使他著迷。', '副词: eternally 名词: eternality');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tick', '[tɪk]', 'n.滴答声,记号,勾号,扁虱;v.滴答地响,标以记号,作滴答声', '1. The clock ticks very loudly. 这只钟发出很响的滴答声。 2. My watch doesn\'t tick because it\'s electronic. 我的表不滴答作响,因为它是电子表。 3. The teacher ticks off a name on a list. 老师在名单上的一个名字旁打勾。 4. Listen carefully and tick the sentences which are correct. 认真听，并标记正确的句子。 5. They could hear the regular tick of the clock. 他们能听见时钟有规律的滴答声。', '过去式: ticked 过去分词: ticked 现在分词: ticking 第三人称单数: ticks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('grant', '[ɡrænt]', 'vt.同意,准予,承认(某事为真)～', '1. Visa exemption does not grant the right to work. 豁免签证并不授予工作的权利。 2. We grant the truth of what you said. 我们同意你说的是事实。 3. I grant that your explanation is reasonable. 我承认你的解释是合理的。 4. I take it for granted you have read this book. 我认为你一定读过这本书。', '形容词: grantable 名词: granter 过去式: granted 过去分词: granted 现在分词: granting 第三人称单数: grants');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('electron', '[ɪ\'lektrɑːn]', 'n.电子', '1. Let us return to electron waves now. 现在我们再回到电子波上来。 2. An electron from one of the atom shells is ejected. 电子从原子的某一壳层中被弹射出来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('wardrobe', '[\'wɔːrdroʊb]', 'n.衣柜,衣厨,衣室,衣服,行头,剧装', '1. The wardrobe takes up too much space. 这衣橱太占地方了。 2. All the shirts hang together in the same wardrobe. 所有的衬衫都挂在同一个衣橱里。 3. Such an outfit would be a useful addition to my wardrobe. 在我的服装中添置这一套会有用的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bug', '[bʌɡ]', 'n.小虫,臭虫;v.装置窃听器,打扰', '1. Why do we need bug spray? 我们要杀虫剂干什么? 2. The police tested the room for bugs. 警察检查房间里是否放有窃听器。 3. There might be a bug in the program. 程序里可能有一个错误。 4. Be careful what you say; our conversation may be being bugged. 说话要当心，咱们的话可能被窃听了。', '名词: bugger 过去式: bugged 过去分词: bugged 现在分词: bugging 第三人称单数: bugs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('prestige', '[pre\'stiːʒ]', 'n.声望,威望,威信', '1. She enjoyed high prestige among the masses. 她在群众中享有很高威信。 2. He is an author of international prestige. 他是有国际声望的作家。 3. The old universities of Oxford and Cambridge still have a lot of prestige. 历史悠久的牛津大学和剑桥大学仍然享有很高的声望。 4. The company would do anything but risk their prestige at stake. 公司绝不愿将自己的信誉孤注一掷。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('brood', '[bruːd]', 'n.(动物中鸟或家禽的)一窝,(同种或同类的)一伙;vt.孵,沉思', '1. The bird was trying to find food for its brood. 鸟儿在为它的一窝小鸟觅食。 2. She grew up amidst a lively brood of brothers and sisters. 她是在一群活泼的兄弟姐妹中间长大的。 3. A brood of modern paintings will be exhibited at the museum. 一批现代画将在博物馆展览。 4. The hen broods ten eggs this time. 这次母鸡孵十个蛋。', '副词: broodingly 过去式: brooded 过去分词: brooded 现在分词: brooding 第三人称单数: broods');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('controversial', '[ˌkɑːntrə\'vɜːrʃl]', 'adj.争论的,争议的', '1. We tried to stay away from controversial topics at the dinner party. 晚宴上我们尽力避免一些有争议的话题。 2. This is a controversial question. 这是个引起争论的问题。', '副词: controversially 名词: controversialist');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('subordinate', '[sə\'bɔːrdɪnət]', 'adj.次要的,从属的,下级的;n.下属;v.服从', '1. He is a subordinate officer. 他是位下级军官。 2. She works in the subordinate hospital of our universtiy. 她在我们学校的附属医院工作。 3. All the other issues are subordinate to this one. 所有问题都要以这个问题为主。 4. He was always friendly to his subordinates. 他对下级一向和蔼可亲。 5. He subordinated his wishes to the general good of the group. 他使自己的愿望服从于集体的利益。', '形容词: subordinative 副词: subordinately 名词: subordinateness 过去式: subordinated 过去分词: subordinated 现在分词: subordinating 第三人称单数: subordinates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('silicon', '[\'sɪlɪkən]', 'n.[化]硅,硅元素', '1. Now people can produce a wafer silicon. 现在人们能够生产一种硅晶薄片。 2. Silicon is usually added by co-evaporation. 硅通常是通过共蒸发来加入的。 3. In computers, these diodes are primarily germanium or silicon crystals. 在计算机中,这些二极管基本上是锗或硅晶体二极管。', '简写符号: Si');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fitting', '[\'fɪtɪŋ]', 'adj.适合的,相称的,适宜的;n.试穿,试衣,装配,装置', '1. A fitting end to the meal would be a glass of port. 餐后一杯波尔图葡萄酒是挺合适的。 2. It was, in fine, a fitting end to the story. 总之，这是故事很恰当的结尾。 3. He expressed his thoughts in clear and fitting language. 他用明白恰当的语言来表达他的思想。 4. The fitting-room is at the corner. 试衣间在拐角处。', '副词: fittingly 名词: fittingness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('formula', '[\'fɔːrmjələ]', 'n.公式,规则,客套语', '1. They are working on the perfection of their new paint formula. 他们正在努力研制尽善尽美的新颜料配方。 2. What is the formula for water? 水的分子式是什么？ 3. Within the braces, you can include any formula. 在大括号内,可以包含任何公式。 4. It\'s the formula for converting gallons into liters. 这是加仑与升的换算公式。 5. His outwardly relaxed manner hides a sharp mind and a keen will to win, something he did a lot of on the nursery slopes of Formula BMW. 他轻松自若的举止下隐藏着敏锐的心思和渴望胜利的决心，这在他参加宝马方程式的培养期里就已经有所体现。', '形容词: formulaic 副词: formulaically 名词复数: formulas');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('radiant', '[\'reɪdiənt]', 'adj.发光的,辐射的,容光焕发的', '1. As you evolve, the petals unfold to reveal a radiant jewel in the center. 当你进化的时候，花瓣绽开显现出中心发光的珠宝。 2. Giant, snow-white in colour and gleaming bright, will beget a radiant people. 一位巨人，雪白的肤色，闪烁着明亮的光，会产生发光的人。 3. Giant, snow-white in colour and gleaming bright, will beget a radiant people. 一位巨人，雪白的肤色，闪烁着明亮的光，会产生发光的人。 4. Quantum theory proposes that radiant energy is transmitted in discrete units. 量子理论的提出辐射的能量能传递离散的单位。', '副词: radiantly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ballet', '[\'bæleɪ]', 'n.芭蕾舞,芭蕾舞剧,芭蕾舞乐曲', '1. He did a sketch of the ballet dancers. 他为这些芭蕾舞者画了一张素描。 2. She invited us to see the ballet. 她邀请我们去看芭蕾舞。', '形容词: balletic');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('signal', '[\'sɪɡnəl]', 'n.信号;adj.信号的;v.发信号,用信号通知', '1. A red lamp is often a danger signal. 红灯常常是危险的信号。 2. I corrected my watch by the time signal. 我按报时信号校正我的表。 3. I\'ve called several times, but I keep getting a busy signal. 我打了好几次了,可是一直是忙音。 4. We live too far from the city to get a strong television signal. 我们住的地方离城里太远, 不能收到清晰的电视图像。 5. The police signalled the traffic to move forward slowly. 警察向来往车辆打信号，示意缓慢前行。 6. People speak of Mark Twain as a signal humourous writer. 人们称马克·吐温为杰出的幽默作家。', '名词: signaler 过去式: signaled/signalled 过去分词: signaled/signalled 现在分词: signaling/signalling 第三人称单数: signals/signals');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('inherit', '[ɪn\'herɪt]', 'vt.继承,遗传而得', '1. The eldest son will inherit the title. 长子将继承爵位。 2. She inherited a house from her father. 她从她父亲那儿继承了一所房子。 3. The two children both inherit left-handedness from their parents. 这两个孩子都从父母身上遗传了左撇子。', '名词: inheritor 过去式: inherited 过去分词: inherited 现在分词: inheriting 第三人称单数: inherits');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('outset', '[\'aʊtset]', 'n.开端,开始', '1. At the outset, it looked like a nice day. 开始的时候，天看上去很晴朗。 2. You should explain this to him from the outset. 你应该一开始就向他解释这事。 3. An ardent outset may be followed by declension. 热情的开端可能继之以冷漠。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('expenditure', '[ɪk\'spendɪtʃər]', 'n.支出,花费', '1. We must try our best to control our expenditure. 我们必须尽力控制开销。 2. The government intends to cut expenditure on arms. 政府打算削减军备开支。 3. Such a great task requires the expenditure of much money and time. 这么庞大的任务需要消耗许多的金钱和时间。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('chronic', '[\'krɑːnɪk]', 'adj.慢性的,延续很长的', '1. There is a chronic unemployment problem in America. 在美国存在长期失业问题。 2. We finally won in this chronic war. 我们终于打赢了这场长期战争。 3. My brother has chronic bronchitis. 我的哥哥患有慢性支气管炎。 4. Have you got any chronic diseases in the past? 你过去有没有慢性病?', '副词: chronically 名词: chronicity');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hospitality', '[ˌhɑːspɪ\'tæləti]', 'n.好客,宜人,盛情', '1. I received the hospitality of the family. 我受到这家人亲切的款待。 2. I\'d like to thank you for your hospitality. 非常感谢你们的热情款待。 3. The natives are noted for their hospitality. 当地人以殷勤好客闻名。 4. The islanders are known for their hospitality. 岛上的居民以好客闻名。', '名词复数: hospitalities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('yell', '[jel]', 'vi.大叫,忍不住笑,呼喊;vt.叫着说;n.叫声,喊声', '1. Don\'t yell at me! 别对我大喊大叫！ 2. You don\'t have to yell; I can hear you. 你用不著喊，我听得见。 3. She yelled out at her mischievous child. 她对她淘气的孩子大喊大叫。 4. We yelled our good-byes as the bus left. 汽车离开时我们大喊再见。 5. She let out a yell and ran home. 她尖叫了一声跑回了家。', '名词: yeller 过去式: yelled 过去分词: yelled 现在分词: yelling 第三人称单数: yells');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rhythm', '[\'rɪðəm]', 'n.节奏,韵律', '1. The song has a syncopated rhythm in the jazz version. 这首歌曲改编为爵士乐後采用了切分音节奏。 2. Stress and rhythm are important in speaking English. 说英语时，重音和节奏是很重要的。 3. He is trying to play the same tune in a different rhythm. 他正试图用不同节奏演奏同一个曲子。 4. The rhythm of her heart beating is normal. 她的心跳节律是正常的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('recognize', '[\'rekəɡnaɪz]', 'vt.认可,承认,公认,赏识;vi.具结', '1. His thorough knowledge and competence were recognized. 他的渊博的学识和工作能力得到了承认。 2. I recognize your right to ask that question. 我承认你有权提出这个问题。 3. Can you recognize her from this picture? 你能从这张照片中认出她吗？ 4. He has the good sense to recognize a good man. 他真是慧眼识真才。', '形容词: recognizable 副词: recognizably 名词: recognizer 过去式: recognized 过去分词: recognized 现在分词: recognizing 第三人称单数: recognizes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bulk', '[bʌlk]', 'n.大小,体积,大批,大多数,散装;vt.显得大,显得重要', '1. It\'s not their weight that makes these sacks hard to carry, it\'s their bulk. 这些袋子难以搬运,倒不是因为重而是体积太大。 2. He heaved his huge bulk out of the chair. 他挺起巨大的身躯，从椅子上站了起来。 3. The bulk of the work has already been done. 大部分工作已经完成。 4. The great bulk of necessary work can never be anything but painful. 大量必须做的工作真令人痛苦。 5. We can manage some bulk carrier within two week. 我们可在两周内安排一些散装船去。 6. A dozen petticoats bulked out her figure. 十几条衬裙把她的身体撑得圆鼓鼓的。 7. The cake bulked up. 蛋糕发起来了。', '过去式: bulked 过去分词: bulked 现在分词: bulking 第三人称单数: bulks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('recycle', '[ˌriː\'saɪkl]', 'v.使再循环,反复应用;n.再循环,再生,重复利用', '1. We should try to recycle all our waste paper. 我们应该把所有废纸回收再利用。 2. One thing you can\'t recycle is wasted time. 唯一无法回收利用的是你浪费掉的时间。 3. We should recycle the used things. 我们应回收利用旧东西。 4. We must recycle the cardboard boxes. 我们必须循环使用纸盒子。 5. The ecological system can recycle by itself. 生态系统本身就可以循环。 6. Water recycle is a good way to save our resources. 水循环利用是一种很好的节约资源的方法。', '形容词: recyclable 名词: recycler 过去式: recycled 过去分词: recycled 现在分词: recycling 第三人称单数: recycles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('slope', '[sloʊp]', 'n.斜坡,斜面,倾斜;v.(使)顺斜', '1. There is always a certain slope in a ship\'s deck. 船的甲板总有几分倾斜。 2. We slid down the grassy slope. 我们顺着草坡滑下去。 3. The hospital is on the eastward slope of the hill. 医院在小山的东坡。 4. There is no slope or angle to the croup. 在臀部没有斜面和角度。 5. They slope the grind so that the water can run away. 他们将地面铺得有坡度以便水能流泻。 6. The floor slopes badly here. 地板在这里倾斜得很厉害。', '副词: slopingly 名词: sloper 过去式: sloped 过去分词: sloped 现在分词: sloping 第三人称单数: slopes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('scar', '[skɑːr]', 'n.伤痕,疤痕;v.结疤,使留下伤痕,创伤', '1. He has a scar running across his left cheek. 他左脸上有一道很长的疤痕。 2. The scar flawed her beauty. 这伤疤损害了她的美貌。 3. The cut in her hand has healed completely, without leaving a scar. 她手上的刀伤完全愈合了,没有留下一点伤痕。 4. In that heart, where there had been a wound, there was a scar. 在他的心上，从前有过一条伤口，后来只剩下一条伤痕。 5. The wound gradually scarred over. 伤口渐渐愈合。', '过去式: scarred 过去分词: scarred 现在分词: scarring 第三人称单数: scars');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('conspicuous', '[kən\'spɪkjuəs]', 'adj.显著的', '1. Lincoln is a conspicuous example of a poor boy who succeeded. 林肯是一个穷苦孩子而功成名就的出色例子。 2. He was conspicuous for his bravery. 他因骁勇而出名。 3. A traffic sign should be conspicuous. 交通标志应该明显。 4. Notices shall be put in conspicuous places. 要保证把布告贴在显眼的地方。', '副词: conspicuously 名词: conspicuousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('vivid', '[\'vɪvɪd]', 'adj.生动的,鲜明的,鲜艳的,大胆的,清晰的,活泼的,逼真的', '1. This place conjures up vivid memories. 这个地方使人回忆起许多生动的往事。 2. My daughter is a child with vivid imagination. 我女儿是一个想象力活跃的孩子。 3. This girl gave a vivid description of the event. 那女孩对这件事作了一番生动的描述。 4. Only the vivid red hair ever stood out. 只有鲜艳的红头发非常令人注目。', '副词: vividly 比较级: vivider 最高级: vividest 名词: vividness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('concise', '[kən\'saɪs]', 'adj.简明的,简练的', '1. His article is concise and comprehensive. 他的文章言简意赅。 2. I like the new concise dictionary very much. 我很喜欢这部新的简明词典。 3. I gave a concise answer to this. 我对于此事给了一个简要的答复。 4. He gave a concise and firm summary of our position. 他扼要而坚定地阐述了我方的立场。', '副词: concisely 名词: conciseness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('status', '[\'steɪtəs]', 'n.身份,地位,情形,状况', '1. Women\'s social status has changed much over the years. 这些年来妇女的社会地位有了很大改变。 2. I\'ll keep you posted on the status. 我会随时告诉你进展的情形。 3. We ask the bank to report on his financial status. 我们请银行报告他的财政状况。 4. There are many fine shadings of status through the social hierarchy. 在各个社会等级之间有许多细微的身分区别。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('disrupt', '[dɪs\'rʌpt]', 'v.使中断,使分裂,使瓦解,使陷于混乱,破坏', '1. Protesters tried to disrupt the meeting. 抗议者试图扰乱会议。 2. The communication was disrupted by the storm. 暴风雨使交通中断。 3. The bad weather has seriously disrupted supplies of food. 恶劣的天气严重地妨碍了食品的供应。 4. The war seemed likely to disrupt the state. 战争可能使这个国家分裂。', '名词: disrupter 过去式: disrupted 过去分词: disrupted 现在分词: disrupting 第三人称单数: disrupts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('watt', '[wɑːt]', 'n.瓦特(1736-1819,英国工程师,发明家)', '1. The lamp needs a 100-watt bulb. 那盏灯需要100瓦的灯泡。 2. By last year the price had fallen to about $2.70 per watt. 到去年为止，这个价格已经下跌到了2.', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fort', '[fɔːrt]', 'n.堡垒,边界上的贸易站', '1. The men in the fort sallied at dawn. 堡垒里的人在黎明时出击。 2. They built an adobe fort, which is now a museum. 他们建造的泥砖堡垒，现已成为博物馆。 3. The enemy soon occupied the fort. 敌人很快占领这座要塞。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('patron', '[\'peɪtrən]', 'n.(对某人,某种目标,艺术等)赞助人,资助人', '1. Modern artists have difficulty in finding patrons. 现代艺术家们很难找到赞助人。 2. He inscribed those poems to his patron. 他将这些诗献给他的赞助人。 3. This store has many patrons. 这家商店有许多老顾客。 4. The usher handed the patron to a reserved seat. 引座员把顾客引到预订的座位上', '形容词: patronal');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('accurate', '[\'ækjərət]', 'adj.正确的,精确的', '1. Hearsay definitely can\'t be regarded as accurate information. 道听途说的决然不能算作很准确的消息。 2. The manager impressed on his office staff the importance of keeping accurate records. 经理让办公室职员认识到做精确记录的重要性。', '副词: accurately 名词: accurateness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('submit', '[səb\'mɪt]', 'v.(使)服从,(使)顺从;vt.提交,递交', '1. We will submit ourselves to the court\'s judgement. 我们服从法庭的判决。 2. We have to submit ourselves to discipline. 我们必须遵守纪律。 3. He submitted his proposal for urban development to the city council. 他将城市发展建议提交市议会。 4. Please fill in and submit the form below. 请填写并递交以下表格。 5. They refused to submit to the unjust decision. 他们拒绝服从这个不公正的决定。', '名词: submittal 过去式: submitted 过去分词: submitted 现在分词: submitting 第三人称单数: submits');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('thanksgiving', '[ˌθæŋks\'ɡɪvɪŋ]', 'n.感谢,[宗]感恩祈祷', '1. We always have turkey for our Thanksgiving meal. 我们在感恩节总是吃火鸡。 2. Thanksgiving is a movable holiday. 感恩节的日期每年不同。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('invaluable', '[ɪn\'væljuəbl]', 'adj.无价的,价值无法衡量的', '1. But the experience they will gain is invaluable. 但他们从此获得的经验是无价的。 2. His experience proved an invaluable help. 他的经验被证明是无价之宝。 3. The painting is an invaluable treasure. 这幅画是无价之宝。 4. This set of ancient china is invaluable. 这套古瓷器非常珍贵。', '副词: invaluably 名词: invaluableness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('involve', '[ɪn\'vɑːlv]', 'vt.包括,笼罩,潜心于,使陷于', '1. A letter of credit will involve unnecessary extra charges. 信用证包含有不必要的额外开支。 2. The Genius is a lovable physicist who is deeply involved in defining the workings of the universe. 老天才是一位可爱的学者，他整天忙于解释天地间的各种现象。. 3. Don\'t involve other people in your trouble. 别把别人牵涉进你的麻烦中去。 4. I got involved in a quarrel about the price. 我被卷入了一场有关价格的争吵。', '名词: involvement 过去式: involved 过去分词: involved 现在分词: involving 第三人称单数: involves');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('resultant', '[rɪ\'zʌltənt]', 'adj.作为结果而发生的,合成的', '1. The resultant human form now ran on electromagnetic energy. 合成的人类形体现在运作着电磁能量。 2. All elements are radiating in phase, and the resultant wave front is perpendicular to the axis of the element array. 所有单元发射相位一致，合成的波前垂直于单元阵列轴线。 3. This snap-in allows you to browse Resultant Set of Policy data. 此管理单元允许您浏览策略数据的结果集。 4. He is arrested for drunkenness and the resultant publicity ruined his career. 他因酗酒被捕，结果这一坏名声毁了他的前程。', '副词: resultantly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hinge', '[hɪndʒ]', 'n.（门、盖等的）铰链,枢纽,关键;vt.装铰链;v.装以绞链,依...而转移', '1. The two bones are articulated like a hinge. 这两块骨头由关节铰链般连接起来。 2. Rust is eating away the iron hinge. 铁锈正腐蚀着铁铰链。 3. This was the hinge of fate of the whole campaign. 这是决定整场战役命运的关键点。 4. Your arm should hinge from the shoulder. 你的手臂应该像从肩膀铰链住一般。 5. His acceptance will hinge upon the term. 他接受与否将依条件而定。', '过去式: hinged 过去分词: hinged 现在分词: hinging 第三人称单数: hinges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tract', '[trækt]', 'n.广阔的地面,土地,地方,地域,(解剖)管道,小册子', '1. He owns a large tract of forest. 他拥有一大片森林。 2. He took many photos of the wide tracts of desert in North Africa. 他拍了许多关于北非的广大沙漠的照片。 3. Osteoporosis is a late complication of digestive tract disease. 骨质疏松症是消化道疾病的晚期并发症之一。 4. He had an infection in the upper respiratory tract. 他上呼吸道感染。 5. He wrote all the campaign tracts. 这些竞选传单全是他写的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('collision', '[kə\'lɪʒn]', 'n.碰撞,冲突', '1. The car was completely wrecked by the force of the collision. 这辆汽车受到很大的撞击力而完全损坏。 2. The liner is reported to have been in collision with an oil tanker. 据报道，这艘客轮与一艘油轮相撞。 3. The Government and the unions are on a collision course. 政府和工会必将发生冲突。 4. This collision had a very unusual cause. 这次冲突有着非同寻常的原因。', '形容词: collisional');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mobilize', '[\'moʊbəlaɪz]', 'v.动员', '1. They are mobilizing their supporters to vote at the election. 他们正在组织其支持者向他们拉选票。 2. Our country\'s in great danger; we must mobilize the army. 我们正处于严重危险之中，我们必须把军人动员起来。 3. The President had constitutional power to mobilize troops in an emergency. 依据宪法，总统有权在紧急情况下调动军队。 4. The troops received orders to mobilize. 部队接到动员令。', '名词: mobilization 过去式: mobilized 过去分词: mobilized 现在分词: mobilizing 第三人称单数: mobilizes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('essential', '[ɪ\'senʃl]', 'adj.本质的,实质的,基本的,提炼的,精华的;n.本质,实质,要素,要点', '1. This is of course still the essential method. 这当然仍是本质的方法。 2. This is desirable but by no means essential to the primary objective of validating mathematical models of aircraft behaviour. 对于验证飞机性能的数学模型这一主要目的来说，这是必须的，但决不是最本质的. 3. Concentration is essential if you want to do a good job. 如果你想把事情做好,专心是必要的。 4. Mass education is essential in promoting democracy. 民众教育对提倡民主是非常重要的。 5. What are the essentials of good teaching? 成功教学的要素是什么?', '副词: essentially 名词: essentiality');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('extreme', '[ɪk\'striːm]', 'adj.尽头的,极端的,极度的,偏激的,最后的;n.极端,极端的事物', '1. Extreme cold can wake a hibernating animal. 极度的寒冷能使正在冬眠的动物苏醒。 2. The extreme heat sapped his strength and health. 极度的暑热逐渐损耗他的体力兴健康。 3. Extreme poverty had reduced them to a state of apathy. 极端的贫困使他们万念俱灰。 4. The capital is in the extreme south of the country. 首都在这个国家的最南端。 5. Love and hate are extremes. 爱和恨是两个极端。', '副词: extremely 名词: extremeness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('batch', '[bætʃ]', 'n.(面包等)一炉,一批', '1. The second batch of sugar is better than the first. 第二批制成的糖比第一批好。 2. There are a batch of tourists over there. 那里有一批旅游者。 3. The first batch of police-women went on duty in Jinan in 1959. 济南第-批女警察是1959年开始值勤。 4. These cakes were baked in batches of twenty. 这些蛋糕是以二十个为一炉烘烤的。', '过去式: batched 过去分词: batched 现在分词: batching 第三人称单数: batches');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('conventional', '[kən\'venʃənl]', 'adj.惯例的,常规的,习俗的,传统的', '1. Her book is a hilarious send-up of a conventional spy story. 她写的书用的是取笑传统侦探小说的笔法，令人捧腹。 2. According to conventional wisdom, voters usually make their choice on the basis of domestic issues. 按一般人在这些问题上的看法，选民常常着眼于国内问题来选择候选人。 3. After a conventional opening remarks, he made a brilliant speech. 在一个常规的开场白后,他做了个很精彩的演讲。 4. I can never get a girl like that with conventional methods. 我用寻常套路可永远也得不到这样的女孩。', '副词: conventionally 名词: conventionalism');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('catastrophe', '[kə\'tæstrəfi]', 'n.大灾难,大祸', '1. The earthquake was a terrible catastrophe. 这次地震是个可怕的灾难。 2. He is teetering on the edge of catastrophe. 他在大灾难的边缘徘徊。 3. The catastrophe would be stamped in their minds. 那场灾难将会深深地印在他们的头脑里。 4. Their other problems paled into insignificance beside this latest catastrophe. 最近发生这一灾祸后,他们其他的问题都显得无关重要了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('militant', '[\'mɪlɪtənt]', 'adj.好战的,积极从事或支持使用武力的', '1. We have militant bonds of friendship. 我们有战斗情谊。 2. We have never been so inspired and militant. 我们从来没有像现在这样意气风发,斗志昂扬。 3. The speaker is shouted down by militant union members. 演讲者被富有战斗精神的工会会员声音所压倒。 4. The militant group has suspected links to al-Qaeda. 该组织被怀疑与基地组织有关联。 5. Our Militant Life is Like a Poem. 我们的战斗生活像诗篇。', '副词: militantly 名词: militance');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('distract', '[dɪ\'strækt]', 'v.转移', '1. The film managed to distract me from these problems for a while. 这部影片分散了我的注意力，让我暂时忘记了这些难题。 2. It was all a ploy to distract attention from his real aims. 那纯粹是障眼法，用以分散人们对他真正意图的注意力。 3. We must change our route to distract the attention of the enemy. 我们必须改变行军路线以转移敌人的注意力。 4. Once she gets involved in a research, nothing can distract her mind from it. 她一旦潜心钻研某一课题,任何事情都无法使她分心。', '形容词: distractive 副词: distractingly 过去式: distracted 过去分词: distracted 现在分词: distracting 第三人称单数: distracts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('coherent', '[koʊ\'hɪrənt]', 'adj.粘在一起的,一致的,连贯的', '1. He welded their stories into a single coherent account. 他把他们的故事连在一起写成一个连贯的报导。 2. The subjects of the curriculum form a coherent whole. 课程中的科目构成了一个连贯的整体。 3. She only became coherent again two hours after the attack. 她发病两小时之后才恢复了清楚地说话的能力。 4. She had felt there was something wrong, but couldn\'t give coherent reasons. 她感到有些不对头，但是讲不清楚理由。', '副词: coherently');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('auction', '[\'ɔːkʃn]', 'n.拍卖;vt.拍卖', '1. We will put the car up for auction. 我们将把这辆小车拍卖。 2. The picture should fetch 2000 pounds at auction. 这张画拍卖可得2000英镑。 3. We had a private view of the jewels before the public auction. 那些珠宝公开拍卖以前我们私下看了预展。 4. They will auction off a collection of oils. 他们将拍卖一批收藏的油画。', '过去式: auctioned 过去分词: auctioned 现在分词: auctioning 第三人称单数: auctions');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sociology', '[ˌsoʊsi\'ɑːlədʒi]', 'n.社会学', '1. Economics and sociology are social sciences. 经济学和社会学都属于社会科学。 2. A few years ago, sociology is the most popular subject for undergraduate. 几年之前，社会学是大学本科生最欢迎的课程。', '形容词: sociologic 副词: sociologically 名词: sociologist');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('abundance', '[ə\'bʌndəns]', 'n.丰富,充裕,丰富充裕', '1. At the party there is food and drink in abundance. 宴会中有丰富的食物和饮料。 2. This country has an abundance of natural resources. 这个国家拥有丰富的天然资源。 3. There was an abundance of corn last year. 去年玉米丰收。 4. Carpets are available in abundance. 可供地毯货源充足。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('install', '[ɪn\'stɔːl]', 'vt.安装,安置,使就职', '1. She installed her air-conditioner without help by herself. 她自己安装了空调。 2. The workers are installing a heating system. 工人们正在安装供暖系统。 3. It is necessary that you install a burglar alarm. 你有必要装防盗警报器。 4. The children are comfortably installed in a new home. 孩子们在新居舒适地安顿下来。', '名词: installer');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mature', '[mə\'tʃʊr]', 'adj.成熟的,到期的,充分考虑的,(票据等)到期的;vt.使成熟;vi.成熟,到期', '1. This is the most mature of his plays. 这是他最成熟的一部剧作。 2. She swept her hair back, so she looks more mature than before. 她把头发往后梳，所以显得比以前成熟。 3. Your fixed account is mature and can be withdrawn any time. 您的定期存款已经到期了，随时可以提取。 4. Young as she is, she cares for others and has a mature mind. 她虽然年轻,但却很为他人着想,考虑周到。 5. Girls mature earlier than boys. 女孩比男孩成熟得早些。', '副词: maturely 比较级: maturer 最高级: maturest 名词: matureness 过去式: matured 过去分词: matured 现在分词: maturing 第三人称单数: matures');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('gigantic', '[dʒaɪ\'ɡæntɪk]', 'adj.巨人般的,巨大的', '1. The new airplane looked like a gigantic bird. 这架新飞机看起来像一只巨大的鸟。 2. City is abstracted into several gigantic buildings. 城市，被抽象化为几个巨大的建筑物。', '副词: gigantically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('album', '[\'ælbəm]', 'n.集邮本,照相簿,签名纪念册', '1. This is one of the songs from her latest album. 这是她最新歌集里的一首歌。 2. The album contains many memorable songs. 这张唱片中包括许多值得收集的歌曲。 3. My album of boyhood photographs often reminds me of the past happiness. 童年时的相册经常让我想起儿时的欢乐。　 4. I see her put stamps in an album. 我看见她在把邮票放进集邮本去。', '名词复数: albums');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('suppress', '[sə\'pres]', 'vt.镇压,抑制,查禁,使止住', '1. The revolt was suppressed in a matter of hours. 叛乱在几小时之内就镇压下去了。 2. All these movements were suppressed by the warlord government. 所有这些运动都受到军阀政府的镇压。 3. A common person would not suppress his real name. 一个平常人是不会隐瞒他的真实姓名的。 4. He couldn\'t suppress his anger. 他简直怒不可遏。', '形容词: suppressible 名词: suppressant 过去式: suppressed 过去分词: suppressed 现在分词: suppressing 第三人称单数: suppresses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('intelligent', '[ɪn\'telɪdʒənt]', 'adj.聪明的,伶俐的,有才智的,[计]智能的', '1. Though very intelligent, she is nevertheless rather modest. 她很聪明，倒也很谦虚。 2. The student gave an intelligent answer. 这个学生给出了一个聪明的回答。 3. Maybe the earth has been visited by intelligent creatures from outer space. 也许太空的智慧生物已经访问过地球。', '形容词: intelligential 副词: intelligently');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('counsel', '[\'kaʊnsl]', 'n.讨论,商议,辩护律师;vt.劝告,忠告', '1. Good counsel has no price. [谚]忠言无价。 2. Listen to the counsel of your elders. 听从长辈的劝告吧. 3. Each side of a case in court has its own counsel. 法庭上原告和被告双方都有各自的律师。 4. The court heard counsel for both sides. 法庭听取了双方律师的陈述. 5. Most experts counsel caution in such cases. 大多数专家建议在这样的情况下要谨慎从事。', '过去式: counseled/counselled 过去分词: counseled/counselled 现在分词: counseling/counselling 第三人称单数: counsels/counsels');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('wealthy', '[\'welθi]', 'adj.富有的,丰裕的,充分的;n.富人,有钱人', '1. She\'s an attractive woman, and wealthy to boot. 她是个很有魅力的女人，而且很富有。 2. A wealthy sponsor came to our rescue with a generous donation. 有个富有的赞助人慷慨捐赠来解救我们。 3. He was the son of a wealthy planter. 他是一个富有的种植园主的儿子。 4. She married her daughter to a wealthy man. 她把她女儿嫁给了一个富人。', '副词: wealthily 比较级: wealthier 最高级: wealthiest 名词: wealthiness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cite', '[saɪt]', 'vt.引用,引证,提名表扬', '1. The lawyer cited a previous case to support his argument. 律师引用了以前的案例来支持他的论点。 2. It\'s no use citing the Bible to somebody who doesn\'t believe in God. 对不信上帝的人引用圣经的话是没用的。 3. I\'ll just cite some figures for comparison. 我要引用一些数字作比较。 4. He was cited for contempt of court. 他因蔑视法庭而被传讯。', '形容词: citable 过去式: cited 过去分词: cited 现在分词: citing 第三人称单数: cites');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('transmit', '[træns\'mɪt]', 'vt.传输,转送,传达,传导,发射,遗传,传播;vi.发射信号,发报', '1. Gypsies frequently transmit recipes orally within the family. 吉普赛人经常以口头形式把秘方世代相传。 2. Please transmit my best regards to your lovely wife. 请转达我向您娇妻的致意。 3. This infection is transmitted by mosquitoes. 这种传染病是由蚊子传染的。 4. The tension soon transmitted itself to all the members of the crowd. 这种紧张情绪很快感染了人群中所有的人。', '形容词: transmittable 过去式: transmitted 过去分词: transmitted 现在分词: transmitting 第三人称单数: transmits');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('massacre', '[\'mæsəkər]', 'n.残杀,大屠杀;v.残杀,集体屠杀', '1. The massacre was a crime against humanity. 这场大屠杀是一桩反人类的罪行。 2. The press has reported the massacre of thousands of people for their religious beliefs. 新闻界报道了那场因宗教信仰原因而对千万人的大屠杀。 3. The game was a complete massacre; we lost 10-0. 那次比赛真是一次惨败，我们0比10输了。 4. Vichy government was the accessory of Nazi to massacre the Jews who lived in France. 维希政府是德国纳粹残害住在法国的犹太人的帮凶之一。', '名词: massacrer 过去式: massacred 过去分词: massacred 现在分词: massacring 第三人称单数: massacres');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('approach', '[ə\'proʊtʃ]', 'n.接近,逼近,走进,方法,步骤,途径,通路;vt.接近,动手处理;vi.靠近', '1. He still had not the courage to approach her. 他仍没有勇气靠近她。 2. Such people as are friendly are easy to approach. 亲切之人容易接近。 3. She approached the bank for a loan. 她向银行要求贷款。 4. There is no one who even approaches his talents. 目前还没有谁的能力能与他媲美。 5. Narration should become a basic approach to preschool education. 叙事应是幼儿教育的基本途径。', '过去式: approached 过去分词: approached 现在分词: approaching 第三人称单数: approaches');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('package', '[\'pækɪdʒ]', 'n.包裹,包', '1. The postman brought me a large package. 邮递员给我送来一个大包裹。 2. He received a compact package. 他收到一个扎得很紧的包裹。 3. The ministers are trying to put together a package that will end the dispute. 大臣们力图搞个一揽子交易结束这场争论。 4. Before you can deploy your solution, you must package it into a CAB file. 在部署解决方案之前,你必须将其打包到CAB文件中。', '名词: packager 过去式: packaged 过去分词: packaged 现在分词: packaging 第三人称单数: packages');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('proficiency', '[prə\'fɪʃnsi]', 'n.熟练,精通,熟练程度', '1. He made little proficiency in literary accomplishments. 他在文学方面成就不多。 2. How do you think of your proficiency in written and spoken English? 你认为你的书面英语和口语熟练程度如何? 3. You need some proficiency in book - keeping for this job. 干这项工作你需要在记帐方面熟练。 4. He acquired some proficiency in English. 他精通英语。', '名词复数: proficiencies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mild', '[maɪld]', 'adj.温和的,温柔的,淡味的,轻微的,适度的,不含有害物质的的', '1. He has a mild nature. 他的性格温和。 2. He gave a mild answer, in spite of his anger. 尽管他十分恼火,他还是态度温和地回答了。 3. The coastal area has very mild winter, but by contrast the central plains become extremely cold. 靠近海岸的地区有很温和的冬天,相比而方,靠近中央的平原就变得非常寒冷。 4. The patient has a mild fever. 那个病人有些轻微的发烧。', '副词: mildly 比较级: milder 最高级: mildest 名词: mildness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('accuse', '[ə\'kjuːz]', 'vt.控告,谴责,非难', '1. How dare you accuse me of lying! 你怎敢谴责我说谎! 2. We resolve not to accuse them to avoid troubles. 我们决定不起诉他们 3. I mustered up enough courage to accuse him. 我鼓起足够的勇气控告他。 4. He was accused of incompetence. 他被指责为不称职。', '副词: accusingly 名词: accuser 过去式: accused 过去分词: accused 现在分词: accusing 第三人称单数: accuses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ensue', '[ɪn\'suː]', 'vi.跟着发生,继起;vt.(基督教《圣经》用语)追求', '1. Observers waited for mayhem to ensue. 观察者等候伤害罪之一种跟着发生。', '过去式: ensued 过去分词: ensued 现在分词: ensuing 第三人称单数: ensues');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ornament', '[\'ɔːrnəmənt]', 'n.装饰物,教堂用品;vt.装饰,修饰', '1. The palace was rich in ornament. 宫廷装饰琳琅满目。 2. The clock is simply for ornament, it doesn\'t actually work. 那时钟纯粹是为了装饰,其实不能走。 3. There is an ornament made of shells on the wall. 墙上有一个贝壳做成的装饰品。 4. We bought some ornaments for the Christmas tree. 我们买了一些装饰品来点缀圣诞树。 5. I ornamented my room with flowers. 我用鲜花装饰房间。', '名词: ornamenter 过去式: ornamented 过去分词: ornamented 现在分词: ornamenting 第三人称单数: ornaments');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tempt', '[tempt]', 'vt.诱惑,引诱,吸引,使感兴趣,考验,试探', '1. The warm weather tempted us into going for a swim. 暖和的天气诱使我们去游泳。 2. I ought not to have let you tempt me into asking you a rude question. 我本来就不应该让你怂恿我跟你提出一个无礼的问题。 3. Those advertisements try to tempt people into buying their products. 那些广告试图怂恿大家去购买其产品。 4. He was tempted into making a false step. 他被引诱做了一件傻事。', '形容词: temptable 名词: tempter 过去式: tempted 过去分词: tempted 现在分词: tempting 第三人称单数: tempts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('overwhelm', '[ˌoʊvər\'welm]', 'vt.淹没,覆没,受打击,制服,压倒', '1. No difficulty can overwhelm us. 困难压不倒我们。 2. If I cannot overwhelm with my quality, I will overwhelm with my quantity. 如果我不能以质量压倒，我就一定要以数量压倒。 3. Your kindness quite overwhelmed me. 你的好意使我感激难言。 4. The village was overwhelmed when the floods came. 这个村庄在洪水泛滥时被淹没了。', '过去式: overwhelmed 过去分词: overwhelmed 现在分词: overwhelming 第三人称单数: overwhelms');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('settlement', '[\'setlmənt]', 'n.沉降,解决,结算,殖民,殖民地', '1. There is no prospect of a settlement of the dispute. 这场纠纷根本不可能获得解决。 2. Negotiators are looking for a peaceful settlement to the dispute. 谈判双方正寻求和平解决争端的办法。 3. After much discussion the negotiators hammered out a compromise settlement. 双方经多次谈判达成一项折衷的解决办法。 4. I enclose a cheque in settlement of your account. 兹附支票一张以结清贵处帐目。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('concede', '[kən\'siːd]', 'vt.勉强,承认,退让;vi.让步', '1. I concede that you are right. 我承认你是对的。 2. You must concede that I have tried my best. 你必须承认我已经尽力了。 3. The defeated side had to concede some of their territory to the enemy. 战败的一方不得不把一部分领土割让给了敌人。 4. You concede nothing to me and I have to concede everything to you. 你对我无论什么都不肯让步；我对你，可无论什么都得让步。 5. Mike had to concede when he confronted his parents 当面对他的父母,麦克不得不让步。', '副词: concededly 名词: conceder 过去式: conceded 过去分词: conceded 现在分词: conceding 第三人称单数: concedes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('draft', '[dræft]', 'n.草稿,草案,草图;vt.起草,为...打样,设计;v.草拟', '1. He drew a draft of the car. 他画了一张汽车的草图。 2. He has drawn up the design draft. 他拟订了设计草图。 3. He drew a draft on a pad then began his formal work. 他在便笺簿上画了草图，然后就开始正式工作了。 4. I propose issuing a time draft for US $ 100,000. 我建议开具价值10万美元的远期汇票。 5. Who will draft the indictment? 谁将起草起诉状？ 6. The Authority may suggest any other proposal it thinks fit for inclusion into the draft corporate plan. 市建局可提议其认为适合包括在事务计划草案内的任何其他提案。', '过去式: drafted 过去分词: drafted 现在分词: drafting 第三人称单数: drafts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mortgage', '[\'mɔːrɡɪdʒ]', 'n.抵押;v.抵押', '1. Mortgage Insurance vs Term Life Insurance. 按揭人寿保险。 2. Mortgage is a security interest in real property. 按揭是不动产的一种物权担保。 3. The bank foreclosed a mortgage on the property. 银行取消了抵押人的财产赎回权。 4. We\'re having difficulty keeping up our mortgage payments. 我们难以继续支付分期偿还的抵押贷款。 5. He will have to mortgage his land for a loan. 他不得不将土地抵押来申请贷款。', '过去式: mortgaged 过去分词: mortgaged 现在分词: mortgaging 第三人称单数: mortgages');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('suspension', '[sə\'spenʃn]', 'n.吊,悬浮,悬浮液,暂停,中止,悬而未决,延迟', '1. I think her suspension from the team was a very harsh punishment. 我认为她被暂停参加队的比赛是很严厉的处罚。 2. The conspicuous suspicious pension is in suspension. 那笔引人注目的可疑养老金被暂停发放。 3. She appealed against her suspension. 她对被停职一事已经上诉。 4. The headmaster has made a decision of suspension of a pupil from school. 校长已经做出对一名学生停学处分的决定。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('overturn', '[ˌoʊvər\'tɜːrn]', 'n.倾覆,破灭,革命;vt.推翻,颠倒;vi.翻倒;n.翻转,毁灭', '1. The boat overturned but didn\'t sank. 小船翻了，但没有沉。 2. The revolutionist planned to overturn this puppet regime. 革命者计划推翻傀儡政府。 3. Some high-ranking officers plotted to overturn the government. 有几名高级军官策划推翻政府。 4. The 21st century will overturn many of our basic assumptions about economic life. 21世纪将会颠覆很多我们关于经济生活的基础假设。 5. This is one of the important reasons for overturn of ro-ro ships. 这是许多滚装船发生倾覆的重要原因之一。', '过去式: overturned 过去分词: overturned 现在分词: overturning 第三人称单数: overturns');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('penalty', '[\'penəlti]', 'n.处罚,罚款', '1. A penalty clause was written into the contract. 在合同中写入了一项罚款条款。 2. She has paid the penalty for her crimes with five years in prison. 她因犯罪受到惩罚被判刑五年。 3. One of the penalties of fame is that people point at you on the street. 当了名人的麻烦之一是在街上被人指指点点。 4. One of the penalties of fame is loss of privacy. 成名的弊端之一是失去了私人活动自由。', '名词复数: penalties');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('conservation', '[ˌkɑːnsər\'veɪʃn]', 'n.保存,保持,守恒', '1. If I may refer back to the problem we discussed, I think we shall stress on the conservation of our natural resource. 请允许我重提我们刚才讨论过的问题，我想我们应该强调保存我们的自然资源。 2. Conservation methods will also help meet their energy needs. 能量保存方法也会有利于满足其能源需求。 3. Most people have come to accept the need for conservation of natural resources. 现在大多数人已认识到保护自然资源的必要。 4. Our community is a leader in the conservation of wildlife. 我们社区在野生动物保护方面走在前头。', '形容词: conservational');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('integrity', '[ɪn\'teɡrəti]', 'n.正直,诚实,完整,完全,完整性', '1. We must respect each other\'s territorial integrity. 我们应当尊重彼此的领土完整。 2. We all have an interest in maintaining the integrity of the ecosystem. 维持生态系统的完整是我们共同的利益。 3. One of the most important features of the steel cables is their structural integrity. 钢索最重要的特点之一，是结构的完善性。 4. My husband is a man of the highest integrity. 我丈夫是个非常正直的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('intrinsic', '[ɪn\'trɪnsɪk]', 'adj.(指价值、性质)固有的,内在的,本质的', '1. You have a natural and intrinsic talent and skill. 你天生就具备内在的天赋和才能。 2. These difficulties are intrinsic to such a situation 这是这种情势下固然会有的困难。 3. The intrinsic worth of the pen is 30 yuan. 这支钢笔本身价值是30元。', '副词: intrinsically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('lens', '[lenz]', 'n.透镜,镜头', '1. Don\'t smear the lens; I\'ve just polished it. 别把镜头弄脏了，我刚刚擦过。 2. Some adjustment of the lens may be necessary. 可能有必要调节一下镜头。 3. The camera lens must be screened from direct sunlight. 照相机的镜头不可受到阳光的直射。 4. He uses lens to make things appear clearer. 他用镜片以便看东西更清楚些。', '形容词: lensed 名词复数: lenses 过去式: lensed 过去分词: lensed 现在分词: lensing 第三人称单数: lenses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('molecule', '[\'mɑːlɪkjuːl]', 'n.[化]分子,些微', '1. A molecule is made up of atoms. 分子由原子组成。 2. Two atoms of hydrogen combine with one atom of oxygen to form a molecule of water. 两个氢原子和一个氧原子结合而成一个水分子。 3. We can see many molecules flying in the air when a sunbeam penetrated the dark room. 当一束光线穿进暗淡的房间时，我们可以看到空气中有许多小颗粒在飞舞。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('practicable', '[\'præktɪkəbl]', 'adj.能实行的,行得通的,可以实行的', '1. That suggestion sounds practicable. 那条建议听起来可行。 2. He put forward wise and practicable proposals. 他提出了明智的和可行的建议。 3. What we need is practicable tools. 我们需要的是适用的工具。 4. In this case, the method may not be practicable. 在这个案例中，这种方法就不适用。', '副词: practicably 名词: practicability');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ecology', '[i\'kɑːlədʒi]', 'n.生态学,[社会]环境适应学,均衡系统', '1. Ecology helps us understand complex problems. 生态学帮助我们把握复杂问题。 2. He started to study ecology and decided to devote his whole life to the science. 他开始研究生态学,并决心将他的一生献身于这门学科。 3. Fossils allow us to reconstruct ancient ecology. 化石可以让我们知道古时的生态环境。 4. Concern about ecology is a recent development. 对生态的关心是最近才有的事。', '形容词: ecological 副词: ecologically 名词: ecologist 名词复数: ecologies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('appearance', '[ə\'pɪrəns]', 'n.出现,露面,外貌,外观', '1. The journal makes its appearance once two months. 这本刊物两个月出版一次。 2. The appearance of Internet marked the beginning of the age of information. 因特网的出现标志着信息时代的开始。 3. I don\'t want to go to the party but I\'d better put in an appearance, I suppose. 我不想参加那个聚会，可是我最好还是要露一下面。 4. We should not judge a person by his appearance. 我们不应该以貌取人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('supersonic', '[ˌsuːpər\'sɑːnɪk]', 'adj.超音波的;n.超声波,超声频', '1. What is classics esophagus supersonic and enchanted graph examination? 什么是经食管超声心动图检查? 2. Have you taken supersonic aircraft? 你坐过超音速飞机吗? 3. These planes travel at supersonic speeds. 这些飞机以超音速的速度飞行。', '副词: supersonically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('absorb', '[əb\'sɔːrb]', 'vt.吸收,吸引', '1. Dry sand absorbs water. 干沙吸收水份。 2. Did you absorb everything the professor said? 教授说的你全部理解了吗? 3. His business absorbs him. 他的业务使他全神贯注。 4. Large nations shouldn\'t absorb smaller ones. 大国不应当吞并小国。', '形容词: absorbable 副词: absorbingly 名词: absorbability 过去式: absorbed 过去分词: absorbed 现在分词: absorbing 第三人称单数: absorbs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fulfill', '[fʊl\'fɪl]', 'vt.履行,实现,完成(计划等)', '1. Whatever happens I\'m determined to fulfill it. 不管发生什么,我都决心完成它。 2. How they laid about them to fulfill the task! 他们是何等竭尽全力来完成这一任务啊！ 3. You must fulfill your promise. 你必须履行诺言。 4. The doctor\'s instructions must be fulfilled exactly. 必须一丝不苟地遵照医嘱去办。', '名词: fulfiller');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('radical', '[\'rædɪkl]', 'adj.根本的,基本的,激进的;n.激进分子', '1. I know you are radical in your thinking, but don\'t go too far. 我知道你思想激进,但不要走的太远。 2. He took up a radical position on this issue. 他对这个问题抱着激进的态度。 3. They called for a radical reform of our tax system. 他们要求对税收制度进行根本改革。 4. Lambert did not reach the more radical conclusion. 兰伯特还没有达到更本质的结论。 5. Ted is a fire-eating radical. 泰德是个咄咄逼人的激进份子。', '副词: radically 名词: radicalness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fundamental', '[ˌfʌndə\'mentl]', 'adj.基础的,基本的;n.基本原则,基本原理', '1. For something fundamental has changed in Venezuela. 因为在委内瑞拉，有一些基本的东西已经改变了。 2. Trial by the jury is a fundamental right. 有陪审团陪同审判是一项基本的权利。 3. From the outset, it had two fundamental flaws. 从一开始，这一合作就有两个根本的缺陷。 4. The fundamental ones are embodied in the Party Constitution. 党章是最根本的党规党法。 5. Primary is about fundamental play. 原始与基础游戏有关。', '副词: fundamentally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('authentic', '[ɔː\'θentɪk]', 'adj.可信的', '1. This is an authentic medieval sword. 这是一把真正的中世纪剑。 2. He found out the most authentic restaurants. 他找到了最正宗的餐馆。 3. The details of the costume were totally authentic. 这件古装的每个小地方都完全真实。 4. He\'s got an authentic letter by Shakespeare. 他弄到了一封莎士比亚的亲笔信。', '副词: authentically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('corpse', '[kɔːrps]', 'n.尸体', '1. The corpse was laid out by the undertaker. 承办殡葬者准备埋葬尸体。 2. The corpse lies face down in a pool of blood. 尸体俯卧在血泊中。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('compete', '[kəm\'piːt]', 'vi.比赛,竞争', '1. Companies must be able to compete in the marketplace. 公司一定要在市场中有竞争力。 2. Several companies are competing for the contract. 几家公司正为争取一项合同而互相竞争。 3. We can compete with the best teams. 我们能与最好的队竞争。 4. He\'s hoping to compete in the London marathon. 他期盼着参加伦敦马拉松比赛。', '过去式: competed 过去分词: competed 现在分词: competing 第三人称单数: competes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('derive', '[dɪ\'raɪv]', 'vt.得自;vi.起源', '1. We shall derive much benefit from reading good novels. 我们将从优秀小说中获得很大好处。 2. We derive our sustenance from the land. 我们从土地获取食物。 3. One kind of vacation is camping, from which many Americans derive pleasure and benefit. 露营是一种度假方式，许多美国人从中得到乐趣，受益匪浅。 4. If we start some a year earlier, we shall derive the benefits a year earlier. 我们如果早开始一年,我们可以早得利一年', '形容词: derivable 名词: deriver 过去式: derived 过去分词: derived 现在分词: deriving 第三人称单数: derives');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('conscientious', '[ˌkɒnʃɪ\'enʃəs]', 'adj.尽责的', '1. The janitor is very conscientious. 那个管理员很认真。 2. He\'s changed into a conscientious worker. 他已成为一个工作认真的人了。 3. Be more conscientious about your work. 要更谨慎做你的工作。 4. This essay is a most conscientious piece of work. 这篇论文是精雕细刻的工作.', '副词: conscientiously 名词: conscientiousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('client', '[\'klaɪənt]', 'n.[计]顾客,客户,委托人', '1. If a lawyer has plenty of clients, he grows rich. 律师如果有大量的诉讼委托人，就会财源不断。 2. The lawyer explained the legal technicalities to his client. 律师给委托人解释法律上的要点。 3. Counsel for the defence submitted that his client was clearly innocent. 被告的律师辩称其委托人显然是无辜的。 4. Now you can build the response to the client. 现在,您可以构建对客户端的响应。', '形容词: cliental 名词: clientage');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('suffice', '[sə\'faɪs]', 'vi.足够,有能力;vt.使满足', '1. The rations will suffice until next week. 这些口粮足够吃到下星期。 2. An hour should suffice for the journey. 这点路程一小时足够了。 3. The rules will suffice for all ordinary needs. 这些规定将能满足所有一般场合的需要。 4. Two meals a day suffice an old man. 老人一天二餐就足够了。', '名词: sufficer 过去式: sufficed 过去分词: sufficed 现在分词: sufficing 第三人称单数: suffices');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('impact', '[\'ɪmpækt]', 'n.碰撞,冲击,冲突,影响,效果;vt.挤入,撞击,压紧,对...发生影响', '1. Seasonality or economic cycles will have minimal impact on secular trends. 季节性或经济周期两者对长期趋势的影响都不大。 2. But what these people fail to see is that international tourism may bring about a disastrous impact on our environment and local history. 但是这些人忽视了国际旅游可能会给当地环境和历史造成的灾难性的影响。 3. The impact of the crash hurtled the driver against the windshield of the car. 碰撞的震力使驾驶员猛撞于车子的挡风玻璃上。 4. The impact of the stone against the windowpane shattered the glass. 石头撞击窗户打碎了玻璃。 5. A vast crowd impacted the square. 广场上挤集了一大群人。 6. The company\'s performance was impacted by the high value of the pound. 公司的业绩受到了英镑高值的冲击。', '名词: impaction 过去式: impacted 过去分词: impacted 现在分词: impacting 第三人称单数: impacts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('uphold', '[ʌp\'hoʊld]', 'vt.支持,赞成', '1. Eight columns uphold the big dome. 八根柱子支撑着这个大圆顶。 2. The President swore to uphold the constitution. 总统宣誓维护宪法。 3. He proffered to uphold justice. 他表示愿意维护正义。 4. The judge upheld the lower court\'s decision. 法官维持初级法院的判决。', '名词: upholder 过去式: upheld 过去分词: upheld 现在分词: upholding 第三人称单数: upholds');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('nickel', '[\'nɪkl]', 'n.[化]镍,镍币,(美国和加拿大的)五分镍币;vt.镀镍于', '1. Danish women have contact allergy caused by nickel. 丹麦妇女因镍造成接触性过敏症。 2. Bear ran over to Pig and bought another hot dog with the nickel. 熊跑到猪那，用这个五分镍币从猪那买了一个热狗。 3. America\'s best buy for a nickel is a telephone call to the right man. 在美国以一枚镍币可购得的最划算的东西，是打电话找到要找的人。 4. Each nickel is worth five cents. 每个五分镍币相当于5美分。 5. Screw plugs, brass nickel plated, with metric thread. 圆形螺旋塞，材质为黄铜镀镍，公制螺纹。', '过去式: nickeled/nickelled 过去分词: nickeled/nickelled 现在分词: nickeling/nickelling 第三人称单数: nickels/nickels');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('process', '[\'prɑˌsɛs]', 'n.过程,作用,方法,程序,步骤,进行,推移;vt.加工,处理', '1. Building a car is a long process. 制造一辆小汽车有很长的工序。 2. They went over every process again, but without result. 他们把每道工序又检查了一遍，却仍没有结果。 3. Growth and decay are vital processes. 生长和衰亡是生命过程。 4. Brazil began importing soybeans to process at home. 巴西开始进口大豆在国内加工。', '名词复数: processes 过去式: processed 过去分词: processed 现在分词: processing 第三人称单数: processes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('plateau', '[plæ\'toʊ]', 'n.高地,高原(上升后的)稳定水平(或时期、状态)', '1. The plateau extends for many miles. 高原连绵许多英里。 2. The ranch is in the middle of a large plateau. 该牧场位于一个辽阔高原的中部。 3. After a period of rapid inflation, price have now reach a plateau. 经急剧通货膨胀之后物价现已趋于平稳。 4. Mortgage rates declined, then reached a plateau. 抵押价格下跌，然后达到稳定水平 5. The athletic footwear market has not yet plateaued. 运动鞋市场并没趋于平稳。', '名词复数: plateaus 过去式: plateaued 过去分词: plateaued 现在分词: plateauing 第三人称单数: plateaus');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('periodic', '[ˌpɪri\'ɑːdɪk]', 'adj.周期的,定期的', '1. Long long ago, we knew the periodic motion of a planet. 很久以前, 我们就知道行星的周期运动。 2. Why are the version numbers not in any particular periodic sequence? 为什么版本号不是按照任何特定的周期序列? 3. The doctor made periodic visit to the house to see if the baby was all right. 医生定期到这家进行拜访,检查婴儿的健康。 4. There is a periodic reshuffle of our company staff. 我们公司定期有人事变动。', '副词: periodically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('elaborate', '[ɪ\'læbəreɪt]', 'adj.精心制作的,详细阐述的,精细;vt.精心制作,详细阐述;v.详细描述', '1. He launched into an elaborate explanation of his theory. 他开始详尽地阐发他的理论。 2. Her elaborate hairstyle, to her disappointment, just amused us. 令她失望的是,她复杂的发型只让我们感到好笑。 3. It was not the old man to indulge in elaborate preliminaries. 这位老人向来不做那种煞费苦心的开场白。 4. She had prepared herself for a very elaborate show. 她准备了一场非常精美的表演。 5. She went on to elaborate her argument. 她进而详尽阐述了她的论点。', '副词: elaborately 名词: elaborateness 过去式: elaborated 过去分词: elaborated 现在分词: elaborating 第三人称单数: elaborates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('linger', '[\'lɪŋɡər]', 'v.逗留,闲荡,拖延,游移', '1. The beautiful melody is lingering in my mind. 美妙的音乐在我心中回荡。 2. She linger after the concert, hoping to meet the star. 音乐会后她徘徊不去，希望能遇见明星。 3. He made excuses to linger on the stairs. 他找借口故意在楼梯口上磨磨蹭蹭。 4. We can\'t linger any more, because we have so many works unfinished. 我们有这么作业还没完成,不能在拖延了。', '副词: lingeringly 名词: lingerer 过去式: lingered 过去分词: lingered 现在分词: lingering 第三人称单数: lingers');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('comparable', '[\'kɑːmpərəbl]', 'adj.可比较的,比得上的', '1. The achievements of an athlete and a writer are not comparable. 运动员的成就与作家的成就不能相提并论。 2. The sets of figures are not comparable. 这几组数字是不可比的。 3. Your achievements are comparable with his. 你的成绩可与他的相媲美。 4. His handwriting is not bad, but it\'s hardly comparable with yours. 他的书法不错，但是很难和你的相比。', '副词: comparably 名词: comparability');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sympathetic', '[ˌsɪmpə\'θetɪk]', 'adj.有同情心的,合意的,赞成的;n.[解]交感神经,容易感受的人', '1. He took a sympathetic attitude toward my situation. 他对我的境遇抱同情的态度. 2. We are sympathetic with the flood sufferers. 我们同情水灾受难者。 3. She was sympathetic to my ideas. 她对我的想法表示支持。 4. They were quite sympathetic to our proposals. 他们非常赞同我们的建议。', '副词: sympathetically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('implement', '[\'ɪmplɪmənt]', 'n.工具,器具;vt.贯彻,实现;v.执行', '1. What implements are needed for gardening? 园艺需要些什么工具？ 2. That implement is useful for many purposes in the kitchen. 那种工具在厨房里有许多用途。 3. The system can preferably implement automatic text categorization for Chinese pages, and has a higher quality. 该系统可以很好地实现一个中文网页的自动分类，且系统中的分类器具有较高的分类质量。 4. Her designs will be put on ice until money is available to implement them. 她的设计将暂时搁起来，等有了钱再去实施。', '名词: implementation 过去式: implemented 过去分词: implemented 现在分词: implementing 第三人称单数: implements');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('violate', '[\'vaɪəleɪt]', 'vt.违犯,亵渎(圣物),冒犯,干扰,违反,妨碍,侵犯,强暴', '1. Don\'t violate other people\'s copyright. 不要侵犯他人版权。 2. I\'m committed not to violate the rules. 我有义务不违反规定。 3. The country violated the international agreement. 这个国家违反了国际协议。 4. The sound of guns violated the peace of the countryside. 炮声扰乱了乡村的宁静。', '形容词: violative 名词: violator 过去式: violated 过去分词: violated 现在分词: violating 第三人称单数: violates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('syndrome', '[\'sɪndroʊm]', 'n.综合病症', '1. This patient provides a typical example of the syndrome. 这位患者是这种症候群的典型病例。 2. Poor appetite is one of the symptoms of TV syndrome. 食欲不振是电视综合症的症状之一。 3. This syndrome is associated with frequent coughing. 这种综合症与经常咳嗽有关。', '形容词: syndromic');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('insane', '[ɪn\'seɪn]', 'adj.患精神病的,精神病患者的,极愚蠢的', '1. Are you insane? 你疯了吗？ 2. I have an insane desire to finish that thing. 我疯狂地渴望去完成那件事。 3. That person is insane. 那人精神错乱。 4. The insane man was committed to an asylum. 那个精神失常的人被送进了精神病院。', '副词: insanely 名词: insaneness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('random', '[\'rændəm]', 'n.随意,任意;adj.任意的,随便的,胡乱的;adv.胡乱地', '1. Men are exposed to more acts of random physical violence. 男人受到更多的任意的身体强烈活动。 2. Most people know that the outcome of a coin toss is random. 大部分人都知道掷硬币的结果是随机的。 3. The computer will generate apparently random numbers. 电脑似乎将随机产生号码。 4. This random approach is not as dubious as one might expect. 这种随意的途径并不象人们所预期的那样无把握。 5. Soiled dishes were piled at random. 脏碟子胡乱地堆放着。 6. Complex organs made up of separate but necessary subsystems cannot be the result of random chance. 复杂的器官是由独立的，必要的子系统组成，而且不能随机地形成。', '副词: randomly 名词: randomness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('huddle', '[\'hʌdl]', 'v.拥挤,卷缩,草率从事,挤作一团;n.杂乱的一堆,拥挤', '1. He shouted into the cavernous arena as if he were shouting into a huddle. 他对着球场吼叫，似乎他面对的是混乱的人群。 2. James insisted the Cavs needed to go bigger and broke from the huddle shaking his head in disagreement. 詹姆斯不住地摇头表示反对，他坚持认为骑士应该换上大个球员，打破场上的混乱局面。 3. The track led them to a huddle of barns and outbuildings. 那条路把他们带到了一片杂乱拥挤的谷仓和库房。 4. At the BeiBei plant, women huddle over a conveyor belt in frigid temperatures, gluing rubber sneakers together. 在贝贝公司，妇女拥挤在寒冷的传送带周围粘橡胶旅游鞋。', '名词: huddler 过去式: huddled 过去分词: huddled 现在分词: huddling 第三人称单数: huddles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('approve', '[ə\'pruːv]', 'vi.赞成,满意;vt.批准,通过;v.批准', '1. The city council approved the building plan. 市议会批准了这项建筑计划。 2. I presume you will approve of the plan. 我相信你会赞成这个计划。 3. You can join the class if your parents approve. 如果你父母同意，你可以参加这个班。 4. I approve of your trying to earn some money, but please don\'t neglect your studies. 我同意你去挣一些钱，可是请不要误了功课。', '形容词: approvable 副词: approvingly 过去式: approved 过去分词: approved 现在分词: approving 第三人称单数: approves');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('intellectual', '[ˌɪntə\'lektʃuəl]', 'adj.智力的,有智力的,显示智力的;n.知识分子', '1. He likes to set himself up as an intellectual. 他喜欢自命为知识分子。 2. These views were common among intellectuals. 这些观点在知识分子中很普遍。 3. The argument was too intellectual for me; I couldn\'t follow a word of it. 这场争论对我来说太深奥了，我一点都搞不明白。 4. Chess is a highly intellectual game. 象棋是需用高度智力的运动项目。', '副词: intellectually 名词: intellectuality');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('layman', '[\'leɪmən]', 'n.外行', '1. He is a layman in politics. 他对政治是个门外汉。 2. This book is written for professionals and laymen alike. 这本书既可供专业人员阅读，又可供外行人看。 3. Where the law is concerned, I am only a layman. 谈到法律, 我不过是门外汉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('exemplify', '[ɪɡ\'zemplɪfaɪ]', 'vt.例证,例示,作为...例子', '1. I will exemplify my point with a story. 我会用一个故事举例说明我的观点。 2. To exemplify this theory,let us examine some species of insect. 为举例说明这种理论，我们来检查一些种类的昆虫。 3. The plays of Wilds exemplify the comedy of manners. 王尔德的戏剧是风尚喜剧的典范。 4. The recent oil price rises exemplify the difficulties which the motor industry is now facing. 最近的石油涨价是汽车工业正面临的困难的一个例子。', '形容词: exemplifiable 名词: exemplifier 过去式: exemplified 过去分词: exemplified 现在分词: exemplifying 第三人称单数: exemplifies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('occupation', '[ˌɑːkju\'peɪʃn]', 'n.职业,占有,占有(房屋等)期间', '1. I haven\'t entered your name and occupation yet. 我尚未记下你的名字和职业。 2. Please state your name, age and occupation. 请说明姓名、年龄和职业。 3. He is a merchant in occupation. 他的职业是经商。 4. He returned from Paris and found his office was under someone else\'s occupation. 他从巴黎回来，发现他的办公室被别人占了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('vast', '[væst]', 'adj.巨大的,辽阔的,大量的,巨额的', '1. That is a vast and lavish party. 那是个规模盛大、极其铺张的宴会。 2. A vast crowd turned out to watch the match. 大群的观众到场观看比赛。 3. There is always a vast chasm between rich and poor. 贫富的鸿沟始终存在。 4. The Pacific Ocean is a vast expanse of water. 太平洋是一片广大的水域。', '副词: vastly 比较级: vaster 最高级: vastest 名词: vastness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('responsible', '[rɪ\'spɑːnsəbl]', 'adj.有责任的,可靠的,可依赖的,负责的', '1. Who\'s responsible for the terrible mess? 谁应该对这种混乱负责？ 2. As a boy, i know, i was responsible to help her. 作为个男生,我知道,我有责任帮助她。 3. We all think of her as a responsible teacher. 我们都认为她是一位很负责的教师。 4. You are supposed to be responsible for them. 你是应当对他们负责的。', '副词: responsibly 名词: responsibleness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('chief', '[tʃiːf]', 'n.首领,领袖,酋长,长官,主要部分,最有价值的部分;adj.主要的,首要的,首席的,主任的', '1. In USA, NewYork City is the chief seat of commerce. 在美国,纽约是主要的商业中心。 2. What are the chief exports of your country? 你们国家有哪些主要的出口物品？ 3. Slow speed is the chief drawback of sea shipment. 海运最大的缺点是速度慢。 4. The chief interchanged the diamond with some pieces of glass. 那首领拿一些玻璃块替换了那些钻石。', '名词: chiefdom');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('overcome', '[ˌoʊvər\'kʌm]', 'vt.战胜,克服,胜过,征服;vi.得胜', '1. I realized that there is no way I can overcome it. 我意识到自己没有办法战胜它。 2. There will be no difficulty in the world that they cannot overcome. 世界上任何困难他们都可以克服。 3. We can and must overcome our shortcomings. 我们能够而且必须克服我们的缺点。 4. He was overcome by the gas fumes. 汽油味使他受不了。 5. We shall overcome! 我们一定胜利！', '过去式: overcame 过去分词: overcome 现在分词: overcoming 第三人称单数: overcomes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('beyond', '[bɪ\'jɑːnd]', 'prep.在(到)...较远的一边,超过,那一边;adv.在远处;n.远处', '1. The level of inflation has gone beyond 8%. 通货膨胀率已经超过了8%。 2. Such philosophical subtleties are beyond my reach. 这种深奥的哲理我可无法理解。 3. The scenery there was beautiful beyond expression. 那儿的风景美丽得无法形容。 4. The road continues beyond the village up into the hills. 这条路绵延不断越过村子直入山中。 5. They crossed the mountains and travelled to the valleys beyond. 他们越过群山，到了那边的山谷。 6. In future, men can travel to the moon and beyond. 未来人们能到月球或更远处去旅行。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('posture', '[\'pɑːstʃər]', 'n.(身体的)姿势,体态,状态,情况,心境,态度;v.令取某种姿势,摆姿势,作出姿态', '1. Only humans have a natural upright posture. 只有人类才有自然直立的姿势。 2. The artist asked his model to take a reclining posture. 画家要求模特取斜倚着的姿势。 3. She has very good posture. 她举止很优雅。 4. The government adopted an uncompromising posture on the issue of independence. 政府在独立的问题上采取了毫不妥协的态度。 5. The war-monger would sometimes posture for peace 战争贩子有时也会装出主张和平的姿态。', '形容词: postural 名词: posturer 过去式: postured 过去分词: postured 现在分词: posturing 第三人称单数: postures');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('knit', '[nɪt]', 'v.编织,密接,结合', '1. She often knits while watching TV. 她常常一边看电视一边织毛衣。 2. She preferred to sew rather than to knit. 她喜欢缝纫而不喜欢编织。 3. The doctor knit the two broken bones in his arm. 医生把他臂上的两块折骨接好了。 4. The treaty knit the economies of the two nations together. 该条约把两国的经济紧密地结合在一起。 5. The son begins to knit a big fishnet. 儿子就开始编织大网了。', '名词: knitter 过去式: knit/knitted 过去分词: knit/knitted 现在分词: knitting 第三人称单数: knits');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('nickname', '[\'nɪkneɪm]', 'n.诨号,绰号,昵称;vt.给...取绰号,给...起浑名', '1. We often call him by his nickname. 我们经常叫他的绰号。 2. Everyone on the team was tagged with a nickname. 队里的每个成员都给起了一个绰号。 3. Jess is just my nickname - my real name is Jessica. 杰西只是我的昵称，我的真名是杰西卡。 4. Your nickname lets a person worry for you. 你的昵称让人替你担心。', '名词: nicknamer 过去式: nicknamed 过去分词: nicknamed 现在分词: nicknaming 第三人称单数: nicknames');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('discrepancy', '[dɪs\'krepənsi]', 'n.相差,差异,矛盾', '1. We\'d like to discuss the details of the contract, especially discrepancy and claim. 我们想讨论合同的各项细目,特别是差异和索赔。 2. The price tag says$100 and you charged me for$120; how do you explain the discrepancy? 货物标签上写的是一百美元,你向我索价一百二十美元,这个差异该怎么解释？ 3. There was a discrepancy in the two reports. 在两个报告中有不一致之处。 4. Shakespeare did not acquiesce in discrepancy. 莎士比亚对于分歧并不是采取默认的态度。', '名词复数: discrepancies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('probability', '[ˌprɑːbə\'bɪləti]', 'n.可能性,或然性,概率', '1. The probability that it will rain today is high. 今天下雨的可能性很大。 2. The probability of making a mistake increases when you are tired. 你累的时候犯错误的可能性就会增加。 3. Sometimes, love is a kind of probability. 有时，爱情就是一种或然率。 4. I don\'t know how to calculate probability accurately. 不知道怎样才可以准确的计算出或然率。', '名词复数: probabilities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('exile', '[\'ekzaɪl]', 'n.放逐,充军,流放,流犯,被放逐者;vt.放逐,流放,使背井离乡', '1. The king was sent into exile. 国王遭到放逐。 2. He was publicly disgraced and sent into exile. 他被当众贬谪，放逐异乡。 3. Everyone is born king,and most people die in exile. 每个人生下来都是王，而大多数人却在放逐中死去。 4. Exile was for him a living death. 他遭流放是进了活地狱。 5. He was exiled from the country for one year. 他被放逐一年。', '形容词: exilic 过去式: exiled 过去分词: exiled 现在分词: exiling 第三人称单数: exiles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('instance', '[\'ɪnstəns]', 'n.实例,建议,要求,情况,场合;vt.举...为例,获得例证', '1. This is only one instance out of many. 这不过是许多例子中的一个。 2. Can you quote a recent instance? 你能举出一个最近的例证吗? 3. You may get along well with your boss but there will always be that specific instance where you want to say more than you should. 也许你和你老板相处得很好，但总是会有一些特殊的场合，你想说的话多于你应该说的。 4. In most instances the pain soon goes away. 在多数情况下,这种疼痛很快就会消失。 5. The game was exciting, as was instanced by the score. 依分数所示, 这场比赛是很紧张的。', '过去式: instanced 过去分词: instanced 现在分词: instancing 第三人称单数: instances');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('decree', '[dɪ\'kriː]', 'n.法令,政令,教令,天命,判决;v.颁布', '1. This decree obliges unions to delay strikes . 这项法令使协会不得不推迟罢工。 2. The decree imposed strict censorship of the media. 这个法令强制实行严格的媒体审查制度。 3. The final decree dissolved their marriage. 最后的判决解除了他们的婚姻关系。 4. This decree has the force of law behind it. 这一裁决有法律的力量作后盾。 5. The dictator decreed that his birthday would be a public holiday. 该独裁者发布命令，将其生日定为公众假期。', '形容词: decreeable 名词: decreer 过去式: decreed 过去分词: decreed 现在分词: decreeing 第三人称单数: decrees');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('constitution', '[ˌkɒnstə\'tjuːʃən]', 'n.宪法,构造,体质,体格,国体,章程,惯例', '1. The President swore to uphold the constitution. 总统宣誓维护宪法。 2. The country\'s constitution embodies the ideals of freedom and equality. 这个国家的宪法体现了自由和平等的理想。 3. The constitution of a primitive society is not necessarily simple. 原始社会的结构并不一定就是简单的。 4. Hunger and disease had weakened his constitution. 他饥饿与疾病交加，体质已削弱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('finance', '[\'faɪnæns]', 'n.财政,金融,财政学;vt.供给...经费,负担经费;vi.筹措资金', '1. He is a well-known expert in finance. 他是知名的金融专家。 2. The Chancellor of the Exchequer is the minister in charge of finance in Britain. 英国财政大臣是负责财政的大臣。 3. Unless we can get more finance, we\'ll have to close the store. 除非我们能得到更多的资金，我们将不得不关闭这家商店。 4. The repairs to the school will be financed by the educational department. 学校的修缮将由教育部门出资。', '形容词: financeable 过去式: financed 过去分词: financed 现在分词: financing 第三人称单数: finances');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('vigorous', '[\'vɪɡərəs]', 'adj.精力旺盛的,有力的,健壮的', '1. Old as he is, he is none the less vigorous and active. 虽然他年纪很大了，他仍然精力充沛。 2. He never ceased to chase after his dream in his vigorous youth. 在精力充沛的年轻时代他从未停止过追求自己的梦想。 3. She gave the floor a vigorous sponge all over. 她用海绵把地板 使劲儿擦了一遍。 4. He uttered several vigorous expletives when he dropped the iron on his foot. 他的熨斗掉下砸在脚上，他随口骂了几声。', '副词: vigorously 名词: vigorousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('specialist', '[\'speʃəlɪst]', 'n.专门医师,专家', '1. We profit from the work of the specialist. 我们从专家的工作中得到益处。 2. The provision of specialist teachers is being increased. 配备专业教员的人数有所增加。 3. He is a plastic surgery specialist. 他是个整形外科医生。 4. Her mother is an eye specialist. 她母亲是眼科专家。', '形容词: specialistic');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('foil', '[fɔɪl]', 'n.箔,金属薄片,[建]叶形片,烘托,衬托;vt.衬托,阻止,挡开,挫败,贴箔于', '1. The foil is a thrusting weapon with no cutting edge. 花剑，没有劈杀用的剑刀，是刺戳用兵器。 2. Our foil packets seal the flavour in. 我们用锡纸包装以保持原味。 3. Aluminum foil can be used for wrapping food. 铝箔用于包装食物。 4. This box of chocolate was wrapped round with foil. 这盒巧克力用箔纸包着。 5. Only confident, people will never foil. 只要有信心，人永远不会挫败。', '过去式: foiled 过去分词: foiled 现在分词: foiling 第三人称单数: foils');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('authority', '[ə\'θɔːrəti]', 'n.权威,威信,权威人士,权力,职权,典据,著作权威', '1. The government is the highest authority in the country. 政府是国家的最高权力机构。 2. Authorities say the fires do look suspicious. 官方表示，火灾看起来确实很奇怪。 3. Both the authorities and the media wondered whether insider dealing had been going on. 官方跟媒体都在怀疑这里面是不是存在内幕交易。 4. The authorities did not interfere with us. 当局不干涉我们。', '名词复数: authorities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('speculate', '[\'spekjuleɪt]', 'vi.推测,思索,做投机买卖', '1. The doctors speculate that he died of cancer. 医生推测他死于癌症。 2. Can you speculate how such damage might arise? 你能否想出这种伤害是怎样引起的? 3. He likes to speculate on the stock market. 他喜欢炒股。 4. It\'s dangerous to speculate. 做投机买卖是很危险的。', '过去式: speculated 过去分词: speculated 现在分词: speculating 第三人称单数: speculates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('force', '[fɔːrs]', 'n.力量,武力,精力,魄力,势力,暴力,[复]军队,影响力;vt.强制,强加,(用武力)夺取,使,推动,施加压力', '1. When persuasion failed they used force. 劝说无效时,他们就使用武力了。 2. We\'ll settle the problem by force if necessary. 如果有必要的话,我们会用武力解决这个问题。 3. If you do not open the door, I am authorized to enter by use of force. 如果你不开门,我有权使用暴力闯入。 4. It is vain to attempt to root out heresy by force. 试图用暴力消除异端邪说是徒劳的。 5. Circumstances force us to adopt this policy. 形势迫使我们采取这项政策。', '形容词: forceable 名词: forcer 过去式: forced 过去分词: forced 现在分词: forcing 第三人称单数: forces');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('apartment', '[ə\'pɑːrtmənt]', 'n.<美>公寓住宅,单元住宅,房间', '1. I have an apartment in downtown Manhattan. 我在曼哈顿中心区有一套住房。 2. We are fascinated by the delicate interior design of the apartment. 我们被这所公寓的精致的室内装潢设计吸引。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('embody', '[ɪm\'bɑːdi]', 'vt.具体表达,使具体化,包含,收录', '1. The country\'s constitution embodies the ideals of freedom and equality. 这个国家的宪法体现了自由和平等的理想。 2. He embodies a new idea in his paintings. 他在画中体现思想。 3. The latest computer model embodies many new features. 最新型的计算机具备许多新功能。 4. The new car embodies many improvements. 这辆新车包含了许多改进的项目。', '过去式: embodied 过去分词: embodied 现在分词: embodying 第三人称单数: embodies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('conservative', '[kən\'sɜːrvətɪv]', 'adj.保守的,守旧的;n.保守派', '1. He was very conservative in the estimate. 他的这一估计很保守。 2. Old people are usually more conservative than young people. 老年人通常比年轻人保守。 3. The professor\'s a radical in politics but a conservative dresser. 教授在政治上是激进派,但衣着却很守旧。 4. The man turned from Radical to Conservative. 这人从激进派变成了保守派。', '副词: conservatively 名词: conservativeness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('linen', '[\'lɪnɪn]', 'n.亚麻布,亚麻制品,亚麻纤维制成的优质纸;adj.亚麻布制的,亚麻的', '1. The old linen smelled of the tomb. 旧亚麻布散发出墓地的气味。 2. Flax is used to make linen. 亚麻用来织亚麻布。 3. Low elasticity, imparting a hard, smooth texture, makes linen subject to wrinkling. 弹性较低，使得质地坚硬光滑，亚麻制品容易起皱纹。 4. He has abandoned suits in favour of linen jackets and khaki trousers and no tie. 他不穿西装，喜欢穿亚麻夹克和卡其布长裤，而且不打领带。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('desirable', '[dɪ\'zaɪərəbl]', 'adj.值得要的,合意的,令人想要的,悦人心意的', '1. It is desirable that we (should) provide for the poor at Christmas. 在圣诞节施舍穷人是可喜的事。 2. It is desirable that atomic energy should be used for peaceful purpose. 原子能应该为了和平的目的而使用，这是合乎情理的。 3. You will also make some desirable acquaintances. 你也可以结识几个合意的朋友。 4. He found her intensely desirable. 他觉得她极其性感。 5. The girl is a desirable. 这个女孩是个有吸引力的人。', '副词: desirably 名词: desirability');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tragic', '[\'trædʒɪk]', 'adj.悲惨的,悲剧的;n.(文艺作品或生活中的)悲剧因素,悲剧风格', '1. This delay was to have tragic results. 这样的延误即将导致悲剧的结局。 2. I don\'t like the tragic ending of the film. 我不喜欢电影悲剧的结尾。 3. Her tragic story touched us all deeply/touched our hearts with sorrow. 她的经历很悲惨，我们都深受感动[我们都很伤心]。 4. She listened to the tragic news ashen-faced. 她听到这一悲惨消息，脸都白了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('isle', '[aɪl]', 'n.小岛,岛;vt.使成为岛屿;vi.住在岛屿上', '1. The tiny isle had a sandy beach. 这小岛有一片沙滩。 2. In a word, the isle was inhabited. 总而言之，这个小岛上确是有居民的。 3. This isle was then floating and unstable. 这座小岛漂浮在水面上并且不稳定。 4. Horses would not have been lacking in the Isle of Wight. 在怀特岛上，马匹是不可或缺的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('persist', '[pər\'sɪst]', 'vi.坚持,持续', '1. I hope you\'ll persist in your efforts. 我希望你们再接再励。 2. He will persist in riding that dreadful bicycle. 他执意要骑那辆破自行车。 3. If you persist, you will annoy them even more. 你若固执，他们就更恼火了。 4. If you persist in breaking the law you will go to prison. 如果你再继续违法的话，你会坐牢的。', '名词: persister 过去式: persisted 过去分词: persisted 现在分词: persisting 第三人称单数: persists');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('emergency', '[i\'mɜːrdʒənsi]', 'n.紧急情况,突然事件,非常时刻,紧急事件', '1. She has the ability to keep calm in an emergency. 她有处变不惊的本事。 2. We took the emergency in our stride. 我们泰然地处理了紧急情况。 3. Ring the bell in an emergency. 情况紧急时请按铃。 4. The rioting grew worse and the government declared a state of emergency. 骚乱恶化，政府只得宣布进入紧急状态。 5. He has made every arrangement to meet any emergency. 他已作好了应急的一切准备。', '名词复数: emergencies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('artery', '[\'ɑːrtəri]', 'n.动脉,要道', '1. Blood was spouting from the severed artery . 血从切断的动脉里喷出来。 2. This widens the inside of the artery, restoring blood flow. 这样会扩展动脉的内腔，达到恢复血流的效果。 3. The Yangtse River is one of the main arteries of traffic in China. 长江是中国的交通要道之一。 4. This is the place where the three main arteries of West London traffic meet. 这是伦敦西区三条主要干线会合的地方。', '名词复数: arteries');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('notion', '[\'noʊʃn]', 'n.概念,观念,想法,意见,打算,主张,(复数)<美语>小饰物', '1. State control is a very un-American notion. 实行国家控制是根本违背美国观念的。 2. They want a system based on the notions of personal equality and liberty. 他们想要基于人的平等﹑ 自由等概念的制度。 3. We had a notion that he was telling a lie. 我们当时的看法是他在说谎。 4. She dinged the notion into our ears. 她老是唠唠叨叨地跟我们讲那个想法。(或：她把那个想法反反复复地灌输给我们)。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('warehouse', '[\'werhaʊs]', 'n.仓库,货栈,大商店;vt.贮入仓库,<俚>[经]以他人名义购进(股票)', '1. They stored their goods in a warehouse. 他们把货物储存在一个仓库里。 2. They operate three factories and a huge warehouse. 他们经营三家工厂和一个大仓库。 3. If necessary, please warehouse the goods. 如有必要，请将该货存入仓库。', '名词: warehouser 过去式: warehoused 过去分词: warehoused 现在分词: warehousing 第三人称单数: warehouses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('discount', '[\'dɪskaʊnt]', 'n.折扣', '1. These goods will be sold at a discount. 这些货物将减价出售。 2. We give 10 percent discount for cash. 现金付款，我们九折优惠。 3. The discount rate is set by the Fed. 贴现率是由联储决定的。 4. The preferred project in this case depends on the discount rate, not the IRR. 该例中，我们倾向选择哪个项目取决于贴现率，而不是内部收益率。 5. That store does not discount at all. 那家商店出售商品一概不打折。 6. We usually only discount acceptance trade and commercial bills. 我们通常只贴现已承兑的商业票据。', '形容词: discountable 过去式: discounted 过去分词: discounted 现在分词: discounting 第三人称单数: discounts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('identify', '[aɪ\'dentɪfaɪ]', 'vt.识别,鉴别,把...和...看成一样;v.确定', '1. Identify how the incident occurred. 鉴定事故如何出现。 2. The test can identify the presence of abnormalities in the unborn child. 这项化验能鉴定胎儿是否有不正常现象。 3. The markings are so blurred that it is difficult to identify. 标记模糊不清，难以识别。 4. Please identify the registered trademark. 请认明注册商标。 5. I found it hard to identify with any of the characters in the film. 我对这部影片里的任何角色都难以认同。', '形容词: identifiable 副词: identifiably 名词: identifier 过去式: identified 过去分词: identified 现在分词: identifying 第三人称单数: identifies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('provided', '[prə\'vaɪdɪd]', 'conj.倘若', '1. I shall go provided that it doesn\'t rain. 假如不下雨我就去。 2. Provided that you reduce the price, I\'ll take all the goods. 假如你减价,我会买下所有的货物。 3. Provided we have adequate supplies, the enemy can never break in. 若有充足的给养，敌人是打不进来的。 4. I will come provided that I am well enough. 只要我身体好一定来。 5. Please put your litter in the bin provided. 请你把废物扔到预备好的垃圾箱里。 6. The newspaper article provided him with fuel for his speech. 报纸上的这篇文章为他的演讲提供了启发。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('application', '[ˌæplɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.请求,申请,申请表,应用,运用,施用,敷用,应用,应用程序,应用软件', '1. The application of new scientific discoveries to industrial production methods usually increases efficiency. 把新的科学发现运用到工业生产上,通常可以提高效率。 2. I didn\'t receive an acknowledgement of my application. 对我的申请,我还没有收到复信告知收悉。 3. The manager received twenty applications for the post. 经理收到了二十份求职申请书。 4. Patience and application will carry us through. 忍耐和专心会使我们度过难关。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cherish', '[\'tʃerɪʃ]', 'vt.珍爱,怀抱(希望等)', '1. Life is hope, so we should cherish life. 生命就是希望 2. I cherish my independence. 我很珍惜我的自由。 3. I cherish the memory of those happy times. 我把那些美好的时光珍藏在自己的记忆里。 4. A mother cherishes her baby. 母亲疼爱孩子。', '副词: cherishingly 名词: cherisher 过去式: cherished 过去分词: cherished 现在分词: cherishing 第三人称单数: cherishes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('allege', '[ə\'ledʒ]', 'vt.宣称,断言', '1. The newspapers allege that the police shot the suspect without warning. 报纸指称说警察未经示警就枪杀那位嫌疑犯。 2. So they alleged, but have they any proof? 他们是这样宣称的，但他们有证据吗？ 3. The police alleged that the man was murdered but they have given no proof. 警方声称这男子是被谋杀的，但未提出任何证据。 4. In your statement you allege that the accused man was seen at the scene of the crime . 在你的口供中，你供述曾经看到被告在犯罪现场。', '形容词: allegeable 名词: alleger 过去式: alleged 过去分词: alleged 现在分词: alleging 第三人称单数: alleges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('abstract', '[\'æbstrækt]', 'n.摘要,概要,抽象;adj.抽象的,深奥的,理论的;vt.摘要,提炼,抽象化', '1. We may talk of beautiful things, but beauty itself is abstract. 我们尽可谈论美的事物，然而美本身却是抽象的。 2. He has some abstract notion of wanting to change the world. 他有一种要改造世界的空想。 3. Abstract paintings did not appeal to him. 抽象派绘画引不起他的兴趣。 4. The whole text of the abstract shall contain not more than 300 Chinese characters. 摘要文字部分不得超过300个字。 5. She abstracted the main points from the argument. 她把论据概括成要点。', '副词: abstractly 名词: abstracter 过去式: abstracted 过去分词: abstracted 现在分词: abstracting 第三人称单数: abstracts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tangle', '[\'tæŋɡl]', 'n.混乱状态;v.处于混乱状态', '1. The wool got in a fearful tangle. 毛线乱成了一团。 2. His financial affairs are in such a tangle. 他的钱财是糊涂帐。 3. We employed a lawyer to straighten our legal tangle. 我们雇了一位律师把法律纠纷理出头绪。 4. The little girl tangled the yarn her mother was knitting. 小女孩把她妈妈在编结的毛线弄得纠结在一起了。 5. He was really a tough guy to tangle with. 他真是一个难缠的人。', '形容词: tangly 过去式: tangled 过去分词: tangled 现在分词: tangling 第三人称单数: tangles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('gland', '[ɡlænd]', 'n.[解剖]腺,[机械]密封管', '1. The prostate is a small gland in men. 前列腺是男性体内的一个小腺体。 2. Many tiny tubes connect each silk gland with a spinneret. 许多极细小的导管把每个造丝腺体与吐丝器相连。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('forum', '[\'fɔːrəm]', 'n.古罗马城镇的广场(或市场),论坛,法庭,讨论会', '1. This is a forum for education and technology. 这是一个有关教育和技术的讨论会。 2. I believe that this is the key issue of the Forum. 我相信,这个问题正是这次研讨会的要旨所在。 3. The letters page of this newspaper is a forum for public argument. 这份报纸的读者来信栏是公众意见的论坛。 4. Wonderful! I put it to the English forum. 太好了!我转到英文论坛去。', '名词复数: forums');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('precede', '[prɪ\'siːd]', 'v.领先(于),在...之前,先于', '1. He precede his speech with a welcome to the guest. 他演讲前先对来宾表示欢迎。 2. He came in, preceded by his wife. 他和他的妻子一前一后地走了进来。 3. The we should always precede the I. 集体总应先于个人。 4. This duty should precede all others. 此项义务应该优先于其他一切义务。 5. The days that preceded were filled with activity. 前几天排满了活动。', '过去式: preceded 过去分词: preceded 现在分词: preceding 第三人称单数: precedes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('marginal', '[\'mɑːrdʒɪnl]', 'adj.记在页边的,边缘的,边际的', '1. Economists call these marginal changes. 经济学家称这些为边际的变化。 2. The marginal illustration is very interesting. 页边的插图很有趣。 3. He won the most marginal seat by only two votes. 他只以两票的微弱优势当选。 4. He had a very marginal victory with only 180 more votes in his favor. 他仅以180票的微弱优势赢得了胜利。', '副词: marginally 名词: marginality');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('objective', '[əb\'dʒektɪv]', 'n.目标,目的,(显微镜的)(接)物镜,[语法]宾格;adj.客观的,[语法]宾格的', '1. From any objective perspective,it is simply too long. 从客观的角度来讲，这实在是太长了。 2. She gives an objective report of what has happened. 她就发生的事情进行客观的报告。 3. He has told a story which sound not objective. 他讲了听起来不真实的一个故事。 4. Her principal objective was international fame as a scientist. 她的主要目标是当个有国际声誉的科学家。', '副词: objectively 名词: objectiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sustain', '[sə\'steɪn]', 'vt.支撑,撑住,维持,持续', '1. His hope for future sustained him. 对未来的希望支持了他。 2. The ice will not sustain your weight. 这冰承受不了你的体重。 3. Some species may not be able to sustain the pressure from such prevalent raids. 一些物种无法承受这种猖撅的偷猎行为带来的压力。 4. They had sufficient food to sustain life. 他们有足够维持生命的食物。', '形容词: sustainable 名词: sustainability 过去式: sustained 过去分词: sustained 现在分词: sustaining 第三人称单数: sustains');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('vehicle', '[\'viːɪkl]', 'n.交通工具,车辆,媒介物,传达手段', '1. No entry for vehicle! 禁止车辆入内！ 2. It is time for the yearly check of vehicle safety. 到车辆安全年审的时间了。 3. Subway is a convenient vehicle for those white collars. 地铁对于白领阶层来说是很方便的交通工具。 4. Television has become an important vehicle for spreading political ideas. 电视已成为传播政治思想的重要媒介。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('accelerate', '[ək\'seləreɪt]', 'v.加速,促进', '1. Our present task is to accelerate economic growth. 加速经济发展是我们当前的任务。 2. The leader is losing ground as the rest of the runners accelerate. 领先者在其余赛跑者加速时就逐渐失去了优势。 3. We will accelerate the reform of the financial system under these circumstances. 在这一背景情况下,我们将加快金融体制改革。 4. The decline of her health seemed to suddenly accelerate. 她的健康状况好像突然提前衰退了。', '形容词: accelerative 过去式: accelerated 过去分词: accelerated 现在分词: accelerating 第三人称单数: accelerates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('suburb', '[\'sʌbɜːrb]', 'n.市郊,郊区', '1. They proposed setting up a school in the suburb. 他们建议在这个郊区成立一所学校。 2. The factory is located in the suburb. 那家工厂坐落于郊区。 3. Ronaldo grew up in Bento Ribeiro, a suburb of Rio. 罗纳尔多在里约热内卢的一个叫本托. 4. Do not you think it would be nice to live in the suburb? 难道你不认为住在郊区是件好事吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('liberal', '[\'lɪbərəl]', 'n.自由主义者,(尤指英国、加拿大等国的);adj.慷慨的,不拘泥的,宽大的,自由主义的', '1. They are liberal in their help. 他们慷慨相助。 2. She is liberal with her money. 她用钱大方。 3. Her parents are very liberal and allow her a lot of freedom. 她的父母很开明，让她享有许多的自由。 4. The headmaster has liberal views about what his pupils should wear. 校长对他的学生应穿什么服装这一点持开明的态度。 5. He is an open-minded liberal. 他是一个开明的自由主义者。', '副词: liberally 名词: liberalness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('indulge', '[ɪn\'dʌldʒ]', 'v.纵容', '1. If you will indulge me for one moment, I think I can explain the matter to you. 你要是容我把话说完,我想我可以把此事给你解释清楚。 2. It pleased me to indulge her wishes. 放手满足她的欲望，使我感到高兴。 3. He no longer indulged himself in smoking. 他不再过度吸烟了。 4. He indulged his children too much. 他太纵容他的孩子们了。 5. I shall forget about dieting today. I\'m just going to indulge. 今天我要把节食计划置之脑后,想吃什么就吃什么。', '名词: indulger 过去式: indulged 过去分词: indulged 现在分词: indulging 第三人称单数: indulges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('lubricate', '[\'luːbrɪkeɪt]', 'vt.润滑;v.加润滑油', '1. My throat needs lubricating. 我需要润润嗓子了。 2. We find it necessary to lubricate machines. 我们认为给机器加润滑油是必要的。 3. If you never bother to lubricate your engine, of course it will seize up. 如果你老是怕麻烦，不给发动机添加润滑油，发动机当然会失灵卡住啦。', '形容词: lubricative 名词: lubrication 过去式: lubricated 过去分词: lubricated 现在分词: lubricating 第三人称单数: lubricates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('advantage', '[əd\'væntɪdʒ]', 'n.优势,有利条件,利益', '1. For a goalkeeper,it\'s a great advantage to have big hands. 对于守门员来说,有一双大手是很大的优势。 2. Rich has an advantage over you since he can speak German. 理奇比你占优势，因为他会讲德语。 3. It is an advantage if you know how to type. 如果你会打字,对你将有利。 4. We should take advantage of all educational opportunities. 我们应该利用一切教育的机会。 5. Such action will advantage our cause. 这样的行动有益于我们的事业。', '过去式: advantaged 过去分词: advantaged 现在分词: advantaging 第三人称单数: advantages');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('glow', '[ɡloʊ]', 'vi.发光,发热', '1. There is a glow of health in his face. 他的脸容光焕发。 2. There midnight\'s all a glimmer and noon (is) a purple glow. 那儿午夜浮光微摇，中午紫光争耀。 3. The sunset glow is very beautiful. 太阳的余辉非常美丽。 4. His face took on an affectionate glow. 他的脸上洋溢着热情的红光。 5. All fireflies glow with about the same brightness. 所有的萤火虫闪耀着差不多相同的光亮。', '过去式: glowed 过去分词: glowed 现在分词: glowing 第三人称单数: glows');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('protest', '[\'proʊtest]', 'n.主张,断言,抗议;v.主张,断言抗议,拒付', '1. Half a million people held a mass protest against racism last night. 昨晚50万人举行了大规模的抗议活动反对种族歧视。 2. Some delegates walked out in a show of protest. 有几位代表退出会场以示抗议。 3. The minister resigned in protest against the decision. 这位部长为反对那项决策而辞职。 4. They protested to the mayor that the taxes were too high. 他们向市长提出抗议说税款过高。', '副词: protestingly 名词: protester 过去式: protested 过去分词: protested 现在分词: protesting 第三人称单数: protests');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('capsule', '[\'kæpsjuːl]', 'n.(植物)蒴果,胶囊,瓶帽,太空舱', '1. The capsule is filled with small soluble cases. 胶囊里充满了可溶的小颗粒。 2. This capsule is to be taken every four hours. 这种胶囊每隔四小时服一次。 3. This capsule is used for animals. 这个太空舱是用来装载动物的。 4. The capsule is a part of the spaceship in which the pilots live and work. 太空舱是宇宙飞船的一部分，宇航员是在太空舱里活动工作的。 5. Would you please capsule the news? 你能概括下这则新闻吗？ 6. This is a capsule description of the event. 这就是关于那个事件的简要介绍。', '过去式: capsuled 过去分词: capsuled 现在分词: capsuling 第三人称单数: capsules');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('decimal', '[\'desɪml]', 'adj.十进的,小数的,以十为基础的,十进制;n.小数', '1. The first two figures after the decimal point indicate tenths and hundredths respectively. 小数点后的头两位数分别表示十分位和百分位。 2. Most countries have a decimal currency. 大多数国家使用十进制货币。 3. There were only decimal math problem on the quiz. 测验中只有十进位的数学题。 4. Britain converted to a decimal currency system in 1971. 英国于1971年改行十进制货币体系。 5. 0.3 is a decimal. 0.', '副词: decimally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('recognition', '[ˌrekəɡ\'nɪʃn]', 'n.赞誉,承认,重视,公认,赏识,识别', '1. Not until 1916 did the UMW finally win recognition from the anthracite operators 直到1916年，美国矿工联合会才终于得到无烟煤矿资方承认。 2. Not only are we at the forefront of electronics, but we\'ve received worldwide recognition for our advances in chemicals and engineering as well. 我们不仅处于电子技术的前沿,而且我们因在化工和工程领域的进展也得到世界范围的承认。 3. After 25 years the town centre had changed beyond all recognition. 25年过去了,市中心变得认不出来了。 4. My recognition of the face was immediate. 我一下子就认出那张面孔了。', '形容词: recognitory');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('deadly', '[\'dedli]', 'adj.致命的,势不两立的,死一般的,极度的,必定的', '1. Cancer is a deadly disease. 癌症是一种致命的疾病。 2. Fog is the sailor\'s deadly enemy. 雾是航海者最致命的敌人。 3. The accident subjected her to a deadly blow. 这次意外使她受到致命的打击。 4. The conference was deadly dull. 会议开得死气沉沉的。 5. Mary is finding life deadly monotonous . 玛丽感到生活非常单调。', '比较级: deadlier 最高级: deadliest 名词: deadliness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('verse', '[vɜːrs]', 'n.韵文,诗,诗节,诗句,诗篇', '1. There are four verses in each poem. 每首诗有四个诗节。 2. She wrote most of her poetry in blank verse. 她所写的诗大部分都是无韵诗。 3. Most of the scenes are written in verse, but some are in prose. 这场戏大部分内容是用韵文写成的,但也有一些是散文形式的 4. There are four verses in each poem. 每首诗有四个诗节。 5. It was in blank verse that she sang. 她以无韵诗体作诗。', '过去式: versed 过去分词: versed 现在分词: versing 第三人称单数: verses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('economical', '[ˌiːkə\'nɑːmɪkl]', 'adj.节约的,经济的', '1. She is an economical housekeeper and feeds her family cheaply. 她是一个节俭的家庭主妇，她全家的花销不大。 2. We are advocate economical life. 我们提倡俭朴的生活。 3. This is not an economical method of heating. 这不是一种经济的取暖方式。 4. She writes novels with economical style. 她以简练的风格写小说。', '副词: economically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('commemorate', '[kə\'meməreɪt]', 'vt.纪念', '1. A monument was built to commemorate the victory. 为了纪念胜利，建造了一座纪念碑。 2. Christmas commemorates the birth of Christ. 圣诞节是为了纪念耶酥的诞生。 3. They reared a monument to commemorate the great musician. 他们建立起一座纪念碑，纪念这位伟大的音乐家。 4. We celebrate this day to commemorate the brave soldiers. 我们庆祝这天，以纪念英勇的士兵。', '名词: commemorator 过去式: commemorated 过去分词: commemorated 现在分词: commemorating 第三人称单数: commemorates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('scrape', '[skreɪp]', 'n.刮,擦,擦痕,刮擦声,困境;vi.刮掉,擦掉,刮出刺耳声;vt.刮,擦,擦伤,挖成', '1. I must have scraped some of the paint off when I was parking the car. 我准是停放汽车的时候刮掉了一些油漆。 2. He bent over to scrape some dirt off his shoes. 他弯腰刮掉鞋子上的尘土。 3. Scrape your shoes on the door mat before you come in. 进屋前先在门口擦鞋垫上擦一擦鞋子。 4. He suffered a few cuts and scrapes. 他割破和擦伤了几个地方。', '过去式: scraped 过去分词: scraped 现在分词: scraping 第三人称单数: scrapes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('affiliate', '[ə\'fɪlieɪt]', 'v.(使...)加入,接受为会员', '1. It is an affiliate of the Red Cross. 它是红十字会的一个份子。 2. Do I get the product as part of the affiliate program? 我得到的附属产品作为节目? 3. I affiliate myself with their team to get more information on the share market. 我和他们组密切联系以获得更多股票市场的信息。 4. The Committee regrets that it cannot right now affiliate your group to their Society. 那个委员会很抱歉，不能马上将你们的团体并入他们的学会。 5. If we affiliate, we will have a better chance to win. 如果我们加入的话，赢的可能性更大。', '名词: affiliation 过去式: affiliated 过去分词: affiliated 现在分词: affiliating 第三人称单数: affiliates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('exposition', '[ˌekspə\'zɪʃn]', 'n.博览会,展览会,说明,曝露,[戏]展示部分,[音]呈示部', '1. They are going to hold an international exposition. 他们打算召开一次国际博览会。 2. So the West Lake Exposition has a long history. 那西湖博览会已有很长的历史了。 3. He entered a landscape painting in the Exposition. 他把一幅风景画送展览会展出。 4. The World Exposition is not the same as a trade fair, in which mainly governments and international organizations participate. 世博会不同于贸易展览会，贸易展览会主要是由政府和国际组织参加的。', '形容词: expositive 名词: expositor');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('novelty', '[\'nɑːvlti]', 'n.新颖,新奇,新鲜,新奇的事物', '1. The novelty of his surroundings soon wore off. 他对环境的新奇感不久就淡薄了。 2. The demand is for quality, variety and novelty. 现在需求的是质量、花式品种和新颖性。 3. I bought some novelties on the boardwalk. 我在海滨人行道上买了一些新颖的小玩意儿。 4. Upon the whole the novelty attracted him. 总的说来，这个新奇的事物吸引着他。', '名词复数: novelties');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('valid', '[\'vælɪd]', 'adj.[律]有效的,有根据的,正当的,正确的', '1. Please provide a valid screen name. 请输入有效的显示名。 2. A credit card is not a valid proof of identity. 银行发的支票保付卡不是有效的身份证明文件。 3. Whether or not you believe the lawsuit is fair or valid, it is vital that you act on the summons. 无论这起诉讼是否是公平的或者是有根据的，认真对待传票对当事人来说是至关重要的。 4. The values may be valid,but are not allowed contextually. 提供的值可能是合法的，但是在当前的上下文环境中不被允许。', '副词: validly 名词: validity');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cooperative', '[koʊ\'ɑːpərətɪv]', 'adj.合作的,协力的', '1. We found him friendly and cooperative. 我们感到他是友好的，乐于合作的。 2. They are trying to adopt a more cooperative posture. 他们正试图采取更为合作的态度。 3. The management would like to thank the staff for being so cooperative. 资方要感谢全体员工的通力合作。 4. The school was very cooperative when we made a film there. 我们到该校拍摄影片时，获得校方的大力协助。 5. They decided to set up a cooperative. 他们决定开办一家合作社。', '副词: cooperatively 名词: cooperativeness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('vein', '[veɪn]', 'n.血管,静脉,叶脉,翅脉,矿脉,纹理,性情,心绪;vt.使成脉络,象脉络般分布于', '1. The doctor injects glucose into the patient\'s vein. 医生把葡萄糖注射入病人的静脉。 2. The selection of a suitable vein model is the key for vein analysis. 摘要选用适用的纹理模型是进行纹理分析的关键。 3. Ginkgo biloba leaf petiole, is actually composed of many vein from the collection of vascular bundle group. 银杏叶的叶柄，实际上是由许多叶脉集合而成的维管束群。', '形容词: veinal 过去式: veined 过去分词: veined 现在分词: veining 第三人称单数: veins');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bypass', '[\'baɪpɑːs]', 'n.旁路;vt.设旁路,迂回', '1. If we bypass the town we\'ll miss all traffic. 我们绕城外走，就不会受交通拥挤之累了。 2. If we bypass the town we\'ll miss all the traffic. 如果我们绕过市区,我们就会避开所有的车辆。 3. You cannot bypass this question. 你不能回避这个问题。 4. He bypassed his colleagues on the board and went ahead with the deal. 他未征求董事会中同事的意见就做了这笔交易。 5. If we take the bypass we\'ll avoid the town centre. 我们走旁道，就能避开市镇的中心。', '过去式: bypassed 过去分词: bypassed 现在分词: bypassing 第三人称单数: bypasses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('alternate', '[\'ɔːltərnət]', 'adj.交替的,轮流的,预备的;v.交替,轮流,改变', '1. Sunny weather alternated with rain. 天气晴雨相间。 2. One should alternate work and relaxation. 工作和休息应交替进行。 3. We alternate in cleaning the room. 我们轮流打扫房间。 4. Meetings are held on alternate Thursdays. 每隔一个星期的星期四举行一次会议。 5. My alternate knows my role really well, she\'s almost better than me. 我的接替者对我的工作非常了解，她甚至比我都好。', '副词: alternately 名词: alternateness 过去式: alternated 过去分词: alternated 现在分词: alternating 第三人称单数: alternates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('shrub', '[ʃrʌb]', 'n.灌木,灌木丛', '1. A rose is a perennial shrub or vine. 玫瑰是一种常青灌木或藤本植物。 2. There are many different kinds of shrub. 灌木有许多不同的种类。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('internal', '[ɪn\'tɜːrnl]', 'adj.内在的,国内的', '1. They were opposed to foreign involvement in their internal affairs. 他们反对外国参与他们本国内政。 2. He worked in internal trade. 他的工作是做国内贸易。 3. We should make an internal inquiry to find out who is responsible for the it. 我们应进行内部调查,找出对此事承担责任的人。 4. She\'s been having some internal problems. 她一直有些内科疾病。', '副词: internally 名词: internality');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('electricity', '[ɪˌlek\'trɪsəti]', 'n.电流,电,电学', '1. The electricity failure paralyzed the water supply. 停电使水供应陷于瘫痪。 2. The interruption of electricity made us unable to do anything. 电力的中断让我们什么也不能做。 3. While I was cooking supper the electricity went off. 我正在做晚饭时停电了。 4. Both students have made quite a few experiments on electricity. 这两个学生都做了不少电学实验。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dwell', '[dwel]', 'vi.居住,踌躇', '1. He decided to dwell on our island. 他决定到我们的岛上居住。 2. I own two flats where I used to dwell alternately. 我拥有两个居所并一直交替地居住。 3. How his words dwell in my mind! 他的一席话在我的脑海里经久难忘。 4. They dwelled in joy. 他们沉浸于欢乐之中。', '名词: dweller 过去式: dwelt/dwelled 过去分词: dwelt/dwelled 现在分词: dwelling 第三人称单数: dwells');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('liability', '[ˌlaɪə\'bɪləti]', 'n.责任,义务,倾向,债务,负债,与assets相对', '1. He admitted his liability for the accident. 他承认自己对这起事故应负责任。 2. The judge exempted them from all liability in these matters. 法官免除了他们在这些事上的所有责任和义务。 3. If your liabilities exceed your assets, you may go bankrupt. 如果你所负的债超过你的资产，你就会破产。 4. But the court ruled in favour of Wilson Parking due to a liability disclaimer printed at the entrance. 但法院统治了倾向于威尔逊停放由于责任声明列印在入口。', '名词复数: liabilities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('scrub', '[skrʌb]', 'v.洗擦,使(气)净化;n.洗擦,擦洗者,矮树,灌木,丛林地,矮小人(或动物);adj.次等的,矮小的,临时凑合的', '1. Give that floor a good hard scrub. 使劲擦洗一下那地板。 2. The country is covered in scrub. 这一地区为矮灌木丛覆盖。 3. We found the animal on a scrub hill. 我们在一个灌木丛生的丘陵上找到这动物。 4. Although she scrubbed the old pot thoroughly, she could not make it look completely clean. 虽然她彻底地用力擦洗那只旧壶，但她无法把它完全洗干净。', '形容词: scrubbable 过去式: scrubbed 过去分词: scrubbed 现在分词: scrubbing 第三人称单数: scrubs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('urban', '[\'ɜːrbən]', 'adj.城市的,市内的', '1. In some developing countries more and more people are migrating to urban areas. 在某些发展中的国家,越来越多的人向市区迁移。 2. The quality of urban living has been damaged by excessive noise levels. 城市生活的质量已被过度的噪音所破坏。 3. You can find out many advantages in urban life. 你会发现都市生活中有许多便利之处。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('legislation', '[ˌledʒɪs\'leɪʃn]', 'n.立法,法律的制定(或通过)', '1. The new legislation is highly discriminatory. 新的法案，有许多地方厚此薄彼。 2. We protect the interests of investors by the legislation in effect. 我们根据现行法律保护投资者的利益。 3. The legislation was made retrospective. 该项法规具有追溯效力。 4. The government will introduce legislation to restrict the sale of firearms. 政府将制定法规限制枪支出售。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bulletin', '[\'bʊlətɪn]', 'n.公告,报告', '1. The mid-day bulletin had not mentioned any definite area. 中午的公报没说具体的地点。 2. Here is a letter adapted from DEAR ABBY, Philadelphia Bulletin, March9,1973. 这里摘登一封＇亲爱的爱毕＇的回信，刊登在一九七三年三月九日的＇费城公报＇上。 3. I finally bought the Bulletin of Ordnance Information. 我终于买到了《兵器情报通报》(期刊)。 4. The radio bulletin warned of the typhoon. 收音机新闻快报发布了台风警报。 5. The company bulletined the staff to attend the meeting. 公司用公告通知全体员工参加会议。', '过去式: bulletined 过去分词: bulletined 现在分词: bulletining 第三人称单数: bulletins');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mob', '[mɑːb]', 'n.(集合词)暴徒,乌合之众,(盗贼等的)一群;v.成群暴动,聚众滋扰', '1. The mob rampaged through the village. 这伙暴徒在村中横冲直撞。 2. The speaker was roughly handled by the mob. 演说者受到暴民的粗暴对待。 3. A mob of youths had been dogging me for some time. 一段时间以来一伙年轻人一直在尾随着我。 4. More sinister is the involvement of the heavy mob. 更危险的是众多无知民众的卷入。 5. Pop stars are always moaning about being mobbed by their fans. 流行歌星总是抱怨他们受到歌迷的包围。', '形容词: mobbish 副词: mobbishly 过去式: mobbed 过去分词: mobbed 现在分词: mobbing 第三人称单数: mobs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('furniture', '[\'fɜːrnɪtʃər]', 'n.家具,设备,储藏物', '1. We will buy some furniture for our new house. 我们得给我们的新房子买些家具。 2. This old table is a valuable piece of furniture. 这张旧桌子是一件很珍贵的家具。 3. The antique furniture was made in 1700. 这件古老的家具是1700年制造的。 4. Children\'s furniture must withstand kicks and blows. 孩子用的家具必须经得起拳打脚踢。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('humanity', '[hjuː\'mænəti]', 'n.人性,人类,博爱,仁慈', '1. Such a man is a stain to humanity. 这种人是人类的耻辱。 2. How can you turn aside from suffering humanity? 面对受苦受难的人类，你怎么能毫无同情心呢？ 3. Humanity is a mixture of good and bad qualities. 人性是善与恶的混合体. 4. He treated the prisoners with humanity. 他人道地对待俘虏。', '名词复数: humanities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('conception', '[kən\'sepʃn]', 'n.观念,概念', '1. I have no conception of what you mean. 我想不出你的意思是什么。 2. His conception of human nature is skewed. 他对人性的看法带有偏见。 3. That the earth is flat is an erroneous concept. 认为地球是平的观念是错的。 4. He\'s got a pretty strange conception of friendship. 他对友谊有一种非常独特的见解。', '形容词: conceptional 副词: conceptively');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('yield', '[jiːld]', 'v.出产,生长,生产;vi.(～to)屈服,屈从;n.产量,收益', '1. The village abounds in fields that yield many bushels of corn. 那个村庄到处都是盛产玉米的农田。 2. The combined investment is expected to yield $5,000 in the first year. 第一年该总投资有望获利5000美元。 3. We\' ve already made it clear that we will not yield to pressure. 我们已经表明我们不会屈服于压力。 4. The shelf is beginning to yield under that heavy weight. 架子被那么大的重量压得弯了下去。 5. So if the share price rises and the dividend does not, then the yield falls. 因此，如果股份上涨而股息不变，收益就下跌。', '名词: yielder 过去式: yielded 过去分词: yielded 现在分词: yielding 第三人称单数: yields');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('privacy', '[\'praɪvəsi]', 'n.独处而不受干扰,秘密', '1. Everyone has his own privacy. 每个人都有自己的隐私。 2. I object to our privacy being invaded. 我反对我们的隐私权受到侵害。 3. He was sentenced to be guilty of intrusion upon my privacy. 他因侵犯我的隐私权被判有罪。 4. I tell you this in strict privacy. 我极秘密地告诉你这件事。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('harmony', '[\'hɑːrməni]', 'n.协调,融洽', '1. An enterprise should be full of fairness and harmony. 一个企业内部应该充满公平与和谐。 2. Their life is a natural harmony. 他们的生活是一种自然的和谐。 3. There was not much harmony in international affairs during those years. 那些年国际事态不很协调。 4. Almost unconsciously she dressed in harmony with this note of simplicity. 她简直不自觉的打扮得跟这朴素的调子很调和。', '名词复数: harmonies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('appropriate', '[ə\'proʊpriət]', 'adj.适当的', '1. You will be informed of the details at the appropriate time. 在适当的时候将把详情告诉你。 2. It is not easy to choose clothes which are appropriate to your beautiful figure. 选择与你漂亮的体型相称的服装是不容易的。 3. She again entreated his forgiveness for so selfishly appropriating the cottage 她为自己这么自私地占用了这座农舍而再次恳求他的原谅。 4. The government has appropriated some funds for education. 政府拨出了一些款项用作教育基金。', '形容词: appropriative 副词: appropriately 名词: appropriateness 过去式: appropriated 过去分词: appropriated 现在分词: appropriating 第三人称单数: appropriates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('oak', '[oʊk]', 'n.[植]橡树,橡木;adj.橡木制的', '1. The birds nested in the oak tree. 鸟在橡树上筑巢。 2. Pine wood saws more easily than oak. 松树要比橡树容易锯。 3. The wine is left to mature in oak barrels. 葡萄酒在橡木桶中陈酿。 4. There was a triptych of pale oak. 有一个浅灰色的三联橡木雕刻。', '形容词: oaken');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('marshal', '[\'mɑːrʃl]', 'n.元帅,典礼官,执行官,司仪官;vt.整顿,配置,汇集;vi.排列,集合', '1. The marshal rode at the head of the parade. 典礼官在检阅队伍的前面骑马行进。 2. The idea is to marshal the body\'s own immune system to fight cancer. 这个思路是重新配置机体自身的免疫系统来对抗肿瘤。', '名词: marshalcy 过去式: marshaled/marshalled 过去分词: marshaled/marshalled 现在分词: marshaling/marshalling 第三人称单数: marshals/marshals');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('superiority', '[suːˌpɪri\'ɔːrəti]', 'n.优越,高傲', '1. This is the only way to demonstrate the superiority of socialism. 只有这样，才能表明社会主义的优越性。 2. Socialist democracy enjoys strong vitality and superiority. 社会主义民主政治具有强大的生命力和优越性。 3. Your army has numerical superiority over theirs. 与他们相比你们的军队占有人数优势。 4. He won the bout by great superiority. 他以绝对优势赢了这场比赛。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('disregard', '[ˌdɪsrɪ\'ɡɑːrd]', 'v.不理漠视;n.漠视,忽视', '1. We cannot disregard his coming late to work so often. 对他上班经常迟到,我们不能不管。 2. He doesn\'t disregard the footnotes. 他并没有不注意脚注。 3. He disregarded his doctor\'s advice. 他无视医生的劝告。 4. You can\'t just disregard the security problem. 你可不能忽视安全问题。 5. The official has shown a total disregard for the needs of the poor. 这个官员对穷人的需求表现出完全漠视的态度。', '形容词: disregardful 名词: disregarder 过去式: disregarded 过去分词: disregarded 现在分词: disregarding 第三人称单数: disregards');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('certainty', '[\'sɜːrtnti]', 'n.确定,确实的事情', '1. I can say with certainty that this is true. 我可以很确定地说这是真实的。 2. Too great certainty destroys certainty itself. 过于确定就会破坏确定本身。', '名词复数: certainties');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('appeal', '[ə\'piːl]', 'n.请求,呼吁,上诉,吸引力,要求;vi.求助,诉请,要求;vt.控诉', '1. Their appeal for help went unheeded. 他们求助的呼吁未受到注意。 2. He made one last appeal to his father to forgive him. 他最後一次恳求父亲宽恕他。 3. His appeal to a higher court was set aside. 他的上诉被驳回。 4. The judge rejected the appeal made by the prisoner for a new trial. 法官驳回了犯人提出重新审理的上诉。 5. The police appealed to the crowd not to panic. 警方向群众呼吁不要惊慌。', '形容词: appealable 名词: appealability 过去式: appealed 过去分词: appealed 现在分词: appealing 第三人称单数: appeals');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('vacant', '[\'veɪkənt]', 'adj.空的,空白的,空灵的,头脑空虚的,神情茫然的,空闲的,空缺的', '1. Absence of occupation is not rest, a mind quite vacant is a mind distress. 无所事事不是休息，十分空虚的心灵是痛苦的心灵。 2. The sky remains infinitely vacant for earth there to build its heaven with dreams. 天空总是无限空虚地用梦在大地构筑天堂。 3. He was appointed to the vacant post. 他被委派填补那空缺。 4. There are some vacant offices on the third floor. 四楼有几间空著的办公室。', '副词: vacantly 名词: vacantness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('standpoint', '[\'stændpɔɪnt]', 'n.立场,观点', '1. This is far away from the viewer\'s standpoint. 这是远离观众的立场。 2. We only look at things based on a certain standpoint. 我们所有的人只是站在某一立场来看待事物。 3. Let\'s look at this from a historical standpoint. 让我们从历史的观点来看待这一切。 4. Don\'t foist your standpoint on me. 不要把你的观点强加于我。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('assimilate', '[ə\'sɪməleɪt]', 'v.吸收', '1. The USA has assimilated people from many different countries. 美国已经同化了许多来自不同国家的人。 2. Europeans and Jews do not readily assimilate. 欧洲人和犹太人不易同化。 3. Immigrants often want to assimilate quickly. 移民经常想迅速同化。 4. Some foods are assimilated more easily than others. 有些食物比另一些食物容易吸收。', '名词: assimilator 过去式: assimilated 过去分词: assimilated 现在分词: assimilating 第三人称单数: assimilates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('instruct', '[ɪn\'strʌkt]', 'vt.教,教导,命令,指示,通知', '1. His uncle instructed him in French. 他的叔叔教他法语。 2. Don\'t instruct your secretary to say you are out when you are in. 不要教你的秘书在你在的时候说不在。 3. It does not pertain to the young to instruct their elders. 年轻人不应该对老年人发号施令。 4. Please instruct me how to do my work. 请指导一下我如何工作。', '过去式: instructed 过去分词: instructed 现在分词: instructing 第三人称单数: instructs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('supervise', '[\'suːpərvaɪz]', 'v.监督,管理,指导', '1. I supervised the workers loading the lorry. 我监督工人把货物装上卡车。 2. The chief clerk supervises the work of the department. 文书组长负责监督该部门的工作。 3. She wants to supervise the cosmetics shop. 她想自己管理那间化妆品店。 4. How many people did you supervise on your last job? 你的上一份工作需要管理多少人?', '过去式: supervised 过去分词: supervised 现在分词: supervising 第三人称单数: supervises');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('oppress', '[ə\'pres]', 'vt.压迫,压抑', '1. Cares oppressed his spirits. 忧虑使他心情抑郁。 2. The king oppressed his people with terrible taxes and punishments. 国王以苛捐杂税和严刑来压迫人民。 3. Free governments do not oppress their people or attack other free nations. 自由政府不会压迫其人民或者攻击其他自由国家。', '名词: oppressor 过去式: oppressed 过去分词: oppressed 现在分词: oppressing 第三人称单数: oppresses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('anxiety', '[æŋ\'zaɪəti]', 'n.忧虑,焦急,渴望,热望', '1. It proved difficult to disguise his anxiety. 他的焦虑难以掩饰。 2. They show great anxiety concerning their retirement allowance. 他们对自己的养老金问题显得十分焦虑。 3. This has caused us much anxiety. 这事使我们极为担心。 4. Some anxiety still lurked in her mind. 她心里还暗暗地有点不放心。', '名词复数: anxieties');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reservation', '[ˌrezər\'veɪʃn]', 'n.保留,(旅馆房间等)预定,预约', '1. I\'d like to make a reservation. 我想订票。 2. I\'ll arrive late, but please keep my reservation. 我会晚一点到达，请保留所预订的房间。 3. Do you require a deposit to confirm a reservation? 确定预定的旅馆房间要不要付定金？ 4. They accepted the proposal without reservation. 他们无保留地接受了这个建议。', '名词: reservationist');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('command', '[kə\'mænd]', 'n.命令,掌握,司令部;v.命令,指挥,克制,支配,博得,俯临', '1. He growled a command to her to stop. 他咆哮着命令她停下来。 2. The company commander roared his command. 连长高声发布命令。 3. He has a hundred men under his command. 他指挥一百个人。 4. The army is under the king\'s direct command. 军队由国王直接统率。 5. The general commanded his men to attack the city. 将军下令部下攻城。', '过去式: commanded 过去分词: commanded 现在分词: commanding 第三人称单数: commands');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('alliance', '[ə\'laɪəns]', 'n.联盟,联合', '1. They broke up the alliance. 他们中止了联盟。 2. The alliance has been forged in the crucible of war. 这个联盟经受了战争的严峻考验。 3. Gerard required a different alliance to aid his career. 则杰拉就需要一个不同的联姻来帮助他的事业。 4. The two countries made an alliance. 两国结盟。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('chord', '[kɔːrd]', 'n.弦,和音,情绪;n.[解]腱', '1. He is replacing the broken chord of his violin. 他正在更换小提琴上那根断了的弦。 2. Love is a chord in life, not a solo alone. 爱是人生的和弦，不是孤独的独奏曲。 3. There are two naturals in this chord. 这一和弦中有两个本位音。 4. Her speech struck a deep chord in my heart. 她的话深深地拨动了我的心弦。', '过去式: chorded 过去分词: chorded 现在分词: chording 第三人称单数: chords');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('metropolitan', '[ˌmetrə\'pɑːlɪtən]', 'adj.首都的,主要都市的,大城市', '1. Metropolitan residents are used to fast rhythm. 大都市的居民习惯于快节奏。 2. He can not adjust himself to the pace of metropolitan life. 他适应不了都市生活的节奏。 3. She left the small island and became famous in metropolitan France. 她离开小岛而在法国的大都市中成名。 4. Metropolitan residents are used to fast rhythm. 大都市的居民习惯于快节奏。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('accomplish', '[ə\'kɑːmplɪʃ]', 'vt.完成,达到,实现', '1. I have accomplished a great deal in the last few months. 在过去几个月里，我完成了相当多的工作。 2. The prediction was literally accomplished. 这个预言确实实现了。 3. The role of a judge is to accomplish fairness. 法官的职责是实现公平。', '形容词: accomplishable 名词: accomplisher 过去式: accomplished 过去分词: accomplished 现在分词: accomplishing 第三人称单数: accomplishes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('acid', '[\'æsɪd]', 'n.[化]酸,<俚>迷幻药;adj.酸的,讽刺的,刻薄的', '1. Acids react with bases to form salts. 酸与碱反应生成盐。 2. The acid burnt a hole in the carpet. 酸把地毯烧了个洞。 3. The acid has burnt a hole in my jacket. 这种酸把我的上衣烧了一个窟窿。 4. The acid in the rain slowly ate away at the stone wall. 雨水中的酸性物质慢慢侵蚀着石墙。 5. Add more sugar if it tastes too acid. 如果尝着太酸的话就多放点糖。', '副词: acidly 名词: acidness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('recur', '[rɪ\'kɜːr]', 'vi.复发,重现,再来', '1. What do you want to make it recur? 如果你能选择的话，你希望让什么重现？ 2. The best way to ensure quality is to write tests that validate data and algorithms and verify that prior mistakes do not recur. 确保质量的最佳方法是编写验证数据和算法并确认以前的错误不再重现的测试。 3. Our patient was successfully treated with diuretics, and the chylothorax did not recur during the following 12 months under a sodium-restricted diet. 此病患成功地以利尿剂治疗且合并低钠饮食的控制下，经一年的追踪，乳糜胸并未再发生。', '名词: recurrence 过去式: recurred 过去分词: recurred 现在分词: recurring 第三人称单数: recurs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('score', '[skɔː]', 'n.得分,乐谱,抓痕,二十,终点线,刻痕,帐目,起跑线;vt.把...记下,刻划,划线,获得,评价;vi.记分,刻痕,得分', '1. Hughes scored two goals before half-time. 休斯在上半场进了两个球. 2. The army continued to score successes in the south. 军队在南方不断取得胜利。 3. They scored the floor-boards by pushing furniture about. 他们推动家具 4. could you please score my name off? 请把我的名字从名单中划掉好吗? 5. I recorded the score in a notebook. 我在笔记本上记下了分数。 6. The home team has yet to score. 主队还没有得分.', '名词: scorer 过去式: scored 过去分词: scored 现在分词: scoring 第三人称单数: scores');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('profound', '[prə\'faʊnd]', 'adj.深刻的,意义深远的,渊博的,造诣深的', '1. Beauty is but superficial while mind is profound. 美貌是肤浅的,而思想才是深邃的。 2. I was impressed by his devotion to his research but I didn\'t have the slightest interest in his profound theories. 给我留下了很深印象,但我对他那些深奥的理论丝毫不感兴趣。 3. Our professor is a man of profound learning. 我们的教授是一个学识渊博的人。 4. Reading makes a full man, meditation a profound man, discourse a clear man. 阅读培养学问丰富的人,思考培养见识深刻的人,演讲培养思路清晰的人。', '副词: profoundly 比较级: profounder 最高级: profoundest 名词: profoundness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('friction', '[\'frɪkʃn]', 'n.摩擦,摩擦力', '1. Constant friction wore out the heels of my shoes. 不断的摩擦磨损了我的鞋跟。 2. Matches are lighted by friction. 火柴由摩擦而生火。 3. Friction lowers the efficiency of a machine. 摩擦减低机器的效率。 4. Friction causes a rolling ball to stop finally. 摩擦力使滚动的球最终停了下来。', '形容词: frictional 副词: frictionally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('impatient', '[ɪm\'peɪʃnt]', 'adj.不耐烦的,急躁的,不耐心的', '1. He tends to snap at people when he gets impatient. 他一不耐烦的时候就对人没有好声气。 2. The impatient teacher slapped the student. 这位不耐烦的老师掌击了学生。 3. Your impatient self clearly suffers from a similar fixed cost of carrying out subtraction. 你身上那个急躁的自我，显然在实施减法时承受着类似的固定成本。', '副词: impatiently');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('critical', '[\'krɪtɪkl]', 'adj.评论的,鉴定的,批评的,危急的,临界的', '1. It is difficult enough to be critical of our own mistakes. 对我们自己的错误采取批评的态度确实非常困难。 2. She viewed the findings with a critical eye. 她以批评的眼光看待这些研究结果。 3. Our clients are very critical on quality. 我们的客户对商品的质量是很挑剔的。 4. Joint strategic maneuver is critical. 联合战略行动是决定性的。 5. These materials become quite soft and flexible above critical temperature. 这些材料在临界温度以上变得十分柔软和易于弯曲。', '副词: critically 名词: criticalness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ultimate', '[\'ʌltɪmət]', 'adj.最后的,最终的,根本的;n.最终', '1. Hard work is the ultimate source of success. 努力工作是成功之本。 2. This had been an ultimate issue. 这个问题是个原则性的问题。 3. GUPTA And the Ironman is the ultimate competition. 甘普塔铁人是一个极限的竞争。 4. I believe that I will bring my ultimate competitiveness in the advanced business management into full play with the guidance of professional teachers. 我认为在精英的师资力量的指导下我将在高级商业管理方面发挥我极限的竞争力。 5. Such behavior is the ultimate in idiocy. 这样的行为愚蠢透顶。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('brace', '[breɪs]', 'n.支柱,带子,振作精神;vt.支住,撑牢,振作起来,奋起;adj.曲柄的;v.支持', '1. It is urgent that we brace against hurricanes. 我们必须做好防飓风的准备。 2. The struts are firmly braced. 那些支柱上得很牢固。 3. She braced herself against the wall. 她靠在墙上。 4. He faced the angry crowd, his arms folded, his legs braced. 面对着愤怒的人群,他抱紧双臂,绷紧双腿。 5. The odor of souls is a brace to the walls. 灵魂的气息是这些砖墙的支柱。', '过去式: braced 过去分词: braced 现在分词: bracing 第三人称单数: braces');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('diminish', '[dɪ\'mɪnɪʃ]', 'v.(使)减少,(使)变小', '1. We should try to diminish the cost of production. 我们应尽力减少生产成本。 2. His illness diminished his health. 疾病侵蚀了他的健康。 3. He likes to diminish the skills of others. 他喜欢贬低别人的技能。 4. The amount of water in the pond will diminish as the dry season continues. 如果旱季还持续下去，池塘中的水量将减少。', '形容词: diminishable 名词: diminishment 过去式: diminished 过去分词: diminished 现在分词: diminishing 第三人称单数: diminishes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reference', '[\'refrəns]', 'n.提及,涉及,参考,参考书目,证明书(人),介绍信(人)', '1. This book is for reference only. 这本书仅供参考。 2. This frame of reference will be determined by the limitations on the rational man\'s knowledge. 这个参照系统决定于理性人知识的限制。 3. Full reference citations are available on the readings page. 全部参考资料的出处可以在阅读资料那页找到。 4. Can we contact your references? 我可以与你的推荐人联系吗? 5. Paraphrasing is not direct quotation, but you still need to reference it. 意译不是直接引用', '形容词: referential 副词: referentially 名词: referencer 过去式: referenced 过去分词: referenced 现在分词: referencing 第三人称单数: references');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reclaim', '[rɪ\'kleɪm]', 'vt.要求归还,收回,开垦', '1. After he stopped paying the hire purchase installment, the finance company tried to reclaim his car. 在他停止支付租购分期付款后，该金融公司试图收回他的汽车。 2. You may be entitled to reclaim some of the tax you paid last year. 你或许有权要求退回去年你交付的部分税金。 3. Their daily work is to reclaim rubber from old tyres. 他们的日常工作是用旧轮胎再生橡胶。 4. It is incumbent on me to reclaim him. 劝他改过是我义不容辞的义务。', '形容词: reclaimable 名词: reclaimant 过去式: reclaimed 过去分词: reclaimed 现在分词: reclaiming 第三人称单数: reclaims');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tow', '[toʊ]', 'n.拖,拖曳所用之绳,麻的粗纤维;vt.拖,曳,牵引;vi.拖行,被拖带', '1. We have to tow that car to the nearest garage. 我们不得不把汽车拖到最近的修车厂。 2. The ship needed two tugs to tow it into port. 这艘船需用两艘拖船把它拖进港。 3. The broken-down car was taken in tow by a lorry. 一辆卡车拉着一辆坏了的汽车。 4. When she sits at the beach, Greenpeace tries to tow her back into the ocean. 你妈妈胖到她座在沙滩上时，绿色和平组织会尝试著把她拉回大海里。 5. My car\'s broken down; will you give me a tow? 我的车抛锚了，能用你的车给我拖一拖吗？', '形容词: towable 名词: tower 过去式: towed 过去分词: towed 现在分词: towing 第三人称单数: tows');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mock', '[mɑːk]', 'v.嘲笑,骗,挫败,嘲弄;adj.假的;n.嘲弄,模仿,仿制品', '1. He went to church only to mock. 他到教堂去只是为了嘲弄宗教。 2. We should not mock at other people\'s religious beliefs. 我们不应该嘲笑别人的宗教信仰。 3. I have a pet monkey which attempts to mock all my actions. 我养了一只猴子当宠物，它试图模仿我所有的动作。 4. His bully make a mock of all the fine thing he say about kindness to others. 他那恃强欺弱的行为对于他所说的待人友善的漂亮言词是一个嘲弄。 5. She handed him the envelope with mock solemnity. 她装出一副郑重其事的样子，把信封交给他。', '副词: mockingly 名词: mocker 过去式: mocked 过去分词: mocked 现在分词: mocking 第三人称单数: mocks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('border', '[\'bɔːrdər]', 'n.边界,国界,边,边沿,边境;vt.与...接壤,接近;v.接壤', '1. We have a herbaceous border round our garden. 我们的花园四周种有草本植物。 2. A series of provocations led up to the border war. 一系列的挑衅事件导致了边境战争的发生。 3. Enemy troops raided our border areas. 敌军对我边境地区进行袭击。 4. I lost a white handkerchief with a blue border. 我丢了一块带蓝色花边的白手绢。 5. France borders Germany along parts of the Rhine. 法国沿莱茵河部分河段与德国接壤。 6. Some of his statements are so incorrect that they border on fraudulence. 他的某些说法非常不正确以致近乎欺诈。', '名词: borderer 过去式: bordered 过去分词: bordered 现在分词: bordering 第三人称单数: borders');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('clutch', '[klʌtʃ]', 'v.抓住,攫住;n.离合器', '1. The boy clutched the marbles and ran away. 那男孩一把抢去弹珠便逃之夭夭。 2. The child clutched his toy. 那个孩子紧抓着他的玩具不放。 3. John jumped up to clutch at the branch,but missed. 约翰跳起来试图抓住那树枝，但是没有成功。 4. It is useless to clutch at a straw. 抓救命稻草是无济于事的。 5. The eagle flew away with a rabbit in the clutch of its claws. 鹰用爪子紧紧抓住一只野兔，飞走了。 6. He\'s won a whole clutch of awards. 他获得一大堆奖。 7. Tmac is a choker and will never be able to get it done during clutch time. 麦迪就像一条围巾，在关键的时候很难从脖子上取下来。', '过去式: clutched 过去分词: clutched 现在分词: clutching 第三人称单数: clutches');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('supplement', '[\'sʌplɪmənt]', 'n.补遗,补充,附录,增刊;v.补充', '1. It comes out each week and it has a magazine supplement. 每周出版一期，还附有杂志增刊。 2. The upset supplement supplier went up with the puppet to the upper room for supper. 心烦意乱的增刊供给者与傀儡一起到上面的房间吃晚餐。 3. The money I got was a useful supplement to my ordinary income. 我得到的那笔钱是很管用的外快。 4. Man\'s work is rather the needful supplement to himself than the outcome of it. 一个人的工作更多地是他自身的必要补充,而非这种补充的结果。 5. She gives private lessons to supplement her income. 她给私人授课以贴补收入。', '形容词: supplementary 名词: supplementarity 过去式: supplemented 过去分词: supplemented 现在分词: supplementing 第三人称单数: supplements');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('stimulus', '[\'stɪmjuləs]', 'n.刺激物,促进因素,刺激,刺激', '1. One wants the stimulus of sympathy. 一个人总需要趣味相投、志同道合的朋友互相鼓励。 2. The nutrient in the soil acts as a stimulus to growth. 土壤中的养分能促进植物生长。 3. Her words of praise were a stimulus for people to work harder. 她赞扬的话鼓舞人们工作更努力。', '名词复数: stimuli');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('naive', '[naɪ\'iːv]', 'adj.天真的', '1. He derides her naive attitude. 他嘲弄她天真的态度。 2. Children always ask naive questions. 小孩子总问天真的问题。 3. This theory was intended to deceive naive people. 这一理论旨在欺骗天真群众。 4. The politician made a naive decision. 这个政治家做了一个幼稚的决定。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('attach', '[ə\'tætʃ]', 'vt.缚上,系上,贴上;v.配属,隶属于', '1. I attach a copy of my notes for your information. 我附上笔记一份供你参考。 2. In confirmation hereof we attach a bank statement. 为作这方面的确认我们附上银行结单。 3. Please attach these labels to your hand luggages. 请把这些标签系在您的手提行李上。 4. Please attach your business card below or fill up the information. 推荐人请在下面框中贴上您的名片,如不贴名片,则请详细填写框中各项。', '形容词: attachable 名词: attachment 过去式: attached 过去分词: attached 现在分词: attaching 第三人称单数: attaches');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('stability', '[stə\'bɪləti]', 'n.稳定性', '1. The government has taken a measure to maintain the stability of prices. 政府已经采取了措施以确保物价稳定。 2. The question of stability of an equilibrium is very important. 一个平衡点的稳定性问题是非常重要的。', '名词复数: stabilities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('inland', '[ˌɪn\'lænd]', 'adj.内陆的,国内的;adv.在内地,向内地;n.内地', '1. Chongqing in his plan is to be an inland Shanghai. 在他的计划里，重庆要成为内陆的上海。 2. Sea winds that blow inland from the west are warmed by a current of warm water that flows through the Pacific Ocean. 从太平洋来的温暖的洋流使得从西吹过内陆的海风变得温暖。 3. We spent a week by the coast before going inland. 在去内陆前，我们在海边住了一个星期。 4. Stockell didn\'t get very far inland that morning. 那天早晨，斯托克并未深入内陆多远。', '名词: inlander');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('distort', '[dɪ\'stɔːrt]', 'vt.弄歪(嘴脸等),扭曲,歪曲(真理、事实等),误报', '1. The reporter distorted the facts. 记者们歪曲了事实。 2. How dare he distort the facts so brazenly! 他怎么敢如此肆无忌惮地歪曲事实！ 3. The government was accused of having systematically distorted the protester\'s case. 政府因为有计划地歪曲抗议者的观点而受到责难。 4. This journalist distorted the spokesman\'s remarks. 这名记者曲解了该发言人的话。 5. The bias of a reporter can easily distort the news. 记者的偏见很容易歪曲新闻的报导。', '名词: distorter 过去式: distorted 过去分词: distorted 现在分词: distorting 第三人称单数: distorts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rap', '[ræp]', 'n.叩击,轻拍,轻敲,斥责;vt.敲,拍,厉声说出,斥责,使着迷;vi.敲击,交谈;abbr.[军]RocketAssistedProjectile,火箭助推炮弹', '1. There is a light rap at the door. 有轻轻的敲门声。 2. He took a bad rap on the head when he fell. 他跌倒时头被猛撞了一下。 3. Louise got a bum rap for taking sides with Richard. 路易斯因为偏袒理查德而受到责骂。 4. The bank clerk got a rap on the knuckles for his carelessness. 那个银行职员因为粗心大意而受到责骂。 5. The chairman rapped on the table for order. 主席敲击桌子以维持秩序。', '过去式: rapped 过去分词: rapped 现在分词: rapping 第三人称单数: raps');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('inferior', '[ɪn\'fɪriər]', 'adj.下等的,下级的,差的,次的,自卑的,劣等的', '1. These people occupy an inferior position in local society. 这些人在当地社会居于下等地位。 2. Captain is an inferior rank to major. 上尉是低于少校的一个官阶 3. A cheaper camera is not always inferior to a more expensive one. 廉价照相机的质量并总不比昂贵的差。 4. They never sell inferior goods. 他们从不销售次货。 5. A gentleman should always be civil, even to his inferiors. 有教养的人应该一直很有礼貌，甚至对待下属也一样。', '名词: inferiority');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cancer', '[\'kænsər]', 'n.癌,毒瘤', '1. He was afflicted with cancer. 他患了癌症。 2. The patient finally died from cancer. 那位病人最终死于癌症。 3. He\'s got a cancer in his liver. 他得了肝癌。 4. The oncologist invented a new kind of interferon to prevent cancer. 那位肿瘤学家发明了一种可以预防癌症的干扰素。 5. I\'m a Cancer and my brother is a Leo. 我是巨蟹座，弟弟是狮子座。', '形容词: cancerous');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hurricane', '[\'hɜːrəkən]', 'n.飓风,狂风', '1. The hurricane destroyed the whole village. 飓风把整个村子都毁掉了。 2. The hurricane screamed outside. 外面飓风呼啸著。 3. The hurricane has a speed of 73 miles per hour. 飓风每小时73英里。 4. The radio alerted the citizens to prepare for the hurricane. 电台警告市民们作好预防暴风准备。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('foam', '[foʊm]', 'n.泡沫,水沫,泡沫材料,泡沫橡皮,泡沫塑料;vi.起泡沫,冒汗水,吐白沫;vt.使起泡沫', '1. The sea was flecked with foam. 大海上涌起点点泡沫。 2. Foam rubber provides good insulation. 泡沫橡胶隔绝性能良好。 3. The fire extinguisher is filled with chemical foam. 这个灭火器充满了化学泡沫。 4. When the horse had finished the race, its sides were wet with foam. 这匹马结束比赛时，它的脊背被汗水湿透了。 5. When he poured the warm beer, it foam up out of the glass. 当他倒鲜啤酒时，啤酒泛起泡沫从杯中流了出来。', '过去式: foamed 过去分词: foamed 现在分词: foaming 第三人称单数: foams');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('relevant', '[\'reləvənt]', 'adj.有关的,相应的', '1. A paper relevant to this research was published by him. 与本研究相关的一篇论文是他发表的。 2. Have you heard of the relevant report? 你听说过相关的报道吗? 3. My next conclusion is more relevant. 我的另一个结论更切题。 4. Portraits of people will draw readers\'attention, especially if the images are relevant and tell a story. 人物肖像可以吸引读者的注意,当图像切题并在讲述一个故事时更是如此。', '副词: relevantly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('convert', '[kən\'vɜːrt]', 'n.皈依者;vt.使转变,转换...,使...改变信仰', '1. The solar cell can convert the energy of sunlight into electric energy. 太阳能电池能把阳光的能量转化为电能。 2. The old barn we bought to convert into flats was practically tumbling down. 那个旧谷仓我们买下想改建住房的，实际上已经快塌了。 3. My mother has converted to Catholicism. 我母亲已转而信仰天主教。 4. Coal can be converted to gas. 煤可以转化成煤气。 5. He is a recent convert to Christianity. 他最近改信基督教了。', '过去式: converted 过去分词: converted 现在分词: converting 第三人称单数: converts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('attract', '[ə\'trækt]', 'vt.吸引;vi.有吸引力,引起注意', '1. The flower show attracted large crowds this year. 今年的花展吸引了大批观众。 2. She gave a quiet cough to attract my attention. 她轻轻地咳了一声好引起我注意。 3. His comments were bound to attract criticism. 他的评论必然会招致批评。', '形容词: attractable 名词: attracter 过去式: attracted 过去分词: attracted 现在分词: attracting 第三人称单数: attracts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('predecessor', '[\'predəsesər]', 'n.前辈,前任,(被取代的)原有事物', '1. The Yunxian Man fossil skull is believed by scientists to belong to homo erectus, a predecessor of homo sapiens that walked on their two legs with an upright body posture. 科学家们认为袁县人属于直立人，是靠两条腿直立行走的智力人的祖先。 2. Recently unearthed fossils trace whales to a doglike predecessor of hoofed plant-eaters, and genetic analysis has identified hippos as whales\' closest living relatives. 最近出土的化石使鲸的祖先可追溯到一种有蹄外形像狗的植食动物，而且基因分析证实了现存动物中河马是鲸的近亲。 3. He undid most of the good work of his predecessor. 他把前任的大部分业绩毁掉了。 4. Our new doctor is much younger than his predecessor. 我们新来的医生比他的前任年轻许多。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('literature', '[\'lɪtrətʃər]', 'n.文学(作品),文艺,著作,文献', '1. She is fond of polite literature. 她喜爱风雅文学。 2. He destroyed feudal ideas in literature. 他摧毁了文学中的封建思想。 3. The principal literature comes from zoology. 主要文献都来自动物学。 4. Beijing was first named ji in literature. 北京最早见于文献的名称叫做蓟。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('deadline', '[\'dedlaɪn]', 'n.最终期限', '1. I hope we can finish this before the deadline. 我希望我们能在最后期限之前完成这项工作。 2. She was working in haste to meet the deadline. 她匆忙工作是为了赶上最后期限。 3. We pulled out all the stops to meet the deadline. 我们竭尽全力在截止日期前完成了工作。', '过去式: deadlined 过去分词: deadlined 现在分词: deadlining 第三人称单数: deadlines');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('shove', '[ʃʌv]', 'n.<口>推,挤;vt.<口>推挤,猛推,强使;vi.推', '1. Don\'t try to shove all the work onto me! 别把工作都推给我！ 2. He dragged her out of the door and shoved her into the street. 他把她拖到门口，猛地把她推到马路上。 3. Then suddenly, Old Grizzly gave Brown Bear a big shove. 突然间，老灰熊给棕色熊一个重重的推撞。 4. Bunt was probably a nickname given to him at school, for going around with his head lowered, ready to bump and shove anybody aside. 铁头可能是他上学时得的绰号，那时他总低着头走路，一副准备随时一头把人撞到一边的架势。 5. The car won\'t start. Can you give it a shove? 这车子启动不了。你能不能推它一把?', '名词: shover 过去式: shoved 过去分词: shoved 现在分词: shoving 第三人称单数: shoves');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reap', '[riːp]', 'v.收割,收获', '1. The peasants are reaping a field of barley. 农民们正在收割大麦。 2. He that soweth virtue shall reap fame. 播下美德，收获名望。 3. If you plant pride, you will reap destruction. 如果你种下骄傲，你就会收获毁灭。 4. It is a season that peasants reap the corn from what they planted in spring. 农民们春季播种玉米，现在是他们收获的季节。 5. They that sow in tears shall reap in joy. 流泪撒种的必欢呼收割。', '过去式: reaped 过去分词: reaped 现在分词: reaping 第三人称单数: reaps');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('chant', '[tʃænt]', 'n.圣歌', '1. Surviving books which contain complete written repertories of the chant with music do not appear before the tenth century, and are well established in the eleventh. 一些保存下来的古书中完整记载着十世纪音乐还没出现前的圣歌和在十一实际已经很好的配上音乐的圣歌。 2. What we call Gregorian chant today first appears distinctly in the Roman repertory of the fifth and sixth centuries. 我们现在说的格立高圣歌最早清楚的出现在5和6世纪的罗马剧目中。 3. The chant of the crowd was \"Work for all\". 群众反复有节奏地呼喊的是\"给大家工作\"。 4. The angels chant the chorus all day long. 天使们整天唱着圣歌，', '副词: chantingly 过去式: chanted 过去分词: chanted 现在分词: chanting 第三人称单数: chants');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('objection', '[əb\'dʒekʃn]', 'n.异议,缺陷,妨碍,拒绝之理由', '1. I have no objection to their plan. 我不反对他们的计划。 2. None of them raised any objection. 他们谁也没提出反对意见。 3. He has a strong objection to getting up early. 他强烈反对早起。 4. I see no objection whatsoever. 我没有任何异议。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mission', '[\'mɪʃn]', 'n.使命,任务,使团,代表团', '1. The minister was sent to Spain on mission. 这位部长奉命前往西班牙。 2. My mission in life is to help poor people. 我的天职是帮助穷人。 3. A Chinese trade mission has been dispatched to Japan. 一个中国贸易代表团已被派往日本。 4. Her mission was to reclaim former criminals. 她的任务是感化过去的罪犯。', '形容词: missional 过去式: missioned 过去分词: missioned 现在分词: missioning 第三人称单数: missions');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('resign', '[rɪ\'zaɪn]', 'n.辞去(职务);v.辞去,辞职', '1. Have you heard of her intention to resign? 你听到她打算辞职的传闻了吗？ 2. He decided to resign his claim to the copyright. 他决定放弃对版权的要求。 3. He has resigned himself to the fact that he will lose the job. 他已经接受他将要失去这份工作的现实。 4. The team refused to resign themselves to being defeated. 该队不甘失败。', '名词: resigner 过去式: resigned 过去分词: resigned 现在分词: resigning 第三人称单数: resigns');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('indifferent', '[ɪn\'dɪfrənt]', 'adj.无关紧要的', '1. He is indifferent to the result of the exam. 他对考试结果漠不关心。 2. She seems indifferent, but deep down she\'s very pleased. 她貌似无动於衷，其实心里非常高兴。 3. Many one or little one is indifferent to me. 多一个或少一个对我是无关紧要的。 4. It was utterly indifferent to her who he was. 封她来说，他是谁，根本是无关紧要的事。', '副词: indifferently');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('stack', '[stæk]', 'n.堆,一堆,堆栈;v.堆叠', '1. The grain has gone mouldy in the stack. 垛里的谷子发霉了。 2. He placed his books in a neat stack. 他把书整整齐齐放成一堆。 3. I\'ve got stacks of work to do. 我有一大堆活儿要做。 4. There is a stack of dishes to be washed in the kitchen. 厨房里还有一大堆盘子要洗。 5. Please stack the materials up here. 请把材料堆在这里。', '形容词: stackable 名词: stacker 过去式: stacked 过去分词: stacked 现在分词: stacking 第三人称单数: stacks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bizarre', '[bɪ\'zɑːr]', 'adj.奇异的(指态度,容貌,款式等)', '1. The building was of bizarre construction. 这建筑构造奇异。 2. She got herself up in a bizarre outfit. 她穿了一套古怪的套装 3. Its bizarre quality was not lost on us. 我们没有被那种异乎寻常的气氛弄得晕头转向。 4. His bizarre behavior attracted our attention. 他怪诞的行为吸引了我们的注意力。', '副词: bizarrely 名词: bizarreness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('successor', '[sək\'sesər]', 'n.继承者,接任者,后续的事物', '1. I am sure that he is a reliable successor. 我确信他是个可靠的接班人。 2. The chairman has designated her as his successor. 主席已指定她作为他的接班人。 3. The vice president was the president\'s successor. 副总统是总统的继任人。 4. Rumour is already rife here as to Dr. Trefoil\'s successor. 关于特雷福伊尔博士的继任人，此间已经谣言蜂起。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('manual', '[\'mænjuəl]', 'n.手册,指南;adj.手的,手动的,手工的,体力的,手册(性质)的,[律]实际占有的', '1. Work done by machines has replaced manual labour. 机器生产已经代替了手工劳作。 2. Making small models requires manual skill. 制作小模型要手巧。 3. Having grown up in the countryside, I\'m used to manual labor. 我生长在农村,习惯体力劳动了。 4. This manual is full of useful tips. 这本小册子里有很多实用的小建议。', '副词: manually');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('intercourse', '[\'ɪntərkɔːrs]', 'n.交往,交流', '1. There was close intercourse between them. 他们过往很密。 2. English is more widespread and more used in international intercourse than German. 英语在国际交往中比德语使用得更为广泛。 3. The whole intercourse was wordless, intense and close. 整个交流都是在默默无声中进行的，强烈而又亲密。 4. The magazine becomes a cultural medium of intercourse between the two peoples. 该杂志成为两民族间文化交流的媒介。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('repertoire', '[\'repərtwɑːr]', 'n.(准备好演出的)节目,保留剧目,(计算机的)指令表,指令系统,<美>(某个人的)全部技能', '1. A repertoire of tricks will astound the esteemed public. 全部节目将使尊敬的观众惊心动魄。 2. That tune is not in my repertoire. 我演出的节目中没有这个曲子。 3. He has a wide repertoire of dirty jokes. 他一肚子下流笑话. 4. Julia has a vast repertoire of smiles. 朱莉娅具有驾御各式微笑的本领。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('clip', '[klɪp]', 'n.夹子,回形针,子弹夹;vt.夹住,剪短,修剪', '1. Do you clip those ear-rings on/Do those ear-rings clip on 你的[这种]耳环是夹上去的吗? 2. There was a cheque clipped to the back of the letter. 在信背面夹着一张支票。 3. The dog\'s fur was clipped short for the show. 为参加狗展狗的毛剪短了。 4. A horse is clipping down the road. 一匹马正沿路奔驰。 5. Winston stroked his nose gently with a paper clip. 温斯顿用一个纸夹子轻轻地擦着鼻子。 6. He gave the sheep a close clip. 他把羊的毛剪得很短。', '过去式: clipped 过去分词: clipped 现在分词: clipping 第三人称单数: clips');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sacrifice', '[\'sækrɪfaɪs]', 'n.牺牲,献身,祭品,供奉;v.牺牲,献出,献祭,供奉', '1. He gave his life as a sacrifice for his country. 他为国牺牲了。 2. She made a big sacrifice for her position today. 她为今天的职位付出了很大的代价。 3. They offered a sacrifice to propitiate the god. 他们供奉祭品以慰诸神。 4. A calf was offered up as a sacrifice to the goddess. 向女神祭献了一头牺牲小牛。 5. You must not sacrifice studies for pleasure. 你不能为享乐而牺牲学业。 6. Sacrifice is the ultimate act of self-giving love. 献祭却是最舍己的爱的行动。', '名词: sacrificer 过去式: sacrificed 过去分词: sacrificed 现在分词: sacrificing 第三人称单数: sacrifices');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('embarrass', '[ɪm\'bærəs]', 'vt.使困窘,使局促不安,阻碍,麻烦', '1. She dragged up that incident just to embarrass me. 她又扯起那件事故意想使我难堪。 2. He was embarrassed by many debts. 他被很多债务弄得焦灼不安。 3. She may embarrass you with her uncouth behavior. 她的粗野行为可能会让你尴尬。 4. You didn\'t embarrass me in the slightest. 你一点也没让我为难。 5. Eye contact may convey sincerity and attentiveness in Western cultures but too much eye contact may embarrass people in some Oriental cultures. 在西方文化，目光接触能传递真诚和关注，但太多的目光接触在某些东方文化中则令人窘迫。', '副词: embarrassedly 过去式: embarrassed 过去分词: embarrassed 现在分词: embarrassing 第三人称单数: embarrasses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ideal', '[aɪ\'diːəl]', 'n.理想;adj.理想的,完美的,想象的,观念的,唯心论的', '1. It is an ideal day for a picnic. 这是一个出外野餐的理想日子。 2. He is looking for a wife but he hasn\'t found his ideal mate. 他正在寻找未来的妻子，但还没有找到理想人选。 3. The facilities were not ideal but we managed as best we could. 设备不理想，但我们已经尽了最大的努力。 4. It\'s my ideal of what a family home should be. 这是我心目中完美的家庭住宅。 5. She \'s looking for a job, but hasn\'t found her ideal yet. 她在找工作,但是还没有找到理想的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('nutrition', '[nu\'trɪʃn]', 'n.营养,营养学', '1. Variety is not a guarantee of good nutrition. 品种多并不能确保营养好。 2. This food provides all the nutrition your dog needs. 本食品含有狗所必须的一切营养。 3. A balanced diet provides nutrition for your body. 均衡的食物使你的身体获得营养。', '形容词: nutritional 副词: nutritionally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('motive', '[\'moʊtɪv]', 'n.动机,目的;adj.发动的,运动的', '1. Her prime motive was personal ambition. 她的主要动机是为了实现个人的志向。 2. I don\'t understand what his motive is. 我不知道他的动机是什么。 3. The police have excluded robbery as a motive for the murder. 警方已排除该谋杀案中有抢劫的动机。 4. Can we assign jealousy as the motive for the crime? 我们能否确定这一犯罪动机是出于嫉妒? 5. The water provides the motive power that turns the mill wheel. 水提供了转动轮子的动力。 6. According to the order,Communist Jiang San motived the mass to fight against the Japanese army.they eradicated the enemy,and killed his brother Jiang Er,who was a traitor. 共产党员蒋三奉命加家乡发动群众开展武装斗争，最后消灭了当地日伪军，除掉汉奸，其兄蒋二。', '过去式: motived 过去分词: motived 现在分词: motiving 第三人称单数: motives');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dominate', '[\'dɑːmɪneɪt]', 'v.支配,占优势', '1. That way, he can dominate the game. 那样他才能支配比赛。 2. He desires to dominate over others. 他很想支配别人。 3. He has authority, but he doesn\'t try to dominate (others). 他有权威 4. They had the ambition to dominate this small country. 他们有控制这个小国的野心。', '形容词: dominative 名词: dominator 过去式: dominated 过去分词: dominated 现在分词: dominating 第三人称单数: dominates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('costume', '[\'kɑːstuːm]', 'n.装束,服装', '1. This traditional costume is of indigo blue. 这件传统服装是靛蓝色的。 2. Her funny costume caused much mirthful laughter among the guests. 她那滑稽的服装引得客人哄堂大笑。 3. The kimono is part of the national costume of Japan. 和服是日本民族服装的一部分。 4. We patched up a costume for the play . 我们临时凑成了一件戏装。 5. Jane costumed a historical play. 简曾为一出历史剧设计服装。 6. A friend of mine was asked to a costume ball a short time ago. 不久前，我的一个朋友被邀请参加一个化装舞会。', '过去式: costumed 过去分词: costumed 现在分词: costuming 第三人称单数: costumes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('expression', '[ɪk\'spreʃn]', 'n.表达,表情,脸色,声调,腔调,榨出,语法,措辞;n.[数]式,表达式,符号', '1. He always shows a doleful expression. 他总是露出忧郁的表情。 2. She gave expression to her sadness. 她流露出了悲伤之情。 3. The scenery was beautiful beyond expression. 那风景美丽得无法形容。 4. I haven\'t heard that expression before. 我以前从未听到过这个词语。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('obedient', '[ə\'biːdiənt]', 'adj.服从的,孝顺的', '1. I was no longer a sweet obedient little boy. 我不再是一个可爱的顺从的小男孩。 2. She is an obedient girl and always obeys her parents. 她是个顺从的孩子，总是服从父母。', '副词: obediently');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('howl', '[haʊl]', 'v.嚎叫,怒吼,嚎啕大哭,喝住,号叫;n.嚎叫,怒号,嚎哭', '1. The howl seemed to freeze the world with fear. 那嚎叫声好像要令整个世界毛骨悚然。 2. You can grip the club when you hear the wolf howl. 听见狼嚎你可以握紧棍子。 3. A sudden howl pierced the silence. 突然一声嗥叫划破了寂静。 4. They listened to the howl of the wind through the trees. 他们听着风在林间呼啸的声音。 5. The dog howled over its master\'s body. 狗对着主人的尸体哀嚎。', '过去式: howled 过去分词: howled 现在分词: howling 第三人称单数: howls');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('subsequent', '[\'sʌbsɪkwənt]', 'adj.后来的,并发的', '1. Subsequent events proved me wrong. 後来发生的事证明我错了。 2. He confessed to other crimes subsequent to the bank robbery. 他供认抢劫银行案後，又坦白了其他罪行。 3. Subsequent to its success as a play, it was made into a film. 该剧在舞台上获得成功之後，又摄制成了电影。 4. Subsequent events confirmed our doubts. 后来发生的事证实了我们的怀疑。', '副词: subsequently 名词: subsequence');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('luggage', '[\'lʌɡɪdʒ]', 'n.行李,皮箱', '1. All the luggage has been strapped up. 所有行李都已捆扎好。 2. He put his bag on the luggage rack. 他把包放在行李架上。 3. The porter was weighed down by all the luggage. 搬运工扛着这些行李压得直不起腰来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('abandon', '[ə\'bændən]', 'vt.放弃,遗弃;n.放任,狂热', '1. Those who abandon themselves to despair can not succeed. 那些自暴自弃的人无法成功。 2. Despite some difficulties, they\'re not going to abandon the plan. 尽管他们遇到了一些困难,但并不打算放弃这个计划。 3. The cruel man abandoned his wife and child. 那个狠心的男人抛弃了他的妻儿。 4. They abandon themselves to drinking. 他们沉湎于饮酒。 5. He signed cheques with careless abandon. 他无所顾忌地乱开支票。', '名词: abandonment 过去式: abandoned 过去分词: abandoned 现在分词: abandoning 第三人称单数: abandons');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('metallic', '[mə\'tælɪk]', 'adj.金属(性)的', '1. This is a kind of metallic paint. 这是一种有金属光泽的涂料。 2. The emery is a hard metallic substance. 金刚砂是非常坚硬的金属物质。 3. I heard metallic sounds when I was studying. 在我学习的时候我听到了金属撞击的声音。 4. He spoke in a thin, metallic voice. 他用尖细的金属般的声音说话。', '副词: metallically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('modest', '[\'mɑːdɪst]', 'adj.谦虚的,谦让的,适度的', '1. We should be modest and prudent. 我们应该谦虚谨慎。 2. She is very modest about her success. 她对自己的成就很谦虚。 3. I bought the house at a modest price. 我以适中的价格买下了这所房子。 4. Young girls must be modest in speech, dress and behavior. 年轻姑娘必须言词谨慎，衣着得体，行为端庄。', '副词: modestly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('companion', '[kəm\'pæniən]', 'n.同伴,共事者', '1. He is a good companion on the journey. 他是个好旅伴。 2. He had always considered her an ideal companion for his son. 他一直以为她是他儿子的理想伴侣。 3. The dog has been her constant companion these past ten years. 过去十年来,这只狗一直与她形影不离。 4. His brother is not much of a companion for him. 他兄弟与他情趣不甚相投。 5. I worked as a companion to an old princess. 我当过一位老公爵夫人的陪伴人。', '过去式: companioned 过去分词: companioned 现在分词: companioning 第三人称单数: companions');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bust', '[bʌst]', 'n.半身像,胸像,(妇女的)胸部', '1. I worked up a lump of clay into a bust of my mother. 我把一块粘土制作成我母亲的半身像。 2. What is your bust size, madam? 小姐, 您胸围的尺寸是多少? 3. The police was engaged in a bust of the drug dealer. 警方正在搜捕那个毒贩子。 4. The movie was a total bust. 这部电影非常失败。 5. I busted my leg playing basketball. 我打篮球的时候弄伤了腿。 6. His company went bust. 他的公司破产了。', '过去式: busted 过去分词: busted 现在分词: busting 第三人称单数: busts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('incorporate', '[ɪn\'kɔːrpəreɪt]', 'adj.合并的,结社的,一体化的;vt.合并,使组成公司,具体表现;vi.合并,混合,组成公司;vt.[律]结社,成为法人组织', '1. I will incorporate the new findings in my report. 我要把新发现并入我的报告。 2. This company is about to incorporate with its parent company. 这公司将要与其母公司合并。 3. We had to incorporate for a company for tax reasons. 鉴于税务原因，我们得组成公司。', '形容词: incorporable 名词: incorporation 过去式: incorporated 过去分词: incorporated 现在分词: incorporating 第三人称单数: incorporates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('premature', '[ˌpriːmə\'tʃʊr]', 'adj.未成熟的,太早的,早熟的', '1. A fire caused the premature closing of the exhibition. 火灾迫使展览会提前结束。 2. This disease produces premature aging of the brain. 这种疾病使大脑过早衰老。 3. The role of the filler is to prevent premature release of CO2. 该填充料的作用是防止过早的释放出二氧化碳。 4. The baby was five weeks premature. 这个孩子是提早五周生下来的。 5. Prompt action saves premature baby 职员反应迅速保早产儿平安', '副词: prematurely 名词: prematureness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('feast', '[fiːst]', 'n.节日,盛宴,筵席,宴会,酒席;vt.盛宴,款待,享乐,请客;vi.参加宴会,享受', '1. The king held a feast for us. 国王为我们举行了盛大的宴会。 2. Enough is as good as a feast. 知足常乐。 3. Preparing for the Christmas Eve feast makes me at my wit\'s end. 筹办圣诞宴会简直使我智穷才竭。 4. His friend treats him to a sumptuous feast. 朋友摆上了丰盛的酒席。 5. He feasted his eye on the beautiful scene. 他尽情欣赏这美丽的景色。', '名词: feaster 过去式: feasted 过去分词: feasted 现在分词: feasting 第三人称单数: feasts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('moral', '[\'mɔːrəl]', 'n.怪物,妖怪', '1. She regards his moral faults with charity. 她宽恕他的品行不端。 2. We differ about moral standards. 我们对道德标准看法不一致。 3. His behavior transgressed the moral rules of the social conduct. 他的行为违背了社会行为的道德准则。 4. It comprises two main sets of rights: the economic rights and the moral rights. 版权包括两种主要的权利:经济权利和精神权利。 5. The moral of this story is ‘Better late than never\'. 这个故事的寓意是｀迟做总比不做好＇.', '副词: morally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('staircase', '[\'sterkeɪs]', 'n.楼梯', '1. I hear someone coming down the staircase. 我听到有人下楼梯。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rivalry', '[\'raɪvlri]', 'n.竞争,竞赛,敌对,敌对状态', '1. He was incited to achievement by rivalry. 竞争激励他努力取得成就。 2. Sibling rivalry is part of the original sin. 兄弟间的敌对相争，是最原始的一种罪。 3. There is great rivalry between the two brothers. 这两兄弟间有一场激烈的竞争。 4. There is cut-throat rivalry among the supermarkets. 这些超级市场之间的竞争可谓你死我活。', '名词复数: rivalries');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('decay', '[dɪ\'keɪ]', 'vi.&n.腐朽,腐烂,衰减,衰退;v.衰落', '1. Naomi: Your entire body is begining to decay. 直美:你的整个身体都在衰退。 2. What made the Roman Empire decay? 罗马帝国为何衰亡？ 3. The dampness of the climate decayed the books. 气候潮湿，把书都霉坏了。 4. The vegetables have begun to decay. 那些蔬菜已开始腐烂。 5. His mental decay is distressing. 他的智力衰退令人苦恼。', '名词: decayer 过去式: decayed 过去分词: decayed 现在分词: decaying 第三人称单数: decays');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tolerant', '[\'tɑːlərənt]', 'adj.容忍的,宽恕的,有耐药力的', '1. Of all the girls, she is the most tolerant. 在所有的姑娘当中，她是最宽容的。 2. As a man, you should be tolerant and magnanimous. 一个男人家，应该宽容大度些！ 3. A priest must learn to be tolerant and always suffer fools gladly. 一个神父必须学会宽容和永远甘心容忍愚妄的人。 4. He is not very tolerant of criticism. 他不大能容忍批评。', '副词: tolerantly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rarely', '[\'rerli]', 'adv.很少地,罕有地', '1. She rarely went anywhere except to her office. 她除了去办公室以外, 很少去别的地方。 2. Rarely did he fail to keep his promise. 他真的很难得失信。 3. Rarely have I seen such a scene. 我难得看到这样的场面。 4. You shouldn\'t miss the opportunity to see the play-it\'s rarely put on. 你不要错过看那出戏的机会,它可是难得上演。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('disperse', '[dɪ\'spɜːrs]', 'v.(使)分散,(使)散开,疏散', '1. The police dispersed the crowd. 警方驱散群众。 2. The wind dispersed the cloud from the sky. 风吹散了天上的云。 3. The enemy had to disperse and hide in caves. 敌人不得不分散藏身于洞穴之中。 4. The crowd dispersed. 人群纷纷散开。', '形容词: dispersible 副词: dispersedly 名词: dispersant 过去式: dispersed 过去分词: dispersed 现在分词: dispersing 第三人称单数: disperses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mental', '[\'mentl]', 'adj.精神的,智力的', '1. It\'s clear that mental activity does not stop when we\'re asleep. 很显然,我们熟睡的时候,思想活动仍然不会停下来。 2. We should pay more attention to our mental health. 我们应该更注重心理健康。 3. I think such mental disorders are hereditary. 我认为这种精神失调是遗传的。 4. Social life is developed by physical labor and mental labor. 社会生活由于体力劳动和脑力劳动的结合才得以发展。 5. The hospital cares for some fifty mental patients. 这家医院照料五十名左右精神病患者。', '副词: mentally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('feminine', '[\'femənɪn]', 'adj.妇女(似)的,娇柔的,阴性的,女性的', '1. Jewelry and lace are mostly feminine belongings. 珠宝和蕾丝大多是女性用品。 2. That\'s a feminine reaction. 这是女性特有的反应。 3. There are three genders in German: masculine, feminine and neuter. 德语中有三性: 阳性、 阴性和中性。', '副词: femininely 名词: feminineness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('predominant', '[prɪ\'dɑːmɪnənt]', 'adj.卓越的,支配的,主要的,突出的,有影响的', '1. The predominant feature of his character was pride. 他的性格中主要的特点是骄傲。 2. Identify any predominant architectural approaches. 明确主要的体系结构方法。 3. It is the land which makes the predominant contribution. 土地为我们作出了最显著的贡献。 4. It has been suggested that most individuals harbour one predominant dermoscopic type among their naevi. 大多数患者的痣都有一个显著的皮肤镜表现型。', '副词: predominantly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('kit', '[kɪt]', 'n.成套工具,用具包,工具箱,成套用具', '1. The plumber lost his kit on the way home. 这位水管工人在回家的路上把工具丢了。 2. There is a repair kit provided in the boot of each car. 每辆车的行李箱内都备有工具箱。 3. They marched twenty miles in full kit. 他们带着全副装备行军二十英里。 4. Kit this man out with everything he needs. 他需要什麽就给他什麽装备。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('predict', '[prɪ\'dɪkt]', 'v.预知,预言,预报', '1. It is virtually impossible to predict the future accurately. 精确预言未来的事实际上是办不到的。 2. The economists predicted an increase in the rate of inflation. 经济学家预言通货膨胀率将会增长。 3. The earthquake had been predicted several months before. 这次地震早在几个月以前就发布了预报。 4. It is impossible to predict what will happen. 预知未来的事是不可能的。', '形容词: predictable 副词: predictably 名词: predictability 过去式: predicted 过去分词: predicted 现在分词: predicting 第三人称单数: predicts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('emphasis', '[\'emfəsɪs]', 'n.强调,重点', '1. They put emphasis on making to quota this quarter. 他们强调要达到这一季的配额。 2. Our English course places great emphasis on conversational skills. 我们的英语课程非常重视会话技能。 3. In recent years, the emphasis has moved away from punishing drug addicts towards helping them. 最近几年,重点从惩罚吸毒者转移到救助他们。 4. You put too much emphasis on the last syllable. 你把最后一个音节读得太重。', '名词复数: emphases');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('concentration', '[ˌkɒnsen\'treɪʃən]', 'n.集中,集合,专心,浓缩,浓度', '1. The tennis players need total concentration during play. 网球运动员在比赛中需要全神贯注。 2. Stress and tiredness often result in a lack of concentration. 紧张和疲劳常使人精神不集中。 3. Concentration is essential if you want to do a good job. 如果你想把事情做好,专心是必要的。 4. His area of concentration is economics. 他专心研究经济学。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dwarf', '[dwɔːrf]', 'n.矮子,侏儒;v.(使)变矮小', '1. You are a giant of words and dwarf of action. 你是言词的巨人,行动的矮子。 2. There is a dwarf apple tree in our garden. 在我们的花园里有一棵矮苹果树。 3. The kind dwarf asked the little princess to have dinner with him. 善良的小矮人邀请小公主和他一起吃晚饭。 4. A dwarf on a giant\'s shoulders sees further of the two. 侏儒站在巨人肩上要比两个人看得远。 5. Each innovation destined to dwarf the extensive accomplishment of the Greeks-Euclidean geometry. 每一个创新都注定希腊人的巨大成就--欧几里德几何相形见绌。 6. They act out their dramas in a setting whose wilderness immensity both dwarf and ennobles whatever they achieve 他们在荒原上奠定了他们的事业，而广阔无际的天地既使他们的成就显得渺小，也显得崇高。', '形容词: dwarfish 名词: dwarfishness 名词复数: dwarfs 过去式: dwarfed 过去分词: dwarfed 现在分词: dwarfing 第三人称单数: dwarfs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('response', '[rɪ\'spɑːns]', 'n.回答,响应,反应', '1. The tax cuts produced a favourable response from the public. 税额削减受到了公众的欢迎. 2. I\'m sorry; the correct response is B. 不好意思,正确回答应该是B。 3. There was an enthusiastic response to my suggestions. 我的提议得到了热情的响应。 4. 他提出指控后迅即得到答复。 他提出指控後迅即得到答覆.', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ceramic', '[sə\'ræmɪk]', 'adj.陶器的;n.陶瓷制品', '1. These ceramic tiles are the ultimate in modern kitchen design. 这种瓷砖是现代厨房装修中的极品。 2. There is a ceramic shop in the Arcade. 商店街中有一家陶器店。 3. I know a retired electrical engineer who has become a highly-paid ceramic artist. 我还认识一个退休的电力工程师，退休之后他成为了一名身价颇高的陶器艺术家。 4. There is a ceramic shop in the Arcade. 商店街中有一家陶器店。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('region', '[\'riːdʒən]', 'n.区域,地方,(世界上某个特定的)地区,(艺术,科学等的)领域,(大气,海水等的)层', '1. Most of the countries in the region have unstable economies. 这个地区大多数国家的经济都不稳定。 2. I guess there are much less people in the Arctic regions than here. 我想北极地区的人要比这里的少得多。 3. The region near the erupting volcano was evacuated rapidly. 火山爆发处附近已迅速撤空。 4. These small spiced cakes are a peculiarity of the region. 这些别有风味的小蛋糕是该地的特产。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('account', '[ə\'kaʊnt]', 'n.计算,帐目,说明,估计,理由;vi.说明,总计有,认为,得分;vt.认为', '1. She squared her account at the store. 她在商店里结清帐目。 2. We have accounts with most of our suppliers. 我们与大多数供应商都是实行赊购制。 3. The agency has lost several of its most important accounts. 这家代理机构失去了几家最重要的老客户。 4. This is a particular account of the accident. 这是一份全面而详尽的事故报告。 5. He has been asked to account for his conduct. 他被要求解释他的行为。', '过去式: accounted 过去分词: accounted 现在分词: accounting 第三人称单数: accounts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('suspicion', '[sə\'spɪʃn]', 'n.猜疑,怀疑', '1. We regard her behaviour with suspicion. 我们对她的行为有怀疑。 2. \"A science fiction cannot not be regarded as a mere entertainment, but in fact it tells the reader much more.\" \"科幻小说不能简单地看成是供消遣的，而实际上它给读者展示更深刻的内容。\" 3. The talks have resulted in a lessening of suspicion. 谈话消减了彼此的怀疑。 4. His words had sowed the seeds of suspicion in their minds. 他的话已在他们心中播下怀疑的种子。', '形容词: suspicional 过去式: suspicioned 过去分词: suspicioned 现在分词: suspicioning 第三人称单数: suspicions');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('locality', '[loʊ\'kæləti]', 'n.位置,地点', '1. There are several supermarkets in the locality. 这个地区有好几家超市。 2. Public transport is a big problem in this locality. 公共交通是这个地区的大问题。 3. People in this locality used to take two meals a day. 这儿的居民过去每天吃两餐饭。 4. They are trying to pinpoint the ship\'s exact locality. 他们正在设法确定轮船的确切位置。', '名词复数: localities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('queer', '[kwɪr]', 'n.同性恋者;adj.奇怪的,可疑的，不舒服的;vt.搞糟;', '1. There is something queer about him. 他有些古怪。 2. Her queer way of dressing attracted the attention of the passerby. 她古怪的着装方式引起了过路人的注意。 3. I have a queer dream last night. 我昨晚做了一个奇怪的梦。 4. I heard some very queer noises in the garden. 我听到花园里有些可疑的声音。 5. His blunder would certainly queer his chances of promotion. 他犯的大错肯定会毁了他晋升的机会。', '形容词: queerish 副词: queerly 比较级: queerer 最高级: queerest 名词: queerness 过去式: queered 过去分词: queered 现在分词: queering 第三人称单数: queers');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('erect', '[ɪ\'rekt]', 'adj.直立的,竖立的,笔直的;vt.盖,使竖立,使直立,树立,建立;vi.[生理]勃起', '1. They erected their tent at the foot of the mountain. 他们在山脚下支起了帐篷。 2. The town will erect a monument to its war heroes . 这个市镇将为该城的战斗英雄们立个纪念碑。 3. Six policemen started to erect a roadblock. 六个警察着手建立一道路障。 4. They plan to erect an apartment house on that property. 他们计划在那片地产上建造一座公寓楼。 5. She held her head erect and her back straight. 她昂着头，把背挺得笔直。', '形容词: erectable 副词: erectly 名词: erectness 过去式: erected 过去分词: erected 现在分词: erecting 第三人称单数: erects');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('offense', '[ə\'fens]', 'n.进攻', '1. Others assume it\'s a victimless offense. 也有些人认为这是无害过错。 2. That dirty old house is an offense to the eye. 那幢肮脏的旧房子令人看了很不舒服。 3. No offense, sir, but we\'re searching every vehicle. 恕我冒犯,但我们在搜查每一辆车。 4. He is quick to take offense. 他很易发怒。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('associate', '[ə\'soʊʃieɪt]', 'vt.使发生联系,使联合;vi.交往,结交;n.合作人,同事;adj.副的', '1. I always associate her with roses. 我总是把她与玫瑰花联想在一起。 2. We should associate ourselves with this large firm. 我们应该和这家大公司联合。 3. Mr. Miller is a business associate of our company. 米勒先生是我们公司的生意伙伴。 4. I got a new job and a new group of work associates. 我有了新工作和一班新同事。 5. He is an associate editor of the newspaper. 他是报纸的副主编。 6. You are wooing troubles if you associate with him. 你和他交往会招来麻烦。', '过去式: associated 过去分词: associated 现在分词: associating 第三人称单数: associates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('classificatio', '[klæsɪfɪ\'keɪʃiːəʊ]', 'n.分类,分级', '1. With the model, the index of cropland classificatio n in Wuxue City,Hubei Province, is compared with original one calculated directl y. 其次,利用此线性模型,并结合湖北省武穴市分等的实际情况,比较系数修正前后的分等指数。 2. Standards for the archives of the national multipurpose investigation of the coastal zone and tidal wetland resources--Classificatio GB/T9852.;3-1988全国海岸带和海涂资源综合调查档案标准分类法 3. ACC programme classificatio 行政协调会方案分类 4. Zurich classificatio 苏黎世黑子分类', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('corrupt', '[kə\'rʌpt]', 'adj.腐败的,贪污的,被破坏的,混浊的,(语法)误用的;vt.使腐烂,腐蚀,使恶化;vi.腐烂,堕落', '1. She wrote a book declaiming against our corrupt society. 她写了一本书抨击我们这腐败的社会。 2. The corrupt judge dismissed the case without a hearing. 腐败的法官没有听审就驳回了这个案子。 3. The official led a corrupt life. 这个官员过着堕落的生活。 4. The manuscript is so corrupt that parts of it make no sense at all. 这稿子由于讹误太多，以致有的部分意义不明。 5. He was sent to prison for trying to corrupt a policeman with money. 他因为试图用钱贿赂一名警察而被送入监狱。 6. Complete power corrupts completely. 绝对的权力造成绝对的腐败。', '形容词: corruptive 副词: corruptly 名词: corrupter 过去式: corrupted 过去分词: corrupted 现在分词: corrupting 第三人称单数: corrupts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('illusion', '[ɪ\'luːʒn]', 'n.幻想', '1. Mirrors in a room often give an illusion of space. 房间里的镜子常给人一种空间增大的错觉。 2. A mirage is an optical illusion. 海市蜃楼是一种视错觉。 3. I thought I saw a ghost but it was just an optical illusion. 我以为我看见鬼了，其实只是一种幻觉。 4. This creates an illusion of variety. 这造成了一种多样化的幻觉。', '形容词: illusional');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('recreation', '[ˌrekri\'eɪʃn]', 'n.消遣,娱乐', '1. In other words, we had better take sufficient recreation to relax after work. 换句话说，我们最好工作后，消遣消遣来轻松一下。 2. Art is both creation and recreation. 艺术是创作，同时也是消遣。 3. Some films combine education with recreation . 有些影片把教育同娱乐融合在一起。 4. Our city needs more facilities for recreation. 我们城市需要更多的娱乐设施。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('decorate', '[\'dekəreɪt]', 'v.装饰,为...做室内装修', '1. We decorated the house for Christmas. 我们装饰房屋过圣诞节。 2. My mother likes to decorate rooms. 我妈妈非常喜欢装饰房间。 3. I\'ll bring some balloons to decorate. 我要带些气球去装饰装饰。 4. May I help you decorate the room? 我可以帮你装饰布置房间吗？', '过去式: decorated 过去分词: decorated 现在分词: decorating 第三人称单数: decorates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('analogy', '[ə\'nælədʒi]', 'n.类似,类推', '1. It is not always reliable to argue by analogy. 用类推法论证并不总是可靠的。 2. He offers an analogy to explain how it works. 他用一个类比来解释这个过程。 3. He drew this conclusion on the analogy of yours. 他根据你的理论类推得出这个结论。 4. No analogy exists between you and me. 你和我之间没有相似之处。', '名词复数: analogies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('revive', '[rɪ\'vaɪv]', 'v.(使)苏醒,(使)复兴,(使)复活,(使)再生效,回想', '1. We tried to revive him but without avail. 我们试图使他苏醒,但没有成功。 2. The flowers will revive in water. 这些花在水中会再活。 3. Revive your spirit and add shine to your hair. 重振你的精神，给你的头发增添光亮。 4. We need something to revive our hopes. 我们需要一些什么东西来重新恢复我们的希望。', '形容词: revivable 名词: reviver 过去式: revived 过去分词: revived 现在分词: reviving 第三人称单数: revives');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('flip', '[flɪp]', 'vt.掷,弹,轻击,鞭等抽打,空翻;vi.用指轻弹,抽打,翻书页(或纸张),蹦跳;n.抛,弹,筋斗;adj.无礼的,冒失的,轻率的', '1. Let\'s flip a coin to see who goes first. 我们来掷硬币看谁先去。 2. Kids flip frisbees while their elders chat. 孩子们玩飞盘，大人聊天。 3. He flipped a crumb across the room. 他把面包屑弹到房间另一头。 4. She flipped the insect from her face. 她将昆虫从脸上弹掉。 5. He flipped to a fresh page and began to write. 他翻到另外一页,开始写了起来。 6. The gymnast had to do a double back flip. 这个体操运动员得做一个360度后空翻。 7. Don\'t be flip with me. 不要对我油腔滑舌。', '比较级: flipper 最高级: flippest 过去式: flipped 过去分词: flipped 现在分词: flipping 第三人称单数: flips');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('nominal', '[\'nɑːmɪnl]', 'adj.名义上的,有名无实的,名字的,[语]名词性的;n.名词性词', '1. He is only the nominal head of the country. 他只是那个国家名义上的元首。 2. He remained in nominal control of the business for another ten years. 他名义上又掌管了这家公司十年。 3. She charged only a nominal fee for her work. 她为所做的工作只收取象征性的费用。 4. Such a nominal phrase mainly acts as the subject or object in a sentence. 这样的名词性词组在句子中主要充当主语和宾语。', '副词: nominally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('idiom', '[\'ɪdiəm]', 'n.成语,方言,土语,习惯用语', '1. This idiom cannot be translated literally. 这个成语无法照字面翻译。 2. From that story comes the idiom \"Draw a snake and add feet to it\". “画蛇添足”这个成语就是从这个故事来的。 3. \"Let the cat out of the bag\" is an idiom meaning to tell a secret by mistake. “让猫从袋子里跑出来”是惯用语，意思是无意中泄露秘密。 4. He spoke in the idiom of the New England countryside. 他讲新英格兰乡下的方言。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('trend', '[trend]', 'n.倾向,趋势;vi.伸向,倾向,通向', '1. The trend of prices is still upward. 物价仍有上涨趋势。 2. The youth like to follow the latest trends in fashion. 年轻人喜好追求最新的流行款式。 3. This quartet represents a major new trend in modern music. 这首四重奏的曲子反映了现代音乐中一种主要的新趋向。 4. The event changed the trend of public opinion. 这件事改变了舆论的趋向。 5. The prices of houses are trending upwards. 房价趋于上涨。', '过去式: trended 过去分词: trended 现在分词: trending 第三人称单数: trends');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('preserve', '[prɪ\'zɜːrv]', 'vt.保护,保持,保存,保藏;vi.做蜜饯,禁猎;n.蜜饯,果酱,禁猎地,禁区,防护物', '1. It is highly important to preserve the environment. 保护自然环境至关重要。 2. It\'s the duty of the police to preserve the public order. 维护公共秩序是警察的职责。 3. You should preserve your papers for future use. 你应当把你的文件保存起来以备将来之用。 4. I tried to preserve my independence. 我试图保持自己的独立性。 5. No hunting is allowed in the preserve . 在禁猎区内不许打猎。', '形容词: preservable 名词: preservability 过去式: preserved 过去分词: preserved 现在分词: preserving 第三人称单数: preserves');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('resistant', '[rɪ\'zɪstənt]', 'adj.抵抗的,有抵抗力的', '1. A healthy diet creates a body resistant to disease. 保健饮食有助于增强体内对疾病的抵抗力。 2. The high walls of rock are made of weather-resistant quartzite. 那高高的岩石墙壁是由对风化有抵抗的石英岩组成的。 3. This new type of infection is resistant to antibiotics. 这种新的传染病对抗菌素有抗药性。 4. They imposed their government by force on the resistant population. 他们以武力把自己的统治强加在持反抗态度的人民头上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('indignant', '[ɪn\'dɪɡnənt]', 'adj.愤怒的,愤慨的', '1. People are indignant by their shooting of innocent civilians. 对于他们枪杀无辜平民，人们感到义愤填膺。 2. He is indignant at the false accusation. 他对被诬告愤愤不平。', '副词: indignantly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('accordance', '[ə\'kɔːrdns]', 'n.一致,和谐', '1. He acted in accordance with his beliefs. 他按照自己的信念行事。 2. I shall be glad if you will forward fifty ton of coal, in accordance with your sample. 请按照贵公司提供的样品，供应我司50吨煤炭，谢谢。 3. The mayor must make policies in accordance with the bill passed in the Congress. 市长要根据议会的议案来制定政策。 4. Install in accordance with the local codes. 安装方法要符合当地规程的要求。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('invariably', '[ɪn\'veriəbli]', 'adv.不变地,总是;n.总是', '1. We always invariably support him. 我们一如既往地支持他。 2. Invariably I take a nap after lunch. 午饭后，我总是睡个午觉。 3. Wives say that men are invariably children at heart. 妻子们说男人实际上永远是孩子。 4. His intuition is invariably correct. 他的直觉常常是正确的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('wretched', '[\'retʃɪd]', 'adj.可怜的,悲惨的,肮脏的,恶劣的', '1. She looked wretched and forlorn, despairing of the arrival of a friend who had promised to meet her. 她看上去又可怜又孤独，对于答应来看她的朋友的到来已不抱希望。 2. The wretched man lost all his money. 这个不幸的男人丢了所有的钱。 3. She lamented to us about her wretched lot. 她向我们哀叹自己悲惨的遭遇。 4. I cannot picture myself in more wretched condition. 我想像不出一个比这更悲惨的境地了。', '副词: wretchedly 比较级: wretcheder 最高级: wretchedest 名词: wretchedness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('upright', '[\'ʌpraɪt]', 'adj.垂直的,竖式的,正直的,诚实的,合乎正道的;adv.笔直,竖立着;n.垂直,竖立', '1. Only humans have a natural upright posture. 只有人类才有自然直立的姿势。 2. Please put the back of your seat in an upright position. 请把座位靠背转到垂直位置。 3. He was a famous upright statesman. 他是一位著名的、正直的政治家。 4. Several columns among the ruins still stood upright. 在废墟中依然挺立着几根柱子。 5. The piano was nearly always an upright. 钢琴差不多总是直立式钢琴。', '副词: uprightly 名词: uprightness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('humble', '[\'hʌmbl]', 'adj.卑下的,微贱的,谦逊的,粗陋的;vt.使...卑下,挫,贬抑', '1. Knowledge makes humble, ignorance makes proud. 博学使人谦逊，无知使人骄傲。 2. The duke did well by people in humble stations. 那位公爵善待地位低下的人。 3. The family lived in a humble cottage. 这户人家住在一所简陋的农舍里。 4. You are welcome to my humble home. 非常欢迎您光临寒舍。 5. She\'ll humble you to the dust. 她一定要把你糟蹋得一文不值。', '副词: humbly 比较级: humbler 最高级: humblest 名词: humbleness 过去式: humbled 过去分词: humbled 现在分词: humbling 第三人称单数: humbles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bargain', '[\'bɑːrɡən]', 'n.契约,合同,成交商品,便宜货;v.议价', '1. He made a satisfactory bargain with them. 他和他们做了一笔满意的交易。 2. If you promote our goods, we will give you a good discount as our part of the bargain. 若你方经销我们的货物，我方愿给予你相当大的优惠作为回报。 3. She knows a bargain when she sees one. 她有辨别便宜货的能力。 4. There never was a better bargain driver. 再没有比这更美好的契约。 5. The salesman refused to bargain over the price. 推销员拒绝讨价还价。', '名词: bargainer 过去式: bargained 过去分词: bargained 现在分词: bargaining 第三人称单数: bargains');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('combination', '[ˌkɑːmbɪ\'neɪʃn]', 'n.结合,联合,合并,化合,化合物', '1. It is the combination of wit and political analysis that makes his articles so readable. 他的生花妙笔与政治分析相得益彰，使他的文章脍炙人口。 2. The firm is working on a new product in combination with several overseas partners. 公司正在联合几家海外合伙人制造新产品。 3. A combination of factors led to her decision to resign. 综合各种因素之後她决定辞职。 4. If you want to open the lock, you must know the combination. 如果你想要打开这把锁,你必须知道密码。', '形容词: combinational');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('irrigation', '[ˌɪrɪ\'ɡeɪʃn]', 'n.灌溉,冲洗', '1. Water is channelled through a series of irrigation canals. 把水引入一系列灌溉渠中。 2. We used the money to set up an irrigation project. 我们把钱用在兴建灌溉工程上了。 3. Irrigation is needed to make crops grow in dry regions. 干旱地区需要灌溉才能使作物生长。 4. If not well managed, irrigation can be harmful. 如果管理不善，灌溉还可能有害处。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hardy', '[\'hɑːrdi]', 'adj.难的,艰苦的，勇敢的;adv.努力地,辛苦地,坚硬地', '1. A few hardy people swam in the icy water. 一些强壮的人在冰冷的水中游泳。 2. Only a hardy man should enter the auto race. 只有胆大的人才能参加摩托赛。 3. Camels are tough and hardy creatures. 骆驼是能吃苦耐劳的动物。 4. Their children are remarkably hardy. 他们的孩子非常能吃苦耐劳。', '副词: hardily 比较级: hardier 最高级: hardiest 名词: hardiness 名词复数: hardies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('compel', '[kəm\'pel]', 'vt.强迫,迫使', '1. Nothing can compel me to do such a thing. 没有什么可以强迫我做这件事。 2. I was compelled to do so by absolute necessity. 我因绝对的需要,被迫这样做的。 3. The heavy rain compelled us to stay indoors. 大雨迫使我们呆在户内。 4. Duty compelled the soldiers to volunteer for the mission. 责任驱使军人必须志愿加入此任务', '形容词: compellable 副词: compellably 名词: compeller 过去式: compelled 过去分词: compelled 现在分词: compelling 第三人称单数: compels');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ingredient', '[ɪn\'ɡriːdiənt]', 'n.成分,因素', '1. Coconut is a basic ingredient for many curries. 椰子是多种咖喱菜的基本成分。 2. Mix all the ingredients in a bowl. 将原料放在盆里调匀. 3. There is a list of ingredients on the side of the packet. 包装袋的边上印有所含配料表。 4. Humor is an effective ingredient of a speech. 幽默是演讲中效果极佳的一个因素。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('groan', '[ɡroʊn]', 'n.呻吟,叹息;vi.呻吟,受折磨,受压迫发出嘎吱声;vt.呻吟着说', '1. The girl groaned in pain. 那女孩在痛苦中呻吟。 2. He was heard to groan. 有人听见他在呻吟。 3. Don\'t moan and groan because of a little setback. 不要受了一点挫折就唉声叹气。 4. The roof creaked and groaned under the weight of the snow. 屋顶被积雪压得发出吱吱嘎嘎的声响。 5. The wounded man uttered a groan. 那个受伤的人发出呻吟。', '副词: groaningly 名词: groaner 过去式: groaned 过去分词: groaned 现在分词: groaning 第三人称单数: groans');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mercury', '[\'mɜːrkjəri]', 'n.水银,汞,[罗神]墨丘利神(众神的信使)', '1. Mercury is a fluid substance. 水银是流体状之。 2. Mercury weighs more than water by about 14 times. 水银比水重约十三倍。 3. Mercury is too dry and poor in oxygen. 水星上面过于干燥，并且缺乏氧气。 4. He has no mercury in him. 他没有精神。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('coalition', '[ˌkoʊə\'lɪʃn]', 'n.合并,接合,联合', '1. There is no coalition of members of the economy. 这种经济的各部门之间不存在联合。 2. The two parties have united to form a coalition. 这两个党已结成联盟。 3. After the election, the coalition fragmented. 选举之后，联盟瓦解了', '名词: coalitionist');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('romance', '[\'roʊmæns]', 'n.冒险故事,浪漫史,传奇文学,风流韵事,虚构;vi.写传奇,渲染,虚构', '1. They kept the romance alive in their marriage for 35 years. 他们35年的婚姻生活一直保持着浪漫色彩 2. That romance movie is a real tear-jerker. 那部言情电影真是令人泪下如注。 3. His romance and adventure were battering at the conventions. 他的传奇和冒险故事粉碎着传统。 4. The biography relishes too much of romance. 这篇传记中传奇色彩太浓。 5. She would often romance about her bitter experiences. 她总是夸大其词地讲她的痛苦经历。', '名词: romancer 过去式: romanced 过去分词: romanced 现在分词: romancing 第三人称单数: romances');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('simultaneous', '[ˌsaɪml\'teɪniəs]', 'adj.同时的,同时发生的', '1. The explosion was timed to be simultaneous with the plane\'s take-off. 爆炸的时间定在飞机起飞的时刻。 2. The simultaneous demonstrations are held in London and New York. 在伦敦和纽约同时举行示威游行。 3. There were several simultaneous attacks by the rebels. 反叛者同时发动了几起攻击。 4. Her work as a simultaneous translator requires strong powers of concentration. 作为同步翻译员，她的工作需要极大的专注力。', '副词: simultaneously 名词: simultaneousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('evidence', '[\'evɪdəns]', 'n.明显,显著,明白,迹象,根据,[物]证据,证物', '1. There wasn\'t enough evidence to prove his guilt. 没有充分的证据能证明他有罪。 2. Evidence weighted against the defendant. 证词很不利于被告。 3. It is a statement in conflict with other evidence. 这一陈述与其他证词不一致。 4. Have you any evidence to support this statement? 你这种说法有根据吗? 5. His answer evidenced a guilty conscience. 他的回答证明他良心有愧。', '过去式: evidenced 过去分词: evidenced 现在分词: evidencing 第三人称单数: evidences');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('diversion', '[daɪ\'vɜːrʒn]', 'n.转移,转换,牵制,解闷,娱乐', '1. There\'s a diversion sign behind the lorry. 那辆卡车后面发出了转向的信号。 2. The diversion of a stream changed the land. 一条小溪的转向使这块土地发生了变化。 3. A smoke bomb created a diversion while the robbery took place. 劫案发生时，一枚烟雾弹转移了人们的视线。 4. I think your last argument was a diversion to make us forget the main point. 我认为你最后的那个论点是在转移目标，以便我们忘掉要点。', '形容词: diversionary');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sentiment', '[\'sentɪmənt]', 'n.情操,情感,情绪,观点,多愁善感,感情', '1. He could feel the sentiment stirring within him. 他可以感觉到这种情绪在心中波动。 2. His speech loosed a tide of nationalist sentiment. 他的讲话表露出一种强烈的民族主义情绪。 3. He could not adequately express his sentiment. 他无法恰当地表达出他的感情。 4. What are his sentiments on this issue? 他对这个问题持什么观点？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('flatter', '[\'flætər]', 'vt.过分夸赞,奉承,阿谀,使高兴,使满意,(画,肖像上的形象)胜过(真人或实物)', '1. My boss likes it when we flatter him. 我的老板喜欢我们奉承他。 2. Friends who flatter you to your face are not true friends. 凡是当面奉承你的朋友不是真朋友。 3. He flattered her about her cooking. 他恭维她的烹调手艺。 4. It\'s impossible for you to ask a girl to teach you how to flatter another. 你不可能让一个女孩教你如何取悦另一个女孩。', '副词: flatteringly 名词: flatterer 过去式: flattered 过去分词: flattered 现在分词: flattering 第三人称单数: flatters');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dentist', '[\'dentɪst]', 'n.牙科医生', '1. The dentist told the boy not to eat too many sweets. 牙医告诫这男孩不要吃太多糖果。 2. I have an appointment with my dentist this afternoon. 我已约好今天下午去看牙医。 3. The dentist took out his bad tooth yesterday. 昨天医生拔掉了他的一颗坏牙。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rebellion', '[rɪ\'beljən]', 'n.谋反,叛乱,反抗,不服从', '1. The rebellion was soon stamped on by the army. 军队很快平息了叛乱。 2. The rebellion was crushed by government forces. 政府军已把叛乱镇压下去。 3. The government has just put down a rebellion. 这个国家刚刚镇压了一场叛乱。 4. The people would rise in open rebellion if oppressed by a monarchy. 如果遭到君主制的压迫，人民就会起来反抗。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('severe', '[sɪ\'vɪr]', 'adj.严厉的,严格的,剧烈的,严重的,严峻的', '1. The premier came under severe criticism. 这位总理遭到严厉的抨击。 2. He\'s suffering from severe mental disorder. 他患有严重的精神病。 3. A severe storm turned the small village down to ground. 一场剧烈的风暴把小村夷为平地。 4. The new product has stood a severe proof . 新产品经受了严格的考验。', '副词: severely 比较级: severer 最高级: severest 名词: severeness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('competence', '[\'kɑːmpɪtəns]', 'n.能力', '1. Competence is prerequisite to promotion. 能力是升职的先决条件。 2. I doubt his competence to do the work. 我怀疑他是否有能力做那件工作。 3. No one doubts her competence as a teacher. 谁也不怀疑她能胜任教师工作。 4. It has beyond the competence of the court. 它已经超出法院的权限。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('watertight', '[\'wɔːtərtaɪt]', 'adj.不漏水的,水密的', '1. This roof is completely watertight. 这屋顶一点也不漏水。 2. We had a couple of suspicious characters but their alibis are watertight. 我们中有几位多疑的人，但是他们的阴谋无懈可击。 3. The system, of course, is not watertight. 当然这套系统也不是天衣无缝的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cardinal', '[\'kɑːrdɪnl]', 'n.枢机主教,红衣主教;adj.主要的,最重要的', '1. I\'ve had dinner with Bill and Cardinal Spellman. 我同比尔和斯佩尔曼红衣主教一起吃过晚饭。 2. The cardinal includes 1, 2, 3, etc. 基数词包括1、2、3等等。 3. A cardinal perched momently on the dogwood branch. 一只北美红雀在山茱萸上停留了片刻。 4. Every one suspects himself of at least one of the cardinal virtues. 每个人都认为他自己至少有一种主要的品德。', '名词: cardinalship');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('configuration', '[kənˌfɪɡjə\'reɪʃn]', 'n.构造,结构,配置,外形', '1. It is something resembling this structure in configuration or pattern. 这是一种在外形或结构上类似这种构造的东西。 2. The configuration of this plant is complex. 这个工厂的布局很复杂。 3. This is the configuration of the earth\'s surface. 这就是地球表面的形状。 4. Where do I put my configuration files? 我把配置文件放在哪里了?', '形容词: configurative 副词: configurationally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('circumstance', '[\'sɜːrkəmstæns]', 'n.环境,详情,境况', '1. He was forced by the circumstances to do this. 他做此事是为环境所迫。 2. The choice of technique is, therefore, a matter of preference, and in some cases circumstance. 因此,技术的选择是偏好的问题,在某些情况下也与环境有关。 3. I cannot recollect the exact circumstance. 我总是想不起确实的情况。 4. Your arrival was a fortunate circumstance. 你的到来是命中注定的。', '过去式: circumstanced 过去分词: circumstanced 现在分词: circumstancing 第三人称单数: circumstances');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('underestimate', '[ˌʌndər\'estɪmeɪt]', 'vt.低估,看轻;n.低估', '1. The figure of $10 million was a serious underestimate. 一千万美元这个数据是一个严重的低估。 2. It seems to have been due to his consistent underestimate of her political weight. 看来是由于希思一贯低估她的政治能量。 3. Never underestimate the power of a woman. 决不要低估妇女的力量。 4. Don\'t underestimate the difficulties of the work. 不要低估了这项工作的艰巨性。', '名词: underestimation 过去式: underestimated 过去分词: underestimated 现在分词: underestimating 第三人称单数: underestimates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('equip', '[ɪ\'kwɪp]', 'vt.装备,配备,训练,准备行装', '1. They can\'t afford to equip their army. 他们无力装备自己的军队。 2. We must equip the army for the modern war. 我们必须装备军队打现代化战争。 3. He is equipped with much experience in teaching. 他具有丰富的教学经验。 4. Could you help me equip the caravan? 你能帮我准备好这辆旅行车上的装备吗?', '过去式: equipped 过去分词: equipped 现在分词: equipping 第三人称单数: equips');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('expend', '[ɪk\'spend]', 'vt.花费,消耗,支出,[海]把(暂时不用的绳)绕在杆上', '1. He lived high and expended largely. 他生活讲究，花费很大。 2. He has expended much time and energy on that experiment. 他已经花费许多时间、金钱在那实验上。 3. The soldiers expended all their ammunition in that fight. 士兵在那场战斗中用尽了所有的弹药。 4. I had expended much time on the work but they told me it\'s useless. 我花了很多时间在这件工作上，他们却告诉我说这是无用的。', '过去式: expended 过去分词: expended 现在分词: expending 第三人称单数: expends');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('investigate', '[ɪn\'vestɪɡeɪt]', 'v.调查,研究', '1. The police are investigating the murder. 警察正在调查这件谋杀案。 2. We might be able to help you; I\'ll investigate the possibilities. 我们也许能帮助你，我要研究一下这种可能性。', '形容词: investigable 过去式: investigated 过去分词: investigated 现在分词: investigating 第三人称单数: investigates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('persuasion', '[pər\'sweɪʒn]', 'n.说服,说服力', '1. Mr. Abel needed no more remonstrance or persuasion. 阿伯尔少爷再不需要什么劝告或说服了。 2. His father was reached by their persuasion at last. 他的父亲最后终于被他们说服了。 3. After a lot of persuasion, she agreed to go. 经过多次劝说后，她同意去了。 4. He was sweetened by her persuasion. 在她的劝说下他变得心平气和了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('detach', '[dɪ\'tætʃ]', 'vt.分开,分离,分遣,派遣(军队)', '1. He detached a link from a chain. 他从链子上拆下一个链环。 2. I tried to detach myself from the reality of these terrible events. 我尽力使自己从这些可怕事件的现实中摆脱出来。 3. We should detach good apples from bad. 我们必须把好的苹果与坏的分开. 4. He detached a link from a chain. 他从链子上拆下一个链环。', '形容词: detachable 副词: detachably 名词: detachability 过去式: detached 过去分词: detached 现在分词: detaching 第三人称单数: detaches');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('napkin', '[\'næpkɪn]', 'n.餐巾,餐巾纸,<英>尿布,<美>月经带', '1. I need another plate and a napkin. 我再要一只碟子和一条餐巾。 2. He wipes his mouth on the napkin. 他用餐巾擦了擦嘴， 3. The mother laid a piece of napkin under the baby\'s body. 这位母亲在婴儿的身体下面铺了一块尿布。 4. According to the demand, it can produce ultra-thin cotton-core or leakage Barrier sanitary napkin. 根据要求可装配超薄棉芯卫生巾，可装配立体护围面料成型。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('prevail', '[prɪ\'veɪl]', 'vi.流行,盛行,获胜,成功', '1. This old custom does not prevail now. 这种旧风俗现在已经不流行了。 2. Misty weather prevails in this part of the country. 该国的这一地区天气多雾。 3. Virtue will prevail against evil. 美德定将战胜邪恶。 4. I tried to prevail on him to stay. 我曾试图说服他留下。', '名词: prevailer 过去式: prevailed 过去分词: prevailed 现在分词: prevailing 第三人称单数: prevails');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('abuse', '[ə\'bjuːs]', 'n.滥用,虐待,辱骂,陋习;v.滥用,虐待,辱骂', '1. The government has set up a working party to look into the problem of drug abuse. 政府已成立工作组调查滥用毒品问题。 2. His political reputation was tainted by his abuse of the power. 他因滥用职权而破坏了政治声誉。 3. He greeted me with a stream of abuse. 他见到我就连声辱骂。 4. It\'s easy to abuse one\'s power. 人容易滥用权力。', '名词: abuser 过去式: abused 过去分词: abused 现在分词: abusing 第三人称单数: abuses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rigorous', '[\'rɪɡərəs]', 'adj.严格的,严厉的,严酷的,严峻的', '1. The planes have to undergo rigorous safety checks. 这些飞机得接受非常严格的安全检查。 2. The work failed to meet their rigorous standards. 工作没有达到他们的严格标准。 3. It further implements the safe production responsibility system, and enforces rigorous safe production laws and regulations and a related accountability system. 进一步实行安全生产责任体系，加强严厉的安全生产法规和相关责任体系。 4. He lived through the rigorous trials of revolutionary war. 他经受了革命战争的严峻考验。', '副词: rigorously 名词: rigorousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('contribution', '[ˌkɑːntrɪ\'bjuːʃn]', 'n.捐献,贡献,投稿', '1. Don\'t undervalue Jim\'s contribution to the research. 不要低估了吉姆在研究工作中的贡献。 2. He has made an important contribution to the company\'s success. 他对公司的成功作出了重要的贡献。 3. All contribution, however small, will be greatly appreciated. 所有捐款，无论数目多么少，我们都深表感谢。 4. The union successfully negotiated increased employer contributions to the health benefits package. 工会成功地让雇主增加对医疗福利的捐赠。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('regiment', '[\'redʒɪmənt]', 'n大量，v严格的管', '1. Our regiment suffered heavy casualties. 我团伤亡惨重。 2. He became a trooper in the Royal Tank Regiment. 他当上了皇家坦克团的装甲兵。', '形容词: regimental 副词: regimentally 名词: regimentation 过去式: regimented 过去分词: regimented 现在分词: regimenting 第三人称单数: regiments');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('caption', '[\'kæpʃn]', 'n.标题，说明,字幕;vt.加上标题,加上说明', '1. There is a caption under the picture. 图片下边附有说明。 2. The Vatican said it wanted the caption removed. 梵蒂冈说，它希望撤掉这段文字。', '过去式: captioned 过去分词: captioned 现在分词: captioning 第三人称单数: captions');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tribute', '[\'trɪbjuːt]', 'n.贡品,礼物,颂词,殷勤,贡物', '1. The victorious nations are demanding tribute from their former enemies. 战胜国要求战败国向其进奉贡品。 2. Many Greek cities had to send yearly tribute to Athens. 许多希腊城市不得不每年向雅典进贡。 3. The musician gave full tribute to his former teacher. 这位音乐家盛赞了他过去的老师。 4. He paid tribute to the way the country had forged national unity. 他称赞这个国家加强民族团结的方式。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('evoke', '[ɪ\'voʊk]', 'vt.唤起,引起,博得', '1. Songs can evoke old memories. 歌曲可以唤起往日的回忆。 2. Pieces of fine art may evoke emotional or spiritual responses in us. 一件件精美的艺术品可以唤起我们情感和精神上的响应。 3. The photographs evoked strong memories of our holidays in France. 照片唤起了我们在法国度假的深深的记忆。 4. His case is unlikely to evoke public sympathy. 他的情况不大可能引起公众的同情。', '形容词: evocable 过去式: evoked 过去分词: evoked 现在分词: evoking 第三人称单数: evokes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('executive', '[ɪg\'zɛkjətɪv]', 'adj.实行的,执行的,行政的;n.执行者,经理主管人员', '1. The executive manager tossed out my application. 行政经理拒绝了我的申请。 2. I was allowed to sit in on an executive meeting. 我获准列席一次行政会议。 3. He is on the executive committee. 他是该执行委员会委员。 4. An executive should be experienced in administration. 一个管理者应有行政管理的经验。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('luxury', '[\'lʌkʃəri]', 'n.奢侈,华贵', '1. The increasing sale of luxury goods is an index of the country\'s prosperity. 奢侈商品销售量日增是该国繁荣的标志。 2. The government has imposed strict controls over the import of luxury goods. 政府对奢侈品的进口采取了严格的管制。 3. If he can afford a luxury yacht, then a fortiori he can afford to pay his debts. 他若能买得起豪华的快艇，就更能匀出钱来还债了。 4. In old society, the gentry lived in luxury. 在旧社会，贵族们生活奢侈。', '名词复数: luxuries');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('collapse', '[kə\'læps]', 'n.倒塌,崩溃,失败,虚脱;vi.倒塌,崩溃,瓦解,失败,病倒', '1. The roof collapsed under the weight of snow. 房顶在雪的重压下突然坍塌下来。 2. If you work too hard,your health may collapse. 如果你工作太累的话，你可能病倒。 3. The enterprise collapsed through lack of support. 该企业因无力支持而倒闭。 4. He collapsed the wheelchair and put it on the boat. 他将轮椅折叠起来放在船上。 5. A flood caused the collapse of the bridge. 洪水使桥倒塌了。', '形容词: collapsible 名词: collapsibility 过去式: collapsed 过去分词: collapsed 现在分词: collapsing 第三人称单数: collapses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fellowship', '[\'feloʊʃɪp]', 'n.伙伴关系,交情,团体,奖学金,友谊', '1. They offer students counselling and fellowship. 他们向学生提供辅导并伸出友谊之手。 2. They offered him the hand of fellowship when he was in difficulties. 当他身处困境时，他们向他伸出了友谊之手。 3. Aleck belonged to a fellowship of revenge. 亚力克属于一个报仇团体。 4. After their initial expedition to Dujiangyan, members of Mr Sun\'s fellowship were soon faced with a number of organisational and logistical constraints. 在抵达都江堰后不久，成都天主教青年团体的成员就遇到了许多组织与后勤方面的约束。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('gamble', '[\'ɡæmbl]', 'n.冒险;v.赌博,投机,孤注一掷', '1. He spends all his time gambling in the casino. 他把时间都消磨在赌场的赌博上。 2. He gambled all his winnings on the last race. 他把赢得的钱全都压在最后一场赛马上了。 3. I wouldn\'t gamble on the weather being fine. 我可不指望天气能一直好下去。 4. Drive carefully and don\'t gamble with your life. 小心驾驶,别拿你的生命冒险。 5. The gamble paid off. 赌赢了。', '名词: gambler 过去式: gambled 过去分词: gambled 现在分词: gambling 第三人称单数: gambles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('devise', '[dɪ\'vaɪz]', 'vt.设计,发明,图谋,作出(计划),想出(办法),遗赠给;n.遗赠', '1. This time we\'ll devise a better solution. 这次我们将设计一种新的解决方案。 2. The government devised a scheme for redeveloping the city center. 政府制定了市中心重建计划。 3. He devised a new type of transistor. 他发明了一种新的晶体管。', '形容词: devisable 名词: deviser 过去式: devised 过去分词: devised 现在分词: devising 第三人称单数: devises');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('stride', '[straɪd]', 'v.大步走(过),跨过,大步行走;n.步幅', '1. In a few strides he crossed the room. 他几大步就穿过了房间。 2. I was three strides from the door. 我距离那门有三大步远。 3. In a big stride he came out of the room. 他一个箭步出了房间。 4. The boy walked with a confident manly stride. 这男孩以自信的男人步伐行走。 5. The boy is too young to stride the ditch. 孩子太小跨不过这条沟。 6. China is striding ahead in her economic construction. 中国正在经济建设方面大步前进。', '名词: strider 过去式: strode 过去分词: stridden 现在分词: striding 第三人称单数: strides');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('clockwise', '[\'klɑːkwaɪz]', 'adj.顺时针方向的;adv.顺时针方向地', '1. It may whirl either clockwise or counterclockwise. 它可能顺时针方向或反时针方向旋转。 2. Regulation is accomplished by rotating the handwheel clockwise. 规则要求按顺时针方向旋转手轮。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fake', '[feɪk]', 'n.假货,欺骗;adj.假的;vt.伪造,赝造,捏造,假造,仿造;vi.伪装', '1. Cops arrest 8 men who manufacture and sale fake collage notice . 警察在本月初逮捕了8名伪造和贩卖假大学录取通知书的人. 2. I can\'t believe he sold me a lousy fake watch! 我真不敢相信,他居然卖给我一块糟糕的假表! 3. He looked like a postman but he was really a fake. 他看上去像个邮递员，但实际上是假冒的。 4. On closer examination the painting was proved to be a fake. 再经仔细观察，证实那幅画是膺品。 5. He faked his father\'s signature. 他伪造父亲的签字。 6. Every politician has to fake a little. 每个政治家都是有点矫揉造作。', '过去式: faked 过去分词: faked 现在分词: faking 第三人称单数: fakes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('perception', '[pər\'sepʃn]', 'n.理解,感知,感觉,DPS公司出的数字影像压缩卡', '1. The public\'s perception of him is slowly changing. 公众对他的观念正在慢慢地发生变化。 2. His analysis of the problem showed great perception. 他对该问题的分析显示出敏锐的洞察力。 3. One of his goals is improving students\' power of perception in this matter. 他的目标之一是提高学生对该问题的认识能力。', '形容词: perceptional');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('passion', '[\'pæʃn]', 'n.激情,热情', '1. The dying embers of the former passion can still be seen in his articles. 往日激情将熄的余烬仍可从他的文章中看出来。 2. Life needs curiosity, enthusiasm and passion, which depends on how we think of the world. 生活需要好奇心、热情和激情,这都取决于我们怎么看待这个世界。 3. I have a passion for American literature. 我酷爱美国文学。 4. His passion for reading never deserted him. 他从未放弃过对读书的热爱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('accommodate', '[ə\'kɑːmədeɪt]', 'vt.供应,供给,使适应,调节,和解,向...提供,容纳,调和;vi.适应', '1. This hotel can accommodate up to 500 guests. 这旅馆可供500位来宾住宿。 2. We must accommodate ourselves to circumstances. 我们必须适应环境。 3. One flat can accommodate a family of five. 一套单元房可容纳一个五口之家。 4. The bank is accommodating its customers more than it used to. 这家银行现在给客户贷款比以前多了。 5. Her eyes took a while to accommodate to the darkness. 过了一会儿，她的眼睛才能适应黑暗。', '形容词: accommodative 名词: accommodativeness 过去式: accommodated 过去分词: accommodated 现在分词: accommodating 第三人称单数: accommodates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('beam', '[biːm]', 'n.梁,桁条,(光线的)束,柱,电波,横梁;v.播送', '1. She beamed at me. 她对我微笑。 2. His face(He) is beaming with delight. 他高兴得笑容满面。 3. From a sky of untarnished blue the sun beamed down upon Beijing. 阳光透过万里碧空照耀着北京城。 4. Television began beaming the national nominating conventions into the homes of Americans. 电视开始向美国家庭播放总统候选人全国提名大会的情况。 5. A rotary table helps to optimize the beam incidence angle. 一张旋转的桌子有助于将光线影响之方式角最佳化。', '过去式: beamed 过去分词: beamed 现在分词: beaming 第三人称单数: beams');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('culminate', '[\'kʌlmɪneɪt]', 'v.达到顶点', '1. Her career culminated in her appointment as director. 她一生事业的顶峰是当上董事。 2. The Christmas party culminated in the distribution of presents. 圣诞晚会在分发礼物时达到最高潮。 3. Everyone feared that the boundary dispute between these two countries would culminate in a war. 人人都担心，这两国间的边境争端将以一场战争告终。 4. Their marriage culminated their long friendship. 他俩交友有年,最后终成眷属。', '名词: culmination 过去式: culminated 过去分词: culminated 现在分词: culminating 第三人称单数: culminates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('isolate', '[\'aɪsəleɪt]', 'vt.使隔离,使孤立,使绝缘,离析;n.隔离种群', '1. We must isolate the handful of enemies to the maximum. 我们要最大限度地孤立一小撮敌人。 2. We should never isolate ourselves from the masses. 我们永远不能脱离群众。 3. The patient should isolate from his child. 这个病人必须立刻和他的孩子隔离。 4. Scientists have isolated the virus causing the epidemic. 科学家们已分离出引起这种流行病的病毒。 5. It would mean inability to close in and isolate him. 这样，就不能把敌人驱逐到狭小的孤立的阵地上去。', '名词: isolator 过去式: isolated 过去分词: isolated 现在分词: isolating 第三人称单数: isolates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('overpass', '[\'oʊvərpæs]', 'n.<美>天桥,陆桥;vt.胜过,通过,忽视', '1. Cross over the pedestrian overpass. 过人行天桥。 2. Overpass is so far away .Let\'s jaywalk. 天桥太远了，我们横穿马路吧。 3. An overpass bridged the highway. 立交桥跨越高速公路。 4. Would you have a look at the overpass in front of us. 你看前面的立交桥。', '过去式: overpassed/overpast 过去分词: overpassed/overpast 现在分词: overpassing 第三人称单数: overpasses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dictate', '[\'dɪkteɪt]', 'v.口述,口授,使听写,指令,指示,命令,规定;n.指示(指理智,变心)', '1. The teacher dictated a passage to the class. 老师给全班同学听写一段文章。 2. He was dictating a letter to his secretary. 他在向秘书口授信稿。 3. He can\'t write but he can dictate. 他不会写但会说。 4. Businessmen often dictate their letters. 商人常口授信稿令人笔录。 5. If I had the dictatorial power in a dictatorship, I will dictate those IT be kept in detention for appearing too pretentious. 我假如拥有独裁政治的专断权，我会命令把她关起来，罪名是外表炫耀做作。', '过去式: dictated 过去分词: dictated 现在分词: dictating 第三人称单数: dictates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('articulate', '[ɑːr\'tɪkjuleɪt]', 'adj.有关节的,发音清晰的;vt.用关节连接,接合,清晰明白地说', '1. Articulate speech is essential for a teacher. 对教师来说,口齿清楚是必不可少的。 2. I\'m a little deaf, please articulate your words carefully. 我有些耳聋，请把话仔细地说清楚。 3. She\'s unusually articulate for a ten-year-old. 作为一个十岁的孩子来说，她的表达力是非常强的。 4. Young people are articulate about the skills they need for everyday life. 年轻人善于表达他们应付日常生活所需的技能。 5. She was too frightened to articulate. 她吓得连话也说不清。', '副词: articulately 名词: articulateness 过去式: articulated 过去分词: articulated 现在分词: articulating 第三人称单数: articulates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('barely', '[\'berli]', 'adv.仅仅,刚刚,几乎不能', '1. He is so weak that he can barely stand up. 他身体虚弱几乎站不起来。 2. I had barely started speaking when he interrupted me. 我刚刚开始讲话，他便打断了我。 3. We had barely enough money to last through the weekend. 我们的钱只能勉强维持到周末。 4. The room was barely furnished. 这个房间里陈设简陋。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('consequently', '[\'kɑːnsəkwentli]', 'adv.从而,因此', '1. The scandal being exposed, he was removed from office consequently. 他的丑闻被曝光了，他因此被调离了职位。 2. The company went bankrupt and consequently he lost his job. 公司破产,因此他失业了。 3. My car broke down and consequently I was late. 我的汽车坏了 4. The rain was heavy, and consequently the road was flooded. 雨很大, 所以路被淹没了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rational', '[\'ræʃnəl]', 'adj.理性的,合理的,推理的;n.[数]有理数', '1. Your choice was perfectly rational under the circumstances. 在那种情况下,你的选择是相当合理的。 2. Man is a rational being. 人是有理性的生物。 3. No rational person would go to work in his pyjamas. 任何神智正常的人都不会穿着睡衣去上班。 4. The rational numbers also fit into this scheme. 有理数也适用于这个图形。', '副词: rationally 名词: rationalness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('applaud', '[ə\'plɔːd]', 'v.拍手喝彩,称赞,赞同', '1. He leaped to his feet and began to applaud. 他跳起来开始鼓掌。 2. Please don\'t applaud until everyone has performed. 请在每个人表演完毕后再鼓掌。 3. Should I applaud my husband or chastise him? 我是该称赞还是责罚我的丈夫呢？ 4. Before I begin to flame anything, I would like to applaud a few folks. 在我开始对任何事激动之前,我想称赞一些人。', '形容词: applaudable 副词: applaudably 名词: applauder 过去式: applauded 过去分词: applauded 现在分词: applauding 第三人称单数: applauds');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('serial', '[\'sɪriəl]', 'adj.连续的', '1. After breakfast, he went on with his serial. 早饭之后,他继续写他的连载故事。 2. Downloaded serial numbers may not be transferred. 下载的序列号不能传输。 3. Please write down your serial number. 请记录下您的序列号。 4. Most of her novels have been made into television serials at some time. 同时她的多数小说拍成了电视连续剧。 5. Currency notes have serial number. 钞票上有连续的号码。', '副词: serially');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pessimistic', '[ˌpesɪ\'mɪstɪk]', '悲观的', '1. I have to say I\'m rather pessimistic. 我得说我相当悲观。 2. Her pessimistic attitude turns him off. 她那悲观的态度很令他不高兴。 3. There is a pessimistic tone to what he is saying. 他的话语中带着悲观的调子。 4. This might account for his pessimistic views. 这也许是他持悲观主义观点的原因。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('confirm', '[kən\'fɜːrm]', 'vt.确定,批准,使巩固,使有效;v.确认,(基督教中)给...行按手礼', '1. His letter confirmed everything. 他的信证实了一切。 2. The treaty was confirmed by the president. 条约已被总统批准。 3. Could you confirm the dispatch date? 您可以确定发货日期吗?', '形容词: confirmable 名词: confirmability 过去式: confirmed 过去分词: confirmed 现在分词: confirming 第三人称单数: confirms');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('eagle', '[\'iːɡl]', 'n.鹰,鹰状标饰', '1. The eagle held a mouse in its claws. 鹰用爪抓住了老鼠。 2. The eagle dived down on the rabbit. 那只鹰向兔子猛扑下来。 3. The eagle poised in mid-air ready to swoop on its prey. 那鹰在半空中盘旋准备扑向猎物。', '过去式: eagled 过去分词: eagled 现在分词: eagling 第三人称单数: eagles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('heave', '[hiːv]', 'v.举起;n.举起', '1. They heave at the heavy box, but can not lift it. 他们想搬动那只很重的箱子，但抬不起来。 2. He hove a chair through the window. 他把椅子从窗户中抛出。 3. Heave the rocks into the ravine. 把这些石头扔进深谷里。 4. It\'s a very bad thing to heave things around. 把东西到处乱扔是很不好的习惯。 5. With one more heave, we got the box onto the shelf. 我们再使把劲,就把箱子抬到架子上了。', '名词: heaver 过去式: heaved 过去分词: heaved 现在分词: heaving 第三人称单数: heaves');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ascertain', '[ˌæsər\'teɪn]', 'vt.确定,探知', '1. I ascertain that he was murdered. 我确定他是被谋杀的。 2. I ascertained the disease to be diphtheria. 我确定该病为白喉。 3. The detective was trying to ascertain exactly who was at the party. 这个侦探试图查明都有谁参加了聚会。 4. I\'m going to ascertain the truth. 我要查明真相。', '形容词: ascertainable 副词: ascertainably 名词: ascertainableness 过去式: ascertained 过去分词: ascertained 现在分词: ascertaining 第三人称单数: ascertains');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('deteriorate', '[dɪ\'tɪriəreɪt]', 'v.(使)恶化', '1. We cannot allow the situation to deteriorate. 我们不容许情况恶化。 2. Relation between the two countries have deteriorated sharply in recent week. 最近几周那两个国家间的关系严重恶化了。 3. Food is apt to deteriorate in summer. 食物在夏天容易变质。 4. The discussion deteriorated into a bitter quarrel. 这场讨论演变成了激烈的争吵。', '形容词: deteriorative 名词: deterioration 过去式: deteriorated 过去分词: deteriorated 现在分词: deteriorating 第三人称单数: deteriorates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('version', '[\'vɜːrʒn]', 'n.译文,译本,翻译', '1. The new version of this dictionary is not in use yet. 这本字典的新版本还未通行。 2. The two newspapers gave different versions of what happened. 两家报纸对发生的事说法不一。 3. The book was translated into many versions and sold all over the world. 这本书被翻译成多种译文并行销全球。 4. This shirt is a cheaper version of the one I saw in that shop. 这件衬衫同我在那家商店里见到的几乎一样，但它是便宜货。', '形容词: versional');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('velvet', '[\'velvɪt]', 'n.天鹅绒,柔软,光滑;adj.天鹅绒的,柔软的,光滑的', '1. The lawn looks like green velvet. 那草坪看上去就像绿色的天鹅绒。 2. The sofa has been finished in red velvet. 沙发的外表已经包好了红色的天鹅绒。 3. She wore a jacket and skirt of purple velvet. 她身穿紫色天鹅绒上衣和裙子。 4. The queen assumed a velvet robe. 王后穿了一件天鹅绒长袍', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('blank', '[blæŋk]', 'adj.空白的,空着的,失色的,没有表情的;n.空白,<美>表格', '1. Give me a blank sheet of paper, please. 请给我一张空白的纸。 2. Many blank spaces are still left in the suburbs. 郊区仍留有许多空地。 3. Her explanations were met with blank incomprehension. 大家对她的解释茫然不解。 4. His expression remained studiously blank. 他的表情仍是那种故作茫然状。 5. My life before that is a blank to me. 那以前的生活对我来说已是一片空白。', '副词: blankly 比较级: blanker 最高级: blankest 名词: blankness 过去式: blanked 过去分词: blanked 现在分词: blanking 第三人称单数: blanks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('weird', '[wɪrd]', 'adj.怪异的,超自然的,神秘的,不可思议的,超乎事理之外的;n.<古><苏格兰>命运,预言,符咒', '1. He looks like nothing on earth in those weird clothes. 他穿著奇装异服难看极了。 2. Jane, I found that guy somewhat weird. 珍妮, 我发觉那家伙有点古怪。 3. That was really a weird movie. 那部电影真怪异! 4. I heard weird shrieks in the darkness. 我在黑暗中听到奇怪的尖叫声。', '副词: weirdly 比较级: weirder 最高级: weirdest 名词: weirdness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('slippery', '[\'slɪpəri]', 'adj.滑的,光滑的', '1. A wet road is usually slippery. 潮湿的路往往是滑的。 2. The road was slippery after the rain. 下雨之后道路很滑。 3. Don\'t lend any money to that slippery person. 不要借钱给那个狡猾的家伙。 4. The England striker says the slippery Portuguese winker got him sent off in Saturday\'s World Cup clash. 英格兰前锋说这个狡猾的葡萄牙人在周六的比赛中迫使自己下场后挤眉弄眼。', '比较级: slipperier 最高级: slipperiest 名词: slipperiness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('shield', '[ʃiːld]', 'n.防护物,护罩,盾,盾状物;vt.(from)保护,防护;v.遮蔽', '1. The shield protected him from the blows of his enemy. 这盾牌保护他免受敌人的打击。 2. There is a shield in the badge of PLA men. 解放军的徽章上有着盾状物。 3. He must pile more sand on top as a shield. 他必须在顶上多加些沙土作为防御物。 4. Motorcyclists must wear helmets to shield them from injury. 摩托车手必须戴头盔保护自己免受伤害。', '名词: shielder 过去式: shielded 过去分词: shielded 现在分词: shielding 第三人称单数: shields');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('restrict', '[rɪ\'strɪkt]', 'vt.限制,约束,限定', '1. In a move to restrict imports, the government raised custom duties. 政府在限制进口的措施中提高了关税。 2. Recent laws have tended to restrict the freedom of the press. 新法例有限制新闻自由的趋势。 3. I restrict myself to smoking two cigarettes a day. 我限定自己每天只抽两支烟。 4. Fog restricted visibility. 雾天能见度很低。', '名词: restrictor 过去式: restricted 过去分词: restricted 现在分词: restricting 第三人称单数: restricts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('psychological', '[ˌsaɪkə\'lɑːdʒɪkl]', 'adj.心理(上)的', '1. There could be some psychological explanation for his bad health. 他的健康不佳可能有心理上的原因。 2. Inhibition of natural impulses may cause psychological problems. 压抑自然的冲动可能会引起心理上的问题。 3. Psychological insight is another requirement. 还有一个要求就是心理上的洞察力。', '副词: psychologically 异体字: psychologic');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('aerial', '[\'eriəl]', 'adj.航空的,生活在空气中的,空气的,高耸的;n.天线', '1. He showed me some aerial photographs. 他给我看了一些空中拍摄的照片。 2. Aerial pollution is a problem that should be solved quickly. 空气污染是一个亟待解决的问题。 3. Airline is the service industry that offers the aerial affair of transport service. 航空公司属于提供航空运输业务的服务行业。 4. The birds perched on the television aerial. 鸟停在电视天线上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('breed', '[briːd]', 'v.(使)繁殖,教养,抚养;n.品种,种类', '1. Wild animals don\'t breed well in captivity. 野生动物圈养时不好繁殖。 2. How often do lions breed? 狮子多长时间产一次仔? 3. I breed some chicks for pets. 我养了一些小鸡当宠物。 4. Spartan youths were bred as warriors. 斯巴达青年被培养成战士. 5. Spaniel is a breed of dog with large ears. 西班牙猎狗是一种长着大耳朵的猎狗。', '过去式: bred 过去分词: bred 现在分词: breeding 第三人称单数: breeds');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('excess', '[ɪk\'ses]', 'n.过度,剩于,无节制,超过,超额;adj.过度的,额外的', '1. Our school has a student number in excess of 800. 我们学校的学生数超过八百人。 2. His excesses at parties are well known. 尽人皆知他在聚会上十分放肆。 3. An excess of fat in one\'s diet can lead to heart disease. 食物中脂肪过多会导致心脏病。 4. This wave of excess density is sound. 这种过剩密度的波就是声波。 5. The fat boy went on a diet to get rid of his excess weight. 这个胖男孩节制饮食以减轻过量的体重。', '过去式: excessed 过去分词: excessed 现在分词: excessing 第三人称单数: excesses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('primarily', '[praɪ\'merəli]', 'adv.首先,起初,主要地,根本上', '1. Most linguists would say they were concerned primarily with the structure of languages. 大多数语言学家都会说，他们主要研究各种语言的结构。 2. He is primarily liable for his debt. 他对债务负主要责任或他是主要债务人。 3. This building was primarily intended to be a dinning hall. 这座建筑原来是打算用作餐厅的。 4. Primarily a teacher, she later became a writer. 她原先是教师，后来成了作家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pedestrian', '[pə\'destriən]', 'n.步行者;adj.徒步的,呆板的,通俗的', '1. We enjoy all pedestrian activities. 我们喜欢所有的步行活动。 2. They ought to stop at the pedestrian crossing. 他们该停在人行横道上。 3. He was rather a pedestrian student. 他原是个相当平常的学生。 4. We present this approach in a pedestrian version. 我们用平铺直叙的方式介绍这个方法。 5. The driver was slanging a pedestrian who had got in his way. 那司机破口大骂挡他的路的行人。', '名词: pedestrianism');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('royalty', '[\'rɔɪəlti]', 'n.皇室,王权', '1. She claims to be descended from royalty. 她声称她是皇室后裔。 2. Salt was an important item on the table of royalty. 盐在皇家餐桌上占有重要的位置。 3. This palace was home to French royalty. 这座宫殿是法国皇族的住宅。 4. His income is mainly from royalty. 他的收入主要来自版税。', '名词复数: royalties');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('massive', '[\'mæsɪv]', 'adj.厚重的,大块的,魁伟的,结实的', '1. A massive boulder blocked the entrance of the cave. 一块巨大的圆石堵住了山洞的入口。 2. We have seen massive changes in recent years. 这几年我们经历了巨大的变化。 3. The soldier suffered a massive haemorrhage and died soon after. 那个战士经受了大量出血的痛苦，不久便去世了。 4. We must make massive efforts to improve things. 我们必须作出极大的努力去改善一切。', '副词: massively 名词: massiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('inspiration', '[ˌɪnspə\'reɪʃn]', 'n.灵感', '1. Many poets and artists have drawn their inspiration from nature. 许多诗人和艺术家从大自然中获得他们的灵感。 2. Her speeches have ever been a fount of inspiration to her audiences. 她的演说对于听众来说永远是灵感之源。 3. His wife was a constant inspiration to him. 他的妻子经常鼓励他。 4. Let\'s give mutual support and inspiration to each other. 让我们互相支持，互相鼓励。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('witness', '[\'wɪtnəs]', 'n.[律]证人,目击者,证据,证明,证词;vt.目击,为...作证,证明,表明;vi.作证,成为证据', '1. The witness was telling about the whole accident. 目击者正在讲述整个事故的过程。 2. The lawyer examined the witness. 律师讯问了证人。 3. A material witness failed to appear in court. 一名重要的证人没有出庭。 4. Did anyone witness the traffic accident? 有谁目击了这场交通事故？ 5. The empty cupboard was a witness of his poverty. 空的食橱就是他贫穷的证明。', '名词: witnesser 过去式: witnessed 过去分词: witnessed 现在分词: witnessing 第三人称单数: witnesses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tribe', '[traɪb]', 'n.部落,部族', '1. A council of elders governs the tribe. 有个叫长老会的组织治理这个部落。 2. Our tribe is under a curse. 我们的部落正受诅咒。 3. I have heard the cannibal tribe in stories. 我在故事里听说过食人部落。 4. That Indian man is a member of the neighbouring tribe. 那个印第安人是临近部落的成员。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('odor', '[\'oʊdə]', 'n.气味,名声', '1. The flowers gave off a fragrant odor. 花发出一阵幽香。 2. The odor penetrated the whole room. 整个房间里弥漫着这种气味。 3. The penetrating odor of garlic soon filled the entire apartment. 大蒜刺鼻的气味很快就弥散了整个屋子 4. What he had done put him in better odor. 他的所作所为使他的名声得到改善。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('refresh', '[rɪ\'freʃ]', 'v.(使)精神振作,(使)精力恢复,更新', '1. A cool drink refreshed me after my long walk. 走了很长的一段路之后，一杯冷饮使我恢复了精神。 2. He has drunk one cup of coffee to refresh oneself. 他喝了一杯咖啡提神。 3. I refreshed myself with a cup of coffee. 我喝了一杯咖啡给自己提提神。 4. Let me refresh your memory with some fact. 我来提几件事帮你恢复记忆吧。', '过去式: refreshed 过去分词: refreshed 现在分词: refreshing 第三人称单数: refreshes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('clasp', '[klæsp]', 'n.扣子,钩,紧握,抱住;v.扣紧,紧握,搂抱,密切合作', '1. The button won\'t clasp. 扣子扣不上。', '过去式: clasped 过去分词: clasped 现在分词: clasping 第三人称单数: clasps');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('keen', '[kiːn]', 'adj.锋利的,敏锐的,敏捷的,热心的,渴望的', '1. The blind have a keen sense of touch. 盲人有敏锐的触觉。 2. Their keen eyes can penetrate the water to a depth of forty feet. 他们锐利的眼睛能透过水面看到40 英尺的深处。 3. Be brave, a fence between makes love more keen. 勇敢点,受到阻隔的爱情会更强烈。 4. The razor has a very keen edge. 这把剃刀有锋利的口。', '副词: keenly 比较级: keener 最高级: keenest 名词: keenness 过去式: keened 过去分词: keened 现在分词: keening 第三人称单数: keens');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('guarantee', '[ˌɡærən\'tiː]', 'n.保证,保证书,担保,抵押品;vt.保证,担保', '1. A diploma is no guarantee of efficiency. 持有文凭不能保证工作效率一定高。 2. I guarantee that this will not happen again. 我保证此类事情不会再发生。 3. We guarantee the fastness of these dyes. 我们担保这些染料不褪色。 4. He put up his house as a guarantee. 他提供房子作为担保。 5. A diploma is no guarantee of efficiency. 持有文凭不能保证工作效率一定高。', '过去式: guaranteed 过去分词: guaranteed 现在分词: guaranteeing 第三人称单数: guarantees');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('flaw', '[flɔː]', 'n.缺点,裂纹,瑕疵,一阵狂风;vt.使破裂,使有缺陷,使无效;vi.生裂缝,变的有缺陷', '1. Unfortunately, I found that your work had a tiny flaw. 很不幸 2. The flaw in this vase makes it less valuable. 这个花瓶因为有点缺陷，不那么值钱了。 3. I can\'t find a flaw in his argument. 在他的论点中,我找不到任何破绽。 4. Your argument has a fatal flaw. 你的论点有一个致命的错误。 5. The jealous colleague decided to flaw the project plans. 这名嫉妒的同事决定给这些项目计划搞破坏。', '形容词: flawy 过去式: flawed 过去分词: flawed 现在分词: flawing 第三人称单数: flaws');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cavity', '[\'kævəti]', 'n.洞,空穴,[解剖]腔', '1. I have a toothache because there is a cavity in one of my teeth. 我牙疼，因为我的一颗牙齿上有个洞。 2. He jammed the material in until the cavity was full. 他用力把材料塞进去，直到空穴完全填满。 3. The peritoneal cavity is a closed sac. 腹膜腔是一个封闭的囊腔。 4. The tumor growing in the enteric cavity blocked excretion of food. 肿瘤在肠腔里生长阻碍了食物排泄。', '名词复数: cavities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('overflow', '[ˌoʊvər\'floʊ]', 'n.溢出,超值,泛滥,充满,洋溢;v.(使)泛滥,(使)溢出,(使)充溢', '1. We must harness the rivers which overflow annually. 我们必须治理那些每年泛滥的河流。 2. The river overflowed its banks. 河水漫过了两岸。 3. The crowd overflowed the auditorium. 人群挤得礼堂无法容纳。 4. Her heart was overflowing with joy. 她的心里洋溢着喜悦。 5. Put a bowl underneath to catch the overflow. 把盆放在下面接住溢出物。', '过去式: overflowed 过去分词: overflowed 现在分词: overflowing 第三人称单数: overflows');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('veto', '[\'viːtoʊ]', 'n.否决,禁止,否决权;vt.否决,禁止', '1. Will they interpose their veto again? 他们还会再次否决吗? 2. An abstention is not regarded as a veto. 弃权不视为否决。 3. Mr Bush\'s veto does not kill stem-cell research. 布什的否决没有彻底封杀干细胞研究。 4. They carried the ministerial veto. 他们行使了内阁否决权。 5. The president last week vetoed the tax cut. 总统上个星期否决了减税法案。', '名词: vetoer 名词复数: vetoes 过去式: vetoed 过去分词: vetoed 现在分词: vetoing 第三人称单数: vetoes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('groove', '[ɡruːv]', 'n.(唱片等的)凹槽,惯例,最佳状态;vt.开槽于', '1. Wheels leave grooves in dirt roads. 车轮在泥路上留下凹痕。 2. Sliding doors and windows move in groove. 滑动门和滑动窗都在凹槽中移动。 3. The needle moves along the groove on a record. 唱针沿着唱片表面的细纹移动。 4. It\'s time to get out of the groove here. 该是摆脱这种枯燥乏味的生活方式的时候了。 5. The sink shelf is grooved so that the water will run off. 洗涤池上开槽是为了让水流走。', '过去式: grooved 过去分词: grooved 现在分词: grooving 第三人称单数: grooves');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sulfur', '[\'sʌlfə]', 'n.[化]硫磺,硫黄;vt.用硫磺处理', '1. Sulfur can be used to make gunpowder. 硫磺可以用来制造火药。 2. A sulfide compound contains at least two sulfur atoms per molecule. 多硫化物每个分子中至少含有两个硫原子的一种硫化物 3. Because the removal of phosphorus and sulfur require special condition that can be met only by the basic process. 因为除去钢中的磷和硫需要一些特殊的条件，这些条件只有碱性法才能满足。', '过去式: sulfured/sulphured 过去分词: sulfured/sulphured 现在分词: sulfuring/sulphuring 第三人称单数: sulfurs/sulphurs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('purify', '[\'pjʊrɪfaɪ]', 'vt.使纯净;v.净化', '1. The endless lea will purify your thought. 一望无际的草原会净化你的思想。 2. Let\'s purify air with a negative ion generator. 我们用负离子发生器净化一下空气吧。 3. We have forgotten that Water can cleanse,and Fire purify,and that the Earth is mother to us all. 我们已经忘了，水可以洗濯洁净，火可以精炼提纯，大地是每个人的母亲。 4. Hindus purify themselves by bathing in the river Ganges. 印度教徒在恒河中浸泡借以涤罪。', '形容词: purificatory 名词: purifier 过去式: purified 过去分词: purified 现在分词: purifying 第三人称单数: purifies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('arrangement', '[ə\'reɪndʒmənt]', 'n.排列,安排', '1. He introduced to us the symmetrical arrangement of the garden. 他为我们介绍了花园中对称的布局。 2. He knew the room arrangement well. 他对房间的布局是很清楚的。 3. This arrangement is agreeable to both sides. 这样安排对双方都合适。 4. We have made all the arrangements for the conference. 我们已做好会议的全部筹备工作。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('quartz', '[kwɔːrts]', 'n.石英', '1. Quartz crystal is perfectly crystallized. 石英晶体是完美的结晶。 2. Quartz crystals are seldom used in such handsets. 石英晶体是很少使用这种手机。', '形容词: quartzose');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fracture', '[\'fræktʃər]', 'n.破裂,骨折;v.(使)破碎,(使)破裂', '1. A fellow team member says it was a clean fracture without complications. 一位队友表示这只是纯粹的锁骨破碎，没有任何并发症。 2. He had several injuries, including three fractures. 他多处受伤，其中三处骨折。 3. If you sneeze too hard, you can fracture a rib. 打喷嚏太用力的话肋骨可能会骨折。 4. Many people predicted that the party would fracture and split. 很多人预言该党将分崩离析。 5. Her leg fractured in two places. 她的腿有两处骨折。', '过去式: fractured 过去分词: fractured 现在分词: fracturing 第三人称单数: fractures');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('option', '[\'ɑːpʃn]', 'n.选项,选择权,[经]买卖的特权', '1. He had no option but to agree. 他除了同意外别无选择。 2. I haven\'t much option in the matter. 在这件事情上我无可选择。 3. Make a list of the various options. 列出可供选择的项目。 4. He had optioned for a film several short stories about two policemen. 他为一部影片选择了几篇关于两位警察的短篇小说。', '过去式: optioned 过去分词: optioned 现在分词: optioning 第三人称单数: options');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pursuit', '[pər\'suːt]', 'n.追击', '1. His life is spent in the pursuit of pleasure. 他一生都在寻欢作乐。 2. We work hard in pursuit of happy life. 我们为追求幸福生活而努力工作。 3. What\'s your favorite pursuit? 你的爱好是什么？ 4. He exercises everyday in pursuit of health. 他为了健康而每天锻炼。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('target', '[\'tɑːrɡɪt]', 'n.目标,对象,靶子', '1. The sights of the gun must be in alignment with the target. 枪的瞄准器必须与射击目标对准成一线。 2. The shot was way off target. 这次射得远离目标。 3. A stationary target is easiest to aim at. 静止的目标是最容易瞄准的。 4. The company has met their export target. 该公司已经实现了它们的出口目标。 5. In the future, the Group will target its marketing and promotional activities to reach the mass of customers through cost effective means. 展望未来,集团将在具成本效益的情况下,以市场推广及宣传活动为目标,把九方推广至广大消费者。', '过去式: targeted 过去分词: targeted 现在分词: targeting 第三人称单数: targets');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('decade', '[\'dekeɪd]', 'n.十年,十', '1. Prices have risen steadily during the past decade. 在过去十年里，物价一直在上涨。 2. Several decades have elapsed since I graduated from the college. 我大学毕业已数十年了。 3. I believed that this struggle is going to go on and it might well be decided in the next decade. 我相信这一对抗还将会持续下去，并可能在下一个十年中得出结果。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('levy', '[\'levi]', 'n.征收,征税,征兵;v.征收,征集,征用', '1. The basis of the proposals is a levy of 0.25 per cent. 建议的征税基点为百分之零点二五。 2. The nation levied all able-bodied man for the war. 国家征召所有壮丁参战。 3. The government has decided to levy a tax on import cars. 政府决定征收进口汽车税。 4. The nation levied all able-bodied man for the war. 国家征召所有壮丁参战。 5. The court may have to levy on your estate to pay your debts. 法庭可能不得不扣押你的房地产，用来偿付你的债务。', '名词: levier 名词复数: levies 过去式: levied 过去分词: levied 现在分词: levying 第三人称单数: levies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('startle', '[\'stɑːrtl]', 'v.震惊', '1. He was startled by the news. 这消息使他大吃一惊。 2. He startled from sleep. 他从睡梦中惊醒起来。 3. The least noise would startle the timid child. 最小的响声也会吓着这个胆小的孩子的。 4. Let\'s hide ourselves behind the door and startle her. 藏在门后面，咱们吓她一下。 5. He gave me a startle. 他吓了我一跳。', '副词: startlingly 名词: startlingness 过去式: startled 过去分词: startled 现在分词: startling 第三人称单数: startles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('plead', '[pliːd]', 'vbl.plead的过去式及过去分词', '1. You should get a lawyer to plead for your case. 你该请一位律师为你的案子辩护。 2. I heard him plead in court only once. 我只有一次听到他在法庭上作辩护。 3. With that kind of man you will plead in vain. 你恳求那种人将是白费力气。 4. He would see her and plead his cause again in person. 他要去见她，当面再度恳求。', '形容词: pleadable 副词: pleadingly 名词: pleader 过去式: pleaded/pled 过去分词: pleaded/pled 现在分词: pleading 第三人称单数: pleads');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('worthwhile', '[ˌwɜːrθ\'waɪl]', 'adj.值得做的,值得出力的', '1. Thank you for making my visit so worthwhile. I shall treasure your friendship and kind hospitality you have given me. 感谢你们使我的访问如此有价值。我将珍惜我们之间的友谊及你们给予我的盛情款待。 2. That\'s worthwhile. 那是值得的。', '名词: worthwhileness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('shatter', '[\'ʃætər]', 'n.粉碎,碎片,落花(叶,粒等);vt.打碎,使散开,粉碎,破坏;vi.粉碎,损坏,落叶', '1. The glass shattered. 这杯子碎了。 2. She shattered the cup when she dropped it on the floor. 她把杯子掉在地板上,摔得粉碎。 3. My dreams have been shattered. 我的梦想已经破灭了。 4. Her experience of divorce shattered her illusions about love. 她的离婚经历使她对爱情的幻想破灭了。 5. The broken vase lay in shatters. 那只打碎了的花瓶的碎片撒了一地。', '副词: shatteringly 过去式: shattered 过去分词: shattered 现在分词: shattering 第三人称单数: shatters');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('promising', '[\'prɑːmɪsɪŋ]', 'adj.有希望的,有前途的', '1. After a promising start, the project soon fizzled out. 这项计划开始时很有希望,但不久就失败了。 2. For a time he was looked on as a promising writer. 人们一度认为他是一个有希望的作家。 3. The results of the experiments are very promising. 实验的结果充满了希望。 4. The coach is bringing on some promising youngsters in the reserve team. 教练正在帮助后备队中有前途的年轻人提高技术。', '副词: promisingly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('medium', '[\'miːdiəm]', 'n.媒体,方法,媒介;adj.中间的,中等的,半生熟的', '1. The blue cap is a medium size. 那顶蓝色的帽子就是中号的。 2. The clothes should be washed at medium temperature. 这衣服需以适中温度洗涤。 3. Commercial television is an effective medium for advertising. 商业电视是有效的广告宣传工具。 4. Sound travels through the medium of air. 声音通过空气这一媒介传播。', '名词复数: media');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bamboo', '[ˌbæm\'buː]', 'n.竹子', '1. He did athletic stunts on bamboo ladders. 他在竹梯上表演了体育绝技。 2. The piece of bamboo makes a musical sound. 这块竹片能发出悦耳的声音。 3. This armchair is made of bamboo. 这个扶手椅是用竹子做成的。 4. Use the bamboo very universal in China. 在中国使用竹子非常普遍。', '名词复数: bamboos');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('slick', '[slɪk]', 'adj.光滑的,熟练的,聪明的,华而不实的,陈腐的,平凡的;adv.灵活地,聪明地;vt.使光滑,使漂亮;n.平滑水面,平滑器,修光工具;vi.打扮整洁', '1. I advised them to watch out for slick spots on the sidewalk. 我叫他们当心人行道上路滑的地方。 2. The slick floor brought me down in a heavy fall. 光滑的地板把我重重地摔了一跤。 3. The hurricane carried away the roof as slick as a whistle. 飓风把屋顶不费吹灰之力地刮掉了。 4. I don\'t trust those slick salesmen. 我不信任那些油嘴滑舌的推销员。 5. He used to slick his hair everyday before school. 他曾经每天在上学之前梳好头发。 6. There is a slick of oil on the water. 水面上有一片浮油。', '副词: slickly 比较级: slicker 最高级: slickest 名词: slickness 过去式: slicked 过去分词: slicked 现在分词: slicking 第三人称单数: slicks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('imply', '[ɪm\'plaɪ]', 'vt.暗示,意味', '1. I don\'t wish to imply that you are wrong. 我无意暗示你错了。 2. What do you want to imply? 你要暗示什么? 3. His silence implied agreement. 他沉默不语意味着同意了。 4. Cheerfulness doesn\'t always imply happiness. 快活并不总是意味着幸福。', '过去式: implied 过去分词: implied 现在分词: implying 第三人称单数: implies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('industrial', '[ɪn\'dʌstriəl]', 'adj.工业的,产业的,实业的,从事工业的;n.工业工人,[商]工业股票', '1. She is an industrial designer. 她是工业设计师。 2. The industrial exposition will be held on September. 工业博览会将于九月召开。 3. The industrial revolution had taken place in England first. 工业革命首先在英国发生。 4. Due to low investment, our industrial output has remained stagnant. 由于投资少，我们的工业生产一直停滞不前。 5. He troubleshoots for a large industrial firm. 他受雇为一家大工业公司检修故障。', '副词: industrially');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('drain', '[dreɪn]', 'n.排水沟,消耗,排水;vt.排出沟外,喝干,耗尽;vi.排水,流干', '1. We must dig a trench to drain away the water. 我们必须挖一条沟排水。 2. They drain the swamp and turn it into fertile land. 他们排干沼泽地的水,将它变成了肥沃的土地。 3. They all rose and drained their glasses. 他们都站了起来,一饮而尽。 4. She felt drained of energy. 她感到精疲力竭。 5. We have to call a plumber to unblock the drain. 我们得叫管工来通一通下水道。', '形容词: drainable 名词: drainer 过去式: drained 过去分词: drained 现在分词: draining 第三人称单数: drains');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('interim', '[\'ɪntərɪm]', 'adj.中间的,临时的,间歇的;n.中间时期,过渡时期,暂定', '1. He worked on an interim basis. 他只是个临时工。 2. Who will lead the interim government? 谁将领导临时政府? 3. They submitted an interim report. 他们递交了一份临时报告。 4. It may turn out to be an interim technology. 这可能只是个过渡技术。 5. What are you doing in the interim? 这期间你在干什么?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('council', '[\'kaʊnsl]', 'n.政务会,理事会,委员会,参议会,讨论会议,顾问班子,立法班子', '1. She\'s on the local council. 她是地方议会的议员。 2. The theatre is under the patronage of the Arts Council. 那家剧院得到了艺术委员会的赞助。 3. Three women have been elected to the Council. 有3名妇女当选为市政委员会委员。 4. We should submit our plans to the council for approval. 我们应该向理事会提交计划以求批准。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('murmur', '[\'mɜːrmər]', 'n.低沉连续的声音,咕哝,怨言,低语;v.发低沉连续的声音,发怨言,低声说,低语', '1. Some of the sailors began to murmur about it bringing bad luck. 一些水手开始低声说这带来了噩运。 2. The old man drooped his head and began to murmur to himself my father\'s name. 老人低下头，低声念叨我父亲的名字。 3. The breeze murmured in the pines. 松林里微风沙沙作响。 4. The little stream murmured at the foot of the hill. 小溪在山脚下潺潺流动。 5. The murmur swelled into a roar. 窃窃私语的声音变大形成一片喧哗。', '形容词: murmurous 副词: murmuringly 名词: murmurer 过去式: murmured 过去分词: murmured 现在分词: murmuring 第三人称单数: murmurs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('defy', '[dɪ\'faɪ]', 'vt.不服从,公然反抗,藐视,挑衅,违抗,使...难于;n.挑战', '1. The pine trees defy severe cold. 松树不畏严寒。 2. If you defy the law, you will be sent to prison. 如果你蔑视法律，你将被送入监狱。 3. He defined the order of the court. 他蔑视法庭的命令。 4. He won\'t allow anyone to defy his ministerial authority. 他不允许任何人挑衅他的教长权威。', '过去式: defied 过去分词: defied 现在分词: defying 第三人称单数: defies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('thesis', '[\'θiːsɪs]', 'n.论题,论文', '1. Charles is writing his graduation thesis now. 查尔斯正在写毕业论文。 2. He has already started his thesis. 他已经开始写毕业论文了。 3. He wrote his doctoral thesis on electromagnetism. 他写有关电磁的博士论文。 4. He\'s been pegging away at his thesis for months. 他写论文已经忙了几个月了。', '名词复数: theses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('terrify', '[\'terɪfaɪ]', 'vt.使恐怖,恐吓', '1. Or will carelessness or corruption allow the theft of a nuclear device to terrify us all? 会不会由于安全部门的疏忽或腐败，让恐怖分子得到核装置用来威胁民众？', '过去式: terrified 过去分词: terrified 现在分词: terrifying 第三人称单数: terrifies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('surpass', '[sər\'pæs]', 'vt.超越,胜过', '1. To be in love is to surpass oneself. 人在爱中超越自我。 2. You seem to surpass yourself in this painting. 你在这幅画的创作上似乎超越了你自己。 3. Her sweetness nothing can surpass. 温柔甜蜜世无双。 4. It is hard to surpass Evans in speed. 要在速度上胜过艾文斯很难。', '过去式: surpassed 过去分词: surpassed 现在分词: surpassing 第三人称单数: surpasses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('despite', '[dɪ\'spaɪt]', 'prep.不管,尽管,不论', '1. Despite old age, she is still learning to drive. 尽管年事已高,她还在学开车。 2. Despite all our efforts we still lost the game. 尽管我们尽了全力，我们还是输掉了比赛。 3. He came to the meeting despite his illness. 尽管生病，他还是来参加会议。 4. She managed despite everything to preserve her sense of humour. 她不管遇到什么情况都竭力保持着幽默感。 5. The statesman scoffed at the despites from his political enemy. 这位政治家对政敌的攻击嗤之以鼻。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('casualty', '[\'kæʒuəlti]', 'n.伤亡', '1. The cottage was a casualty of the forest fire. 那小屋被森林大火烧毁。 2. She read through the casualty list anxiously. 她忧虑地把伤亡人员名单从头到尾看了一遍。 3. The casualty of the traffic accident was a doleful record. 这一交通事故地伤亡人数是一个令人伤心的记录.', '名词复数: casualties');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('drastic', '[\'dræstɪk]', 'adj.激烈的,(药性等)猛烈的', '1. His view brings a drastic argument. 他的观点引起激烈的争论。 2. Drastic measures were taken to combat inflation. 已采取激烈措施对付通货膨胀。 3. Talk to me before you do anything drastic. 你采取任何重大行动之前要跟我谈谈。 4. Our budget needs drastic revision. 我们的预算需作重大修改。', '副词: drastically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('identification', '[aɪˌdentɪfɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.辨认,鉴定,证明,视为同一', '1. A line of people is formed for identification. 人们排成一行等待确认身份。 2. He gave a positive identification of the killer. 他明确的认出了凶手。 3. Jewellery identification is a hard job. 珠宝鉴定不是一件容易的工作。 4. Fingerprint identification is widely used. 指纹鉴定被广泛运用。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('substitute', '[\'sʌbstɪtuːt]', 'n.代用品,代替者,替代品;v.代替,替换,替代', '1. Water is not a proper substitute for wine. 水不是酒的适当代用品。 2. Is saccharin a good substitute for sugar? 糖精是糖的良好替代品吗? 3. We recommend this brand as a good substitute. 我们推荐的新品种可以完全替代原来的产品。 4. His friend Humboldt was his substitute. 他的朋友洪堡接替了他。 5. Only art can substitute for nature. 唯有艺术能代替自然。', '形容词: substitutable 名词: substitutability 过去式: substituted 过去分词: substituted 现在分词: substituting 第三人称单数: substitutes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cable', '[\'keɪbl]', 'n.电缆,海底电报,缆,索;v.打(海底)电报', '1. Cable television has been around for some time now. 有线电视面世已有些时日了。 2. They are building a submarine cable tunnel. 他们正在建设一条海底电缆隧道。 3. A number of cables are needed in this project. 这项工程需要大量电缆。 4. Try replacing the cable with a known working cable. 试著以确定是工作良好的缆线替换缆线。 5. News of his death was cabled to his family. 他的死讯已电告其家属。', '名词: cabler 过去式: cabled 过去分词: cabled 现在分词: cabling 第三人称单数: cables');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('preach', '[priːtʃ]', 'v.鼓吹', '1. The priest preached a sermon on the need of charity. 牧师在布道会上宣讲慈爱的必要。 2. Those people go around preaching revolution. 那些人到处宣扬革命。 3. Christ preached that we should love each other. 基督在布道中说人们应该互敬互爱。 4. She preached economy as the best means of solving the crisis. 她大力鼓吹节约是解决危机的关键。 5. The priest preached to the congregation about the Sermon on the Mount. 那位祭司就山中圣训向会众说教。', '副词: preachingly 过去式: preached 过去分词: preached 现在分词: preaching 第三人称单数: preaches');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tile', '[taɪl]', 'n.瓦片,瓷砖', '1. The reconciled reptiles rest on a fragile tile. 和解的爬行动物歇在易碎的瓷砖上。 2. We have put tiles on the wall behind the bath. 我们在浴缸后的墙上贴了瓷砖。 3. I entered the kitchen, with its old tile floor and its cherrywood cabinets. 我走进了厨房，年月久远的瓷砖地面，樱桃木材质的各色橱柜。 4. The rain came in for want of tile on the roof. 因房顶缺少瓦片，雨渗进来了。', '过去式: tiled 过去分词: tiled 现在分词: tiling 第三人称单数: tiles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('professional', '[prə\'feʃənl]', 'n.自由职业者,专业人员,职业运动员,职业艺人;adj.专业的,职业的', '1. Don\'t wear those clothes to work; try to look more professional! 别穿这些衣服去工作，要穿得象个专业人员的样子。 2. That doctor has been accused of professional misconduct. 那位医生被指控违反医德。 3. She was always punctual and professional. 她总是准时并具有专业能力。 4. He is a professional journalist. 他是一位专门的新闻从业人员。 5. She is a real professional. 她是个真正的专家。', '副词: professionally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('transform', '[træns\'fɔːm]', 'vt.转换,改变,改造,使...变形;vi.改变,转化,变换;n.[数]变换(式),[语]转换', '1. She is responsible for the character part of the hero\'s devoted mother. 她负责这个主人公的忠诚的母亲的角色部分。 2. The magician transformed the frog into a princess. 魔术师把青蛙变成了公主。 3. His plans were transformed overnight into reality. 他的计划迅速变为现实。 4. We should try to transform heat into power. 我们应该设法将热转化为能量。', '形容词: transformable 过去式: transformed 过去分词: transformed 现在分词: transforming 第三人称单数: transforms');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pasture', '[\'pæstʃər]', 'n.牧地,草原,牧场;v.放牧,牧(牛、羊)等,吃草', '1. The land was used chiefly for pasture. 这土地多半用作牧场。 2. We have put our cattle out to pasture. 我们已经把牛放到牧场上吃草去了。 3. Cows are grazing in the pasture. 牛正在草原吃草。 4. Draping the skin over his shoulders, he went to the pasture to wait for the lion. 把羊皮披在身上后，猎人到草原上去等狮子。 5. There we saw herds of cows grazing on the pasture. 我们在那里看到一群群的牛在草地上吃草。 6. Cows are left to graze in the pasture. 奶牛都是留给放牧在牧场。', '形容词: pasturable 名词: pasturer 过去式: pastured 过去分词: pastured 现在分词: pasturing 第三人称单数: pastures');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('drought', '[draʊt]', 'n.干旱,缺乏', '1. The long drought famished many people. 久旱使很多人陷入饥饿。 2. Famine is often the sequel to war or drought. 饥荒往往是战争或干旱造成的。 3. We have not enough food to eat because of the drought. 因为旱灾，我们没有足够的食物可吃。 4. The soil is cracking up because of the drought. 土地因干旱而正在龟裂。', '形容词: droughty 异体字: drouth');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('preside', '[prɪ\'zaɪd]', 'v.主持', '1. Mr Smith will preside over the next meeting. 史密斯先生将主持下一次会议。 2. The old professor had presided over a seminar for theoretical physicists. 老教授主持了一次理论物理学家的研讨会。 3. He will preside at the election of school officers. 他是校际选举大会的主席。 4. When the Assembly holds its meeting, the chairman shall preside over the Assembly. 会员大会召开会议时，理事长担任会议主席。', '名词: presider 过去式: presided 过去分词: presided 现在分词: presiding 第三人称单数: presides');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('crumble', '[\'krʌmbl]', 'v.弄碎,粉碎,崩溃;n.面包屑', '1. The masonry of the old building began to crumble. 旧楼房的砖石结构开始崩落。 2. The earthquake made the wall sink and start to crumble. 这次地震把这堵墙震得下陷并开始崩塌。 3. He crumbled the bread in his fingers. 他用手指把面包捏碎了。 4. Even these hard parts may crumble to dust. 甚至这些坚硬的部分也会破碎成粉末。', '过去式: crumbled 过去分词: crumbled 现在分词: crumbling 第三人称单数: crumbles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('initial', '[ɪ\'nɪʃl]', 'adj.最初的,词首的,初始的;n.词首大写字母', '1. This is a letter paper personalized with his initials. 这是一张有他姓名首字母的信纸。 2. After the initial cheers,the noise of the crowd began to die away as the group started playing. 开始的欢呼声结束以后，乐队开始演奏，人们的喧闹声也随之逐渐消失。 3. We are through the initial testing period. 我们通过了最初的考试阶段 4. The word “hour” is pronounced without an initial aspirate. hour一词的首字母h不发送气音。 5. She initialed a handkerchief and gave it to that young man. 她在手帕上绣上姓名的首字母，把它送给了那个年轻人。', '副词: initially 名词: initialness 过去式: initialed/initialled 过去分词: initialed/initialled 现在分词: initialing/initialling 第三人称单数: initials/initials');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('genetic', '[dʒə\'netɪk]', 'adj.遗传的,起源的', '1. He chose genetic engineering to be his lifelong career. 他选择了遗传工程学作为终生的事业。 2. Most chromomeres contain a genetic unit. 绝大多数染色粒包含一个遗传单位。 3. The disease is caused by a genetic defect. 这种疾病的起因是基因缺陷。 4. Every living thing has its own genetic chips. 每种生物都有自己的基因芯片。', '副词: genetically 异体字: genetical');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('quiver', '[\'kwɪvər]', 'n.震动,颤抖,箭袋,箭袋中的箭;vi.颤抖,振动,射中;vt.使颤动;adj.敏捷的', '1. The old man quivered with rage. 这位老人气得发抖。 2. The skylark quivered its wings. 云雀抖动它的双翼。 3. There was a slight quiver in his voice as he spoke. 他说话时声音有些颤抖。 4. A quiver of fear ran through her. 一阵恐惧的颤抖传遍了她的全身。', '形容词: quivery 过去式: quivered 过去分词: quivered 现在分词: quivering 第三人称单数: quivers');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('periodical', '[ˌpɪri\'ɑːdɪkl]', 'adj.周期的,定期的;n.期刊,杂志', '1. The periodical is obtainable on the very first day of every month. 这本杂志每月一号出版。 2. She refereed for a periodical a few years ago. 几年前她为一期刊担任编审。 3. They have already put out a new periodical. 他们已经出版了一种新的期刊。 4. I should be glad if you could insert this article into your periodical. 如果能把这篇文章登在你的期刊上我将很高兴。 5. I expect regular periodical reports from you. 我期待你定期汇报。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('detective', '[dɪ\'tektɪv]', 'n.侦探;adj.侦探的', '1. The detective laid great stress on details. 侦探特别强调细节。 2. The detective was trying to ascertain exactly who was at the party. 这个侦探试图查明都有谁参加了聚会。 3. The detective thought the stick was relative to the murder case. 侦探认为这根木棒和谋杀案有牵连。 4. The detective tried to reason out how the thief had escaped. 这个侦探反复琢磨想弄明白那个窃贼是怎样逃跑的。 5. She read detective stories as an escape. 她看侦探小说解闷。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('energetic', '[ˌenər\'dʒetɪk]', 'adj.精力充沛的,积极的', '1. His son is an energetic child. 他的儿子是个精力旺盛的孩子。 2. He seems an energetic person. 他似乎是一个精力充沛的人。 3. Her wiry athletic body seems energetic. 她瘦长结实的身体看上去精力充沛。 4. We should give energetic support to agriculture. 我们要大力支援农业。', '副词: energetically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('vice', '[vaɪs]', 'n.恶习,恶行,坏脾气,罪恶,堕落,老虎钳,缺点,缺陷;vt.钳住;prep.代替', '1. He who thinks too much of his virtues reminds others of his vice. 念念不忘自己长处的人,会使别人想起他的缺点。 2. The vice of drinking is increasing. 酗酒之风正在增长。 3. Virtue and vice are two different things: the former leads to peace, the latter to misery. 美德与邪恶是不同的：前者带来和平,后者导致痛苦。 4. There is a lot of vices in big cities. 大城市存在许多道德败坏的行为。 5. He reported on the whole event to the vice premier. 他把整个事件向副总理作了汇报。 6. John was appointed postmaster vice Richard retired. 约翰被任命为邮政局长,取代退休的理查德。 7. She is vice-chair of the education committee. 她是教育委员会的代理主席。 8. The vice is bolted to the work-bench. 老虎钳是用螺栓拧在工作台上的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('scan', '[skæn]', 'v.细看,审视,浏览,扫描;n.扫描', '1. Could you teach me how to scan an image? 你可以教我如何扫描一个影像吗? 2. I scanned the newspaper when I was waiting for the bus. 等公共汽车的时候，我匆匆浏览了一下报纸。 3. She scanned his face, looking for signs of what he was thinking. 她审视他的脸,试图探寻他在思考什么。 4. I scanned my pocket for change. 我仔细查看囗袋找零钱。 5. The verses scan well. 这些诗句符合韵律。 6. The doctors gave him an ultrasonic brain scan. 医生给他做了脑部超声波扫描检查。', '形容词: scannable 名词: scanner 过去式: scanned 过去分词: scanned 现在分词: scanning 第三人称单数: scans');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('optimum', '[\'ɑːptɪməm]', 'n.最适宜;adj.最适宜的', '1. The market offers optimum condition for sale. 市场为销售提供了最佳条件。 2. You have established the optimum price. 你已制定了最佳价格。 3. The optimum starting age is ten. 最佳起始年龄是10岁。 4. Now your advice is very optimum. 现在你的建议是很适宜的。 5. Strive for optimum, not maximum, performance. 不求最多、最花哨，只求最适宜。', '名词复数: optima');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('definitive', '[dɪ\'fɪnətɪv]', 'adj.最后的,确定的,权威性的', '1. Her book is the definitive work on Milton. 她的书是论述米尔顿的权威著作. 2. She\'s written the definitive history of Vienna. 她写下了权威性的维也纳历史。 3. Clearer fossil may provide a definitive answer. 如果能发现更清晰的化石,那么可能提供明确的答案。 4. There is no definitive answer to this. 没有什么确定的答案。', '副词: definitively 名词: definitiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('equality', '[i\'kwɑːləti]', 'n.等同性,同等,平等,相等,等式', '1. In some countries black people do not have equality with white people. 在某些国家黑人没有和白人同等的权利。 2. Genuine racial equality still seems light-years away. 真正的种族平等似乎仍遥遥无期。 3. The country\'s constitution embodies the ideals of freedom and equality. 这个国家的宪法体现了自由和平等的理想。 4. Martin Luther King made many adversaries in his nonviolent quest for equality. 马丁·路德·金在以非暴力手段寻求平等的过程中树立了许多敌人。', '名词复数: equalities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('critic', '[\'krɪtɪk]', 'n.批评家,评论家,吹毛求疵者', '1. She is a very discerning art critic. 她是位眼光敏锐的艺术评论家。 2. He has a reputation for being a forthright critic. 他是以直率著称的评论家。 3. Have you read the article written by that famous critic? 你读过那个著名的批评家写的这篇文章吗？ 4. A critic is a man whose watch is five minutes ahead of other people\'s watch. 批评家，是一个他的表要比别人的表快上五分钟的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('convention', '[kən\'venʃn]', 'n.大会,协定,习俗,惯例', '1. The convention looms as political battle. 这场大会将是一场政治角斗。 2. Delegates will be picked at a convention. 代表将在大会上选出。 3. This convention results in no ambiguity. 这个协定不会导致误解。 4. The countries all agreed to sign the convention. 各国都同意签署这项协定。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sergeant', '[\'sɑːrdʒənt]', 'n.警官,军士', '1. The sergeant expects obedience from his men. 中士要士兵服从他的命令。 2. A police sergeant is below an inspector. 巡佐的级别低于巡官。 3. You may fade away and the sergeant will take over. 你可以走了，军士会来接替你的。 4. The sergeant gave his men the command \"At ease!\" 警官命令战士们“稍息！”', '名词: sergeancy');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('imaginative', '[ɪ\'mædʒɪnətɪv]', 'adj.想象的,虚构的', '1. Scott was an imaginative writer. 司格特是位富于想象力的作家。 2. Money still talks, but in more imaginative ways. 金钱仍然是万能的，不过是通过更加富于想象力的方式。', '副词: imaginatively 名词: imaginativeness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('unity', '[\'juːnəti]', 'n.团结,联合,统一,一致', '1. These works, taken together, are essentially a unity. 这些作品，放在一起，基本上是一个整体。 2. The figure on the left spoils the unity of the painting. 左边的人物有损于画面的整体性。 3. He made a speech about the need for unity. 他发表了有关统一之必要的演讲。 4. They maintained only formal unity among themselves. 他们只在表面上保持一致。', '名词复数: unities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('contemplate', '[\'kɑːntəmpleɪt]', 'v.凝视,沉思,预期,企图', '1. He stood contemplating the painting. 他站着审视那幅图画。 2. It terrified me to contemplate the consequence of your action. 一想到你行动的后果,我就感到害怕。 3. The doctor contemplated the difficult operation he had to perform. 医生细想他要进行的棘手的手术。 4. We contemplate obtaining a technical license. 我们希望获得一项技术许可证。', '名词: contemplator 过去式: contemplated 过去分词: contemplated 现在分词: contemplating 第三人称单数: contemplates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('irritate', '[\'ɪrɪteɪt]', 'vt.激怒,使急躁;v.刺激', '1. His letter irritated me a little. 他的信使我有点恼怒。 2. Don\'t irritate her, she\'s on a short fuse today. 别惹她，她今天动不动就发火。 3. Wool irritates my skin. 毛织物会使我的皮肤过敏。 4. Insect bites irritate your skin. 虫子叮疼了你的皮肤。', '副词: irritatingly 名词: irritator 过去式: irritated 过去分词: irritated 现在分词: irritating 第三人称单数: irritates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('qualitative', '[\'kwɑːlətətɪv]', 'adj.性质上的,定性的', '1. Indeed, every property is both qualitative and dispositional. 每个属性都是性质上的和趋势上的。 2. This will cause qualitative change. 这将会引起质的变化。 3. There are qualitative differences between the two products. 这两种产品存在着质的差别。 4. We can draw a few qualitative conclusions. 我们可以得出一些定性的结论。', '副词: qualitatively');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('moreover', '[mɔːr\'oʊvər]', 'adv.而且,此外', '1. He was, moreover, a poet of promise. 此外，他还是一个有前途的诗人。 2. It was, moreover, a waste of time. 此外,那是浪费时间。 3. Moreover,I will thank all the people who helped me. 此外，我要感谢所有帮助过我的人。 4. I don\'t like skating, moreover, the ice is too thin. 我不喜欢滑冰，而且冰又太薄。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('property', '[\'prɑːpərti]', 'n.财产,所有物,所有权,性质,特性,(小)道具', '1. The property was returned to the original owner. 财产已归还原主。 2. But you do not have the right to initiate force against the life, liberty and property of others. 但是,你没有发起强占其他人生命,自由和所有物的权利。 3. He has a large property in the county. 他在这个县有一大片地产。 4. Cheerfulness is a property of her personality. 开朗乐观是她的性格特征。', '形容词: propertyless 名词复数: properties');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('performance', '[pər\'fɔːrməns]', 'n.履行,执行,成绩,性能,表演,演奏', '1. His performance gripped the audience. 他的表演深深地吸引住观众。 2. Proposal is easier than performance. 建议容易实行难。 3. His good performance in school does great credit to his mother. 他在学校的优良表现为他母亲带来极大的荣誉。 4. He was assiduous in performance of duty. 他勤勉地履行职责。', '动词: perform');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('legitimate', '[lɪ\'dʒɪtɪmət]', 'adj.合法的,合理的,正统的;v.合法', '1. I\'m not sure that his business is strictly legitimate. 我说不好他的生意是否全部合法。 2. He is a legitimate heir to the throne. 他是王位的合法继承人。 3. a legitimate son. 婚生子 4. Politicians are legitimate targets for satire. 政治家理所当然是讽刺的靶子。 5. Distributed Denial of Service, which depletes the network\'s resource and denies service to legitimate users, is one of the hardest security problems in the Internet. 分布式拒绝服务攻击，目的在于耗尽网络资源从而使合法用户的服务请求被拒绝，是最难解决的网络安全问题之一。', '副词: legitimately 名词: legitimateness 过去式: legitimated 过去分词: legitimated 现在分词: legitimating 第三人称单数: legitimates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('streak', '[striːk]', 'v.飞跑,加上条纹', '1. It is time to start a new winning streak. 是开始新一轮地连胜的时候了。 2. She has had a long streak of bad luck. 她遭遇了一连串的不幸。 3. There was a streak of blood on his face. 他脸上有一道血痕。 4. The fox tabby cat has clearly, the obvious streak. 狸花猫有非常清楚、明显的斑纹。 5. The Indians used to streak their faces with paint. 印第安人过去常用颜料在脸上涂条纹。', '名词: streaker 过去式: streaked 过去分词: streaked 现在分词: streaking 第三人称单数: streaks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('inhibit', '[ɪn\'hɪbɪt]', '抑制,约束,[化][医]抑制', '1. You should inhibit wrong desires and impulses. 你应当抑制不正当的欲望和行动。 2. These compounds inhibit microbial growth. 这些化合物能抑制微生物的生长。 3. Why didn\'t you inhibit him from doing that? 为何你不阻止他做那种事? 4. They passed a law to inhibit people from parking in the street. 他们通过一项法令以阻止人们在街上停车。', '形容词: inhibitable 过去式: inhibited 过去分词: inhibited 现在分词: inhibiting 第三人称单数: inhibits');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('yacht', '[jɑːt]', 'n.游艇,快艇,轻舟;vi.驾游艇,乘游艇', '1. Huge waves drove the yacht onto the rocks. 巨浪把游艇卷到岩石上。 2. The yacht hit a rock and damaged her bows. 游艇碰上了礁石，撞坏了船头。 3. Our little dinghy was dwarfed by the big yacht. 我们的小船跟大游艇一比显得很小。 4. They were able to position the yacht by means of radar. 他们能够用雷达测定快艇的方位。', '过去式: yachted 过去分词: yachted 现在分词: yachting 第三人称单数: yachts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('release', '[rɪ\'liːs]', 'n.释放,让渡,豁免,发行的书,释放证书;vt.释放,解放,放弃,让与,免除,发表;n.版本,发布', '1. The prisoner was questioned before his release. 囚犯被释放之前受到了审问。 2. The puffball is ready to release its spores. 尘菌已经要释放孢子了。 3. The electrons in the upper band eventually release energy, thereby emitting photons. 上层能带中的电子最后会发射光子释放能量。', '过去式: released 过去分词: released 现在分词: releasing 第三人称单数: releases');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reconciliation', '[ˌrekənsɪli\'eɪʃn]', 'n.和解,调和,顺从', '1. The two sides come to reconciliation at last. 这两方最后讲和了。 2. He brought about reconciliation between former enemies. 他使旧时的仇敌和解了。 3. We\'ve tried our best to effect reconciliation between the two parties. 我们已尽了最大努力希望促成双方和解。 4. The key to reconciliation rests with them. 和解的关键在他们。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('boring', '[\'bɔːrɪŋ]', 'n.钻(孔);adj.令人厌烦的', '1. It is awfully boring. 太叫人厌烦了。 2. It is boring to listen to the same story. 听相同的故事是令人厌烦的。 3. His long boring story made me yawn. 他的冗长的故事听得我直打呵欠。 4. He gave a boring speech full of stale jokes. 他的发言很乏味,满是陈腐的笑话。', '副词: boringly 名词: boringness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('trademark', '[\'treɪdmɑːrk]', 'n.商标', '1. Nobody has a trademark on it so the name is open. 尚无人用此商标，所以这个名字可以使用。 2. Have you noticed the trademark on the bottle? 你注意到瓶子上的商标了吗？', '过去式: trademarked 过去分词: trademarked 现在分词: trademarking 第三人称单数: trademarks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('retrieve', '[rɪ\'triːv]', 'v.重新得到;n.找回', '1. The company is fighting to retrieve its market share. 这个公司正在为恢复其市场份额(占有率)而奋斗。 2. She tried to retrieve the situation by making profuse apologies. 她不住的道歉,力图挽回局面。 3. I should like to retrieve my umbrella which I left in the car. 我想取回我留在车上忘记带走的雨伞。 4. The dog is trained to retrieve. 这狗受过训能找到并带回猎物。 5. This is a loss beyond retrieve. 这是无可挽回的损失。', '形容词: retrievable 副词: retrievably 名词: retrievability 过去式: retrieved 过去分词: retrieved 现在分词: retrieving 第三人称单数: retrieves');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fascinate', '[\'fæsɪneɪt]', 'vt.使着迷,使神魂颠倒;vi.入迷,极度迷人的', '1. Anything to do with old myths and legends fascinates me. 任何与上古神话传说有关的东西都会使我着迷。 2. The place continues to fascinate visitors, cloaked in its mystery. 这个地方笼罩在神秘气氛下，继续使游览者着迷。 3. The students were fascinated by his ideas. 学生们都被他的思想吸引住了。 4. I watched her, fascianted. 我瞧着她,完全被她吸引住了。 5. It seems that the private lives of movie stars never fail to fascinate. 电影明星的私生活似乎总是使人津津乐道。', '过去式: fascinated 过去分词: fascinated 现在分词: fascinating 第三人称单数: fascinates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mute', '[mjuːt]', 'n.哑巴,哑音字母,[律]拒不答辩的被告,弱音器;adj.哑的,无声的,沉默的;vt.减弱...的声音;vi.排泄', '1. He\'s a deaf mute and cannot tell anyone secret. 他是个聋哑人，不会把他们的秘密告诉任何人。 2. He has been passing himself off as a deaf - mute . 他一直装聋作哑。 3. You need get a mute on your guitar to make the tune soft. 你得给吉他安个弱音器好让音柔和一点。 4. The letter \"e\" in \"mouse\" is mute. “mouse”中的字母“e”不发音。 5. He tried to speak but he was still mute. 他尽力想说，却仍然哑口无声。 6. Please mute a music instrument. 请减低乐器的声音。', '副词: mutely 比较级: muter 最高级: mutest 名词: muteness 过去式: muted 过去分词: muted 现在分词: muting 第三人称单数: mutes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('blunt', '[blʌnt]', 'adj.钝的,生硬的', '1. Blunt scissors don\'t cut cleanly. 钝剪刀剪不齐。 2. My pencil is blunt, could you lend me a knife to sharpen it? 我的铅笔钝了，你能借我把刀子削一削吗？ 3. It involves systematic yet banal design, and blunt reportage. 它使用系统的，然而平庸的设计和迟钝的新闻报道。 4. He\'s very blunt and will tell you what he thinks about anything. 他的个性非常直率,会把他所想的都说出来。 5. His mind was blunted by boredom. 他的头脑因厌烦而变得迟钝。', '副词: bluntly 比较级: blunter 最高级: bluntest 名词: bluntness 过去式: blunted 过去分词: blunted 现在分词: blunting 第三人称单数: blunts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('assess', '[ə\'ses]', 'vt.估定,评定', '1. He can quickly assess a person\'s character. 他能很快地评定出某人的品质。 2. How do you assess your students? 你如何评估学生们？ 3. We will assess the damages caused by the flood. 我们将对洪灾造成的损失进行评估。 4. She looked at the house and assessed its market value. 她看了看房子并估算了其市场价值。', '形容词: assessable 过去式: assessed 过去分词: assessed 现在分词: assessing 第三人称单数: assesses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('attribute', '[\'ætrɪbjuːt]', 'n.属性,品质,特征,加于,归结于', '1. Most historians attribute such declines to wars and conquests. 大多数的历史学家把这样的衰亡归于战争和征服。 2. Many people\'s success can be attributed to hard work and a bit of luck. 很多人的成功都可以归于勤奋加上一点儿运气。 3. Public perception can also create a legal right for an attribute of a product. 公众的认知也能为产品的某个属性创造法律权利。 4. The attribute that indicates that the same copy of a routine cannot be used by another task. 一种属性，表示某一例行程序的同一副本不能被另一个任务使用。', '形容词: attributable 名词: attributer 过去式: attributed 过去分词: attributed 现在分词: attributing 第三人称单数: attributes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('trifle', '[\'traɪfl]', 'n.琐事,少量,蛋糕,小事;v.开玩笑,玩弄,闭混,浪费,嘲弄', '1. I do not want to make a fuss over such a trifle. 我不想为这种小事大惊小怪。 2. They had an altercation about a trifle. 他们为一点小事争吵起来。 3. He told her not to pester him with trifles. 他告诉她别拿些琐事来烦他。 4. I have only a trifle of wine left. 我只剩下一点点酒了。 5. Don\'t trifle away your time on curio hunting. 别把时间都浪费在搜集古玩上面。', '名词: trifler 过去式: trifled 过去分词: trifled 现在分词: trifling 第三人称单数: trifles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('probe', '[proʊb]', 'n.探针,探测器;vt.(以探针等)探查,查明', '1. They launched a probe into the disappearance of government funds. 他们发起了对政府资金流失一事的调查. 2. Pressure on the industry was building even before the latest probe. 事实上,在最近的调查之前,压力就已经在这个行业聚集。 3. The image sent back by the probe is very clear. 探针传回的图像非常清晰。 4. The brain surgeon asked the nurse to pass him a probe. 脑外科医生要护士将探针递给他。 5. The doctor will probe your stomach with a camera. 医生会用带摄像头的胃镜检查你的胃。', '副词: probingly 名词: prober 过去式: probed 过去分词: probed 现在分词: probing 第三人称单数: probes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('elastic', '[ɪ\'læstɪk]', 'adj.弹性的', '1. The new policy was sufficiently elastic to accommodate both views. 新政策充分灵活地适用两种观点。 2. Rubber is elastic. 橡皮是有弹性的。 3. This swimming costume is made of elastic material. 这件游泳衣是由弹性材料做成的。 4. The slacks have an elastic waistband. 这条便裤的腰带可伸缩。 5. It snapped back like a piece of elastic. 它像一条橡皮带那样迅速弹回。', '副词: elastically 名词: elasticity');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('illustrate', '[\'ɪləstreɪt]', 'vt.举例说明,图解,加插图于,阐明;vi.举例', '1. He pointed at the diagram to illustrate his point. 他指着图表来说明他的论点。 2. In this section, I\'ll illustrate some of these differences. 在这一节,我将举例说明一些不同之处。 3. Our textbook is very well illustrated. 我们的课本插图丰富。 4. This chart is used to illustrate all the changes. 这张图片用来解释所有的变化。', '形容词: illustratable 名词: illustrator 过去式: illustrated 过去分词: illustrated 现在分词: illustrating 第三人称单数: illustrates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('credible', '[\'kredəbl]', 'adj.可信的,可靠的', '1. It is hardly credible. 这是难以置信的。 2. These denials are simply not credible. 这些否认是不可信的。 3. So far, there is only one credible proposal. 到目前为止，只有一个可靠的建议。 4. But I believe real things are more credible. 但是我认为还是现实的东西比较可靠。', '副词: credibly 名词: credibleness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('overt', '[oʊ\'vɜːrt]', 'adj.明显的,公然的', '1. In many emerging economies corruption is egregious and overt. 许多新兴经济体中的腐败是异乎寻常的和公开的。 2. Supreme People\'s Court promulgated the regulations on overt enforcement. 最高人民法院颁布执行公开的规定。 3. It was full of overt propaganda and the props were primitive. 节目充满了明显的宣传，一点也不精致，道具都是简单。 4. Spotting them can be tricky, since many animals display few overt symptoms. 确诊蓝舌病本身已经很难，因为很多染病动物并无明显的临床症状。', '副词: overtly 名词: overtness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sturdy', '[\'stɜːrdi]', 'adj.强健的,坚定的,毫不含糊的;n.[兽医]家畜晕倒病', '1. The sturdy young man removed the rock without effort. 那个壮实的小伙子没费多大劲便把石块搬开了。 2. His son has grown up into a sturdy hardworking young man. 他的儿子已成长为一个健壮勤劳的小伙子。 3. That chair doesn\'t look very sturdy. 椅子看上其不坚固。 4. Have you any sturdy hiking boots? 有没有耐用的健行靴？', '副词: sturdily 比较级: sturdier 最高级: sturdiest 名词: sturdiness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('transit', '[\'trænzɪt]', 'n.经过,通行,搬运,运输,运输线,转变;vt.横越,通过,经过;vi.通过;n.[天]中天,经纬仪', '1. The goods were lost in transit. 这些货物在运输中丢失了。 2. The transit was damaged by flood. 运输线被洪水破坏了。 3. Firstly, the drug inhibits octopamine transit in insect brains. 第一，可卡因能抑制真蛸胺这种药物在昆虫大脑中经过。 4. The city supported an initiative to turn this space, a place of transit, into an actual facility with a more permanent character and a new urban identity and artistic spirit. 该城市支持了一项倡议，把这个空间里转变成为一个实际的设施，且与更长期的和新的城市特征及艺术气息相融合。 5. We will transit the strait at night. 我们将在夜间通过那个海峡。 6. Our ship used the canal to transit to the east. 我们的船通过这条运河驶往东方。', '过去式: transited 过去分词: transited 现在分词: transiting 第三人称单数: transits');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('gracious', '[\'ɡreɪʃəs]', 'adj.亲切的，和谐的；优美的；雅致的，雍容华贵的', '1. The Queen greeted the crowed with a gracious smile. 女王带着亲切的微笑向人群致意。 2. I received a gracious letter of acknowledgement. 我收到一封有礼貌的感谢信。 3. I\'ll be greatly honoured by your gracious presence. 如蒙光临，不胜荣幸。 4. Insist the gracious living style to experience the essential life spirit. 坚持以高尚的生活方式，体验生活本质的精神态度。', '副词: graciously 名词: graciousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('considerable', '[kən\'sɪdərəbl]', 'adj.相当大(或多)的,值得考虑的,相当可观的', '1. The mayor is a considerable official. 市长是一位重要的官员。 2. He is a considerable person in that college. 他是那所学院相当重要的人物。 3. The economy was a considerable issue in the campaign. 在竞选运动中经济是一个重要问题。 4. His remarks provoked considerable comment. 他的话引起了相当大的议论。', '副词: considerably');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('municipal', '[mjuː\'nɪsɪpl]', 'adj.市政的,市立的,地方性的,地方自治的', '1. An angry mob gathered outside the municipal building. 一群愤怒的暴民聚集在市政大楼的外面。 2. The municipal authorities put forth a new set of traffic regulations some time ago. 前不久市政当局公布了一套新的交通法规。 3. She works in a municipal library. 她在一所市立的图书馆工作。 4. Mr. Charles was elected chairman of the municipal education committee. 查尔斯先生当选为市教育委员会的主任。', '副词: municipally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('screw', '[skruː]', 'n.螺丝钉,螺旋,螺杆,螺孔,螺旋桨,吝啬鬼;vt.调节,旋,加强,压榨,强迫,鼓舞;vi.转动,旋,拧', '1. Turn the screw to the right to tighten it. 将螺钉向右旋紧。 2. One of the screws is loose. 一只螺丝松了。 3. The screw did its work, and Ressel was pleased. 由于螺旋桨起了作用，所以莱塞尔感到高兴。 4. He used all of his efforts to loosen the screw. 他用尽全力来拧开这个螺旋装置。 5. The table legs are screwed to the floor. 这张桌子的腿是用螺丝固定在地板上的。', '形容词: screwable 名词: screwer 过去式: screwed 过去分词: screwed 现在分词: screwing 第三人称单数: screws');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('leisure', '[\'liːʒər]', 'n.空闲,闲暇,悠闲,安逸', '1. Are you at leisure just now? 你现在有空吗？ 2. Life today is compartmentalized into work and leisure. 现今生活分成工作和闲暇两部分。 3. I have no leisure for playing cards. 我没有闲暇玩牌。 4. He\'s a gentleman of large leisure. 他是一个逍遥自在的绅士。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('skeleton', '[\'skelɪtn]', 'n.(动物之)骨架,骨骼,基干,纲要,万能钥匙', '1. The block is still just a skeleton of girders. 这片建筑还只是仅有主梁的骨架。 2. The director set out the plan in skeleton form. 主任提纲挈领地说明了这一计划。 3. I\'ve written the skeleton of my report, but I have to fill in the details. 我已写出报告的梗概，但我必须补充细节。 4. The shell of a snail is its skeleton. 蜗牛的壳是它的骨骼。 5. As a part of the whole skeleton, oral maxillofacial bone loss has some association with systemic osteoporosis. 做为全身骨骼的一部分，颌骨的骨丢失一直被认为与全身骨质疏松存在关联性。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('illuminate', '[ɪ\'luːmɪneɪt]', 'vt.照明,照亮,阐明,说明,使灿烂,以灯火装饰(街道等);vi.照亮', '1. plastic food 2. A sudden smile illuminated her face. 突然的微笑使她容光焕发。 3. Footnotes illuminate the difficult passage of the book. 脚注中解释了书中许多难懂的道理。 4. Our interesting teacher could illuminate almost any subject we studied. 我们这位有趣的老师几乎能解释清楚我们所学的所有科目。', '副词: illuminatingly 过去式: illuminated 过去分词: illuminated 现在分词: illuminating 第三人称单数: illuminates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('exotic', '[ɪɡ\'zɑːtɪk]', 'adj.异国情调的,外来的,奇异的', '1. Exotic pets are the in thing right now. 外国宠物眼下很时髦。 2. The film retains much of the book\'s exotic flavour. 这部电影保存了原著的许多异国情调。 3. The taste of this exotic dish puts me off. 这道异国菜肴的味道令我望而却步。 4. The exotic atmosphere will fascinate you. 这里的异国情调风格将会把您深深地迷住。', '副词: exotically 名词: exoticness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('epoch', '[\'epək]', 'n.新纪元,时代,时期,时间上的一点,[地质]世', '1. Ice age refers to the latest glacial epoch. 冰河时期指的是最近的一个冰川时期。 2. The Revolution had many of these men, proportioned to the epoch. 革命时期有过许多那样的人，都和那时代相称。 3. Einstein\'s theory marked a new epoch in history. 爱因斯坦的理论标志著历史上一个新时代的开始。 4. The epoch of revolution creates great figures. 革命时代造就伟大的人物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('perfume', '[pər\'fjuːm]', 'n.香味,芳香,香水;vt.使发香,洒香水于,发香味', '1. The room reeked of cheap perfume. 房间里弥漫著劣质香水的呛鼻气味。 2. The smell of her perfume lingered in the empty house. 空屋里仍然飘溢著她的香水味。 3. A mist of perfume hung in the air. 空气中飘溢著香水的雾气。 4. Can you smell the perfume of the roses? 你能闻到玫瑰花的香味吗？ 5. She perfumed herself with Eau de Cologne. 她身上洒著古龙水。', '过去式: perfumed 过去分词: perfumed 现在分词: perfuming 第三人称单数: perfumes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('behave', '[bɪ\'heɪv]', 'vi.举动,举止,运转;v.行为表现', '1. How is your new car behaving? 你的新车性能如何？ 2. I\'ll trust you to behave responsibly while I\'m out. 我相信你在我外出期间会认真办事的。 3. If you behave like that, you\'ll get yourself disliked. 如果你的行为那样，你会让人厌恶的。 4. It\'s hard to train children to behave well at the table. 培养儿童用餐时举止得体是很困难的。', '过去式: behaved 过去分词: behaved 现在分词: behaving 第三人称单数: behaves');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('irony', '[\'aɪrəni]', 'n.反话,讽刺,讽刺之事', '1. The good point is that the irony fully reflected. 好的地方是反讽完全出来了。 2. Irony was widely used in the works of Kafka and LuXun. 卡夫卡和鲁迅的小说中都广泛应用了反讽的艺术手法。 3. The great irony is that despite all his explanation nobody believed him. 最具讽刺意味的是：尽管他竭力解释，可没一个人相信他。 4. After Peanuts left,I could not help thinking about this irony. 落花生去后，我总是不住的这样想这件讽刺的事。', '名词复数: ironies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('successive', '[sək\'sesɪv]', 'adj.继承的,连续的', '1. We have had three successive years of good harvest. 我们已连续三年丰收。 2. He dropped the nails on the ground and successive clangs were heard. 他把钉子掉到了地上，听见了一连串的叮当声。 3. Continuity is ensured by using the same props in successive scenes. 在连续的场景中使用同样的道具以确保前后衔接。 4. Andrea paid no attention to the successive charges which were brought against him. 安德烈听着维尔福起诉书中接连提出来的罪名。', '副词: successively 名词: successiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('facet', '[\'fæsɪt]', 'n.(多面体的)面,(宝石等的)刻面,小平面,方面,琢面;vt.在...上刻画', '1. They beat us in every facet of the game. 他们在比赛的每个小层面都打败了我们。 2. He has perfected himself in every facet of his job. 他已使自己对工作的各个方面都得心应手。 3. Locomotion is merely one facet of action. 移动只是行动的一个方面而已。 4. Being a well-paid business woman is only one facet of her life. 高薪阶层职业妇女的身份只是她生活的一个方面。', '形容词: faceted');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('slack', '[slæk]', 'n.松弛,静止,淡季,闲散;adj.松弛的,不流畅的,疏忽的,软弱的,漏水的,呆滞的,懒散的;adv.马虎地,缓慢地;vt.使松弛,使缓慢,马虎从事;vi.松懈,减弱,松驰', '1. A rope is slack if it hasn\'t been pulled tight. 如果一根绳子没有拉紧,那它是松的。 2. She was shocked at the slack discipline in the school. 对于学校松弛的纪律她感到震惊。 3. He is slack in answering letters. 他疏于回信。 4. After intense work in the summer, we are slack off now. 夏季紧张的工作过後，我们现在放松了。 5. There is too much slack in the rope. 这条绳子太松了。 6. The driver slacked up before reaching the crossroads. 司机在驶近十字路口时减慢了速度。 7. You should slack the rope before trying to untie the knot. 解结之前你应该先将绳索放松。', '副词: slackly 比较级: slacker 最高级: slackest 名词: slackness 过去式: slacked 过去分词: slacked 现在分词: slacking 第三人称单数: slacks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('marble', '[\'mɑːrbl]', 'n.大理石,(玩具)弹球.石弹子,雕刻品;adj.大理石的,冷酷无情的,坚硬的', '1. This table is made of marble. 这个桌子是大理石的。 2. Michelangelo carved in marble. 米开朗琪罗在大理石上雕刻。 3. There are many perpendicular marble columns in Greek temples. 希腊庙宇有很多垂直的大理石柱。 4. My little son has many marbles. 我的小儿子有许多弹珠。', '形容词: marbly 过去式: marbled 过去分词: marbled 现在分词: marbling 第三人称单数: marbles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reform', '[rɪ\'fɔːrm]', 'n.改革,改善,改良运动,感化;vt.改革,革新,重新组成;vi.革新,改过,重组', '1. Our reform made an inexorable march of progress. 我们的改革取得了势不可挡的进展。 2. Many reforms must be made to the education system. 教育体制要作许多改革。 3. The reform and open policy has Brought us Chinese people a rich and colourful life. 改革开放的政策给我们中国人民带来了富裕和多彩的生活。 4. He intends to make several reforms in the prison system. 他打算在监狱制度方面实行一些改良。 5. A new leader will reform the unjust system. 新的领导人将改革不当的制度。', '形容词: reformable 名词: reformability 过去式: reformed 过去分词: reformed 现在分词: reforming 第三人称单数: reforms');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('detection', '[dɪ\'tekʃn]', 'n.察觉,发觉,侦查,探测,发现', '1. Our main detection device is sonar. 我们主要的探测装置是声波定位仪。 2. The word radar means radio detection and ranging. 雷达这个词的意思是指无线电探测和测距。 3. The detection of crime is not always easy. 侦查罪行并非易事。 4. Detection is not properly a function of the customs service. 严格地说来，侦查工作不是海关的一项职责。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('likelihood', '[\'laɪklihʊd]', 'n.可能,可能性', '1. There is no likelihood of his succeeding. 他没有成功的可能性。 2. The likelihood for peace in the Middle East remains questionable. 中东和平的可能性仍让人怀疑。 3. The likelihood of completing the research on schedule is low. 按时完成任务的可能性很小。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('domestic', '[də\'mestɪk]', 'adj.家庭的,国内的,与人共处的,驯服的', '1. The store deals in objects of domestic utility. 那家商店出售家庭用品。 2. My value for domestic tranquility should much exceed theirs. 我应该远比他们重视家庭的平静生活。 3. Washington responded by freezing the price of domestic oil. 华盛顿作出的反应是冻结国内的石油价格。 4. We adopt an active attitude towards drawing on overseas fund to make up for domestic fund shortage. 我们采取积极的态度吸引海外资金以弥补国内资金短缺。 5. His domestics are all in years. 他的佣人全都上了年纪。', '副词: domestically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reverse', '[rɪ\'vɜːrs]', 'n.相反,背面,反面,倒退;adj.相反的,倒转的,颠倒的;vt.颠倒,倒转', '1. The government has failed to reverse the economic decline. 政府未能扭转经济滑坡的趋势。 2. He reversed the car into a tree. 他倒车撞到了树上。 3. Statistics showed a reverse trend to that recorded in other countries. 统计数字表明这种趋向与其他国家所示情况迥异。 4. Count down in reverse order 10, 9, 8... 倒数--10、 9、 8... 5. In hot weather, the reverse happens. 在热天,情况相反。', '副词: reversely 名词: reverser 过去式: reversed 过去分词: reversed 现在分词: reversing 第三人称单数: reverses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bewilder', '[bɪ\'wɪldər]', 'vt.使迷惑,使不知所措,使昏乱', '1. You bewildered me. 你把我搞糊涂了。 2. Big city traffic bewilders me. 大城市的交通使我晕头转向。', '副词: bewilderedly 名词: bewilderedness 过去式: bewildered 过去分词: bewildered 现在分词: bewildering 第三人称单数: bewilders');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('armor', '[\'ɑːmə]', 'n.装甲', '1. In the past, knights used to wear armor in battle. 在过去，骑士在战斗中身穿盔甲。 2. Never underestimate the power of extra armor. 永远不要低估额外的盔甲。 3. My armor will crush your pathetic forces. 我的装甲部队将会打垮你可怜的军队。 4. Dreams are the armor for our fragile hearts. 梦想是装甲为我们易碎的心脏。', '过去式: armored 过去分词: armored 现在分词: armoring 第三人称单数: armors');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('assume', '[ə\'suːm]', 'vt.假定,设想,采取,呈现', '1. Let\'s assume it to be true. 让我们假定这是真的。 2. We assume his guilt. 我们假定他是有罪的。 3. They assumed their operational positions. 他们设想了自己在实施中的作用。 4. I am not afraid to assume the responsibility. 我不怕承担责任.', '形容词: assumable 副词: assumably 名词: assumer 过去式: assumed 过去分词: assumed 现在分词: assuming 第三人称单数: assumes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('prophet', '[\'prɑːfɪt]', 'n.先知,预言者,提倡者', '1. Once in a while, the prophet indulges in fantasy. 偶尔，那个预言家会纵情于幻想。 2. A prophet made a prophecy that the kingdom would fall. 一位预言家预言那个王国将要灭亡。 3. The prophet said that war will break out. 先知预言战争将爆发。 4. No man is a prophet in his own country. 先知在自已家乡从来不被认可。', '名词: prophethood');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fraud', '[frɔːd]', 'n.欺骗,欺诈行为,诡计,骗子,假货', '1. She was put on trial for fraud. 她因涉及诈骗罪而受审。 2. Investigation of fraud was their commission. 调查诈欺舞弊是他们的任务。 3. He told people that he was a serious and well-known musician, but he was actually a fraud. 他告诉人们说他是一个严肃的著名音乐家,实际上却是个骗子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('timid', '[\'tɪmɪd]', 'adj.胆小的,羞怯的', '1. They taunted him for being timid. 他们讥笑他胆小。 2. He is as timid as a sheep. 他像绵羊一样怯懦。 3. The least noise would startle the timid child. 最小的响声也会吓着这个胆小的孩子的。 4. He is a timid boy; it\'s impossible for him to brawl with anyone. 他是一个胆小的男孩，他不可能和任何人吵架。', '副词: timidly 比较级: timider 最高级: timidest 名词: timidity');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('overhear', '[ˌoʊvər\'hɪr]', 'vt.无意中听到,偷听', '1. I managed to overhear a few interesting snippets of information. 我设法偷听到一点零星有趣的消息。 2. People say in the Tanabata night, can see the cowherd meet, or in the Milky Way under the melon and fruit can overhear in heaven when they meet silently whispers. 人们传说在七夕的夜晚，抬头可以看到牛郎织女的银河相会，或在瓜果架下可偷听到两人在天上相会时的脉脉情话。', '名词: overhearer 过去式: overheard 过去分词: overheard 现在分词: overhearing 第三人称单数: overhears');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('defendant', '[dɪ\'fendənt]', 'n.被告;adj.辩护的,为自己辩护的', '1. The plaintiff accused the defendant of fraud. 原告指控被告欺诈。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('enrich', '[ɪn\'rɪtʃ]', 'vt.使富足,使肥沃,装饰,加料于,浓缩', '1. The expanding economy enriched the peasants. 不断发展的经济使农民们富裕起来。 2. The library was enriched with new books. 购买新书使图书馆得到了充实。 3. Farmers enrich the soil with organic and inorganic manures. 农民用有机肥料和无机肥料来提高土壤的肥力。 4. An appreciation of art will enrich your life. 艺术欣赏将会丰富你的生活', '名词: enricher 过去式: enriched 过去分词: enriched 现在分词: enriching 第三人称单数: enriches');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('compatible', '[kəm\'pætəbl]', 'adj.谐调的,一致的,兼容的', '1. The proposed new regulation is not compatible with the existing policy. 提出的新规定与现有的政策不符。 2. We should remain the compatible family relationships. 我们应该维持和谐的家庭关系。 3. He and his wife are not compatible 他跟他的妻子合不来。 4. It may not be compatible with your version of Mac OS X. 它可能与您的Mac OS X版本不兼容。 5. He drove a car at a speed compatible with safety. 他以安全速度行车。', '副词: compatibly 名词: compatibility');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('permanent', '[\'pɜːrmənənt]', 'adj.永久的,持久的', '1. The incident left permanent traces on his mind. 那件事在他头脑里留下了永久的印象。 2. I am looking for a permanent position. 我在找一个永久性的职业。 3. These factors usually have a longer and more permanent impact on share prices. 这项因素通常会对股价产生更加长远和持久的影响。', '副词: permanently 名词: permanentness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bowel', '[\'baʊəl]', 'n.肠;adj.内部,同情心', '1. Do you have a bowel movement today? 你今天上过厕所吗？ 2. Her bowel will engorge quite often, I\'m afraid. 她的肠将会经常充血,我害怕。 3. He had cancer of bowel. 他得了肠癌。 4. What is it like in the bowels of the earth? 地球内部是什么样子？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('missionary', '[\'mɪʃəneri]', 'adj.传教的,传教士的;n.传教士', '1. The missionary was sent to India last year. 这名传教士去年被派到印度。 2. He disguised himself as a missionary. 他伪装成传教士。 3. We need to motivate members to do missionary work. 我们必须策励教友传教的工作。 4. Our missionary work had an important breakthrough. 我们的传教工作有了很重要的突破。', '名词复数: missionaries');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cholesterol', '[kə\'lestərɔːl]', 'n.胆固醇', '1. This cooking oil is low in cholesterol. 这种烹调油胆固醇含量低。 2. Would you expect the cholesterol to be elevated? 你考虑胆固醇会升高吗? 3. There are many food products that claim to reduce cholesterol levels. 很多食品都宣称可以降低胆固醇水平。 4. A high cholesterol level in the blood can cause heart disease. 血液中胆固醇含量高可导致心脏病。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('muddy', '[\'mʌdi]', 'adj.多泥的,泥泞的', '1. It\'s muddy underfoot. 地上很泥泞。 2. The country roads were muddy and full of furrows left by farm carts. 乡间道路泥泞不堪，布满了牛车压出的车辙。 3. The police dredged up the parcel from the muddy river. 警方从浑浊的河水中捞出包裹。 4. There is a muddy expression in his face. 他脸上有一种糊涂的表情。 5. Don\'t muddy your new shoes. 别把泥巴沾到新鞋子上面去。', '副词: muddily 比较级: muddier 最高级: muddiest 名词: muddiness 过去式: muddied 过去分词: muddied 现在分词: muddying 第三人称单数: muddies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('breach', '[briːtʃ]', 'n.违背,破坏,破裂,裂口;vt.打破,突破', '1. Union officials denounced the action as a breach of the agreement. 工会负责人谴责这一行动破坏了协议。 2. You are in breach of your contract. 你违反了你签的合同。 3. It caused a lifelong breach with his father. 这使得他们父子终身失和。 4. The huge waves made a breach in the sea wall. 大浪在堤上冲出一个缺口。 5. He never do the things breach the benefits of group. 他不做任何违背集体利益的事。', '过去式: breached 过去分词: breached 现在分词: breaching 第三人称单数: breaches');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('elicit', '[i\'lɪsɪt]', 'vt.得出,引出,抽出,引起', '1. The detectives tried to elicit where he had hidden his loot. 侦探试图诱使他说出他藏匿赃物的地方。 2. I could elicit no response from him. 我从他那里套不出任何反应。 3. At last we have elicited the truth from him. 我们终于从他那里探得真相。 4. He succeeded in eliciting the information he needed from her. 他从她那里问出了他所需要的信息。', '名词: elicitation 过去式: elicited 过去分词: elicited 现在分词: eliciting 第三人称单数: elicits');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('visualize', '[\'vɪʒuəlaɪz]', 'vt.形象,形象化,想象;vi.显现', '1. Your ability to visualize will help you convince others of the possibilities. 你能把可能性形象化，这会帮助你说服别人。 2. Users visualize the Undo facility in different ways, depending on the situation and their expectations. 取决于各种情况和期望，用户对撤销功能有着不同的形象化理解。 3. Try to visualize him as an old man. 尽量设想他是一位老人。', '名词: visualization 过去式: visualized 过去分词: visualized 现在分词: visualizing 第三人称单数: visualizes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tan', '[tæn]', 'n.日晒后的颜色,棕褐色,茶色;adj.棕褐色的,茶色;v.晒黑,晒成褐色', '1. I bought a pair of tan leather shoes the other day. 前几天我买了双棕褐色的皮鞋。 2. It took me all summer to get this tan. 我花了整个夏天才晒出这样的棕褐色。 3. My tan\'s beginning to fade. 我晒黑的肤色逐渐变浅了。 4. The skin of your cheeks will tan. 你双颊的皮肤将被晒得黝黑. 5. These shoes are tan, not dark brown. 这些鞋是棕黄色的，不是深褐色的。', '形容词: tannish 比较级: tanner 最高级: tannest 过去式: tanned 过去分词: tanned 现在分词: tanning 第三人称单数: tans');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sufficient', '[sə\'fɪʃnt]', 'adj.充分的,足够的', '1. The money I have saved is sufficient for buying a car. 我所存的钱足以买一辆汽车。 2. I doubt whether they really have sufficient manpower. 我怀疑他们是否真有足够的人力。 3. There is sufficient food for everybody. 有足够的饭菜供大家吃。 4. We must work hard, but equally we must get sufficient rest. 我们必须努力工作,但同时也要有充分的休息。', '副词: sufficiently');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('numerical', '[nuː\'merɪkl]', 'adj.数字的,用数表示的;adj.数字的,用数字表示的', '1. Budgeting is the formulation of plans for a given future period in numerical terms. 预算是用数字的形式来表示将来某一确定期间的计划。 2. This includes text, numerical calculations, mathematical derivations, diagrams, graphs, computer programs, and output. 这包括本文，数字的计算，数学的引出，图表，曲线图，计算机计画和输出。 3. Hash values are unique and compact numerical representations of a piece of data. 哈希值是一块数据唯一和紧凑的数字表示形式。', '副词: numerically 异体字: numeric');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cabin', '[\'kæbɪn]', 'n.小屋,船舱', '1. He made out of the cabin on hearing the siren. 他一听到汽笛声就立即走出船舱。 2. Fine. Can you let me have a cabin for two? 好的，能给我订一间二人船舱吗? 3. My cabin is on E deck. 我的舱位在E层甲板。 4. Cabin light will be dim for takeoff. 机舱灯将会因飞机起飞而变暗。 5. The criminal was cabined all the day. 这个犯人整天受到限制。 6. The old man cabined in the forest. 这位老人住在森林的小屋里。', '过去式: cabined 过去分词: cabined 现在分词: cabining 第三人称单数: cabins');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('emerge', '[i\'mɜːrdʒ]', 'vi.显现,浮现,暴露,形成,(由某种状态)脱出,(事实)显现出来', '1. A wonderful idea emerged in my mind. 我的脑海里浮现出一个极妙的想法。 2. Man has gradually emerged from barbarism into civilization over the long history. 在悠久的历史长河中人类逐渐脱离野蛮状态而进入文明。 3. Many facts emerged as a result of the investigation. 调查结果,许多事实暴露出来。', '过去式: emerged 过去分词: emerged 现在分词: emerging 第三人称单数: emerges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('provision', '[prə\'vɪʒn]', 'n.供应,(一批)供应品,预备,防备,规定', '1. We set out with enough provisions. 我们带上足够的食品出发了。 2. Provision of shelter was the Red Crosss main concern for the disaster victims. 为灾民提供避难处是 红十字会的主要工作。 3. The present law makes no provision for this. 现行的法律对此未作任何规定。 4. Both sides should act according to the provisions of the agreement. 双方都应按协议条款办事。 5. They provisioned the ship for a long voyage. 他们为远航的船只准备了食品和必需品。', '名词: provisioner 过去式: provisioned 过去分词: provisioned 现在分词: provisioning 第三人称单数: provisions');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('myth', '[mɪθ]', 'n.神话,神话式的人物(或事物),虚构的故事,荒诞的说法', '1. This is the story of a myth of our times. 这是一个关于我们这个时代的神话故事。 2. Venus is one of the goddess in Greek myth. 维纳斯是希腊神话中的女神之一。 3. The rich uncle of whom he boasts is only a myth. 他吹嘘的那个有钱的叔叔只是个乌有翁。 4. His story about is very wealthy is a complete myth. 关于他非常富有的说法完全是捏造出来的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('champagne', '[ʃæm\'peɪn]', 'n.香槟酒,香槟色', '1. The champagne was quaffed from huge golden goblets. 香槟酒被从金色的高脚杯里一饮而尽。 2. Champagne is full of bubbles. 香槟酒有很多气泡。 3. The champagne cork popped when he pulled it out. 他拔香槟酒的瓶塞时它砰的一声开了。 4. He was drinking cheap champagne with a raffish air. 他喝著廉价的香槟酒，样子十分放荡。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('surgeon', '[\'sɜːrdʒən]', 'n.外科医生', '1. The surgeon has performed the operation. 外科医生做了手术。 2. The surgeon operated on her for appendicitis. 外科医生为她做阑尾切除手术。 3. The surgeon asked him if he felt nervous. 外科医生问他是否感到紧张。 4. He is reputed as the best surgeon in Paris. 他被认为是巴黎最好的外科医生。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('repression', '[rɪ\'preʃn]', 'n.镇压,抑制,抑压', '1. The repression of one\'s true feelings is wrong. 抑制自己的真实情感是不对的。 2. His goal was the repression of insolence. 他的目标是抑制傲慢的态度。 3. His repression broke out. 他的压抑终于爆发了。 4. The repression of your true feelings is harmful to your health. 压抑你的真实感情有害健康。', '形容词: repressionist');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('overwhelming', '[ˌoʊvər\'welmɪŋ]', 'adj.压倒性的,无法抵抗的', '1. He bounced back by winning an overwhelming election victory. 他通过赢得一次势不可挡的选举胜利迅速恢复了过来。 2. The scenic splendors of the Rocky Mountains are overwhelming. 落基山脉的壮丽景色使人赞叹不已。 3. Our football team has won an overwhelming victory. 我们的足球队取得了压倒性的胜利。 4. The general effect of the painting is overwhelming. 这幅画给人总的印象是很有气势。', '副词: overwhelmingly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hinder', '[\'hɪndər]', 'adj.后面的;v.阻碍,打扰', '1. The crowd hindered him from leaving. 人群使他无法脱身。 2. Heavy snow hindered the construction work. 大雪妨碍了这项建筑工程的进行。 3. Don\'t let me hinder you from going. 别让我妨碍了你走。 4. Don\'t hinder me. 不要妨碍我。 5. The hinder leg of this horse was broken. 这匹马的后腿断了。', '名词: hinderer 过去式: hindered 过去分词: hindered 现在分词: hindering 第三人称单数: hinders');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mobile', '[\'moʊbl]', 'adj.可移动的,易变的,机动的;n.运动物体', '1. Additionally, consumers continue to embrace mobile personal devices. 此外,消费者接受移动个人设备的热情依然不减。 2. He had a mobile, expressive, animated face. 他有一张多变的，富于表情的，生动活泼的脸。 3. He has a broken leg and isn\'t very mobile. 他的腿摔伤了,活动不便。 4. A specially equipped car makes a handicapped person more mobile. 有特殊装置的汽车使得残障者比以前更易于活动。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hypothesis', '[haɪ\'pɑːθəsɪs]', 'n.假设', '1. The hypothesis promptly attracted some interest. 这个假说很快引起了注意。 2. The validity of the hypothesis can be tested. 这种假说的可靠性是经得起考验的。 3. His hypothesis turned out to be correct. 事实证明他的假设是正确的。 4. The survey result consisted with our hypothesis. 调查结果和我们的假设相一致。', '名词复数: hypotheses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ideology', '[ˌaɪdi\'ɑːlədʒi]', 'n.意识形态', '1. An obsolete ideology can hamper an economy. 过时的意识形态会束缚经济。 2. Nothing lay outside the scheme of our ideology. 我们的意识形态领域包罗万象。 3. Consensus came at the cost of ideology. 共识是通过放弃意识形态立场而获得的。 4. His attitude to ownership is rooted in communist ideology. 他的所有制观点源自共产主义思想。', '名词: ideologist 名词复数: ideologies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('humidity', '[hjuː\'mɪdəti]', 'n.湿气,潮湿,湿度<美>沼泽中的肥沃高地', '1. My laundry will not dry because of the humidity. 由于湿度关系，我的衣物无法晾干。 2. Humidity is a measure of moisture in the atmosphere. 湿度是空气内含水分多少的量度。 3. It\'s said by forecast that the humidity in the air today is 60%. 据预报说今天的空气湿度是百分之六十。 4. Humidity caused me another fit of rheumatism. 湿气使我的风湿病又发作了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('engagement', '[ɪn\'ɡeɪdʒmənt]', 'n.约会,婚约,诺言,交战,接站,雇拥,[机]接合', '1. I have numerous engagements for next year. 我明年有许多约会。 2. Fidelity to engagement is a virtue. 信守诺言是一种美德。 3. Their engagement was announced in the papers. 他们订婚的消息登报了。 4. He broke off his engagement to her. 他对她解除了婚约。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('crew', '[kruː]', 'n.全体人员,(工作)队;vbl.crow的过去式', '1. The ship set sail after all the crew came on board. 全体船员上船后，船就开了。 2. The crew abandoned the sinking ship. 全体船员离开了正在下沉的船。 3. The plane crashed, killing all its passengers and crew. 飞机失事了，所有乘客和机组人员都遇难了。 4. The captain piped the crew down after work. 船长吹哨让全体船员下班。', '过去式: crewed 过去分词: crewed 现在分词: crewing 第三人称单数: crews');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('slice', '[slaɪs]', 'n.薄片,切片,一份,部分,片段;v.切(片)', '1. Please give me a slice of bread. 请给我一片面包。 2. This is just a slice of life. 这只是人生的一个片段罢了。 3. He also gets a slice of the profit. 他也得到一份利润。 4. A slice is a curving shot from left to right with severe sidespin. 右曲球是一种带有相当于顺时钟旋转导致剧烈向右弯曲的击球。 5. Slice the mushrooms thinly and fry in butter. 把蘑菇切成薄片,用黄油抄。', '形容词: sliceable 名词: slicer 过去式: sliced 过去分词: sliced 现在分词: slicing 第三人称单数: slices');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('correspondence', '[ˌkɔːrə\'spɑːndəns]', 'n.相应,通信,信件', '1. We have carried on a correspondence for years. 多年来,我们一直互相通信。 2. I\'ve fallen behind with my correspondence. 我积压了许多信没回。 3. I\'ve got through a lot of correspondence today. 今天我处理了一大批信件。 4. As her private secretary he has access to all her correspondence. 他是她的私人秘书，能接触到她所有的信件。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('seam', '[siːm]', 'n.接缝,线缝,缝合线,衔接口,伤疤,层;vt.缝合,接合,焊合,使留下伤痕;vi.裂开,发生裂痕', '1. We can mend a seam but not a big hole. 我们可以缝好脱线处，但不是补大洞。 2. The seam of her skirt ripped. 她的裙子的接缝裂开了。 3. You should seam up the shirt without using sewing-machine. 你不要用机器去缝制这件衬衣。 4. She seamed two pieces of carpet together. 她将两块地毯缝在一起。 5. The fields dried and seamed in the heat. 农田在高温下干裂。', '名词: seamer 过去式: seamed 过去分词: seamed 现在分词: seaming 第三人称单数: seams');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('restrain', '[rɪ\'streɪn]', 'vt.抑制,制止', '1. He couldn\'t restrain his curiosity. 他抑制不住自己的好奇心。 2. She tried to restrain her sobs. 她设法抑制住自己的悲泣。 3. Shame may restrain what the law does not prohibit. 羞耻或许能阻止法律所不能禁止之事。 4. We must not restrain children of their liberty. 我们绝对不要限制孩子们的自由。', '形容词: restrainable 副词: restrainedly 名词: restrainer 过去式: restrained 过去分词: restrained 现在分词: restraining 第三人称单数: restrains');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ascribe', '[ə\'skraɪb]', 'vt.归因于,归咎于', '1. He ascribes his success to good luck. 他把他的成功归功于幸运。 2. You should not ascribe your failure to bad luck. 你不应该把自己的失败归因于运气不好。 3. It \'s wrong to ascribe all that have happened simply to the war . 把发生的一切归咎于战争是错误的。 4. This song is often ascribed to Bach. 这首歌曲常被说成是巴赫做的。', '过去式: ascribed 过去分词: ascribed 现在分词: ascribing 第三人称单数: ascribes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('enforce', '[ɪn\'fɔːrs]', 'vt.强迫,执行,坚持,加强', '1. You can\'t enforce cooperation between the players. 队员间的配合并非强迫命令而成。 2. Don\'t enforce your will on the child, please. 请别把你的意愿强加给这孩子。 3. Contracts are promises that the law will enforce. 合同是可强制执行的一项或一组诺言。 4. It may be possible to enforce part of a contract. 合同可以部分被强制执行。', '形容词: enforceable 名词: enforceability 过去式: enforced 过去分词: enforced 现在分词: enforcing 第三人称单数: enforces');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pattern', '[\'pætərn]', 'n.模范,式样,模式,样品,格调,图案;vt.模仿,仿造,以图案装饰;vi.形成图案', '1. The two buildings are modeled after the same pattern. 这两座建筑是按照同一模式建造的。 2. Training and education follow different patterns in different regions. 培训和教育在不同的地区遵循不同的模式。 3. This cloth has a pattern of blue and white squares. 这种布有蓝白格子的图案。 4. Threads of different colors and textures were woven into an intricate pattern. 各种花色和质地的线织成了一幅复杂的图案。 5. I like the carpets patterned with peonies. 我喜欢印有牡丹花图案的地毯。', '过去式: patterned 过去分词: patterned 现在分词: patterning 第三人称单数: patterns');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('owe', '[oʊ]', 'vt.欠(债等),受到...的思想,感激,把...归功于;v.欠,应感激,应该把…归功于(to);vi.欠钱', '1. I gotta get back there, I owe it to them. 我要回到那,我欠他们的。 2. Incidentally, I think you still owe me some money. 顺便说一句, 我想你还欠我一些钱。 3. I owe you one. 我欠你一个人情。 4. You owe yourself a holiday. 你应该给自己安排个假期。', '过去式: owed 过去分词: owed 现在分词: owing 第三人称单数: owes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('segregate', '[\'seɡrɪɡeɪt]', 'v.隔离', '1. Why should the handicappedbe segregated from the able-bodied? 为什么要把伤残人士和身体健康的人分开? 2. Some societies still segregate men and women. 有的社会仍然将男女隔离。 3. Mixture of black powder and magnesium has a tendency to segregate. 黑药和镁的混合物具有离析的倾向。', '形容词: segregative 名词: segregator 过去式: segregated 过去分词: segregated 现在分词: segregating 第三人称单数: segregates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bruise', '[bruːz]', 'n.瘀伤,擦伤;v.打伤,撞伤', '1. His face is a mass of bruise after the fight. 他打完架后脸上青一块紫一块的。 2. She is lucky to get off with just a few bruise. 她幸免于难,只是有几处擦伤。 3. She had a dilly of a bruise on her arm. 她手臂上有一块显眼的伤痕。 4. It can range from a minor Bruise or sprain to a skull fracture with Brain damage or a spinal-cord injury with paralysis. 其范围从小型挫伤或扭伤到大脑受损的头颅裂开或麻痹性脊椎伤害。 5. Soft fruit bruises easily. 细嫩的水果容易碰损。 6. She fell and bruised her knee. 她摔倒在地，膝盖上起了紫血块。', '过去式: bruised 过去分词: bruised 现在分词: bruising 第三人称单数: bruises');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('species', '[\'spiːʃiːz]', 'n.种类,(原)核素;n.[律]式样;n.[宗]圣餐物', '1. He is wearing a strange species of hat. 他戴着一种奇怪的帽子。 2. There are more than 1,000 alien species in China. 中国的外来物种有1000多种。 3. The giant panda has become an endangered species. 大熊猫已成了一种濒临灭绝的动物。 4. There has been a sharp decline in the number of species. 物种数量骤然下降。', '名词复数: species');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('swap', '[swɑːp]', 'v.交换;n.交换', '1. He offerd to swap his camera for hers. 他表示要与她交换相机。 2. He swap his old car for a new motorcycle. 他用旧车换了一辆新摩托车。 3. They swapped stories about their army days. 他们互相讲述了他们在军队中的经历。 4. Can I swap your pencil box for my pencil? 我能用我的铅笔换你的文具盒吗? 5. As you like my dress and I like yours, shall we do a swap? 既然你喜欢我的连衣裙而我也喜欢你的，咱们交换好吗？', '名词: swapper');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('compulsory', '[kəm\'pʌlsəri]', 'adj.必需做的,必修的,被强迫的,被强制的,义务的', '1. Attendance at evening prayers is not compulsory. 参加晚祷并非硬性规定。 2. I think it is compulsory. 我认为这是非做不可的。 3. The car insurance is compulsory. 这项汽车保险是强制性的。 4. I think it is compulsory to look over the house. 我认为检查这栋房子势在必行。', '副词: compulsorily 名词: compulsoriness 名词复数: compulsories');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('relieve', '[rɪ\'liːv]', 'vt.减轻,解除,援救,救济,换班', '1. The Government acted quickly to relieve the widespread distress caused by the earthquake. 地震造成大范围的灾难,政府迅速采取行动赈济灾民。 2. This medicine will relieve your headache. 这药将减轻你的头痛。 3. The route was designed to relieve traffic congestion. 这条路是为缓解交通拥挤而开辟的。 4. The general was relieved of his command. 将军被解除了指挥权。', '形容词: relievable 名词: reliever 过去式: relieved 过去分词: relieved 现在分词: relieving 第三人称单数: relieves');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('machinery', '[mə\'ʃiːnəri]', 'n.[总称]机器,机械', '1. We use tractors to pull farm machinery. 我们使用拖拉机牵引农业机械。 2. There was a ceaseless noise of machinery. 机器不停地发出噪音。 3. Some of the machinery is still standing idle. 有些机械仍然闲置着。 4. There was very little outlay on new machinery. 添置新机器的开支微乎其微。', '名词复数: machineries');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('demonstrate', '[\'demənstreɪt]', 'vt.示范,证明,论证;vi.示威', '1. How can you demonstrate to us that your story is true? 你怎样才能向我们证明你所说的属实呢? 2. Realized benefits demonstrate good practice. 已实现的利益证明好的实践。 3. You have to demonstrate how to operate the computer. 你得演示一下如何使用这台计算机。 4. The students are demonstrating a chemical law in the laboratory. 学生们正在实验室里演示一条化学定理。 5. The workers marched through the streets with flags and banners to demonstrate against the rising cost of living . 工人们在街上游行，手执旗帜示威抗议生活费用的高涨。', '过去式: demonstrated 过去分词: demonstrated 现在分词: demonstrating 第三人称单数: demonstrates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('immerse', '[ɪ\'mɜːrs]', 'vt.沉浸,使陷入', '1. I immerse my clothes in the water. 我把衣服浸在水里。 2. Please immerse the plant in water for a few minutes. 把那棵植物在水里浸泡几分钟。 3. He immersed himself totally in his work. 他埋头于工作。 4. I immerse myself into reciting English vocabulary. 我专心于背英语词汇。', '过去式: immersed 过去分词: immersed 现在分词: immersing 第三人称单数: immerses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('limitation', '[ˌlɪmɪ\'teɪʃn]', 'n.限制,局限性', '1. The government has imposed limitation on imports. 政府已经对进口加以了限制。 2. There will be no limitation to persons from any specific countries. 并不局限于任何特定国家的国民。 3. Every interest has its own boundary and limitation. 任何利益都有自己的边界和限度。 4. He knows his limitations. 他知道自己的能力有限。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('retort', '[rɪ\'tɔːrt]', 'v.反驳,反击,回报;n.曲颈甑,曲颈瓶,蒸器', '1. He retorted that it was my fault as much as his. 他反驳说我的错误并不比他的小。 2. The analysts could retort only that the geometric proofs were clumsy and inelegant. 分析学家只能回嘴说几何的证明是笨拙而不优美的。 3. \'Don\'t be ridiculous!\' Pat retorted angrily. “别荒唐了！”帕特生气地回答道。 4. Her roommate\'s retort made her angry. 她同屋的反驳使她生气。', '名词: retorter 过去式: retorted 过去分词: retorted 现在分词: retorting 第三人称单数: retorts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('colleague', '[\'kɑːliːɡ]', 'n.同事,同僚', '1. Please allow me to introduce my colleague Professor Zhang to you. 请允许我把我的同事张教授介绍给你。', '名词: colleagueship');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('gasp', '[ɡæsp]', 'vi.喘息,气喘;vt.气吁吁地说', '1. He gasped out the message. 他喘着气说出了这个消息。 2. I gasped as I jumped into the cold river. 当我跳进冰冷的河里时，简直透不过气来。 3. I gasped with surprise at the unexpected news. 听到意外的消息，我惊讶地吸了一口气。 4. The exhausted runner was gasping for air. 那人跑得疲惫已极，上气不接下气。 5. Michelle recognized him and gave a gasp of shock. 米歇尔认出了他，吃惊地直喘气。', '过去式: gasped 过去分词: gasped 现在分词: gasping 第三人称单数: gasps');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('telecommunication', '[ˌtelikəˌmjuːnɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.电讯,长途通讯,无线电通讯,电信学', '1. The telecommunication service is a government monopoly. 电信为政府专营。 2. Recently there have been many new telecommunication services. 最近出现了许多电信新业务。 3. Our postal and telecommunication services are expanding rapidly. 邮电通信业务正在迅速发展。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mass', '[mæs]', 'n.块,大多数,质量,群众,大量;adj.群众的,大规模的,集中的;vt.使集合;vi.聚集', '1. After harvest we will have a mass of rice. 秋收后，我们将获得大量稻谷。 2. There were masses of dark clouds in the sky. 天上有朵朵乌云。 3. Football stars seem larger-than-life to the mass of fans. 在众多的球迷看来,足球明星是十分杰出的。 4. Modern education is a mass enterprise. 现代教育是一项大规模的企业。 5. Crowds massed along the road where the king would pass. 群众聚集在国王要经过的街道旁。 6. The priest sings Mass. 牧师吟唱弥撒曲。', '过去式: massed 过去分词: massed 现在分词: massing 第三人称单数: masses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('aggressive', '[ə\'ɡresɪv]', 'adj.好斗的,敢作敢为的,有闯劲的,侵略性的', '1. He has an aggressive manner. 他的态度咄咄逼人。 2. His style of argument in meetings is not so much aggressive as pertinacious. 他在会议上的辩论态度并非锋芒逼人而是坚持己见。 3. Red fire ants are very aggressive and readily attack anything that disturb them. 红火蚁攻击性强,容易攻击任何干扰它们的生物。 4. America has a lot of aggressive weapons now. 美国现在有很多进攻性武器。', '副词: aggressively 名词: aggressiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('magnify', '[\'mæɡnɪfaɪ]', 'vt.放大,扩大,赞美,夸大,夸张;vi.有放大能力', '1. I want to magnify my mother\'s picture. 我想放大我母亲的照片。 2. Magnify the magnitude of the magnetism. 放大磁性的大小。 3. He is inclined to magnify difficulties. 他老是爱夸大困难。 4. These groups and individuals magnify hate crimes by blacks in order to back their social agenda. 这些团体和个人为了给自己提出的社会议题造舆论而极力夸大黑人的攻击性犯罪。', '过去式: magnified 过去分词: magnified 现在分词: magnifying 第三人称单数: magnifies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('millionaire', '[ˌmɪljə\'ner]', 'n.百万富翁,大富豪', '1. He spends as if he were a millionaire. 他用起钱来像个百万富翁似的。 2. Now a millionaire, he typifies the self-made man. 他成了百万富翁，可以说是白手起家的典型。 3. He is not poor, on the contrary, he is a millionaire. 他不穷，相反，他是个百万富翁。 4. The library\'s latest acquisitions were donated by a millionaire. 图书馆最近增添的书籍是一位百万富翁捐献的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('misfortune', '[ˌmɪs\'fɔːrtʃuːn]', 'n.不幸,灾祸', '1. One misfortune followed hard on another. 不幸接踵而来。 2. He had the misfortune to break his left arm. 他不幸把左胳臂折断了。 3. They bravely buffeted misfortune\'s billows. 他们勇敢地与灾祸的恶浪搏斗。 4. Falsehood is the jockey of misfortune. 谎言是灾祸的骑师。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ascend', '[ə\'send]', 'v.攀登,上升', '1. The stairs in the hotel ascend in a graceful curve. 这个旅店的楼梯以优美的曲线上升。 2. It is easier to descend than to ascend. 下降容易上升难。 3. A small party is planning to ascend Mount Everest. 一小伙人正计划攀登珠穆朗玛峰。 4. Setting foot on the island, he began to ascend the trail. 他踏上荒岛，开始顺着小径往上攀登。', '形容词: ascendable 过去式: ascended 过去分词: ascended 现在分词: ascending 第三人称单数: ascends');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('gloom', '[ɡluːm]', 'n.阴暗,阴沉;v.(使)变阴暗,优伤地说,繁荣', '1. My eyes slowly grew accustomed to the gloom. 我的眼睛对黑暗慢慢适应了。 2. In the gloom I could only just discern the outline of a building. 在黑暗中我只能依稀分辨出一座建筑物的轮廓来。 3. He walked through the gloom of the thick forest. 他穿过茂密阴暗的森林。 4. The crimes committed there invested the place with an air of mystery and gloom. 在那里发生罪案后,该地笼罩上一种阴森诡秘的气氛。 5. Poets were often visited by fits of gloom. 诗人常有一阵阵忧郁。', '过去式: gloomed 过去分词: gloomed 现在分词: glooming 第三人称单数: glooms');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dome', '[doʊm]', 'n.圆屋顶', '1. Italian architect celebrated for his work during the Florentine Renaissance. His greatest achievement is the octagonal ribbed dome of the Florence cathedral. 布鲁内莱斯基，菲利波1377－1446意大利建筑师，其作品在佛罗伦萨文艺复兴时期享有盛名。其杰作是佛罗伦萨大教堂的八边形肋骨穹隆 2. A transparent dome on the top of an aircraft, through which celestial observations are made for navigation. 天文观测舱，领航舱飞机顶部的一个透明圆顶形结构，航行时可通过它作天文观测 3. Upward pressure from underlying magma domes the surface. 地下岩浆的向上推力使地面成圆顶形。 4. The dome of St. Paul Cathedral is well known in the world. 圣保罗教堂的圆顶闻名于世。', '过去式: domed 过去分词: domed 现在分词: doming 第三人称单数: domes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('vegetation', '[ˌvedʒə\'teɪʃn]', 'n.[植]植被,(总称)植物、草木,(植物的)生长、呆板单调的生活', '1. Coal is carbonized and lithifyied vegetation. 煤由植物碳化及石化所成。 2. The lush vegetation spoke of a damper climate here. 茂盛的植物说明这里的气候是潮湿的。 3. The hills are covered in lush green vegetation. 这片丘岭草木茂盛，郁郁葱葱。 4. This place is desolate of all vegetation. 这个地方不长草木。', '形容词: vegetational');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('depression', '[dɪ\'preʃn]', 'n.沮丧,消沉,低气压,低压', '1. He suffers from acute depression. 他患有严重的抑郁症。 2. He committed suicide during a fit of depression. 他一时想不开，自杀了。 3. Many people were idle during the depression. 在那萧条时期，很多人都无事可做。 4. Roughly speaking, I think we are heading for the depression. 大体说来,我认为我们正走向萧条。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('refrain', '[rɪ\'freɪn]', 'n.重复,叠句,[乐]副歌;vi.节制,避免,制止', '1. Sunlight can refrain the growth of melatonin in the body. 阳光能抑制身体中褪黑激素的生长。 2. I carefully refrained from looking at him. 我留意着避免朝他看。 3. I wish he would refrain from scattering his ash all over the carpet. 我希望他不要将烟灰往地毯上乱弹。 4. You must refrain from smoking in this area. 在这个区域，你必须克制自己不抽烟。 5. Will you all join in singing the refrain, please? 请大家一道来唱副歌好吗?', '名词: refrainer 过去式: refrained 过去分词: refrained 现在分词: refraining 第三人称单数: refrains');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('obligation', '[ˌɑːblɪ\'ɡeɪʃn]', 'n.义务,职责,债务', '1. We are invited, but we are under no obligation to go. 我们是被邀请了,但并不意味着我们有义务一定要去。 2. Some people suggest that the old people\'s children have the obligation to look after their old parents. 一些人认为：老年人的子女有义务照看他们的父母。 3. I have an obligation to keep secret for the taxpayer. 我有责任为纳税人保密。', '形容词: obligational');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('trigger', '[\'trɪɡər]', 'vt.引发,引起,触发;n.板机', '1. Price increases will trigger off demands for wage increases. 价格上涨会激发人们增长工资的要求。 2. The odour of food may trigger people\'s appetite. 食物的香味能引起人的食欲。 3. A detonator is used to trigger an explosive device. 雷管用来引爆爆炸装置。 4. I pulled the trigger and the gun went off. 我一扣扳机，枪就响了。', '过去式: triggered 过去分词: triggered 现在分词: triggering 第三人称单数: triggers');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pirate', '[\'paɪrət]', 'n.海盗,盗印者,盗版者,侵犯专利权者;vt.盗印,盗版,掠夺,翻印;vi.做海盗', '1. The sailor suddenly saw a pirate jumping onto the deck. 那水手忽然看到一名海盗跳上了甲板。 2. Those software pirates have made a great fortune. 这些软件的盗版者发了大财。 3. We will immediately call the police once we find our CDs being pirated. 一旦发现我们的唱片被盗版,我们会立即报警。 4. A gang of bandits pirated the cargo ship. 一帮土匪抢劫了那艘货船。', '形容词: piratic 副词: piratically 过去式: pirated 过去分词: pirated 现在分词: pirating 第三人称单数: pirates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fold', '[foʊld]', 'n.折,羊栏,折痕,信徒;vt.折叠,包,合拢,抱住,笼罩,调入,交迭;vi.折叠起来,彻底失败', '1. Dark clouds folded the hills. 乌云笼罩着群山。 2. I folded the handkerchief and put it in my pocket. 我折好手绢，放进口袋里。 3. The paper should be folded in half. 这张纸应该对折。 4. The border guard folded his arms across his chest and glared the front. 边防战士双手交叉于胸前紧紧瞪着前方。 5. if a business folds, it closes because it is not able to make enough money. 如果有公司倒闭关门,那是因为它没办法赚取足够的钱。', '形容词: foldable 过去式: folded 过去分词: folded 现在分词: folding 第三人称单数: folds');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('defect', '[\'diːfekt]', 'n.过失,缺点', '1. If it were not for this defect, I shall hire him at once. 如果不是因为这个缺点，我会马上雇用他。 2. The new car had to be withdrawn from the market because of a mechanical defect. 那种新汽车因有机械缺陷只好撤出市场。 3. We thought that his troops might defect. 我们认为他的部队会叛变。', '名词: defection 过去式: defected 过去分词: defected 现在分词: defecting 第三人称单数: defects');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('degenerate', '[dɪ\'dʒenəreɪt]', 'adj.退化的;v.退化', '1. Watching TV too much would degenerate your brain. 多看电视会使你的头脑退化。 2. His health is degenerating rapidly. 他的健康状况迅速恶化。 3. Will too much freedom make them degenerate? 太多的自由会令他们堕落吗? 4. He didn\'t let riches and luxury make him degenerate. 他不因财富和奢华而自甘堕落。 5. The thief was a degenerate member of a fine family. 那小偷是优秀家族的堕落的成员。 6. This degenerate seduced my daughter! 这个道德败坏的人勾引我的女儿！', '副词: degenerately 名词: degenerateness 过去式: degenerated 过去分词: degenerated 现在分词: degenerating 第三人称单数: degenerates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('oppose', '[ə\'poʊz]', 'vt.反对,使对立,使对抗,抗争;vi.反对', '1. It was courageous of him to oppose his chief. 他敢反对他的上司，真是勇敢。 2. The rabbles met on the square to oppose their new mayor. 平民们在广场上集会反对他们的新市长。 3. They opposed the government\'s new policies. 他们反对政府的新政策。 4. We\'re firmly opposed to the practice of powerpolitics between nations. 我们强烈反对在国与国之间实行强权政治。', '名词: opposer 过去式: opposed 过去分词: opposed 现在分词: opposing 第三人称单数: opposes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('construct', '[kən\'strʌkt]', 'vt.建造,构造,创立', '1. This factory was constructed by our company. 这家工厂是由我们公司建设的。 2. They are planning to construct a new supermarket. 他们正在计划建造一个新的超级市场。 3. You must learn how to construct a logical argument. 你必须学会怎样确立合乎逻辑的论点。 4. He taught us how to construct sentences. 他教我们怎样造句。 5. There is a contrast between lived reality and the construct held in the mind. 现实生活与头脑所持概念之间有明显差别。', '形容词: constructible 名词: constructor 过去式: constructed 过去分词: constructed 现在分词: constructing 第三人称单数: constructs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('grain', '[ɡreɪn]', 'n.谷物,谷类,谷粒,细粒,颗粒,粮食', '1. We ship grain to Africa. 我们把谷物运往非洲。 2. There are a few grains of rice in a bowl. 碗中有几颗米粒。 3. There isn\'t a grain of truth in it. 那事无丝毫真实性。 4. The coffee was good, but thick with grains. 咖啡很好, 但满是粒子。 5. Physical isolation goes against the corporate grain, the hierarchy being organized around the office. 身体上的隔绝违反合作意愿，使办公室周围形成特定阶层。', '名词: grainer 过去式: grained 过去分词: grained 现在分词: graining 第三人称单数: grains');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('verify', '[\'verɪfaɪ]', 'vt.检验,校验,查证,核实;[计]打开或关闭文件的读写校验', '1. He tried in every way to verify this theory. 他想一切办法来验证这个理论。 2. Men were sent out to verify whether it was true. 几个人被派去查清事实。 3. The truth verified the allegations. 事实证明了这些说法。 4. The reader should verify this calculation. 此式可由读者自行证明。', '名词: verifier 过去式: verified 过去分词: verified 现在分词: verifying 第三人称单数: verifies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ignite', '[ɪɡ\'naɪt]', 'v.点火,点燃', '1. Large pieces of wood do not ignite easily. 大块木材是不易着火的。 2. Ammonia-air mixtures are quite difficult to ignite. 氨与空气的混合气体不易燃烧。 3. The burning gases can ignite the lean mixture. 燃烧着的气体能点燃稀的混合气。 4. What can you do to ignite your own passion? 有什么办法可以点燃你的热情？', '形容词: ignitable 名词: igniter 过去式: ignited 过去分词: ignited 现在分词: igniting 第三人称单数: ignites');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('canvas', '[\'kænvəs]', 'v.彻底讨论探究;n.帆布', '1. The artist showed me his canvases. 画家给我看了他的油画。 2. He bought the canvas for ten thousand dollars. 他以一万美元买下这幅油画。 3. The hole was covered (over) with canvas. 这个洞被帆布遮盖住了。 4. The plumber stowed all his gear in a canvas bag. 管子工把他所有的工具都装进一只帆布袋里。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hesitate', '[\'hezɪteɪt]', 'v.犹豫,踌躇,不愿', '1. Do not hesitate to tell us if you have a problem . 你有问题就直截了当地告诉我们。 2. I would hesitate to get involved in this adventure. 我犹豫是否参加这次探险。 3. She hesitated to hurt the child\'s feelings. 她不想伤害孩子的感情。 4. I hesitate to spend so much money on clothes. 我舍不得把这麽多钱花在穿衣服上.', '副词: hesitatingly 名词: hesitation 过去式: hesitated 过去分词: hesitated 现在分词: hesitating 第三人称单数: hesitates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('limp', '[lɪmp]', 'adj.柔软的,易曲的;vi.跛行', '1. Two weeks later, the dog could walk with a limp. 两周后，狗儿可以跛行了。 2. The injury left him with a permanent limp. 他受伤后就一直瘸了。 3. This young man is wearing a limp grey sweater. 这个年轻人穿着一件柔软的灰色运动衫。 4. The man\'s shrieked whistle struck his limp ears. 男人尖细的口哨声传到它那柔软的耳朵里。 5. He that lives with cripples learns to limp. 近朱者赤，近墨者黑。', '副词: limply 比较级: limper 最高级: limpest 名词: limpness 过去式: limped 过去分词: limped 现在分词: limping 第三人称单数: limps');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('productive', '[prə\'dʌktɪv]', 'adj.生产性的,生产的,能产的,多产的', '1. Their productive cycle covers several decades. 它们的生产周期可延续几十年。 2. Our productive task is making the machine. 我们的生产任务是造机器。 3. They work hard, but their efforts are not very productive. 他们很努力，但效率不太高。 4. I spent a very productive hour in the library. 我在图书馆里的这一小时收获很大。', '副词: productively 名词: productiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('preview', '[\'priːvjuː]', 'adj.在前的,早先的;adv.在...以前;返回上一级菜单', '1. They sent the recording for our preview. 他们把那录音送来给我们预先审查。 2. After a sneak preview of the film they decided to shelve it. 该影片在试映后，他们决定把它搁置起来。 3. Please do the preview and review work. 请做好预习和复习工作。 4. And some Japanese who saw the preview were pleasantly surprised. 一些日本人在看过电影预告后大表惊艳。 5. You may also preview and buy my work here. 你也可以在这里查看与购买我的作品。', '过去式: previewed/prevued 过去分词: previewed/prevued 现在分词: previewing/prevuing 第三人称单数: previews/prevues');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('disturbance', '[dɪ\'stɜːrbəns]', 'n.骚动,动乱,打扰,干扰,骚乱,搅动', '1. He was imprisoned for creating public disturbance. 他因扰乱公共治安而坐牢。 2. The drunken man was run in for creating a public disturbance. 那个醉汉因扰乱公共秩序而被拘留。 3. They were charged by the police with causing a disturbance. 他们被警方控告引起骚动。 4. The noise of cars passing along the road is a continual disturbance to our quiet at home. 马路上来往的车辆声音不断地破坏我们家的安宁。', '动词: disturb 形容词: disturbing 副词: disturbingly 名词复数: disturbances');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('award', '[ə\'wɔːrd]', 'n.奖,奖品;vt.授予,判给', '1. It is impossible to honor her with the award. 奖品授给她是不可能的。 2. The child smiled at his teacher as he received the award. 孩子接过奖品时朝老师微笑着。 3. It is the highest award a producer can receive. 这是一个制作人所能获得的最高奖项。 4. Bill accepted the championship award on behalf of the team. 比尔代表他的队接受了冠军奖。 5. The university awarded him an honorary degree. 这所大学授给他名誉学位。', '形容词: awardable 名词: awarder 过去式: awarded 过去分词: awarded 现在分词: awarding 第三人称单数: awards');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ingenious', '[ɪn\'dʒiːniəs]', 'adj.机灵的,有独创性的,精制的,具有创造才能', '1. The ingenious boy made a radio set for himself. 这个聪明的男孩自己做了一台收音机。 2. He invented an ingenious excuse for being late. 他为迟到编造了一个巧妙的借口。 3. It was an intricate and ingenious system. 这是一个复杂而精致的体系。 4. I never heard anything more ingenious than your suggestion. 我从来没有听见过象你这样有独创性的提法。', '副词: ingeniously 名词: ingeniousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('execute', '[\'eksɪkjuːt]', 'vt.执行,实行,完成,处死,制成,[律]经签名盖章等手续使(证书)生效', '1. Congress makes the laws; the President executes them. 国会制定法律，总统执行法律。 2. We then execute the code that we want to test. 接下来,我们执行我们要测试的代码。 3. Now that we have made the decision, we may execute the scheme as previously agreed. 既然我们已经做了决定,我们就可以实行既定方案了。 4. They executed the king. 他们把国王处决了。', '形容词: executable 名词: executer 过去式: executed 过去分词: executed 现在分词: executing 第三人称单数: executes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('psychiatrist', '[saɪ\'kaɪətrɪst]', 'n.精神病医师,精神病学家', '1. The psychiatrist corrected him gently. 精神病医师彬彬有礼地纠正他。 2. A psychiatrist analyzes his patients using various methods. 精神病医师使用不同方法对其病人进行精神分析。 3. The psychiatrist has done a lot of work with obsessives. 该精神病学家对强迫症患者做了大量工作。 4. She went to a psychiatrist to try to sort out her problems. 她去找精神病学家去解决她的问题。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('considerate', '[kən\'sɪdərət]', 'adj.考虑周到的', '1. It was considerate of you to bring me my raincoat. 你为我带来雨衣,真是想得周到。 2. It is considerate of you to call on your relatives from time to time. 你时时拜望亲戚很周到啊。 3. He is no more considerate of others than his brother is. 他不体谅别人，就跟他弟弟一样。 4. She\'s a very considerate and caring person. 她是一个很懂得体贴和关心的人。', '副词: considerately 名词: considerateness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('condense', '[kən\'dens]', 'v.(使)浓缩,精简', '1. He condense his speech to half its original length. 他把演讲的长度浓缩了一半。 2. You can condense milk by boiling away much of the water in it. 煮去牛奶中大部分的水分可使它浓缩。 3. Steam condenses into water when cooling down. 蒸汽冷却时凝结成水。 4. Water vapors can condense to form clouds. 水蒸汽能凝结成云。', '形容词: condensable 名词: condensability 过去式: condensed 过去分词: condensed 现在分词: condensing 第三人称单数: condenses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('warfare', '[\'wɔːrfer]', 'n.战争,作战,冲突,竞争', '1. This is as true of warfare as it is of diplomacy. 这是真正的战争，就像刚才提到的外交。 2. Warfare has always expedited military technology. 战争总是在促进军事科技的进步。 3. In countries like Nigeria they precipitate coups or tribal warfare. 而在尼日利亚这样的国家，则敏感到会导致政变和部族冲突。 4. That intensified the conflict, as the Tatars were now unrestrained in their warfare against Khmelnytsky. 这让冲突更为激烈，鞑靼人在与赫梅利尼茨基交战时更加不受限制。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('respond', '[rɪ\'spɑːnd]', 'v.回答,响应,作出反应;vi.有反应', '1. I invited her to dinner but she did not respond. 我请她吃晚饭，但她未作回答。 2. The screen is sensitive and can respond to slight touch. 触摸屏反应灵敏,能响应轻微的触碰。 3. He tried to be amusing, but I didn\'t respond. 他试图逗乐,可我一点都没反应。 4. The car responds well to the controls. 这辆汽车操纵灵敏.', '名词: responder 过去式: responded 过去分词: responded 现在分词: responding 第三人称单数: responds');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('criticize', '[\'krɪtɪsaɪz]', 'v.批评,责备', '1. You should not criticize him so harshly in his face. 你不应该当面这么严厉地批评他。 2. Basicly there is nothing to criticize in his works. 他的作品基本上无可挑剔。 3. Would you like to read and criticize my new novel? 您愿意阅读并评论一下我的新小说吗? 4. He is too ready to criticize others. 他很喜欢评论别人。', '形容词: criticizable 名词: criticizer 过去式: criticized 过去分词: criticized 现在分词: criticizing 第三人称单数: criticizes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hazard', '[\'hæzərd]', 'n.冒险,危险,冒险的事;vt.冒...的危险,赌运气,使遭危险', '1. The car had its hazard warning lights on. 这辆汽车亮起了危险信号灯。 2. He had put his own life in hazard. 他是在拿自己的生命来冒险。 3. There are many serious health hazards associated with smoking. 许多危害健康的情况都与吸烟有关。 4. He hazarded all his money in the attempt to save the business. 他为挽救这家企业，不惜冒险投入他的全部金钱。', '过去式: hazarded 过去分词: hazarded 现在分词: hazarding 第三人称单数: hazards');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tickle', '[\'tɪkl]', 'n.搔,胳肢,发痒;vt.胳肢,逗笑,使高兴,使发痒;vi.觉得痒,使人痒', '1. Babies like to be tickled and hugged. 婴儿喜欢轻轻呵痒和紧紧拥抱。 2. The comedian tickled the crowd with his jokes. 那个喜剧演员讲的笑话把人们都逗笑了。 3. I\'m tickled pink that my essay won the prize. 我的文章获奖了，我高兴得要命。 4. My ear tickles. 我耳朵痒。 5. The little girl laughed when her uncle gave her a tickle. 叔叔呵那个小姑娘的痒时，小姑娘笑起来。', '过去式: tickled 过去分词: tickled 现在分词: tickling 第三人称单数: tickles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('quest', '[kwest]', 'n.寻求', '1. This fruitless quest was called alchemy by the Arabs. 这种无谓的的探索被阿拉伯人称作炼金术。 2. Man will suffer many disappointments in his quest for truth. 人类在探索真理过程中必然会遭受挫折。 3. The quest for gold was difficult. 寻找金矿是很困难的。 4. The lawyer was on a quest for further evidence. 律师正在到处找寻更多的证据。 5. He decided to go on and continue with his quest. 他决定继续前进，继续寻找问题的答案。', '名词: quester 过去式: quested 过去分词: quested 现在分词: questing 第三人称单数: quests');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('assemble', '[ə\'sembl]', 'vt.集合,聚集,装配;vi.集合', '1. The students assembled in the school garden. 学生们在校园集合。 2. If the fire-alarm goes, staff should assemble outside the building. 火警警报响时全体人员应到楼外集合。 3. Assemble your papers and put them in the file . 把你们的论文收集起来归档。 4. The processing and assemble business is a component part of our foreign trade. 加工和装配贸易是我国对外贸易的一个组成部分。', '过去式: assembled 过去分词: assembled 现在分词: assembling 第三人称单数: assembles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('literal', '[\'lɪtərəl]', 'adj.文字的,照字面上的,无夸张的', '1. A literal translation is not always the closest to the original meaning. 逐字翻译不一定最接近原义。 2. He made a literal interpretation. 他逐字解释。 3. There had been a literal truth in his declaration. 从字面上看，他刚才说的话并不假。 4. We can get the answer by literal interpretation. 我们单从字面上就可以找到答案.', '名词: literalness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('crime', '[kraɪm]', 'n.犯罪,犯罪行为,罪行,罪恶', '1. He was acquitted of the crime. 他被宣告无罪。 2. His addiction to drugs propelled him towards a life of crime. 他吸毒成瘾使他走上了犯罪的道路。 3. The government is alarmed by the dramatic increase in violent crime. 政府对暴力犯罪案件的急剧增加感到担心。 4. It\'s a crime the way he bullies his children. 像他那样欺负自己的孩子真缺德。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('compound', '[\'kɑːmpaʊnd]', 'n.混合物,[化]化合物;adj.复合的;v.混合,配合', '1. Water is a compound of hydrogen and oxygen. 水是氢和氧的化合物。 2. \'Bus conductor\', \'dark-haired\' and \'policeman\' are compounds. bus conductor,dark-haired和policeman都是复合词。 3. Medicines are usually compounds. 药品通常是复合物。 4. All prisoners were frog-marched (out) into the compound. 犯人都被迫反剪双臂(出来)进入院子。 5. \"Fingerprint\" is a compound word. “Fingerprint”（指纹）是一个复合词。 6. He compounded various ingredients into an effective drug. 他将各种成分混合成一种有效的药物。 7. He compounded with his creditors for a remission of what he owed. 他和他的债权人谈妥免除其债务。', '形容词: compoundable 名词: compounder 过去式: compounded 过去分词: compounded 现在分词: compounding 第三人称单数: compounds');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('stable', '[\'steɪbl]', 'adj.稳定的', '1. Markets are flourishing and prices are stable. 市场繁荣, 物价稳定。 2. In order that our country could flourish and achieve its own goals, a stable environment within the country is definitely not dispensable. 国家要发展，要实现自己的目标，这是必不可少的条件，就是要国内有安定的环境。 3. The Sunnis hold a majority in four provinces and any government will have to respect them if they wish to administer a stable state. 逊尼派在四个省份里都是多数群体，而任何政府只要想管理一个安定的国家，就不得不对他们予以尊重。 4. He is a bit neurotic, but his wife is a very stable person. 他有点神经质，但他的妻子是一个非常稳重的人。 5. The horse in the stable has broken out. 马厩里的那匹马跑了。 6. Where do you stable your pony? 你那匹矮种马养在哪儿?（《牛津高阶英汉双解词典》）', '副词: stably 比较级: stabler 最高级: stablest 名词: stableness 过去式: stabled 过去分词: stabled 现在分词: stabling 第三人称单数: stables');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('masterpiece', '[\'mæstərpiːs]', 'n.杰作,名著', '1. The critics hailed his work as a masterpiece. 评论家们认定他的作品为杰作。 2. Do you think it was a masterpiece? 你认为这是杰作吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('phase', '[feɪz]', 'n.阶段,状态,相,相位;v.定相', '1. No phase transition evidence is found. 没有发现任何相位跃迁的证据。 2. Distortion can result from phase shifts. 相位变化将造成失真。 3. This is but one phase of the subject. 这仅是问题的一个方面。 4. They are talking about the changing phases of society. 他们谈论着不断变化的社会状况。 5. The use of lead-free petrol is now being phased in. 无铅汽油的应用现正逐步推广。', '形容词: phasic 过去式: phased 过去分词: phased 现在分词: phasing 第三人称单数: phases');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reveal', '[rɪ\'viːl]', 'vt.展现,显示,揭示,暴露', '1. Several withered trees on the sides of the road reveal the desolation here. 道路两旁的几棵枯木显示出这里的荒凉。 2. His deed revealed him to be a kind man. 他的行为显示他是个好心的人。 3. The journalist did not want to reveal the identity of his informant. 那个新闻工作者不想透露消息提供人的身分。 4. He would not reveal what decisions had been reached. 他不肯透露做出了什么决定。', '形容词: revealable 名词: revealer 过去式: revealed 过去分词: revealed 现在分词: revealing 第三人称单数: reveals');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('locomotive', '[ˌloʊkə\'moʊtɪv]', 'n.机车,火车头;adj.运动的', '1. He is a locomotive engineer. 他是一名火车司机。 2. They detached the locomotive from the train. 他们使火车头与列车脱离了。 3. The locomotive was dashed to pieces. 机车撞得粉碎。 4. The locomotive pulled a long line of freight cars. 那台机车拖了一长列货车。 5. Hands and feet are locomotive organs. 手和脚是运动器官。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('intimate', '[\'ɪntɪmət]', 'adj.亲密的,隐私的;vt.宣布,明白表示;n.熟友', '1. She was so kind as to forgive her intimate friend who had betrayed her when she was in a great difficulty. 她如此善良,竟能原谅在她处境最艰难时背叛她的挚友。 2. The magazine published intimate details of their affair. 这本杂志刊登出了他们恋情的私密细节。 3. Island communities commonly feel an intimate connection with the sea and with seafarers. 岛国的居民一般都会感觉自己与海洋和水手之间存在着紧密的联系。 4. He stated what others had only dared to intimate. 他说出了别人只敢暗示的话。 5. Sir Reginald was known to his intimates as \"Porky\". 雷金纳德爵士的至交都叫他“胖子”。', '副词: intimately 名词: intimateness 过去式: intimated 过去分词: intimated 现在分词: intimating 第三人称单数: intimates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('relative', '[\'relətɪv]', 'n.亲戚,关系词,相关物,亲缘植物;adj.有关系的,相对的,比较而言的', '1. Motion is absolute while stagnation is relative. 运动是绝对的,而静止是相对的。 2. They are now living in relative comfort. 他们现在过着比较安逸的生活。 3. Relative to the size, the city is sparsely populated. 与其面积相比, 这个城市的人口是稀少的。 4. The teacher asked me some questions relative to my paper. 老师问了我一些和我的论文有关的问题。 5. He showed such concern that people took him to be a relative. 他很关心别人，因而大家都把他当作亲人。', '名词: relativeness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('achievement', '[ə\'tʃiːvmənt]', 'n.成就,功绩', '1. Effort and achievement are always in full accord. 努力和成就总是相辅相承的。 2. You haven\'t realized the magnitude of her achievement. 你没有认识到她这一成就的重大意义。 3. I felt a great sense of achievement when I reached the top of the mountain. 当我到达山顶的时候，我有一种巨大的成就感。 4. Coming top in the exam was quite an achievement. 考第一是很了不起的成绩。', '动词: achieve');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('jeopardize', '[\'dʒepərdaɪz]', 'v.危害', '1. If you are rude to the boss, it may jeopardize your chance of success. 如果你对老板没有礼貌，那也许会危及你事业的成功。 2. Overworking can jeopardize your health. 工作过量可能会危及你的健康。 3. Being late so often will jeopardize your chances for promotion. 这么常迟到会危及你升迁的机会。 4. Soldiers jeopardize their lives in war. 士兵们在战争中使他们的生命陷入险境。', '过去式: jeopardized 过去分词: jeopardized 现在分词: jeopardizing 第三人称单数: jeopardizes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pretext', '[\'priːtekst]', 'n.借口,托辞;v.借口', '1. He stayed away under the pretext of ill health. 他以身体不佳为借口而避开了。 2. He refused to see them on one pretext or another. 他以种种借口拒绝见他们。', '过去式: pretexted 过去分词: pretexted 现在分词: pretexting 第三人称单数: pretexts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('compact', '[\'kɑːmpækt]', 'adj.紧凑的,紧密的,简洁的;n.契约,合同,小粉盒', '1. He received a compact package. 他收到一个扎得很紧的包裹。 2. As writers, they like a structure that is compact. 写文章的时候，他们喜欢采用紧凑的结构。 3. Regulator shall be corrosion resistant, compact and lightweight. 这种调节阀应该是耐腐蚀的，紧凑的和轻型的。 4. We\'d love to buy a compact car. 我们想买一辆简洁的车。 5. The kids are try to compact the sand into the mold. 孩子们正在设法把这沙土堆积到模子里。 6. You should sign your name on the right side of the compact. 你应该在合约的右边签上你的名字。', '副词: compactly 名词: compactness 过去式: compacted 过去分词: compacted 现在分词: compacting 第三人称单数: compacts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('facilitate', '[fə\'sɪlɪteɪt]', 'vt.（不以人作主语的）使容易,使便利,推动,帮助,使容易,促进', '1. Friendly contacts between different peoples facilitate the cultural and economic interchange. 各国人民的友好接触促进文化和经济交流。 2. We facilitate them to resist the enemy. 我们帮助他们与敌人对抗。 3. The new underground railway will facilitate the journey to all parts of the city. 新的地下铁路将为去城市各处提供方便。', '形容词: facilitative 名词: facilitator 过去式: facilitated 过去分词: facilitated 现在分词: facilitating 第三人称单数: facilitates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('majority', '[mə\'dʒɔːrəti]', 'n.多数,大半;n.[律]成年', '1. The majority of people seem to prefer TV to radio. 多数人喜欢电视胜过广播。 2. Racism is abhorrent to the majority of people. 种族主义是大多数人都憎恨的。 3. The Democrats became the majority in the election. 民主党在这次选举中变成了多数党。 4. The Democrats became the majority in the election. 民主党在这次选举中变成了多数党。', '名词复数: majorities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hike', '[haɪk]', 'v.远足,飞起,步行;n.远足,增加', '1. He always bring a canteen with him on a hike. 他作徒步旅行时总是带着水壶。 2. The storm upset their plans for a hike. 暴风雨破坏了他们的远足计划。 3. The government announced a 300 per cent hike in bread prices. 政府宣布面包涨价三倍。 4. He wants to hike round the world. 他打算徒步旅行环游世界一周。', '名词: hiker 过去式: hiked 过去分词: hiked 现在分词: hiking 第三人称单数: hikes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('radiate', '[\'reɪdieɪt]', 'vt.放射,辐射,传播,广播;vi.发光,辐射,流露;adj.有射线的,辐射状的', '1. Eight roads radiate from the square. 八条大道从广场呈辐射形伸展出去。 2. Heat radiated from the stove. 炉子散发的热量。 3. Heat radiates from the heating radiator and spreads to every corner of the room. 热从暖气片散发出来并传播到室内各个角落。 4. The radiance of electric lights radiates from the ceiling. 电灯的光芒从天花板上辐射下来。', '形容词: radiative 过去式: radiated 过去分词: radiated 现在分词: radiating 第三人称单数: radiates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('variation', '[ˌveri\'eɪʃn]', 'n.变更,变化,变异,变种,[音]变奏,变调', '1. Finally, the cherry in Fujian Wuyi Mountain should be treated as a new variation of Cerasus subhirtella in taxonomy. 最后，建议在分类学关系上将福建武夷山野生早樱做为大叶早樱新变种处理。 2. This is a set of variations on a theme by Mozart. 这是以莫扎特某一乐曲为主题的一组变奏曲。 3. Prices are subject to variation. 价格可以变动。 4. The dial records showed a very slight variation in pressure. 刻度盘显示出压力有极微小的变化。', '形容词: variational');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('triple', '[\'trɪpl]', 'n.三倍数,三个一组;adj.三倍的;vt.三倍与;vi.增至三倍', '1. The plan has a triple purpose. 该计划有三个目的。 2. I want a triple room with mountain view. 我想要一间向山的三人房。 3. Its population is about triple that of Venice. 它的人口大约是威尼斯的三倍。 4. The price is triple of what it\'s actually worth. 这个价格是它实际价值的三倍。 5. Output should triple by next year. 到明年产量应增至三倍。 6. Twelve is the triple of four. 十二是四的三倍数。', '过去式: tripled 过去分词: tripled 现在分词: tripling 第三人称单数: triples');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('eclipse', '[ɪ\'klɪps]', 'n.食,日蚀,月蚀,蒙蔽,衰落;vt.引起日蚀,引起月蚀,超越,使黯然失色', '1. It will take an hour to reach full eclipse stage. 从月食到全食历时一个小时。 2. It was reported that there would be a lunar eclipse tomorrow evening. 据报道说，明天晚上有月食。 3. The moon is partly eclipsed. 月偏食了。 4. It was reported that there would be an annular eclipse tomorrow. 据报道说，明天有日环食。 5. Its economy may well eclipse Japan\'s in size in 20 years or so.\" 中国经济的规模在20年左右的时间里完全可能超过日本。', '过去式: eclipsed 过去分词: eclipsed 现在分词: eclipsing 第三人称单数: eclipses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('exclude', '[ɪk\'skluːd]', 'vt.拒绝接纳,把...排除在外,排斥', '1. At this stage we cannot entirely exclude the possibility of staff cuts. 在目前这个阶段,我们还不能完全排除裁员的可能性。 2. I mean the last thing we would think about is to exclude the children from this plan. 我的意思是,我们绝不会考虑把孩子们排除在这个计划之外的。 3. Thick curtains help to exclude street noises. 厚窗帘有助于隔绝街上的噪音。 4. The court excluded the improperly obtained evidence. 法院不接受非正常渠道获得的证据', '形容词: excludable 名词: excludability 过去式: excluded 过去分词: excluded 现在分词: excluding 第三人称单数: excludes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('invert', '[ɪn\'vɜːrt]', 'adj.转化的;vt.使颠倒,使转化;n.颠倒的事物', '1. The little boy caught the insect by inverting the cup over it. 小男孩把杯子倒过来就逮住了那只昆虫。 2. The chairs were inverted on the table. 椅子被倒置过来放在了桌子上。 3. Place a plate over the cake tin and invert it. 在蛋糕烤模上盖一个盘子，然后将其翻倒过来。 4. Please invert the word order in a sentence. 请把句中的词序颠倒下。', '形容词: invertible 过去式: inverted 过去分词: inverted 现在分词: inverting 第三人称单数: inverts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('evil', '[\'iːvl]', 'adj.邪恶的,带来麻烦的,不幸的,有害的,诽谤的;n.邪恶,不幸,罪恶', '1. His evil designs were frustrated. 他的罪恶企图未能得逞。 2. The book gives, as it were, a picture of the evil old society. 这本书可谓是展现过去那个邪恶社会的图画。 3. Drug dealer is evil to the society. 毒品交易者有害社会。 4. What an evil smell! 多么臭的气味！ 5. My father taught me to render good for evil. 我父亲教导我要以德报怨。', '副词: evilly 比较级: eviler 最高级: evilest 名词: evilness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('prosperous', '[\'prɑːspərəs]', 'adj.繁荣的', '1. At no time has the country been more prosperous than at present. 我国任何时候都没有现在这样繁荣。 2. There are some areas of poverty, but the country as a whole is fairly prosperous. 这个国家有些地区比较贫困, 但总的来说是相当富裕的。 3. The city at one time must have been prosperous, for It enjoyed a high level of civilization. 这座古城在一个时期准是很繁荣的，因为它曾享有高度文明。 4. His business is prosperous. 他的事业兴旺发达。', '副词: prosperously 名词: prosperousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('interrupt', '[ˌɪntə\'rʌpt]', 'vt.打断(在说话或动作人),中断,妨碍,插嘴;vi.打断(别人的话或行动);n.(发给电脑的)中断信号', '1. It\'s not polite to interrupt a speaker. 打断人的谈话是不礼貌的。 2. The sudden noise from the next room interrupted my train of thinking. 从隔壁房间突然传来的吵闹声打断了我的思路。 3. I must go on, so please don\'t interrupt me. 我必须做下去,请不要打扰我。 4. Excuse me, I wonder if I could interrupt you for a moment. 对不起,能不能打扰您一会儿? 5. When I nod my head, that\'s your cue to interrupt the meeting. 我一点头，就是暗示你把会议中断。', '形容词: interruptible 名词: interruption 过去式: interrupted 过去分词: interrupted 现在分词: interrupting 第三人称单数: interrupts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('forge', '[fɔːrdʒ]', 'v.稳步前进,铸造,伪造', '1. These machine parts have been forged with the finest steel. 这些机器零件得用优质的钢锻造。 2. George was forced to forge a signature. 乔治被迫伪造签名。 3. They forged their manager\'s signature on the cheque. 他们在支票上伪造了经理的签名。 4. They tried to forge an alliance. 他们试图建立同盟。 5. Some people forge official documents. 有些人伪造公文。 6. He began to heat, like iron in the forge. 他象锻炉里的铁一样热起来。', '形容词: forgeable 名词: forgeability 过去式: forged 过去分词: forged 现在分词: forging 第三人称单数: forges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('barricade', '[ˌbærɪ\'keɪd]', 'v.设路障;n.路障', '1. Please step behind the police barricade. 请站在警戒线之后。 2. The soldiers make a barricade across the road. 士兵在路上设路障。 3. The soldiers stormed the barricades erected by the rioting crowd. 士兵们向暴乱分子设置的街垒发起了猛攻。 4. Everyone should be guarded by legal barricades. 人人都应受法律保障。 5. Residents were ready to go to the barricades to fight the school closure. 居民关于反对学校关闭一事准备展开争论。 6. They barricaded the main road with fallen trees. 他们用倒下的树堵住了主要道路。', '名词: barricader 过去式: barricaded 过去分词: barricaded 现在分词: barricading 第三人称单数: barricades');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('analysis', '[ə\'næləsɪs]', 'n.分析,分解', '1. His analysis of the problem showed great perception. 他对该问题的分析显示出敏锐的洞察力。 2. We agreed with his acute analysis of the political situation. 我们都同意他对政治形势的深刻分析。 3. Close analysis of sales figures showed clear regional variations. 对销售额的仔细分析显示出明显的地区差别。 4. In the final analysis I think our sympathy lies with the heroine of the play. 总之，我们认为我们都同情剧中的女主人公。', '名词复数: analyses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bronze', '[brɑːnz]', 'n.青铜(铜与锡合金),铜像;adj.青铜色的', '1. The statue is made of bronze. 这座雕像是青铜铸成。 2. We fuse copper and tin to make bronze. 我们把铜和锡熔制成青铜。 3. The woods today are burnished bronze. 今天的树林是一片发亮的青铜色。 4. The sanctuary lamp and the metal furniture were bronze. 圣灯和一切金属器物都是青铜制品。 5. The sculpture was a bronze cast. 这个雕塑是青铜铸成的 6. His face had been bronzed by the sun. 他的脸被太阳晒成古铜色。', '形容词: bronzy 名词: bronzer 过去式: bronzed 过去分词: bronzed 现在分词: bronzing 第三人称单数: bronzes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('slight', '[slaɪt]', 'adj.轻微的,微小的', '1. He has a slight wheeze in his chest. 他呼吸时胸部发出轻微的响声。 2. Our army suffered a slight reverse. 我们的部队受到轻微的挫败。 3. The salve will heal slight burns. 这药膏能治疗轻微烧伤。 4. Her slight frame was shaken by bouts of coughing. 她纤弱的身躯因阵阵咳嗽而发颤。 5. We shouldn\'t slight anybody even if he\'s a nobody. 我们不应该轻视任何人，即使他是一个小人物。 6. I was hurt by the obvious slight. 这种明显的怠慢伤害了我的感情。', '比较级: slighter 最高级: slightest 名词: slightness 过去式: slighted 过去分词: slighted 现在分词: slighting 第三人称单数: slights');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('wax', '[wæks]', 'n.蜡,蜡状物,增加,月亮由亏转盈;vi.变大,增大,月亮渐满;vt.上蜡于', '1. Blobs of wax covered the candlestick. 烛台上全是一团团的蜡。 2. He is modeling a unicorn in wax . 他在用蜡制作独角兽。 3. They bought wax and honey up by the great. 他们大量购进蜜蜡和蜂蜜。 4. Why did she have to wax the floors herself? 她干什么非要自己动手给地板打腊? 5. The moon is waxing. 月亮越来越圆。', '过去式: waxed 过去分词: waxed 现在分词: waxing 第三人称单数: waxes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('conscious', '[\'kɑːnʃəs]', 'adj.有意识的,有知觉的,故意的,羞怯的', '1. His rudeness was conscious, not accidental. 他的粗暴无礼是故意的,不是偶然的。 2. He was conscious of his guilt. 他自知有罪。 3. I am conscious that I have done right. 我相信自己做得不错。 4. I had to make a conscious effort not to be rude to him. 我得刻意约束自己不要对他粗鲁。 5. ou avoid conflict between your conscious and subconscious in the sleepy state. 在你处于昏昏欲睡状态时，你要避免你的表意识和潜意识之间的冲突。', '副词: consciously');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('brink', '[brɪŋk]', 'n.(峭岸、崖的)边缘', '1. Natalie is living on the brink of panic. 娜塔丽正生活在痛苦的边缘。 2. She knows well that she and Louis are on a brink. 她深深知道，她和路易斯是到了危险的边沿。 3. Prosecutors said he left Enron because he knew the company was on the brink of bankruptcy. 检察官说他离开的原因是因为他知道公司已经处于破产的边沿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('maximum', '[\'mæksɪməm]', 'n.最大量,最大限度,极大;adj.最高的,最多的,最大极限的', '1. This hall holds a maximum of seventy people. 这厅最多容纳七十人。 2. The child turned the volume up to the maximum. 小孩把音量转到了最大。 3. It is the maximum the insurance company will pay. 这是保险公司所能付给的最大金额。 4. Our goal is to achieve the maximum of efficiency. 我们的目标是取得最高的效率。 5. The maximum price we can pay is 50 pence per yard. 我们所能出的最高价格是每码50便士。', '名词复数: maximums');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('unfold', '[ʌn\'foʊld]', 'vt.打开,显露,开展,阐明;vi.伸展,开花,呈现;vt.放(羊)出栏', '1. The war seemed to unfold in the blink of an eye. 这场战争在眨眼间就展开了。 2. That\'s how life tends to unfold before us. 生活就是这样在我们前面展开。 3. She seemed to unfold like a strong white lily under this genial breath of admiration and homage. 她似乎在这赞赏和尊敬的真诚氛围之中象一朵白色的水仙那样猛烈地开放了。 4. A walk through town will unfold many interesting buildings. 一条穿越城镇的行道将显露很多有趣的建筑物。', '名词: unfoldment 过去式: unfolded 过去分词: unfolded 现在分词: unfolding 第三人称单数: unfolds');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('orbit', '[\'ɔːrbɪt]', 'n.轨道,势力范围,生活常规,眼眶;vt.绕...轨道而行;vi.进入轨道,沿轨道飞行,盘旋', '1. Hou Kou district fell into Japanese orbit before the outbreak of the second sino-Japan war. 虹口区在抗日战争爆发前就已落入日本人手中。 2. In the right orbit, an external ethmoidectomy was done, while in the left, a transnasal endoscopic approach was used to remove the inferomedial wall. 两边皆以外侧眼眶切开术行外侧眼窝减压术合并内侧及部分眼窝底减压术。 3. Conclusions For patients undergoing enophthalmos caused by a crepitant frature in orbit, it is the best way to perform an operation as early as possible. 结论对于眼眶爆裂性骨折引起的眼球内陷可考虑早期手术，其效果优于晚期手术者。 4. The spacecraft is in orbit around the moon. 该航天器在绕月球轨道运行。 5. The space shuttle will orbit a weather satellite. 太空梭将把一个气象卫星送入运行轨道。 6. Make one more orbit to the left again. 左转弯再盘旋一圈。', '过去式: orbited 过去分词: orbited 现在分词: orbiting 第三人称单数: orbits');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('faith', '[feɪθ]', 'n.信任,信念,宗教信仰,忠实,保证,诺言,约定', '1. Christians profess their faith when they say the Creed. 基督教徒在念信经时就表明了他们的宗教信仰。 2. Missionaries went far afield to propagate their faith. 传教士到远方去传播其信仰。 3. The disaster caused him to waver in his faith. 这件灾难使他对信仰发生了动摇。 4. He has great talent, but he has lost his faith. 他很有天赋，但是他已经丧失了信心。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('overthrow', '[\'oʊvərθroʊ]', 'n.推翻,打倒,扔得过远得球;vt.打倒,推翻,颠覆', '1. They attempted to overthrow the monarch. 他们企图推翻国王。 2. They were plotting the overthrow of the government. 他们正在策划推翻政府。 3. The big Sam absolutely has the strength to overthrow Jerry. 高大的山姆绝对有力量打倒杰瑞。 4. Indeed,the day when this gigantic net is formed will undoubtedly be the day of the complete overthrow of Japanese imperialism. 实际上，日本帝国主义完全打倒之日，必是这个天罗地网大体布成之时。 5. They schemed for the overthrow of the government . 他们阴谋推翻政府。', '过去式: overthrew 过去分词: overthrown 现在分词: overthrowing 第三人称单数: overthrows');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('distinguish', '[dɪ\'stɪŋɡwɪʃ]', 'v.区别,辨别', '1. Speeches distinguish human beings from animals. 人类和动物的区别在于人会说话。 2. It\'s important to distinguish fact from fiction. 把现实与虚构区分开来是很重要的。 3. The twins were so much alike that it was impossible to distinguish one from the other. 这对孪生子像得使人无法分辨。 4. We should distinguish between right and wrong. 我们应辨别是非。', '形容词: distinguishable 副词: distinguishably 过去式: distinguished 过去分词: distinguished 现在分词: distinguishing 第三人称单数: distinguishes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('stroll', '[stroʊl]', 'n.漫步,闲逛,四处流浪;v.闲逛,漫步,跋涉于', '1. She decided to take a stroll in the garden. 她决定在花园散步。 2. A stroll round the garden hardly qualifies as exercise! 在花园转转算不上锻炼！ 3. My father sometimes goes out for a stroll with a stick in his hand. 父亲有时候带着手杖出去散步。 4. A casual stroll through a lunatic asylum shows that faith does not prove anything. 疯人院的一次闲庭漫步说明信念并不能证明一切。 5. We stroll through a meadow full of tall grass. 我们漫步走过长满高草的牧场。', '过去式: strolled 过去分词: strolled 现在分词: strolling 第三人称单数: strolls');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('infectious', '[ɪn\'fekʃəs]', 'adj.有传染性的,易传染的,有感染力的', '1. Measles is an infectious disease. 麻疹是种传染病。 2. When you have this anthema, you are still infectious. 身上还有这种疹子就仍然有传染性。 3. Flu is an infectious disease characterized by fever, aches and pains and exhaustion. 流感是一种传染病，其特征是发热、全身疼痛和疲乏无力。 4. He expressed infectious enthusiasm to his voters. 他对他的选民表现出很有感染力的热情。', '副词: infectiously 名词: infectiousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rehearsal', '[rɪ\'hɜːrsl]', 'n.排演,演习,预演,试演', '1. The symphony is in rehearsal now. 这支交响乐正在排练中。 2. This is not a concert, but more of a rehears. 与其说那是一场音乐会，倒不如说是一次排练。 3. Is there a rehearsal for the concert? 音乐会有彩排吗? 4. I had panic attacks during rehearsal. 彩排的时候我有过多次的恐慌。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sparkle', '[\'spɑːrkl]', 'v.发火花,(使)闪耀,(香槟酒等)发泡,用眼神表达,发光闪烁;n.火花,闪光,光彩,活力,发泡', '1. There was a sparkle of excitement in her eyes. 她眼里闪耀着激动的光芒。 2. A single sparkle shone at first, like a first sparked wispling. 一个火花先闪烁了起来，如同一个首次闪亮的幽光般。 3. The stars sparkle in the dark sky. 夜晚的天空上星星闪闪发光。', '过去式: sparkled 过去分词: sparkled 现在分词: sparkling 第三人称单数: sparkles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('addict', '[\'ædɪkt]', 'vt.使沉溺,使上瘾;n.入迷的人,有瘾的人', '1. The young generation should addict themselves to science. 年轻的一代应该酷爱科学。 2. His tastes addict him to the study of antiquity. 嗜好使他沉迷于研究古代的事物。 3. He was addicted to cocaine. 他吸可卡因上瘾。 4. He is turning into an internet addict. 他快变成网虫了。', '形容词: addictive 过去式: addicted 过去分词: addicted 现在分词: addicting 第三人称单数: addicts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('debate', '[dɪ\'beɪt]', 'v.争论,辩论;n.争论,辩论', '1. After a long debate, the house of commons approved the bill. 经过长时间的辩论，下议院通过了议案。 2. We had a long debate as to whether we should spend so much money on space technology. 至于我们要否花那么多钱在太空技术上,我们辩论了很久。 3. Her resignation caused much public debate. 她辞职一事引起群众议论纷纷。 4. There has been heated debate about whether the film should be allowed. 关于这场电影是否该通过,人们展开了热烈的讨论。 5. I don\'t wish to debate my opinions with you. 我不想就我的看法同你辩论。 6. This is a question that they have often debated. 这是个他们常讨论的问题。', '名词: debatement 过去式: debated 过去分词: debated 现在分词: debating 第三人称单数: debates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('racial', '[\'reɪʃl]', 'adj.人种的,种族的,种族间的', '1. We should not have racial discrimination. 我们不该有种族歧视。 2. This hatred was generated by racial prejudice. 这种仇恨是由种族偏见引起的。 3. Genuine racial equality still seems light-years away. 真正的种族平等似乎仍遥遥无期。 4. A new law has been brought in to discourage racial prejudice. 一项反对种族歧视的新法律已被提出。', '副词: racially');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('absence', '[\'æbsəns]', 'n.不在,缺席,缺乏,没有', '1. His long absence raised fears about his safety. 他长期不在引起了大家对他的安全的担心。 2. What was the real reason for your absence? 你缺席的真正原因是什么？ 3. We are in the absence of experience. 我们缺乏经验。 4. The absence of color in that drawing make it dull. 那幅画因没有着色而显得晦暗。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('congress', '[\'kɑːŋɡrəs]', 'n.(代表)大会,[C～](美国等国的)国会,议会', '1. This matter will be discussed in congress tomorrow. 这个问题将在明天的代表大会上讨论。 2. The National People\'s Congress is the supreme organ of state power. 全国人民代表大会是最高国家权力机关。 3. The mayor must make policies in accordance with the bill passed in the Congress. 市长要根据议会的议案来制定政策。 4. A new peace initiative was approved by Mexico\'s congress. 墨西哥立法机关通过了一项最新的和平方案。', '形容词: congressional 副词: congressionally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('span', '[spæn]', 'n.跨度,跨距,范围;v.横越', '1. Modern medicine has increased man\'s life span. 现代医学延长了人的寿命。 2. He has settled here for a long span of time. 他已经在这儿定居很长一段时间了。 3. The arch has a span of 60 meters. 拱门的跨度为60米。 4. The spider has a leg span of 3 inches. 这个蜘蛛的腿的长度为3英寸。 5. The shipwrecks span nearly a century. 这些船只残骸已有近百年历史。', '过去式: spanned 过去分词: spanned 现在分词: spanning 第三人称单数: spans');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('testimony', '[\'testɪmoʊni]', 'n.证词(尤指在法庭所作的),宣言,陈述', '1. His hearty laughter is testimony of his happiness. 他尽情的欢笑可以证明他很幸福。 2. Nothing could refute her testimony that the driver was drunk. 她关于那个司机已经喝醉的证词无可辩驳。 3. The witness is giving false testimony. 那个证人在作伪证。 4. The statement is confirmed by testimony. 这个说法由证据所证实了。', '名词复数: testimonies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('routine', '[ruː\'tiːn]', 'n.例行公事,常规,日常事务,程序', '1. We must introduce some system into our office routine. 我们须在我们日常公务中建立一些制度。 2. They did it as a matter of routine. 他们那样做只是例行公事。 3. This type of work rapidly becomes routine. 这种工作很快就变得乏味无聊。 4. You just need to break out of that boring routine. 你只需改变一成不变的无聊生活。 5. The film is a love story, with routine portraits of a conductor and a violinist. 那部电影是一个爱情故事,对於乐队指挥和小提琴手之间的爱情描写都是老一套。', '副词: routinely 名词: routinism');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('denote', '[dɪ\'noʊt]', 'vt.指示,表示', '1. A smile often denotes pleasure and friendship. 微笑常常表示高兴和友善。 2. These nouns denote a state of joyful exuberance. 这些名词都指示洋溢着欢乐的状态。 3. Dark clouds denote a coming storm. 黑云表明风暴要来临。 4. We often denote danger by red letters. 我们常常用红字表示危险。', '形容词: denotable 过去式: denoted 过去分词: denoted 现在分词: denoting 第三人称单数: denotes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dizzy', '[\'dɪzi]', 'adj.(指人)晕眩的,昏乱的,(指地点,情况)使人晕眩的', '1. The airplane climbed to a dizzy height. 飞机爬到令人头晕目眩的高度。 2. Riding on merry-go-round makes me feel dizzy. 骑木马让我觉得眩晕。 3. Prices keep rising at a dizzy rate. 物价以极快的速度不断上涨。 4. He likes to drive at a dizzy speed. 他喜欢开快车。 5. The old woman was dizzied by the strong wind. 那位老太太被风吹得头昏眼花。', '副词: dizzily 比较级: dizzier 最高级: dizziest 名词: dizziness 过去式: dizzied 过去分词: dizzied 现在分词: dizzying 第三人称单数: dizzies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('revenge', '[rɪ\'vendʒ]', 'n.报仇,复仇;vt.替...报仇,复仇', '1. They vowed revenge on their enemies. 他们发誓要向敌人报仇。 2. She said she would take her revenge on Tom. 她说她要向汤姆报仇。 3. Thoughts of revenge kept running through his mind. 他脑海里时刻萦绕着复仇的念头。 4. I want revenge against her on more scores than one. 我有种种理由要向她报复。 5. They thirsted to revenge themselves upon the enemy. 他们渴望向敌人报复。', '名词: revenger 过去式: revenged 过去分词: revenged 现在分词: revenging 第三人称单数: revenges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('available', '[ə\'veɪləbl]', 'adj.可用到的,可利用的,有用的,有空的,接受探访的', '1. Do you have a room available? 你们有空房间吗？ 2. The swimming pool is available only in summer. 这个游泳池只在夏天开放。 3. All sorts of lamps are available in that shop. 在那家商店可买到各式各样的灯具。 4. The Prime Minister was not available for comment. 首相无暇作出评论。', '副词: availably 名词: availability');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('midst', '[mɪdst]', 'n.中间;prep.在...中间', '1. He was but recently in our midst. 他只是最近才到我们中间。 2. In his escape, he walked six days in the midst of howling wilderness. 在逃亡期间，他在人迹罕至的旷野中走了6天。 3. We must weed out the traitors in our midst! 我们必须清除我们中间的叛徒! 4. The girls had got on well together until the apple of discord in the person of a handsome young man arrived in their midst. 姑娘们一直相处很好，后来一个英俊的小伙子来到她们中间，引起了她们之间的不和。 5. So Paul went out from their midst. 于是保罗从他们当中出去了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('offset', '[\'ɔːfset]', 'n.偏移量,抵销,弥补,分支,平版印刷,胶印;vt.弥补,抵销,用平版印刷;vi.偏移,形成分支', '1. The pay raise will be offset by inflation. 增加的工资会被通货膨胀所抵销。 2. Higher mortgage rates are partly offset by increased tax allowances. 抵押款提高了，其中一部分可由免税额增加而抵消。 3. Hedge can help them offset inventory loss when commodity price fall. 在商品价格下跌时,套期保值能够帮助他们抵补存货价跌的损失。 4. He raised his prices to offset the increased cost of materials. 他提高售价以补偿材料增加的成本。 5. Offset requirements also vary between these areas. 补偿要求在这些地区也各有不同。', '过去式: offset 过去分词: offset 现在分词: offsetting 第三人称单数: offsets');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('access', '[\'ækses]', 'n.通路,访问,入门;vt.存取,接近', '1. This is the only means of access to the building. 这是进入这栋楼的唯一入口。 2. The avalanche cut off the access to the mountain village. 雪崩切断了进入山村的通道。 3. The only access to that building is along the track. 到那座大楼的唯一通道就是沿这条小路走。 4. Only high officials have access to the president. 只有高级官员才可以接近总统。 5. An error occurred when we tried to access the inventory database. 当我们试图进入存货数据库时，屏幕上显示出现了错误。', '过去式: accessed 过去分词: accessed 现在分词: accessing 第三人称单数: accesses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('statement', '[\'steɪtmənt]', 'n.声明,陈述,综述', '1. She refused to make a statement to the police lest she （should） incriminate herself. 她拒绝向警方作陈述以免受连累。 2. Her views were fully elaborated in a written statement. 她的观点在一篇书面声明中得到了充分的阐述。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('presumably', '[prɪ\'zuːməbli]', 'adv.推测起来,大概', '1. Presumably the bad weather has delayed the flight. 大概恶劣的天气使飞机误点了。 2. She is aware of the difficulties, presumably? 她对这些困难大概了解吧? 3. They have been purposefully perforated, presumably to be strung together. 而且还被有目的的穿孔了，据推测是为了把它们穿起来。 4. Presumably Bryant would only leave to a team that offered an equal or greater chance to win a title. 据推测，布莱恩特将只会留在一个能提供给他平等或更大机会赢得总冠军的一支球队。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('consultant', '[kən\'sʌltənt]', 'n.顾问,商议者,咨询者', '1. Of all the consultants, only Mr. Wang gave us some proposals in point. 所有的顾问当中，只有王先生提了一些中肯的建议。 2. The spy\'s cover was that she was a consultant engineer. 那女间谍伪装成顾问工程师。 3. The consultant was a woman who had many unanswered questions. 这个女性咨询者有许多有待解决的问题。', '名词: consultantship');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('scatter', '[\'skætər]', 'v.分散,散开,撒开,驱散', '1. She wanted us to scatter her ashes to the winds. 她希望我们把她的骨灰散播到风中。 2. The farmers were scattering seed on the fields. 农夫把种子撒在田里。 3. Let\'s try not to scatter food or drink on the table. 别把饭或汤撒到桌上。 4. The police scattered the crowd. 警察驱散了人群。 5. Small villages scatter at the foot of the mountain. 村庄零零落落地散布在山脚下。 6. She gave the soup a quick scatter of herbs. 她把香料快速撒在汤上。', '名词: scatterer 过去式: scattered 过去分词: scattered 现在分词: scattering 第三人称单数: scatters');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('utmost', '[\'ʌtmoʊst]', 'n.极限,最大可能,极力;adj.极度的,最远的', '1. He had the utmost respect for his teachers. 他极度尊敬他的老师。 2. His giving up has put us in a position of the utmost difficulty. 他的放弃已经把我们置于一个极度困难的境地。 3. The train was crowded to the utmost capacity. 火车拥挤到了最大限度。 4. The bus was already filled to its utmost limit. 这辆公共汽车乘坐人数已达到最大限额。 5. That was the utmost we could do. 那是我们能做的极限。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pitch', '[pɪtʃ]', 'n.程度,斜度,树脂,投掷,定调,船前后颠簸,沥青;vt.投,掷,向前倾,定位于,用沥青涂,扎营;vi.搭篷,投掷,坠落,倾斜', '1. The pitch is too small to play football on. 球场太小了, 无法踢足球。 2. Speculation has reached such a pitch that a decision will have to be made immediately. 这种胡乱猜测甚嚣尘上，已经到了必须立即解决的程度了。 3. The pitch depends on the frequency. 音调的高低是由频率决定的。 4. He has a very clever sales pitch. 他推销商品的口才很好。 5. She pitched the ball as far as she could. 她尽力把球投得远一些。', '过去式: pitched 过去分词: pitched 现在分词: pitching 第三人称单数: pitches');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('notation', '[noʊ\'teɪʃn]', 'n.符号', '1. He introduced a notation for negative numbers. 他为负数引进了一个符号。 2. A more convenient notation will now be given. 现在将给出一种较为方便的表示法。 3. You Westerners use the five-line staff notation. 你们西方人用的是五线谱。 4. He made a notation on his engagement calendar. 他在约会日程上作了记载。', '形容词: notational');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('polish', '[\'pɑːlɪʃ]', 'n.磨光,光泽,上光剂,优雅,精良;vt.擦亮,发亮,磨光,推敲;vi.发亮,变光滑;adj.波兰的;n.波兰人', '1. A hot plate will spoil the polish on this table. 热盘子会毁坏桌面的光泽。 2. This car polish is an effective shield against rust. 这种汽车上光蜡很有防锈作用。 3. With this polish you can give a good high gloss to the wood. 使用这种上光蜡可使木器表面极为光亮平滑。 4. Now we have a presentable great speaker whose polish reminds me of Will Smith. 现在我们能言善辩的总统，他的优雅一直让我想起了威尔史密斯。 5. I polished my buttons with a handkerchief. 我用手帕把钮扣擦亮。 6. When I awoke, a Polish man came to my room, held my hand and looked at me with friendly eyes. 当我醒来时,一名波兰人走过来,他握着我的手,亲切地望着我。 7. My spoken Polish is better than my written Polish. 我的波兰语说得比写得好。', '名词: polisher 过去式: polished 过去分词: polished 现在分词: polishing 第三人称单数: polishes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('impetus', '[\'ɪmpɪtəs]', 'n.推动力,促进', '1. His articles provided the main impetus for change. 他的那些文章是促进变革的主要推动力。 2. The present conflict may provide fresh impetus for peace talk. 目前的冲突可能会给和谈提供新的推动力。 3. Her speech gave an impetus to my ideas. 她的讲话激发了我的思绪。 4. His articles provided the main impetus for change. 他的那些文章是促进变革的主要推动力。', '名词复数: impetuses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('lunar', '[\'luːnər]', 'adj.月的,月亮的', '1. The astronauts piloted their craft down to the lunar surface. 宇航员驾驶宇宙飞船在月球表面降落。 2. Lunar eclipse occur when the earth\'s shadow fall on the moon. 地球的影子落在月球上时,就发生月蚀。 3. It was reported that there would be a lunar eclipse tomorrow evening. 据报道说，明天晚上有月食。 4. All traditional Chinese festivals are lunar calendar festivals. 中国的传统节日都是按照太阴历计算的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('diploma', '[dɪ\'ploʊmə]', 'n.文凭,毕业证书,证明权力、特权、荣誉等的证书,奖状', '1. He obtained a diploma in architecture. 他获得了建筑学的学位证书。 2. The youth won his diploma after only three years. 那青年仅用了3 年时间就取得毕业文凭。 3. When a person has successfully completed a certain course of study, he is given a diploma by the school. 当一个人成功地完成了某一课程的研读,学校将授予他一张文凭。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mask', '[mæsk]', 'n.面具,掩饰,石膏面像;vt.戴面具,掩饰,使模糊;vi.化装,戴面具,掩饰,参加化装舞会', '1. They did so under the mask of charity. 他们是打着慈善的幌子这么做的。 2. He longed to throw off the mask of respectability. 他渴望丢掉那副道貌岸然的伪装。 3. Her sociable manner is really a mask for a very shy nature. 她那好交际的作风，实际上是她腼腆天性的伪装。 4. The bank robber wears a stocking mask. 那个抢劫银行的匪徒戴着长筒袜面罩。 5. Her smile masked true feelings. 她的微笑掩饰了她的感情。', '形容词: maskable 过去式: masked 过去分词: masked 现在分词: masking 第三人称单数: masks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('edible', '[\'edəbl]', 'adj.可食用的', '1. Is linseed oil edible? 亚麻籽油可以食用吗？ 2. Some of the algae are edible. 有些藻类是可以吃的。 3. Throw that tainted meat away; it\'s not edible. 把那块腐烂的肉扔掉，不能再吃了。 4. This food is scarcely edible. 这种食物真是难以下咽。 5. I eat everything that is edible. 我吃食品的每件事物。', '名词: edibility');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('imitate', '[\'ɪmɪteɪt]', 'vt.模仿,仿效,仿制,仿造;v.模仿', '1. You should imitate great and good people. 你应仿效伟大善良的人。 2. Teachers provide a model for children to imitate. 教师是孩子们仿效的典范。 3. People imitate diamonds with crystal. 人们用水晶仿造钻石。 4. He can imitate his teacher perfectly. 他能维妙维肖地模仿他的老师。', '名词: imitator 过去式: imitated 过去分词: imitated 现在分词: imitating 第三人称单数: imitates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('security', '[sə\'kjʊrəti]', 'n.安全', '1. I\'ll undertake for your security. 我将保证你的安全。 2. The visitors were secarched for security reasons. 为了安全起见,来宾受到了检查。 3. Our own actions are our security. 我们的行为是自己的保证。 4. He traded in securities and became rich. 他做证券交易发了财。', '名词复数: securities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mansion', '[\'mænʃn]', 'n.大厦,官邸,公寓(用复数,用于专有名词中)', '1. The family owns a lordly mansion. 那个家族拥有一座气派的大厦。 2. The portal of the mansion looks magnificent. 这座大厦的正门看上去富丽堂皇。 3. The poor girl was astonished by the sumptuous furnishings of the mansion. 这个贫穷的女孩被大厦里的豪华的陈设惊呆了。 4. The broad steps in front of the mansion made it look very dignified. 宽阔的台阶使大厦的正面显得很气派。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('web', '[web]', 'n.网,蛛丝,蹼,翼手,织物,圈套,卷筒纸;vi.使陷入罗网,形成网;vt.织蜘蛛网于,使落入圈套;环球网', '1. A spider weaves a web to catch prey. 蜘蛛为捕猎昆虫而织网。 2. The tiger was enmeshed in the web laid by hunter. 老虎缠在猎人布下的网里。 3. Do you think art and design are melding on the web? 你认为在网络上艺术和设计是相结合的吗？ 4. He breathlessly watched the spider attempt to spin its web for the third time. 他凝神屏息地观看那蜘蛛试图第三次结网。 5. Do you think that the spider can web anything? 你觉得这蜘蛛能用网捕住什么吗?', '过去式: webbed 过去分词: webbed 现在分词: webbing 第三人称单数: webs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reserve', '[rɪ\'zɜːrv]', 'n.储备(物),储藏量,预备队;vt.储备,保存,保留,预定,预约', '1. We reserve the right to lodge a claim for loss. 我们保留要求赔偿损失的权利。 2. I have reserved a table at the restaurant. 我已在饭店预订了一桌菜。 3. The court will reserve judgement. 法庭将延期判决。 4. He has played very well on the reserve side but this chance in the first team should put him on his mettle. 他在候补队中表现非常出色,但这次作为正式队员参赛将对他的能力进行考验。 5. He spoke with reserve. 他说话谨慎。', '形容词: reservable 名词: reserver 过去式: reserved 过去分词: reserved 现在分词: reserving 第三人称单数: reserves');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('handicap', '[\'hændikæp]', 'n.障碍,阻碍,障碍赛跑;v.妨碍,使不利,阻碍', '1. Blindness is a great handicap. 失明是极大的障碍。 2. Deafness can be a serious handicap. 耳聋算是严重的缺陷。 3. Poor eyesight is a handicap to a student. 视力不好对学生来说是一个障碍。 4. It takes a lot of grit to overcome a physical handicap. 要很大的毅力来克服生理上的障碍。 5. Ignorance can handicap the progress of a city. 无知会妨碍城市的进步。', '过去式: handicapped 过去分词: handicapped 现在分词: handicapping 第三人称单数: handicaps');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('seemingly', '[\'siːmɪŋli]', 'adv.表面上地', '1. Any seemingly viable proposition will be tested by market research. 任何表面上可行的建议都要通过市场研究予以检验。 2. The utility, though seemingly rebuffed, in fact got what it wanted, or thereabouts. 公司虽然表面上遭到了挫败，实际上得到了它所要求的，或者相差不多的增额。 3. She plays with seemingly effortless skill. 她演奏得似乎毫不费力。 4. He is seemingly to have lost enthusiasm in reading. 他似乎在阅读上已经失去了热情。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('customary', '[\'kʌstəmeri]', 'adj.习惯的,惯例的', '1. That\'s his customary shortcoming. 那是他一个习惯的毛病。 2. Obviously, this has gone beyond their customary limits. 显然，这已经超出了置业习惯的限制。 3. He refused to have his portrait conventionalized into the customary smooth beauty of the pharaoh god. 他不让他的画像具有惯例的法老神的那种传统的温和的美。 4. In addition, the personal right of copyright can be restricted by the laws related, the customs, especially the professional customary practices. 此外，著作人身权还要受到相关法律和习惯，尤其是行业惯例的限制。', '副词: customarily 名词: customariness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pore', '[pɔːr]', 'n.毛孔,小孔,气孔;vi.熟读,凝视,细想,沉思;vt.因凝视过度使...疲劳', '1. He was sweating through every pore. 他每个毛孔都在冒汗。 2. Sweat exudes through the pores. 汗从毛孔中渗出。 3. Water seeped into the pores of the rock. 水迅速被岩石的空隙吸收。 4. He had spent several hours in the library poring over those musty documents. 他一连好几个小时呆在图书馆里仔细翻阅那些发霉味的文献资料。', '过去式: pored 过去分词: pored 现在分词: poring 第三人称单数: pores');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('figure', '[\'fɪɡjər]', 'n.外形,体形,图形,画像,数字,形状,身份;vt.描绘,塑造,表示,象征,演算,认为;vi.出现,考虑,出名,扮演角色', '1. Our textbook has many figures to help explain the lessons. 我们的教科书有许多图表帮助解释课文。 2. The figure is expressed as a percentage. 那数字是以百分比表示的。 3. He has a more angular figure than his father. 他的体型比他的父亲更显得有棱角。 4. I like the color of the hat instead of its figure. 虽然我喜欢这顶帽子的颜色,但我不喜欢它的形状。 5. My feelings about the matter didn\'t seem to figure at all. 我对这个问题的意见似乎根本无足轻重。', '名词: figurer 过去式: figured 过去分词: figured 现在分词: figuring 第三人称单数: figures');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('basis', '[\'beɪsɪs]', 'n.基础,基本,根据,主要成分(或要素),(认识论中的)基本原则或原理', '1. His research formed the basis of his new book. 他的研究成果是他这本新书的基础。 2. We drew this conclusion on the basis of experiments. 我们是在试验的基础上得出这个结论的。 3. What basis do you have for saying that? 你那样说有什么根据啊? 4. Rates of work are calculated on a weekly basis. 工资是以周为计算基准的.', '名词复数: bases');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('peel', '[piːl]', 'v.剥,削,剥落', '1. She threw the banana peel into the trash can. 她将香蕉皮扔进垃圾筒。 2. It is said that the apple peel contains a lot of vitamins. 据说苹果皮富含维生素。 3. The paper was beginning to peel off the walls. 墙上的纸渐渐脱落了. 4. He likes to peel an apple before he eats it . 吃苹果前，他喜欢削皮。 5. He got sunburn and his skin began to peel. 他被日光灼伤后,皮肤开始脱落。', '过去式: peeled 过去分词: peeled 现在分词: peeling 第三人称单数: peels');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('institution', '[ˌɪnstɪ\'tuːʃn]', 'n.公共机构,协会,制度', '1. The institution of school rules is necessary. 制定学校规则的是很有必要的。 2. Marriage is an institution in most societies. 婚姻是大多数社会早已确立的制度。 3. Marriage is love. Love is blind. Therefore marriage is an institution for the blind. 婚姻就是爱情,爱情是盲目的,所以婚姻是一所收容盲人的机构。 4. My uncle has become quite an institution at the club. 我叔叔在俱乐部里已是颇有名气的人物了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bribe', '[braɪb]', 'n.贿赂;vt.贿赂,向...行贿', '1. He is so honest that he will not accept bribe. 他忠诚老实，不肯受贿。 2. There is a big stink about his accepting a bribe. 他收受贿赂，引起一场大纠纷。 3. He demeant himself by accepting a bribe. 他接受了贿赂，辱没了自己。 4. He bribed his way past the guard and escaped. 他买通看守而逃之夭夭了。', '形容词: bribable 名词: briber 过去式: bribed 过去分词: bribed 现在分词: bribing 第三人称单数: bribes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reassure', '[ˌriːə\'ʃʊr]', 'vt.使...安心,再保证,使...恢复信心,打消...的疑虑', '1. The police reassured her about the child\'s safety. 警察让她放心，她的孩子很安全。 2. We went to the hospital to reassure ourselves about his condition. 我们去医院查明他的病情以使我们安心。 3. The manager tried to reassure her that she will not lose her job. 经理试图使她解除疑虑,她是不会失去工作的。 4. A glance in the mirror reassured him that his tie wasn\'t crooked. 他照了一下镜子，领带确实没有戴歪。', '副词: reassuringly 名词: reassurance 过去式: reassured 过去分词: reassured 现在分词: reassuring 第三人称单数: reassures');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('momentum', '[moʊ\'mentəm]', 'n.动力,要素', '1. They began to lose momentum in the second half of the game. 在比赛的下半场，他们的势头就逐渐减弱。 2. We should continue to maintain good growth momentum. 我们应继续保持良好的增长势头。 3. I am picking up momentum every single day. 我现在每天都会获得动力。 4. The peace movement gained momentum. 和平运动获得了动力。', '名词复数: momenta');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('conflict', '[\'kɑːnflɪkt]', 'n.斗争,冲突;vi.抵触,冲突', '1. Both sides suffered heavy casualties in the border armed conflict. 在这次边界武装冲突中双方都遭到了重大伤亡。 2. He was wounded in the conflict. 他在战斗中负伤。 3. This is an irreconcilable conflict. 这是一个不可调和的矛盾。 4. He\'s got involved in a political conflict he can\'t extricate himself from. 他陷在一场政治斗争中不能脱身。 5. Your interests conflict with mine. 你的利益和我的冲突。', '形容词: conflictive 名词: confliction 过去式: conflicted 过去分词: conflicted 现在分词: conflicting 第三人称单数: conflicts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('donate', '[\'doʊneɪt]', 'v.捐赠,赠予', '1. I can donate one hundred dollars at best. 我充其量只能捐助100美元。 2. We donate to the school endowment fund every year. 我们每年向学校的捐赠基金捐款。 3. The government calls on the youth to donate their blood voluntarily. 政府号召青年义务献血。', '名词: donator 过去式: donated 过去分词: donated 现在分词: donating 第三人称单数: donates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('incredible', '[ɪn\'kredəbl]', 'adj.<口>难以置信的', '1. I think it\'s incredible. 我认为这是难以置信的。 2. That\'s the most incredible coincidence I\'ve ever heard of! 那是我听说过的最难以置信的巧合！ 3. He showed an incredible indifference to the matter. 他对这件事表现出令人难以置信的淡漠。 4. He has an incredible house! 他有一所极美的房子！', '副词: incredibly 名词: incredibility');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('flush', '[flʌʃ]', 'n.奔流,晕红,激动,萌芽,活力旺盛,发烧,一手同花的五张牌,惊鸟;adj.挥霍的,直接的,丰足的,泛滥的;adv.齐平地,直接地;vi.(脸)发红,奔涌,充沛,惊飞;vt.淹没,冲洗,使脸红,使齐平,使惊飞,使激动', '1. Father asked me to flush off the garage floor. 父亲叫我冲洗车库的地板。 2. The toilet won\'t flush properly. 马桶不好冲。 3. Don\'t forget to flush the toilet after use. 用完厕所,不要忘了冲。 4. Mary flushed crimson with embarrassment. 玛丽羞得脸红了。 5. A flush of excitement crept into his face. 兴奋的红晕爬上他的脸。', '比较级: flusher 最高级: flushest 名词: flusher 过去式: flushed 过去分词: flushed 现在分词: flushing 第三人称单数: flushes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('frequent', '[\'friːkwənt]', 'adj.时常发生的,频繁的', '1. My girlfriend writes frequent letters to me. 我的女朋友频繁地给我写信。 2. Traffic accidents are alarmingly frequent of late. 近来交通事故频繁得吓人。 3. He is a frequent visitor to our house. 他是我们家的常客。 4. He suffers from frequent bouts of depression. 他患多发性抑郁症。 5. He used to frequent the town\'s bars and night-clubs. 他从前常去镇上的酒吧和夜总会。', '名词: frequentation 过去式: frequented 过去分词: frequented 现在分词: frequenting 第三人称单数: frequents');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('transaction', '[træn\'zækʃn]', 'n.办理,处理,会报,学报,交易,事务,处理事务', '1. Had you not helped us, we should have canceled this transaction. 假如没有你的帮助，这笔生意早就告吹了。 2. His failure in this transaction was due to nothing else than his own carelessness. 他在这笔交易中的失利完全是由于他自己的粗心大意。 3. Payments by cheque easily outnumbered cash transactions. 用支票付款在数量上大大超过现金交易。 4. They charge a fixed rate for each transaction. 他们对办理的每项业务收取一定的费用。', '形容词: transactional');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('affection', '[ə\'fekʃn]', 'n.友爱,爱情,影响,疾病,倾向', '1. He\'s so susceptible that she easily gained his affection. 他易受感情影响，所以她很轻易就得到了他的爱。 2. You appear to me to allow nothing for the influence of friendship and affection. 我觉得你未免否定了友谊和感情对于一个人的影响。 3. Don\'t squander your affection on him, he\'ll never love you. 不要把感情浪费在他身上，他是永远不会爱你的。 4. He\'s so susceptible that she easily gained his affection. 他易受感情影响，所以她很轻易就得到了他的爱。', '形容词: affectional 副词: affectionally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('entity', '[\'entəti]', 'n.实体', '1. A corporation is treated by the law as an entity. 法人在法律上被视为一个实体。 2. It describes the change in an entity\'s state. 它描述了一个实体的状态变化。', '名词复数: entities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('frantic', '[\'fræntɪk]', 'adj.狂乱的,疯狂的', '1. That noise is driving me frantic. 那种噪音真要把我弄疯了。 2. The child\'s parents were frantic when she did not return home on time. 那孩子没有按时回家，她父母都要急疯了。 3. Don\'t drive him frantic by worrying him with endless questions. 不要以无穷尽的问题困扰他而使他狂乱。 4. She was frantic with worry. 她愁得要命。', '副词: frantically 名词: franticness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rape', '[reɪp]', 'n.掠夺,强奸,葡萄渣,油菜;vt.掠夺,强奸', '1. She showed a prurient interest in the details of the rape case. 她对那强奸案的细节津津乐道。 2. There is mention of capital penalties for rape. 对强奸有死刑的规定。 3. Their action led to the rape of the countryside. 他们的行为破坏了乡村。 4. He attempts to rape the heroine. 他想去强奸女主人公。', '名词: raper 过去式: raped 过去分词: raped 现在分词: raping 第三人称单数: rapes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('primary', '[\'praɪmeri]', 'adj.第一位的,主要的,初步的,初级的,原来的,根源的', '1. The primary task for socialism is to develop the productive forces. 社会主义的首要任务是发展社会生产力。 2. Another primary reason is that there seems to be too many private cars and not enough public buses. 另一个主要原因是私家车过多而公交车不够。 3. The demand for primary products is on the increase in European market. 欧洲市场对初级产品的需求在增长。 4. Primary education comes under the umbrella of local government. 小学教育受地方政府的保护。 5. We should place development on the primary in governing and rejuvenating the country. 我们应将发展放在执政兴国中的第一位。', '名词复数: primaries');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('adhere', '[əd\'hɪr]', 'vi.粘附,胶着,坚持;v.坚持', '1. They failed to adhere to our original agreement. 他们未能遵守我们原定的协议。 2. We should adhere to our opinions. 我们应当坚持我们的意见。 3. We adhere to the principle stand of marxism. 我们坚持马克思主义思想原则。 4. The new paint won\'t adhere to the walls so I\'ll have to strip it all off and start from scratch. 新涂的油漆粘不住墙壁,因此我得把它全部刮掉,重新刷过。', '过去式: adhered 过去分词: adhered 现在分词: adhering 第三人称单数: adheres');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('curb', '[kɜːrb]', 'n.路边', '1. He parked his car along the curb. 他把汽车停靠在路边。 2. I stood at the curb trying to breathe. 我站在人行道沿上想缓口气。 3. You must try to put a curb on your bad temper. 你必须学着克制自己暴躁的脾气。 4. High interest rates put a curb on spending. 高利率抑制了消费 5. I could be able to curb my desires. 我能够抑制住自己的欲望。', '过去式: curbed 过去分词: curbed 现在分词: curbing 第三人称单数: curbs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('activate', '[\'æktɪveɪt]', 'vt.刺激,使活动;vi.有活力', '1. You can activate the system by buttons or voice recognition. 你可以通过按钮或者声音识别来激活系统。 2. The burglar alarm was activated by mistake. 防盗铃误响了。 3. I think if you flip the blue switch near the bottom it will activate the air conditioner. 我想，如果你把下方的蓝色开关轻轻地推上，冷气就会出来了。 4. These push buttons can activate the elevator. 这些按钮能启动电梯。', '名词: activation 过去式: activated 过去分词: activated 现在分词: activating 第三人称单数: activates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bacteria', '[bæk\'tɪriə]', 'n.细菌', '1. Many diseases are caused by bacteria. 许多疾病是由细菌引起的。 2. Bacteria are too small to see with the naked eye. 细菌太小，肉眼看不见。 3. It is possible to multiply bacteria and other living organisms in the laboratory. 在实验室能够繁殖细菌和其他生物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('management', '[\'mænɪdʒmənt]', 'n.经营,管理,处理,操纵,驾驶,手段', '1. The farm prospered through good management. 由于管理有方，农场兴旺发达。 2. The failure of the scheme was due to bad management. 计划的失败是由于管理不善。 3. The management took all reasonable safety precautions. 管理部门采取了一切合理的安全措施。 4. She gets them to accept these changes by tactful management. 她用机智的手段使他们接受了这些改变。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('federal', '[\'fedərəl]', 'adj.联邦的,联合的,联邦制的,同盟的;n.(南北战争)北部联邦同盟盟员;连邦软件公司,国内正版经销商', '1. Switzerland is a federal republic. 瑞士是联邦制的共和国。 2. Expenditures by the Federal Government have been steadily pared. 联邦政府的开支正在逐渐削减。', '副词: federally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('productivity', '[ˌprɑːdʌk\'tɪvəti]', 'n.生产力', '1. We should aim with efforts for higher productivity. 我们应该力争达到更高的生产率。 2. This will help do away with heavy manual labour and raise productivity. 这可以帮助消除繁重的体力劳动，提高劳动生产率。 3. Improved productivity justifies an increase in wages. 提高了生产力理应增加工资。 4. The workers are trying their best to increase productivity. 工人们正竭尽全力提高生产力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('consumption', '[kən\'sʌmpʃn]', 'n.消费,消费量,肺病', '1. The government encourages individual consumption. 政府鼓励个人消费。 2. Internet shopping is a new way of consumption. 网上购物是当今消费的一种新途径。 3. The meat was condemned as unfit for human consumption. 这种肉已宣布不适宜人们食用。 4. The car scored well in fuel consumption. 那部汽车在燃料消耗方面获得好评。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('contend', '[kən\'tend]', 'v.斗争,竞争,主张', '1. Three armed groups were contending for power. 三个武装集团在争夺权力。 2. John has to contend with great difficulties. 约翰得与那些艰难困苦作斗争。 3. They have to contend against drought every year. 他们每年都得与干旱做斗争。 4. But the potential is simply too significant, the experts contend. 但是专家们主张，潜力是非常重要的。', '名词: contender 过去式: contended 过去分词: contended 现在分词: contending 第三人称单数: contends');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fantastic', '[fæn\'tæstɪk]', 'adj.幻想的,奇异的,稀奇古怪的,荒谬的,空想的', '1. We watched a fantastic play yesterday evening. 昨天晚上我们看了一场非常精彩的演出。 2. I have a fantastic amount of work to do. 我有大量的工作要做。 3. My daughter likes to describe her fantastic dreams to me. 我女儿喜欢给我讲她那些奇怪的梦。 4. It is so fantastic that a child of 5 can speak so good English. 真难以置信,一个五岁的孩子英语竟然说得这么好。', '副词: fantastically 异体字: fantastical 名词: fantasticality');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('occur', '[ə\'kɜːr]', 'vi.发生,出现', '1. That plane crash occurred only minutes after take-off. 空难在起飞几分钟后就发生了。 2. Misprints occur on every page. 每页都有印刷错误。 3. A connection error might occur. 可能会出现连接错误。 4. Didn\'t it occur to you that he was lying? 你当时没想到他在撒谎吗？', '过去式: occurred 过去分词: occurred 现在分词: occurring 第三人称单数: occurs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('motel', '[moʊ\'tel]', 'n.汽车旅馆', '1. I went back to the motel to phone Jane. 我回到汽车旅馆给珍打电话。 2. The motel is dead ahead about a mile from here. 那家汽车旅馆就在前方大约一英里的地方。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('entertainment', '[ˌentər\'teɪnmənt]', 'n.款待,娱乐,娱乐表演', '1. There are few entertainments in that town. 那个镇上几乎没有娱乐设施。 2. Television provides universal entertainment. 电视提供大众化的娱乐。 3. Wrestling is in a twilight zone between sport and entertainment. 摔跤是介於运动和娱乐两者之间的活动。 4. This hotel is famous for its entertainment. 这家旅馆以殷勤待客著称。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('monetary', '[\'mʌnɪteri]', 'adj.货币的,金钱的', '1. The monetary unit of the US is the dollar. 美国的货币单位是元。 2. He has changed his stance on monetary union. 他已经改变了对货币联盟的态度。 3. The monetary system of some countries used to be based on gold. 过去有些国家的货币制度是金本位制的。 4. The current monetary policy is strangling the economy. 现行金融政策抑制了经济的发展。', '副词: monetarily');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('progressive', '[prə\'ɡresɪv]', 'n.改革论者,进步论者;adj.前进的,(税收)累进的,进步的', '1. She is the most progressive writer of that times. 她是那个时代最进步的作家。 2. That famous progressive thinker was asked to deliver a speech at the meeting. 那位著名的进步思想家被邀请在会议上发表演讲。 3. History can not hold progressive movement. 历史无法阻挡前进的步伐。 4. He noted a progressive speech impediment. 他发觉，说话障碍逐渐厉害起来。 5. The butchers at Pingkiang killed progressive people. 平江惨案的那些刽子手，他们把进步分子杀了。', '副词: progressively 名词: progressiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('jog', '[dʒɑːɡ]', 'n.轻推,轻撞,漫步;v.轻推,(使)蹒跚行进,(使)慢跑', '1. He goes jogging every night. 他每晚慢跑。 2. You jogged my elbow and spoiled what I was drawing. 你撞到了我的手肘，弄坏了我正在画的图画。 3. The wagon jogged along on the rough road. 马车沿着崎岖不平的道路颠簸前行。 4. I go for a jog in the park every morning. 每天早晨我在公园里慢跑。', '名词: jogger 过去式: jogged 过去分词: jogged 现在分词: jogging 第三人称单数: jogs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('instinct', '[\'ɪnstɪŋkt]', 'n.本能', '1. Don\'t trust anything except your instinct. 只管相信你的直觉。 2. She had, too, a true instinct as to the man. 她对这男人还有一种正确的直觉。 3. It is his instinct to reckon on women as constant by their nature. 他的直觉使他认为女人在本质上就是一成不变的。 4. You should not go by instinct in deciding a question. 在决定一个问题时，你不能靠直觉。 5. She likes to hear words instinct with love. 她喜欢听充满爱意的言辞。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('specification', '[ˌspesɪfɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.详述,规格,说明书,规范', '1. Can you give me a price list with specification? 你能否给我一份有规格说明的价目单吗？ 2. In case of need we can offer you some other brand of the same specification. 万一有需要,我们可供应同样规格的其它品牌货品。 3. I want to know his specification of details. 我想知道他对细节的详述。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('quota', '[\'kwoʊtə]', 'n.配额,限额', '1. Why is my Daily Resultb Quota so sall? 为什么我的每日工作限额那么小？ 2. Calculate the total Sentence Quota of the summary. 计算出摘要应包含的句子的限额。 3. The committee reversed its decision on import quota. 委员会取消了对进口货物的配额的决定。 4. The quota on import cars has been lifted. 对汽车的进口配额已被取消。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('induce', '[ɪn\'duːs]', 'vt.劝诱,促使,导致,引起,感应', '1. The medicine will induce sleep. 这种药会引起睡意。 2. They hoped their work would induce social changes. 他们希望自己的工作可以引起社会上的某些变化。 3. I can\'t think what induced her to marry him. 我想不出到底是什么原因促使她嫁给他。 4. Alcohol can induce a loosening of the tongue. 酒精可使人信口开河。', '形容词: inducible 过去式: induced 过去分词: induced 现在分词: inducing 第三人称单数: induces');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('interaction', '[ˌɪntər\'ækʃn]', 'n.交互作用,交感', '1. Price is determined through the interaction of demand and supply. 价格在供需的相互作用中形成。 2. Often the development groups have little in common and no interaction with one another. 通常情况下,开发团队的共性很少,相互之间也没有交互。 3. There should be a lot more interaction between the social services and local doctors. 社会公益服务机构和当地医生应该加强协作。 4. People get job satisfaction from different factors, such as social interaction with colleagues. 人们在从工作得到不同的方面工作满足,同事之间的相互交流。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cemetery', '[\'seməteri]', 'n.墓地,公墓', '1. He was buried in this cemetery. 他被安葬在这个公墓里。 2. They buried the urn in the cemetery. 他们将骨灰瓮埋在了公墓里。 3. His remains were shipped back and laid away in a cemetery. 他的遗体被运回，埋葬在一个公墓里。', '名词复数: cemeteries');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('imperative', '[ɪm\'perətɪv]', 'n.命令,诫命,需要,规则,祈使语气;adj.命令的,强制的,紧急的,必要的,势在必行的,[语法]祈使的', '1. It is imperative that we make a quick decision. 我们要尽快做出决定。 2. It\'s imperative that you apologize to him immediately. 你必须立即向他道歉。 3. \"Go!\" is in the imperative mood. “Go！”是祈使语气的句子。 4. Survival is our first imperative. 我们当务之急是设法生存下来。', '副词: imperatively 名词: imperativeness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('relief', '[rɪ\'liːf]', 'n.(痛苦等的)减轻,(债务等的)免除,救济,调剂,安慰,浮雕,地貌', '1. The pills gave her some relief. 药片减轻她一些痛苦。 2. This medicine will give you quick relief. 这种药将迅速解除你的病痛。 3. A doctor\'s life is consecrated to the relief of suffering. 医师的一生奉献于解除世人的疾苦。 4. His jokes provided some comic relief in what was really a dull speech. 他说的笑话给极沉闷的讲话增加几分轻松气氛。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('van', '[væn]', 'n.有篷货车,先锋,前驱,前卫;vt.用车搬运', '1. As the bus turned the corner, it collided with a van. 公共汽车转过拐角时与客货车相撞。 2. I was bundled into a police van. 我被推进警车。 3. He brought three people to the party in his van. 他用客货车载了三个人来参加聚会。 4. Two men in boiler suits emerged from inside the rear van of the train. 两个穿连衫裤工作服的男人从火车行李车厢后面冒出来。 5. The race horses were vanned from here to there. 赛马被用有篷卡车从这里运送到那里。', '过去式: vanned 过去分词: vanned 现在分词: vanning 第三人称单数: vans');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('independence', '[ˌɪndɪ\'pendəns]', 'n.独立,自主', '1. The country attained its independence in 1972. 这个国家在1972年获得了独立。 2. The government adopted an uncompromising posture on the issue of independence. 政府在独立的问题上采取了毫不妥协的态度。 3. I tried to preserve my independence. 我试图保持自己的独立性。 4. This money gives me independence from my family. 这笔钱使我能离家自立了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('destruction', '[dɪ\'strʌkʃn]', 'n.破坏,毁灭', '1. It will cause pollution and the destruction of our seas and oceans. 这会引起污染，破坏我们的海洋和江河。 2. Scientific knowledge was perverted to help cause destruction and war. 科学知识被滥用于破坏和战争。 3. Gambling was his destruction. 赌博把他毁了。 4. We must not bring mass destruction on ourselves by waging an atomic world war. 我们千万不要发动世界核子战争而自招集体毁灭。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pole', '[poʊl]', 'n.棒,柱,杆,竿,极,磁极,电极;vt.用竿支撑,用棒推;vi.撑篙', '1. Pole vaulters need long run-ups. 撑竿跳需要长距离助跑。 2. The hut was made of poles covered with grass mats. 茅屋用木杆搭成，上面以草席覆盖。 3. He had put up a basket on a pole in the back yard. 他在后院一根柱子上安一个球篮。 4. When Scott reached the South Pole he found Amundsen had anticipated him. 当斯科特抵达南极的时候，发现阿蒙森比他到得更早。', '过去式: poled 过去分词: poled 现在分词: poling 第三人称单数: poles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ozone', '[\'oʊzoʊn]', 'n.新鲜的空气,[化]臭氧', '1. CFCs cause depletion of atmospheric ozone. 氟氯化碳会损耗大气臭氧。 2. Dyes have to be more resistant to ozone. 染料更能抵制臭氧。 3. Just breathe in the ozone on the sea. 吸吸海上的新鲜空气吧。', '形容词: ozonic');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dub', '[dʌb]', 'vt.[电影]配音,轻点,授予称号,打击;n.鼓声,笨蛋', '1. Is the film dubbed or does it have subtitles? 这部影片是经过配音的还是配上字幕的？ 2. We can also translate, subtitle and dub your company videos. 我们也可以为贵公司的宣传录像进行翻译、上字幕及配音。 3. The papers dubbed them The Fab Four\'. 报刊给他们起了个绰号叫｀四绝＇. 4. This led the official Chinese media to dub Rio a “dishonourable woman”. 这使得中国媒体将力拓称为“不忠诚的女人。”', '名词: dubber 过去式: dubbed 过去分词: dubbed 现在分词: dubbing 第三人称单数: dubs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bureaucracy', '[bjʊ\'rɑːkrəsi]', 'n.官僚,官僚作风,官僚机构', '1. All this is a product of corrupt bureaucracy. 这一切都是腐朽的官僚制度的产物。 2. The bureaucracy has become ossified. 官僚主义已变得僵化了。 3. The dead hand of bureaucracy is slowing our progress. 官僚主义的流毒拖慢了我们的进步。 4. You will find a lot of bureaucracy in this company. 你会在这个公司看到很严重的官僚作风。', '名词复数: bureaucracies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('virgin', '[\'vɜːrdʒɪn]', 'n.处女,处男;adj.处女的,童贞的,纯洁的,洁白无瑕疵的,未被玷污的,原始的,处于原状态的,未伐过的森林;美国游戏公司', '1. I could call her nothing in my own mind save \"stainless virgin\". 我的心里除了叫她为“白壁无瑕的处女”而外，实在找不出其它的称呼来。 2. She remained a virgin all her life. 她终生未婚。 3. There are vast expanses of virgin land in the remote regions. 在边远地区有大片大片未开垦的处女地。 4. You are the virgin angel in my dream. 你是我梦中纯洁的天使！ 5. Virgin Islands National Park also offers stunning white-sand beaches and 22 hiking trails. 维尔京群岛国家公园也有极美的白沙沙滩，还有二十二条健行步道。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('lease', '[liːs]', 'n.租借,租约,租赁物,租期,延续的一段时间;vt.出租,租出,租得', '1. Our present lease on the flat expires next month. 我们这套公寓的租约下月到期。 2. An astute tenant always reads the small print in a lease. 精明的租户对租契上的每个细小之处都要讲究。 3. Does your current lease provide for showings prior to the tenant vacating the property? 您当前的租契是否规定了在房客搬出房间之前可以提前展售？ 4. The lease of my house has only a year to run . 我的房子的租约期限只有1年了。 5. This company leases out property. 这个公司出租房地产。', '形容词: leasable 名词: leaser 过去式: leased 过去分词: leased 现在分词: leasing 第三人称单数: leases');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('function', '[\'fʌŋkʃn]', 'n.官能,功能,作用,职责,典礼,仪式,[数]函数;vi.(器官等)活动,运行,行使职责', '1. What is his function on the committee? 他在委员会里担任什么职务? 2. The teacher did not explain its grammatical function. 老师没有解释它的文法功能。 3. The function of the ear is to listen. 耳的功能是听。 4. Periodic change imposed on a controlled variable or a function by a controller. 通过控制器控制某一变量或函数进行周期性变化。 5. However, many system features and tasks will not function correctly. 但是,许多系统功能和任务将无法正常运行。', '形容词: functionless 过去式: functioned 过去分词: functioned 现在分词: functioning 第三人称单数: functions');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rupture', '[\'rʌptʃər]', 'v.破裂,裂开,断绝(关系等),割裂;n.破裂,决裂,敌对,割裂', '1. The negotiation came to a rupture. 谈判破裂了。 2. He died of a rupture of blood-vessels. 他血管破裂而死。 3. Failure of the machine may be caused by the rupture of the triangle belt. 这台机器的故障可能是由三角带断裂引起的。 4. I nearly gave myself a rupture lifting that pile of books. 提那一大堆书差点儿让我得了疝气。 5. He\'ll rupture a muscle if he goes on dancing like that! 他要是继续那样跳舞，会跳得皮开肉裂！', '形容词: rupturable 过去式: ruptured 过去分词: ruptured 现在分词: rupturing 第三人称单数: ruptures');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('emphasize', '[\'emfəsaɪz]', 'vt.强调,着重;v.强调', '1. He emphasized the importance of careful driving. 他强调小心驾驶的重要性。 2. We cannot emphasize too much the importance of learning English. 我们再怎样强调学英文的重要性也不为过。 3. Which word should I emphasize? 我应该重读哪个词? 4. I would like to emphasize that we are ready to meet the management at any time. 我想着重指出，我们愿意在任何时候与管理部门会谈。', '过去式: emphasized 过去分词: emphasized 现在分词: emphasizing 第三人称单数: emphasizes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('staple', '[\'steɪpl]', 'n.钉书钉,钉,主要产品(或商品),原材料,主要成分,来源;adj.主要的,常用的,大宗生产的;v.把...分类,把...分级', '1. He used a pair of scissors to take the staple out of the document. 他用剪刀将订书钉从文件上取了出来。 2. Coffee is the staple of this district. 咖啡是这个地区的主要产品。 3. Bread, potato and other staple continue to rise in price. 面包、土豆及其他主食的价格继续上涨。 4. For example, rice is a staple crop in much of Asia. 例如，在亚洲大米是原料农作物。 5. Short stories are her staple reading. 短篇小说是她经常看的读物。 6. He stapled the paper together. 他把文件钉在一起。', '过去式: stapled 过去分词: stapled 现在分词: stapling 第三人称单数: staples');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('accumulate', '[ə\'kjuːmjəleɪt]', 'v.积聚,堆积', '1. They set out to accumulate a huge mass of data. 他们开始积累大量的资料。 2. Dust and dirt soon accumulates if a house is not cleaned regularly. 房屋不经常打扫,尘土很快就越积越多。 3. True poetry accumulates meaning every time it is read. 真正好诗愈念涵义愈丰富。 4. However, as the evidence began to accumulate, experts from the zoo felt obliged to investigate. 然而，当证据日趋增多时，该动物园的专家们感到有必要进行调查。', '形容词: accumulable 过去式: accumulated 过去分词: accumulated 现在分词: accumulating 第三人称单数: accumulates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('exert', '[ɪɡ\'zɜːrt]', 'vt.尽(力),施加(压力等),努力;v.发挥,竭尽全力,尽', '1. He exerted all his influence to make them accept his plan. 他用尽一切影响力使他们接受他的计划。 2. He doesn\'t have to exert himself on my behalf. 他不必为我费那么大力气。 3. You have to exert more efforts if you want to catch up with your classmates. 你要想赶上你的同学的话,就得多花些功夫。 4. His teachings still exert a strong influence. 他的教导仍在产生巨大影响。', '过去式: exerted 过去分词: exerted 现在分词: exerting 第三人称单数: exerts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('smuggle', '[\'smʌɡl]', 'n.走私,偷带;v.走私', '1. They deny conspiring together to smuggle drugs. 他们否认共谋走私毒品。 2. Well, sir, when you smuggle things you lose them. 好了，先生，如果您走私东西，您就要失去这些东西。 3. He tried to smuggle diamonds into Japan. 他企图把钻石偷运进日本。 4. The syndicate collaborated with vice syndicates in the Mainland to smuggle women into Hong Kong for providing sex services. 该集团亦与内地的卖淫集团勾结，偷运女子来港卖淫。', '名词: smuggler 过去式: smuggled 过去分词: smuggled 现在分词: smuggling 第三人称单数: smuggles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('margin', '[\'mɑːrdʒən]', 'n.页边的空白,(湖、池等的)边缘,极限,利润,差数,(时间、金额等的)富余;vt.加边于,加旁注于', '1. We came to the margin of the wood. 我们来到树林的边缘。 2. We allowed a margin of 20 minutes in catching the train. 我们有20分钟的余地赶火车。 3. There is no margin for error in our plan. 我们的计划中不留有误差幅度。 4. Our pricing policy aims at producing a 35% gross margin. 我们的定价政策目的在于赢得35%的毛利润。 5. The shore was margined with foam. 岸边都是泡沫。', '形容词: margined 过去式: margined 过去分词: margined 现在分词: margining 第三人称单数: margins');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('champion', '[\'tʃæmpiən]', 'n.冠军,拥护者,战士;vt.拥护,支持', '1. He is a champion of women\'s rights. 他是妇女权利的卫士. 2. He is the undisputed champion. 他是无可争辩的冠军。 3. He is a champion at writing familiar essays. 他是写小品文的好手。 4. Every absurdity have a champion to defend it. 任何谬论都拥有拥护它的斗士。 5. He is forced to champion unpopular causes. 他被迫去支持一些不得人心的事业。', '过去式: championed 过去分词: championed 现在分词: championing 第三人称单数: champions');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('necessitate', '[nə\'sesɪteɪt]', 'v.成为必要', '1. It would be best if these disputes could be resolved without recourse to the courts, but the broad reach of electronic networking will probably necessitate changes in common law. 如果诸如此类的争议可以不上法庭就获得解决，是最好不过了，但电子网路的无远弗届或许会迫使普通法改变。', '形容词: necessitative 名词: necessitation 过去式: necessitated 过去分词: necessitated 现在分词: necessitating 第三人称单数: necessitates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('manifest', '[\'mænɪfest]', 'n.载货单,旅客名单;adj.显然的,明白的;vi.出现;vt.表明,证明', '1. His generosity manifests itself in times of difficulties. 他的慷慨在困境中表现了出来。 2. Opportunities will manifest in ways you never even dreamed of. 机会的到来出乎你的意料。 3. No one can manifest the truth of his statement. 没人能证明他讲的是真话。 4. The contradiction manifested itself in the employment situation. 在就业问题上矛盾暴露了。 5. It was manifest to us at a glance. 我们对此事一目了然。 6. Can you give us a copy of import manifest? 能给我们一份进口舱单吗?', '副词: manifestly 过去式: manifested 过去分词: manifesed 现在分词: manifesting 第三人称单数: manifests');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('lofty', '[\'lɔːfti]', 'adj.高高的,崇高的,高傲的,高级的', '1. There are lofty fells behind this village. 这个村庄后面是高高的荒山。 2. Longer shadow falls from lofty mountain. 山高投影长。 3. They saw the lofty peak in all its majesty. 他们看到了高耸的山峰，气势雄伟壮丽。 4. He has lent his name to the lofty cause. 他以自己的名义支持这一崇高的事业。', '副词: loftily 比较级: loftier 最高级: loftiest 名词: loftiness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('invalid', '[ɪn\'vælɪd]', 'n.病人,残废者;adj.有病的,残废的', '1. A passport that is out of date is invalid. 护照过期是无效的。 2. Unless a check is signed, it is invalid. 支票除非签了名，否则是无效的。 3. She looks after her invalid mother. 她照看病弱的母亲。 4. Nobody looks after the invalid. 没人照顾这个病人。 5. He was invalided out of the army because of the wounds he received. 他因负伤而退役。', '副词: invalidly 名词: invalidity 过去式: invalided 过去分词: invalided 现在分词: invaliding 第三人称单数: invalids');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('divorce', '[dɪ\'vɔːrs]', 'n.离婚,脱离;vt.使离婚,与...脱离', '1. They demanded the divorce of the subsidiary from the parent firm. 他们要求子公司与母公司分离。 2. Boredom is not a ground for divorce. 日久生厌不能成为离婚的理由。 3. She has filed a petition for divorce. 她已向法院申请离婚。 4. Divorce has become an everyday occurrence. 离婚已成为每天都有的事了。 5. He is unable to divorce fantasy from reality. 他不能将幻想与现实分开。 6. My information is they\'re going to divorce. 我所得到的信息是他们打算离婚。', '过去式: divorced 过去分词: divorced 现在分词: divorcing 第三人称单数: divorces');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dignity', '[\'dɪɡnəti]', 'n.尊严,高贵', '1. He would do nothing beneath his dignity. 他决不愿意干任何有损自身尊严的事。 2. The real dignity of a man lies in what he is, not in what he has. 一个人的真正尊严在于他的品格，而非他的财富。 3. A man\'s dignity depends not upon his wealth but upon his character. 人高尚与否不取决於他的财富,而取决於他的品格。 4. She bears herself with dignity. 她举止庄重大方。', '名词复数: dignities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('agony', '[\'æɡəni]', 'n.苦恼,极大的痛苦', '1. It was great agony to watch him passing away. 看着他死去是极大的痛苦。 2. The agony of that moment was terrific. 那一刹那的痛苦是可怕的。 3. He was in an agony of remorse. 他处于悔恨的海洋中。 4. Rescue the jobber girl who struggles in agony. 救救痛苦中挣扎的打工妹。', '名词复数: agonies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hitherto', '[ˌhɪðər\'tuː]', 'adv.迄今,至今', '1. Hitherto, this is the advanced method. 到目前为止，这是先进的方法。 2. Hitherto he had experienced no great success in his attempt. 到目前为止，他的这种尝试还没有取得任何重大的成功。 3. For hitherto though I have lost all my time. 迄今我虽然失去了全部的时日。 4. I had hitherto continued to board with Godfrey. 迄今我仍在戈费雷处用膳。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('interpret', '[ɪn\'tɜːrprɪt]', 'v.解释,说明,口译,通译,认为是...的意思', '1. To interpret at the UN is a difficult task. 在联合国做口译是件难 度很大的差事. 2. We need somebody to interpret from Russian into English. 我们需要一个把俄语口译为英语的人。 3. She interpret his silence as arrogance. 她把他的沉默解释为傲慢。 4. The guide interpreted the woman\'s remarks for us. 向导把那个女人的话翻译给我们听。', '形容词: interpretable 名词: interpretability 过去式: interpreted 过去分词: interpreted 现在分词: interpreting 第三人称单数: interprets');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ancient', '[\'eɪnʃənt]', 'adj.远古的,旧的', '1. This is an ancient parable. 这是一个古老的寓言。 2. It\'s an ancient tale which appears in various guises in several languages. 那是一个以几种语言叙述的古老的故事。 3. Soldiers in ancient time used escutcheon to fight. 古代的士兵用饰有花纹的盾作战。 4. This stone axe is a relic of ancient times. 这把石斧是古代的遗物。 5. The ancients believed that the sun and moon were planets. 古人相信太阳和月亮都是星球。', '副词: anciently 名词: ancientness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('skeptical', '[\'skeptɪkəl]', 'adj.怀疑性的,好怀疑的,<口>无神论的', '1. He is skeptical about everything. 他对于一切事都持怀疑的态度。 2. Her tone is skeptical and detached. 她的声音是怀疑的，冷漠的。 3. The leader had the gift of being able to infuse enthusiasm into the most skeptical member of the group. 那位领导人很有天赋，能使团体中最持怀疑态度的人都充满热情。', '副词: skeptically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('obtain', '[əb\'teɪn]', 'vt.获得,得到', '1. He failed to obtain a scholarship. 他没有获得奖学金。 2. At last, their company obtained the mining concession. 他们的公司最终获得了采矿权。 3. Those who were penitent obtained absolution. 悔过者获得了赦免。 4. They obtained a loan from the government. 他们从政府那里得到一笔贷款。 5. Your dress still obtains now. 你的这款套裙现在还很流行。', '形容词: obtainable 名词: obtainer 过去式: obtained 过去分词: obtained 现在分词: obtaining 第三人称单数: obtains');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('longevity', '[lɔːn\'dʒevəti]', 'n.长命,寿命，供职期限，资历', '1. His longevity vexed his heirs. 他的长寿令他的继承人们不快 2. Proper rest and enough sleep contribute to longevity. 适当的休息和足够的睡眠有益于长寿。 3. The worms have a longevity of about two years. 蠕虫的寿命大概是两年。', '形容词: longevous 名词复数: longevities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('burial', '[\'beriəl]', 'n.埋葬', '1. His body was brought back to England for burial. 他的遗体已运回英国埋葬。 2. The burial will be on Wednesday. 遗体将在周三被埋葬。 3. He was given an honorable burial. 他的葬礼很体面。 4. The body was placed in bier before burial. 在举行葬礼以前尸体被放在棺材里。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('heir', '[er]', 'n.继承人,后嗣', '1. Tilda seems to be his only heir. 迪儿特似乎是他唯一的继承人。 2. The young heir played away the whole of the estate. 那个年轻的继承人把全部遗产都赌输了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('susceptible', '[sə\'septəbl]', 'adj.易受影响的,易感动的,容许...的;n.(因缺乏免疫力而)易得病的人', '1. Children are more susceptible than adults. 孩子比成人易受外界的影响。 2. Some people are susceptible to advertising. 一些人易受广告的影响。 3. The plant is not susceptible to disease. 这种植物不容易受病害侵袭。 4. Children are susceptible to various illnesses. 孩子易患各种疾病。', '副词: susceptibly 名词: susceptibleness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cognitive', '[\'kɑːɡnətɪv]', 'adj.认知的,认识的,有感知的', '1. Thinking in terms of dualisms is common in our cognitive culture. 我们的认识文化通常具有两重性思考。 2. The second cognitive revolution is a post-modern one and it results in the establishment of social constructionism. 第二次认知革命是后现代主义的革命,它导致了社会建构论的产生。 3. Linguistics is an important branch in cognitive science. 语言学是认知科学的一个重要分支。', '副词: cognitively');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('combine', '[kəm\'baɪn]', 'v.(使)联合,(使)结合;n.联合企业,联合收割机;n.联合收割机', '1. Two parties will combine to defeat the third. 两党派将联合以击败第三党。 2. We can\'t always combine work with pleasure. 我们并不总是能在工作中享受到乐趣。 3. He combines creative imagination and true scholarship. 他同时具有创造性想象力和真正的治学谨严学风。 4. We should combine work with rest. 我们应劳逸结合。 5. The newspaper combine threatened all the smaller papers. 这家报刊集团威胁者小报社的生存。', '名词: combiner 过去式: combined 过去分词: combined 现在分词: combining 第三人称单数: combines');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tuition', '[tu\'ɪʃn]', 'n.学费', '1. The money is sufficient to cover the tuition. 这笔钱够付学费。 2. She relies on her parents for tuition. 她的学费依赖于父母。 3. Thank you for your tuition. 谢谢您的教诲。 4. Mary has derived a lot of benefit from her tuition. 玛丽从她的教学中得到很大收益。', '形容词: tuitional');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('characterize', '[\'kærəktəraɪz]', 'vt.表现...的特色,刻画的...性格', '1. The novelist characterizes his heroine as capricious and passionate. 这位小说家把女主人公刻画成变化无常而又多情的人。 2. He may be characterized as a man of hobbies. 他可以被称作是一个有癖好的人。 3. Your work is characterized by lack of attention to details. 你的工作特点是缺乏对细节的注意。 4. Bold outlines and warm colors characterize his dominate style in painting. 他大胆的绘画和所有的暖色调表现了他独有的绘画特色。', '名词: characterizer 过去式: characterized 过去分词: characterized 现在分词: characterizing 第三人称单数: characterizes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('imaginary', '[ɪ\'mædʒɪneri]', 'adj.假想的,想象的,虚构的', '1. We play out an imaginary confrontation in our mind. 我们的脑海中浮现出一种想象的冲突。 2. The boy\'s fears were only imaginary. 这小孩的恐惧只是一种想象。 3. People still have a general fear for the imaginary infernal powers. 人们对于虚构的地狱中的鬼神仍具有一种普遍的恐惧。 4. All the characters in this book are imaginary. 这本书中的人物都是虚构的。', '副词: imaginarily 名词: imaginariness 名词复数: imaginaries');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cancel', '[\'kænsl]', 'vt.取消,删去', '1. The match had to be cancelled due to the bad weather. 比赛因天气不好只得取消。 2. If the worst comes to the worst, we\'ll have to cancel our holiday plans. 要是情况不妙，我们就只好取消度假计划了。 3. I\'ve lost my crdit card, so I have to go to the bank to cancel it. 我的信用卡弄丢了,我得去银行申请作废。 4. The ticket shall be cancelled once you enter the cinema. 你一进入电影院后,这张票就得注销了。', '形容词: cancelable 名词: canceler 过去式: canceled/cancelled 过去分词: canceled/cancelled 现在分词: canceling/cancelling 第三人称单数: cancels');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('linear', '[\'lɪniər]', 'adj.线的,直线的,线性的', '1. Students do not always progress in a linear fashion. 学生不会总是顺着一条直线进步。 2. The flow is linear, with some iterations in the planning phase. 过程流程是直线的，在计划阶段会有一些迭代。 3. He\'s making linear measurements. 他正在进行长度测量。 4. Not all types of motions are linear in character. 并非所有类型的运动在性质上都是线性的。', '副词: linearly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('radioactive', '[\'reɪdioʊ\'æktɪv]', 'adj.放射性的,有辐射能的', '1. Radioactive ray is material thing. 放射线是实际的物质。 2. Radium and uranium are radioactive elements. 镭和铀是放射性元素。 3. Radioactive waste must be stored on land. 有放射性的废物都必须存放在陆地上。', '副词: radioactively');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('previous', '[\'priːviəs]', 'n.事先查看,[计]预览;vt.事先查看,预展,预演', '1. His previous attempts had been unsuccessful. 他以前的尝试没有成功。 2. It happened previous to his arrival there. 事件发生于他到那儿以前。 3. You must collect enough materials previous to your writing. 你在写作之前必须收集好足够的材料。', '副词: previously 名词: previousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('latitude', '[\'lætɪtuːd]', 'n.纬度,范围,(用复数)地区,行动或言论的自由(范围)', '1. The latitude of the island is 30 degrees north. 这个岛的纬度是北纬三十度。 2. Latitude reaches a maximum of 90°at the poles. 两极纬度的最大值为90°。 3. You have a wide latitude to act as you think best. 你拥有自己认为最好的、广泛的行动上的自由。 4. We allow considerable latitude at these hearings. 我们在这种听证会上允许相当大的自由。', '形容词: latitudinal 副词: latitudinally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('junction', '[\'dʒʌŋkʃn]', 'n.连接,接合,交叉点,汇合处', '1. The junction was not connected properly. 接口没有正确连接。 2. They decided to effect a junction of two armies. 他们决定两军会师。 3. The map is in error regarding the junction. 这张地图在这个交点上是绘制错了。 4. The gas station is at the junction of two highways 这个加油站位于两条公路的会合处。', '形容词: junctional');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('scheme', '[skiːm]', 'n.安排,配置,计划,阴谋,方案,图解,摘要;v.计划,设计,图谋,策划', '1. Their scheme was exposed. 他们的阴谋被暴露了。 2. The police have uncovered a scheme of robbery. 警察当局破获了一起阴谋抢劫案。 3. They were bitterly opposed to the scheme. 他们强烈反对这个计划。 4. I rather doubt if such an ambitious scheme could be made a success of. 我真怀疑这样一个雄心勃勃的计划是否会成功。 5. He is scheming for power. 他在图谋争权。', '名词: schemer 过去式: schemed 过去分词: schemed 现在分词: scheming 第三人称单数: schemes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('overlap', '[ˌoʊvər\'læp]', 'v重叠', '1. A fish\'s scales overlap each other. 鱼鳞是一片片上下交叠起来的。 2. You need to overlap the pieces of wood slightly. 你需要把这些木片搭叠起来。 3. These two papers overlap in content. 这两篇论文有交叉的内容。 4. The programme has been so organized that none of the talks overlap. 日程做了精心安排，以使每一讲都没有重复内容。 5. Channel ranges must not overlap. 频道范围不能重叠。 6. There is a small overlap between the two circles. 在这两个圆周有一小部分重叠。', '过去式: overlapped 过去分词: overlapped 现在分词: overlapping 第三人称单数: overlaps');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reliance', '[rɪ\'laɪəns]', 'n.信任,信心,依靠,依靠的人或物', '1. I place complete reliance on his judgment. 我完全信赖他的判断。 2. I have no reliance about his assurance. 我不信赖他的保证。 3. Don\'t place too much reliance on what he said. 对他所说的话不要过于信赖。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('soluble', '[\'sɑːljəbl]', 'adj.可溶的,可溶解的', '1. Soluble metallic hydroxides are bases that are alkalies. 可溶解的金属氢氧化合物都是碱。 2. A subsequent wet depithing serves to remove soluble and strongly adhering pith. 后续的除髓工序可以继续除去可溶解的和粘附牢固的蔗髓。', '副词: solubly 名词: solubleness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mistress', '[\'mɪstrəs]', 'n.主妇,女主人,女能人,情妇', '1. Wealth is a good servant, a very bad mistress. 财富是个好仆人，也是一个坏主妇。 2. Experience is the mistress of fools. 经验是蠢货的主妇。 3. The dog ran alongside his mistress. 狗在女主人的身边奔跑。 4. Rogue and mistress of Patterne do not go together. 罗格与帕忒恩的女主人不能并列。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('presume', '[prɪ\'zuːm]', 'vt.假定,假设,认为', '1. The law presumes innocence until guilt is proved. 在罪状未证实前，法律假定被告无罪。 2. We presume that the factory has been fully engaged. 我们推测工厂的生产已经满负荷了。 3. That\'s the new assistant, I presume. 我想那就是新来的助理 4. I presume that this is your final answer. 我认为这就是你最后的答复。 5. May I presume to advise you? 我可以冒昧向你进一言吗？', '副词: presumedly 名词: presumer 过去式: presumed 过去分词: presumed 现在分词: presuming 第三人称单数: presumes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pudding', '[\'pʊdɪŋ]', 'n.布丁(一种以面粉,牛奶,鸡蛋等为基料的糊壮甜食)', '1. The pudding was made with evaporated milk. 这布丁是用淡炼乳做的。 2. Let the pudding chill for an hour. 把布丁冰镇一小时。 3. This pudding has two pounds of fresh fruit in it. 这个布丁里有两磅鲜果。 4. All I know is that the traditional breakfast in rural Ireland began with black pudding. 我所知道的真正的爱尔兰早餐是以黑香肠开始的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('devote', '[dɪ\'voʊt]', 'vt.投入于,献身', '1. You must devote your attention to your work. 你必须专心于工作。 2. After he graduated, he continued to devote himself to the research. 毕业以后,他继续潜心于这项研究。 3. He devoted himself entirely to music. 他将一生奉献给了音乐。 4. He started to study ecology and decided to devote his whole life to the science. 他开始研究生态学,并决心将他的一生献身于这门学科。', '名词: devotement 过去式: devoted 过去分词: devoted 现在分词: devoting 第三人称单数: devotes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('conceive', '[kən\'siːv]', 'vt.构思,以为,持有;vi.怀孕,考虑,设想', '1. I cannot conceive of him as a genius. 我不能设想他会是一个天才。 2. I cannot conceive that he would wish to harm us. 我不能想像他会伤害我们。 3. I can not conceive of anything funnier than that . 我想不出有比那更有趣的东西。 4. She was told she couldn\'t conceive. 她得知自己不能怀孕。', '形容词: conceivable 副词: conceivably 名词: conceivability 过去式: conceived 过去分词: conceived 现在分词: conceiving 第三人称单数: conceives');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('strive', '[straɪv]', 'v.努力,奋斗,力争,斗争', '1. He strove for recognition as an artist. 他为获得艺术家的声誉而奋斗。 2. We should all strive to reunify the motherland. 我们共同努力,实现祖国统一。 3. I strive automatically to bring the world into harmony with my own nature. 我机械地努力以使这世界跟自己的性情协调一致。 4. The scientists strive for a breakthrough in cancer research. 科学家们力争在癌症研究方面有个突破。', '副词: strivingly 名词: striver 过去式: strove 过去分词: striven/strived 现在分词: striving 第三人称单数: strives');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('heighten', '[\'haɪtn]', 'v.提高,升高', '1. A weakened immune system does not heighten the risks of catching a cold. 一个弱免疫系统是不会增加感冒的感染可能性的。 2. An older more experienced swimmer will shave his entire body to reduce resistance and heighten sensation in the water. 年龄较大更有经验的游泳运动员将会把他的全身收紧以减少阻力并增加水感。 3. The financial management must be strengthened so as to heighten economic profits. 要提高经济效益，必须加强财务管理。 4. So it is urgent for curriculum reform to reinforce teachers\' team building and heighten the integrated quality of teachers. 加强教师队伍建设，提高教师的整体素质，是新课程改革的迫切要求。', '名词: heightener 过去式: heightened 过去分词: heightened 现在分词: heightening 第三人称单数: heightens');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('inertia', '[ɪ\'nɜːrʃə]', 'n.惯性,惯量', '1. Inertia carried the car to the pavement. 惯性使汽车驶到了人行道上。 2. Inertia is evident in our every day experiences. 惯性在我们日常生活中是很常见的。 3. Everyone has his psychological inertia, or in some way, indolence. 每个人都有一种思维惯性或者说惰性。 4. Because of the sheer inertia of the system many badly needed reform is never introduced. 纯粹是由於制度本身有惰性，很多事急需改革却从未实行。', '形容词: inertial 副词: inertially');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dispatch', '[dɪ\'spætʃ]', 'vt.分派,派遣;n.派遣,急件', '1. A messenger was dispatched to take the news to the soldiers at the front. 一名通讯员被派去给前线士兵送消息。 2. We have to ask you to dispatch the consignment immediately. 我们得要求你立即发送该批货物。 3. We soon dispatched the chocolate cake. 我们很快就吃完了那个巧克力蛋糕。 4. The criminal will be dispatched today. 那名罪犯将于今日被处决。 5. I threw the dispatch to him and asked him to take prompt actions. 我把那份急件扔给他,让他立刻采取措施。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pose', '[poʊz]', 'n.姿势,姿态;v.(使...)摆好姿势,形成,引起,造成;vi.摆姿势,佯装,矫揉造作', '1. Please sit still while you pose for your photo. 你摆好姿势拍照时请坐着别动。 2. The artist posed his model carefully. 这个艺术家仔细地把他的模型放好。 3. All the subjects are well posed. 所有的东西都摆好了位置。 4. Pollution poses a threat to the continued existence of this species. 污染对这一物种的继续生存造成了威胁。 5. She always liked to strike a noble pose. 她总是喜欢摆出一副高贵的样子。', '形容词: posable 过去式: posed 过去分词: posed 现在分词: posing 第三人称单数: poses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rectify', '[\'rektɪfaɪ]', 'vt.矫正,调整,[化]精馏', '1. Please rectify the mistake in my bill. 请改正我帐单上的错误。 2. The captain had to rectify the compass reading. 船长不得不校正罗盘读数。 3. He cleaned the bottle with rectified spirit. 他用精馏酒精清洗瓶子。 4. Diodes are electronic devices which rectify alternating current to direct current. 二极管是将交流电整流成直流电的电子装置。', '形容词: rectifiable 名词: rectification 过去式: rectified 过去分词: rectified 现在分词: rectifying 第三人称单数: rectifies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dubious', '[\'duːbiəs]', 'adj.可疑的,不确定的', '1. I feel dubious about his honesty. 我对他的诚实表示怀疑。 2. I am dubious about accepting the offer of the job. 我犹豫不定是否接受提供给我的那份工作。 3. I remain dubious about her motives. 我对她的动机仍存疑念。 4. The testimony given by him is dubious. 他所作的证据是可疑的。', '副词: dubiously 名词: dubiousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('apply', '[ə\'plaɪ]', 'vt.申请,应用;vi.申请,适用', '1. We should not only know the theory but also how to apply it to practice. 我们不仅要知道理论，还要知道怎样把理论应用于实践。 2. The plastic coating is easy to be applied on any surface. 塑性涂料容易涂在任何表面上。 3. I am applying for a fellowship. 我在申请研究生奖学金。 4. Above terms shall apply unless otherwise mention. 除非另有说明书,上述条件一概适用。', '过去式: applied 过去分词: applied 现在分词: applying 第三人称单数: applies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('famine', '[\'fæmɪn]', 'n.饥荒,<古>饥饿,严重的缺乏', '1. War, famine and flood are terrible evils. 战争、饥荒和洪水都是可怕的灾祸。 2. Famine is often the sequel to war or drought. 饥荒往往是战争或干旱造成的。 3. It\'s impossible to remain unmoved by her reports of the famine. 任何人对她报道的饥荒情况都不可能无动于衷。 4. We are collecting money for the famine victim. 我们在为遭受饥荒的灾民募捐。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sensitive', '[\'sensətɪv]', 'adj.敏感的,灵敏的,感光的', '1. She\'s got very sensitive hearing, skin, etc. 她的听觉、 触觉等很灵敏。 2. Don\'t be so sensitive and I was not criticizing you. 别那么敏感,我不是在批评你。 3. What food and fruit are sensitive? 哪些食物和水果是感光的？ 4. The film is coated with light sensitive chemicals, which are change by the different shades and colors of light. 胶卷上涂了一层感光的化学物质，这些物质因光的不同色度与颜色而改变。', '副词: sensitively 名词: sensitiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('contrast', '[\'kɑːntræst]', 'vt.使与...对比,使与...对照;vi.和...形成对照;n.对比,对照,(对照中的)差异', '1. Black and white shows a striking contrast. 黑和白形成明显的对比。 2. There is a great contrast between good and evil. 善与恶有明显的差别。 3. The little village was a total contrast to San Francisco. 这个小村庄与圣弗朗西斯科形成强烈对照。 4. When you contrast their work records, Julie is clearly more qualified. 对比他们的工作记录,你会发现茱莉更有能力。 5. The microscope image contains contrast effects. 显微镜所成的图像具有反差效应。', '形容词: contrastable 副词: contrastingly 过去式: contrasted 过去分词: contrasted 现在分词: contrasting 第三人称单数: contrasts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('stream', '[striːm]', 'n.溪,川,流,一股,一串,河流;v.流,涌,流注', '1. On either bank of the stream stand rows of willow trees. 小河两岸柳树成行。 2. Sand and leaves trapped the water in the stream. 沙子和树叶堵住了小河的水流。 3. Visitors to the exhibition came in an endless stream. 参观展览会的人络绎不绝。 4. Cars stream along the highway. 汽车在公路上流水般地行驶。', '形容词: streamy 过去式: streamed 过去分词: streamed 现在分词: streaming 第三人称单数: streams');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('tanker', '[\'tæŋkər]', 'n.油轮', '1. The tanker sank and pollute the sea. 油轮沉没了，污染了海水。 2. The ship sank through a collision with an oil tanker. 这条船因与油轮相撞而沉没。 3. These planes can be refueled in the air by tanker. 这些飞机可在空中接受加油。 4. The driver of the fuel tanker crashed to avoid a car. 该燃油罐车的司机为躲避一辆汽车翻车了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('refusal', '[rɪ\'fjuːzl]', 'n.拒绝,推却,优先取舍权,优先取舍的机会', '1. I translate his silence as a refusal. 我把他的沉默解释为拒绝。 2. She couched her refusal in very polite terms. 她用十分委婉的措辞表示拒绝。 3. Your words amount to a refusal. 你的话等于回绝了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('retain', '[rɪ\'teɪn]', 'vt.保持,保留', '1. His speech could not retain the interest of his audience. 他的讲话不能保持住听众的兴趣。 2. I will retain my right. 我将保留我的权力。 3. Does it retain the key elements of the original story? 它是否保留了原作的关键要素? 4. She has a good memory and finds it easy to retain matters. 她记忆力好,很容易记住事情。', '形容词: retainable 名词: retainability 过去式: retained 过去分词: retained 现在分词: retaining 第三人称单数: retains');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('booklet', '[\'bʊklət]', 'n.小册子', '1. This booklet defines the committee\'s functions. 这本小册子说明该委员会的职能。 2. It is all right to write the essay in your booklet. 把文章写在小册子里就可以。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bang', '[bæŋ]', 'n.重击,突然巨响;v.发巨响,重击', '1. The door shut with a bang. 门砰的一声关上了。 2. He was awakened by a terrific bang. 一声巨响把他从睡梦中惊醒。 3. He fell and got a nasty bang on the head. 他跌了一跤，头部磕得很重。 4. She is keeping a long bang. 她现在是留着长刘海。 5. He fell and banged his knee. 他跌倒了，膝盖重重撞了一下。 6. The light went out bang in the middle of the performance. 表演正好进行到一半时停电了。', '过去式: banged 过去分词: banged 现在分词: banging 第三人称单数: bangs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('equivalent', '[ɪ\'kwɪvələnt]', 'adj.相等的,相当的,同意义的;n.等价物,相等物', '1. Is there a French word that is the exact equivalent of the English word `home\'? 法语中有没有和英语home完全一样的对应词?', '副词: equivalently');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('incur', '[ɪn\'kɜːr]', 'v.招致', '1. Your despite at him will incur his revenge. 他会因你的藐视态度而报复你的。 2. If you don\'t do the job properly, you will incur blame. 如果你不把工作做好,你将会招人责难。 3. A slowdown in the economy caused us to incur great losses. 经济的减缓使我们遭受了很大的损失。 4. He incurred substantial losses during the stock market crash. 他在股市猛跌时蒙受了巨大的损失。', '过去式: incurred 过去分词: incurred 现在分词: incurring 第三人称单数: incurs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('provocative', '[prə\'vɑːkətɪv]', 'adj.煽动的;n.刺激物', '1. She said nothing particularly provocative. 她没有说过特别够刺激性的活。 2. Your question was not merely provocative . 你的问题不仅仅是挑衅性的。 3. She looked very provocative in her bikini. 穿着比基尼泳装的她看来十分具挑逗性。', '副词: provocatively 名词: provocativeness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('prose', '[proʊz]', 'n.散文', '1. This is a verbal translation of the prose. 这是那篇散文的逐字直译。 2. He has lately set forth a book on prose. 他最近出版一本论散文的著作。 3. His prose is written in elegant language. 他的散文写得十分优雅。 4. I want to glance over one time this piece of prose. 我想浏览一下这篇散文。', '过去式: prosed 过去分词: prosed 现在分词: prosing 第三人称单数: proses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pedal', '[\'pedl]', 'n.踏板;v.踩...的踏板', '1. The pedal of a cycle is attached to a crank. 自行车的踏板与曲柄相连。 2. He pushed hard on the brake pedal to avoid a collision. 他使劲踩下煞车踏板以避免撞车。 3. He had to pedal hard to get up the hill. 他得用力踩动，以便上山。 4. I saw him pedal to school every morning. 我看到他每天早晨骑自行车上学。', '过去式: pedaled/pedalled 过去分词: pedaled/pedalled 现在分词: pedaling/pedalling 第三人称单数: pedals/pedals');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('imitation', '[ˌɪmɪ\'teɪʃn]', 'n.模仿,效法,冒充,赝品,仿造物', '1. Young children learn how to speak by imitation. 儿童通过模仿学说话。 2. He grew beards in imitation of the actor. 他为了模仿那个演员,蓄起了胡子。 3. His style is a slavish imitation of his teacher\'s. 他一味模仿教师的风格，毫无创意。 4. Her innocence is only an imitation. 她的天真只是一种伪装。', '形容词: imitational');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('impose', '[ɪm\'poʊz]', 'vt.征税,强加,以...欺骗;vi.利用,欺骗,施影响', '1. I don\'t want to impose on you by staying too long. 我不想打扰你,不多耽搁了。 2. Do not try to impose your belief upon others. 别试图把你的信仰强加在别人头上。 3. We could not impose our own standards on others. 我们不能把我们的标准强加于他人。 4. He helped the Mongols impose taxes, interceding with the Khan to prevent reprisals when rebellions broke out. 因害怕在诺夫哥罗德人造反时遭到报复，他协助蒙古人征敛赋税。', '名词: imposer 过去式: imposed 过去分词: imposed 现在分词: imposing 第三人称单数: imposes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('traverse', '[trə\'vɜːrs]', 'n.横贯,横断,障碍,否认,反驳,通廊;vt.横过,穿过,经过,在...来回移动,反对,详细研究;vi.横越,旋转,来回移动;adj.横断的,横的', '1. The railway traverses hundreds of miles of desert. 这条铁路贯穿数百英里的沙漠。 2. The traverse across the country will be long and arduous. 穿越这个国家将是漫长而又艰苦的旅程。 3. The traverse in the room was easily seen from the doorway. 从门口看过去，很容易看见房间门窗的横档。 4. The railway traverses hundreds of miles of desert. 这条铁路贯穿数百英里的沙漠。', '形容词: traversable 名词: traversal 过去式: traversed 过去分词: traversed 现在分词: traversing 第三人称单数: traverses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('transistor', '[træn\'zɪstər]', 'n.[电子]晶体管', '1. He devises a new type of transistor. 他发明了一种新的晶体管。 2. We must give great care upon transistor biasing. 我们必须十分重视晶体管的偏置。 3. The old man always carries about a transistor. 这位老人总是随身携带一台晶体管收音机。 4. This transistor has two batteries. 这个晶体管收音机有两块电池。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('descend', '[dɪ\'send]', 'vi.下来,下降,遗传(指财产,气质,权利),突击,出其不意的拜访;v.下去', '1. The sun descended behind the hills. 太阳下山了。 2. I wish that the prices can descend. 但愿物价会下降。 3. I didn\'t expect him to descend to personal abuse. 我没料到他会堕落到对我进行人身攻击的地步。 4. At 6:30 p.m. the tropical darkness descends. 在傍晚六点半的时候,热带地区的黑夜降临。 5. The custom has descended to our day. 这一习俗一直传到今天。 6. Armed thieves descended on the helpless travelers. 一群武装盗贼袭击了无依无靠的旅客。', '形容词: descendible 过去式: descended 过去分词: descended 现在分词: descending 第三人称单数: descends');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('terrain', '[tə\'reɪn]', 'n.地形', '1. The car blitzed through rough terrain. 这辆汽车长驱穿越了崎岖地带。 2. Valley glaciers are confined to valleys in mountainous terrain. 山谷冰川只限于多山地带的山谷。 3. It\'s a difficult terrain for tanks. 这是坦克作战的困难地形。 4. They stopped and began to reconnoitre the terrain. 他们停下来，开始勘测地形。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('parameter', '[pə\'ræmɪtər]', 'n.参数,参量,<口>起限定作用的因素', '1. One parameter which always comes into play is the national economy. 国民经济是一个经常起作用的参量。 2. Spend by each department have to fall within certain parameter. 每个部门的开支必须属于确定的系数之内。 3. You can pass report parameters to a DMX query parameter. 您可以将报表参数传递到DMX查询参数。 4. A notable question is whether there is parameter in it. 一个值得注意的问题是是否有限定因素.', '形容词: parametric 副词: parametrically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('perfection', '[pər\'fekʃn]', 'n.尽善尽美,完美,完成', '1. The design approximates perfection. 这个设计几乎是完美的。 2. As an actress, she is perfection itself. 作为一名女演员，她是完美的典型。 3. Incomplete beauty is the perfection. 不完善的美，就是完美。 4. Our style is distinctive and our goal is perfection! 与众不同是我们的风格，追求完善是我们的宗旨！', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hatred', '[\'heɪtrɪd]', 'n.憎恨,乱意,仇恨', '1. His words stirred up my hatred. 他的话激起了我的仇恨。 2. There is implacable hatred between the two nations. 两国之间有无法消除的仇恨。 3. This hatred was generated by racial prejudice. 这种仇恨是由种族偏见引起的。 4. I have a vehement hatred of people who is cruel to animal. 我对残害动物的人怀有强烈的憎恨。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('disorder', '[dɪs\'ɔːrdər]', 'n.杂乱,混乱,无秩序状态;vt.扰乱,使失调,使紊乱', '1. The meeting terminated in disorder. 会议在混乱中结束。 2. This school is completely in disorder. 这所学校完全在混乱状态当中。 3. The whole country of Hungary is in disorder right now. 整个匈牙利现在陷入了一片混乱。 4. The room is in dreadful disorder. 房间里乱七八糟。 5. A series of accidents disordered the shop. 一连串的意外事件把店里弄得乱七八糟。', '过去式: disordered 过去分词: disordered 现在分词: disordering 第三人称单数: disorders');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('shaft', '[ʃæft]', 'n.轴,杆状物', '1. In rotating, the shaft splashes oil up into the bearings. 当轴旋转的时候就把油溅入轴承。 2. The air flows down to a shaft and thus loses potential energy. 空气向下进入竖井，因而失去势能。 3. The horse stood between the shafts of the carriage. 马站在大车车辕中间。 4. If you bring them back to the lonely moor, you have to hit the shield three times with the shaft of the spear and then the silence of the moor will be broken forever. 如果你把这矛和盾带回到偏僻的荒野来，你必须要用矛的柄击银盾三下，这样荒野的寂静就能永远被打破。', '过去式: shafted 过去分词: shafted 现在分词: shafting 第三人称单数: shafts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cereal', '[\'sɪriəl]', 'n.谷类食品,谷类', '1. He sprinkled sugar over his cereal. 他在麦片粥里撒上了糖。 2. I have a bowl of cereal every morning. 我每天早晨吃一碗麦片粥。 3. The breakfast cereal is enriched with vitamins. 维生素增加了早餐谷类食物的营养价值。 4. The disease attacks cereal crop. 这种疾病侵害了谷类作物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fusion', '[\'fjuːʒn]', 'n.熔化,熔解,熔合,熔接', '1. There is now a worrying fusion of information and entertainment. 现在信息和娱乐已经出现令人忧虑的相互融合。 2. She was a fusion of the dreamer and doer. 她是空想者和实干者的结合。 3. The movie displayed a perfect fusion of image and sound. 这部电影展示了音响与影像的完美结合。 4. Brass is formed by the fusion of copper and zinc. 黄铜是由铜和锌熔合制成的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('accommodation', '[əˌkɑːmə\'deɪʃn]', 'n.住处,膳宿,(车,船,飞机等的)预定铺位,(眼睛等的)适应性调节,(社会集团间的)迁就融合', '1. There travelling students found accommodation at moderate terms. 旅游的学生们感到那儿的膳宿费是公道的。 2. If labour and management don\'t reach an accommodation there will be a strike. 如果劳资双方达不成妥协，就会发生罢工。 3. We can provide accommodation for six people at a push. 如情况需要，我们可以安排六个人的住处。 4. Hotel accommodation was scarce during the Olympic Games. 奥运会期间，旅馆房间很难找。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('inventory', '[\'ɪnvəntɔːri]', 'n.详细目录,存货,财产清册,总量', '1. The job of compiling the inventory took several hours. 编辑详细目录的工作花了好几个小时。 2. The inventory showed that the store was overstocked. 清单显示商店存货过多。 3. All of the inventory has been tagged and referenced. 所有存货清单都被贴上了标签，以备参考。 4. Is the shop inventory verified before the commencement of a sales promotion? 有否在减价开始前按公司清单核实存货? 5. He inventories the minor losses and submitted it to the management. 他将那些较小的损失编进目录，上交给管理层。', '形容词: inventorial 副词: inventorially 名词复数: inventories 过去式: inventoried 过去分词: inventoried 现在分词: inventorying 第三人称单数: inventories');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('audience', '[\'ɔːdiəns]', 'n.听众,观众,接见,拜见', '1. The audience was no less than five thousand. 听众有五千人之多。 2. Someone in the audience began to laugh. 观众中有人开始笑起来。 3. The concert drew a large audience. 音乐会吸引了大量的观众。 4. The article was put out in a national magazine to reach a larger audience. 为了能影响更多的读者,文章被登发在一份国家级杂志上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('diligent', '[\'dɪlɪdʒənt]', 'adj.勤勉的,用功的,细心而继续不断的', '1. The diligent student gets up before dawn every day. 这个勤奋的学生每天天亮以前就起床了。 2. Their students are diligent about their studies. 他们的学生勤奋学习。 3. She is more diligent than any other students in her class. 她是班上最用功的学生。', '副词: diligently');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('spectator', '[\'spekteɪtər]', 'n.观众(指比赛或表演)', '1. Baseball is largely a spectator sport. 棒球在很大程度上是一种观众型运动。 2. Many a spectator poured down the street to the football ground. 许多观众沿街向足球场走去。 3. Hanlei looks at the world as a spectator, waiting. 韩磊以一个旁观者的身份观察世界,他善于等待。 4. It is the spectator, and not life, that art really mirrors. 艺术所真正要反映的是旁观者，而不是生活。', '形容词: spectatorial 名词: spectatorship');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('lace', '[leɪs]', 'n.饰带,花边,缎带,鞋带;vt.扎带子,扎,饰以花边;vi.缚带子', '1. He stopped to do up his shoe lace. 他停下来把鞋带系上。 2. My shoe lace keeps coming undone. 我的鞋带老是松开。 3. My daughter wears a dress embellished with lace and ribbons today. 今天我女儿穿了一件有花边和饰带的连衣裙。 4. She wears a dress with delicate lace. 她穿了一件带有精致花边的裙子。 5. If you don\'t lace up your shoes, you\'ll trip over. 如果你不系好鞋带，你会被绊倒的。', '形容词: laceless 名词: lacer 过去式: laced 过去分词: laced 现在分词: lacing 第三人称单数: laces');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('slaughter', '[\'slɔːtər]', 'n.屠宰,残杀,屠杀;v.屠宰,残杀,屠杀', '1. He had no strong feelings about human slaughter. 他对人类残杀没有强烈的感情。 2. I am really terrified to witness the slaughter. 我亲眼目睹这场屠杀，真是吓坏了。 3. Wholesale slaughter was carried out in the name of progress. 大规模的屠杀在维护进步的名义下进行。 4. He waded through slaughter to the throne. 他行杀戮而得王位。 5. Hundreds of innocent civilians were cruelly slaughtered. 数百名无辜平民遭残杀。', '形容词: slaughterous 名词: slaughterer 过去式: slaughtered 过去分词: slaughtered 现在分词: slaughtering 第三人称单数: slaughters');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('erosion', '[ɪ\'rəʊʒn]', 'n.腐蚀,侵蚀', '1. Therefore, the corrosion was caused by erosion of rainwater during ocean shipping. 因此，这些腐蚀是海运途中雨水的浸蚀造成的。 2. The erosion of beach here is serious. 这里海岸的腐蚀很严重。 3. The cement petrified after many years\' erosion. 经过多年的侵蚀，水泥石化了。 4. The erosion of the soil is damaging the forest. 土壤侵蚀使得森林遭到了破坏。', '形容词: erosional 副词: erosionally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('instantaneous', '[ˌɪnstən\'teɪniəs]', 'adj.瞬间的,即刻的,即时的', '1. Relief was instantaneous. 痛苦的消除是瞬间的事 2. Death is instantaneous in a fatal accident. 在致命的事故中，死亡是即刻发生的。 3. The reaction of the audience was instantaneous. 观众即刻有了反应。 4. He had an instantaneous response. 他立刻作了反应。', '副词: instantaneously 名词: instantaneity');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('clone', '[kloʊn]', 'n.无性系,无性繁殖,克隆;v.无性繁殖,复制', '1. Above all, we must first clone a panda. 最重要的是我们必须首先克隆一只熊猫。 2. The first clone farm has appeared in New Zealand. 第一家克隆农场在新西兰出现。 3. At the outset they must contain several ramets of every selected clone. 在开始时每个入选无性系必须包括几个无性繁殖后代。 4. Clone is the nonsexually-produced descendants of a single plant or animals. 克隆就是无性繁殖单个的植物或动物后代。 5. The first clone farm has appeared in New Zealand. 第一家克隆农场在新西兰出现。', '形容词: clonal 副词: clonally 名词: cloner 过去式: cloned 过去分词: cloned 现在分词: cloning 第三人称单数: clones');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('polar', '[\'poʊlər]', 'adj.[天]两极的,极地的,南辕北辙的,南极的,(北极星似的)指引的,极性的,北极的;n.极线,极面', '1. Are there any animals in the polar circles? 南极圈和北极圈内有动物存在吗？ 2. The two systems of government are polar opposites. 这两种政体正好相反。 3. The two systems of government are polar opposites. 这两种政体正好相反。 4. Love and hatred are polar feelings. 爱与恨是完全相反的感情。 5. A molecule where the centers do not coincide is called a polar molecule. 正负电荷中心不重合的分子称为极性分子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('barren', '[\'bærən]', 'adj.不生育的,不孕的,贫瘠的,没有结果的,无益的,单调的,无聊的,空洞的;n.荒地', '1. No one could raise crops on this barren land. 没人能够在这么贫瘠的土地上种庄稼。 2. Life is a barren field frozen with snow. 生命就像是被雪覆盖的荒芜土地。 3. We shall turn this piece of barren land into wheat fields. 我们要把这块不毛之地变为麦田。 4. He was engaged in a barren argument with Paul. 他在同保罗作无用的争论。', '副词: barrenly 名词: barrenness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('paralyze', '[\'pærəˌlaɪz]', 'vt.使瘫痪,使麻痹', '1. Otherwise, my dread of criticism can paralyze me. 不然的话，我对批评的恐惧将让我行为瘫痪。 2. Even the smallest slip could permanently paralyze the patient. 即使最小的失误都会导致小朱利安终身瘫痪。', '副词: paralyzingly 名词: paralyzation 过去式: paralyzed 过去分词: paralyzed 现在分词: paralyzing 第三人称单数: paralyzes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('physiological', '[ˌfɪziə\'lɒdʒɪkl]', 'adj.生理学的,生理学上的', '1. The physiological needs are reasonably satisfied. 生理的需要得到合理的满足。 2. Objective To Study the effect of Haematococcus pluvialis powder on physiological metabolism of Wistar rats. 目的观察红球藻粉对大鼠生理的影响。 3. Certain species of aquatic animals are capable of producing physiological shocks. 某些种类的水生生物能够引起生理学的电击。 4. From a physiological standpoint \"health\"refers to a persons quality of health and their ability to adapt to the outer world. 从生理学的角度来看，体质是指人的健康水平和对外界的适应能力。', '副词: physiologically 异体字: physiologic');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('wreck', '[rek]', 'n.失事船(或飞机),残骸,(船,飞机的)失事;vt.破坏,拆毁', '1. The ship was wrecked on the rock. 船在岩石上撞毁了。 2. The train wrecked at midnight. 这列火车半夜出轨了。 3. His drinking wrecked their marriage. 他的酗酒毁坏了他们的婚姻。 4. Nobody can wreck the friendship between us. 没有人能破坏我们之间的友谊。 5. They save the cargo from the wreck. 他们从遇难船上抢救出货物。', '过去式: wrecked 过去分词: wrecked 现在分词: wrecking 第三人称单数: wrecks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('colonial', '[kə\'loʊniəl]', 'adj.殖民的,殖民地的n.殖民地居民', '1. France was once a colonial power. 法国一度是占有殖民地的强国。 2. American Independence War is really a colonial war. 美国的独立战争实际是一场关于殖民地的战争。 3. His forefathers were colonial in the control of England. 他祖先是英国殖民地居民。', '副词: colonially');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('substance', '[\'sʌbstəns]', 'n.物质,实质,主旨', '1. The Substance and Prospect of \"East China Sea\" Dispute between China and Japan 中日\"东海问题\"的实质及展望 2. The emery is a hard metallic substance. 金刚砂是非常坚硬的金属物质。 3. Beware of what you do with this dangerous substance. 你处理这些危险品时，可要当心。 4. Later he became a man of substance. 后来，他成为颇具资产的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('controversy', '[\'kɒntrəˌvɜːsɪ]', 'n.论争,辩论,论战', '1. The mayor will try to accord the controversy over the housing scheme. 市长试图调解住房规划方面的争议。 2. The remark touched off a heated controversy. 这句话引起了热烈的争论。 3. The new government appointments have caused much controversy. 政府在人事上作的新的委任，引起了许多争论。', '名词复数: controversies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('vicinity', '[və\'sɪnəti]', 'n.邻近,附近,接近', '1. There\'s a factory in the vicinity of the school. 学校邻近有个工厂。 2. No one was aware of his vicinity. 没有人发现他就在附近。 3. All the ships in the vicinity of the crash joined in the search for survivors. 撞船事故发生地区的所有船只都参加了搜寻幸存者的工作。 4. Pearl Harbor and vicinity had been turned into complete chaos. 珍珠港和附近地区一片混乱。', '名词复数: vicinities');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('illegal', '[ɪ\'liːɡl]', 'adj.违法的,不合规定的', '1. The jewellery firm is just a front for their illegal trade in diamonds. 该珠宝公司不过是进行非法的钻石交易的幌子。 2. All protests are brutally repressed by the government as illegal. 所有的抗议活动都遭到当局的野蛮镇压，并被宣布为非法。 3. Their speculative buying of grain is illegal. 他们投机购买谷物是不合法的。 4. Abortion is illegal in this country. 人工流产在这个国家是不合法的。 5. The illegals couldn\'t be admitted by the authority. 非法移民是不被政府认可的。', '副词: illegally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('opaque', '[oʊ\'peɪk]', 'n.不透明物;adj.不透明的,不传热的,迟钝的', '1. This is an opaque cup. 这是一个不透明的杯子。 2. The window is made of opaque glass. 这扇窗是用不透明的玻璃做的。 3. The report was written in long, opaque sentences. 报告中的句子又长又难懂。 4. Their intentions remained opaque. 他们的意图仍然令人费解。', '副词: opaquely 名词: opaqueness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('setback', '[\'setbæk]', 'n.顿挫,挫折,退步,逆流,(疾病的)复发', '1. He met with many a setback in his lifetime. 他一生中遭到过许多挫折。 2. This setback has drained away my keenness. 这次挫折削弱了我的热情。 3. Undaunted by his first setback, he decided to try once more. 不为最初的失败而动摇，他决定再试一次。 4. This latest arrest was just one minor setback. 最近的逮捕只不过是一个小小的退步。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('circus', '[\'sɜːrkəs]', 'n.马戏团,杂技团,马戏场,杂技场', '1. He performs riding stunts in the circus. 他在马戏团表演骑马绝技。 2. The circus placarded the city with advertisements. 马戏团满城张贴广告。 3. The fascinations of the circus are endless. 马戏表演非常吸引人。 4. The Roman circus was used for chariot and horse races. 罗马竞技场是用来举行敞篷双轮马车竞赛和赛马比赛的。', '形容词: circusy');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('destructive', '[dɪ\'strʌktɪv]', 'adj.破坏(性)的', '1. The destructive force of the storm is huge. 暴风雨的破坏力是巨大的。 2. Are all small children so destructive? 是不是儿童都喜欢破坏? 3. Jealousy is an extremely destructive emotion. 嫉妒是一种极其破坏性的情绪。 4. A locust is a kind of destructive insect. 蝗虫是一种害虫。', '副词: destructively 名词: destructiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('stereotype', '[\'steriətaɪp]', 'n.[印]铅版,陈腔滥调,老套;vt.使用铅版,套用老套,使一成不变', '1. He doesn\'t conform to the usual stereotype of the city businessman with a dark suit and rolled umbrella. 他不像典型的城市商人那样，穿一身深色的套服、 带一把收好的雨伞。 2. He fits the stereotype of a scholar. 他是典型的学者。 3. The idea is an old-fashioned stereotype. 这观点是老一套了。 4. It\'s wrong to stereotype people. 把人看作都是一样的是错误的。', '形容词: stereotypic 副词: stereotypically 名词: stereotyper 过去式: stereotyped 过去分词: stereotyped 现在分词: stereotyping 第三人称单数: stereotypes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('expose', '[ɪk\'spoʊz]', 'vt.使暴露,受到,使曝光;v.揭露', '1. The reporter was killed because he tried to expose a plot. 这名记者因为试图揭露一个阴谋而被杀害。 2. I hate the paparazzi.They always expose the people\'s privacy. 我讨厌狗仔队,他们老曝光别人的隐私。 3. We should not expose our children to horrors. 我们不应该让孩子看恐怖片。 4. Keep indoors and don\'t expose your skin to the sun. 待在室内,不要把皮肤暴露在阳光下。', '名词: exposer 过去式: exposed 过去分词: exposed 现在分词: exposing 第三人称单数: exposes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('lame', '[leɪm]', 'adj.跛足的,僵痛的,不完全的,金属薄片,不知内情的人,(辩解、论据等)无说服力的;vi.变跛,瘸行;vt.使成残废', '1. He gave a lame excuse for being late. 他说了个站不住脚的理由解释他迟到的原因。 2. Mary offered only a lame apology. 玛丽只作了一个站不住脚的辩解。 3. He is lame in one leg and walks with the help of a crutch. 他的一条腿跛了，走路借助于拐杖。 4. The work was hard for the lame old man. 这工作对他这个跛脚的老先生来说是很辛苦的。 5. The accident made him lame in the left leg 出事後他的左腿瘸了', '副词: lamely 比较级: lamer 最高级: lamest 名词: lameness 过去式: lamed 过去分词: lamed 现在分词: laming 第三人称单数: lames');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('curse', '[kɜːrs]', 'n.诅咒,咒语,祸根,祸因;vt.诅咒,咒骂,降祸,使受罪', '1. Our tribe is under a curse. 我们的部落正受诅咒。 2. He muttered a curse at the other driver. 他低声咒骂另一位开车的人。 3. Foxes can be a curse to farmers. 狐狸可给农民带来祸害。 4. She cursed him for ruining her life. 她诅咒他，说他毁了她的一生。 5. The Fore knew kuru as a curse cast by sorcerers. 弗尔族人认为，库鲁是由男巫发出的诅咒。', '名词: curser 过去式: cursed/curst 过去分词: cursed/curst 现在分词: cursing 第三人称单数: curses');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('sticky', '[\'stɪki]', 'adj.粘的,粘性的', '1. I am uncomfortable because my body is sticky . 我身上粘粘的，很不舒服。 2. Yuanxiao is a kind of sticky round dumplings. 元宵是一种粘粘的圆的面团。 3. A hot, sticky day makes a person listless. 天气闷热使人觉得身上有气无力。 4. They put me in a sticky position. 他们将我置于一个困难的境地。', '副词: stickily 比较级: stickier 最高级: stickiest 名词: stickiness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('evaluate', '[ɪ\'væljueɪt]', 'vt.评价,估计,求...的值;v.评价', '1. Let\'s evaluate the evidence. 让我们评定一下此证据的价值。 2. The school has only been open for six months, so it\'s too early to evaluate its success. 这所学校开办还不过六个月，所以要对它的成绩作出评价为时尚早。 3. Enterprise should acquaint with its storage status, that\'s the reason why it needs to evaluate the storage material. 企业应对自身库存状况有清楚的了解,这就需要对各个物资做出评价。 4. At the conclusion of the test run, evaluate the test results. 在测试完成之后,对测试的结果进行评估;', '形容词: evaluative 名词: evaluation 过去式: evaluated 过去分词: evaluated 现在分词: evaluating 第三人称单数: evaluates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('grave', '[ɡreiv]', 'n.墓穴,坟墓;adj.严重的,(颜色)黯淡的,(声音)低沉的;v.雕刻,铭记', '1. She laid the bouquet on the newly turfed grave. 她把那束花放置在新铺上草皮的坟墓上。 2. You are just digging your own grave if you go on smoking so heavily. 你继续这样过度吸烟，就是在自掘坟墓。 3. His face was grave when I told him my decision. 当我告诉他我的决定时，他的脸色很严肃。 4. The situation poses a grave threat to world peace. 这局势对世界和平构成了严重的威胁。', '副词: gravely 比较级: graver 最高级: gravest 名词: graveness 过去式: graved 过去分词: graven/graved 现在分词: graving 第三人称单数: graves');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('acceptance', '[ək\'septəns]', 'n.接受,承诺,容忍,赞同,相信', '1. The proposal met with general acceptance. 这个建议得到普遍的认可。 2. The idea rapidly gained acceptance in political circles. 这一想法很快得到了政界的认可。 3. The proposal was met with general acceptance. 这建议得到普遍的赞同。 4. We usually only discount acceptance trade and commercial bills. 我们通常只贴现已承兑的商业票据。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('gleam', '[ɡliːm]', 'n.微弱的闪光,一丝光线,瞬息的一现;vi.闪烁,隐约地闪现;vt.使发微光,使闪烁', '1. The lighthouse of the island gleamed in the distance. 远处岛上的灯塔在闪耀着。 2. His face gleamed with pleasure. 他的脸上闪现出欢快的神色。 3. I could see the faint gleam of light in the distance. 我能看见远处微弱的灯光。 4. I saw the gleam of the knife as it flashed through the air. 我看见了刀在空中划过时的闪光。', '名词: gleamer 过去式: gleamed 过去分词: gleamed 现在分词: gleaming 第三人称单数: gleams');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('occasional', '[ə\'keɪʒənl]', 'adj.偶然的,非经常的,特殊场合的,临时的', '1. He\'s someone I have an occasional chat and joke with. 我偶然跟他闲聊，一起说笑话。 2. An occasional outburst of anger creates wrinkles on the face. 一次愤怒的偶然爆发会在脸部产生皱纹。 3. All in a occasional chance, he got the out-of-print book in a secondhand bookstore. 纯粹由于偶然的机会，他在一家二手书店里找到了那本绝版的书. 4. He is only an occasional workman. 他只是个临时雇工。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('indispensable', '[ˌɪndɪ\'spensəbl]', 'n.不可缺少之物;adj.不可缺少的,绝对必要的', '1. The computer is now an indispensable tool in many businesses. 目前计算机是很多公司不可或缺的用具。 2. Air is indispensable to life. 空气是生命所必需的东西。 3. A good dictionary is indispensable for learning a foreign language. 学习外语离不开好的词典。 4. Air, food and water are indispensable to life. 空气，食物，水皆为生命不可缺者。', '副词: indispensably 名词: indispensability');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('installment', '[ɪn\'stɔːlmənt]', 'n.部分', '1. We will pay for houses by monthly installments. 我们将按月分期付款买房。 2. Buy goods on the installment plan has become epidemic in recent year. 近几年来，用分期付款的办法购物十分流行。 3. The last installment will be split into two movies. 故事的最后一部分将会拍成两部电影。 4. The installment of the new system took an hour. 安装新系统花了一个小时。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('betray', '[bɪ\'treɪ]', 'vt.出卖,背叛,泄露(秘密),露出...迹象', '1. He betrayed his country. 他背叛了他的国家。 2. He promised never to betray the organization. 他发誓永不背叛组织。 3. He was seduced to betray his friend. 他受唆使而出卖朋友。 4. As long as you don\'t betray me, I\'ll do whatever you ask me to. 只要你不出卖我,要我做什么我都愿意。', '名词: betrayal 过去式: betrayed 过去分词: betrayed 现在分词: betraying 第三人称单数: betrays');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('evolution', '[ˌiːvə\'luːʃn]', 'n.进展,发展,演变,进化', '1. Charles Darwin and Alfred Russell Wallace discovered evolution independently. 查尔斯·达尔文和阿尔弗雷德· 罗素·华莱士各自独立地发现了进化论。 2. Within 30 years,humans could be debating whether to take charge of their own evolution. 不出30年，人类将讨论是否要掌控自身的进化。 3. Our watchword is: ‘Evolution, not revolution’. 我们的口号是: ‘要循序渐进,不要剧烈变革’。 4. Our political institutions are in continuous evolution. 我们的政治制度正在不断发展中。', '形容词: evolutional 副词: evolutionarily');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('emotion', '[ɪ\'moʊʃn]', 'n.情绪,情感,感情', '1. Love, joy, hate, fear and grief are all emotions. 爱、喜、恨、惧、悲都是情感。 2. The speaker appealed to our emotions rather than to our minds. 演讲者激发了我们的情感而不是启发我们的思考。 3. I hate this kind of cheap emotion. 我讨厌这种肤浅的感情。 4. Chopin aroused very complicated emotions in her. 肖邦的乐曲唤起了她极其复杂的感情。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('expire', '[ɪk\'spaɪər]', 'v.期满,终止,呼气,断气,届满', '1. Our holidays expire next week. 我们的假期于下星期结束。 2. My passport is due to expire in two months. 我的护照再过两个月就到期了。 3. When does your driving licence expire? 你的驾驶执照何时到期? 4. My credit card will expire in June. 我的信用卡六月过期。', '过去式: expired 过去分词: expired 现在分词: expiring 第三人称单数: expires');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ritual', '[\'rɪtʃuəl]', 'n.典礼,(宗教)仪式,礼节;adj.典礼的,(宗教)仪式的', '1. Don\'t be overly solemn or feel that you are taking part in some special ritual; 不要太严肃,或觉得自己正在进行某种仪式; 2. She objects to the ritual of organized religion. 她反对规范的宗教仪规。 3. A strange ritual was enacted before our eyes. 在我们眼前展现出一种奇特的仪式. 4. He performed his ablution before the ritual. 他在典礼前沐 5. So nightly baths have become a part of their ritual even to this day. 所以晚间沐浴成为他们结束一天仪式的一部分。', '副词: ritually');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('loom', '[luːm]', 'n.织布机,织机;v.隐现,迫近', '1. I don\'t know how to use a hand loom. 我不知道怎样使用手工织布机。 2. The fabric was weaving at her loom. 她的织布机正编织着这些织物。 3. The shuttle flies back and forth on the loom. 织布机上梭子来回飞动。 4. The children are so excited to watch for the first loom of the land. 孩子们兴奋地注视着陆地的初现。 5. The mountainous island loomed on the horizon. 那座巨大的岛屿隐隐约约浮现在地平线上。', '过去式: loomed 过去分词: loomed 现在分词: looming 第三人称单数: looms');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('extinct', '[ɪk\'stɪŋkt]', 'adj.熄灭的,灭绝的,耗尽的;vt.<古>使熄灭', '1. This is an extinct species of fish. 这是一种已经灭绝的鱼。 2. This species will be extinct in a few decades. 几十年后这个物种将会灭绝。 3. An extinct volcano can no longer erupt. 一个灭绝的火山已不能再爆发。 4. My hope of getting some employment was extinct. 我要找到工作的希望落空了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('compile', '[kəm\'paɪl]', 'vt.编译,编辑,汇编', '1. Your first program is ready to compile and run. 你的第一个程序可以编译和运行了。 2. We are trying to compile a list of suitable people for the job. 我们在努力编制一份适合做这项工作的人员的名单。 3. How do we compile a balance of payments statements? 我们如何编制收支平衡表? 4. It takes many years of hard work to compile a good dictionary. 编纂一部好词典要花多年心血。', '过去式: compiled 过去分词: compiled 现在分词: compiling 第三人称单数: compiles');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('desire', '[dɪ\'zaɪər]', 'vt.想望,期望,希望,请求(官方丈礼);n.愿望,心愿,要求;v.要求', '1. I am filled with the desire to go back home. 我心中充满了回家的渴望。 2. Young people have no desire to work for the government. 年轻人没有在政府部门工作的意愿。 3. Her desire to dominate other people has caused trouble in her family. 她想支配他人的欲望在家庭中引起了麻烦。 4. She desires for a breakthrough in her research. 她渴望自己的研究能够出现突破。', '名词: desirer 过去式: desired 过去分词: desired 现在分词: desiring 第三人称单数: desires');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('recipient', '[rɪ\'sɪpiənt]', 'adj.容易接受的,感受性强的;n.容纳者,容器', '1. China is now the world\'s sixth-largest trading partner and the second-largest recipient of foreign investment after the United States. 中国现在是世界第6大贸易国，仅次于美国的世界第二大外国投资接受国。 2. The recipients of prizes had their names printed in the paper. 获奖者名单登在报上。 3. The postman spent almost a whole day looking for the recipient of the letter. 邮递员几乎花了整整一天时间寻找该信的收信人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fraction', '[\'frækʃn]', 'n.小部分,片断,分数', '1. Mother\'s careful with her money, and spends only a fraction of her earnings. 母亲用钱很审慎,只花自己收入很小的一部分。 2. The door opened a fraction. 门稍微开了条缝。 3. I can only pay a fraction of my bill. 我只付我的帐单的一小部分。 4. Open the window a fraction, please. 请把窗户打开一点。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('versatile', '[\'vɜːrsətl]', 'adj.通用的,万能的,多才多艺的,多面手的', '1. Versatile actors can play all kinds of roles. 多才多艺的演员能演各种类型的角色。 2. He is one of the most versatile actors. 他是最多才多艺的演员之一。 3. These cotton towels are quite versatile for this reason. 鉴于这点,这些毛巾都是通用的。 4. I bought a versatile kitchen machine last month. 我上个月买了一部多功能的厨房用机器.', '副词: versatilely 名词: versatility');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('gossip', '[\'ɡɑːsɪp]', 'n.闲话,闲谈', '1. There has been much gossip in political circles. 政界里有许多流言蜚语。 2. I loathe people who spread malicious gossip. 我讨厌那些散布充满恶意的流言蜚语的人。 3. He\'s a terrible gossip. 他专爱说人闲话。 4. I have no time to engage in gossip. 我无暇闲聊。 5. She loves to gossip to her neighbors. 她喜欢议论邻居们的是非长短。', '形容词: gossipy 名词: gossiper 过去式: gossiped 过去分词: gossiped 现在分词: gossiping 第三人称单数: gossips');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('forthcoming', '[ˌfɔːrθ\'kʌmɪŋ]', 'adj.即将来临的;n.来临', '1. He was exhilarateed by the thought of his forthcoming trip. 他想到即将到来的旅行，就兴高采烈。 2. Do you have a list of forthcoming books? 你有即将问世书本的目录吗? 3. The money we asked for was not forthcoming. 我们要的钱尚未得到。 4. She\'s never very forthcoming about her plans. 她一直不很愿意说出自己的计划。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('minimum', '[\'mɪnɪməm]', 'adj.最小的,最低的;n.最小值,最小化', '1. That is the minimum number necessary to complete the circuit. 这是完善循环的最低限度人数。 2. The minimum wage is 4.25 dollars an hour. 最低工价为每小时四点二五美元。 3. Repairing your car will cost a minimum of 100 dollars. 修理你的汽车最低限度要100美元。 4. The class needs a minimum of 6 pupils to continue. 这个班最低限度要六个学生才可以继续办下去。', '名词复数: minimums');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dimension', '[ˌdɪ\'menʃən]', 'n.尺寸,尺度,维(数),度(数),元', '1. Height is an external dimension. 高是外部尺寸。 2. When a dimension\'s origin is in doubt use the datums specified. 当不能确定尺寸原点时，使用规定的基准。 3. The fifth dimension creates everything that is on earth. 第五次元创造了地球上所有的东西。 4. The crystal extractors from that dimension cross through all dimensions. 从那个次元的水晶提取器穿越所有的次元。 5. We were told to dimension off the plots. 吩咐我们在图表上标出尺寸。', '形容词: dimensional 副词: dimensionally 名词: dimensionality 过去式: dimensioned 过去分词: dimensioned 现在分词: dimensioning 第三人称单数: dimensions');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('vicious', '[\'vɪʃəs]', 'adj.恶的,不道德的,恶意的,刻毒的,堕落的,品性不端的,有错误的', '1. I won\'t listen to such vicious remarks. 我不想听这种恶毒的话。 2. She used vicious remarks to insult people. 她恶言伤人。 3. Vicious gossip is spreading throughout the school. 校园里到处流传着恶意的闲言碎语。 4. He made a vicious stab at me with a broken bottle. 他用破瓶子向我猛烈地刺过来。', '副词: viciously 名词: viciousness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('garbage', '[\'ɡɑːrbɪdʒ]', 'n.垃圾,废物', '1. Please put the garbage in the dustbin. 请把垃圾放在桶里。 2. She threw the leftovers in the garbage. 她把剩饭倒进垃圾桶。 3. The smell of the garbage overpowered me. 垃圾的臭味使我无法忍受。 4. You are a garbage! 你真是个废物！', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('beforehand', '[bɪ\'fɔːrhænd]', 'adv.预先', '1. I had made preparations beforehand. 我预先作了准备。 2. He warned me beforehand what to expect. 他预先提醒过我这件事。 3. We were aware of the problem beforehand. 我们事先就知道有这个问题。 4. Actually I meant to notify you beforehand. 实际上我是想事先通知你的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('plunge', '[plʌndʒ]', 'n.跳进,投入;vi.投入,跳进,陷入;vt.使投入,使插入,使陷入', '1. She was about to plunge into something. 她就要采取什么行动了。 2. Don\'t plunge head first into another person\'s room. 别冒冒失失地撞进别人的房间。 3. The sudden jolt plunged her forward. 突然颠了一下，她向前打了个趔趄。 4. I waved my dog to plunge into the water. 我挥手示意我的狗跳入水中。 5. So why not take the plunge and have it over? 你为什么不鼓起勇气把这事赶紧解决了呢?', '过去式: plunged 过去分词: plunged 现在分词: plunging 第三人称单数: plunges');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('embark', '[ɪm\'bɑːrk]', 'v.上船,上飞机,着手,从事,装于船上,登上', '1. We embarked for Calais at midday. 我们中午乘船去加来。 2. Passengers with cars must embark first. 带汽车的乘客必须先上船。 3. The cargo ship will embark the unloaded freight from the draft trucks. 货船将会装载载重卡车卸下的货物。 4. The ship embarked passengers and food at a Spanish port. 这艘船在西班牙的一个港口装载了乘客和食品。', '名词: embarkation 过去式: embarked 过去分词: embarked 现在分词: embarking 第三人称单数: embarks');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('constrain', '[kən\'streɪn]', 'vt.强迫,抑制,拘束', '1. I felt constrained to do what he told me. 做他叫我做的事,我心里很不舒服。 2. She tried to constrain herself from a cough in class. 上课时她竭力忍住不咳嗽。 3. Cold weather constrains the plant\'s growth. 寒冷的天气抑制了植物的生长。 4. Don\'t constrain yourself only to class study. 不要把自己的学习只局限于课堂。', '形容词: constrainable 副词: constrainedly 名词: constrainer 过去式: constrained 过去分词: constrained 现在分词: constraining 第三人称单数: constrains');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hurl', '[hɜːrl]', 'n.<俚>[棒球]用力或猛烈的投掷;vt.用力投掷,愤慨地说出,丢下,推翻;vi.猛投,猛掷', '1. The hunter hurled his spear at the tiger. 猎人用力把他的长矛向虎投去。 2. I\'ll hurl him out of the club if he dare tell the secret! 如果他胆敢泄密，我就要把他赶出俱乐部。 3. To hurl abuse is in no way to fight. 谩骂决不是战斗。 4. Businessmen will hurl their money about to get noticed. 商人愿意挥霍钱财来引起注意。', '名词: hurler 过去式: hurled 过去分词: hurled 现在分词: hurling 第三人称单数: hurls');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('spoil', '[spɔɪl]', 'vt.损坏,搞糟,宠坏,溺爱;v.扰乱', '1. A fond mother may spoil her child. 溺爱的母亲可能会宠坏她的孩子。 2. The child was spoilt by his grandfather. 这个孩子被他的爷爷给惯坏了。 3. The children kept quarreling and spoiled our holiday. 孩子们不断吵架，破坏了我们的假期。 4. He had spoiled the soup by putting in too much salt. 他往汤里放盐太多，把汤给糟蹋了。 5. The invaders made spoil of all in their way. 侵略者所到之处无不洗劫一空。', '过去式: spoiled/spoilt 过去分词: spoiled/spoilt 现在分词: spoiling 第三人称单数: spoils');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('hound', '[haʊnd]', 'n.猎犬;vt.带猎犬狩猎,卑鄙的人,追捕,激励,使追逐', '1. They went hunting with a pack of hounds. 他们带一群猎狗去打猎。 2. The hound was quartering the woods. 这只猎犬在树林中四处搜寻猎物。 3. News hound sniffs the air. 狗仔队闻着空气里的味道。 4. My sister is a movie hound. 我妹妹是个影迷。 5. He has been hounded by his creditors in the past few months. 近几个月来，他一直被债主追债。', '名词: hounder 过去式: hounded 过去分词: hounded 现在分词: hounding 第三人称单数: hounds');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('regulation', '[ˌreɡju\'leɪʃn]', 'n.规则,规章,调节,校准', '1. We need the regulation of share prices. 我们需要对股票价格的管制。 2. From now on any violation of the regulation must be cruelly punished. 今后任何违反秩序的行为会受到严厉惩罚。 3. It\'s wrong of you to get around the regulation. 你存心规避规章制度是不对的。 4. This regulation refers only to children. 这些规定仅适用于儿童。 5. She was fined for driving above the regulation speed. 她因超速开车而被罚款。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('shabby', '[\'ʃæbi]', 'adj.破旧的,褴褛的,低劣的,卑鄙的,不公平的', '1. He owns nothing beyond the shabby house. 除了那个破旧的房子,他一无所有。 2. His shabby appearance creates a bad impression. 他那寒酸的样子给人留下不好的印象。 3. She is none the less beautiful for her shabby clothing. 即使她衣衫褴褛，却仍然美丽。 4. His reasoning is weak, even shabby. 他的论证软弱无力，甚至可以说很拙劣。', '副词: shabbily 比较级: shabbier 最高级: shabbiest 名词: shabbiness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('adequate', '[\'ædɪkwət]', 'adj.适当的,足够的', '1. We had adequate food for a week\'s journey. 我们有足够的食物可以做一星期的旅行。 2. He sought for an adequate solution to the problem. 他寻求解决这个问题的适当办法。 3. I hope he will be adequate to the job. 我希望他将胜任这一工作。', '副词: adequately 名词: adequacy');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('salvation', '[sæl\'veɪʃn]', 'n.拯救,救助', '1. They hope God can give them salvation. 他们希望上帝能够拯救他们。 2. Their toils and tireless courage were our salvation. 他们艰苦的工作和不倦的勇气拯救了我们。 3. She works for the Salvation Army. 她为救世军工作。 4. After so much dry weather, the rain has been the farmer\'s salvation. 天气干旱了这么久，这场雨成了农民的救星。', '形容词: salvational');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('galaxy', '[\'ɡæləksi]', 'n.星系,银河,一群显赫的人,一系列光彩夺目的东西', '1. The sun is only a very small star in the Galaxy. 太阳只是银河系中一颗很小的恒星。 2. The earth is one of the planets in the Galaxy. 地球是银河系中的星球之一。 3. Each galaxy contains myriads of stars. 每一星系都有无数的恒星。 4. The solar system is a small part of our galaxy. 太阳系是我们星系的一个小部分。', '名词复数: galaxies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('revenue', '[\'revənuː]', 'n.收入,国家的收入,税收', '1. National tax revenue grew by a large margin every year. 国家税收连年大幅度增长。 2. The state does not collect enough revenue to cover its expenditure. 政府征收的税收不能满足支出。 3. Rent is one form of revenue. 房租是一种收入。 4. The document states that all revenue has to be declared to the tax office. 该文件规定必须向税务局申报所有收入。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('complicated', '[\'kɑːmplɪkeɪtɪd]', 'adj.复杂的,难解的', '1. The novel is too complicated for your age. 这小说就你的年龄来说太复杂了。 2. The tax laws are so complicated that only an expert can provide enlightenment. 税务法非常复杂，只有专家才能解释清楚。 3. Obtaining a refund from the company is a complicated procedure. 向公司索取退款手续很复杂。 4. An automobile is a complicated apparatus. 汽车是台复杂的机器.', '副词: complicatedly 名词: complicatedness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('project', '[\'prɑːdʒekt]', 'n.计划,方案,事业,企业,工程;v.设计,计划,投射,放映,射出,发射(导弹等),凸出', '1. Our project was scrubbed. 我们的计划被取消了。 2. They doubted of the feasibility of the project. 他们怀疑这个计划的可行性。 3. The project is proceeding as planned. 工程正在按计划进行。 4. We are discussing the project to establish a new national park 我们正在讨论建立一个新的国家公园的工程。 5. The government projected a tax decrease. 政府计划降低税收。', '形容词: projectable');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('extent', '[ɪk\'stent]', 'n.广度,宽度,长度,范围,程度,区域,[律]<英>扣押,<美>临时所有权令', '1. A particle has no extent so that its position is a point. 质点没有广度因此它的位置是一个点。 2. As a result, the Census Bureau should obtain a better picture of the extent of intermarriage in the United States. 这样，人口普查局就能够更好地了解美国异族通婚的广度。 3. Percentage increase in extent size. 范围大小增加的百分比。 4. The extent of the regions was determined by the descriptor basicity. 这三个数据区的范围大小是由算符的碱性度决定的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('mall', '[mɔːl]', 'n.购物商场,商业街,林荫路', '1. The local kids hang out at the mall. 当地的孩子常在商业街闲荡。 2. The mall is only one mile away from here. 购物中心离这儿只有一英里远。 3. There is a shopping mall nearby. 附近有个大型的购物中心。 4. They reached the grassy mall which fronted on the State Building. 他们来到了州议会大厦前面的那片林荫草地。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('reunion', '[ˌriː\'juːniən]', 'n.团圆,重聚', '1. New Year\'s Day is a day for family reunion. 元旦是一个亲属团聚的日子。 2. All our kin came to the family reunion. 我们的亲属全都参加了这次家庭团聚会。 3. Her description of the meeting is an exact reproduction of the reunion. 她对会面的描述是这次团聚的真实再现。 4. We hold an annual reunion of former students of the college. 我们每年举行一次大学校友联欢会。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('indicative', '[ɪn\'dɪkətɪv]', 'adj.(～of)指示的,预示的,可表示的', '1. Use the indicative mood to make a sentence. 请用陈述语气造句。 2. There are three moods, indicative, imperative and subjunctive in English. 英语中有三种语气，即陈述语气，祈使语气和虚拟语气。', '副词: indicatively');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('definition', '[ˌdefɪ\'nɪʃn]', 'n.定义,解说,精确度,(轮廓影像等的)清晰度', '1. To give a definition of a word is more difficult than to give an illustration of its use. 给一个词下定义要比举例说明它的用法困难。 2. My duties require clearer definition. 我的职责需要更清楚的说明。 3. The photo lacks definition. 这张照片不够清晰。', '形容词: definitional');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('detect', '[dɪ\'tekt]', 'vt.察觉,发觉,侦查,探测;v.发现', '1. Do I detect a tinge of irony? 我觉得这话有点儿像反话吧? 2. If you read between the lines, you can detect his contrived explanation. 在字里行间，你可以看出他牵强的解释。 3. I seemed to detect some anger in his voice. 我似乎在他的声音中听出一些怒气。 4. Small quantities of poison were detected in the dead man\'s stomach. 在死者胃中找到了少量的毒药。', '形容词: detectable 名词: detecter 过去式: detected 过去分词: detected 现在分词: detecting 第三人称单数: detects');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('insurance', '[ɪn\'ʃʊrəns]', 'n.保险,保险单,保险业,保险费', '1. I am an insurance broker. 我是一名保险经纪人。 2. He works in an insurance company. 他在一家保险公司上班。 3. I have paid my car insurance. 我已经交了汽车保险费。 4. His insurance is $ 300 a year. 他的保险费是每年三百美元。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('descent', '[dɪ\'sent]', 'n.降下,降落,世系,血统,侵袭', '1. There was a descent of temperature after rain. 雨后气温下降了。 2. The trail zigzagged down the abrupt descent of the canyon. 这条小路弯弯曲曲的顺着峡谷那陡削的下坡蜿蜒而下。 3. He traces his descent back to an old norman family. 他追踪自己的世系上溯至一个古老的诺曼家族。 4. Many Americans are of English descent. 许多美国人的祖籍是英国。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('partial', '[\'pɑːrʃl]', 'adj.部分的,局部的,偏袒的,偏爱的;n.泛音', '1. around three 2. The research project was only a partial success. 那个研究课题只取得部分成功。 3. You will receive some partial credit even you don\'t finish it. 如果你没作完的话,你还是可以得到部分的分数。 4. His partial attitude called forth a lot of criticism. 他的偏袒态度招致了不少批评。', '名词: partialness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('input', '[\'ɪnpʊt]', 'n.输入;v.输入', '1. I\'d appreciate your input on this. 我将感激你在这方面的投入。 2. The input was larger than the output, so they lost money. 投入大于产出,所以他们亏本了。 3. The state has further increased its input in the family planning undertaking. 国家进一步加大了对计划生育事业的投入。 4. There are several errors in the input. 输入中有好几处错误。 5. I have inputted the data into a computer. 我已经把数据输入到计算机中了。', '过去式: inputted/input 过去分词: inputted/input 现在分词: inputting 第三人称单数: inputs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('pamphlet', '[\'pæmflət]', 'n.小册子', '1. He gave me a pamphlet for my call numbers. 他给了我一个小册子记录电话号码。 2. The pamphlet was written to his party. 这本小册子是特地为他的政党所写的。', '形容词: pamphletary');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('benefit', '[\'benɪfɪt]', 'n.利益,好处;vt.有益于,有助于;vi.受益', '1. It was for the benefit of your company that we did that. 我们这样做都是为了你们公司的利益。 2. Applications for unemployment benefits dropped last month. 上个月申请失业津贴的人数下降了。 3. A benefit performance will be held tonight. 今晚有义演。 4. The unemployed are entitled to receive other unemployment insurance benefits during the period of receiving unemployment insurance compensation. 失业人员在领取失业保险金期间,按照规定同时享受其他失业保险待遇。 5. The new hospital will benefit the entire community. 新医院将有益于整个社区。', '过去式: benefited/benefitted 过去分词: benefited/benefitted 现在分词: benefiting/benefitting 第三人称单数: benefits');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('crowd', '[kraʊd]', 'n.人群,群众,一堆(东西),一伙;v.群集,拥挤,挤满', '1. We had to push our way through the crowd. 我们得从人群中挤过去。 2. From across the fields came cheers of the crowd. 从田野的那一边传来群众的欢呼声。 3. A large crowd was waiting at the bus stop. 一大群人在公共汽车站等候。 4. A crowd gathered at the scene of the fire. 许多人聚集在火灾现场。 5. They had managed to crowd into a train. 他们勉强挤上了一列火车。', '名词: crowder 过去式: crowded 过去分词: crowded 现在分词: crowding 第三人称单数: crowds');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('awkward', '[\'ɔːkwərd]', 'adj.难使用的,笨拙的', '1. It\'s a little awkward, because he\'s my friend but I\'m still his boss. 他是我朋友,而我又是他老板,这真有点尴尬。 2. He felt awkward and uncomfortable. 他感到尴尬和不舒服。 3. He seemed as awkward and rough as ever. 他跟从前一样拙笨和粗鲁。 4. Swans are surprisingly awkward on the land. 天鹅在陆地上笨的出奇。', '副词: awkwardly 名词: awkwardness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('partition', '[pɑːr\'tɪʃn]', 'n.分割,划分,瓜分,分开,隔离物;vt.区分,隔开,分割', '1. The key to resolve the problem is elaborate partition for time and manpower. 关键的解决这人问题的方法是把时间和人力精心划分。 2. I could hear what he was saying on the phone through the partition. 我能隔着墙听见他在电话里说了些什么。 3. Our office is comparted by a partition board. 我们的办公室用一个隔扇分成两部分。 4. There is a plywood partition between the two rooms. 两个房子中间有一个夹板墙。 5. The workers partition a room into three parts. 工人们把一间房间分成三部分。', '名词: partitioner 过去式: partitioned 过去分词: partitioned 现在分词: partitioning 第三人称单数: partitions');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('leaflet', '[\'liːflət]', 'n.小叶,传单', '1. Leaflet blades with scattered oil glands. 小叶叶片具星散的油腺体。 2. Leaflet blade abaxially with lateral vein axils yellowish crinite. 小叶叶片背面具侧脉腋淡黄具长软毛。 3. I rustle up a few helper to hand out leaflet. 我找到几个助手散发传单。 4. They distributed leaflets to customers. 他们给客户散发传单。 5. We were paid to leaflet the mall with advertisements. 有人雇佣我们在购物中心发放广告传单。', '过去式: leafleted/leafletted 过去分词: leafleted/leafletted 现在分词: leafleting/leafletting 第三人称单数: leaflets');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('climax', '[\'klaɪmæks]', 'n.高潮,顶点', '1. The music approached a climax. 乐曲接近高潮。 2. The climax of the celebration was a firework display. 庆祝会的高潮是燃放烟火。 3. The heat of summer has reached its climax. 已经是夏季最热的天气了。 4. The air war over Europe was reaching its climax. 欧洲的空战已近白热化。', '过去式: climaxed 过去分词: climaxed 现在分词: climaxing 第三人称单数: climaxes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('certify', '[\'sɜːrtɪfaɪ]', 'v.证明,保证', '1. I certify that this is a true copy. 我证明这是真副本。 2. I certify that he has received your money. 我证明他已经收到了你的钱。 3. Can you certify for his ability as a teacher? 你可以保证他能胜任老师的工作吗? 4. I certify on my honour that he is innocent. 我用人格担保他是清白无辜的。', '名词: certifier 过去式: certified 过去分词: certified 现在分词: certifying 第三人称单数: certifies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('classic', '[\'klæsɪk]', 'n.杰作,名著;adj.第一流的', '1. \"War and Peace\" is a literary classic. 《战争与和平》是一部经典文学著作。 2. The idea of a classic is historically bound up with the view. 从历史上来看，古典的想法和这个观点有着密切的联系。 3. This is a really classic French champagne. 这确实是上等的法国香槟酒。 4. The novel is regarded as one of the classic works. 这篇小说被公认为是最优秀的作品之一。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fossil', '[\'fɑːsl]', 'n.化石,僵化的事物;adj.化石的,陈腐的,守旧的', '1. Coal is a fossil fuel. 煤是一种矿物燃料。 2. This fossil may be over 2 million years old. 这化石可能超过二百万年了。 3. He found a piece of fossil of an ancient bird. 他发现一块古代鸟类的化石。 4. Professor Baboon is not an old fossil. 巴布恩教授不是落伍的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('perplex', '[pər\'pleks]', 'v.困惑', '1. When new math was introduced into schools, many parents were perplexed by it. 当学校开设新的数学课时，许多家长对此感到迷惑不解。 2. Faced with that dilemma, he was perplexed. 他面对进退两难的局面，不知如何是好。', '副词: perplexingly 过去式: perplexed 过去分词: perplexed 现在分词: perplexing 第三人称单数: perplexes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('background', '[\'bækɡraʊnd]', 'n.背景,后台,不重要或不引人注目的地方或位置', '1. He has a strong political background. 他有强大的政治背景。 2. It is wrong to differentiate between people according to their family background. 根据出身不同而区别待人是不对的。 3. With my working-class background I feel like a fish out of water among these high-society people. 我出身于工人阶级,在上流社会中感到很不自在。 4. Her marketing background made her a natural choice for the job. 她的经销经历使她成为这一职位的必然人选。 5. To background themselves, reporters dug through all available files on the case. 为掌握有关背景资料,记者们搜集了对此案有关的可获得的所有文件资料。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('database', '[\'deɪtəbeɪs]', 'n.[计]数据库,资料库', '1. Can you set up a database? 你能建一个数据库吗? 2. This database is only accessible by the authorized manager. 只有授权的管理员才可以访问此数据库。 3. The database is updated monthly. 数据库每月更新。 4. The information is stored on a large database. 信息储存在巨大的数据库中。', '过去式: databased 过去分词: databased 现在分词: databasing 第三人称单数: databases');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('entail', '[ɪn\'teɪl]', 'vt.使必需,使蒙受,使承担,遗传给;n.[建]限定继承权', '1. This job entails a lot of hard work. 这项工作需要十分努力。 2. It will entail driving a long distance every day. 这意味着每天都要长途开车。 3. The alteration would entail an expenditure of 50 pounds. 此项改变将带来为数五十英磅的花费。 4. He would have sold the property long ago had it not been entailed. 这些财产若非限定继承的话，他早就卖掉了。 5. You allude perhaps to the entail of this estate. 你大概是说产业的继承权问题。', '名词: entailment 过去式: entailed 过去分词: entailed 现在分词: entailing 第三人称单数: entails');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('generalize', '[\'dʒenrəlaɪz]', 'vt.归纳,概括,推广,普及', '1. It is dangerous to generalize about people. 以偏概全地谈论人是危险的。 2. You cannot generalize about the effects of the drug from one or two cases. 不能根据一两个病例就得出该药是否有效的结论。 3. It is difficult to generalize about job trends in the West. 对西方的就业趋势做一个归纳概括并非易事。 4. Don\'t generalize a conclusion from a few examples. 不要从几个事例中归纳出结论。', '过去式: generalized 过去分词: generalized 现在分词: generalizing 第三人称单数: generalizes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('complaint', '[kəm\'pleɪnt]', 'n.诉苦,抱怨,牢骚,委屈,疾病', '1. You have no cause for complaint. 你没有理由抱怨。 2. You\'re always having complaints. 你一直都有怨言。 3. I have a complaint of the chest. 我胸部不适。 4. She poured out her complaints before me. 她在我面前倾诉苦衷。', '动词: complain');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('whereas', '[ˌwer\'æz]', 'conj.然而,反之,鉴于,尽管,但是', '1. Some people like coffee, whereas others like tea. 有人喜欢咖啡,然而也有人喜欢茶。 2. His children are well bred, whereas those of his sister\'s are naughty. 他的孩子很有教养，但他姐姐的孩子却调皮得很。 3. Whereas we want a flat, they would rather live in a house. 我们想住公寓房，而他们却想住一所房子。 4. Whereas the peoples of the colonies have been grieved and burdened with taxes... 鉴于各殖民地民众备受重税负担之苦....', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('commercial', '[kə\'mɜːrʃl]', 'adj.商业的,贸易的', '1. Do you fancy having a go at doing a commercial feature film? 对制作商业的影片有没有兴趣? 2. The downtown area is zoned for commercial use. 市中心被划出供商业用。 3. They were much more realistic about its long term commercial prospects. 他们对它的长远商业前景更为现实。 4. The Dole commercial is the first time Pfizer has promoted Viagra through television. 多尔的广告是辉瑞首次通过电视推销伟哥。', '副词: commercially');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('negotiate', '[nɪ\'ɡoʊʃieɪt]', 'v.(与某人)商议,谈判,磋商,,买卖,让渡(支票、债券等),通过,越过', '1. We\'ve decided to negotiate with the employers about our wage claim. 我们决定就工资问题与雇主谈判。 2. We are happy to negotiate with you in that way. 我们很高兴用这种方式来和贵方协商交易。 3. Trade union leaders went back to negotiate with the government. 工会领导回去和政府进行交涉。 4. Since our contract is near its term we must negotiate a new one. 由于我们的合同快到期了，我们必须谈判新的合约。', '形容词: negotiatory 名词: negotiator 过去式: negotiated 过去分词: negotiated 现在分词: negotiating 第三人称单数: negotiates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('aisle', '[aɪl]', 'n.走廊,过道', '1. It\'s down on the end of this aisle. 沿着这条走廊走到底就是。 2. I think our seat is near the centre aisle. 我想我们的座位靠近中间走廊。 3. The organ play as the bride come down the aisle. 当新娘沿著通道走过来时，风琴演奏了起来。 4. The girl ushered me along the aisle to my seat. 引座小姐带领我沿著通道到我的座位上去。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('warrant', '[\'wɔːrənt]', 'n.授权,正当理由,根据,证明,凭证,委任状,批准,许可证;vt.保证,辩解,担保,批准,使有正当理由', '1. The police obtained a search warrant for his house. 警察拿到了搜查他家的搜查证。 2. Have you got a warrant of fitness for your car? 你有没有一张汽车合格证书? 3. You shouldn\'t arrest him without warrant. 你不能毫无根据地逮捕他。 4. He had no warrant for his suspicion. 他没有理由那么怀疑。 5. I will warrant him an honest and reliable man . 我担保他是个诚实可靠的人。', '形容词: warrantable 副词: warrantably 名词: warrantability 过去式: warranted 过去分词: warranted 现在分词: warranting 第三人称单数: warrants');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('intent', '[ɪn\'tent]', 'n.意图,目的,意向,[律](犯罪或侵权行为的)故意;adj.专心的,决心的,热心的', '1. He\'s intent on going to Australia. 他热切希望到澳大利亚去。 2. Her intent look showed how much she had missed her sister. 她的专心的目光说明她是多么想念她的姐姐。 3. He\'s intent on moneymaking. 他一心一意地赚钱。 4. She is intent on getting the job done quickly. 她决心尽快把这件事情做好。 5. No one could spy out the intent and meaning of it. 没有人能查出它的意图和意义。', '副词: intently 名词: intentness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('generate', '[\'dʒenəreɪt]', 'vt.产生,发生', '1. 75% of France\'s electricity is generated by nuclear reactors. 法国75%25的电能产生于核反应堆。 2. We can\'t generate enough power for the entire city. 我们不能为整个城市产生足够的能量。 3. We need someone to generate new ideas. 我们需要有人出新主意。 4. This hatred was generated by racial prejudice. 这种仇恨是由种族偏见引起的。', '过去式: generated 过去分词: generated 现在分词: generating 第三人称单数: generates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('coward', '[\'kaʊərd]', 'n.懦弱的人,胆小的人', '1. Only a coward gives in to his fate. 只有懦夫向命运屈服。 2. He is a coward by his own admission. 他自己承认是个胆小鬼。 3. There is a coward silence when the stern principal come in. 严厉的校长走进来时,大家胆怯得不敢出声。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('attendant', '[ə\'tendənt]', 'n.服务员', '1. An unexpected accident is attendant upon carelessness. 粗心大意将导致意外事故发生。 2. Miseries are attendant on violence. 暴力往往会带来种种的不幸。 3. If you need anything, just ring for the attendant. 如果您要什么，就按铃叫服务员。 4. I asked the attendant to conduct him out. 我让服务员领他出去。', '副词: attendantly');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('chase', '[tʃeɪs]', 'n.追赶,追击;vt.追赶,追逐,雕镂', '1. Chase the cow out of the garden. 把牛逐出花园。 2. He chased (after) the burglar but couldn\'t catch him. 他追赶窃贼却未捉住。 3. Why do modern people chase material possessions? 为什么现在的人们追求物质财富？ 4. The criminal was caught after a car chase. 开着汽车追来追去才把罪犯捉住。', '过去式: chased 过去分词: chased 现在分词: chasing 第三人称单数: chases');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('commence', '[kə\'mens]', 'v.开始,着手', '1. I commence from this point. 我从此点开始。 2. The second term commences in March. 第二学期自三月开始。 3. We will commence with this work. 我们要着手进行这项工作。 4. I commence a round of visit. 我开始着手一系列访问。', '名词: commencer 过去式: commenced 过去分词: commenced 现在分词: commencing 第三人称单数: commences');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('dilute', '[daɪ\'luːt]', 'v.冲淡,变淡,变弱,稀释;adj.淡的,弱的,稀释的', '1. Dilute the bleach in a gallon of water. 用一加仑水稀释漂白粉。 2. The fragrances are highly diluted. 芳香剂被高度稀释了。 3. The nurse diluted the drug with saline water. 护士用生理盐水把药加以稀释。 4. He thought Rear Admiral Henry\'s presence might dilute the tension of the dinner. 他认为亨利少将的参加也许可以冲淡这顿晚餐的紧张气氛。 5. Readers feel dilute after reading Wei Yingwu\'s poetry, in reality, the poet concealed his solitude under this kind dilute style. 韦应物诗歌给人以冲淡的感觉，其实在这种冲淡的风格下隐含着诗人性格的孤独因素。', '形容词: dilutive 名词: diluter 过去式: diluted 过去分词: diluted 现在分词: diluting 第三人称单数: dilutes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('terrace', '[\'terəs]', 'n.梯田的一层,梯田,房屋之平顶,露台,阳台,倾斜的平地;adj.(女服)叠层式的;vt.使成梯形地,使有平台屋顶', '1. We sat on the terrace in the evening. 晚上我们坐在平台上。 2. The terrace afforded a fine view. 从屋顶平台上可以看到美好的景色。 3. Do you wish to sit at a table on the terrace? 你想坐在阳台上的桌旁吗? 4. The terrace channels are convenient for irrigation. 梯田的沟渠便于灌溉。 5. You may have to terrace your land or build raised beds. 你可能需要把地弄成梯田状，或是垫高。', '过去式: terraced 过去分词: terraced 现在分词: terracing 第三人称单数: terraces');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('complexion', '[kəm\'plekʃn]', 'n.面色,肤色,情况,局面', '1. That colour doesn\'t suit your complexion. 那颜色不适合你的肤色。 2. He has a dark complexion. 他肤色黝黑。 3. She has a pale complexion. 她面色苍白。 4. Her sparkling jewellery served as the perfect foil for her fine complexion. 她戴着闪闪生辉的首饰,更显得容貌姣好。', '形容词: complexional');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('lieutenant', '[luː\'tenənt]', 'n.陆军中尉,海军上尉,副职官员', '1. A young lieutenant was named for duty. 一名年轻的中尉被任命担任这项职务。 2. The ventilation is poor, the lieutenant admits. 中尉承认，通风设备很糟糕。 3. The lieutenant saluted and marched quickly down the corridor. 副官敬了个礼，然后快速的走下回廊，报信去了。 4. He prevailed on the lieutenant to send in a short note. 他说动那个副官，递上了一张简短的便条进去。', '名词: lieutenancy');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('negative', '[\'neɡətɪv]', 'n.否定,负数,底片;adj.否定的,消极的,负的,阴性的;vt.否定,拒绝(接受)', '1. Now I am afraid of getting a negative response. 现在真害怕收到否定的答复。 2. You can\'t learn anything with negative attitude. 你用消极的态度什么也学不到。 3. He conducted a negative campaign against his opponent. 他对他的对手进行了负面打击。 4. This negative pressure phase is of short duration. 负压周期的延续时间很短。 5. The answer to my request was in the negative. 对我的请求的答复是否定的。 6. The government negatived our request for financing. 政府否决了我们融资的请求。', '副词: negatively 名词: negativeness 过去式: negatived 过去分词: negatived 现在分词: negativing 第三人称单数: negatives');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('negligible', '[\'neɡlɪdʒəbl]', 'adj.可以忽略的,不予重视的', '1. The damage to my car is negligible. 我的汽车的损坏是极轻微的。 2. The rumors and slanders is negligible to me. 流言蜚语对于我来说是可以忽略的。 3. Details are negligible as far as I know. 我认为这些细节完全可以忽略。 4. The risks were represented as negligible. 把这么冒险的事说得微不足道。', '副词: negligibly 名词: negligibility');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('alienate', '[\'eɪliəneɪt]', 'v.疏远', '1. We\'d better not alienate ourselves from the colleagues. 我们最好还是不要与同事们疏远。 2. The Prime Minister\'s policy alienated many of her followers. 首相的政策使很多拥护她的人疏远了她。 3. His attempts to alienate the two friends failed. 他离间那一对朋友的企图失败了。 4. She tried to alienate him from his brother 她企图离间他和他的兄弟。', '名词: alienator 过去式: alienated 过去分词: alienated 现在分词: alienating 第三人称单数: alienates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('cute', '[kjuːt]', 'adj.可爱的,聪明的,伶俐的,装腔作势的', '1. Isn\'t she a cute baby! 她是个多么逗人喜爱的孩子啊！ 2. Leila kept smiling her outrageously cute smile. 莱拉脸上始终挂着非常可爱的笑容。 3. It was cute of you to spot that. 你能把那个挑出来真是精明的很。 4. Listen, if you drop the cute act and ask me honestly, I\'ll tell you the truth. 听着,你要是不耍这些小花招,老老实实地问我的话,我会告诉你实情的。 5. I walked in the damp and dark path of the hill, in the light of this cute orange latern. 我提着这灵巧的小橘灯，慢慢地在黑暗潮湿的山路上走着。', '副词: cutely 比较级: cuter 最高级: cutest 名词: cuteness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('competitive', '[kəm\'petətɪv]', 'adj.竞争的', '1. It\'s getting very competitive in the car industry. 汽车工业方面的竞争日益加剧。 2. Nobody can entirely keep away from this competitive world. 没有人能够完全远离这个竞争社会。 3. Ford has a more competitive environment. 福特公司具有一个较有竞争力的环境。 4. Our prices are competitive. 我们的价格是有竞争性的。', '副词: competitively 名词: competitiveness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('adapt', '[ə\'dæpt]', 'vt.使适应,改编', '1. This novel has been adapted for radio from the Russian original. 这部小说已由俄文原著改编成无线电广播节目。 2. She adapted herself quickly to the new climate. 她很快就适应了这种新气候。 3. You must adapt to the norms of the society you live in. 在社会中生活就要遵循社会行为准则。 4. It\'s hard to adapt this novel for children. 要将这部小说改编为适合小孩的阅读水准很难。', '过去式: adapted 过去分词: adapted 现在分词: adapting 第三人称单数: adapts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('prevalent', '[\'prevələnt]', 'adj.普遍的,流行的', '1. Is malaria still prevalent among the populationhere? 疟疾是否仍为此地居民的多发病? 2. Eye diseases are prevalent in some tropical countries. 在一些热带国家，眼疾很流行。 3. This argument was prevalent at the time. 这是当时流行的论调。 4. The prevalent opinion is in favour of reform. 一般舆论都支持改革。', '副词: prevalently');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('graduate', '[\'ɡrædʒuət]', 'n.(大学)毕业生,研究生;v.(使)(大学)毕业', '1. He is a graduate in medicine. 他是医科毕业生。 2. He is a graduate of Tokyo University. 他是东京大学的毕业生。 3. They graduate 30,000 engineers every year. 每年有3万名工程师从学校毕业。 4. This ruler is graduated in centimeters. 这把尺的刻度是厘米。 5. He will graduate from the school in May. 他将要在五月份毕业。 6. She was taken on as a graduate trainee. 她应聘为新毕业的实习生。', '名词: graduator 过去式: graduated 过去分词: graduated 现在分词: graduating 第三人称单数: graduates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('output', '[\'aʊtpʊt]', 'n.产量,输出,输出量', '1. Output has tripled. 产量已增加到三倍。 2. This country ranks last in industrial output. 这个国家的工业生产排名最後。 3. The average output of the factory is 20 cars a day. 该工厂的平均产量是每天20辆汽车。 4. Have you got the one which has an output of 150 horsepower? 你们有没有输出功率是一百五十（150）马力的? 5. The printer will output colour chart. 打印机将会输出彩色图表。', '过去式: outputted/output 过去分词: outputted/output 现在分词: outputting 第三人称单数: outputs');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('theme', '[θiːm]', 'n.(谈话,写作等的)题目,主题,学生的作文,作文题,[音乐]主题,主题曲,主旋律', '1. Peace was the dominant theme of the conference. 和平是大会的首要议题。 2. What is the essential theme of the play? 这剧本的主题是什麽? 3. The theme for tonight\'s talk is education. 今天谈话的题目是教育。 4. The theme of our discussion was Europe in the 1980\'s\'. 我们讨论的题目是｀八十年代的欧洲＇.', '形容词: themeless');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('finite', '[\'faɪnaɪt]', 'adj.有限的,[数]有穷的,限定的', '1. The world\'s resources are finite. 世界的资源是有限的。 2. Fortunately, the casualties were finite. 幸运的是，人员伤亡有限。 3. It is quite possible that space and time are finite. 很有可能空间和时间是有限的。 4. Any battery has a finite life span no matter what device it powers. 任何电池都具有有限的寿命，无论它具有多大的能量。', '副词: finitely 名词: finiteness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('upgrade', '[ˌʌp\'ɡreɪd]', 'n.升级,上升,上坡;adv.往上;vt.使升级,提升,改良品种', '1. Please click here to upgrade your Player. 请单击此处,升级您的播放器。 2. Companies need to upgrade servers. 公司需要对服务器升级。 3. We need to upgrade the pay and status of teachers. 我们需要提高教师的工资和地位。 4. We must try to upgrade our cattle to the required standard of meat. 我们必须努力提高牛的品级，使之达到所要求的食用肉标准。 5. After a short break, the climbers continued upgrade. 稍事休息後,攀登者们继续往山上走。 6. The power plant received a new upgrade. 那个电厂进行了一次升级改造。', '过去式: upgraded 过去分词: upgraded 现在分词: upgrading 第三人称单数: upgrades');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('semester', '[sɪ\'mestər]', 'n.学期', '1. His writing has improved greatly in this semester. 这学期他的写作有了很大进步。 2. This semester will be my last one in this university. 这个学期将是我在这所大学的最后一学期了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fiction', '[\'fɪkʃn]', 'n.虚构,编造,小说', '1. Real life is sometimes stranger than fiction. 现实生活有时比小说还离奇。 2. I like to read science fiction. 我喜欢读科幻小说。 3. It\'s important to distinguish fact from fiction. 把现实与虚构区分开来是很重要的。 4. His testimony is a complete fiction. 他的证言全是虚构。', '形容词: fictional 副词: fictionally 名词: fictionality');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('loyal', '[\'lɔɪəl]', 'adj.忠诚的,忠心的', '1. A loyal man stands by his friends in weal or woe. 一个忠诚的人无论祸福都会支持他的朋友。 2. We are loyal to our motherland. 我们忠于祖国。 3. I may say in all sincerity that you have been my most loyal friend. 我可以非常真诚地说，你一直是我最忠实的朋友。 4. The royal destroyer employs lots of loyal employees. 皇家驱逐舰雇佣了很多忠心的雇员。', '副词: loyally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('external', '[ɪk\'stɜːrnl]', 'adj.外部的,客观的,[医]外用的,外国的,表面的;n.外部,外面', '1. This news program only covers external events. 这一新闻节目只报道国外消息。 2. The external sector performance also improved significantly during the period. 在此期间,我国的涉外经济成绩斐然。 3. This force takes two forms, one internal and one external. 这个权力有两种形式:一种是对内的,一种是对外的。 4. All his injuries are external. 他受的伤都是外伤。 5. The external features of the building are very attractive. 这座建筑物的外观是很吸引人的。', '副词: externally');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('streamline', '[\'striːmlaɪn]', 'adj.流线型的', '1. I know you can streamline this kind of airship. 我知道你能把这种飞艇设计成流线型。 2. The V-shaped nose guard helps to streamline the design. 这款V字型的护鼻塞有助于它的流线型设计。 3. The aim is to streamline the business and achieve higher productivity. 目标是将业务合理化，提高生产力。 4. He endeavored to streamline the plant organization. 他努力使工厂组织简化而更有效地运作。', '过去式: streamlined 过去分词: streamlined 现在分词: streamlining 第三人称单数: streamlines');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('transfer', '[træns\'fɜːr]', 'v搬转移', '1. The exhibition was transferred to another city two days later. 两天后,这个展会转移到另外一个城市。 2. She has been transferred to another department. 她已被调往另一个部门。 3. I took the subway and then transferred to the bus. 我搭乘地铁然后再改乘公共汽车。 4. Our company will have a transfer to London. 我们公司将迁往伦敦。', '形容词: transferable 名词: transferability 过去式: transferred 过去分词: transferred 现在分词: transferring 第三人称单数: transfers');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('stereo', '[\'sterioʊ]', 'n.立体声系统,立体声,[印]铅版,立体照片;adj.立体的,立体感觉的', '1. Who originated the concept of stereo sound? 立体声是谁发明的？ 2. We\'re being deafened by next door\'s stereo. 隔壁的立体声音响要把我们耳朵震聋。 3. This is no time to lash out on a new stereo. 现在不是奢侈花钱买新立体音响的时候。', '名词复数: stereos');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('thrill', '[θrɪl]', 'v.发抖', '1. It gave me a real thrill to see her again after so many years. 那么多年后与她重逢,我非常激动。 2. With a thrill I realized that I had won. 我意识到自己获得了胜利 3. It was a real thrill to meet the Queen. 能见到女王的确是令人兴奋的事。 4. Hester looked at him with a thrill of another joy. 海丝特望着他，心头又是一阵喜悦的震颤。 5. It\'s a sight that never fails to thrill me. 那是一种永远让我激动不已的景象。', '副词: thrillingly 过去式: thrilled 过去分词: thrilled 现在分词: thrilling 第三人称单数: thrills');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('glare', '[ɡler]', 'n.眩目的光,显眼,怒目而视,(冰等的表面)光滑的表面;v.闪耀', '1. I like turning a corner from the shade of a house into the full torrid glare of an open space. 我喜欢将来自房子的色度的一个角落变成开着空间的完整晒焦的闪耀光。 2. These sunglasses are designed to reduce glare. 这些太阳镜是为减少刺眼的强光而设计的。 3. The glare of the oncoming headlights temporarily blinded me. 迎面车灯刺眼的光照得我瞬间什么也看不见。 4. Eyelashes defend the eye by shading it from glare. 眼睫毛通过遮掩眼睛而使眼睛避免受眩光刺激。', '过去式: glared 过去分词: glared 现在分词: glaring 第三人称单数: glares');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('splash', '[splæʃ]', 'n.溅,飞溅,斑点;v.溅,泼,溅湿', '1. There was splash in the pond, and a big goldfish bobbed up. 水池里扑通一声，一条大金鱼窜了起来。 2. He jumped into the water with a splash. 他噗通一声跳进水里。 3. There\'s a splash of paint on the white wall. 白墙上溅上了一片油漆。 4. He achieved a perfectly clean entry,and there is almost no splash. 他的入水非常漂亮，几乎没有溅起水花。 5. The boys always splash about in rainwater. 孩子们总是在雨水里玩耍。', '名词: splasher 过去式: splashed 过去分词: splashed 现在分词: splashing 第三人称单数: splashes');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('inspire', '[ɪn\'spaɪər]', 'vt.吸(气),鼓舞,感动,激发,启示,使生灵感,产生;vi.吸入,赋予灵感', '1. We\'re trying to inspire him with confidence. 我们在努力鼓舞他的自信心。 2. The sight inspired him with nostalgia. 这景象激起了他的怀旧之情。 3. The failure inspired him to greater efforts. 失败激发他作更大的努力。 4. You inspire me with admiration. 你使我产生爱慕之心。', '名词: inspirer 过去式: inspired 过去分词: inspired 现在分词: inspiring 第三人称单数: inspires');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('religious', '[rɪ\'lɪdʒəs]', 'adj.信奉宗教的,虔诚的,宗教上的,修道的,严谨的;n.僧侣,尼姑,修道士', '1. The religious affairs have been reestablished. 宗教事务已经恢复。 2. He was troubled by religious doubt. 他因对宗教的疑惧而十分烦恼。 3. Secular music refers to music which is not religious. 世俗音乐是指非宗教的音乐。 4. She is very religious and goes to church three times a week. 她非常虔诚，每周去教堂三次。', '副词: religiously 名词: religiousness 名词复数: religious');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('calorie', '[\'kæləri]', 'n.卡路里', '1. The calorie is a historical relic. 卡是历史的遗迹。 2. The calorie content in this ice cream is very high. 这种冰激凌的卡路里含量很高。 3. Diving can be as calorie consuming as you would like it to be. 潜水可以尽可能多地消耗卡路里。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('outfit', '[\'aʊtfɪt]', 'n.用具,配备,机构,全套装配,;vt.配备,装备;vi.得到装备', '1. She was prancing along in her new outfit. 她穿著全套新衣服神气活现地走著。 2. Such an outfit would be a useful addition to my wardrobe. 在我的服装中添置这一套会有用的。 3. The company will provide the sports outfits for all the players. 这家公司将为所有运动员提供全套运动服装。 4. His father bought a ski outfit for him on his birthday. 他父亲在他生日那天给他买了一套滑雪用具。 5. The mountain climbers were outfitted with the latest equipment. 登山者用最新的设备装备起来。 6. We will outfit two days before sailing. 我们将在出航前两天整装。', '名词: outfitter 过去式: outfitted 过去分词: outfitted 现在分词: outfitting 第三人称单数: outfits');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('render', '[\'rendər]', 'vt.呈递,归还,着色,汇报,致使,放弃,表演,实施;vi.给予补偿;n.交纳,粉刷,打底', '1. We are going to render them economic assistance. 我们打算向他们提供经济援助。 2. The power of the ocean was beautifully rendered in the poem. 这首诗将大海的力量表现得非常完美。 3. His back injury had rendered him unfit for work. 他的背伤使他无法胜任这份工作。 4. The jury has rendered its verdict. 陪审团已经作出了裁决', '形容词: renderable 名词: renderer 过去式: rendered 过去分词: rendered 现在分词: rendering 第三人称单数: renders');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('excursion', '[ɪk\'skɜːrʒn]', 'n.远足,游览,短程旅行,远足队,离题,[物]偏移,漂移', '1. The excursion was the high spot of our holiday. 我们那个假日的最大乐趣是远足。 2. We are planning an excursion to the blue mountain. 我们正在计划去蓝山远足。 3. I was roped in for this excursion before I knew it. 我不知不觉被拉来参加了这次远足旅行。 4. We shall make an excursion to Hangzhou this weekend. 这个周末我们将去杭州旅行。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('banquet', '[\'bæŋkwɪt]', 'n.宴会', '1. The manager was called on to speak at the banquet. 经理应邀在宴会上讲了话。 2. He met the foreign friends and gave a banquet in their honour. 他会见了外国朋友，并设宴招待了他们。 3. The president gave the Prince and his attendants a farewell banquet. 总统为王子和他的随员举行了告别宴会。 4. We gave him a farewell banquet yesterday. 我们昨天为他举行了告别宴会。 5. It\'s interesting for me to banquet. 对我来说参加宴会很有意思。 6. They banqueted her like a queen when she became director of that company. 她成为公司的董事后，他们把她当成女王般设宴款待她。', '名词: banqueter 过去式: banqueted 过去分词: banqueted 现在分词: banqueting 第三人称单数: banquets');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('turbulent', '[\'tɜːrbjələnt]', 'adj.狂暴的,吵闹的', '1. He was born in that turbulent period of history. 他出生在那个动荡的历史时期。 2. In the turbulent war age, he guides the elf to know the death aright. 在动荡的战争年代，他导引精灵们正确认识死亡。 3. The oarsman was feathering through the turbulent waves. 划桨者正平掠过汹涌的波浪。 4. The Rhosili is a turbulent, swift-flowing river, full of dangerous rapids and currents. 罗西里是一条汹涌的迅速滚滚的河，充满着危险的险滩和湍流。', '副词: turbulently');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('scope', '[skoʊp]', 'n.(活动)范围,机会,余地', '1. He gets a work that gives scope for his abilities. 他得到了一份有机会发挥他才能的工作。 2. He has no scope for his particular talents. 他没有施展自己特殊才能的机会。 3. It is within my scope. 那是在我的范围之内。 4. This subject is outside the scope of our inquiry. 这个问题不在我们探讨的范围之内。 5. He scopes the big picture of Israeli-Arab relations. 他认真地查看关于以色列和阿拉伯关系的大图片。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('apt', '[æpt]', 'adj.易于...的,有...倾向的,灵敏的,灵巧的,适当的,切题的,敏捷,倾向是', '1. In many ways, the comparison is apt. 在诸多方面，这个对比是恰当的。 2. I imagine that you may deduce an apt moral from my tale. 我觉得你也许能从我的际遇中引出恰当的教训。 3. Henry is an apt student of the practical science. 亨利在实践科学上是个聪明的学生。 4. He is a clever boy but apt to get into mischief. 他是个聪明却很调皮的孩子。 5. He has a handful of intelligent and apt students. 他有许多天资聪颖的学生。', '副词: aptly 名词: aptness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('nonetheless', '[ˌnʌnðə\'les]', 'adv.虽然如此,但是', '1. Though he\'s fool, I like him nonetheless. 虽然他很笨, 我仍然喜欢他。 2. Nonetheless, the science is pushing forward at a rapid pace. 尽管如此，研究正在迅速向前推进。 3. There are possible risks, but nonetheless, we feel it\'s a sound investment. 有可能存在危险,但是我们仍然感到这是可靠的投资。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('turnover', '[\'tɜːrnoʊvər]', 'n.翻覆,翻折,半圆卷饼,流通量,营业额,周转;adj.有一部分翻转的,可翻转的', '1. The firm has an annual turnover of 75 million. 这家公司的年营业额为7500万英镑。 2. The shop has a turnover of 500,000 dollar a week. 该店营业额为每周五十万元。 3. They have a very high turnover of staff. 他们的职员更换很快。 4. Why does your company have such a rapid turnover of staff? 贵公司人员变动为什么这么快?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bully', '[\'bʊli]', 'n.欺凌弱小者;vt.威吓,威逼', '1. The little girl stood up to a bully. 小女孩勇敢地对付暴徒。 2. The bully whacked my brother with a stick. 那恶棍用棒头狠揍我兄弟。 3. Leave that little girl alone, you big bully! 离那小姑娘远点儿, 你这个大坏蛋! 4. You are not discreet; you mustn\'t bully me. 你真不客气，你休想恐吓我。', '名词复数: bullies 过去式: bullied 过去分词: bullied 现在分词: bullying 第三人称单数: bullies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('assert', '[ə\'sɜːrt]', 'v.断言,声称', '1. She asserted that he was innocent. 她断言，他是无罪的。 2. Upon inspection, we assert that the systems development process is empirical 通过以上分析,我们断言系统开发过程是经验的 3. We encouraged him to assert his view of the matter. 我们鼓励他坚持自己对此事的看法。 4. The laws of historical development will assert themselves. 历史发展的规律是不可抗拒的。', '形容词: assertable 名词: asserter 过去式: asserted 过去分词: asserted 现在分词: asserting 第三人称单数: asserts');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('ivory', '[\'aɪvəri]', 'n.象牙', '1. The men trafficked with the natives for ivory. 这些人与土着居民做买卖以换取象牙。 2. The professor lived in an ivory tower. 这个教授生活在象牙塔中。 3. His nails resemble the ivory keys of the spinet. 他的指甲象白色的琴键一样。', '名词复数: ivories');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('bibliography', '[ˌbɪbli\'ɑːɡrəfi]', 'n.(有关一个题目或一个人的)书目,参考书目', '1. Bibliography usually appears at the end of a book. 参考书目通常在书后列出。 2. The book ought to include a bibliography of the subject. 这本书应包括一份关于这一学科的参考书目。 3. Please include your quotations in the bibliography. 请在参考文献处标明你的引文出处。 4. We have quoted in the bibliography a large number of items. 文献目录中列举了大量文献。', '形容词: bibliographical 副词: bibliographically 名词复数: bibliographies');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('messenger', '[\'mesɪndʒər]', 'n.报信者,使者', '1. Maybe I can act as a messenger for you. 也许我能给你当信差。 2. Some have feared it as a messenger of evil. 有些人害怕它是个不吉利的兆头。', '过去式: messengered 过去分词: messengered 现在分词: messengering 第三人称单数: messengers');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('commit', '[kə\'mɪt]', 'vt.犯(错误),干(坏事),把...交托给,提交,答应负责', '1. They committed outrages on innocent citizens. 他们对无辜的市民犯下了暴行。 2. He committed suicide rather than sell out to the enemy. 他宁愿自杀而没有向敌人投降。 3. He didn\'t commit himself to anything. 他没有作任何承诺。 4. The girl was committed to the care of an aunt. 这女孩被交给姨母照顾。', '形容词: committable 过去式: committed 过去分词: committed 现在分词: committing 第三人称单数: commits');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('yoke', '[joʊk]', 'n.轭,轭状物,套,束缚,支配;v.把...套上轭,结合,连接', '1. An ass and an ox, fastened to the same yoke, were drawing a wagon. 驴子和公牛一起套在轭上拉车。 2. The plow was pulled by a yoke of oxen. 一对公牛同轭拉着一头犁。 3. Slaves are under the yoke of their masters. 奴隶们受其主人的束缚。 4. He had got his neck out of the yoke of matrimony. 他已经摆脱了婚姻的枷锁。 5. Every farmer knows how to yoke the oxen together. 每个农民都知道怎样把牛拴在一起。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('candidate', '[\'kændɪdət]', 'n.候选人,投考者', '1. There are three candidates for the vacancy. 这一空缺有三名候选人。 2. She had been nominated as candidate for the presidency. 她已被提名为总统候选人。 3. He made several favorable comments about their candidate. 他对他们的候选人发表了一些有利的评论。 4. Most candidates passed in grammar. 参加考试的人大多数语法及格。', '名词: candidacy');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('constituent', '[kən\'stʃuənt]', 'n.委托人,要素;adj.有选举权的；有宪法制定［修改］权的', '1. Do you know the constituents of the mixture? 你知道这种混合物的成分吗？ 2. Punctuality is an important constituent of good character. 准时是优良品格的一个重要成分。 3. Last week, a constituent contacted me and asked me to help him construe an article contained within the constitution. 上星期，一位选民跟我联系，让我帮他解释一下宪法中包含的某则条款。 4. The chemical dissolves into its constituent parts when heated. 该化学药剂加热时会分解成其组成的分子。', '副词: constituently');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('literacy', '[\'lɪtərəsi]', 'n.有文化，有教养，有读写能力', '1. I can\'t believe that he failed the literacy test. 我无法相信他识字测试不及格。 2. Mass literacy was only possible after the invention of printing. 发明了印刷术后文化教育才得以普及。 3. Literacy may not be an inalienable human right. 能读写可能算不得是一项不可剥夺的人权。 4. Literacy was not the lecturers\' only concern. 大学讲师所担心的不仅是读写能力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('logical', '[\'lɑːdʒɪkl]', 'adj.合乎逻辑的,合理的', '1. Every argument was stated with logical precision. 每一个论点都阐述得精确严密，符合逻辑。 2. You must learn how to construct a logical argument. 你必须学会怎样确立合乎逻辑的论点。 3. My argument follows the rules of logical induction. 我是遵循逻辑归纳的法则进行论证的。 4. The article has a logical composition. 这篇文章布局合理。', '副词: logically 名词: logicality');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('wealth', '[welθ]', 'n.财富,财产,大量', '1. Health is better than wealth. 【谚】健康胜于财富。 2. He\'s always flaunting his wealth. 他总是摆阔。 3. She is responsible for the character part of the hero\'s devoted mother. 她负责这个主人公的忠诚的母亲的角色部分。 4. He has gambled away all his wealth. 他赌博输掉了全部财产。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('commonwealth', '[\'kɑːmənwelθ]', 'n.国民整体,共和国,联邦', '1. The three republics have decided to forma a commonwealth of independent states. 这三个共和国家决定组成一个独立国家联合体。 2. He is the chairman of the commonwealth of artists. 他是艺术家协会的主席。 3. Puerto Rico remains a US commonwealth, not a state. 波多黎各至今仍然是美国的一个自治政区，而不是一个州。 4. Dominion is a part of the British Commonwealth. 自治领是英联邦的一个组成部分。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('accord', '[ə\'kɔːrd]', 'n.一致,符合,调和,协定;vt.一致,给与;vi.符合', '1. The two countries reached an accord. 两国签订了一项协议。 2. His words are in accord with his ideas. 他心口一致。 3. Their views were found to be in perfect accord. 人们发现他们的意见是完全一致的。 4. Your behavior is not in accord with your principle. 你的行为与你的原则不符。 5. Our information does not accord with his reports. 我们所了解的情况与他的报告不一致。', '过去式: accorded 过去分词: accorded 现在分词: according 第三人称单数: accords');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('counter', '[\'kaʊntər]', 'n.计算器,计数器,计算者,柜台,筹码;adv.prep.相反地', '1. He placed the money on the counter. 他把钱放在柜台上。 2. Shoppers got into a scrum round the bargain counter. 顾客在廉价品柜台周围你争我夺。 3. The circuit is a conventional ring counter. 此线路是一个普通的环形计数器。 4. They had always had the counter effect of making him beastly. 女人总产生相反的效果，使他更像野兽。 5. He acted counter to his promise. 他的行动与他的诺言相反。 6. I counter their plan with my own. 我用自己的方案去反对他们的计划。', '过去式: countered 过去分词: countered 现在分词: countering 第三人称单数: counters');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('formidable', '[\'fɔːrmɪdəbl]', 'adj.强大的,令人敬畏的,可怕的,艰难的', '1. He was one of the most formidable intellects of his time. 他是该时代的盖世奇才。 2. His mother is a most formidable lady. 他的母亲是个最令人生畏的妇人。 3. They climbed up the last part of the mountain in formidable weather conditions. 他们在恶劣的天气条件下登上了山的顶峰。 4. Martin is formidable. His left hook is devastating. 马丁很难对付，他的左钩拳极有威力。', '副词: formidably 名词: formidability');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('therefore', '[\'ðerfɔːr]', 'adv.因此,所以', '1. He was the only candidate; therefore, he was elected. 他是唯一的候选人，因此，他当选了。 2. We do not have enough money. Therefore we can not afford to buy the new car. 我们的钱不够,因此买不成这辆新车。 3. I was ill, and therefore I could not come. 我病了,所以没能来。 4. He was very tired, and therefore he didn\'t give the market report. 他非常疲倦，所以没能作市场报告。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('analyse', '[\'ænəlaɪz]', 'n.&v.分析,分解', '1. He analysed the food and found that it contained poison. 他对这种食物做了化验，发现有毒。 2. Let\'s analyse the problem and see what went wrong. 让我们分析一下这道题，看什么地方出错了。 3. The coach tried to analyse the cause of our defeat. 教练努力设法分析我们失败的原因。 4. We must try to analyse the causes of the strike. 我们得研究一下罢工的原因。', '动词: analyze 形容词: analytic 副词: analytically');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('rash', '[ræʃ]', 'adj.轻率的,匆忙的,卤莽的;n.[医]皮疹', '1. While you have this rash you are still infectious. 身上还有这种疹子，就仍然有传染性。 2. A rash has appeared on his body. 他身上出现了丘疹。 3. The heat brought him out in a rash. 因气温很高，他浑身长了皮疹。 4. As soon as popular songs were accepted, fans appeared in a rash 流行歌曲一被接受, 追星族就大量涌现。 5. Don\'t do anything rash. 不要鲁莽行事。', '副词: rashly 比较级: rasher 最高级: rashest 名词: rashness');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('compartment', '[kəm\'pɑːrtmənt]', 'n.间隔间,车厢', '1. This is a case with separate compartments for shoes, jewelry, etc. 这是一个分格存放鞋、珠宝等的箱子。 2. and the rats move into the front compartment. 老鼠就会移入前间隔间。 3. Since there was no one else in the compartment I was able to spread myself. 车厢间隔里没有别人，我正好能伸胳膊伸腿舒坦一下。 4. The first-class compartments are in the front of the train. 头等车室在列车的前面。 5. Life today is compartmented into work and leisure. 现今生活分成工作和闲暇两部分。', '形容词: compartmental 过去式: compartmented 过去分词: compartmented 现在分词: compartmenting 第三人称单数: compartments');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('inaugurate', '[ɪ\'nɔːɡjəreɪt]', 'vt.举行就职典礼,创新,开辟,举行开幕(落成、成立)典礼.', '1. Mr. Clinton was inaugurated as the President of the U.S.A. 克林顿就职美国总统。 2. The city library was inaugurated by the mayor. 市长主持了市图书馆的落成仪式。 3. Watt inaugurated the age of steam. 瓦特开创了蒸汽时代。', '名词: inaugurator 过去式: inaugurated 过去分词: inaugurated 现在分词: inaugurating 第三人称单数: inaugurates');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('captive', '[\'kæptɪv]', 'n.俘虏,被美色或爱情迷住的人;adj.被俘的,被迷住的', '1. The captive was whooped and jeered. 俘虏被叱责讥笑。 2. We were held captive for three months. 我们当了三个月俘虏。 3. If a hero is of any importance, Homer also mentions the captive girl with whom he shares his tent and his bed. 荷马的史诗每提到一个重要的英雄，都要讲到同他共享帐篷和枕席的被俘的姑娘。 4. With full knowledge that the experiments were conducted on captive humans, the U.S. recruited the doctors to work for them. 在充分了解到在被俘的人身上进行的实验，美国招募了这批医生为他们工作。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `cet-6` VALUES ('fluctuate', '[\'flʌktʃueɪt]', 'vi.变动,波动,涨落,上下,动摇;vt.使动摇,使波动,使起伏', '1. Fruit prices fluctuate with the seasons. 水果价格随着季节波动。 2. Some investors panic when stock prices fluctuate wildly. 当股票价格大幅波动时,一些投资者便开始恐慌起来。 3. While the psychological unbalance may fluctuate the individual\'s original philosophy and regular act tendency which make conditions for the naissance of aberrance. 而心理的失衡极大地动摇了个体原有的人生观和行为定势 ,为越轨行为的产生创造了条件。 4. Both the light and radio outputs fluctuate markedly. 光和无线电的输出都引人注目地起伏变化。', '形容词: fluctuant 名词: fluctuation 过去式: fluctuated 过去分词: fluctuated 现在分词: fluctuating 第三人称单数: fluctuates');
